INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(92,"Champagne Punch","0","PT5M","PT5M","Here is a good punch recipe for any special occasion.  We serve this every year for Christmas Eve.  It is always a big hit.","Punch Beverage",5.0,30.0,236.8,0.2,0.0,0.0,14.2,41.6,0.2,38.1,0.6,"20.0","Champagne Punch Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix the juice concentrates in punch bowl (do not add water). 2: Stir in the Gingerale then add the Champagne (do not stir after adding the champagne!) 3: ** Note ** The large bottles of Gingerale and Champagne should be equal volumes (I use 2 L.  bottles).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(93,"Butterscotch Apple Dumpling","PT30M","PT45M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Butterscotch Apple Dumpling recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,271.6,8.9,5.5,22.9,321.8,48.0,1.5,33.2,1.8,"8.0","Butterscotch Apple Dumpling Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift flour and salt.  Add sugar.  Rub in butter, then add water and mix to a soft dough. 2: Peel and quarter apples. 3: Divide pastry into 8 equal portions. 4: Roll out each portion of pastry and wrap each around an apple quarter. 5: Place in an oven proof dish. 6: Combine sauce ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. 7: Pour sauce over pastries in dish. 8: Bake 25-30 minutes in  a moderate oven, about 325 degrees Fahrenheit.  Serve with ice cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(94,"Buttermilk-Oat Bread","PT20M","PT30M","PT50M","Make and share this Buttermilk-Oat Bread recipe from Food.com.","Yeast Breads",4.5,6.0,68.7,0.7,0.3,1.4,88.4,13.3,0.6,1.7,2.1,"16.0","Buttermilk-Oat Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: For toasted rolled oats, place oats in a shallow baking pan.  Bake at 350 for 15 to 20 minutes or till oats are lightly browned, stirring occasionally.   Cool. 2: Add all of the ingredients to a bread machine according to manufacturer''s  directions.   Bake the bread using the regular or white setting.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(96,"Blueberry Pancake Syrup","PT36M","PT50M","PT1H26M","I''ve made this blueberry syrup several times, but I bet it would work well for raspberries.  It''s worth a try!","Sauces",5.0,4.0,1329.7,1.0,0.1,0.0,16.6,342.8,7.1,328.9,2.2,"0.0","Blueberry Pancake Syrup Recipe Instructions:  1: Pour the blueberries into a saucepan and crush them with a potato masher or a wooden spoon until most of the skins are broken. 2: Add 1 cup of water  and strips of lemon peel and bring to a simmer. 3: Turn heat down to low and cook the berries for 5 minutes at just under a simmer. 4: Pour the hot berries into a strainer lined with two layers of cheesecloth and let the blueberry juice drip through. 5: Twist the cloth to extract all the juice; there should be about 2 cups. 6: Discard the berry pulp. 7: Combine the remaining  2 cups water with the sugar in a small saucepan. 8: Bring the mixture to a boil, stirring, until the sugar is dissolved and the mixture is clear. 9: Wash down the sides of the pan with a wet pastry brush, then boil the syrup, without stirring, until it reaches 260 degrees on a candy thermometer. 10: Add the blueberry syrup to the sugar syrup and bring the mixture to boil. 11: Boil for 1 minute.  Let the syrup cool, then add lemon juice to taste. Pour the syrup into two pint jars and refrigerate if you plan to use it in a month or two. 12: To can (for indefinite storage) Pour into canning jars with 1/2 inch headspace.  Process in hot water bath for 30 minutes. 13: Cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(97,"Chanfana Ou Lampantana","PT4H","PT20M","PT4H20M","This dish was typical of the Beira provinces in Mozambique where it was served at large gatherings.  This dish is best prepared a day in advance and reheated. It is preferable to use an iron pot, but a good quality oven proof pot will do. Lamb may be used instead of goat.","Very Low Carbs",0.0,0.0,1266.0,42.5,10.6,302.1,598.5,17.5,0.8,4.7,106.2,"0.0","Chanfana Ou Lampantana Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 200 degrees C.  Place the meat and bacon in a pot and add the oil and lard.  Add the onions, spices, herbs and seasonings.    Cover completely with the wine. Cover the pot and place it in a very hot oven (200 degrees C) for 1 hour. 2: Remove the lit and stir.   Add more wine if necessary. 3: Cover the pot again and reduce the oven temperature of 100 degrees C. 4: Continue cooking, preferably overnight or until the meat is tender. 5: (The time taken will depend on the age of the lamb or goat.)  Serve with potatoes boiled in their Jackets.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(98,"Cherry Sandwich Maker Snack","0","PT30M","PT30M","Make and share this Cherry Sandwich Maker Snack recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,5.0,73.3,0.8,0.2,0.0,171.3,14.3,0.6,1.1,1.9,"0.0","Cherry Sandwich Maker Snack Recipe Instructions:  1: Spread a thin layer between buttered bread and place in sandwich maiker. 2: Note: do not add too much filling or it will make one terrible mess in sandwich maker. 3: Let brown. 4: Remove from sandwich maker and sprinkle with powdered sugar. 5: Makes two triangular tarts. 6: My kids love them.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(99,"Cheesecake Cupcakes with Blueberries","0","PT50M","PT50M","Make and share this Cheesecake Cupcakes with Blueberries recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",5.0,6.0,249.5,12.7,6.5,67.9,126.4,31.1,0.5,23.7,3.8,"12.0","Cheesecake Cupcakes with Blueberries Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 325 degrees.Line 12 muffin cups with foil liners. 2: Place a cookie in bottom of each liner; trim cookies to fit if necessary.Beat together cream  cheese and sugar on med. 3: speed in large bowl until smooth. 4: Add eggs, beating  just until blended. 5: Beat in sour cream, vanilla and lemon rind. 6: On low speed,  beat in flour. 7: Stir in blueberries. 8: Spoon batter into cups, dividing  equally.Bake for 35-40 min., until cakes are set. Cool cakes in pan on rack for  20 min. 9: Remove cakes to rack to cool. 10: Refrigerate.                    - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(101,"Cheese and Pineapple Dip","PT2H","PT20M","PT2H20M","Make and share this Cheese and Pineapple Dip recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",0.0,0.0,98.7,4.7,2.9,12.1,182.7,11.1,1.1,7.0,4.1,"0.0","Cheese and Pineapple Dip Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix reduced cream, tomato & onion soup, cheese and crushed pineapple together until well combined. 2: Chill for 2 hours before serving. 3: Makes  about 3 cups. 4: Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 5: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(102,"Chicken and Pineapple Salad With Curry Mayonnaise","PT1H5M","PT20M","PT1H25M","This is nice, I have used ordinary roast chicken.   CHICKEN AND PINEAPPLE SALAD WITH CURRY MAYONNAISE","Whole Chicken",5.0,5.0,409.7,27.9,11.9,43.5,362.5,30.2,4.3,15.3,13.3,"4.0","Chicken and Pineapple Salad With Curry Mayonnaise Recipe Instructions:  1: CURRIED MAYONNAISE: 2: Combine all ingredients thoroughly. 3: CHICKEN AND PINEAPPLE SALAD: 4: Toast coconut on oven tray in moderate oven for about 5 minutes. 5: Cut chicken and pineapple into chunks; place in bowl, mix in coconut, shallots and Mayonnaise. 6: Refrigerate 1 hour before serving. 7: Serves 4. 8: Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 9: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(104,"Carrie''s Pizza Rolls","PT3H30M","PT55M","PT4H25M","Make and share this Carrie''s Pizza Rolls recipe from Food.com.","Low Cholesterol",4.0,1.0,3521.8,108.1,39.0,183.9,2905.4,548.4,96.2,29.7,134.2,"1.0","Carrie''s Pizza Rolls Recipe Instructions:  1: Dough: Dissolve yeast with honey and 1/2 cup  water; let stand 10 minutes. 2: Put 4 cups flour in large  mixing bowl; stir in oil, water and yeast mixture. Mix   thoroughly. 3: Knead 8 to 10 minutes. 4: Let dough rise 1 hour until  doubled. 5: Punch  down and roll on floured surface to about 1/2- inch. 6: Cut into rectangles about 4 x 6-inches or desired size of  pizza roll. 7: Sauce: Place all ingredients (except  the  Mozzarella cheese) in a crock-pot and simmer on low for  about 2 hours. 8: Let cool to room temperature. Hot sauce will  make dough soggy. 9: Rolls: Place a small amount of sauce on the  dough rectangles, spreading it to cover the entire   piece of dough. 10: Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over half of the  dough. 11: Roll up the  dough burrito-style, sealing edges with  moistened fingers. 12: Place rolls on a  cookie sheet. Allow to rest for  about 10 minutes. 13: Bake in a hot 500 degrees  oven until  dough is golden brown. 14: Serve rolls with a side bowl of hot pizza  sauce  for dipping the pizza rolls inches. 15: These freeze beautifully. 16: Can be   reheated in the microwave. Variations: You may wish to add slices of  mushroom,  olive, shredded beef, pepperoni slices or  whatever in addition to the  Mozzarella cheese inside the pizza roll.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(105,"Almond Fudge Banana Cake","PT1H","PT50M","PT1H50M","Make and share this Almond Fudge Banana Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,23.0,224.8,9.2,1.8,34.9,246.8,33.9,1.9,21.8,3.8,"0.0","Almond Fudge Banana Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Mash bananas and set aside.  Beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy. 2: Beat in eggs, liqueur and vanilla. 3: Combine dry ingredients. 4: Stir in almonds. 5: Add to sugar mixture alternately with bananas. 6: Beat well. 7: Pour batter into greased 10-inch Bundt pan. 8: Bake in preheated 350°F oven 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out almost clean and cake pulls away from side of pan. 9: Cool 10 minutes. 10: Remove cake from pan to wire rack to cool completely. 11: Drizzle glaze over top and down side of cake.  Make 16-20 servings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(106,"Cherry Tomatoes on Provolone Garlic Bread","PT1H10M","PT35M","PT1H45M","Make and share this Cherry Tomatoes on Provolone Garlic Bread recipe from Food.com.","Weeknight",5.0,7.0,488.6,38.6,10.0,24.8,483.5,23.7,2.9,7.2,13.4,"4.0","Cherry Tomatoes on Provolone Garlic Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: For the tomatoes, mix tomatoes, scallions, parsley, rosemary, garlic, olive oil and vinegar in a shallow bowl. 2: Season with salt and pepper. 3: Cover bowl and let tomatoes marinate at room temperature for at least 1 hour, but preferably 3-4 hours. 4: Stir occasionally to distribute seasonings. 5: For the bread, combine olive oil and garlic and let mixture stand for about 10 minutes so flavors can mingle.  Meanwhile, heat the broiler. 6: Brush one side of each bread slice with garlic and olive oil mixture and broil them oiled-side up until lightly browned. 7: Put a slice of provolone and a generous sprinkling of Parmesan on each slice, reserving a little of the parmesan for garnish. 8: Set aside.  Just before serving, heat up broiler again and toast cheese until bubbly. 9: Serve bread in shallow bowls, spooning about 3/4 cup of tomatoes and marinade over each slice, garnishing with remaining parmesan.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(107,"Cheesy Chicken Noodle Casserole","0","PT35M","PT35M","Make and share this Cheesy Chicken Noodle Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",3.0,1.0,544.0,22.0,7.8,107.8,747.1,59.1,4.2,8.2,30.4,"4.0","Cheesy Chicken Noodle Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook egg noodles in boiling water till chewy. 2: Cook chicken in olive oil, and  Lawry salt till chicken is not pink in middle, then drain oil. 3: Combine cream of chicken soup, egg noodles, and chicken till boiling. 4: Reduce heat, and add  Velveeta cheese, corn, and pepper. 5: Cook until all of Velveeta is melted. 6: Remove from heat and sprinkle with parsley flakes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(108,"Caramel Sultana Square","PT30M","PT20M","PT50M","Make and share this Caramel Sultana Square recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,3770.5,198.6,123.2,742.8,1963.4,468.4,5.1,302.6,44.2,"0.0","Caramel Sultana Square Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter and sugar, add egg then dry ingredients. 2: Divide shortcake in two. 3: Press one half in tin. 4: Melt together and pour over base.  Sprinkle with sultanas and cover with remaining mixture.  Bake in a moderate oven 20 - 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(109,"&quot;21&quot; Apple Pie","PT1H6M","PT1H45M","PT2H51M","Make and share this &quot;21&quot; Apple Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",3.0,1.0,694.3,25.1,15.0,96.2,222.5,113.0,13.6,61.9,7.2,"0.0","&quot;21&quot; Apple Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Add the cold butter cubes and, with a pastry blender, blend in the flour until mixture becomes mealy ans butter forms peas-size nuggets plainly visible in the flour. 2: The water should be added to the flour slowly to ensure that only the minimum amount of water is used. 3: Do not over-mix the dough. 4: When the dough has been mixed just sufficiently to combine the ingredients, form it into a ball and wrap in a piece of plastic wrap and refrigerate for several  hours. 5: To prepare the filling, melt the butter in a large saute pan until it  begins to brown. 6: Add the sliced apples and cook over medium heat until they begin to soften, about 2 to 3 minutes. 7: In a bowl, combine the lemon juice, sugars, Southern Comfort, and  cinnamon. 8: Add this mixture to the apples and cook 2 to 3 minutes over medium-high heat until the apples are completely caramelized and covered with all the sugar. 9: Remove filling from the heat and  allow to cool. 10: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees. 11: When ready to use, remove the dough from the refrigerator, lightly flour a pastry board and a rolling pin, and unwrap the dough. 12: Divide the dough into 2 equal pieces and begin to roll out into a circle by rolling evenly outward from the center and turning   the dough in small 1/8th turns to keep the rolling even. 13: When the  dough is  rolled out to an even thickness and is about 12 inches in  diameter and 1/8-inch thick, it is ready to be transferred to a 10-inch pie pan or plate. 14: Lightly butter the pie plate, partially roll the dough up on the rolling pin, lift the dough and center it in the pie pan and unroll. 15: Roll the second half of the pie dough into a round slightly larger than the pie pan. 16: Fill the bottom crust with the cooked apples using a slotted spoon to drain the apples. 17: Reserve juices if desired, for sauce. Brush an egg wash coating over the lip of the dough. 18: This is where it will be sealed to the top  crust. Cover the apples  with the top half of the pie dough. 19: Trim any excess  from the top  crust before using both hands to crimp the edges of the two crust together to seal. 20: With a sharp knife, make several crosshatch slits in the top  crust. Brush with the egg wash and bake for 35 to 40 minutes. 21: Remove from the oven and cool 20 minutes. 22: Serve with vanilla ice cream. 23: Reserved juices can be reduced with heavy cream for a sauce for the pie.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(110,"Campfire Orange Cake","0","PT30M","PT30M","When I was a child, my mother made orange cake every time we went camping. She would scoop out an orange, fill it with (I think) white jiffy cake mix, wrap it in foil and put it it the campfire to bake.  They were wonderful!","Dessert",4.5,2.0,332.5,9.6,2.4,0.0,453.6,59.2,2.8,38.3,3.6,"6.0","Campfire Orange Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: You could probably do this with any cake mix.  Foil is nice (keeps ash  out), but apparently not necessary unless you are worried about burning the  bottom of the orange cups.  Follow the directions on the package for the  cake batter and do like below: 2: Gingerbread Cups  Halve and clean inside of oranges out.  Prepare a package of  gingerbread mix, fill cups 3/4 full. 3: Place cups in a bed of coals, not too  hot.  Bake slowly, turning around from time to time.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(111,"Bugwiches","0","PT40M","PT40M","A little bit of fun for the kids this summer. Happy Hunting! Deborah   Bugwiches:  Whatever filling you choose to put between the top and bottom of your dinner rolls, your little critters are sure to get the shivers when they sit down to eat. You''ll want to slice your vegetables a variety of ways in order to make such body parts as legs and antennae, and scales and eyes.  What you''ll need:","Lunch/Snacks",0.0,1.0,84.0,2.0,0.5,0.3,145.9,14.1,0.8,0.7,2.4,"1.0","Bugwiches Recipe Instructions:  1: How to assemble: Slice roll horizontally, about 1/2 inch from bottom. 2: Pull out  bread from top half, leaving walls about 1/2 inch thick. 3: Place cucumber or  radish slices over bottom halves of rolls, sticking out slightly to make mouths  or tongues. 4: Spoon a mound of filling on top and cover with top halves of rolls. 5: Insert carrot sticks into filling for legs. 6: Make two slits on each side of top  half of bun and insert lettuce leaves as wings. 7: Decorate with vegetable pieces  for eyes, antennae, scales and other body parts. 8: Attach using mayonnaise.");
