INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(119,"Cold Celery","0","PT40M","PT40M","Make and share this Cold Celery recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",3.0,2.0,135.1,5.3,0.8,0.0,1546.3,19.7,7.8,13.5,5.2,"1.0","Cold Celery Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash the celery and cut into 1 inch lengths. 2: Put into a large pan, cover with cold water and bring to the boil, drain and immediately cover with water. 3: Chill completely under cold running water. 4: Drain. 5: Add the salt, soy sauce, sugar and sesame oil. 6: Mix well and serve chilled.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(120,"Coconut-Lemon Macaroons","PT30M","PT35M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Coconut-Lemon Macaroons recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,2495.0,147.0,129.8,0.0,304.0,287.6,38.2,217.9,34.4,"0.0","Coconut-Lemon Macaroons Recipe Instructions:  1: In a medium pan combine coconut, sugar, 1 egg white, lemon rind and strained lemon juice.  Stir over a low heat until lukewarm, cool. 2: Beat remaining egg whites until soft peaks form. 3: Gradually fold egg whites into cooled mixture.  Add sifted flour, combine gently. 4: Place mixture in heaped teaspoonfuls on greased oven trays which have been lightly dusted with cornflour. 5: Bake in slow oven 30 minutes. 6: Cool on trays.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(121,"Chicken Flambe","PT35M","PT35M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Chicken Flambe recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",0.0,0.0,304.6,14.6,4.5,88.0,158.6,6.6,0.8,2.2,25.6,"4.0","Chicken Flambe Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to  350  F. 2: Lightly season the chicken breasts with salt and pepper. 3: In a large skillet over medium heat, brown chicken breasts on both sides. 4: Add onions and mushrooms and stir cook until the onions soften. 5: Transfer mixture to a shallow casserole dish and bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes. 6: In a small sauce pan warm the orange liqueur over low heat (should be lukewarm, not hot). Take the casserole out of the oven. 7: Pour the liqueur over the chicken and vegetables and ignite it. When the flames die out, add the wine and return the casserole to the oven for another 15 minutes or until chicken breasts are no longer pink inside. Remove the casserole from the oven. 8: Arrange the chicken and vegetables on a warm platter and keep hot. Mix butter and flour to make a paste. Stir this into the pan juices, add cream and simmer over low heat for 5 minutes until thickened. 9: Pour sauce over chicken. 10: Serve with wild rice and vegetables.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(122,"Chicken Curry","PT42M","PT1H5M","PT1H47M","Accompany curry with  pappadams and chutney.  This particular combination of spices, which includes  cardamom and cinnamon, gives a mild heat and rich fragrance to  the dish.  You can adjust the spices to suit your taste.","Curries",5.0,16.0,360.1,10.7,4.9,93.2,1251.6,38.0,4.6,23.5,31.1,"4.0","Chicken Curry Recipe Instructions:  1: In a dry skillet over medium heat, toast coriander and cumin  seeds until fragrant, 1 to 2 minutes. 2: Transfer to spice grinder, add  crushed red-pepper flakes, and grind to a powder. 3: Place in a small  bowl, and add turmeric, ginger, cloves, salt, and black pepper. 4: Add  chicken, and toss to coat. Heat peanut oil in a large pot over medium-high heat.  Add  chicken, cooking until browned, 3 to 5 minutes. 5: Remove chicken. 6: Set  aside. Reduce heat, and add ginger, garlic, and onions. 7: Cook until  softened and deep-brown in color, 8 to 10 minutes. 8: Add cinnamon  sticks, bay leaf, and cardamom pods; cook for 10 minutes. 9: Add  tomatoes, chicken stock, and cooked chicken. 10: Raise heat to medium  high, and cook until liquid is reduced, about 15 minutes. 11: Meanwhile,  toast pappadams. 12: Reduce heat to low, and stir in yogurt and  raisins. 13: Cook until warmed throughout; add cilantro. 14: Serve with  basmati rice, and garnish with cashews.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(123,"Chicken Goulash on a Sour Cream Crust","PT55M","PT30M","PT1H25M","Make and share this Chicken Goulash on a Sour Cream Crust recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",0.0,0.0,695.5,46.4,22.0,166.1,275.1,41.8,2.6,3.7,24.2,"6.0","Chicken Goulash on a Sour Cream Crust Recipe Instructions:  1: Lightly saute the onions in 1 Tbsp of the oil until golden. 2: Meanwhile place the seasoned flour and paprika in a mixing bowl, add the chicken to coat.  Remove the onions from the pan, Add the rest of the oil and saute the chicken for 2 - 3 minutes. 3: Return onions to the pan, add the tomato paste, wine and stock. 4: Bring to the boil and simmer for 6 - 7 minutes. 5: Remove pan from the heat and stir in the yoghurt.  (This can be made in advance and stored in the refrigerator.) CRUST Place the butter, sour cream and egg into a bowl, mix to combine. Stir in the flour and parsley to form a soft dough. 6: Press the dough into a lightly greased casserole or flan dish, working it well up the sides to a thickness of 12 mm. 7: Spoon the filling, cover and bake at 180C for 35 minutes. 8: Uncover and bake for a further 10 minutes or until golden and crusty.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(124,"Chicken in Pizza Dough","PT2H35M","PT1H15M","PT3H50M","Make and share this Chicken in Pizza Dough recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,2.0,545.0,5.9,1.6,69.7,628.0,97.3,3.9,1.4,22.8,"0.0","Chicken in Pizza Dough Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare pizza dough (see recipe following).  While dough rises, prepare baked  chicken and vegetables. 2: After dough has risen and chicken has finished baking,  turn  dough onto a lightly floured board. 3: Cut off a small piece of  dough the  size of a tennis ball to use for a top decoration. 4: Form remaining dough into a  ball and roll out to a 12 x 17-inch  rectangle. Place chicken, breast side down, in the middle  of the dough. 5: Arrange vegetables around chicken. 6: Wrap sides  and  ends of dough over chicken. 7: Turn right side up and place  on a baking sheet.  Brush surface with beaten egg. 8: Roll out  reserved piece of dough. 9: Using a cookie cutter, cut out a  design and place on top of dough wrapped chicken. 10: Brush with  egg. 11: Bake in pre-  heated 425 degrees oven for 30 minutes, until  golden brown. 12: To serve, let everyone tear off the bread, then cut up  the chicken. 13: PIZZA DOUGH: Dissolve yeast, sugar and salt in warm water. 14: In  large bowl,  combine 2 cups of flour and yeast  mixture; beat with an electric mixer several  minutes. 15: Stir in enough  additional flour to make a stiff dough. 16: Turn out on a   floured board and knead 5 minutes until smooth and elastic. Place  dough in a  lightly oiled bowl; turn to coat surface of dough  with oil. 17: Cover with a damp  cloth and let rise in a warm  place until double in bulk (about 2 hours).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(125,"Chicken Lasagna","PT2H","PT30M","PT2H30M","Make and share this Chicken Lasagna recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",5.0,2.0,209.3,10.3,4.7,29.4,693.5,10.9,0.8,3.1,18.1,"8.0","Chicken Lasagna Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix filling ingredients in large bowl. 2: Spread 1 cup filling on bottom of each of 2 8x8 pans. 3: Cook noodles for 3 min (or not at all). Break noodles to fit pans and layer over filling. 4: Repeat. Evenly divide remaining filling for the final layer. 5: Sprinkle with paprika. 6: Freeze. To serve, sprinkle cheddar cheese on top and bake from frozen to done for 1-2 hours at 400 deg.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(126,"Chicken Liver Pate","PT3H","PT35M","PT3H35M","Make and share this Chicken Liver Pate recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Livers",0.0,0.0,201.2,17.9,10.9,144.2,301.2,1.9,0.2,0.7,6.2,"8.0","Chicken Liver Pate Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring liver, onions, chicken broth, brandy to boil. 2: Cook 5 min. 3: Put in  blender. 4: Add paprika, salt and cayenne pepper. 5: Blend on high. 6: Add butter and cream cheese. Pour in a mold or container. 7: Let stand covered in refrigerator until  firm about 3 hours. 8: Serve with crackers or party rye.                    - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(127,"Chicken Liver Pate II","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Chicken Liver Pate II recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Livers",5.0,1.0,233.6,21.0,12.8,146.5,93.5,6.6,1.4,0.8,5.8,"4.0","Chicken Liver Pate II Recipe Instructions:  1: Marinate livers in the cognac overnight. Drain Soak dried mushroom in hot water  for 1 hour. 2: Drain it squeezing out all the liquid Melt 1 tbs butter in a pan Add the livers, onion, mushroom and garlic. Cook until almost all the red has  disappeared. 3: Add the cream, the funghi,  and the spices and cook to reduce by  half over high heat. Turn off heat, process everything and mix in the butter  while still hot.. 4: Pour into a mold and refrigerate If you like you may top it  with gelatin");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(128,"Coconut Shrimp With Orange Mustard Sauce","0","PT45M","PT45M","Make and share this Coconut Shrimp With Orange Mustard Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Coconut",5.0,2.0,2620.3,118.8,98.5,714.4,6021.8,274.4,34.5,93.0,109.9,"0.0","Coconut Shrimp With Orange Mustard Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel and devein the shrimp leaving the tails intact. Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a medium bowl, stirring well. 2: Make a well in center of the flour mixture. Gradually add beer stirring until batter is smooth. 3: Dip shrimp in batter then dredge in the coconut. Fry shrimp in hot oil until lightly browned. 4: Drain in paper towels. 5: Orange Mustard Sauce:  Combine marmalade, juice and mustard in a small bowl, stirring well.  Makes 1 cup. 6: Jan.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(129,"Chicken Liver Pate III","PT13H3M","PT1H15M","PT14H18M","Make and share this Chicken Liver Pate III recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Livers",0.0,0.0,968.4,72.0,40.0,1418.7,747.2,2.8,0.3,0.6,63.1,"0.0","Chicken Liver Pate III Recipe Instructions:  1: Using a large skillet, sweat the livers in 4 oz of the butter. 2: After 3 minutes,  add the onion, salt, and pepper. 3: Cook until the livers are just off-pink. 4: Set  aside and hold warm. 5: Line a 2 l/2quart mold with a single layer of the bacon  slices. 6: Chill the mold. 7: Puree the liver and onion mixture in a food processor. 8: Gently warm the remaining butter. 9: Add to the livers with the brandy and cream. 10: Mix again to assure uniformity Pour into the well-chilled mold. 11: Place the mold  in a water bath that reaches to I in. 12: (2.5 cm) from the top of the mold. 13: Bake  45-60 minutes at 3250F (1630C) until the pate sets. 14: Shake the pan gently to  observe the texture. A metal cake tester should come out clean. 15: The time will  vary depending on the thickness of the mold. 16: Record the time for future  reference. Remove from the oven and water bath. 17: Cover and chill for a minimum of 12 hours. 18: Unmold, plate, and garnish for presentation.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(130,"Appetizers-Easy Stuffed Mushrooms","PT7M","PT35M","PT42M","Hi,  Here is a great recipe for Stuffed Mushrooms that is easy to make and is usually goes over well.   You can make these a day ahead and bake before serving.","< 60 Mins",5.0,20.0,81.8,6.2,3.7,15.3,195.8,5.5,0.8,1.5,2.0,"6.0","Appetizers-Easy Stuffed Mushrooms Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash and dry the mushrooms. 2: Remove and chop the stems. 3: Melt butter in a 12 inch skillet over medium high heat.  Add the mushroom stems, celery and  onion. 4: Saute until the onion is translucent, stirring occasionally. 5: Stir in the bread crumbs, Worcestershire Sauce and seasonings. 6: Mound the stuffing onto the mushroom caps. 7: Arrange caps on a greased baking sheet.  Bake for 5-7  minutes, or until thoroughly heated. 8: If you like mushrooms, you will like this!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(131,"Anzac Biscuits","PT15M","PT10M","PT25M","These biscuits (cookies in America) are called Anzacs because they were baked by Australian women and sent to their ANZAC soldier sons/husbands serving in Europe and Middle east during WW I. It was more like 2 months before they were received back then, so they certainly do travel well! :-)  ** Please note that 1 Australian Tablespoon =  20 mls whereas in most others countries it = 15 mls.  Anzac Biscuits","< 30 Mins",5.0,32.0,199.4,10.4,6.8,22.3,143.4,25.0,1.5,10.9,2.2,"12.0","Anzac Biscuits Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix oats, flour, sugar and coconut together. 2: Melt syrup and butter together. 3: Mix the bicarb with boiling water and add to butter and syrup mixture.  Add this to dry ingredients. 4: Place tablespoonsful of the mixture on a greased oven slide (cookie sheet).  Bake at 150 - 160 C (300-325F) for 20 minutes. 5: Good luck.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(132,"Ancho Chile Rub","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Ancho Chile Rub recipe from Food.com.","Free Of...",0.0,0.0,75.5,2.7,0.4,0.0,3658.7,14.2,7.3,0.8,3.3,"0.0","Ancho Chile Rub Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine ancho chiles, mild chili powder, hot chili powder, chimayo chili powder, cayenne pepper, black pepper, salt, and chipotle paste in a large bowl. 2: Makes about 2 cups.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(133,"Amish Six Layer Dinner","PT2H","PT0S","PT2H","Make and share this Amish Six Layer Dinner recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",4.0,8.0,338.4,16.9,6.5,74.8,1453.8,23.1,4.7,6.1,23.8,"4.0","Amish Six Layer Dinner Recipe Instructions:  1: Grease a casserole dish. 2: Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper before adding the next layer.  Place potatoes in the bottom of the casserole.  Add the layer of  celery.  Add the layer of hamburger.  Add the layer of onions.  Add the green  pepper. 3: Pour the tomatoes over the mixture. 4: Bake for 2 hours at 350°F (I  cover with foil after about an hour).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(134,"Chicken on Sunday  (Or Whenever)","PT2H","PT35M","PT2H35M","Make and share this Chicken on Sunday  (Or Whenever) recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",4.0,1.0,951.2,31.8,9.5,129.1,769.2,118.7,2.8,1.5,42.4,"6.0","Chicken on Sunday  (Or Whenever) Recipe Instructions:  1: Grease large 9x13-inch pan. 2: Heat soups and milk together in a large saucepan. 3: Stir in Minute Rice (you want the mixture to be rather juicy). Pour into 9x13-inch pan. 4: Place chicken part on top and then sprinkle with seasoning salt, pepper and curry lightly. 5: Cover all with foil. 6: Bake at 325°F for 2 hours and 15 minutes. 7: I have baked this on a higher temp with less baking time but, you have to watch that you don''t make the rice get hard and crusty by doing so.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(135,"Chicken Pot Pie Lasagna","PT1H35M","PT35M","PT2H10M","Make and share this Chicken Pot Pie Lasagna recipe from Food.com.","Savory Pies",5.0,8.0,334.8,13.8,7.2,68.1,517.3,19.2,2.1,3.2,30.8,"10.0","Chicken Pot Pie Lasagna Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare pasta according to package directions. 2: Spray a Dutch oven or large   skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot. Add  chicken  and saute 4 minutes or until cooked through. 3: Drain well and set  aside.   Recoat Dutch oven with cooking spray and place over medium-high heat until   hot. Add  mushrooms, carrots and onions; saute 6 minutes. 4: Set aside.  Place flour in a  medium saucepan. 5: Gradually add milk, stirring with a wire   whisk until blended; stir in sherry. 6: Bring to a boil over medium heat and  cook for 5 minutes or  until thickened, stirring constantly. 7: Stir in salt  and  red pepper. 8: Reserve one cup of sauce and set aside.  In a bowl, combine ricotta cheese, 1 cup mozzarella cheese and Swiss  cheese.  Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 9: Spread 1 cup of the  sauce over the bottom of  a  13 x9 x 2-inch pan. 10: Arrange 4 pieces of the lasagne (3 lengthwise, 1  widthwise)over the sauce. Top with half of ricotta cheese  mixture, half of   chicken mixture and half of remaining sauce mixture.   Repeat layers, ending with 4 pieces of lasagne. Spread reserved 1 cup of  sauce over  the last complete layer of lasagne, being sure to cover the  lasagne completely. 11: Cover lasagne with foil and bake 1 hour. 12: Uncover  lasagne,  sprinkle remaining  1/2 cup mozzarella cheese on top and bake an additional  5  minutes uncovered. 13: Re-cover and let stand 15 minutes before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(136,"Chicken Roll-Ups","PT20M","PT50M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Chicken Roll-Ups recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",5.0,8.0,330.7,19.4,10.2,76.0,552.7,31.8,2.3,3.7,7.5,"4.0","Chicken Roll-Ups Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil chicken until done and no pink remains. 2: Cool and chop into  small cubes. 3: In a large bowl, mix together the cream cheese, butter, onion,  pimento, milk,  salt, and pepper. 4: Stir in chicken and set aside.  Open crescent rolls and place each piece of dough flat on a  lightly greased baking sheet.  Place several  tablespoons of chicken mixture on the center of  each piece of dough. 5: Roll up  dough around the chicken mixture making sure are  edges are sealed. 6: Dip each  chicken roll in melted butter and roll in the crushed  croutons or corn flakes  (optional). Place on baking sheet.  Bake at 350°F for 15-20 minutes or  until golden brown. 7: Serve with chicken gravy if desired. 8: To make chicken  gravy add 1 can cream of chicken soup to a  small saucepan. 9: Add 1 tablespoon  fresh lemon juice and stir well. 10: Add milk or sour cream to thin to desired  consistency. 11: Cook over  low heat until hot. Serve over chicken roll-ups.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(137,"Chicken Supreme with Mushrooms","PT1H","PT50M","PT1H50M","Make and share this Chicken Supreme with Mushrooms recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,1.0,411.0,26.8,12.2,128.0,209.7,7.3,1.0,3.2,32.0,"4.0","Chicken Supreme with Mushrooms Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt 15g of the butter in a pan. 2: Add the onions and saute until soft. Add the  mushrooms and salt and pepper to taste and cook until soft. Add the wine, tomato puree and stock and continue cooking, stirring, until the liquid is well  concentrated; chill. 3: Beat out the chicken breasts to an even thickness and place each one on a sheet of foil. 4: Divide the mushrooms mixture between them and dot  with the remaining butter. 5: Fold the foil over the top and seal the edges. 6: TO FREEZE Place parcels on a baking sheet and freeze, then pack in a plastic  bag. 7: Seal, label and return to the freezer. 8: TO SERVE Place the foil parcels on a baking sheet. Cook from frozen in a  preheated hot oven, 220 C , for about 1 hour. 9: Remove the foil and sprinkle with  parsley.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(138,"Cola Roast","PT3H","PT15M","PT3H15M","Make and share this Cola Roast recipe from Food.com.","Free Of...",4.5,7.0,632.0,24.9,7.0,211.2,2236.9,27.6,5.2,17.6,73.1,"4.0","Cola Roast Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 325F. 2: In a small bowl, combine the salt, pepper, and garlic powder; rub over surface of roast.  In a Dutch oven, heat the oil to hot and brown roast on all sides. 3: Transfer roast to roasting pan. 4: Combine all the remaining ingredients; pour over roast.  Cover and roast for 2 1/2-3 hours until tender.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(139,"Cola Cake","PT35M","PT20M","PT55M","Make and share this Cola Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,560.7,24.9,15.1,108.1,403.6,80.2,1.2,52.8,6.1,"8.0","Cola Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat all but eggs and marshmallows for two minutes. 2: Add eggs and beat two minutes more.  Stir in marshmallows. 3: Bake in 9 X 13 pan for 35 minutes. 4: FROSTING: 1/2 cup butter or margarine  3 tablespoon cocoa 1 pound powdered sugar 1/3 cup Coke or Pepsi 1 cup chopped nuts Mix butter, cocoa, sugar and Coke well together and add chopped nuts. 5: Pour over hot cake.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(140,"Chicken Sate with Peanut Sauce","0","PT20M","PT20M","We prefer the chicken breasts whole, with the sauce accompanying, but you can cut it into chunks and skewer it if you prefer.  The sauce is SO good that I eat the leftovers with a spoon!  (Also very good on toasted English muffins...)","Chicken Breast",5.0,11.0,527.6,37.9,13.0,109.1,1525.5,12.2,3.4,3.2,38.2,"6.0","Chicken Sate with Peanut Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine butter, 1/4 cup soy sauce, coriander, and 2 Tbsp lime juice. Marinate chicken in this while you make peanut sauce:  Saute onion and garlic in oil  until tender. 2: Cool. 3: Place in blender, add everything else, and blend carefully. 4: Slowly and carefully add enough boiling water to form a thick paste.  Now, broil chicken until done, basting with marinade.  Serve with peanut sauce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(141,"Coconut Crunch Beans","PT48H3M","PT10M","PT48H13M","Garden-fresh beans receive an exotic twist with a lightly spiced crunchy coconut and sesame seed topping.","Coconut",4.0,1.0,269.9,23.4,18.8,10.1,191.6,15.5,8.8,3.7,4.5,"4.0","Coconut Crunch Beans Recipe Instructions:  1: In nonstick skillet, cook sesame seeds, stirring, over medium heat for 2 minutes or until slightly golden. 2: Stir in half of the butter until melted. 3: Stir in coconut, chili powder, turmeric and salt; cook, stirring, for 1 minute or until coconut turns deep golden. 4: (Coconut mixture can be stored in airtight container at room temperature for up to 24 hours.) In large pot of boiling salted water, cook beans for 3 minutes; drain well. 5: (Beans can be prepared to this point, chilled under cold water, drained and refrigerated in towel-lined airtight container for up to 24 hours.) In nonstick skillet, melt remaining butter over medium heat; cook beans for about 3 minutes or until tender-crisp. 6: Toss with coconut topping.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(142,"Coconut Chicken Bites","PT25M","PT40M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Coconut Chicken Bites recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,29.0,1094.1,81.8,50.7,319.5,1046.4,34.6,7.9,3.3,57.0,"2.0","Coconut Chicken Bites Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 400°F. 2: Mix flour, coconut, salt, pepper and garlic powder together. 3: Dip chicken bites in the egg, then in the flour mixture. Place the chicken bites onto a greased cookie sheet or baking pan. 4: Drizzle with melted butter. 5: Bake approximately 25 minutes or until the chicken is browned and cooked through. 6: Turn once during cooking. 7: This is good served with an apricot or plum dipping sauce.  Jan.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(143,"Chocolate Pound Cake","PT1H41M","PT1H35M","PT3H16M","I am resending this recipe.  This is the corrected version!  I really made a  goof up on the original.  Sorry about the mistake I''ve made.","Dessert",4.5,5.0,2905.2,168.7,101.2,1031.4,1092.8,321.9,9.2,178.0,38.2,"1.0","Chocolate Pound Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Use a 8 x 4 x 2 1/2\ 3: ,  4: ,  5: ,  6: ,  7: ,  8: Increase to medium speed and beat for 1 minute to  develop the cake''s structure.  Scrape down the sides. 9: Gradually add the  remaining chocolate mixture in 2 batches, beating 20 seconds after each addition to incorporate the ingredients and strengthen the structure.  Scrape down the  sides. 10: Scrape the batter into the prepared pan and smooth the surface with a  spatula. 11: The batter will be almost 1/2 inch from the top of a 4-cup pan. 12: (if your  pan is slightly smaller, use any excess batter for cupcakes.)  Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, (40 to 50 minutes in a fluted tube pan) or until a wooden toothpick  inserted in the center comes out clean. 13: Place loosely with buttered foil over  the cake after 20 minutes to prevent over browning. 14: The cake should start to  shrink away from the sides of the pan only after removal from the oven. 15: Let the cake cool in the pan on a rack for 10 minutes. 16: Loosen the sides with a metal  spatula and invert onto a greased wire rack. 17: If baked in a loaf pan, to keep  the bottom from splitting, reinvert so that the top is up and cool completely  before wrapping airtight. 18: TOPPING:  This is for extra moistness and gives a subtle coffee accent. 19: In a  small pan, stir together 1/4 cup water and 2 Tbsp sugar. 20: Bring to a full rolling boil. 21: Cover and remove from heat.  When cool, add 1 tbsp Kahlua. 22: When cake is baked, brush half the syrup onto the top. 23: Cool the cake 10 minutes and invert it onto a lightly greased rack. 24: Brush the bottom and sides with remaining syrup. 25: Reinvert onto rack, top side up, to finish cooling.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(144,"Chicken With Portabella Mushrooms-","0","PT15M","PT15M","For extra richness, finish with a Tablespoon of butter, My suggestion  is to serve with a nice pasta side,  salad and fresh baked bread.","Chicken Breast",3.0,3.0,521.0,27.4,5.8,92.8,96.9,32.8,2.2,3.0,35.2,"2.0","Chicken With Portabella Mushrooms- Recipe Instructions:  1: Dredge the chicken breast pieces in flour and saute in olive oil. 2: In a non stick pan you can get by with very little. 3: Add the onions and mushrooms and saute till soft. 4: Add the lemon juice and fresh herbs, saute for 1 minute  till the flavors  combine.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(145,"Low-Fat Apple &amp; Apricot","0","PT20M","PT20M","Make and share this Low-Fat Apple &amp; Apricot recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,164.5,0.3,0.0,0.0,7.9,42.4,2.5,35.5,1.4,"4.0","Low-Fat Apple &amp; Apricot Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a 3-quart pot. 2: Simmer uncovered for the better part of an hour, stirring often. 3: Add more juice if necessary and discard spice packet at end of cooking time. 4: Serve warm or chilled. 5: Keeps for days in the refrigerator.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(146,"Chicken, Mozzarella & Pepper Tarts","PT25M","PT30M","PT55M","Make and share this Chicken, Mozzarella & Pepper Tarts recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",5.0,1.0,54.8,3.8,1.7,16.0,72.5,0.7,0.1,0.4,4.3,"0.0","Chicken, Mozzarella & Pepper Tarts Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 F. 2: In a non-stick skillet, stir cook the chicken just until it turns white. Add the onion, pepper, tomatoes and basil. 3: Continue to stir cook until the onions are tender. 4: Remove from the heat and let cool. 5: Stir the Mozzarella into the cooled chicken mixture then fill the tart shells. 6: Bake in the oven for 20-25 minutes or until the pastry is golden brown and the filling is bubbly.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(148,"Cola Fruit and Date Loaf","PT1H","PT50M","PT1H50M","--Adopted Recipe--  The original submitter says that this fruity loaf showed up in Coke and Seven-Up cookbooks. The recipe was adapted  from &quot;Cooking With Coke&quot; - a publication of the Coca Cola Company.  Be sure to make a day ahead of time, because it is best the next day.","Quick Breads",5.0,3.0,267.0,6.2,0.7,17.6,150.0,51.4,2.6,32.2,3.6,"12.0","Cola Fruit and Date Loaf Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 Fahrenheit. 2: Generously grease a 9 by 5 inch loaf pan. 3: Chop dates. 4: Heat cola to boiling.  Remove from heat and stir in dates, mixing very well. 5: Stir in sugar and oil.  Cool while preparing other ingredients. 6: Stir dry ingredients together and add to cola mixture.  Stir in egg, extract and nuts. 7: Spoon batter into pan.  Bake about 1 hour until cake tests done.  Cool on a rack for 20 minutes then remove from pan and wrap. 8: Store overnight before slicing.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(149,"Coca-Cola Cake","PT1H","PT35M","PT1H35M","Make and share this Coca-Cola Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,9.0,1012.3,44.7,8.8,47.1,1006.8,148.8,2.8,116.3,9.2,"8.0","Coca-Cola Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine flour, sugar, salt, cocoa and baking soda. 2: In small saucepan, bring butter and Coca-cola to a boil. 3: Add dry ingredients to mixture and then add buttermilk, eggs, and marshmallows. 4: (batter will be thin). Bake in 9x12 inch baking pan at 350 degrees for about 45 to 60 minutes or until tooth pick comes out clean. 5: Topping for coca-cola cake: Combine butter cocoa and coke in a small saucepan and bring to a boil. 6: Pour over sugar and mix well. 7: Add nuts an vanilla. 8: Pour over cake while still hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(150,"Chicken-Fried Steak With Cracked Pepper Gravy","PT15M","PT1H20M","PT1H35M","Make and share this Chicken-Fried Steak With Cracked Pepper Gravy recipe from Food.com.","Steak",5.0,10.0,1635.7,147.3,34.5,241.1,1017.8,46.0,1.9,0.3,32.9,"4.0","Chicken-Fried Steak With Cracked Pepper Gravy Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare the flour spice by blending the flour, salt, pepper, and cayenne. Set aside on a plate or wax paper. 2: Prepare the batter by mixing the eggs with a whisk, in a large bowl. 3: Add the cream, and beer. Whisk to blend. 4: Set aside. In a deep, heavy skillet, heat the oil to 350 degrees. While the oil is heating, prepare the round steaks by dredging them in the flour spice, taking care to evenly coat the meat. Shake off any  excess. 5: Dip the meat into the batter, and then again in the flour  spice, evenly coating the batter so it is dry on the outside. When  the oil temperature reaches 350 degrees (when a drop of batter sizzles when dropped in it), gently slide one steak into the hot oil. Cook the steak about 5 minutes. 6: Turn in, taking care not to break  the coating, and cook the meat 5 more minutes, or until the batter is nicely browned. Drain the cooked steak on paper towels. Repeat with the other steaks. 7: Hold the cooked steaks in a 225 degree oven until all four are done. Pour Cracker-Pepper Gravy over the steaks and serve. Yield: 4 servings. 8: CREAM GRAVY Melt the butter in a heavy saucepan. 9: When the foam goes down, whisk in the flour. Continually whisk until the flour cooks, becoming a fragrant light brown. 10: Slowly add the milk, continuing to whisk to  keep lumps from forming. 11: Season with salt and pepper. 12: Simmer gravy for 10 minutes to cook and reduce. Serve hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(152,"Claudi Sanders'' Refrigerator Rolls","PT4H20M","PT40M","PT5H","Make and share this Claudi Sanders'' Refrigerator Rolls recipe from Food.com.","Healthy",5.0,1.0,329.0,10.6,3.1,5.7,201.2,51.3,1.6,8.5,6.9,"0.0","Claudi Sanders'' Refrigerator Rolls Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400. 2: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. 3: Add potatoes and cream again. 4: In separate pot,m heat milk to lukewarm, and dissolve yeast.  Pour milk mixture into shortening, sugar and potatoes. 5: Ad enough flour (about 4 cups) to make a like a cake dough consistency. 6: Stir in salt.  Cover. 7: Let rise 2 hours, stir in balance of flour (about 6 to 7 cups), baking soda and powder to make like biscuit dough-knead. 8: Cover and refrigerate 1/2 hour, make into tolls. 9: Let rise until double in size.  Bake about 15-20 minutes. 10: Refrigerate and use over 5 or 6 days. 11: Makes 24 rolls.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(153,"$20,000 Prize-Winning Chili Con Carne","PT2H20M","PT35M","PT2H55M","Make and share this $20,000 Prize-Winning Chili Con Carne recipe from Food.com.","Pork",4.0,4.0,558.1,16.8,5.0,133.8,1004.2,38.5,10.0,13.8,55.6,"0.0","$20,000 Prize-Winning Chili Con Carne Recipe Instructions:  1: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, brown half the meat; pour off fat. Remove meat. 2: Brown remaining meat; pour off all fat except 2 Tbsps. 3: Add onion, garlic; cook and stir until tender. 4: Add meat and remaining ingredients except flour, cornmeal and warm water.   Mix well. 5: Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer covered 2 hours. 6: Stir together flour and cornmeal; add warm water.   Mix well. 7: Stir into chili mixture.  Cook covered 20 minutes longer. 8: Serve hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(154,"Chilies Corn Muffins","PT25M","PT35M","PT1H","Make and share this Chilies Corn Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,7.0,163.6,5.3,0.8,17.8,155.6,26.2,0.9,9.2,3.1,"12.0","Chilies Corn Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400. 2: Spray a standard muffin pan with cooking spray. 3: In medium bowl, whisk flour, cornmeal, both sugars, baking powder and salt.  In medium  bowl, mix remaining ingredients. 4: Make well in dry ingredients. 5: Add milk  mixture and stir until just blended. 6: Divide batter among prepared muffin cups. 7: Bake 15 to 20 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly pressed. 8: Let cool in pan 5 minutes, them loosen edges and turn out on rack and cool completely.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(155,"Classic Cream Scones","PT20M","PT1H5M","PT1H25M","You''re best off describing scones to a German by saying that they are like a   cross between a Kuchen (cake), a Plaetzchen (cookie), and a Broetchen   (roll), but are very unique and not really like anything else found in   Germany. My German husband *loves* this recipe:  Classic Cream Scones   (from Simply Scones, by Leslie Weiner and Barbara Albright)","Scones",5.0,29.0,168.2,8.1,4.9,36.5,82.4,21.5,0.8,7.2,2.7,"0.0","Classic Cream Scones Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 425F. 2: Lightly butter a baking sheet. In a large bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.   Cut the butter into 1/2-inch cubes and distribute them over the flour   mixture. With a pastry blender or two knives used scissors fashion, cut in   the butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. 3: In a small bowl, stir   together the cream, egg, and vanilla. 4: Add the cream mixture to the flour   mixture and stir until combines. 5: Stir in the currents/raisins (optional). With lightly floured hands, pat the dough into a 1/2-inch thickness on a   lightly floured cutting board. 6: Using a floured 2 1/2-inch-diameter round   biscuit cutter or a glass, cut out rounds from the dough and place them on   the prepared baking sheet. Gather the scraps together and repeat until all   the dough is used. 7: Lightly brush the tops of the scones with the egg mixture,   if desired. 8: Bake for 13-15 minutes, or until lightly browned. 9: Remove the baking sheet to a wire rack and cool for 5 minutes. 10: Using a   spatula, transfer the scones to the wire rack to cool. 11: Serve warm or cool   completely and store in an airtight container. 12: Makes about 14 scones. 13: Variation: Add about 1 1/2 teaspoons of grated lemon peel to the dry ingredients. 14: My variation: Classic Scones 280 grams all-purpose flour 65 g granulated sugar 2 teaspoons baking powder 1/8 teaspoon salt 110 g unsalted butter, chilled 6 tablespoons milk 1 large egg 1 teaspoon vanilla sugar 125 g raisins Preheat oven to 220C. 15: Directions as above.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(156,"Chinese Chicken","PT1H30M","PT25M","PT1H55M","Make and share this Chinese Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",4.5,3.0,373.4,21.8,6.3,103.5,491.8,13.5,2.3,1.2,28.0,"6.0","Chinese Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash and dry chicken. 2: Combine the rest of the ingredients together and mix well. 3: Add the chicken, coat well with the marinade.  Allow to stand several hours or overnight in refrigerator. 4: Place chicken in a baking dish and pour over marinade.  Cover dish with foil. 5: Bake in a moderate oven 1 1/2 hours, remove foil, bake a further 30 minutes, brushing frequently with marinade.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(157,"Classic Chicken and Coconut Soup","PT32M","PT55M","PT1H27M","Make and share this Classic Chicken and Coconut Soup recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",4.5,4.0,587.8,52.0,41.2,46.4,836.8,11.8,0.1,0.9,24.5,"2.0","Classic Chicken and Coconut Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil in heavy medium saucepan. 2: Reduce 3: heat, add chicken and simmer until almost cooked through, turning occasionally, about 12 minutes. 4: Transfer chicken to plate; cool. 5: Remove chicken skin and bones. 6: Cut meat into 1/2-inch pieces. 7: Strain soup through sieve into small saucepan. 8: Add 1 Tbsp lime juice and jalapeno to soup and simmer until reduced to 2 cups, about 20 minutes. 9: Add chicken and simmer just to heat through. 10: Taste, adding more lime juice if desired. 11: Ladle soup into bowls. 12: Sprinkle with fresh cilantro.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(158,"Chinese Hot and Sour Chicken Noodle Salad","0","PT1H20M","PT1H20M","Make and share this Chinese Hot and Sour Chicken Noodle Salad recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,1.0,340.7,12.7,2.5,30.9,375.7,45.0,9.2,1.1,15.9,"6.0","Chinese Hot and Sour Chicken Noodle Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: In a 5-6 quart pan, bring about 3 quarts of water to a boil. 2: Add chicken, cover  and bring to a boil. 3: Remove from heat and let stand, covered, until meat is  white in thickest part, about 20-25 min. 4: Lift out chicken, let cool and reserve  water. 5: Remove and discard skin and bones*; tear chicken into bite-size shreds. 6: If made ahead, cover and chill chicken and water until next day. 7: Bring water to a boil and add linguine. Boil, uncovered, until just tender to  bite, 6-8 min. 8: Drain; immerse in cold water until cool, then drain well again. 9: Remove any debris from peppercorns. 10: In a 6-8\ 11: ,  12: ,  13: ,  14: ,  15: ,  16: - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  NOTES : * I just use boneless, skinless chicken breasts to start with.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(159,"Clam - Lobster Bake","PT6H40M","PT1H15M","PT7H55M","Even if you don''t live at the beach, you can enjoy an impressive backyard clambake. Simply substitute a combination of greens and damp cheesecloth for seaweed, firewood for driftwood and heavy duty aluminum foil for the traditional sand covering.  About 12 lbs. of mixed greens (collard greens, kale, etc.) and 15 yards of cheesecloth will hold in moisture as food cooks. Three rolls of heavy duty 37 1/2  ft. aluminum foil will both line and seal pit","Lobster",5.0,1.0,990.1,30.8,8.4,357.7,704.2,71.1,7.3,9.6,107.2,"8.0","Clam - Lobster Bake Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare your favorite clam chowder as an appetizer. 2: Serve clambake with plenty of melted butter, lemons, and watermelon. 3: \ 4: ,  5: ,  6: ,  7: Soak corn-on-the-cob (with silk removed) and mixed greens in cold water while fire is burning. 8: Wash clams and set aside. Refrigerate lobster on ice. Peel onions; remove ends.  Oil potatoes. 9: Once fire has burned down, work quickly to prevent rocks from losing heat. Tamp down embers. 10: On top of rocks, layer pit in the following order: Half of the greens, strips of wet cheesecloth, potatoes, corn, onions, chicken halves, live lobsters and clams. 11: Cover food with remaining wet cheesecloth, then greens. 12: Cover pit with heavy duty aluminum foil. 13: Crimp all sides to the edges of aluminum foil used to line the pit. Let food steam cook 40 to 60 minutes. 14: Remove foods immediately when done. Cooking times will vary depending on temperature of rocks. 15: Peek at clams after 40 minutes.  If they are open and lobsters are bright red, dinner is ready. 16: Serve with melted butter and lemon.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(160,"Civil War Cake","PT3M","PT1H20M","PT1H23M","Someone was looking for a cake that didn''t have any milk in it.  Well I found this one of my mothers. It is got to be over 67 years old. It is really good it tastes like a spice cake.    Civil War Cake   (or-Eggless, Butterless, Milkless Cake)","Dessert",5.0,2.0,871.4,26.6,6.6,0.0,616.1,155.8,3.9,83.8,8.1,"8.0","Civil War Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine raisins, sugar, 1 cup of water, shortening, salt & spices in a saucepan. 2: Bring to a boil, simmer 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, then cool till  lukewarm, then add the other cp of water. 3: Dissolve soda in 2 teas. 4: of water, set aside.  Stir sifted & measured flour into raisin mixture & beat until smooth. 5: Add dissolved soda last. Pur into greased floured 13x9 [am & bale 50-55 min. 6: at  350 degrees. 7: It may also be cooked in a tube pan. 8: Serve with whipped cream or caramel frosting. 9: Combine 3/4 cup of brown sugar 1/2 cup of water 1/2 tsp salt in a saucepan. 10: Cook 6 min. 11: stirring often. 12: Cool to lukewarm and stir in 3 Tbsp. 13: of butter. 14: Then gradually stir in 21/4 cups of sifted confectionery sugar, beating until smooth. 15: Stir in 1 teas. 16: vanilla and spread on cake. You will be surprised how good it taste with such little ingredients.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(161,"Chinese Hot and Sour Pork Soup","0","PT40M","PT40M","Make and share this Chinese Hot and Sour Pork Soup recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,52.0,368.7,13.0,2.9,31.1,1459.3,32.1,3.0,10.5,31.6,"4.0","Chinese Hot and Sour Pork Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring stock to a simmer. 2: Add soy sauce, pork, mushrooms and chile paste. Simmer  for 10 minute. 3: Add pepper, vinegar, bamboo shoots, water chestnuts, fungus and  tofu. 4: Simmer 5 minute. 5: Mix cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water and add. 6: Bring back to simmer and pour  the eggs in a very thin stream over the surface. Let stand for 10 sec. before  stirring in the sesame oil. 7: Serve with a garnish of chopped scallions. 8: NOTE: The pepper, chile paste and vinegar can be varied for taste. I also omit the pork and use less egg.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(162,"Citrus Glazed Barbecued Pork Loin","PT35M","PT15M","PT50M","Make and share this Citrus Glazed Barbecued Pork Loin recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,5.0,835.8,50.8,13.1,136.1,3187.2,47.0,2.6,30.9,46.7,"6.0","Citrus Glazed Barbecued Pork Loin Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: In a small saucepot add canola oil and saute onions and garlic until translucent. 3: Add chipotle and arbol chilies and continue to cook until chiles start to toast. 4: Add cracked black pepper and deglaze with Worcestershire sauce and orange juice; reduce until starts to thicken. 5: Then add in your favorite barbecue sauce, reduce to low heat, and simmer for about 15 minutes. 6: Season with hot sauce, lemon juice and to taste with salt.  Strain barbecue sauce and set aside. 7: On a large sheet pan rub the pork loin with olive oil and season with salt and cracked pepper. 8: Roast in a 350 degree oven (basting with the citrus glaze about every 15 minutes) until the internal temperature is about 140 degrees. 9: Remove from oven and let meat set for about 5 minutes, slice, and enjoy!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(163,"Citrus Chicken","PT4H30M","PT10M","PT4H40M","Make and share this Citrus Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,15.0,167.7,10.2,2.4,46.4,46.1,3.6,0.1,2.2,15.3,"4.0","Citrus Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Rinse chicken; pat dry. 2: Sprinkle with salt and pepper. 3: Place chicken in plastic bag set in shallow dish. 4: For marinade, combine lemon, lime, and orange juices, oil,  sugar and oregano in small bowl. 5: Pour over chicken; seal bag. 6: Marinate in  refrigerator 4 to 24 hours, turning occasionally. 7: Drain chicken, reserving marinade. 8: Grill chicken on rack of uncovered grill directly over medium coals  12 to 15 minutes or until tender and no longer pink inside, turning once and brushing  occasionally with marinade during first half of cooking. 9: Or, broil on unheated rack of broiler pan 4 to 5 inches from heat 12 to 15 minutes, turning once and  brushing occasionally with marinade during first half of cooking. 10: Discard any remaining marinade.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(164,"Citrus Baked Halibut","PT30M","PT45M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Citrus Baked Halibut recipe from Food.com.","Halibut",4.5,4.0,755.0,22.2,8.8,176.1,918.0,36.8,1.9,29.4,97.7,"2.0","Citrus Baked Halibut Recipe Instructions:  1: OVEN COOKING: 2: Rinse halibut in cold water and dry using paper toweling. 3: Arrange  halibut in a 9\ 4:  oven-proof baking dish. 5: Preheat oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit. 6: In a frying pan, add butter, onion and garlic. Saute until translucent. 7: Remove from heat; stir in parsley, orange rind, salt and pepper. 8: Spread mixture over  halibut steaks. 9: In a small bowl, mix together orange juice and lemon juice. 10: Sprinkle juice over steaks, but be careful not to wash away the onion/garlic  mixture. 11: Bake fish in preheated 400 degree Fahrenheit oven for 20 to 22 minutes, turning over  at about 10 minutes of cooking time. 12: Continue cooking until time expires or until fish flakes easily with a fork. 13: DO NOT OVERCOOK FISH. 14: Spoon hot juices  over fish. 15: Serve at once. 16: MICROWAVE COOKING: 17: Prepare and arrange fish and onion/garlic as above. 18: Reduce orange juice by 2 tablespoons. 19: Cover fish with a clear plastic wrap vented. 20: Cook on HIGH (full power) for 4 minutes. 21: Turn fish over and cook for an additional 3 to 4 minutes on HIGH (full power) or until fish flakes easily with  a fork. 22: Spoon juices over fish and serve at once. 23: If desired, serve with Tartar Sauce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(166,"Chinese Plum Sauce","PT1H45M","PT10M","PT1H55M","Make and share this Chinese Plum Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Sauces",4.5,16.0,316.1,1.0,0.1,0.0,295.1,79.7,5.6,71.9,2.8,"0.0","Chinese Plum Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: In large heavy saucepan, bring plums, onions, water, ginger and garlic to boil over medium heat; cover, reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, until plums and onions are very tender, about 30 minutes. 2: Press through food mill or sieve and return to clean pan; stir in sugar, vinegar, coriander, salt, cinnamon, pepper and cloves. 3: Bring to boil, stirring; reduce heat to low and simmer until mixture reaches consistency of applesauce, about 45 minutes. 4: Fill and seal jars; process in boiling water bath for 30 minutes. 5: Makes about 4 cups");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(167,"Chinese Meatballs","PT48M","PT1H","PT1H48M","Make and share this Chinese Meatballs recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,7.0,230.3,11.1,2.6,115.4,1114.8,7.0,0.3,1.4,23.9,"6.0","Chinese Meatballs Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine pork, shrimp, water chestnuts, ginger, green onion, 1 Tbsp soy sauce, wine, salt, 1/2 tsp sugar, 1 Tbsp cornstarch, and egg. 2: Make twelve meatballs. 3: Heat oil in wok. 4: Add meatballs; cook 6-8 minutes, until browned, stirring occasionally. 5: Transfer meatballs to 5-qt saucepan; discard drippings. 6: Add chicken broth, 2 Tbsp soy sauce and 1/2 tsp sugar. 7: Bring to a boil. 8: Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer 30 minutes. 9: Meanwhile, core cabbage.  Cut base of leaves into 2\ 10: Cut leafy tops in half. 11: Place over meatballs; cover and simmer 10 minutes more.  Transfer meatballs and cabbage to serving platter. 12: Blend 2 Tbsp cornstarch and 3 Tbsp water, and stir into pan juices cooking until slightly thickened. 13: Add sesame oil and serve over meatballs.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(168,"Cinnamon Curry Rice","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Cinnamon Curry Rice recipe from Food.com.","Rice",5.0,1.0,3892.1,94.2,39.2,269.6,630.4,647.4,42.6,39.6,110.7,"0.0","Cinnamon Curry Rice Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring cinnamon to boil in 2 cups water, simmer covered until reduced to 1 cup;  strain, discard pulp, reserve broth. 2: Cook enough rice for 5 persons. 3: Heat butter in a wok, add flour and stir well to mix and thicken; then add curry powder and  stir well to mix; then add a little stock or water and mix well; return to boil, add carrot, potatoes, and apple, cover, simmer on low heat. 4: In a separate wok or pan, stir-fry sliced pork quickly in a little oil along with garlic. 5: Remove and  reserve. When carrots and potatoes are almost done, add cinnamon broth, pork and onions to the pot, return to boil, simmer for a few minutes, then serve over  rice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(169,"Chocolate Almond Scones","PT10M","PT40M","PT50M","Make and share this Chocolate Almond Scones recipe from Food.com.","Scones",5.0,1.0,375.0,21.1,10.9,89.8,443.9,41.0,2.5,10.3,7.6,"12.0","Chocolate Almond Scones Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit. 2: Combine flour, baking  powder, sugar and salt. 3: Cut in  butter until it resembles course meal. 4: Add 2  eggs (1 egg is reserved for later use), almond extract and cream. 5: Stir until  soft dough forms; mix in chocolate  chips and toasted almonds. 6: Pat out dough until 3/4  inch thick. 7: Cut into diamond shape; brush  with reserved egg. 8: Place on baking  pan coated with cooking spray. 9: Bake for 10  minutes until lightly browned. 10: Serve warm.");
