INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(171,"Chunky Tomato Cheese Pie","PT40M","PT35M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Chunky Tomato Cheese Pie recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",5.0,2.0,444.6,28.8,14.0,56.1,1340.5,29.4,2.2,5.7,17.6,"6.0","Chunky Tomato Cheese Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit. 2: Cut 4 of tomatoes into cubes; slice remaining tomato. 3: On a lightly floured surface roll out pastry; fit into a 9-inch pie pan; flute edges. 4: In a large bowl combine tomato cubes, cheese cubes, bread crumbs, flour, sugar and salt. Toss until well blended. 5: Spoon into pie shell. 6: Bake 30 minutes until cheese cubes melt and tomato cubes are soft. 7: Remove from oven and garnish with tomato slices. 8: Add cheese strips. 9: Return to oven. 10: Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted and tomatoes are soft.  Cut into wedges and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(172,"Chocolate Bread and Butter Pudding","PT45M","PT30M","PT1H15M","I copied this out of a  magazine yesterday while at the hairdresser, being made more beautiful (Grin)","Dessert",3.0,1.0,433.4,22.4,12.7,136.8,378.1,46.8,1.7,22.1,10.7,"4.0","Chocolate Bread and Butter Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut crusts from bread. 2: Butter and bread, cut into triangles and layer with chocolate in a ovenproof dish. 3: Beat eggs, milk, sugar, sherry and vanilla together and pour over the bread. 4: Leave to stand for 15 minutes to fully absorb liquid. 5: Heat oven to 160 C. 6: Bake for 30 minutes until golden and set.  Dust with icing sugar to serve. Hope it tastes good.");
