INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(395,"Blue Mountain Blueberry Pie","PT45M","PT45M","PT1H30M","Make and share this Blue Mountain Blueberry Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,50.0,155.8,3.2,0.6,0.0,70.7,32.9,2.0,26.2,1.0,"8.0","Blue Mountain Blueberry Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Have an 8-inch double crust pie shell ready. 2: Sort, rinse and drain blueberries. 3: Sprinkle lemon juice over berries. 4: Combine sugar, flour, lemon peel, cinnamon,  nutmeg and salt. Toss this mixture gently with the blueberries to coat well. 5: Put  berry mixture into pie shell; dot with margarine. Place second crust on top of  pie, seal edges and cut 3 slashes in top to allow steam to escape. Bake in  preheated 450°F oven for 10 minutes. 6: Lower heat to 350°F and continue  baking 30-35 minutes more. Cool pie before slicing. 7: NOTES : This is an old fashioned pie recipe that is juicy, fragrant and  delicious.  It is important to use the freshest blueberries you can find.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(397,"Cherry-Pistachio Biscotti","0","PT1H35M","PT1H35M","Make and share this Cherry-Pistachio Biscotti recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,2.0,40.4,1.6,0.5,9.5,11.4,5.6,0.3,2.8,1.0,"0.0","Cherry-Pistachio Biscotti Recipe Instructions:  1: Oven to 350 degrees. 2: Lightly grease a large cookie sheet. In a food processor,  process flour, sugar, lime peel and baking powder until blended. 3: Add butter and  cherries. 4: Pulse until cherries are coarsely chopped. 5: Spoon off and reserve 1  tablespoon of beaten eggs. 6: Add remaining eggs and pistachios and pulse until  dough is evenly moistened. 7: Turn dough out onto on a well-floured surface.(Dough  will be sticky). Divide dough in 1/4s. 8: With hands, roll each portion into a 9\ 9: Place logs crosswise 3\ 10:  wide. Brush with reserved egg. 11: Bake 25 min.  or until golden brown. 12: Let cool on sheet on a wire rack 10 min. 13: Loosen with a spatula and remove to a  cutting board. 14: Let cool 10 min.  longer. 15: Using a large heavy knife, cut each log  diagonally in 1/2\ 16: ,  17: ,  18: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(398,"Orange Hazelnut Biscotti","0","PT1H30M","PT1H30M","Make and share this Orange Hazelnut Biscotti recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,2.0,91.3,3.8,0.5,11.8,64.0,13.0,0.6,5.9,1.8,"36.0","Orange Hazelnut Biscotti Recipe Instructions:  1: Oven to 350 degrees. 2: Lightly grease baking sheets. 3: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a bowl. 4: Beat oil, orange peel, orange juice, eggs and  sugar in large bowl until smooth. 5: On low speed, beat flour mixture into orange  mixture. Add hazelnuts. 6: Divide dough in half; shape each half into 10x1 1/2\ 7: ,  8: ,  9: ,  10:  thick  slices. 11: Lay slices back on baking sheets. 12: Bake 10 min. 13: Remove baking sheets from oven; turn biscotti over. 14: Bake another 10 min. 15: remove biscotti from baking  sheets to wire racks to cool. 16: Chocolate Glaze: Combine chocolate and vegetable  shortening in small saucepan. 17: Melt over low heat, stirring frequently, until  smooth. 18: Cool slightly. 19: Dip cooled biscotti into chocolate mixture. Cool on wire  rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(399,"Alaskan Blueberry Pie","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Alaskan Blueberry Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,6.0,259.5,9.1,2.8,3.8,131.1,44.4,2.0,29.6,1.8,"8.0","Alaskan Blueberry Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook the first seven ingredients until very thick. 2: Fold in the 2 cups fresh or frozen blueberries and pour into a baked pie shell. 3: Let pie cool and top with whipped cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(400,"Calzones II","PT10M","PT15M","PT25M","Make and share this Calzones II recipe from Food.com.","European",5.0,1.0,289.5,14.5,7.7,56.2,876.0,17.9,0.4,0.5,21.5,"4.0","Calzones II Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400F and spray baking sheet with cooking spray. 2: In bowl combine first four ingredients; set aside. 3: Roll  each biscuit between 2 sheets of floured wax paper, forming  four 6-inch circles. 4: Spoon 1/4 of cheese mixture onto center of  each. 5: Moisten edges of dough slightly, then fold each circle in half over the cheese filling (the edges can be attractively crimped with the times of a fork). 6: Bake ten minutes or until golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(404,"Tamarillo Steak Casserole","PT2H30M","PT10M","PT2H40M","Make and share this Tamarillo Steak Casserole recipe from Food.com.","New Zealand",5.0,1.0,198.1,9.3,3.8,45.5,75.4,12.1,1.6,1.6,16.0,"12.0","Tamarillo Steak Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Toss cubes of steak in a mixture of flour and salt and pepper. 2: Place in a casserole and cover with the bacon. 3: Cover with a layer of tamarillos, a layer of onions, then a layer of potatoes. 4: Cover tightly and bake at 180 degrees Celsius (350 degrees Fahrenheit) for 2 hours. 5: About 30 minutes before the end of cooking remove the lid and dot the potatoes with butter.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(405,"Fha Chicken Chilies Casserole","PT2H","PT35M","PT2H35M","Make and share this Fha Chicken Chilies Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",0.0,0.0,1078.3,54.6,23.7,177.8,2165.2,81.7,4.9,5.5,62.5,"6.0","Fha Chicken Chilies Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Bake chicken, wrapped in foil, at 400 degrees Fahrenheit for 1 hour. 2: Cut into bite sized  pieces. 3: Blend cream of celery soup, cream of mushroom soup and milk in a bowl. 4: Layer 1/3 of the soup mixture, half the tortillas, chicken, onion, green chilies and cheese in a 9 x l3-inch baking dish. 5: Repeat with half the remaining soup mixture, remaining tortillas, chicken,  onion, green chilies, remaining soup mixture and cheese. 6: Bake at 350 degrees Fahrenheit for  1 hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(406,"Apricot Chicken Casserole","PT55M","PT15M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Apricot Chicken Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Thigh & Leg",0.0,0.0,298.9,13.0,3.5,118.3,880.9,14.3,1.9,5.5,29.8,"6.0","Apricot Chicken Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Place chicken drumsticks in a casserole dish. 2: Mix onion soup mix, cornflour and ginger into the apricot puree. 3: Season with salt and pepper. 4: Pour over the chicken. 5: Cover and bake at 180 degrees Celsius (350 degrees Fahrenheit) for 50 to- 55 minutes or until chicken is cooked. 6: To serve, sprinkle with chopped chives.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(407,"Luscious Applesauce Bars","PT31M","PT1H15M","PT1H46M","Make and share this Luscious Applesauce Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",4.0,2.0,122.7,5.1,3.1,21.5,118.6,18.5,0.4,11.2,1.1,"0.0","Luscious Applesauce Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. 2: Grease and flour a 13x9-inch pan. 3: In a large bowl, cream brown sugar and butter until light and fluffy. 4: Add applesauce and egg; blend well. 5: Stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, cloves and  nutmeg until well mixed. 6: Stir in cereal. 7: Spread mixture into prepared pan. 8: Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out  clean. 9: Prepare glaze: 10: Melt butter over low heat and stir in brown sugar. 11: Cook about 1  minute or until mixture bubbles, stirring constantly. 12: Remove from heat and stir in powdered sugar. 13: While glaze is still hot, drizzle it over warm bars. 14: Cool completely; cut into squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(408,"Remarkable Rhubarb Bites","PT45M","PT30M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Remarkable Rhubarb Bites recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",5.0,32.0,148.4,4.6,1.1,7.8,82.9,25.9,0.5,17.4,1.4,"24.0","Remarkable Rhubarb Bites Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Mix together rhubarb and 1/2 cup sugar. 3: Set aside.  Cream shortening, remaining 1/2 cup sugar and brown sugar. 4: Add egg and then  stir in baking soda, salt, cinnamon and flour. 5: Stir in vanilla, then rhubarb  mixture. Place batter in a greased and floured 13x9\ 6: ,  7:  squares. 8: Nancy {:-).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(409,"English Sherry Trifle","PT45M","PT55M","PT1H40M","This layered dessert is best presented in a clear glass bowl. It looks very  elegant but is so easy to prepare.  (An adopted recipe.  I have not prepared this particular version, myself, but I do love trifle.)","Dessert",0.0,0.0,5527.5,238.5,136.2,2108.3,3757.8,744.8,22.4,481.2,85.6,"1.0","English Sherry Trifle Recipe Instructions:  1: Spoon approximately 1/3 of whipping cream into bottom of glass serving bowl. 2: Next, a layer of 1 cup fruit cocktail, a layer of banana, a layer of 1 cup  puried strawberries, and finally half of the sponge cubes. 3: Pour 1 cup of Sherry over cake cubes. 4: Put 1/3 whipping cream on top, and repeat with alternate layers  of fruit cocktail, banana, strawberry, and cubes with Sherry. 5: Top with remaining whipped cream, and whole berries for garnish. 6: Sponge Cake:  beat egg yolks and lemon juice until pale, add 3/4 cup sugar and beat well. 7: In a separate bowl, beat egg whites, add salt, and 1/4 cup sugar beating until stiff. 8: Stir 1/4 of the whites into yolk mixture.  Spoon the rest carefully into yolk. 9: Sift flour on top, fold in melted butter until blended. 10: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. 11: Pour batter into tube pan, bake 45 minutes (or until toothpick comes out clean).  Invert and cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(410,"M&amp;m Super Snack Bars","PT1H15M","PT40M","PT1H55M","Make and share this M&amp;m Super Snack Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",0.0,0.0,143.0,7.2,1.2,11.6,143.7,18.3,0.8,10.0,1.9,"32.0","M&amp;m Super Snack Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. 2: Mix granulated sugar, brown sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs in large bowl until well blended. 3: Stir in flour, corn flakes, 3/4 cup of the pecans, 2/3 cup M&M candies, oats, baking soda, baking powder and salt. 4: Spread mixture in an ungreased 13x9x2 inch rectangular pan. 5: Sprinkle remaining pecans and 1/3 cup M&M candies. 6: Bake until golden brown 35 to 40 minutes; cool. 7: Cut into 2\ 8: ,  9: Heat oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit. 10: Decrease granulated sugar to 2/3 cup and brown sugar to 2/3 cup. 11: Bake 30 to 35 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(411,"Spice Scones","PT6M","PT45M","PT51M","Make and share this Spice Scones recipe from Food.com.","Scones",0.0,0.0,23.6,1.3,0.4,0.0,1.3,2.9,0.0,2.6,0.0,"60.0","Spice Scones Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. 2: Combine the flour, ginger, and nutmeg. 3: In a large mixing  bowl, cream vegetable shortening and brown sugar. 4: Beat in the molasses and brandy. 5: Gradually blend in the dry ingredients. 6: Drop the dough by spoonfuls 2-1/2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets. 7: Bake 5 to 6 minutes until golden brown. 8: As  soon as the cookies are cool enough to handle, remove them from the baking sheet and roll up around metal cone shapes. 9: Place seam side down on wire racks to cool. 10: Nancy {:-).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(412,"Fruit Loop Cookies and Orange Icing","0","PT55M","PT55M","I adopted this recipe from Recipezaar in February 2005.  I made several changes based on the review posted by Jenna Marie.  I''m really happy with the changes I''ve made to the recipe.  These cookies are great with or without icing and would be perfect for a child''s party.","Dessert",0.0,1.0,103.5,5.7,2.4,18.5,27.5,12.5,0.1,9.4,0.8,"36.0","Fruit Loop Cookies and Orange Icing Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375°F. 2: Cream together butter, shortening, sugar and brown sugar. 3: Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. 4: Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and orange extract; mix well. 5: Stir in Fruit Loops. 6: Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto a baking sheet or baking stone. 7: Bake for 10-12 minutes, until light golden brown. 8: Remove baking sheet from oven and allow cookie to cool on baking sheet for about 5 minutes before moving them to a wire rack to cool completely. 9: For orange icing, combine confectioners'' sugar and orange juice together in a small bowl, mixing until smooth. 10: Ice cookies and garnish with additional Fruit Loops.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(413,"Gado Gado: Indonesian Salad","PT5M","PT40M","PT45M","Make and share this Gado Gado: Indonesian Salad recipe from Food.com.","Indonesian",5.0,3.0,139.6,2.7,0.9,93.0,452.4,23.3,5.3,6.7,8.1,"6.0","Gado Gado: Indonesian Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring the water to a boil; add salt, cabbage, bean sprouts, and green beans. 2: Boil vegetables for 5 minutes; drain. 3: Boil potatoes in a separate pot until tender then peel them. 4: Cut potatoes, eggs and cucumber into slices. 5: Heat peanut sauce on low heat. 6: Arrange the green vegetables on a very large platter. 7: Cover them with the sliced potatoes, eggs and cucumbers. 8: Pour the peanut sauce over the entire platter and serve. 9: Serving Ideas : Serve with white rice and a meat dish. 10: NOTES : The peanut sauce may be made by hand or bought. 11: We put the Gado Gado in a large casserole dish.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(414,"Greek Lemon Potatoes","PT1H15M","PT30M","PT1H45M","Make and share this Greek Lemon Potatoes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,15.0,176.3,4.7,0.7,0.0,11.8,31.2,4.1,1.6,3.7,"6.0","Greek Lemon Potatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6. 2: Cut the potatoes into bite sized  chunks and put them in a large ovenproof dish. 3: Add the olive oil, lemon  rind and juice, water, garlic, bay leaves, rosemary, thyme, oregano,  sugar, salt and pepper. 4: Stir well. 5: Bake the potatoes for 1-1 1/4 hours or  until they are cooked through and crispy. 6: Stir every now and then during  cooking to coat with the herby oil. 7: Finally sprinkle with the chopped  parsley.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(415,"Pastitsio","PT1H25M","PT1H10M","PT2H35M","Make and share this Pastitsio recipe from Food.com.","Greek",4.5,3.0,604.4,34.6,17.9,196.0,330.9,41.3,2.0,2.7,27.0,"8.0","Pastitsio Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Melt 1 oz of butter in large skillet and saute onion til soft and transparent. Add the meat, cook until browned. 3: Mix tomato paste with wine and add to meat. Continue cooking, adding nutmeg, salt, pepper, and cinnamon. 4: Cook about 15 minutes, take off heat, cool and mix in half the breadcrumbs and half the grated cheese. Set aside. Do not allow meat to \ 5: , keep it separated. 6: Cook the macaroni in boiling water with oil til soft. Drain and set aside. Make crema: melt butter, add flour, cook briefly stirring constantly. 7: Gradually add milk stirring constantly until it starts to boil and thickens   slightly. 8: Add seasonings. 9: In a separate bowl, beat eggs. 10: Add about 1 cup of   the hot sauce to the eggs, stirring constantly. 11: Add the egg mixture back into   the saucepan, stirring constantly. 12: Stir in 1/4 cup cheese. To Assemble: Grease a baking dish (LIKE A LASAGNA PAN) and sprinkle it with breadcrumbs. 13: Spread half the cooked pasta over the bottom of the dish and sprinkle it with 1/4 cup reserved cheese. Spread all of the meat over the pasta. 14: Pour half the sauce over the meat and spread the rest of the pasta over it. Sprinkle it with 2 tablespoons of cheese. 15: Pour the rest of the sauce on top and smooth with a spatula. 16: Sprinkle with the rest of the cheese and breadcrumbs and bake in the preheated oven 50-60 minutes. 17: Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(417,"Summer Corn and Tomato Pasta","PT23M","PT20M","PT43M","Make and share this Summer Corn and Tomato Pasta recipe from Food.com.","Corn",4.5,3.0,324.6,9.4,4.4,22.2,682.9,52.1,9.3,7.1,11.7,"6.0","Summer Corn and Tomato Pasta Recipe Instructions:  1: In large bowl, stir together corn, tomatoes, beans, coriander, olive oil, garlic, jalapeno, green onions, salt and pepper. 2: Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes or for up to 2 hours. 3: In large pot of boiling water, cook pasta for 8 minutes or until tender but firm; drain and return to pot. 4: Add tomato mixture; stir over medium heat just until heated through. 5: Serve sprinkled with feta. 6: Make ahead: 7: To serve cold, rinse hot pasta  under cold water and add to tomato mixture; cover and refrigerate for up to 1  day.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(419,"Lentil Dal","PT38M","PT5M","PT43M","Make and share this Lentil Dal recipe from Food.com.","Lentil",4.5,46.0,376.4,3.4,0.6,0.0,313.3,72.0,12.5,4.3,14.3,"6.0","Lentil Dal Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat olive oil in large saucepan over medium-high heat. 2: Add onion, ginger, cumin, turmeric, red peppers, and garlic. 3: Saute 2 minutes. 4: Add cauliflower and tomatoes; saute 1 minute. 5: Stir in water and lentils; bring to a boil. 6: Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 35 minutes or until lentils are tender. 7: Stir in lime  juice, cilantro, and salt. 8: Serve 1 cup lentil mixture with 1 cup rice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(420,"Macadamia Nut Lemon Squares","PT43M","PT1H","PT1H43M","Make and share this Macadamia Nut Lemon Squares recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",0.0,0.0,234.6,12.2,3.9,33.4,54.3,29.5,1.5,20.5,3.2,"0.0","Macadamia Nut Lemon Squares Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine flour and butter and mix until crumbly. 2: Press into greased 8-inch square pan. 3: Bake at 350 degrees F for 16 minutes. 4: In a mixing bowl combine eggs, brown sugar, baking powder and vanilla; beat with an electric mixer for 2 minutes. 5: Stir in 3/4 cup macadamia nuts and cereal. 6: Pour over hot crust and spread evenly. 7: Return to oven and bake 25 minutes or until firm in center when touched. 8: Remove from oven and partially cool. 9: Combine powdered sugar, lemon juice and lemon peel; beat well. 10: Spread over macadamia nut crust. Sprinkle with the remaining 1/4 cup macadamia nuts. 11: Cool. 12: Cut into 2-inch squares. 13: Recipe courtesy of Macadamia Nut Festival, Hilo, Big Island HI.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(421,"Basic Crepes II","PT1H","PT5M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Basic Crepes II recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",5.0,1.0,100.1,4.5,2.5,52.7,74.6,11.0,0.3,0.1,3.6,"10.0","Basic Crepes II Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients in a blender. 2: Whirl one minute; scrape down and blend 15 seconds more. 3: Refrigerate at least one hour before making crepes. 4: Heat a lightly greased 6 inch skillet; remove from heat. 5: Spoon in 2 Tbsp batter; lift and tilt skillet to spread evenly. 6: Return to heat; brown on one side only. 7: To remove, invert pan over paper toweling. 8: Repeat with remaining batter.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(422,"Basic Crepes","PT1H","PT5M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Basic Crepes recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",4.0,2.0,102.3,4.4,2.3,62.2,59.3,11.4,0.3,0.1,3.9,"12.0","Basic Crepes Recipe Instructions:  1: Place all ingredients in blender container. 2: Blend. 3: Let stand at least one hour before  making crepes. 4: Heat a lightly greased 6 inch skillet; remove from heat. 5: Spoon in 2 Tbsp batter; lift and tilt skillet to spread evenly. 6: Return to heat; brown on one side only. 7: To remove, invert pan over paper toweling. 8: Repeat with remaining batter.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(423,"Mississippi Mud Pie","PT30M","PT45M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Mississippi Mud Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",4.0,7.0,1357.2,84.0,31.0,70.3,1341.3,139.0,4.7,94.2,18.6,"8.0","Mississippi Mud Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix margarine, flour and nuts; pat into a 13 x 9 inch pan. 2: Bake at 350 degrees Fahrenheit for 20 to 30 minutes until lightly browned. 3: First Layer: 4: Mix confectioners sugar, Cool Whip, and cream cheese until smooth. 5: Spread over cooled crust. 6: Second Layer: 7: Beat instant chocolate pudding, instant vanilla pudding, and milk until thickened. 8: Careful spread over first layer. 9: Cool until set in refrigerator. 10: Top with remaining Cool Whip. 11: Sprinkle shaved Chocolate on top for decoration. 12: Refrigerate or freeze for up to two months.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(424,"Couscous Cakes With Tomato-Garlic Ragout","PT1H6M","PT55M","PT2H1M","Make and share this Couscous Cakes With Tomato-Garlic Ragout recipe from Food.com.","Healthy",4.0,2.0,363.4,9.2,2.6,97.2,520.8,53.3,4.6,4.2,13.0,"6.0","Couscous Cakes With Tomato-Garlic Ragout Recipe Instructions:  1: Put the water into a saucepan over high heat. 2: When the water comes to a boil, add the salt, pepper, and couscous. 3: Remove the pan from the heat, cover it, and  let it sit undisturbed for 5 minutes. 4: Fluff the couscous by lightly running a  fork or whisk back and forth in the pan, starting with the top layer and  gradually working your way down. 5: In a large bowl, whisk the eggs; slowly whisk in the flour. 6: With a spoon, stir in the parsley and the blue cheese. 7: Add the couscous and chill the batter for 30 minutes. 8: SAUCE: 9: In a medium saucepan, heat 1 Tbsp olive oil; add the onion. 10: Sauté over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. 11: Add the garlic and sauté for 5 minutes more. 12: Add the tomatoes, white wine, and water. 13: Let the ragout simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, until it has the consistency of a thick sauce. 14: Season it with salt and pepper and keep it warm. 15: When the couscous mixture has cooled, heat a large skillet with 1 Tbsp olive oil over medium-high heat. 16: When the oil is hot, drop couscous batter onto the  skillet to form 3-inch cakes. 17: Sear them on one side for about 3 minutes, or  until the undersides are golden brown. 18: Flip them with a spatula and sear them on the other side, for about 3 minutes. 19: Remove the cakes to a plate and add more batter to the pan. 20: Continue making cakes until all the couscous batter is used. 21: You should have 3 cakes per person. 22: Serve the cakes hot on top of the warmed tomato-garlic ragout.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(425,"Galaktoboureko - Greek Custard Pastry","PT55M","PT55M","PT1H50M","Make and share this Galaktoboureko - Greek Custard Pastry recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,582.9,18.5,9.7,149.7,408.2,92.2,1.5,51.2,12.4,"10.0","Galaktoboureko - Greek Custard Pastry Recipe Instructions:  1: In a saucepan over medium heat add milk, sugar, semolina, 2 ounces  butter, vanilla, salt and a sliver of lemon peel. 2: Bring to a boil, whisking  constantly, until mixture thickens remove from heat and allow to cool  slightly. 3: Beat eggs in a separate bowl then stir into milk mixture. Set  aside. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 4: Line a 9 X 13 buttered baking pan with half the sheets of phyllo,  brushing each sheet with the melted butter and allowing the edges to overlap  the sides. 5: Spread custard evenly over phyllo. 6: Cover with remaining sheets of  phyllo, brushing each sheet with the melted butter. 7: Trim the edges and fold  in carefully to seal the filling. 8: Brush the top with melted butter and seal  edges with a bit of cold water. 9: Bake 45 minutes or until golden. 10: Meanwhile make the syrup;  In a small saucepan combine the sugar, water, lemon juice and sliver of  lemon peel and boil for 10 minutes. 11: When Galaktoboureko is done and still hot from the oven, spoon syrup over  a little at a time until absorbed by the pastry. 12: Cool completely, cut into  diamond shape and serve. 13: NOTES : This is best made the day before it is needed.  It gives the  pastry time to absorb the syrup and the filling to become firm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(426,"Cappuccino Coffee Mix","0","PT20M","PT20M","Make and share this Cappuccino Coffee Mix recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",4.5,7.0,54.3,2.2,2.0,0.0,12.4,8.0,0.1,6.8,0.7,"15.0","Cappuccino Coffee Mix Recipe Instructions:  1: Finely grind coffee and orange peel in a blender or food processor. 2: Add remaining ingredients and process until well blended. 3: Store in an airtight container. 4: To serve: Stir 2 or more teaspoons of coffee mix into 6 ounce hot water.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(427,"Frosty Latte Smoothie","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Frosty Latte Smoothie recipe from Food.com.","Smoothies",4.5,8.0,96.1,1.2,0.8,4.9,30.6,20.3,0.0,20.5,2.2,"4.0","Frosty Latte Smoothie Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large pitcher, whisk together coffee, milk and honey until thoroughly  combined and honey is dissolved; chill. 2: Just before serving; blend coffee  mixture with ice in blender until frothy and smooth.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(428,"Whipped Cappuccino","0","PT25M","PT25M","Make and share this Whipped Cappuccino recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",5.0,1.0,252.8,6.7,4.2,26.0,107.2,42.9,0.0,41.6,6.4,"2.0","Whipped Cappuccino Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve espresso powder in hot water. 2: Allow to cool to room temperature. (The  quickest way is to mix the ingredients in a small metal bowl and swirl.) 3: Combine cooled espresso mixture, sweetened condensed milk and ice in a blender. 4: Blend on high for one minute until no visible chunks of ice are left. 5: Serve with a spoon and a straw. 6: Makes 2 tall or 4 short drinks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(429,"Spanakopita","0","PT1H30M","PT1H30M","Make and share this Spanakopita recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,1.0,695.0,48.9,28.4,297.4,1180.2,44.9,6.7,4.0,23.4,"6.0","Spanakopita Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash spinach in plenty of water and cut in small pieces; place in bowl. 2: Salt lightly; stir to spread salt evenly. 3: Take spinach, a handful at a time; squeeze out the excess water; place it in another bowl. 4: Saute the onion  in half the butter until it is a light, golden color. 5: Add the scallions and cook until they wilt. 6: Add spinach; stir until all vegetables take on a light  color. 7: Stir in the dill, parsley, salt and pepper. 8: Cover the pot and cook until all the water from the spinach is absorbed. 9: Remove from the  heat; turn into a bowl, and immediately add the evaporated milk (to cool the spinach). 10: Beat the eggs in another bowl and add the cheese to them; add to the cooled spinach; mix well. 11: Line a pan with 8 sheets of phyllo dough, brushing each sheet with the  melted butter before topping it with the next sheet. Do not trim the  overhanging sections. 12: Pour in the spinach mixture, spreading it evenly over the phyllo. 13: Fold the part of the phyllo that extends out of the back of the pan over the filling. 14: Lay the remaining phyllo on top, again brushing each sheet with melted butter before adding the next. Trim the overlap. 15: Brush additional melted butter on top of the pie. 16: Score it into square or diamond-shaped serving pieces. 17: Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in a preheated 300 degree Fahrenheit oven. 18: Let stand for 30 minutes before serving. 19: NOTE: This can also be made without precooking the spinach. In that case, squeeze the spinach free of as much water as possible, mix it with the seasonings, and proceed as above, baking it for 1 hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(430,"Dublin Coddle II","PT1H5M","PT25M","PT1H30M","Make and share this Dublin Coddle II recipe from Food.com.","Pork",3.5,3.0,536.2,32.6,10.8,119.9,2023.5,24.9,3.1,2.5,35.2,"8.0","Dublin Coddle II Recipe Instructions:  1: Place sausage and ham in boiling water and cook for 5 minutes. 2: Drain meat, but reserve the liquid. 3: Put meat into a large saucepan along  with the onions, potatoes and parsley. 4: Add enough of the reserved liquid  to almost, but not quite cover the contents of the saucepan. 5: Cover and  simmer gently for 1 hour, or until the liquid is reduced by half and all  the ingredients are cooked through but not soggy. 6: Season with salt and  pepper.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(431,"Maple Salmon","PT2H14M","PT10M","PT2H24M","Serve wilted  spinach, roasted new potatoes and a glass of stout or full bodied Chardonnay,  like Cave Spring or Penfold''s Koonunga Hill.","High Protein",5.0,68.0,561.8,14.1,2.6,146.3,2255.8,37.2,0.3,32.3,69.0,"2.0","Maple Salmon Recipe Instructions:  1: Marinate the 2 salmon fillets in mixture of 1/3 cup maple syrup and 1/4 cup of soy sauce for at least 2 hours in the refrigerator. 2: Remove from refrigerator,  spoon out marinade into a saucepan and reduce over medium-low heat until you''re left with about half the original volume (about 10 minutes). 3: Broil the fillets in a lightly oiled pan for about four minutes, skin side up. 4: Flip the fillets over and brush the flesh side liberally with the reduced marinade. 5: Sprinkle  sesame seeds over top and broil for another 4 minutes or until the surface is  caramelized and the salmon is no longer translucent in the centre.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(432,"Irish Dark Soda Bread","PT45M","PT15M","PT1H","Make and share this Irish Dark Soda Bread recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,7.0,158.4,0.8,0.3,1.5,267.5,32.5,2.5,3.6,5.7,"16.0","Irish Dark Soda Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit. 2: Grease two loaf pans. 3: Sift all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, baking soda and baking powder together into a large bowl. 4: Add brown sugar and stir well to incorporate, being very careful to break up any lumps of brown sugar. 5: Add buttermilk and stir well. 6: Divide the dough between the two prepared loaf pans. 7: Bake for about 45 minutes or until brown and crunchy. 8: Cool on wire racks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(433,"Fire Ant Mound","0","PT40M","PT40M","Make and share this Fire Ant Mound recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,7761.9,504.5,269.8,1281.0,7961.6,754.9,16.5,533.9,88.5,"1.0","Fire Ant Mound Recipe Instructions:  1: Crush cookies in blender. 2: Place layer on bottom of large bowl. 3: Combine butter,  Cool Whip, cream cheese and confectioners sugar. 4: Place layer over cookie layer. 5: Combine pudding, milk and vanilla. 6: Add layer over first mixture. Alternate  layers of mixture while building dirt layer along sides of bowl. 7: Save sufficient  \ 8:  for top layer. 9: Chill for at least one hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(434,"Seared Salmon with Horseradish Tomato Vinaigrette","PT9M","PT1H10M","PT1H19M","Make and share this Seared Salmon with Horseradish Tomato Vinaigrette recipe from Food.com.","Summer",4.0,3.0,797.3,38.2,8.0,156.5,823.9,36.2,3.1,9.4,71.3,"6.0","Seared Salmon with Horseradish Tomato Vinaigrette Recipe Instructions:  1: Season the salmon fillets with salt and pepper. 2: Heat oil in a saute pan. 3: Sear   salmon on both sides for 1 to 2 minutes until golden brown. 4: Fish should still be raw in the center. 5: Combine the horseradish, bread crumbs, butter, rosemary,  tarragon, thyme. salt and pepper. 6: Add the white wine and mix to paste.  Spread  the top of the salmon with equal amounts of the bread crumbs. 7: Place fillets on  an oiled sheet tray. 8: Place tray in a preheated 375-degree oven. 9: Bake for 5 to  7 minutes until the fish is cooked through and the crust is golden brown. 10: Serve with horseradish-tomato vinaigrette. (HORSERADISH-TOMATO VINAIGRETTE): Combine horseradish, honey, vinegar, tomatoes, tomato paste,  Dijon mustard, black peppercorns and tarragon in a blender. 11: Blend until smooth. 12: While blender is running add oil in a thin steady stream  until well mixed and thick. 13: Cover and leave at room temperature.  Makes 9 oz.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(435,"Apricot Chicken With Pasta","PT18M","PT30M","PT48M","Make and share this Apricot Chicken With Pasta recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",3.5,2.0,1213.5,30.0,7.2,260.8,138.7,173.5,11.8,25.9,62.3,"2.0","Apricot Chicken With Pasta Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel onion and chop finely. 2: Crush, peel and chop garlic. 3: Heat oil in a saucepan and saute onion and garlic for 5 minutes  or until onion is transparent. 4: Cut chicken breasts into thin strips. 5: Add chicken strips to pan and stir fry 2 or 3 minutes, or until chicken is cooked. 6: Drain apricots, leaving about 2 Tbsp of the juice. 7: Puree apricots in a food processor or blender. 8: Add malt vinegar, ginger, cayenne pepper,  salt and pepper. 9: Mix to combine; pour into the saucepan. 10: Bring mixture to the boil. 11: Cook fettucine in boiling salted water for 8 to 10 minutes, or until  tender. 12: Drain. 13: Serve chicken over pasta.");
