INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(530,"Corn Dogs","PT10M","PT10M","PT20M","Here''s a good basic recipe for corn dogs. I''m looking forward to trying some of the suggestions from reviews as to adding dry mustard or other seasonings to the batter.","Lunch/Snacks",4.5,22.0,290.2,15.8,6.2,58.6,701.2,27.0,1.5,1.7,9.8,"0.0","Corn Dogs Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and egg; mix well. 2: Stir in milk to make a thick batter; place in a tall narrow glass. Let stand 4 minutes to thicken. 3: Meanwhile, heat oil to 375 degrees F. 4: Pat hot dogs dry. Dust with flour if desired. Insert sticks in hot dogs; dip into batter. Let excess drip off. 5: Fry until golden brown, about 5-6 minutes. (I''ve found it works best to fry them one at a time. Unless you have a fryer that is big enough to handle more without them touching.). 6: Drain on paper towel.");
