INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(532,"Fresh Crab Cocktail","0","PT20M","PT20M","Make and share this Fresh Crab Cocktail recipe from Food.com.","Crab",0.0,0.0,34.2,0.3,0.0,0.0,956.2,7.8,2.1,5.9,1.7,"4.0","Fresh Crab Cocktail Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients by hand and chill thoroughly. 2: Crab Cocktail  2 whole fresh Dugeness crab, cleaned and cracked  Shredded fresh icebury lettuce  2 fresh lemons, quartered  Line a serving bowl with the shredded lettuce. Arrange a cracked  crab attractively on top of lettuce and garnish with lemon quarters. 3: Serve cocktail sauce in separate bowl. 4: Serves 4  a  list for those seeking a lost favorite or family recipe");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(533,"Bacon-Swiss Tossed Salad","PT2H","PT10M","PT2H10M","Make and share this Bacon-Swiss Tossed Salad recipe from Food.com.","Free Of...",4.0,1.0,618.6,51.3,19.1,91.3,990.4,17.5,2.5,7.0,21.8,"0.0","Bacon-Swiss Tossed Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, salt and pepper. 2: In a large salad bowl, layer a third of the greens and a third of the mayonnaise mixture, onion, peas and cheese. 3: Repeat the layers twice. 4: Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. 5: Just before serving, add the bacon and toss.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(534,"Fried Cornbread","0","PT40M","PT40M","This recipe has been in my family for several generations.  In Louisiana, we serve this with boiled cabbage, turnip greens, black-eyed peas, and butterbeans.  It is delicious, but takes practice to make it just right.","Quick Breads",4.5,15.0,611.2,6.2,0.9,0.0,3459.0,128.6,12.3,0.0,15.2,"0.0","Fried Cornbread Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix cornmeal and salt together in large mixing bowl. 2: Pour approximately 2 cups boiling water over dry ingredients. 3: Mix well. 4: After the mixture cools slightly, shape mixture into balls about the size of golfballs, one at a time.  You must wet your hands with water before you make each ball. 5: Flatten the ball with your fingers. 6: Fry in skillet (preferably cast iron) with about 1/2 inch of hot oil. 7: Fry until golden brown on both sides. 8: Delicious!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(535,"Fried Green Tomatoes","PT15M","PT40M","PT55M","Make and share this Fried Green Tomatoes recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,9.0,134.3,8.0,4.9,20.3,277.5,14.3,1.7,5.0,2.6,"6.0","Fried Green Tomatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: Sprinkle sliced tomatoes with sugar, let stand about 15 minutes. 2: Combine flour, salt and pepper and coat tomato slices. 3: Melt 2 tbsp  butter in skillet. 4: Brown  tomatoes  slowly on both sides. 5: Remove each batch to oven proof platter and  keep in oven until all tomatoes are cooked. 6: Add more butter if needed. 7: For  crisp slices, serve as is. 8: Or add 1/2 cup light cream or dairy half and half to skillet. Heat, stirring into drippings, and pour over tomatoes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(536,"Fried Yellow Squash","PT5M","PT5M","PT10M","Make and share this Fried Yellow Squash recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,25.0,579.6,5.6,1.9,9.8,295.5,112.4,8.1,17.2,21.9,"0.0","Fried Yellow Squash Recipe Instructions:  1: Soak squash in buttermilk to cover, at least 5 minutes. 2: Mix dry ingredients together. 3: Dredge marinated squash in cornmeal mixture (I use a Ziploc baggie & shake until covered). 4: Fry in  vegetable oil until golden, turn and fry until lightly golden on other side. 5: Salt lightly, remove from oil, & drain on paper towels. 6: This is delicious - also  works for fried green tomatoes (cut green tomatoes at least 1/4\ 7: ,  8: Dredge in same mixture  as above & salt as you do for squash & drain on paper towels.");
