INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(538,"Baked Apple Slices","PT20M","PT25M","PT45M","Make and share this Baked Apple Slices recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,3.0,292.6,12.0,7.4,30.5,104.3,50.3,6.6,40.9,0.8,"8.0","Baked Apple Slices Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut apples into 8 or 12 slices each (like quarters). 2: toss in bowl with sugar and cinnamon, then toss in the melted butter. put in baking dish and bake at 425 basting every 10 min until done. Slices will be tender but will hold their shape.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(539,"Fruit Salad","0","PT25M","PT25M","Make and share this Fruit Salad recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",4.5,5.0,234.8,14.5,6.7,31.8,132.7,25.0,1.9,18.9,3.7,"15.0","Fruit Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Dip chopped banana pieces in pineapple juice to keep them from turning too brown. 2: Drain and discard pineapple juice. 3: Mix  fruits, nuts, cream cheese and sugar in bowl. 4: Fold  in whipped topping. 5: Spread  in 9 x 13-inch pan. 6: Freeze  until firm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(540,"Garam Masala","PT33M","PT45M","PT1H18M","This is one of the spices to be added in preparing food to give it good flavour and is to be used generally in small powdered quantity to give that aroma","Asian",4.0,1.0,410.1,24.8,3.8,0.0,215.9,64.5,31.5,2.3,14.2,"1.0","Garam Masala Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 200. 2: Spread the cinnamon, cardamom, cloves, cumin, coriander  and peppercorns in one layer in a large shallow roasting pan. 3: Roast on the  bottom shelf of the oven for 30 minutes, stirring and turning the mixture 2 or 3 times with a large wooden spoon. 4: Do not let the spices brown. 5: Break open the cardamom pods between your fingers or place them one at time on a flat surface and press down on the pod with the ball of your thumb to snap it  open. 6: Pull the pod away from the seeds inside and discard it.  Set the seeds  aside.  Place the roasted cinamon sticks between the 2 layers of a folded linen  towel and pound them with a rolling pin or a kitchen mallet until they are  finely crushed. 7: Combine the cardamom seeds, crushed cinnamon, cloves, cumin seeds, coriander  seeds and peppercorns in a small pan or bowl and stir them together until they  are well mixed. 8: Grind the spices a cup or so at a time by pouring them into the jar of an electric blender and blending at high speed for 2 or 3 minutes, until  they are completely pulverized and become a smooth powder. 9: If the machine clogs and stops, turn it off, stir the spices once or twice, then continue blending. 10: As each cupful of the spices is grounded, transfer it to a jar or bottle with a  tightly fitting lid. 11: Garam Masala may be stored at room temperature in an airtight container, and  will retain its full flavor for 5 to 6 months.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(542,"Garlic Meatballs in Lemon Sauce","PT6H","PT20M","PT6H20M","Make and share this Garlic Meatballs in Lemon Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Meat",0.0,1.0,5069.0,496.2,204.4,1046.2,4241.4,73.1,11.1,18.2,80.6,"0.0","Garlic Meatballs in Lemon Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: LEMON SAUCE: 8 oz can tomato sauce grated rind of 2 lemons 1/4 cup lemon juice salt and pepper to taste 1 Tbsp minced mint Combine all ingredients for the meatballs and form into walnut-sized balls. 2: Place in crockpot.  Mix the sauce ingredients together and pour over the meatballs. 3: Cover and cook on LOW 4 - 6 hours. 4: Serve with rice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(543,"Garlic Mushroom Sauce","PT6M","PT30M","PT36M","Make and share this Garlic Mushroom Sauce recipe from Food.com.","< 60 Mins",4.0,5.0,120.3,6.5,4.0,16.0,741.5,4.0,0.5,1.1,1.8,"4.0","Garlic Mushroom Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Crushed garlic, peel and chop finely. 2: Wipe mushrooms and slice finely. 3: Melt butter in a saucepan and add garlic and mushrooms. 4: Cook 2 minutes. 5: Add the red wine and peppercorns. 6: Bring to the boil and simmer 3 - 4 minute.  Stir in the sour cream and salt.  Drizzle sauce over chicken or steaks. 7: Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 8: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(544,"Garlic Potato Balls","PT15M","PT5M","PT20M","Make and share this Garlic Potato Balls recipe from Food.com.","Potato",4.0,1.0,208.8,6.0,3.7,15.3,87.4,35.9,5.5,2.6,3.9,"2.0","Garlic Potato Balls Recipe Instructions:  1: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat. 2: Add potatoes and sprinkle with garlic salt. 3: Cook and stir for 15-18 minutes or until golden brown. 4: Garnish with parsley.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(545,"German Onion Cake","PT35M","PT1H15M","PT1H50M","It actually looks like a pie when its finished.  We would have this in Germany every fall with new wine, it was so good.","Dessert",4.0,1.0,317.2,17.5,7.8,46.8,526.5,34.4,1.6,2.0,6.0,"8.0","German Onion Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: In medium skillet, saute the onions in butter over low heat until they just begin to brown, about 15 minutes. 2: Season with 1/4 tsp of the salt, the marjoram and the pepper. 3: Set aside to cool. 4: Preheat oven to 450°F. 5: In a food processor bowl place flour, cornstarch, baking powder, and the remaining salt; mix. 6: Add the shortening and process just until it is the texture of soft crumbs. 7: Add the milk and mix quickly to form a soft dough. 8: Oil a 10 inch round cake pan and lightly use your fingers to spread the dough out evenly. 9: Spread the cooked onion over the top. 10: Beat the egg and sour cream together. 11: Spoon the mixture over the onion, and spread it out to the very edge of the pan. 12: Sprinkle lightly with poppy seeds and paprika. 13: Bake for 20 minutes. 14: Let cool slightly, then cut into wedges.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(546,"Corn, Onion and Corn Rolls","PT20M","PT30M","PT50M","These are tasty and go down well with visitors.  Corn, Onion and Corn Rolls  Makes about 40 small rolls.","Breads",1.0,1.0,42.7,0.8,0.3,0.9,177.3,7.5,0.4,0.7,1.4,"0.0","Corn, Onion and Corn Rolls Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix 1 can reduced cream, 1 pkt onion soup mix, and spread about 1 Tbsp over each slice of bread. 2: Roll up and secure with a toothpick. Place on an oven tray,toothpick side down. Brush each roll lightly with melted butter. 3: Bake in pre-heated oven 200 C for 15-20 minutes or until golden brown. 4: Remove toothpicks and cut each roll in half before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(547,"Cornbread and Cheese Muffins","PT5M","PT30M","PT35M","Make and share this Cornbread and Cheese Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",3.0,2.0,137.8,5.0,2.6,14.2,229.1,17.5,2.0,1.5,6.7,"0.0","Cornbread and Cheese Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400. 2: Lightly spray muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray. 3: In a large bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt; mix well. 4: In a separate bowl, combine egg substitute, creamer, and cottage cheese; blend  until smooth. 5: Using electric mixer, add egg mixture to flour mixture and blend  until smooth. 6: Fold in shredded cheese and let stand 5 minutes at room  temperature.  Fill muffin cups 3/4 full and bake 25 to 30 minutes, until  toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(548,"Bacon and Potato Pie","PT45M","PT25M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Bacon and Potato Pie recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",4.0,2.0,439.1,24.3,8.3,140.8,439.3,41.3,4.5,2.4,14.0,"4.0","Bacon and Potato Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim bacon, chop finely. 2: Peel potatoes and grate.  Peel and chop onion finely, and mix all together. 3: Add flour. 4: Beat eggs and season, add milk. 5: Blend with bacon mixture.  Melt dripping in shallow pan. 6: Pour mixture in . 7: Bake at 400 F for 3/4 hour. 8: When cooked cut into squares and serve. Cheers, Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 9: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(549,"Flake-and-Fruit Squares","PT1H","PT35M","PT1H35M","Make and share this Flake-and-Fruit Squares recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",0.0,0.0,152.1,8.6,2.4,7.6,66.6,17.8,1.8,9.2,3.1,"0.0","Flake-and-Fruit Squares Recipe Instructions:  1: Line 9-inch (2.5 L) square pan with foil and grease foil. 2: In large bowl, combine cornflakes, sunflower seeds, almonds, sesame seeds, dates and apricots. 3: In large saucepan, melt butter over low heat; stir in marshmallows and heat until melted, stirring constantly. 4: Stir in vanilla. 5: Stir into cornflake mixture until well blended; spoon into prepared pan and pack firmly. 6: Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour. 7: Remove from pan; cut into squares. 8: (Store in airtight container in refrigerator for up to 3 days.) Makes 16 squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(550,"Four Treasure Chicken Soup","0","PT45M","PT45M","Make and share this Four Treasure Chicken Soup recipe from Food.com.","Clear Soup",4.0,1.0,831.9,20.9,5.9,72.6,6059.5,81.4,12.2,20.8,66.6,"0.0","Four Treasure Chicken Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Mince half of the water chestnuts and combine with chicken, 2 t.sp onions, soy   sauce, mustard and flour. 2: Reserve remaining water chestnuts and onions. 3: In a   large saucepan mix broth, sherry and garlic powder; boil. 4: Drop chicken  mixture  by teaspoonfuls into broth. 5: Add carrots and simmer 3 to 4 minute. 6: until  meatballs  are cooked. 7: Add remaining water chestnuts, green onions and pea  pods. 8: heat  through and serve immediately. 9: From: Lisa Tucker Source: http://soar.Berkeley.edu/recipes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(551,"Fragrant Lamb Stew with Dried Fruits","PT1H38M","PT45M","PT2H23M","Make and share this Fragrant Lamb Stew with Dried Fruits recipe from Food.com.","Stew",5.0,14.0,690.8,27.9,9.8,120.0,352.6,70.3,11.4,11.1,38.1,"6.0","Fragrant Lamb Stew with Dried Fruits Recipe Instructions:  1: -Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. 2: Heat olive oil in bottom of 4 to 5 quart  heavy-bottomed Dutch oven. 3: Brown cubes of lamb in oil, in batches, remove lamb  to plate. Add onions to pot, scraping up brown bits and stirring. 4: When  softened, add crushed garlic; stir to incorporate, then add carrots. 5: Cook 2 to  3 minutes. 6: Add curry, salt, pepper, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, lemon zest,  cayenne or pepper flakes, and rosemary. 7: Stir to mix in well, then add water and wine. Raise heat and let the liquids bubble.  Lower heat, then add the tomatoes, balsamic vinegar, and the lamb cubes. 8: Add dried fruits, the lemon juice, and the almonds. 9: Adjust seasonings to taste, adding more water if the stew seems too  thick. 10: Add 1/2 cup of cilantro, cover pot, and place in oven for 75 to 90  minutes. 11: From time to time, check stew, adding water as needed to keep it moist. When lamb is tender and dried fruits have softened almost enough to become part  of the sauce, remove from oven and stir in remaining cilantro. 12: Let stew rest 5  minutes and serve.");
