INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(722,"Tom''s Double Barrel Habanero Hot Sauces","0","PT30M","PT30M","Make and share this Tom''s Double Barrel Habanero Hot Sauces recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",5.0,3.0,469.7,15.5,1.2,0.0,133.9,77.9,13.4,38.1,13.5,"0.0","Tom''s Double Barrel Habanero Hot Sauces Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute the onion and garlic in the oil until soft. 2: Add the carrots with a small  amount of water. 3: Bring to a boil, reduce the heat, and simmer until the carrots are soft. 4: Place the chilies, vinegar and lime juice in a blender and blend until peppers are finely minced. 5: Add the onion, garlic and carrots and  puree the mixture until smooth. 6: Return the mixture to the stove and simmer for 5 minutes. 7: Strain the mixture into an empty hot sauce bottle.  You''ll get about 4  ounces. 8: This is a fiery hot sauce that you need to use with care. 9: Place the  ingredients that were strained out into a jar and refrigerate. 10: It  will have  the consistency of finely grated horseradish and the flavor of  habanero fruit. 11: I love this on just about everything.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(723,"Tortilla Beef","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Tortilla Beef recipe from Food.com.","Meat",5.0,3.0,1933.3,106.3,41.6,662.3,3394.9,41.4,10.9,21.7,195.7,"1.0","Tortilla Beef Recipe Instructions:  1: Spread minced garlic on round steak and  sprinkle with salt, pepper and  lime  juice. Place in the slow cooker and add  remaining ingredients. 2: Set   cooker on  low and cook for 8 hours. 3: Meat  should be fork tender and shred  easily. 4: Fill  tortillas with favorite fillings and  meat.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(728,"Beef Liver and Bacon ''n'' Onion Sauce","PT25M","PT0S","PT25M","Make and share this Beef Liver and Bacon ''n'' Onion Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Beef Organ Meats",0.0,0.0,318.4,16.7,6.2,335.9,421.7,12.2,0.4,1.3,28.3,"6.0","Beef Liver and Bacon ''n'' Onion Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook bacon in a saucepan until crisp. 2: Drain, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings; set bacon aside. 3: Saute onion in reserved drippings until tender. 4: Blend in flour and bouillon mix. 5: Gradually stir in milk. 6: Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture just comes to a boil and thickens. 7: Keep warm. 8: Pan fry or broil liver to desired degree of doneness. 9: To serve pour sauce over individual servings of liver and top with crisp bacon.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(729,"Lobster Newburg","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lobster Newburg recipe from Food.com.","Lobster",0.0,0.0,409.6,33.4,19.8,312.9,251.7,3.3,0.0,0.6,17.2,"6.0","Lobster Newburg Recipe Instructions:  1: Into a large kettle of boiling salted water plunge lobster, head first, and boil covered for 8 minutes from the time the water returns to a boil. 2: Transfer lobsters using tongs to cutting board, cool till they can be handled. 3: Break off the claws at the body, crack and remove the meat and cut into 1/2 inch pieces. 4: Remove the rest of the meat and do the same.  In heavy sauce pan cook the meat in butter over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, for 2 minutes. 5: Add 2 tbsp. sherry and 3 tbsp. brandy and cook the mixture , stirring, for 2 minutes. 6: Transfer meat with a slotted spoon to a bowl. 7: Add the cream to the sherry mixture and boil till it is reduced to about a cup. 8: Reduce heat to low and stir in the 1 tsp. sherry and brandy, nutmeg, cayenne and salt to taste. 9: Whisk in the egg yolks. 10: Cook the mixture, whisking constantly, until it registers 140* on a deep fat thermometer,, and cook it whisking, for 3 minutes more. Stir in meat and serve over toast.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(731,"Lots of Berries Pie","PT45M","PT15M","PT1H","Make and share this Lots of Berries Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",4.5,3.0,394.3,18.1,5.6,7.6,280.2,56.3,4.0,29.0,3.4,"8.0","Lots of Berries Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: In a saucepan, combine sugar, salt, cornstarch, and cinnamon. 2: Stir in berries. 3: Add water and lemon juice. 4: Cook over medium heat just to the boiling point. 5: Pour into pie shell; dot with butter. 6: Top with lattice or full crust. 7: If using a full crust, cut slits in the top, brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar. 8: Bake in oven preheated to 350F for about 45 minutes or until the crust is golden.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(735,"Low-Fat Strawberry Butter","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Low-Fat Strawberry Butter recipe from Food.com.","Strawberry",0.0,0.0,135.9,0.5,0.0,0.0,2.7,34.9,3.1,30.1,1.1,"0.0","Low-Fat Strawberry Butter Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all of the ingredients in a medium saucepan. 2: Bring to a boil, reduce to a simmer and cook until berries are soft. Drain, reserving the juices. 3: Place the berries in a food processor or blender and puree until smooth. 4: Pass through a fine strainer. 5: If too thick, add a few drops of reserved juices to thin.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(736,"BBQ Ranchero Chicken Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this BBQ Ranchero Chicken Salad recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,13.0,301.7,6.0,1.0,78.1,1002.9,34.6,4.1,10.5,28.6,"6.0","BBQ Ranchero Chicken Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Brush both sides of chicken with barbecue sauce; grill or broil about 5\ 2: ,  3: ,  4: ,  5: ,  6:  thick slices; arrange over lettuce. Drizzle salads with dressing and sprinkle with remaining 3/4 cup cheese. Chicken may be cooked, cooled, covered and refrigerated up to 1 day before serving. 7: Reheat chicken or served chilled. 8: Lettuce mixture and dressing may be prepared separately, covered and refrigerated up to 4 hours before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(739,"Low-Fat Blueberry Grunt","0","PT0S","PT45M","Make and share this Low-Fat Blueberry Grunt recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,4.0,243.3,1.4,0.6,3.2,186.8,56.1,3.2,33.8,3.9,"8.0","Low-Fat Blueberry Grunt Recipe Instructions:  1: In large nonaluminum saucepan, combine berries and 1/2 cup brown sugar. 2: Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until berries come to a boil. 3: Meanwhile, sift flours, baking powder, salt, remaining sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg into medium bowl. 4: Add milk, mixing just to moisten. 5: Drop dumplings by tablespoonfuls into boiling berries. 6: Cover with tight-fitting lid. 7: Lower heat slightly. 8: Cook without lifting lid, about 15 minutes. 9: To serve, using large spoon, transfer dumplings into bowl. 10: Surround with berries. 11: Break dumplings open with two forks. 12: Serve warm, topped with vanilla ice cream or nondairy frozen vanilla dessert.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(740,"Low-Fat Cauliflower Tomato Casserole","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Low-Fat Cauliflower Tomato Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Cauliflower",5.0,9.0,130.9,5.4,3.0,13.5,431.7,15.8,4.1,5.9,7.0,"4.0","Low-Fat Cauliflower Tomato Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350F. 2: Place cauliflower in a steamer basket over boiling water. 3: Cover saucepan and steam 4-5 minutes or until cauliflower is almost tender. 4: Arrange cauliflower in a buttered shallow baking dish. 5: Arrange tomatoes over cauliflower. 6: Sprinkle with salt and pepper. 7: Combine cheeses in a bowl and sprinkle over cauliflower mixture. Sprinkle with breadcrumbs, drizzle with butter and bake 20-25 minutes or until top is golden.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(741,"Low-Fat Cauliflower with Bacon","0","PT0S","PT0S","I am not a cauliflower lover but we did have this again over the holidays and well, I am back to loving it.","Cauliflower",5.0,5.0,75.6,5.2,1.7,7.7,121.2,5.2,2.3,2.2,3.1,"4.0","Low-Fat Cauliflower with Bacon Recipe Instructions:  1: Place cauliflower in a steamer basket over boiling water. 2: Cover pan and steam about 8 minutes or until almost tender. 3: Remove steamer basket and set aside. Heat a heavy nonstick skillet over medium high heat. Cook bacon 4-5 minutes or until browned. 4: Add scallions, cauliflower and salt and pepper to taste. Cook 2 minutes, stirring frequently until hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(742,"Low-Fat Fudge Bars","PT25M","PT15M","PT40M","Make and share this Low-Fat Fudge Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",5.0,3.0,74.3,0.4,0.2,0.0,13.1,17.7,1.1,12.8,1.7,"16.0","Low-Fat Fudge Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine the flour, oat bran, cocoa, sugar and salt, if desired, and stir to mix well. 2: Add the sweet potato, egg whites, and vanilla extract, and stir to mix well. 3: Fold in nuts if desired. 4: Coat an 8-inch square pan with non-stick cooking spray. 5: Spread the mixture evenly in the pan and bake at 325° for about 25 minutes or until the edges are firm and the center is almost set. 6: Cool to room temperature, cut into squares and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(743,"Indian Spiced Chicken","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Indian Spiced Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,12.0,302.5,8.7,1.7,151.0,275.9,3.0,0.8,0.5,50.6,"4.0","Indian Spiced Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: In small bowl, stir together oil and garlic. Stir in water, paprika, ginger, coriander, cumin, nutmeg, turmeric and cayenne pepper. 2: Spoon 1 tbsp (15 mL) into another small bowl; stir in lemon juice and set aside. Arrange chicken in single layer in shallow glass dish; brush with remaining spice mixture. Cover and refrigerate chicken for 1 hour. 3: (Chicken can be prepared to this point and refrigerated for up to 24 hours; let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.) Place chicken, flesh side down, on greased grill over medium-high heat; close lid and cook for 5 minutes. 4: Turn and brush flesh with reserved lemon mixture. Close lid and cook, turning often, for about 12 minutes longer or until chicken is no longer pink inside and juices run clear when chicken is pierced. 5: Serve with lemon wedges.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(745,"Low-Fat Potatoes Romanoff","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Low-Fat Potatoes Romanoff recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,4.0,224.7,8.6,5.3,25.8,575.2,27.7,3.4,1.5,10.0,"6.0","Low-Fat Potatoes Romanoff Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil potatoes until tender. 2: Mash with butter, sour cream, onions, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper. 3: Turn mixture into buttered 1-1/2 quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika. 4: Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(752,"Lasagna Pinwheels","PT40M","PT20M","PT1H","Make and share this Lasagna Pinwheels recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",0.0,0.0,302.3,12.8,7.0,57.8,332.3,21.0,0.8,1.0,24.6,"8.0","Lasagna Pinwheels Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375. 2: Coat rectangular 2-quart baking dish with no-stick cooking  spray. 3: Brown turkey in non-stick skillet. While turkey is cooking combine  ricotta, mozzarella, Parmesan , eggs and parsley in medium mixing bowl; stir to  blend. 4: Spread a scant 1/4 cup cheese mixture on each lasagna noodle. Roll up  starting with a short end. 5: Place seam side down in baking dish. 6: Add pasta sauce  to turkey in skillet and heat. Pour sauce over rolls in baking dish. 7: Cover with  foil. 8: Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through. 9: Let stand 5 minutes before  serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(753,"Baked Red Onions","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Baked Red Onions recipe from Food.com.","Onions",4.0,1.0,160.2,9.1,1.3,0.0,5.3,17.7,1.5,11.5,1.1,"12.0","Baked Red Onions Recipe Instructions:  1: In large saucepan, cover onions and lemon rind with water; bring to 2: boil and boil for 5 minutes. 3: Drain; refresh under cold running water and drain again. 4: Discard rind. 5: Peel onions and arrange in 13x9 inch casserole; pour olive oil over. 6: Bake, uncovered, in 375= F oven, basting occasionally for 40 minutes. 7: Add raisins, port, vinegar, sugar, and pepper to taste.  Bake for 30 minutes or until juices are syrupy.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(757,"Lemon Cake","PT40M","PT15M","PT55M","Make and share this Lemon Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,14.0,506.8,22.4,2.6,75.4,409.5,72.3,0.6,53.3,5.5,"0.0","Lemon Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix together; beat 4 minutes.  Put into greased tube pan. 2: Bake in 350°F oven 35-40 minutes. 3: Cool, then   pierce the top of the cooled cake with a fork. 4: Make icing  from confectioners'' sugar and lemon juice, drizzle over cake.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(763,"Lemonade Cake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lemonade Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,4.0,5926.7,245.7,36.5,754.4,4123.3,901.6,7.0,692.8,55.5,"1.0","Lemonade Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 300. 2: Grease and flour a Bundt pan. 3: Dissolve Jello in hot water  and set aside - DO NOT JELL. 4: In a large bowl, mix next 3 ingredients. 5: Add Jello  and beat together 3 minutes. 6: Turn into Bundt pan. 7: Bake 1 hour or until inserted  knife comes out clean. 8: Meanwhile: While cake is baking mix next 2 ingredients and let sit. While cake is still warn, loosen it from edges of pan but leave cake in pan. 9: Pour lemonade mixture over cake allowing it to run down the sides. 10: Save some lemonade mixture. When you turn your cake out onto your, rack put some wax paper under rack and pour saved lemonade mixture over top of cake. This cake is simply divine. Enjoy...");
