INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1037,"Bread Machine Sage-Wheat Bread","PT3H","PT5M","PT3H5M","Make and share this Bread Machine Sage-Wheat Bread recipe from Food.com.","Yeast Breads",4.0,5.0,76.0,1.3,0.5,2.1,81.8,14.1,1.6,0.6,2.7,"16.0","Bread Machine Sage-Wheat Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Add all of the ingredients to a bread machine according to the manufacturer''s  directions. 2: Bake the bread using the wheat, regular, or white setting.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1038,"Beef Crumble","PT50M","PT25M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Beef Crumble recipe from Food.com.","Meat",2.0,2.0,403.2,40.4,16.8,56.1,188.9,4.0,0.9,1.7,5.8,"4.0","Beef Crumble Recipe Instructions:  1: TOPPING 3/4 cup wholemeal flour 1/3 cup rolled oats 1 oz butter 1/3 cup grated cheese 1/2 tsp dried mixed herbs Fry mince over a medium heat in its own fat, turning, until evenly browned. 2: Add the onion, celery, mushrooms and carrot and fry for 5 minutes. 3: Stir in the flour and cook a further minute.  Add the stock, sauce and salt and pepper to taste.  Bring to the boil, stirring. 4: Cover and simmer 30 - 40 minutes. 5: To make Topping:- Place the flour and rolled oats in a bowl. 6: Rub in the butter until mixture resembles coarse breadcrumbs. 7: Stir in the cheese, herbs and salt and pepper to taste.  Transfer the meat to a greased casserole and spoon topping over. 8: Bake at 375 F for 20 - 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1041,"Salsa","PT2H","PT30M","PT2H30M","Hello, My daughter lives in the UK    Cornwall  Anyway we love spicy foods and this is a wonderful salsa recipe.  Make it as  hot or as mild as you want    the flavor will still be wonderful.    It can be  doubled or tripled or whatever.  This recipe will feed 4 adults a snack.  Let  me know what you think.","Sauces",5.0,131.0,35.3,1.4,0.2,0.0,442.0,5.7,1.5,3.0,1.1,"4.0","Salsa Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all the ingredients and chill for 2 hours before serving with chips. 2: The Cilantro is very important to this dish.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1042,"Salty Milk Biscuits","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Salty Milk Biscuits recipe from Food.com.","Breads",4.5,2.0,1025.8,47.7,29.4,121.9,485.1,129.8,4.6,0.5,18.1,"0.0","Salty Milk Biscuits Recipe Instructions:  1: Sieve flour and salt and rub in the butter. 2: Gradually mix with milk to make a stiff dough. 3: Roll out VERY thinly, brush lightly with beaten egg  or milk and sprinkle with salt. 4: Bake 400 F for 10 - 15 minutes. 5: Cheers, Doreen Randal,Wanganui,New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1044,"Savoury Bread Dish","PT1H15M","PT15M","PT1H30M","Make and share this Savoury Bread Dish recipe from Food.com.","Manicotti",0.0,0.0,233.0,9.4,4.2,175.7,367.7,24.9,0.9,1.9,11.6,"4.0","Savoury Bread Dish Recipe Instructions:  1: Take slices of sandwich bread and put thick sliced cheese on three of them and spread with mustard. 2: Top with the other slices and cut into quarters. 3: Stand these in a greased ovenproof dish. 4: Sprinkle with a tsp of garlic salt.  Beat together eggs and milk, pour over the bread making sure all the bread is dampened. 5: Cover and leave to stand at least 30 minutes, spooning milk over the exposed bread every now and then. 6: Cook uncovered at 190 C 30 - 45 minutes, depending on the depth of the dish, until crisp and golden brown and centre is set. Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 7: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1048,"Scottish Scones","PT30M","PT25M","PT55M","Make and share this Scottish Scones recipe from Food.com.","Scones",4.5,3.0,271.7,14.2,8.7,36.5,360.4,32.5,1.5,8.4,4.1,"8.0","Scottish Scones Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 375 degrees. 2: Lightly grease cookie sheet. In med. 3: bowl, combine  flour, oats, brown sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; mix well. 4: With  pastry blender or fork, cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. 5: Add milk all at  once; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened. 6: On floured surface, gently  knead dough 5 or 6 times. 7: Place on greased cookie sheet; press into a 6\ 8:  thick. 9: Brush top with melted butter. 10: In small bowl, combine sugar and  cinnamon; mix well. 11: Sprinkle over top. 12: Cut into 8 wedges; separate slightly. 13: Bake for 20-30 minute. 14: or until golden brown. 15: Serve warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1049,"Beef Enchiladas","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Beef Enchiladas recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.5,17.0,489.9,25.8,10.8,66.9,742.4,40.0,3.4,3.0,24.2,"0.0","Beef Enchiladas Recipe Instructions:  1: To prepare enchilada sauce, in medium saucepan, combine sauce ingredients. 2: Simmer 30 minutes. 3: (Cast iron skillets work well for following)  To prepare beef filling, in large skillet, cook ground beef and onion  (you may sprinkle with additional chili powder) and drain. 4: Add 3/4 cup  enchilada sauce to meat and cook low 10 minutes or until sauce absorbed. 5: To assemble enchiladas, in ungreased skillet, heat each tortilla low  heat, ~15 seconds per side, dip in sauce, fill with ~2 Tbsp beef   filling and roll up. 6: Place seam side down in 12 x 8 inch baking dish. 7: Cover enchiladas *evenly* with remaining sauce. Sprinkle with cheeses and   bake uncovered at 350 for 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1063,"Slow Cooker BBQ Pinto Beans","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Slow Cooker BBQ Pinto Beans recipe from Food.com.","Beans",4.0,8.0,350.6,1.5,0.2,0.0,567.9,68.1,13.2,16.0,17.4,"6.0","Slow Cooker BBQ Pinto Beans Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine first 4 ingredients in an electric slow cooker on low heat. Cover and cook about 7 hours or until beans are tender. 2: Drain cooking liquid. 3: Stir in remaining ingredients. 4: Set on high heat and cook uncovered 10-15 minutes, or until heated through.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1066,"Snow Flurry Brownies","PT30M","PT20M","PT50M","Make and share this Snow Flurry Brownies recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",4.5,3.0,192.4,11.7,5.6,39.6,149.3,21.9,1.4,15.9,2.5,"0.0","Snow Flurry Brownies Recipe Instructions:  1: In a bowl, whisk together sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla. 2: Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; add to sugar mixture and mix well. 3: Stir in vanilla chips and nuts. 4: Spread into a greased 8-in. square baking pan. 5: Bake at 35O°F for 25-30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out with moist crumbs (do not overbake). Cool on a wire rack. 6: Cut into diamond shapes if desired or garnish with melted white chocolate.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1069,"Soft Zucchini Spice Cookies","PT8M","PT15M","PT23M","Make and share this Soft Zucchini Spice Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",4.5,11.0,66.7,2.9,1.4,9.1,60.2,9.6,0.3,5.5,0.9,"0.0","Soft Zucchini Spice Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and brown sugar; add the egg and mix well. 2: Combine the dry ingredients; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Stir in zucchini, nuts, raisins, and orange peel. 3: Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheets. 4: Bake at 350°F for 12-14 minutes or until edges are lightly browned and cookies are set. 5: Makes about 4 dozen.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1070,"Solo Chicken Breast and Rainbow Rice","PT20M","PT1H","PT1H20M","Make and share this Solo Chicken Breast and Rainbow Rice recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",0.0,0.0,881.5,57.7,8.2,75.5,151.6,60.1,3.9,4.9,30.5,"1.0","Solo Chicken Breast and Rainbow Rice Recipe Instructions:  1: In the afternoon, or at least one hour before making the dish, combine the olive oil,juice. Place chicken breast  in a plastic bag and add olive oil  juice  mixture then refrigerate for at least an hour. 2: Make sure that the marinade  coats the meat.  The rest of this process should only take 20 minutes if the  steps are followed in order. 3: Remove the chicken and place on a hot grill (  total cooking time will be  20 minutes.) and immediately proceed to the next  step. 4: Add the water to the rice and place in a covered pan over a stove burner  with a very low flame.( total heating time will be 15 minutes).   After the chicken and the rice have cooked for 10 minutes; turn the chicken  breast over. 5: Chop the onion and peppers and set aside.  After the chicken and  rice have cooked for another 5 minutes, turn off the flame under the rice, but  do NOT remove the cover. 6: Heat up a small amount of butter and/or olive oil in a  frying pan; heat the onion and bell peppers  until soft.  After the chicken has  cooked for an additional 5 minutes ( 20 minutes total) remove from the heat.  Remove the cover on the rice and stir in the heated onion and bell pepper. 7: Pour  the rice mixture on a plate and place the chicken breast on top. 8: Salt ( I like  lemon salt) and pepper to taste.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1071,"Some ''Berry'' Good Fruit Dip Ideas!","0","PT0S","PT0S","FRUIT PLATTER A BERRY GOOD IDEA For many, the arrival of warm weather means a long-awaited supply of fresh - and varied - fruit. And whether you decide to pick your own or buy from a favorite roadside vendor, serving fruit with any meal is, well, a berry good idea. Not only do fruits make a colorful and flavorful accompaniment to breakfast, lunch or dinner, they make a refreshing and healthy snack in the middle of a hot day or under a welcoming shady tree on an outing with family or friends.  HELPFUL HINTS Storing berries: After selecting healthy-looking berries - you''ll want to avoid bruised or moldy fruit of any kind - refrigerate them in a single layer, loosely covered. To freeze, arrange washed berries in a single layer on a baking sheet and place in freezer until solid. Transfer them to a plastic freezer bag or container, leaving half-an-inch at the top. Return to freezer.  Preparing a platter: You''ll want at least three types of fruit for an attractive platter.","Fruit",0.0,0.0,1040.8,79.3,49.9,249.5,672.6,68.9,0.2,60.8,18.0,"0.0","Some ''Berry'' Good Fruit Dip Ideas! Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat all ingredients together, adding more orange juice if needed to thin sauce. Makes 2 cups. 2: Fruit Dip: 1 cup plain yogurt 3 tbsp. icing sugar 1/2 tsp. grated lemon peel Stir ingredients together. Makes 1 cup. 3: Caramel Fruit Dip: 1 cup sour cream 1 tbsp. brown sugar 1 tbsp. Kahlua Combine all ingredients. Add more brown sugar if you want to omit Kahlua. Makes  1 cup. 4: Chocolate-dipped Fruit: 2/3 cup semisweet chocolate chips 1 tbsp. parowax (cut into bits to measure) Heat chocolate chips and wax in top of double boiler or pan over hot water. Stir until smooth and remove from heat. Return mixture to heat as chocolate cools.  Dip fruit (strawberries, Mandarin orange slices, pineapple chunks, clusters of  seedless grapes) into mixture, covering about 2/3 of each piece. Place on  undipped end to cool or lay on a piece of waxed paper. Chill until about one  hour before ready to serve, when fruit should be placed at room temperature. HINT: The drier the fruit, the better the results.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1080,"Spaetzle","PT10M","PT20M","PT30M","Make and share this Spaetzle recipe from Food.com.","German",5.0,17.0,397.5,10.7,4.1,103.3,1557.5,61.3,2.1,0.3,12.2,"4.0","Spaetzle Recipe Instructions:  1: Using an electric mixer, blend the eggs, lard or oil, water and milk. 2: Stir the  flour together with 1/2 tsp of the salt and the baking powder in a dry bowl. 3: Blend this mixture into the liquid. 4: Mix well and set aside for a moment. Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil and add 2 tsp of salt. Using a spaetzle maker  or spaetzle press squeeze the dough into the boiling water. 5: Use about 1/3 of the dough for each batch. 6: When the dumplings float to the surface, they are done.  Remove them with a slotted spoon and place in a colander. 7: They can be served  with way with paprika gravy or pan fried with a little butter, just until they  are a bit golden, and topped with parsley. 8: Note: These dumplings can also be made by using  piping bag or dropping very  small amounts from a spoon. 9: The latter takes much longer.");
