INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1098,"Spinach Torte","PT25M","PT20M","PT45M","I adopted this from the recipezaar account in early 2005.  Have not had a chance to make it yet but will be making it soon and will be ''tweeking'' the ingredients and directions if necessary.","< 60 Mins",0.0,0.0,570.6,30.5,11.1,136.2,638.6,60.6,4.9,2.3,14.6,"4.0","Spinach Torte Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven 400°F. 2: Heat oil in skillet large enough to hold spinach. 3: Saute  garlic and onion in skillet over medium heat until golden. 4: Add spinach to pan  and stir over medium heat until spinach is reduced and cooked. 5: Drain in  colander. 6: Meanwhile, beat eggs until frothy. 7: Add to spinach mixture. crush dill  between fingers and add to spinach and egg mixture. Cool. 8: In a small  saucepan,melt butter. 9: Prepare Phyllo as per directions on box (defrost 8 hours at room temperature before use). Separate three sheets of Phyllo dough and place on counter.Using a pastry brush,sparingly coat top layer with butter. 10: Sprinkle  with  a tablespoon of breadcrumbs.Separate three more sheets of Phyllo on top of the first layer. 11: Again, lightly brush with melted butter.Sprinkle with bread  crumbs.Continue six times, or until you have counted a total of 18 layers of  Phyllo. 12: Evenly spread out spinach mixture onto the top. 13: Starting with the long end, roll up as a jelly roll, keeping it as tight as you can. 14: Place on buttered  baking sheet seam side down. 15: Bake immediately in oven  25 minutes. 16: To serve,  slice in one inch interval diagonally.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1099,"Spoon Bread Chili Pie","PT35M","PT15M","PT50M","Make and share this Spoon Bread Chili Pie recipe from Food.com.","Savory Pies",4.5,9.0,529.3,35.7,16.0,90.5,1239.7,39.3,7.9,6.4,16.1,"6.0","Spoon Bread Chili Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic over medium heat for 8 minutes. 2: Add chili pepper, tomatoes, corn and beans and cook for five minutes. 3: Turn into casserole dish and  set aside. Scald milk with butter and salt.  Gradually add corn mean while   stirring. 4: Cook until thickened - 4 minutes. 5: Remove from heat and stir in  cheese and egg. 6: Spread topping over casserole.  Bake at 375°F for 35  minutes or until topping has set.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1104,"Squash & Golden Onion Risotto","PT50M","PT40M","PT1H30M","Make and share this Squash & Golden Onion Risotto recipe from Food.com.","Short Grain Rice",3.0,1.0,336.9,8.6,5.2,20.6,585.4,52.4,4.1,6.9,6.4,"6.0","Squash & Golden Onion Risotto Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat broth in one saucepan. 2: Melt 1/4 cup butter in a large saucepan. 3: When butter foams, add onion and garlic.  Saute over med. heat until pale yellow. 4: Add squash and sage; cook until starting to become tender. 5: Add wines and reduce. 6: Add balsamic vinegar and lower heat. 7: And rice, mix well. 8: When rice is coated, stir in 1-2 ladles of broth, cook until absorbed. 9: Continue this routine for 15-20 min. 10: Season with pepper.  Serve with Parmesan.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1107,"Steak & Tomato-Basil Pasta","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Steak & Tomato-Basil Pasta recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,1.0,757.8,35.0,13.2,143.1,525.0,71.0,11.0,6.6,41.0,"6.0","Steak & Tomato-Basil Pasta Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook pasta according to package directions; keep warm. 2: Meanwhile, in a large saucepan or Dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion and garlic; cook and stir until tender. 3: Add remaining sauce ingredients. 4: Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low. 5: Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. 6: Place beef steaks on grid over medium, ash-covered coals. 7: Grill steaks, uncovered, 13 to 15 minutes (15 to 18 minutes for top loin steaks) for medium rare to medium doneness, turning once. Season with salt and pepper. 8: Trim fat from steaks. 9: (Cut top loin steaks crosswise in half.) Combine tomato sauce, basil, cheese and pasta; toss to coat. Serve steaks with pasta.");
