INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1113,"Strawberry Marbled Cheesecake","PT50M","PT45M","PT1H35M","Make and share this Strawberry Marbled Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",4.0,2.0,434.1,29.7,16.6,134.5,332.1,35.3,0.8,29.1,8.5,"12.0","Strawberry Marbled Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: In blender container, combine strawberries and cornstarch; blend until smooth. 2: In heavy saucepan, over med. 3: heat, cook and stir until thickened. 4: Add food  coloring, if desired. 5: Reserve 1/3 cup sauce; cool. 6: Chill remaining sauce.  Preheat oven to 300 degrees. 7: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter; press onto bottom of 9\ 8: ,  9: ,  10: ,  11: ,  12: Spoon half  the reserved strawberry sauce in small amounts over batter. 13: Repeat, ending with  sauce. With a knife, cut through batter to marble.  Bake 50 minute,oven temperature 350 degrees. 14: or until center is set. Cool. 15: Chill. 16: Remove side of pan. 17: Serve with chilled strawberry sauce. Refrigerate leftovers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1114,"Strawberry ''n Oat Bars","PT25M","PT0S","PT25M","Make and share this Strawberry ''n Oat Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",5.0,8.0,261.8,12.2,2.5,0.0,204.0,36.2,1.8,20.0,3.2,"0.0","Strawberry ''n Oat Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 400°F. 2: Beat 3/4 cup margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. 3: Add combined flour, soda and salt; mix well. 4: Stir in oats and nuts. 5: Reserve  1/2 cup crumb mixture.  Press remaining crumb  mixture onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. 6: Spread the strawberry preserves over the first layer. 7: Sprinkle  with reserved crumb mixture.  Bake 20-25 minutes. Cool. 8: Melt Chips and 4 teaspoons margarine over low heat (or microwave),  stirring until smooth. 9: Drizzle over crumb mixture. Refrigerate 1 hour; cut into bars.");
