INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1259,"Peppered Fish in Herbed Butter","PT6M","PT1M","PT7M","Make and share this Peppered Fish in Herbed Butter recipe from Food.com.","Very Low Carbs",4.0,2.0,191.0,13.3,7.9,93.7,173.3,0.4,0.1,0.1,17.0,"4.0","Peppered Fish in Herbed Butter Recipe Instructions:  1: Sprinkle fish with pepper. 2: Combine butter, juice and herbs in a large shallow dish, cook on HIGH for 1 minutes. 3: Add the fish in a single layer, cover and cook on HIGH for 5 minutes or until fish is tender.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1261,"Beef Jerky","PT24H","PT5M","PT24H5M","Make and share this Beef Jerky recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",4.0,1.0,13.4,0.0,0.0,0.0,1.5,3.0,0.2,0.1,0.6,"0.0","Beef Jerky Recipe Instructions:  1: Take a raw London broil, slice thin across the grain. 2: Place in a large glass bowl, and cover with soy sauce (I use the ''lite'' kind) ''until the beef is swimming in it! 3: Mince a few cloves of garlic, add, stir well. 4: Cover and refrigerate for about a day. 5: To dry, I usually used a food dehydrator. You can also dry them in a gas oven set to 170F. by placing parchment paper directly on the oven racks, then the beef strips. Either way, check on them every couple of hours, turning as they begin to dry. 6: Store in a sealed container when completely dry.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1266,"Coconut Macaroon Cheesecake","PT1H20M","PT30M","PT7H40M","Make and share this Coconut Macaroon Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",4.5,2.0,338.7,28.7,16.8,97.8,193.8,17.0,2.0,14.4,5.6,"14.0","Coconut Macaroon Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: In a small bowl combine 1 cup toasted coconut, ground pecans and butter. 2: Press  onto bottom of 9\ 3: ,  4: ,  5: ,  6: ,  7: ,  8: Fold in 2/3 cup toasted coconut. Carefully spread  atop partially baked cheesecake. Return to oven and bake 20 min. 9: more. Cool on  wire rack for 15 min. 10: Loosen side of cheesecake from pan. 11: Cool 30 min. 12: more;  remove side of pan. 13: Cool completely. 14: Cover and chill at least 4 hours before  serving. 15: To serve, garnish with strawberries and/or additional toasted coconut.                    - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1269,"Chicken Fajitas","PT10M","PT8H","PT8H10M","Make and share this Chicken Fajitas recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,20.0,273.4,16.6,2.5,72.6,280.2,5.5,1.0,2.0,24.8,"8.0","Chicken Fajitas Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients, except tortillas, in a large bowl, mix well and  refrigerate overnight. 2: Drain mixture. 3: In a large skillet, over medium high heat, add 2 tablespoons olive oil and saute chicken mixture until chicken is no longer pink. 4: Serve in tortillas.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1276,"Apple and Ginger Dessert Pizza","PT45M","PT0S","PT45M","Make and share this Apple and Ginger Dessert Pizza recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,317.5,10.1,5.9,54.0,93.1,50.0,3.3,20.0,5.6,"0.0","Apple and Ginger Dessert Pizza Recipe Instructions:  1: To make the base:- Combine yeast, sugar and water in a small bowl. 2: Stand bowl  covered with plastic wrap, in a small place for 10 minutes until the mixture is  foamy. 3: Sift flour into a large bowl and make a well in centre. Add yeast  mixture, butter and egg; mix with a knife to a soft dough. 4: Turn out onto a  lightly floured surface; knead for 5 minutes until smooth and elastic. 5: Place  in a oiled bowl, cover with plastic wrap; stand in a warm place for 1 hour or  until doubled in size. To Make Topping:- Peel, core the apples and cut into slices. 6: Combine sultanas  and brandy in a small bowl and set aside.  Melt butter in pan, add ginger; stir  to combine.  Add water and maple syrup; cook over a low heat for 4 minutes until thickened slightly. 7: Cool. 8: Preheat oven to 210°C. 9: Brush a 30cm round pizza tray with melted butter. 10: Knead dough again for 1 minute, roll out to a 26cm round. 11: Place onto prepared tray tuck edges under to form a rim. 12: Drain sultanas,  sprinkle over base.  Arrange apple slice over the base, drizzle with syrup. 13: Brush rim of base with a little melted butter. 14: Bake for 25 minutes until crust  is golden brown. 15: Serve warm with whipped cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1278,"Apple Brown Betty","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apple Brown Betty recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,616.9,25.6,15.1,61.0,301.8,94.8,7.0,57.9,6.6,"8.0","Apple Brown Betty Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. 2: Cut apples into 1/4 inch slices and place in a  bowl. 3: Combine with granulated sugar and flour. 4: Brush a 9 X 13 inch pan with some butter and sprinkle bottom with 1 cup of breadcrumbs. 5: Sprinkle 1/2 cup  granulated sugar over breadcrumbs and top with half the apples. 6: Repeat layers  with remaining ingredients.Drizzle top with remaining butter and sprinkle evenly with superfine sugar. 7: Bake on middle rack in oven until bubbling and browned,  about 45 minutes. 8: Cool on a rack. 9: Cut into squares and serve warm or at room  temperature.                    - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1280,"Bisquick Apple Cinnamon Muffins","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Bisquick Apple Cinnamon Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",4.5,13.0,150.2,6.2,1.2,16.6,228.0,21.2,0.9,9.6,2.7,"12.0","Bisquick Apple Cinnamon Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400. 2: Spray with nonstick cooking spray bottom only of 12 medium size muffin cups. 3: Beat egg slightly, stir in remaining ingredients just till  moistened. 4: Divide batter evenly among cups. 5: Bake until golden brown, 15 to 17  minutes.");
