INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1372,"Kalbi","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Kalbi recipe from Food.com.","Meat",5.0,9.0,7798.2,689.3,290.5,1378.9,11675.9,105.4,3.2,93.1,283.9,"1.0","Kalbi Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all sauce ingredients. 2: Dip each piece of meat in the sauce and layer  in a flat dish or pan. 3: Pour more marinade on top. 4: Marinate 4 hours before  grilling over coals or broiling.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1374,"Malassadas","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Malassadas recipe from Food.com.","Breads",0.0,0.0,440.6,38.9,6.5,29.1,78.1,21.8,0.4,10.5,2.5,"24.0","Malassadas Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat milk to lukewarm. 2: Moisten yeast in lukewarm water. 3: Add the yeast, salt,  sugar and melted butter to the milk. Stir in part of the flour, beating well with a wooden spoon to prevent lumps. 4: Add beaten eggs and remaining flour to form a soft dough. 5: Cover the dough and set it in a warm place until it doubles in bulk. 6: Heat oil to 350-degrees. 7: Drop dough by the tablespoon into the hot oil and fry until evenly browned. 8: Drain on absorbent paper and roll in sugar.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1377,"Potato Pancakes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Potato Pancakes recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",0.0,0.0,427.8,3.8,1.2,141.0,851.4,86.2,10.8,4.1,14.1,"0.0","Potato Pancakes Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel potatoes. 2: Grate potatoes into a bowl of cold water to prevent  darkening. 3: Drain thoroughly but not dry. 4: Add beaten eggs and salt. Stir. 5: Add enough pancake mix to blend well and drop onto greased griddle.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1378,"Oatmeal Pancakes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Oatmeal Pancakes recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",4.0,4.0,1053.3,22.5,7.2,442.6,4244.6,157.5,13.6,30.4,54.7,"1.0","Oatmeal Pancakes Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix oats with buttermilk. 2: Add eggs and dry ingredients. 3: Fry on lightly greased griddle until edges are cooked and center bubbles. 4: Turn and brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1379,"Butter Shortbreads","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Butter Shortbreads recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,36.0,2.7,1.7,7.1,19.1,2.7,0.1,0.8,0.3,"0.0","Butter Shortbreads Recipe Instructions:  1: Have butter at room temperature. Combine butter, sifted icing sugar,  sifted flour and lemon juice, with and electric beater; beat on low  speed to combine all the ingredients, increase speed to medium and  beat for 10 minutes. 2: Spoon the mixture into a large piping bag fitted  with a star shaped tube. Pipe small stars on lightly greased oven  trays. 3: Cook in a moderate oven for 10 - 15 minutes or until golden. 4: Stand on tray for a few minutes. 5: Cool on a wire rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1380,"Melting Moments","PT20M","PT0S","PT20M","Make and share this Melting Moments recipe from Food.com.","Candy",5.0,4.0,1335.7,94.7,58.6,243.8,995.8,115.8,5.7,28.3,10.8,"0.0","Melting Moments Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter and sugar and work in other ingredients. 2: Roll into small balls, place on greased trays, press down each biscuit with a fork (this mixture may be put through a biscuit forcer). 3: Bake about 20 minutes at 350°F. 4: Put together with your favourite icing. 5: Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 6: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1383,"Amish Biscuits","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Amish Biscuits recipe from Food.com.","Breads",4.5,5.0,62.3,4.7,1.6,22.7,124.5,4.1,0.1,0.1,1.1,"24.0","Amish Biscuits Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder. 2: In a separate bowl combine eggs, Amish Starter and oil. 3: Mix well. 4: Add starter to dry ingredients and mix until dough pulls away from sides  of bowl. 5: Transfer to a lightly floured surface and roll until 1/2 inch  thick. 6: Using a 3 inch circle cutter or floured glass cut out biscuits and  place on a lightly grease cookie sheet. Brush top of biscuits with melted  butter. 7: Cover and let rise 30 minutes. 8: Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 15 - 20 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1384,"Amish Cornbread II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Amish Cornbread II recipe from Food.com.","Sourdough Breads",0.0,0.0,298.0,14.2,3.2,79.0,475.7,36.0,2.5,1.8,7.7,"6.0","Amish Cornbread II Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 425 degrees and grease a 9 inch baking pan. 2: In a large mixer bowl combine starter, eggs, milk, sugar, flour and cornmeal. 3: Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. 4: Mix in oil, baking soda, salt and baking powder. 5: Transfer mixture to prepared baking pan and bake for 25 - 30 minutes. 6: Cool 10 minutes in pan, remove and cool completely on wire racks. 7: - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - NOTES : *NOTE: You can use 2 cups of any of the following, or mix each until you have 2 cups;       Grated Carrot       Chopped  Apple       Raisins       Walnuts");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1386,"Mammy''s Apple Crisp","PT45M","PT15M","PT1H","Make and share this Mammy''s Apple Crisp recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,24.0,318.9,12.1,5.3,20.3,16.3,53.2,2.2,42.0,2.3,"6.0","Mammy''s Apple Crisp Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375°F. 2: Arrange apple slices in an 8-inch square baking dish. 3: Combine flour, sugar and butter. 4: Mix with hands until small lumps form. 5: Add  nuts and sprinkle over apples. 6: Bake for 40-45 minutes or until apples are  tender and top is lightly browned. 7: Serve warm or room temperature.  Teri''s Recipe Page Pennsylvania Dutch Cookery.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1391,"Beef and Bean Burritos","PT15M","PT10M","PT25M","Make and share this Beef and Bean Burritos recipe from Food.com.","Beans",4.5,8.0,963.9,65.8,25.0,74.9,1185.0,72.2,8.0,3.8,20.1,"12.0","Beef and Bean Burritos Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute onion in oil until tender. 2: Add beef and garlic and  cook until beef is no longer pink. 3: Drain. 4: Add chili  powder, cumin & other seasonings. 5: Stir in tomato sauce and simmer 5  minutes. 6: Add refried beans and cook and stir until well blended. 7: Set aside  to cool completely. 8: Divide meat mixture into 12 portions. 9: Soften tortillas, according to  package instructions, and place a portion of meat on each. 10: Roll up, burrito  style. 11: Bake at 375 degrees for 15-20 minutes. 12: These may be frozen as follows. 13: Place seam side down on a cookie sheet  and freeze until frozen. 14: Wrap each individually and return to freezer.");
