INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1393,"Old Fashioned Butter Cookies","PT7M","PT0S","PT7M","Make and share this Old Fashioned Butter Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,4.0,3323.5,192.3,118.7,699.5,1265.7,359.3,8.4,119.7,40.5,"1.0","Old Fashioned Butter Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine butter, sugar, egg and vanilla in a large bowl with mixer on medium speed  until smooth and fluffy, 4 minutes. 2: Stir together flour and salt in a small bowl. 3: Add to butter mixture and beat on low speed until combined. 4: To shape cookies:  For cookie press, spoon dough into press. 5: Form desired shapes on ungreased  cookie sheets. 6: For slice and bake cookies, refrigerate dough, wrapped, 45 minute. 7: Divide dough in half. 8: Shape each half on wax paper into 6\ 9: Chill in refrigerator 1 hour or in freezer 30 minutes. 10: Slice cookies 1/8\ 11: ,  12: ,  13: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1395,"Marzia''s Beef or Chicken Curry","PT40M","PT20M","PT1H","Make and share this Marzia''s Beef or Chicken Curry recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Thigh & Leg",0.0,0.0,914.6,91.7,35.2,114.4,529.6,11.8,2.5,6.3,11.9,"4.0","Marzia''s Beef or Chicken Curry Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oil in a medium pot. Add onion and brown. 2: Add chicken and cook until  slightly browned. 3: Add remaining ingredients with 1/2 cup water if appears too  dry. 4: Cover and simmer until chicken is tender. 5: Serve with rice, chapati or  roti. 6: If beef is used, make sure to steam it in a pot with water for 1 hour or  in a pressure cooker for 20 minutes. 7: Use stock instead of water.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1399,"Chili Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chili Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",4.0,7.0,32.3,0.1,0.0,0.0,142.5,7.7,0.8,6.4,0.5,"0.0","Chili Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: This will take a large kettle and you should use one that is fairly heavy  so that the heat will be evenly conducted throughout with no hot spots. 2: Tomatoes have a terrible tendency to \ 3:  and burn and if that  happens, your entire batch can be spoiled. 4: In the kettle combine all of  the ingredients. 5: Bring to a boil over high heat and then immediately  reduce the heat to low and simmer until the sauce is thick enough for  your taste. This will take from 1 to 3 hours depending on how much juice  the tomatoes contained. 6: Stir regularly and often while the sauce is  cooking. 7: When the sauce is thick enough, pour the hot chili sauce into  prepared bottles and process in a boiling water bath canner. 8: Chili sauce  should be processed for 15 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1400,"Chocolate Caramel Oatmeal Bars","PT27M","PT20M","PT47M","Adopted recipe.This is pretty easy to make. They are very sweet and very sticky, but also very good.They go best with a tall, cold, glass of milk.Try to recuit help with unwrapping the caramels. They are a pain!!","Bar Cookie",5.0,1.0,183.7,9.0,4.0,7.4,126.7,25.5,0.5,11.6,2.3,"30.0","Chocolate Caramel Oatmeal Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut butter into cookie mix in bowl until crumbly. 2: Press into bottom of greased  9 x 13-inch pan, reserving 1 cup. 3: bake at 350 degrees for 12 minutes. 4: Sprinkle  with chocolate chips. 5: Melt caramels in evaporated milk saucepan, stirring  constantly. 6: Pour over chocolate chips. 7: Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture. bake  for 15 minutes longer. 8: Cool completely, apprx. 1 hour. 9: These are generous sized servings.If you cut the squares smaller, you can get more servings.");
