INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1428,"Viv''s Raisin Pie","PT25M","PT15M","PT40M","Make and share this Viv''s Raisin Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,3.0,2526.4,84.4,29.7,61.1,1505.2,449.7,19.3,289.2,21.4,"0.0","Viv''s Raisin Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil raisins, first amount water, and juice, for 5 minutes in a covered pot. Combine the following:  brown sugar, cornstarch,  cinnamon, orange rind, salt (dissolved in second amount of water).  Add to cooked raisins. 2: Bring to boil, stirring. 3: Remove from heat. Add vinegar and butter. 4: Pour into unbaked pie shell. 5: Top with other pastry. 6: Bake in  hot oven (425 F) for 25 min or until done.  From: Vivian Hillier, Martensville SK.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1438,"Twice Baked Potatoes III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Twice Baked Potatoes III recipe from Food.com.","Potato",0.0,0.0,191.0,6.2,3.9,16.6,389.9,30.6,2.8,1.4,4.2,"8.0","Twice Baked Potatoes III Recipe Instructions:  1: Bake potatoes until done. 2: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; scoop out   insides leaving a thin shell. 3: Mash potatoes with butter and salt.   Gradually add soup and beat until light and fluffy. 4: Spoon into   shells. 5: Bake in a 2 1/2 qt. shallow baking dish (9 x 13\");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1444,"Fiesta Yellow Squash","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Fiesta Yellow Squash recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,10.0,90.4,6.3,1.4,0.0,373.6,7.7,2.3,5.6,2.6,"4.0","Fiesta Yellow Squash Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter in skillet; add onion and green pepper. 2: Cook until tender. 3: Add squash and seasonings. 4: Mix well. 5: Cook, covered, over moderately low heat for 10 to 15 minutes  until crisp-tender.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1448,"Yellow Squash Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Yellow Squash Pie recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",3.5,6.0,167.0,3.0,0.9,124.1,45.5,26.8,0.5,25.9,4.2,"0.0","Yellow Squash Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. 2: Cook (steaming works well) enough yellow squash (crookneck, not butternut or such) to a nice soft consisitency, enough to equal 2 full cups cooked and drained, about 20 minutes. 3: In mixing bowl, combine squash, eggs and sugar; stir, but do not beat. 4: Add lemon extract. 5: Pour into a lightly buttered pie plate and bake approximately 40 minutes at 350 degrees or until pie is custard consistency.  Let cool and chill in refrigerator. 6: Serve cold.  Tastes like lemon custard. 7: Note:  recipe originally had 1 cup sugar, which has been reduced to 3/4 cup (or even less, depending on your preferred taste).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1468,"Italian Salad Dressing Mix","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Italian Salad Dressing Mix recipe from Food.com.","Salad Dressings",5.0,22.0,295.4,16.7,6.7,29.3,536.0,22.3,6.1,1.8,18.9,"1.0","Italian Salad Dressing Mix Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix ingredients and store in an air-tight container. 2: Will keep for  several months. 3: To use in an oil-and-vinegar dressing:  Mix 1 Tbsp mix with 1/4 cup vinegar, 2 Tbsp water, and 2/3 cup oil (or a  combination of oils to equal this amount) in a covered container. 4: Shake  vigorously. 5: To use with mayonnaise or yogurt as a salad dressing:  Mix 1 Tbsp mix with 1/4 cup mayonnaise and 1 Tbsp water in a covered  container. 6: Shake vigorously. 7: To use with mayonnaise, yogurt or sour cream as a dip:  Mix 1 Tbsp mix with 1/4 cup of spread. 8: (You can also add some Dijon  mustard and other herbs to your preference.) Serve with raw vegetables.");
