INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1515,"Marinated Green Peppers","PT10M","PT10M","PT20M","Make and share this Marinated Green Peppers recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,1.0,1123.7,109.3,15.3,0.0,2351.1,39.5,12.4,21.4,6.6,"0.0","Marinated Green Peppers Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash peppers, cut in half,  remove seeds and fibrous linings. 2: Dry the pepper halves and place them  under high heat in the broiler. 3: Broil until the skins are brown. 4: Remove from fire and peel off burnt surface.  Combine the vinegar, water, oil, bay leaf, salt, sugar, peppercorns  and garlic in a jar. 5: Shake well to blend. 6: Put peppers in a jar. 7: Pour marinade over them. 8: Store in the  refrigerator for at least 3 hours. 9: These are usually served as a pickle or relish.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1516,"Stuffed Green Bell Peppers II","PT22M","PT10M","PT32M","You can blanch the peppers ahead of time for 3 min in boiling water and then freeze them for later use.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,316.0,14.6,6.2,125.9,1008.9,21.3,3.4,2.9,26.2,"4.0","Stuffed Green Bell Peppers II Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut green pepper in half lengthwise; remove core and seeds. 2: Place peppers, hollow-side-up, in a shallow, heat-resistant,  non-metallic baking dish. 3: In a medium-sized bowl, crumble beef. 4: Add rice, salt, pepper, oregano, garlic powder, water, egg and 1/2  cup of tomato sauce. Mix until thoroughly combined. 5: Spoon mixture  into pepper halves. 6: Spoon remaining tomato sauce over peppers. 7: Heat, covered loosely with wax paper, 14 minutes in Micro- wave Oven  or until meat is cooked and peppers are as tender as desired. 8: Allow to stand 4 minutes, covered, before serving.");
