INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1529,"Biscotti Di Anise","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Biscotti Di Anise recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,2.0,962.5,46.4,17.3,219.6,636.7,120.1,6.4,52.3,21.6,"8.0","Biscotti Di Anise Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large bowl place the butter and sugar, and cream them together. 2: One at a  time add the eggs and beat them in. 3: Add the anise seeds and mix them in. 4: Add  the vanilla and anisette and beat them in. 5: In a mixing bowl place the flour and  baking powder, and mix them together. 6: Add the flour to butter mixture. Combine  the ingredients together well. 7: Add the almonds and stir them in well. 8: Form the  dough into a flat loaf. 9: Cover it and place it in the refrigerator overnight.  Preheat the oven to 375xF. 10: Place the loaf on a cookie sheet and bake it for 20  minutes, or until it is firm. 11: Remove the loaf and let it cool. 12: Slice it  diagonally into 3/4\ 13: ,  14: ,  15: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1537,"Boerenkool (Kale with Potatoes and Meat)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Boerenkool (Kale with Potatoes and Meat) recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.5,6.0,712.2,34.0,13.8,49.5,1385.4,84.5,12.7,2.4,24.9,"0.0","Boerenkool (Kale with Potatoes and Meat) Recipe Instructions:  1: Strip the kale, wash, and boil for about 1 hour. 2: Drain, and mince very  fine. Use a large pot; place potatoes in it and half cover with water. 3: Add  kale, fat, and salt. Simmer. 4: cover and cook for 30 minutes, or until  mixture is rather dry. 5: Serve with knackwurst on top of kale and potatoes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1539,"Dutch Mayonnaise","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Dutch Mayonnaise recipe from Food.com.","Dutch",3.0,1.0,1627.2,181.1,14.7,302.1,477.1,1.4,0.2,0.2,4.1,"0.0","Dutch Mayonnaise Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat the eggs in a mixing bowl. 2: Add the salt, pepper and mustard powder. 3: Using an electric mixer, beat the egg yolk mixture at a consistent speed. 4: Add a little oil and a little vinegar on an alternating basis. 5: If the oil  separates from the mixture, add a touch of warm water.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1540,"Erwtensoep (Green Pea, Pigs Feet &amp; Frankfurter Soup)","PT3H","PT8H","PT11H","Make and share this Erwtensoep (Green Pea, Pigs Feet &amp; Frankfurter Soup) recipe from Food.com.","Pork",4.0,1.0,609.0,49.6,18.3,81.7,1138.1,22.8,5.4,9.0,18.2,"6.0","Erwtensoep (Green Pea, Pigs Feet &amp; Frankfurter Soup) Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook peas in the water until tender. 2: When peas are tender press mixture  through a sieve or whirl in blender. 3: To this, add pig''s feet and simmer for  2 hours. 4: Add extra water when necessary. 5: Remove pig''s feet, bone and cube  meat, and add to soup. 6: Add bacon. 7: Clean and slice leaks and onions. 8: Melt  butter and saute leeks and onions until tender but not brown. 9: Add to soup  with parsley, celery, and celery root. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour. 10: Cut  frankfurters into crosswise slices and add to soup. 11: Remove from heat the  let stand overnight. Reheat the next day. 12: Add salt and pepper. 13: Stir well  since standing will make it thicker, and add a little more water if  necessary. 14: Remove bacon and cut into slices. 15: Serve bacon slices on  pumpernickel with the soup which has been reheated until piping hot. Makes  6 generous servings, for this is served as the whole meal. 16: formatted by Pamela Creeden (Busty the Happy Cooker)   - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1541,"Slavinken","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Slavinken recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,1.0,125.4,11.1,3.7,16.3,806.2,2.9,0.3,0.2,3.3,"4.0","Slavinken Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix the pork, salt, spices and bread crumbs well. 2: Form 4 cylinder-shaped  rolls. 3: For each roll, place 2 slices of bacon parallel on the counter. 4: Roll the bacon slices around the meat roll, then fold a third slice of  bacon lengthwise around the meat roll to cover the ends. 5: Fasten this slice  with 2 toothpicks, 1 at each end. 6: Place the bacon rolls on a cookie sheet.   Bake in a preheated oven at 350 degrees F. 7: for 1/2 hour. 8: Remove  toothpicks and serve.   - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  NOTES : Slavinken are traditionally served with boiled potatoes and  vegetables such as cauliflower, peas, spinach or endive and, of course, a  Dutch-style salad. 9: MasterCook Formatted by Carol H.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1543,"Dutch Buttercake","PT10M","PT35M","PT45M","Make and share this Dutch Buttercake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,2.0,312.7,19.1,11.8,65.4,58.5,32.7,0.7,13.5,3.2,"10.0","Dutch Buttercake Recipe Instructions:  1: Grease a 1 1/2 X 8\ 2: ,  3: ,  4: ,  5: ,  6: ,  7: ,  8: ,  9: Bake 350 F. for 30-35 minutes. 10: Allow to cool thoroughly before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1544,"Gehaktballen: Dutch meatballs","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Gehaktballen: Dutch meatballs recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,13.0,233.8,15.9,8.2,105.1,1068.0,8.5,0.8,1.3,13.9,"4.0","Gehaktballen: Dutch meatballs Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix the meat with the egg, bread, onion, salt and spices and form 4-5 meatballs. 2: Chill for about 30 minutes. 3: Make into 4-6 meatballs. 4: Heat the butter and brown the meatballs for about 15 minutes, turning them a couple of times. 5: Reduce the heat to simmer and cook the meatballs for another 15 minutes, turning a few times. 6: Remove the meatballs, add the water or beef stock and bring to a high heat.  Add a little ketjap manis or Maggi seasoning to the mixture and you will have a lovely gravy to serve with the meatballs. 7: NOTES : Some people coat the meatballs with breadcrumbs before frying. 8: We soak the bread in a bit of milk, and then press out the milk from the bread before adding to the ground beef. 9: We almost always use just the ground beef, and it is very good. 10: This is good served with homefries and lots of mayonnaise.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1550,"Cafe Diablo","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cafe Diablo recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",5.0,1.0,992.9,8.7,5.0,0.0,103.1,144.3,3.8,136.5,2.3,"1.0","Cafe Diablo Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat water, brown sugar, chocolate, cloves, and cinnamon to boiling in  3-quart saucepan; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes. 2: Stir  in coffee. Remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes. 3: Stir in  vanilla. 4: Strain coffee through 4 thicknesses of cheesecloth. 5: Keep hot in saucepan after straining. 6: Heat brandy  just until warm in small, long-handled saucepan. 7: Remove from heat;  ignite. Pour flaming brandy over coffee. Allow flame to burn out; stir. 8: Pour coffee into cups or mugs. 9: Top each with whipped cream and 1 Tbsp  liqueur. 10: Garnish with cinnamon stick, if desired.");
