INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1867,"Brownies in a Jar","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Brownies in a Jar recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",5.0,21.0,183.8,8.5,4.0,46.2,174.8,25.5,0.8,18.9,2.4,"0.0","Brownies in a Jar Recipe Instructions:  1: Pour sugar into a clean and dry one quart jar. 2: Press down firmly. 3: Add cocoa powder and press down firmly. 4: Pour in chopped pecans, making sure they are evenly layered. 5: Combine flour, baking powder and salt, pour into jar and seal. 6: Attach following directions to jar: Empty mix into large bowl. 7: Stir to blend thoroughly. 8: Add 3/4 cup butter or margarine and 4 beaten eggs. 9: Mix until completely blended. 10: Spread batter onto lightly greased 9x13 pan. 11: Bake at 350 F for 30 minutes or until done.  Cool in pan and cut into 2 inch squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1876,"Civil War Pound Cake","PT1H","PT10M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Civil War Pound Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,4.0,627.8,34.4,20.5,220.9,278.0,65.4,1.1,33.7,8.8,"12.0","Civil War Pound Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix the butter and sugar together well and beat in the eggs. 2: Sift the  flour and salt together; mix in to the butter mixture until thoroughly  blended. 3: Add the lemon peel, nutmeg, and brandy, mix well and pour into  two small buttered loaf pans or one large one. 4: Bake in a moderate oven (350F) for about 1 hour or until cake tests done.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1886,"Autumn Moon Cafe''s Apple Crisp","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Autumn Moon Cafe''s Apple Crisp recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,5.0,821.1,33.3,19.9,81.3,219.3,124.5,4.5,75.1,9.6,"6.0","Autumn Moon Cafe''s Apple Crisp Recipe Instructions:  1: Apple Mixture: 5 Granny Smith apples, peeled, cored & sliced 2 tablespoons sugar 2 teaspoons cinnamon 2 teaspoons lemon juice Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. 3: For the  topping: Mix together the flour, oats, sugar and spices in a large bowl. 4: Using  the large holes of a grater, grate the butter into the bowl. 5: Blend until the  mixture just begins to come together, being careful not to over mix. 6: Toss the  apples in a large bowl with the sugar, cinnamon, and lemon juice.  Spoon into  the baking pan and sprinkle the topping mixture over the fruit. Bake for 45 to  60 minutes, or until the apples are tender and the topping is browned and crisp. 7: Serve warm with a scoop of rich vanilla ice cream.");
