INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1983,"Feta Dressing","0","PT0S","PT0S","Feta Dressing  Feta is lower in fat than many other cheeses but still has plenty of flavor.    Yields: 1/2 cup","Very Low Carbs",4.5,2.0,827.5,79.8,25.5,107.2,1355.4,7.7,1.5,5.1,17.5,"0.0","Feta Dressing Recipe Instructions:  1: Process the feta, vinegar and oregano in a blender or food processor until  smooth. 2: Then with the machine running, slowly pour the oil through the feed tube and  process until smooth. 3: Taste and adjust the seasoning with the salt and  pepper. 4: Use immediately or cover and refrigerate.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1990,"Dirk''s Hot Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Dirk''s Hot Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",0.0,0.0,294.4,1.9,0.3,0.0,993.7,68.6,12.3,39.0,11.0,"0.0","Dirk''s Hot Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Blend the tomatoes, peppers, garlic, cilantro, and half the onion. 2: I like to  chop the other half by hand to make it chunkier. 3: Add salt and sugar to taste.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1992,"Pumpkin Fudge","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Pumpkin Fudge recipe from Food.com.","Candy",4.0,4.0,86.5,0.5,0.3,1.8,6.9,20.7,0.0,20.0,0.4,"20.0","Pumpkin Fudge Recipe Instructions:  1: In a 2 quart saucepan cook together sugar, pumpkin, spice, cornstarch and milk, stirring frequently, until mixture reaches 234 degrees on a candy thermometer or a small amount forms a soft ball in a little cold water. 2: Add vanilla and cool in a pan of ice water to 110 degrees. 3: Beat until fudge loses its gloss. 4: Pour into a lightly buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and cool. 5: Score and cut when almost cold. 6: Store in a wax paper lined metal can. 7: Will keep for several weeks. 8: If nuts are desired, mix in 1 cup of broken walnuts when the vanilla is added.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(1995,"Baked Barbecue Sauce Chicken","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Baked Barbecue Sauce Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",5.0,23.0,317.8,19.3,5.4,86.2,279.2,13.3,0.7,11.2,21.9,"6.0","Baked Barbecue Sauce Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Melt margarine, fry onion until softened (about 5 minutes), add  remaining ingredients (except chicken)to onion and boil for 3 minutes. 3: Place skinned chicken pieces in a casserole dish, and pour sauce over. 4: Bake uncovered for 1 hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2008,"Creamy Turkey Pie","PT30M","PT10M","PT40M","Make and share this Creamy Turkey Pie recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",0.0,0.0,349.6,15.8,5.9,123.0,458.7,25.1,2.1,4.5,25.8,"6.0","Creamy Turkey Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large skillet, cook ground turkey or turkey sausage, onion, pepper and salt, until meat is browned, stirring to break up meat. Drain. 2: Stir in cream cheese till combined.  Add mushrooms and set aside. 3: For the crust: Lightly grease a 9 inch pie plate with non-stick spray.  Unwrap crescent rolls and separate. Arrange them in pie plate, pressing onto the bottom and up the sides of the plate, extending the biscuits at 1/2 inch intervals, if desired. 4: Spoon turkey mixture into shell, spreading evenly. 5: In blender or food processor, combine egg, cottage cheese, and flour.  Cover and blend or process until smooth.  Spoon over turkey  mixture. 6: Bake, uncovered, for 25-30 minutes at 350 degrees Fahrenheit or until edges are  browned and filling is set. Let stand 5-10 minutes. 7: Cut into wedges and garnish with chopped tomatoes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2010,"Caribbean Chicken","PT55M","PT15M","PT1H10M","This recipe was originally named Caribbean Jerk Chicken.   However it''s not a true jerk chicken recipe.   With the help of Toni who was kind enough to help me we have come up with a more appropriate name.   Hope you enjoy it.","Chicken",4.0,5.0,178.0,5.0,1.0,72.5,572.1,2.2,0.3,0.3,29.6,"4.0","Caribbean Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Puree in blender lime juice, soy sauce, oil, hot pepper sauce, ginger, garlic,  thyme, pepper, allspice and salt. Combine marinade with chicken in plastic  food-storage bag. 2: Seal. 3: Marinate in refrigerator overnight. Place oven rack in  top position. 4: Heat oven to 500°F: 5: Drain chicken; discard marinade. Pat dry. 6: Arrange in roasting pan. 7: Roast on top rack in 500°F: oven 25 minutes for breasts,  30 minutes for thighs and drumsticks, or until instant-read thermometer  registers 170°F: without touching bone.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2019,"Baked Acorn Squash With Spicy Maple Syrup","PT45M","PT5M","PT50M","Make and share this Baked Acorn Squash With Spicy Maple Syrup recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,38.0,143.6,4.0,2.5,10.2,7.2,28.4,2.2,12.1,1.2,"6.0","Baked Acorn Squash With Spicy Maple Syrup Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 350 degrees. 2: Split the squash into thirds and remove the seeds. 3: Cut a slice off the bottom of each piece so that it sits evenly, skin-side down, in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. 4: In the hollow of each piece, place 1 teaspoon unsalted butter, 1 tablespoon maple syrup, cinnamon and nutmeg to taste. Bake in the heated oven until fork tender, about 45 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2020,"Sweet Potato Pie II","PT20M","PT30M","PT50M","Make and share this Sweet Potato Pie II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,2.0,258.0,13.5,6.6,61.1,185.3,31.3,0.5,20.0,3.6,"16.0","Sweet Potato Pie II Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream eggs and sugar. 2: Add sweet potato, vanilla flavoring and melted butter, mix then add milk.  Mix well. 3: Pour into unbaked pie shells. 4: Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees F. 5: Serves 8 for each pie.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2029,"Ramen Foo Yung","PT15M","PT0S","PT15M","Make and share this Ramen Foo Yung recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.5,18.0,615.6,34.3,16.8,402.5,1975.0,54.7,2.0,1.7,21.6,"1.0","Ramen Foo Yung Recipe Instructions:  1: Open ramen package and remove seasoning packet, it will be retained for later. 2: Boil noodles until soft, and drain. 3: In a separate fry pan melt butter or margarine on medium-high heat. once melted and bubbling, add seasoning packet and stir. 4: Then add the drained noodles and fry them for several minutes, stirring and turning them as you go. 5: The noodles will start to separate from the clump as they get done.  they will be slightly turning golden brown. 6: In a separate bowl, scramble the two eggs. 7: When noodles are slightly browned, add the eggs and stir thoroughly. 8: Reduce heat to medium-low immediately. 9: Flip and let the top cook. 10: Enjoy!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2031,"Red Capsicum Toasts","0","PT0S","PT0S","Went to a wee do on Saturday and everyone had to bring a finger food that was a  bit different.  I took these and they were delicious, the lime just finishes  them off.  We all decided the mixture would make a nice ''chutney'' for cold meats too.","Low Protein",5.0,1.0,436.6,14.6,2.0,0.0,35.1,59.4,7.9,47.9,3.9,"0.0","Red Capsicum Toasts Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut capsicums in quarters, remove membrane and seeds. 2: Grill capsicum, skin side  up, until skin blackens and blisters; peel skins from them. 3: Finely chop  capsicum. 4: Heat oil in pan, stir in peppers and sugar, cook over low heat,  covered, for about 45 minutes or until capsicums are soft, stirring  occasionally. 5: Stir in wine and vinegar, bring to the boil, simmer, uncovered  for about 15 minutes or until thick, remove from heat; strain, cool then stir in the basil. 6: Remove the crusts and cut  the bread into 2 1/2cm squares, place on an ungreased oven tray and bake in a moderate oven about 10 minutes or until  lightly browned, cool. 7: Spoon capsicum mixture onto toast squares, top with lime  wedges. 8: The capsicum and toasts can be made a day ahead of time.");
