INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2045,"Butter Tarts","PT25M","PT15M","PT40M","Make and share this Butter Tarts recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,2.0,88.1,3.5,2.0,34.1,39.4,13.9,0.0,10.6,0.8,"0.0","Butter Tarts Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 425°F. 2: Prepare muffin pans by rolling out pie dough and cutting 4-inch circles; fit dough circles into muffin cups; set aside in fridge until ready to fill. 3: In a large bowl, using a wooden spoon, mix together the soft butter, brown sugar, salt and corn syrup; stir well until sugar is dissolved and butter is creamed. 4: Add vinegar, eggs and vanilla and mix well. 5: Divide butter mixture into all tarts, not filling more than 2/3 full. 6: Bake at 425F for 5 minutes; reduce heat to 375F and continue baking for 15 to 20 minutes (filling will be lightly browned but still bubbling). 7: Let cooked butter tarts cool in pans for 10 minutes after removing from oven; then remove and place on racks until completely cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2048,"Butter Tarts II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Butter Tarts II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,583.7,28.4,15.6,149.1,304.8,83.4,2.9,76.8,4.8,"0.0","Butter Tarts II Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter and pour over sugar. 2: Beat well. 3: Beat egg yolks and mix with all ingredients. 4: Beat egg whites and fold in last. Line miniature muffin pans (or use regular ones) with rich pie crust. Put filling in and bake at 350 degrees for 35 min-  utes. 5: (I always halve this recipe and it makes a lot of Butter Tarts.) 6: BUTTER TARTS Pastry For Tarts: 5 cup flour 1 tsp. salt 1 Tbsp sugar 1 tsp. baking powder 2 cup shortening 1 egg 1 Tbsp vinegar 1 tsp. vanilla 7: Mix dry ingredients; add shortening and mix well. 8: Beat the egg in a measuring  cup; add enough lukewarm water to make 3/4 cup liquid. 9: Add vanilla and vinegar  to this liquid, then mi x into flour, shortening mixture. Treat as pie crust. Cut into circles and place in muffin tins. 10: Fill with: 2 eggs 2 Tbsp vinegar 1 tsp. vanilla 2 cup brown sugar (pack) 1 1/2 cup raisins 1/2 cup melted margarine 11: Beat eggs in bowl. 12: Add brown sugar, vinegar and vanilla. 13: Stir in melted butter  and raisins. 14: Pour in shells about 1/2 full. 15: Bake in 350 degrees oven for 15 to  18 minutes. 16: Makes about 24 to 30 tarts.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2049,"Velveeta Cheese Fudge","PT15M","PT10M","PT25M","Make and share this Velveeta Cheese Fudge recipe from Food.com.","Candy",4.5,19.0,3007.0,117.5,35.0,89.6,2752.0,477.1,4.0,453.3,23.3,"0.0","Velveeta Cheese Fudge Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt cheese and butter in saucepan over low heat, stirring almost constantly. 2: Sift sugar and cocoa together, stir into cheese butter mixture. 3: Stir in vanilla and nuts. 4: Spread in buttered pans, cool, cut into squares and store in tightly covered tin or container.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2050,"Pizzelle Waffle Cones","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pizzelle Waffle Cones recipe from Food.com.","European",3.0,2.0,116.0,5.4,3.2,40.1,87.8,14.9,0.2,7.6,2.0,"0.0","Pizzelle Waffle Cones Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat the eggs and  gradually  beat  in  the  sugar  until the mixture is creamy. 2: Stir in the melted butter and vanilla. 3: Combine the flour and baking powder, and  then  add  it to the mixture.  Blend it in well. 4: Drop about 4 tsp  of  the   batter  into  a  heated  pizelle iron, and cook both sides over medium-high   heat for about 1  minute  each,  or  until  golden  brown. 5: Remove  the  waffle   from  the  pizelle  iron  and  immediately shape it into a cone while it is  still  pliable.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2051,"Dot''s Creamy Fudge","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Dot''s Creamy Fudge recipe from Food.com.","Candy",0.0,0.0,2570.2,108.5,30.0,71.7,2390.2,388.5,5.7,363.8,23.4,"0.0","Dot''s Creamy Fudge Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt margarine, Velveeta cheese and vanilla in double boiler. 2: Remove from  heat. Add powdered sugar, cocoa and nuts. 3: Mix together well. 4: This sets up  fast. Press in buttered casserole dish. 5: Makes about 5 pounds good fudge.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2055,"Mrs. Field''s Lemon Macadamia Cookies","PT25M","PT15M","PT40M","Make and share this Mrs. Field''s Lemon Macadamia Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",5.0,2.0,135.1,8.1,3.0,16.1,65.9,14.9,0.7,8.9,1.6,"0.0","Mrs. Field''s Lemon Macadamia Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 300* f. 2: In a medium bowl combine flour, soda and  salt. Mix well and set aside. In a large bowl blend sugars well with  an  electric mixer set at  med speed. 3: Add the butter and cream cheese,  and mix to form a smooth paste. Add the egg and lemon extract, and  beat at medium speed until light and soft.  Scrape down sides of bowl  occasionally. 4: Add the flour mixture and nuts. 5: Blend  at low speed just  until combined. 6: Do not overmix. 7: Drop by rounded tablespoons  onto  ungreased cookie sheets, 2 inches apart. Bake 23-25 min. 8: Immediately   transfer to a cool flat surface.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2063,"Hush Puppies","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Make and share this Hush Puppies recipe from Food.com.","Healthy",2.0,1.0,44.2,0.5,0.1,9.1,169.4,8.6,0.5,0.5,1.4,"0.0","Hush Puppies Recipe Instructions:  1: Stir together to mix thoroughly flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and garlic  powder. 2: Add egg, buttermilk and onion; mix well. 3: Drop batter by rounded  teaspoonfuls into deep hot fat (375 degrees). 4: Cook, turning frequently, about 3  - 5 minutes, until golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2064,"Southern Spoon Bread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Southern Spoon Bread recipe from Food.com.","Breads",0.0,0.0,212.5,12.3,6.7,119.0,699.2,20.4,1.5,2.3,6.2,"6.0","Southern Spoon Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 350 F and grease or oil a shallow 2 quart pan  (I use my \ 2:  pyrex lasagna pan). Mix cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt in a medium saucepan. 3: Stir in the milk and cook over a medium heat until milk is absorbed, which only takes a few minutes. 4: Stir gently but constantly to prevent the mixture from catching on the bottom of the saucepan. 5: Remove from heat.  Stir in the butter, and slightly beaten egg yolks. 6: Beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form. 7: Fold into cornmeal mixture, and turn it all out into the prepared 2 quart pan. 8: Bake for 35 minutes, or until puffed and golden. 9: I hope this is what you are looking for! regards, Spooky");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2067,"Virginia Spoon Bread","PT40M","PT10M","PT50M","Make and share this Virginia Spoon Bread recipe from Food.com.","Breads",0.0,0.0,338.1,25.6,14.9,167.7,515.9,22.1,1.8,0.3,6.2,"6.0","Virginia Spoon Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375° and grease a 8x8x2-inch baking pan. 2: Stir cornmeal  and grits into water very slowly over low heat until the mixture is thick and  smooth. 3: Stir frequently, it will take about 30 minutes. 4: Beat in the butter,  cream and salt, then the egg yolks. 5: Whip egg whites until soft peaks form and  fold into cornmeal. 6: Pour into prepared pan  and bake for 30 minutes, or until  puffed and lightly browned. 7: •Serving Ideas : Serve immediately with lots of butter.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2068,"Texas Spoon Bread","PT45M","PT10M","PT55M","Make and share this Texas Spoon Bread recipe from Food.com.","Breads",5.0,2.0,207.2,9.5,4.9,115.2,522.0,22.2,1.5,0.9,8.8,"6.0","Texas Spoon Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: In saucepan, scald the milk; stir in cornmeal. 2: Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly. 3: Remove from heat; stir in butter, sugar, salt and baking powder. 4: In small bowl, beat egg yolks. 5: Gradually stir a small amount of the hot mixture into yolks; return all to pan and mix well. 6: In mixing bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form. 7: Fold egg whites into hot mixture until well blended. 8: Pour into greased 8-inch square baking dish. 9: Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes or until well puffed. 10: Use a spoon to serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2072,"Jade Tree Salad Dressing","0","PT5M","PT5M","Make and share this Jade Tree Salad Dressing recipe from Food.com.","Salad Dressings",0.0,0.0,3202.3,323.6,48.8,44.0,3095.9,62.9,4.9,50.6,26.5,"0.0","Jade Tree Salad Dressing Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix first seven ingredients together and refrigerate. 2: Immediately before serving, add 1/2  cup Parmesan cheese and 1/4 cup sesame seed. 3: Serve on lettuce with chopped water chestnuts. 4: Note: I usually add the cheese and sesame seed directly to the salad, so as not to spoil the dressing for later use.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2073,"Harvard Beets","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Harvard Beets recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,4.0,935.3,35.5,22.0,91.6,703.9,148.4,10.4,116.1,9.0,"0.0","Harvard Beets Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine sugar, cornstarch, butter, water and vinegar. 2: Cook until smooth and thick. 3: Add beets. 4: Heat thoroughly and  serve while hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2074,"Harvard Beets (Sweet Sour Red Beets)","PT15M","PT2M","PT17M","Make and share this Harvard Beets (Sweet Sour Red Beets) recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,10.0,285.4,8.0,4.9,20.4,975.2,52.7,3.4,46.8,2.9,"3.0","Harvard Beets (Sweet Sour Red Beets) Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix together the dry ingredients. 2: Add vinegar and water and stir until smooth. 3: Cook 5 minutes. 4: Add beets and let stand desired minutes. (Can marinate in fridge overnight or just while you prepare other dishes). 5: Before serving, heat to boiling point and add butter. 6: Serve warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2075,"Colorado Beef Stroganoff","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Colorado Beef Stroganoff recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.0,1.0,228.5,19.4,11.6,50.2,608.6,9.5,1.0,4.6,4.1,"6.0","Colorado Beef Stroganoff Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim fat from beef and cut into 1/2-inch slices. 2: Over high heat sear the beef  quickly in 1 tablespoon butter. 3: In 3 tablespoons butter (same pan) saute onion,  garlic and mushrooms about 5 minutes. 4: Remove from heat. Stir in flour, meat  extract paste, catsup, salt and pepper. 5: Stir until smooth. 6: Gradually add  bouillon, stirring constantly bring to a boil. 7: Reduce heat and simmer for 5  minutes. 8: Over very low heat, add wine, dill and sour cream. 9: Add beef, simmer  only until beef is hot. Serve over wild rice. Serves 6.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2081,"Lemon Poppy Seed Cake","PT45M","PT10M","PT55M","Make and share this Lemon Poppy Seed Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",1.0,1.0,423.7,25.9,4.1,85.6,364.6,43.5,1.0,25.3,5.5,"10.0","Lemon Poppy Seed Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix above ingredients together until smooth. 2: Bake in a loaf pan or Bundt pan 45 minutes at 350°F. 3: Cool 5 minutes. 4: Remove from pan and glaze with mixture  of 5 tablespoons lemon juice and 1/2 cup sugar. 5: jen.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2083,"Molasses Taffy","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Molasses Taffy recipe from Food.com.","Candy",0.0,0.0,1855.8,11.8,7.3,30.5,270.6,451.8,0.0,386.8,0.1,"1.0","Molasses Taffy Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine first 4 ingredients. 2: Boil until it reaches the brittle or crack stage. When just about ready to remove from the stove, add the pinch of soda. 3: Cool on platter until able to touch it. Butter your hands and pull until it is light in color. 4: Cut into sticks (if still able to do anything!) Lots of fun for a party. 5: A family oriented website    http://home.sprynet.com/~jmjohnsn      Seasonal Page Topic - Fall Foliage");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2084,"Basic Tea Biscuits","PT10M","PT20M","PT30M","Make and share this Basic Tea Biscuits recipe from Food.com.","Breads",3.0,1.0,111.9,5.3,1.5,2.3,260.2,13.8,0.5,0.1,2.3,"0.0","Basic Tea Biscuits Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 450 degrees F. 2: Combine dry ingredients. 3: Cut in shortening with two knives or a pastry  blender until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. 4: Make a well in the centre  and add liquid all at once. Stir vigorously until dough comes freely from  the sides of the bowl. 5: Turn dough onto a lightly floured board and roll or  pat to 1/2-inch thick. 6: Cut out 2-inch biscuits with a floured water glass  or biscuit cutter. 7: Place on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 12 to 15  minutes, until tops are golden brown. 8: Serve immediately with butter, jam or  honey. 9: Variations:  Cheese Tea Biscuits  Use only 3/4 tsp salt and 1/4 cup shortening. 10: Add 3/4 cup shredded cheese (yellow or marble) to dry ingredients. 11: Buttermilk Tea Biscuits  Use only 2 tsp baking powder  Add 1/2 tsp baking soda  Replace milk with 1 cup   buttermilk or sour milk. 12: Raisin or Nut Tea Biscuits  Add to dry ingredients  1/4 cup sugar; and  3/4 cup seedless raisins or chopped nuts  Use only 7/8 cup milk  Whole Wheat Tea Biscuits  Replace 1 cup of white flour with 1 cup whole wheat flour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2085,"English Cream Scones","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this English Cream Scones recipe from Food.com.","Scones",4.0,2.0,211.5,8.5,2.4,55.0,307.1,28.2,0.8,3.3,5.3,"0.0","English Cream Scones Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 450 degrees F. 2: Combine dry ingredients. 3: Cut in shortening with two knives or a pastry blender until mixture has the consistency of coarse cornmeal. 4: Set aside. Reserve a little of the egg whites (to brush over tops of scones) and beat eggs until light. Stir in milk. 5: Make a well in the dry ingredients and add liquid all at once, stirring with a fork vigorously until dough comes freely from the sides of the bowl. 6: Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and pat dough out to 3/4-inch thickness. 7: Cut into 8 triangles or squares or form into \ 8: . 9: Brush tops with egg whites and sprinkle generously with sugar. 10: place on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until tops are golden. 11: Variations: Raisin Scones Add to dry ingredients 1/2 cup seedless raisins, currants, Craisins or other fruits (fresh blueberries or raspberries, apple chunks etc). Cheese Scones Reduce sugar to 1 tsp Add 1 cup of shredded sharp cheese to dry ingredients. 12: Do Not sprinkle with sugar before baking.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2086,"Prize Butter Tarts","PT25M","PT5M","PT30M","Butter Tarts, a wonderful Canadian dessert, sort of like pecan pie without nuts, if you can imagine such a thing. This (old) Canadian recipe should do the trick!","Dessert",4.5,9.0,299.6,16.0,6.0,29.4,220.6,37.2,0.7,21.5,2.8,"0.0","Prize Butter Tarts Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375°F. 2: Prepare pastry dough; cut in circles and line 3-inch tart pans with pastry circles. 3: Combine balance of ingredients. 4: Spoon mixture into unbaked pastry lined pans, filling each no more than 2/3 full (if the filling bubbles over it makes one heck of a mess!). Bake for 20 minutes or until filling has cooked and pastry is golden. 5: Notes: This can be made without the raisins or nuts, but  they are very plain. 6: I generally make these with a combination of nuts and raisins. 7: Craisins can be substituted for the raisins. 8: For Jam Tarts: Line tart pan cups with pastry. 9: Fill cups 1/2 full with your choice of jam. 10: Bake at 400°F for 20 minutes or until pastry is golden.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2089,"Nurnberger","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Nurnberger recipe from Food.com.","Candy",5.0,1.0,3906.9,32.8,6.0,186.0,2338.1,841.2,16.8,560.3,51.4,"1.0","Nurnberger Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat honey to boiling in sauce pan. 2: Cool. 3: Stir in sugar, egg, lemon juice and rind. 4: Stir together flour, soda, and spices. 5: Mix into honey mixture. Stir in citron and nuts. 6: Chi ll in plastic wrap overnite.  Heat oven to 350 deg. 7: Shape into 1 inch balls and flatten. 8: Place on greased baking sheet. Press almond halves into cookes and cherry slice into center. 9: Bake just until set 10-12 minutes. 10: Glaze while warm. 11: Glaze:  stir ingredients until smooth. 12: Store in air tight container and let mellow.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2092,"Caribbean Key Lime Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Caribbean Key Lime Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,7.0,3858.6,223.3,169.7,802.6,998.0,411.5,32.8,359.9,78.1,"0.0","Caribbean Key Lime Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: To prepare crust, place coconut in thin layer on 2 (10 x 13-inch) cookie sheets. 2: Toast coconut in 350 degrees oven for 10 minutes or until light golden brown. 3: Stir frequently, and watch carefully. 4: Remove from oven and let cool. 5: Meanwhile,  reduce the oven to 250 degrees. 6: In small mixing bowl, beat egg whites to stiff  peaks, then slowly beat in superfine sugar until completely dissolved. 7: Fold in  cooled coconut. Press this mixture into greased 9-inch pie plate and bake at 250  degrees for 7 minutes and set. Remove from oven and let cool. 8: To make filling: 9: Blend together sweetened  condensed milk, lime juice, lime rind and rum in large  mixing bowl. 10: Beat in the egg yolks. 11: Gently mix in sour cream to combine well. 12: Pour into cooled crust. Swirl meringue over top of filling. 13: Bake in 350 degrees  oven 20 minutes or until meringue is nicely browned. 14: Cool, then chill at least  30 minutes before serving. 15: To make Meringue: 16: Beat egg whites in large mixing bowl until soft peaks are formed. 17: Gradually beat  in sugar until whites are stiff, but not dry, being sure the sugar is dissolved.");
