INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2100,"Fresh Rhubarb Pie","PT40M","PT0S","PT40M","Make and share this Fresh Rhubarb Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,32.0,196.9,3.0,1.9,7.6,28.5,43.4,1.2,38.8,0.7,"8.0","Fresh Rhubarb Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Roll half of pastry to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.  Place in a 9-inch pie plate; trim off excess pastry along edges. 2: Cover with plastic wrap, and chill until ready to fill. 3: Combine sugar, cornstarch and nutmeg in a heavy saucepan, stirring to blend cornstarch well. 4: Stir in orange rind, juice and butter. 5: Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. 6: Stir in rhubarb. 7: Spoon rhubarb mixture into prepared pastry shell. 8: Roll remaining pastry to 1/4-inch thickness; cut into 1/2-inch strips. 9: Arrange strips, lattice fashioned, across top of pie.  Trim strips even with edges; fold edges under and flute.  Bake at 425°F or 10 minutes. 10: Reduce heat to 350°F and bake an additional 30 minutes or until crust is brown. 11: ENJOY!");
