INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2121,"Zucchini Puff Pies","PT30M","PT40M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Zucchini Puff Pies recipe from Food.com.","Pie",0.0,0.0,493.5,32.5,11.2,69.0,387.3,38.5,1.8,1.9,11.9,"0.0","Zucchini Puff Pies Recipe Instructions:  1: Steam marrow until tender. 2: Puree marrow in blender / food processor. 3: Saute onions in minced garlic in butter until tender. 4: Shred cheddar cheese. Add onions, garlic, cheese, bread crumbs, eggs and herbs to zucchini. 5: Thaw frozen puff pastry 20 minutes. 6: Roll out each sheet on slightly floured board. 7: Divide each sheet into 4 squares. 8: Fill each of the 8 squares with marrow mixture leaving 1-inch border on all sides. 9: Brush border with egg white; prick top with fork. 10: Place pies on cookie sheet and bake in 400F oven for 30 minutes or till golden brown. 11: Serve warm. 12: See cheese puff pies for frozen puff pastry directions.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2127,"Crisco Cookies","PT12M","PT0S","PT12M","Make and share this Crisco Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,4.0,82.1,4.8,1.5,4.8,17.0,9.1,0.1,4.7,0.7,"44.0","Crisco Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream Crisco and sugar together; add egg. 2: Sift soda, cream of tartar and flour together. 3: Add vanilla. 4: Form into balls the size of walnuts. 5: Roll in sugar; place on cookie  sheet. Press down with thumb. 6: Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes.");
