INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2165,"Peanut Butter Squares","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Peanut Butter Squares recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",5.0,1.0,3214.1,167.1,35.0,186.0,2976.8,385.0,19.3,220.0,63.4,"1.0","Peanut Butter Squares Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream margarine with the sugars. 2: Blend in egg. 3: Add peanut butter and vanilla. 4: Mix flour, oats, soda and salt and spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. 5: Bake in  a 350 degrees oven for 20 to 25 minutes. 6: While still hot, sprinkle with 6 ounces of chocolate chips. 7: Spread over top. 8: Make icing of 1/4 cup peanut butter, 1/2  cup powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons of milk or cream. 9: Swirl on top of melted  chocolate. Cool and cut into squares. 10: PEANUT BUTTER SQUARES 1 (18 oz.) crunchy peanut butter 1 cup margarine 2 1/2 cup graham cracker crumbs 1 box powdered sugar 1 tsp. 11: vanilla flavor To pping: 1 (16 oz.) bag chocolate chips 1/2 cup margarine Over low heat melt crunchy peanut butter or margarine. Add graham cracker  crumbs, one box powdered sugar and one teaspoon vanilla. 12: Mix well. 13: Then press  into square pan. 14: Topping: Melt over very low heat chocolate chips and 1/2 cup   margarine and stir thoroughly. 15: Spread over peanut mixture. Let cool, then cut  into squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2167,"East-West Flank Steak Wraps","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this East-West Flank Steak Wraps recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,3.0,398.8,19.7,5.9,91.8,323.8,19.8,0.9,4.9,33.8,"4.0","East-West Flank Steak Wraps Recipe Instructions:  1: In large bowl, combine dressi ng ingredients; whisk until blended. 2: Place beef  steak in plastic bag; add 3/4 of dressing, turning to coat. Close bag securely  and marinate in refrigerator 10 minutes. 3: Meanwhile add coleslaw mix, green onions, salt and pepper to remaining 1/4 of dressing  in bowl; toss. 4: Set aside. Wrap tortillas in aluminum foil. 5: Remove steak from  dressing; discard dressing. 6: Place steak on grid over medium, ash-covered coals. 7: Grill, uncovered, 17 to 21 minutes fro medium rare to medium doneness, turning  once. A few minutes before steak is done, place tortilla packet on grid near  edge of grill to heat. Remove steak from grill; let rest 2 to 3 minutes. 8: Season  steak with salt and pepper, as desired; carve diagonally into thin slices. 9: To  assemble, layer an equal amount of beef, coleslaw mixture and the peanuts down center of each tortilla. 10: Fold bottom edge of tortilla up over  filling. 11: Fold right and left sides to center, overlapping edges. 12: Garnish with  green onion and  peanuts, if desired. 13: Tip: To broil, place steak on rack in broiler pan so surface of meat is 2 to 3  inches from heat. Broil 13 to 18 minutes, turning once. Thinly sliced green  cabbage may be substituted for packaged coleslaw mix.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2172,"Almond Creme Brulee","0","PT1M","PT1M","Make and share this Almond Creme Brulee recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,701.6,58.9,29.7,351.8,85.8,38.5,2.5,31.5,9.4,"6.0","Almond Creme Brulee Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat cream in a heavy saucepan. 2: Add granulated sugar and stir until  dissolved. 3: Beat egg yolks until light and creamy. 4: Add t  he hot cream to the  egg yolks gradually, whipping constantly with a wire whisk (not an electric  beater). Stir in remaining ingredients except the brown sugar. 5: Pour into  a 6-cup souffle dish, and sprinkle brown sugar on top. 6: Bake at 325 degrees  for 45 minutes, or until custard tests done.   - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  NOTES : This is not for anyone on a low cal, low fat, or low cholesterol  diet.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2174,"Poppy Seed Cake","0","PT1M","PT1M","Make and share this Poppy Seed Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",3.0,1.0,415.4,20.9,10.8,112.0,418.3,51.4,1.6,30.4,7.0,"12.0","Poppy Seed Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix poppy seeds and buttermilk together, and let stand in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.  Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.  Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time; beat in vanilla and grated orange rind. 2: Stir in flour mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture in about 4 additions of each, stirring until just smooth. 3: Spoon half of batter into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. 4: Mix remaining sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle mixture over batter. 5: Pour rest of batter into the pan. 6: Bake in 350°F oven for about 1 hour, or until a wooden pick comes out clean. 7: Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then turn out to finish cooling. 8: Cover tightly and let season for a day or two for best flavor.");
