INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2419,"Heavenly Chilled Orange Cheesecake","PT10M","PT1H","PT1H10M","Make and share this Heavenly Chilled Orange Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",0.0,1.0,775.0,62.7,38.5,194.7,502.4,45.0,0.8,32.5,11.8,"0.0","Heavenly Chilled Orange Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Soften gelatin in juice. Combine crumbs and butter. 2: Press into bottom of 9 spring form pan. 3: Bake at 350 F for 10 minutes. 4: Cool. 5: Stir over low heat until dissolved. 6: Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing well on medium. 7: Gradually add gelatin. 8: Chill until slightly thickened, fold in whipped cream and peel. 9: Pour over crust. Chill until firm. 10: Garnish with orange slices and fresh mint, if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2422,"Chicken Livers in Black Bean Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chicken Livers in Black Bean Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",4.0,1.0,1216.9,53.5,10.9,1383.6,4282.5,77.1,28.3,39.6,111.9,"0.0","Chicken Livers in Black Bean Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim livers, discarding any core part.  Cut into 2cm pieces. 2: Place livers in a bowl with the soy sauce, sherry, salt, sugar, pepper and stock powder. 3: Marinate 5 minutes. 4: Heat the oil in a large frying pan and quickly cook the chicken livers over a high heat until almost cooked. 5: This is best done in two batches. 6: Transfer to a plate.  Add the capsicum to the pan and cook 1 minute.  Tear the large bok choy leave in halve lengthwise.  Add all the leaves to the pan and sprinkle the livers on top. 7: Cover and cook 1 minutes. 8: Mix together the sauce ingredients and pour into the pan. 9: Toss until the sauce is hot and the bok choy has wilted and the livers just cooked. 10: Season with salt and pepper if wished and serve on noodles.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2423,"Home Fries","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Home Fries recipe from Food.com.","Potato",4.0,1.0,820.0,1.0,0.3,0.0,63.9,186.1,23.4,8.3,21.5,"1.0","Home Fries Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil potatoes with jackets on until the fork goes in  fairly easily. 2: Peel potatoes after they cool. 3: Put small  amount of oil in skillet. Slice and fry until brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2424,"Home Fried Potatoes","PT25M","PT10M","PT35M","Make and share this Home Fried Potatoes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,8.0,401.7,17.4,6.8,16.3,626.6,56.2,7.2,2.5,6.5,"4.0","Home Fried Potatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: Press potatoes between paper towels; sprinkle with seasonings. 2: Heat  drippings in heavy skillet; add potatoes. 3: Cover and cook over low heat 5  minutes. 4: Remove cover and fry over medium heat for about 20 minutes,  turning to brown evenly.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2425,"Home-Fried Potatoes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Home-Fried Potatoes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,11.0,751.5,14.4,2.0,0.0,48.8,144.1,18.3,12.2,16.3,"2.0","Home-Fried Potatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel and cube potatoes. 2: Cook in oil in covered skillet, turning often  about 5 minutes. 3: Add onions, salt and pepper to taste and continue to cook  over l  ow heat until potatoes are almost cooked, turning often. 4: Remove  cover and continue cooking until well browned and slightly crisped. 5: Serves  2 to");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2431,"Sweet Potato Casserole","PT35M","PT10M","PT45M","Make and share this Sweet Potato Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Potato",4.0,1.0,560.1,41.3,22.1,108.9,264.6,46.0,4.7,30.2,5.5,"8.0","Sweet Potato Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350F and grease a 3 quart casserole. 2: Mix together mashed sweet potatoes, eggs, vanilla, butter, milk and coconut. 3: Pour into greased 12-inch round casserole. 4: For topping, mix together brown  sugar, nuts, flour and butter. 5: Crumble over the sweet potatoes (not too thick as it''s sweet). 6: Bake for 25 to 35 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2437,"Grandma''s Apple Muffins","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Grandma''s Apple Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,8.0,160.4,7.9,4.0,33.1,136.4,20.9,0.7,12.2,2.2,"0.0","Grandma''s Apple Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare Streusel Topping by mix topping ingredients in small bowl until crumbly. 2: Set aside. 3: In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and cloves. 4: Add apple and walnuts; toss to coat. 5: In small bowl, beat eggs with fork; beat in buttermilk and butter. 6: Add to flour mixture; stir just until blended. 7: Fill greased pans 2/3 full. 8: Sprinkle with Streusel Topping. 9: Bake in preheated 400 degrees oven until pick inserted in center comes out clean, 15 to 25 minutes for muffins, 30 to 35 minutes for 9-inch square coffee cake.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2442,"Pumpkin Soup","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pumpkin Soup recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,12.0,324.2,21.5,13.0,66.4,299.9,26.4,2.1,4.9,8.6,"6.0","Pumpkin Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel and dice pumpkin and potatoes Melt half the butter or margarine in a  saucepan and saute the onion until golden brown. 2: Add the diced pumpkin and  potatoes and milk.Bring to a boil,reduce heat and simmer for about 40 minutes. 3: Sieve or puree in an electric blender. 4: Season to taste with salt and pepper. 5: Saute the leeks in the remaining butter or margarine. Add to the soup with the  chicken stock.Bring to a boil. 6: Reduce heat and simmer for five minutes. 7: Before  serving,stir in cream and chopped parsley.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2447,"Carrot Apple Casserole","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Carrot Apple Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Apple",5.0,1.0,244.7,6.1,3.7,15.3,91.4,49.5,3.9,40.9,1.0,"4.0","Carrot Apple Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook carrots in boiling water until barely tender. 2: Do not overcook them because they are going into the oven. 3: Drain and mix the carrots and apples in a baking dish that has been lightly buttered. 4: Combine sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon, sprinkle over the carrot and apple mixture. Dot with the butter. 5: Pour the orange juice over all and bake 350: for about an hour. 6: This dish can be expanded very easily.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2453,"Cucumber Raita","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cucumber Raita recipe from Food.com.","Asian",3.5,3.0,124.2,4.5,2.7,15.9,64.2,17.2,1.6,10.8,6.4,"0.0","Cucumber Raita Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine cucumbers with yogurt in a bowl. 2: Fry cumin in a dry pan for 1 minute until fragrant, then add to yogurt mixture with the ginger. 3: Season with salt and pepper. 4: Place in a bowl and dust with paprika. 5: Serve chilled. 6: Can be refrigerated up to 2 days.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2458,"Chocolatetown Special Cake (Chocolate Cake)","PT35M","PT10M","PT45M","Very rich because of the addition of buttermilk. I like to use Recipe #261024 for the icing. Or Recipe #95416 if I need to decorate the cake.","Dessert",5.0,3.0,331.1,13.2,3.6,36.3,295.9,50.4,1.8,30.7,5.1,"12.0","Chocolatetown Special Cake (Chocolate Cake) Recipe Instructions:  1: In small bowl combine cocoa and boiling water, set aside. Heat oven to 350 degrees F. 2: Grease and flour 2 9-inch round pans. (Don''t use 8-inch pans or they will overflow!). 3: Cream shortening, sugar, and vanilla until light and fluffy. 4: Add eggs, beat well. 5: Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture. Blend in cocoa mixture. Pour into prepared pans. 6: Bake for 35-40 minutes or until they test done. Cool and frost with a icing of your choice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2459,"Dark Chocolate Cake","PT50M","PT10M","PT1H","While it takes slightly longer to prepare this recipe than a box mix, the resulting moist, delicious cake makes it VERY worth the little extra time. I consider this ''perfect'' chocolate cake. This cake is excellent with  both with Recipe #261024 and Recipe #208959 (the dark flavor version). (I use Recipe #95416 when I''m decorating the cake.) I love how the leftovers are still moist even a day or two later. (I store my loosely covered with plastic wrap.)
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2461,"Pumpkin Pie Crunch","PT50M","PT15M","PT1H5M","Several reviewers complain about the recipe being too sweet and/or too buttery as originally written. I''ve included the amounts I use, which I think are ''just right''. Also, since I usually don''t have pumpkin pie spice in the house, I use 1 1/2 tsp. cinnamon, 1/2 tsp. nutmeg, 1/4 tsp. cloves and 1/2 tsp. ginger instead. (Tip: Using 2/3 of the cake mix instead of half makes it easy to make 8 cupcakes with the remaining box since the mix calls for 3 eggs.)","Pie",5.0,75.0,318.5,18.2,7.7,57.8,336.3,36.7,1.0,24.1,4.1,"20.0","Pumpkin Pie Crunch Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Grease bottom of 13x9x2-inch pan. 3: Combine pumpkin,  evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, pumpkin pie spice and salt in large bowl. 4: Pour into pan. 5: Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin mixture. Top with  pecans. 6: Drizzle with melted butter. 7: Bake at 350°F for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden. (Check it early). 8: Cool completely. Serve with whipped topping. Refrigerate leftovers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2464,"Chocolate Pumpkin Spice Cake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Chocolate Pumpkin Spice Cake  This very moist, smooth cake combines the typ  ical flavor of pumpkin pie with  the sensual charms of chocolate.","Dessert",4.0,4.0,6583.2,335.5,139.3,1334.0,2917.6,868.2,57.2,503.8,99.1,"1.0","Chocolate Pumpkin Spice Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. 2: Grease and flour a 10-inch bundt pan  or tube pan. 3: In a large heavy saucepan over medium heat, melt the butter. 4: Remove from heat and mix in the sugar, pumpkin puree, vanilla, and eggs. 5: Add the baking powder and baking soda in pinches, breaking up any lumps  with your fingers. 6: Stir in thoroughly. 7: Stir in the salt, cinnamon,  ginger, cloves, nutmeg, and cocoa. 8: Stir in the flour, just until blended,  then the nuts and raisins. 9: Pour and scrape the batter into the pan. 10: Smooth the top. 11: Bake for 45 minutes. 12: Cool in the pan on a rack for 10  minutes. 13: Remove from the pan and cool on the rack for about 15 minutes  more. When cool, dust top with confectioners'' sugar, if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2465,"Pumpkin Bundt Cake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pumpkin Bundt Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,8.0,674.6,41.2,5.3,74.4,412.6,71.3,4.0,40.8,9.6,"0.0","Pumpkin Bundt Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. 2: Grease and flour a 10-inch bundt pan or tube pan. 3: In a large mixing bowl, mix the eggs with a large fork until well blended. 4: Mix in the sugar. 5: Add the oil in a steady stream, mixing all the while, until the mixture is thick and smooth. 6: Mix in the  pumpkin, vanilla, cinnamon, clove and salt. Add the baking soda and baking powder in pinches, breaking up any lumps with your fingers. 7: Stir in thoroughly. 8: Stir in the whole wheat and all-purpose flours just until blended. 9: Stir in the walnuts. 10: Pour and scrape the batter into the pan and bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until a tester inserted in the center comes out clean. 11: Cool in the pan on a rack for 10 minutes. 12: Invert, remove the pan, and cool on the rack for about 15 minutes more.  (Makes 10-12 servings)");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2468,"Pumpkin Roll","PT1H","PT30M","PT1H30M","An impressive recipe that really isn''t that hard to make. Everyone always raves about how good it is. One tip, use a linen towel to wrap it in. A terry cloth one will stick...don''t ask me how I know. ;o)","Vegetable",5.0,34.0,192.7,8.7,3.5,50.5,319.1,26.2,0.5,20.6,3.2,"16.0","Pumpkin Roll Recipe Instructions:  1: Line 10x15 inch jellyroll pan with waxed paper and grease. Preheat oven to 375°F. 2: In a large bowl, beat eggs and sugar with an electric mixer on high speed for five minutes. Gradually mix in pumpkin. Combine the flour, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon; stir into the pumpkin mixture. 3: Spread batter evenly into the prepared pan. Bake at 375°F for 15 minutes. 4: After you take it out of  the oven sprinkle top with powdered sugar, and flip onto a dish towel. Remove the waxed paper and sprinkle with more powdered sugar; roll up like a jellyroll in the dish towel. 5: Refrigerate for 1 hour or put in freezer for 15 minutes. Unroll; spread filling on roll and roll again without the towel. 6: Place in container or Reynolds Wrap. Refrigerate or you  may freeze for up to 4 months.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2472,"Lite or Light Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Muffins","PT18M","PT15M","PT33M","Make and share this Lite or Light Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,47.0,235.4,9.8,3.4,31.0,246.3,36.2,1.6,21.5,3.5,"0.0","Lite or Light Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix first 5 ingredients together; separately, mix dry ingredients. 2: Blend the  two mixtures together, fold in chips. 3: Generously fill 24 greased or  paper-lined muffin cups. (I have found the paper liners don''t work very well.). 4: Bake at 400 degrees F. for 16-20 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2473,"Pumpkin Pie Spice Bread","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","Nothing says AUTUMN quite like pumpkin with the warming notes of spices! A moist delicious bread that is wonderful &quot;as is&quot; or with cream cheese spread on it. YUM! I''ve also included healthier ingredient alternatives.","Quick Breads",5.0,67.0,392.1,15.2,2.3,46.5,344.8,60.7,1.0,38.0,4.7,"0.0","Pumpkin Pie Spice Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large bowl, combine sugar, oil and eggs. 2: Add pumpkin and mix well. 3: Combine dry ingredients; add to the pumpkin mixture alternately with water. 4: Pour into two greased 9-in. x 5-in. x 3-in. loaf pans. 5: Bake at 350 F for  60-70 minutes or until bread tests done. Cool in pans 10 minutes before  removing to a wire rack; cool completely.");
