INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2504,"Oriental Style One-Dish Dinner","0","PT0S","PT0S","Oriental Style One-Dish Dinner  For entertaining, make this in your fanciest skillet or flameproof casserole to take right to the table from the stove.","Low Cholesterol",5.0,1.0,467.6,17.7,6.4,56.9,1466.8,54.1,4.6,6.1,22.8,"6.0","Oriental Style One-Dish Dinner Recipe Instructions:  1: Lightly oil wok or skillet; add pork and stir-fry until meat is no longer pink. 2: Stir in cabbage, carrots, onion, mushrooms, water chestnuts and ginger; stir-fry for 2 minutes. 3: Mix in soy sauce, then rice; stir gently. 4: Pour in stock. 5: Cover tightly and simmer about 20 to 25 minutes until liquid is almost absorbed. 6: Stir in zucchini and asparagus; continue to cook about 5 minutes longer. 7: Season with salt, and pepper to  taste. Serve garnished with green onions.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2505,"New England Fish Chowder","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this New England Fish Chowder recipe from Food.com.","Chowders",3.5,2.0,167.3,4.7,2.1,51.7,411.6,9.6,0.8,4.9,20.8,"6.0","New England Fish Chowder Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut fillets into 1/2 - 1 inch cubes. 2: Fry the bacon until it is crisp. 3: Add the onions and brown them slightly. 4: Add the potatoes, and water to just cover, and cook for 10 minutes or until the potatoes are slightly tender. 5: Add the fish and cook until it flakes easily with a fork. 6: Add the milk and seasonings and reheat. Serve immediately with chopped parsley sprinkled over the top.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2506,"Tuna Noodle Casserole Delight","PT50M","PT0S","PT50M","Make and share this Tuna Noodle Casserole Delight recipe from Food.com.","Tuna",4.5,6.0,120.3,1.4,0.3,12.9,622.6,14.3,4.1,4.5,12.7,"6.0","Tuna Noodle Casserole Delight Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350. 2: Prepare a 2-quart casserole dish with cooking spray; set aside. Heat water to boiling. 3: Add noodles and salt. Boil for 9 minutes and drain. 4: Add milk to soup and mix well. 5: Arrange half of noodles, half of tuna, half of peas, and half of soup mixture in layers in prepared dish. 6: Repeat layers. 7: Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. 8: Bake for 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2507,"Pumpkin Spice Cake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pumpkin Spice Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,242.7,3.4,0.7,0.3,202.8,51.9,2.2,29.9,3.5,"16.0","Pumpkin Spice Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat sugar with margarine, using electric mixer. 2: Add egg, beating until light.  Beat in buttermilk, pumpkin, orange rind and vanilla. 3: Combine flours, cinnamon,  baking soda and raisins. 4: Stir into pumpkin mixture until combined. 5: Bake in  lightly-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan at 325 degrees for 60 to 65  minutes or until toothpick inserted in centre comes out clean. 6: Cool 20 minutes  and remove from pan. 7: Glaze: Blend icing sugar with orange juice. Drizzle over  cooled cake.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2508,"Stuffed Zucchini","PT40M","PT15M","PT55M","Make and share this Stuffed Zucchini recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,49.0,192.9,15.3,5.0,46.2,178.7,8.7,2.4,6.0,7.2,"7.0","Stuffed Zucchini Recipe Instructions:  1: Slice zucchini in half lengthwise.  Scoop out insides leaving about 1/4-in shell. 2: Finely chop zucchini pulp; set aside.  Saute onion in oil in large heavy skillet.  Add mushrooms, garlic and reserved chopped zucchini; cook over medium heat until most of moisture evaporates. 3: Add cream cheese, egg, Parmesan, parsley, and pepper. 4: Mix well; cook for about 10 minutes. 5: Cool filling slightly and fill zucchini shells. 6: Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.  Place on jelly roll pans; bake for 30 minutes at 350°F until bubbly and golden brown on top.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2509,"Peanut Butter Cream Pie","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Peanut Butter Cream Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",0.0,0.0,955.9,67.5,30.1,128.9,622.0,73.4,3.0,54.8,20.1,"0.0","Peanut Butter Cream Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: FILLING:  Beat cream cheese - beat in condensed milk, peanut butter and vanilla. 2: Whip heavy cream and fold into cream cheese mixture. 3: Melt together chopped milk chocolate and  heavy cream. 4: Drizzle over top. 5: Refrigerate until ready to serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2512,"Good Ol'' Grits Pie","PT45M","PT15M","PT1H","Make and share this Good Ol'' Grits Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,1.0,347.6,12.4,4.4,55.2,176.8,54.2,0.7,27.0,5.1,"8.0","Good Ol'' Grits Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. 2: In a bowl, combine the grits, brown sugar,  flour, and eggs. 3: Blend well, then stir in the milk and butter or margarine. Add  the vanilla and vinegar, and blend well. 4: Pour the mixture into the pie shell and bake for 35 to 40 minutes,  or until the center is just set. Let cool briefly, then serve while still warm. 5: Serve warm by itself or topped with ice cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2513,"Sweet Tamales","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sweet Tamales recipe from Food.com.","Mexican",0.0,0.0,96.2,8.1,2.7,6.1,91.3,6.2,0.4,5.2,0.3,"0.0","Sweet Tamales Recipe Instructions:  1: Soak husks according to directions in Basic Tamales. 2: For tamale dough:  Beat lard and salt until fluffy. 3: Slowly beat in masa mix alternately  with water until very light and fluffy. 4: Add brown sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg, mixing until well blended. 5: To assemble tamales: Drain corn husks; pat dry. 6: Spread 2 tablespoons dough on center of husks, forming a 3 x 2-inch rectangle and spreading completely to right edge.  Spoon 1 teaspoon each pecans and raisins  lengthwise down center of rectangle. To enclose and steam tamales, proceed according to directions in Basic Tamales.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2514,"Shrimp Dip","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Shrimp Dip recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,7.0,1978.9,158.3,55.9,311.0,3673.7,124.0,8.0,55.5,28.9,"1.0","Shrimp Dip Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat soup, dissolve gelatin stirring constantly until dissolved. 2: Let cool  slightly, put in mixer with cream cheese and mayonnaise and mix. 3: By hand add  shrimp, celery and onion and mix. 4: Serve with crackers. May be frozen. 5: Grease  container and pour into a mold to set in refrigerator, and then unmold to serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2516,"Low-Fat Creamy Macaroni & Cheese","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Low-Fat Creamy Macaroni & Cheese recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",4.5,4.0,334.5,3.8,1.9,13.2,357.7,52.0,2.1,6.3,21.8,"4.0","Low-Fat Creamy Macaroni & Cheese Recipe Instructions:  1: Coat a two-quart casserole dish with non-stick spray. 2: Cook macaroni according to package directions. 3: Drain macaroni, reserving two tablespoons cooking water. 4: Toss macaroni with reserved cooking water, cheeses, sour cream, milk, onions, egg white, margarine, cheese-flavored granules, mustard and peppers until well combined. 5: Spoon into casserole dish. 6: Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and paprika. 7: Cover. 8: Bake casserole at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. 9: Uncover and bake until golden brown an d bubbly, about five minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2517,"Gold Medal Caramel Bars","PT25M","PT0S","PT25M","Make and share this Gold Medal Caramel Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",3.0,2.0,4.2,0.3,0.2,0.0,0.1,0.6,0.1,0.5,0.0,"0.0","Gold Medal Caramel Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°. 2: Prepare a 9 x 13 pan with cooking spray; set aside. In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix and sweetened condensed milk. 3: Batter will be thick. 4: Press 2/3 of batter into prepared pan. 5: Bake for 8 minutes. 6: Remove from oven and pour caramel topping over cake. Sprinkle with chocolate chips. 7: Crumble remaining batter over top. 8: Bake for 17 minutes more or until top is dry to the touch. 9: Cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2518,"Cilantro Lime Soup","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cilantro Lime Soup recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,3.0,223.0,8.0,2.2,36.3,1021.6,19.1,3.0,5.0,20.4,"4.0","Cilantro Lime Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat broth in medium pot. Add onion, garlic, chili powder, tomatoes, bunch cilantro and chile. Simmer for 15 minutes. 2: Add chicken and simmer until cooked (about 10 minutes). Discard bunch cilantro. 3: Add corn and cook 2-3 minutes. 4: Add chopped cilantro and lime juice. Garnish with sour cream and baked tortilla strips (cut corn tortillas in strips, spray with cooking spray, bake in 350 degree oven until crisp).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2519,"Whipped Potatoes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Whipped Potatoes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",0.0,0.0,155.2,0.3,0.1,0.7,215.4,34.5,4.2,1.9,4.5,"6.0","Whipped Potatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: ..Place the potatoes in a five quart pan. 2: Add cold water to 1 inch above the potatoes. 3: Place the pan over high heat and bring the water to a boil. 4: Reduce the heat and simmer for about 20 minutes. 5: When potatoes pierce easily with a fork, remove from the pan from the stove and drain. 6: ..Place the drained potatoes into the large bowl of an electric mixer. 7: At low speed, begin to break up the potatoes. 8: As the potatoes break up, slowly raise the speed of the mixer to medium. 9: Add the milk, Butter Buds, nonfat sour cream, salt and pepper and mix until smooth. 10: Spoon the whipped potatoes into a warmed serving bowl and dust with the papri ka and parsley.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2522,"Rice Pudding with Fresh Fruit","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Rice Pudding with Fresh Fruit recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,1231.7,28.1,16.9,102.5,945.1,216.1,13.4,83.0,32.1,"1.0","Rice Pudding with Fresh Fruit Recipe Instructions:  1: In a saucepan, combine rice, milk, sugar, and salt. Cook over medium heat until mixture begins to bubble. Reduce heat and cover. 2: Cook 1 hour, stirring occasionally. 3: Remove from heat.  Add vanilla and Pernod. 4: Cool, then refrigerate at least 3 hours. 5: Halve pears lengthwise, slice thinly, and spread out into a fan shape.   Place pear and rice pudding on plates, and garnish with raspberries and anise seeds.");
