INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2527,"Nuts & Dried Fruit Mooncake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Please remember that these mooncake need to made with a mooncake mold.   Nuts & Dried Fruit Mooncake - Traditional Taiwan Style  Pastry Crust","Dessert",0.0,0.0,4832.9,278.4,40.9,332.4,1356.3,522.4,47.6,168.6,85.3,"1.0","Nuts & Dried Fruit Mooncake Recipe Instructions:  1: Fillings: (A) Red Bean Filling 450g red bean paste (B) Dried Fruit & Nuts Filling:   100g pitted black dates 200 cc  water 2 Tbsp white grape wine 2 Tbsp wine 2 Tbsp Sugar Syrup* 1 Tbsp flour  1 Tbsp glutinous flour 50g almond 50g sugar 60g toasted sesame 80g walnut  30g pine nuts 30g raisins 20g oil  Light Color Pastry Shine Oil 1 egg yolk 2 tsp cooking wine ,  1/2 tsp milk Dark Color Pastry Shine Oil 1 egg yolk 2 tsp cooking wine 1 sugar syrup,  heated  (like caramel sort ) Make filling. 2: Cook the dates with the 200 cc water on low heat until all the  water is absorbed. 3: Add wines, syrup and flours. 4: Cook to thicken. 5: Remove the  dates and mash . 6: Cut raisins and  other fruit and nuts into thin stripes or  little pieces . 7: Mix with the mashed dates . 8: Shape into dough with hands. 9: Let  cool. 10: Divide into 30 g balls. 11: Make Pastry crust. Mix both type of flour and baking powder then sift and place  it into a large bowl. 12: Dig a hole in the middle of dough . 13: Mix the sugar-water  and oil and pour it into the hole. Slowly mix well. 14: Then knead till the dough no longer sticky to hand and is shiny. 15: Don''t use too much force to knead. 16: Divide  dough into 12 portion . 17: Each portion should weight 25g. 18: On each piece of dough  place the filling--either the red bean paste or the dried fruit/nuts filling. 19: Sprinkle flour in mooncake mold. 20: Place the mooncake into the mold and press into shape. Get rid of the extra flour on the mold. 21: Then brush the top  with the  shine oil. 22: Bake at 190C degree for 15 minutes. 23: ** For red bean paste mooncake the crust is same as the  above one.   ** If no mold shape in round with hand    Cantonese Style Mooncake ( Red Bean Paste with egg yolk )   Pastry :  (A)2C cake flour , 1T milk powder , 2/5C fine sugar ,  1/8t  baking powder       (B ) 1/3C oil , 1/2t salt , 1/3C honey , 1 egg yolk   Filling: 900g Red bean paste , 20 Salted Egg Yolks   Sieve ingredient (A) on the flour, dig a hole in the middle ,  add  the   (B)  ingredients. 24: Stir them and knead into a very soft  dough. 25: Cut into 10 portions. 26: Divide the red bean paste into 10 portions , wrap 2  egg yolks  into each of the  portion.(before this the yolk may be dip with wine   and bake in oven for 5  minutes). Wrap each of the (2) into each of the (1). Press into the  mooncake  mold , tip it out of the mold, apply beaten egg on the  surface. Bake in oven  bake for 20 minutes at 180C degree.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2529,"Chicken Noodle Soup","PT52M","PT10M","PT1H2M","Make and share this Chicken Noodle Soup recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",3.0,5.0,83.8,5.9,1.7,29.2,29.5,0.0,0.0,0.0,7.2,"4.0","Chicken Noodle Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a  boil. 2: Simmer 5 to 7 minutes over low heat. 3: CHICKEN NOODLE SOUP  1 lb. (about) chicken breasts  2 (13 3/4 oz.) cans chicken  broth  1/2 cup each chopped onion,  carrots and celery  1 cup water  medium egg noodles 4: In large saucepan combine all ingredients except noodles. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes. 5: Remove chicken and cut off  bones and cut into small pieces. 6: Add to soup. 7: Stir in noodles. 8: Simmer, covered, 15 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2530,"Chicken Soup II","PT30M","PT30M","PT1H","Make and share this Chicken Soup II recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",0.0,0.0,733.0,14.2,3.9,65.7,497.6,116.8,12.8,11.8,37.6,"6.0","Chicken Soup II Recipe Instructions:  1: Place chicken in a stockpot and cover with water. 2: Boil chicken until it falls off the bone. 3: Remove bones and gristle. 4: Set aside. 5: Cook potatoes in fresh water until tender (not mushy). 6: Rinse. 7: Cook carrots in broth until  tender. 8: Add remaining ingredients and cook at least another 30 minutes.");
