INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2598,"Ground Beef Stuffed Red Bell Peppers","PT40M","PT0S","PT40M","Make and share this Ground Beef Stuffed Red Bell Peppers recipe from Food.com.","Peppers",3.0,1.0,1754.0,86.2,33.6,357.1,1559.3,126.7,12.7,27.5,114.6,"0.0","Ground Beef Stuffed Red Bell Peppers Recipe Instructions:  1: Salt, pepper, chopped fresh parsley, minced garlic for taste. Wash  the peppers and dry them very well. 2: Cut each one into two pieces (longitudinally). Get out  all the seeds and any white part. Preheat oven. 3: FILLING: Put the bread in a cup with the milk. 4: Wait until the bread absorb all the  liquid it can. 5: Then squeeze it; only the humid bread without liquid will be  used. 6: Aside, put in  a bowl the ground beef, the very finely chopped onion,  the minced garlic and  the parsley. 7: Mix all very well. 8: Add the humid bread cut  in small pieces; put enough salt and pepper. 9: Fill the peppers halves. 10: Sprinkle each one with grated dried bread. 11: Put them on a shell with a thin oil  layer. 12: Cook in the oven for about 30-40 minutes until the peppers are tender and the cover (the grated bread)  gold brown. 13: Bon appetit!  The same filling can be used to stuff zucchini and aubergines, for instance.  These ones must be cooked previously in salted boiling water (already cut in  halves). Then you have to empty each half with a tablespoon, taking care of not  damaging  the skin. 14: Part of the fruit retired (and chopped) can be mixed in the  filling. 15: I hope you like these ideas.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2599,"Sugared Walnuts","0","PT30M","PT30M","However here is one that I used to bag up and sell at craft shows..  Sugared Walnuts (or Pecans or Almonds)**","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,8.0,938.8,64.7,6.7,4.3,239.5,86.7,6.7,73.3,15.9,"0.0","Sugared Walnuts Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine brown sugar, milk, grated orange peel, salt and cinnamon in large saucepan. 2: Stir to combine.  Cook over low heat until candy thermometer registers 236 degrees. 3: Remove from heat and add nuts and vanilla. 4: Stir mixture until it begins to look grainy. 5: Turn out onto wax paper and separate nuts to cool entirely. 6: Will keep in covered containers in refrigerator but do not freeze. 7: **Does not work well on Brazil nuts. Coating does not stick. 8: *I have used up to 4 cups of nuts per batch with good results.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2600,"Summer Citrus Punch","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Summer Citrus Punch recipe from Food.com.","Punch Beverage",4.0,1.0,231.8,0.4,0.1,0.0,4.7,28.2,1.6,21.7,1.6,"0.0","Summer Citrus Punch Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine first four ingredients in punch bowl. 2: Stir until sugar dissolves. 3: Add 50 ice cubes, orange slices, lemon slices and berries and stir gently to combine. 4: Fill glasses with ice. 5: Ladle punch into glasses and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2601,"Summer Pudding","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Summer Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,85.8,2.5,1.2,5.7,138.4,13.6,0.6,1.7,2.1,"4.0","Summer Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Take a 2 pint pudding basin, or souffle dish. 2: Cut the bread to get the base and  sides of the dish. 3: Put the blackberries and blackcurrants and sugar to taste  into a pan with the water. 4: Simmer gently until almost soft, add the raspberries  and strawberries and cook for a further 3 minutes. 5: Put the mixture in the basin  (reserving 2-3 oz juice). Top with the bread, pressing down firmly. 6: Cover the  basin with a plate or saucer to fit the top exactly. 7: Place a weight on top and  leave in the refrigerator overnight. Turn out on to a serving dish just before  serving. 8: Use the reserved juice to cover any parts of the bread which have been  left white. Serve with whipped cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2602,"Sweet Chicken Curry","PT25M","PT10M","PT35M","This is an adaptation of my mother''s curry recipe.  It produces a delightfully mild (depending on your curry mix) and sweet stew.  This mixture makes enough mild, sweet curry to feed six unashamedfly hungry people, and freezes well.To lose the syrupy/sweet aspect, use plain coconut cream instead of the colada mix.  If you can''t find coconut milk, use some plain yogurt and brown sugar or honey instead.","Chicken Breast",5.0,1.0,114.2,8.1,2.2,35.5,37.2,1.0,0.2,0.3,9.0,"48.0","Sweet Chicken Curry Recipe Instructions:  1: In a pot, brown the meat, onions and garlic in oil (Chicken should be skinned).  Generously sprinkle curry powder on meat (commercial preparations are fine on their own or cut with some homemade). 2: Mix your stock and thickener in a cup. 3: Add stock mixture, coconut milk and cream to the chicken. 4: If you don''t want to break the bank over one meal, forage in your refrigerator for any questionable vegetables you want to use up and start dicing potatoes and throw them in now. 5: Season to taste.  Simmer for at least 10 minutes- thickening your sauce to desired consistency, though feel free to torment your family and/or guests by cooking this for a few hours. 6: Serve with rice, thick pita bread, salad and your fave condiments. 7: Suggested condiments include corn kernels, peanuts (or other nuts), raisins, chopped hard-boiled eggs, sliced banana in lemon or lime juice, sliced cucumber in yoghurt (or in a cream dressing- we like garlic), dried coconut, raisins and other dried fruits, and chutney.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2603,"Beef Burgers With Orange Barbecued Sauce","PT30M","PT0S","PT30M","Make and share this Beef Burgers With Orange Barbecued Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Very Low Carbs",0.0,0.0,495.9,26.9,9.6,32.1,817.2,62.9,8.4,36.9,7.8,"0.0","Beef Burgers With Orange Barbecued Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown the burgers and saute the onion gently in the oil. 2: Place in a casserole.  Make a roux with the butter and flour, add the orange juice, rind, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and tomato paste.  Cook well, stir in the tomatoes and season well. 3: Pour into the casserole and cook at 160 C 30 - 40 minutes. 4: Taste and adjust seasonings before serving. 5: Serve with baked potatoes and green salad with slices of orange. Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 6: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2604,"Sweet Sour Sauce Secrets","PT5M","PT5M","PT10M","With a little imagination, and some courage, the quest for unique sweet sour sauce can be fulfilled with this simple formula. First thing to try to appreciate is that cooking is a creative sport. SO... Here is a formula that will lead to your own Great Sweet Sour Sauce.","< 15 Mins",5.0,10.0,277.9,0.2,0.0,0.0,685.0,69.1,0.2,67.0,1.1,"0.0","Sweet Sour Sauce Secrets Recipe Instructions:  1: The point is that as long as you stick to the basic idea of tomato/sweetener/vinegar/sweet liquid -- 2: You can Create your own Sweet Sour Sauce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2605,"Taco Seasoning Mix","0","PT5M","PT5M","Make and share this Taco Seasoning Mix recipe from Food.com.","Mexican",5.0,288.0,29.0,0.7,0.1,0.0,2372.5,6.0,1.5,1.5,0.9,"0.0","Taco Seasoning Mix Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl and blend well. 2: Spoon mixture onto a 6-inch square of aluminum foil and fold to make airtight. Label as Taco Seasoning Mix. 3: Store in a cool, dry place and use within 6 months. 4: Makes 1 package (about 2 T) of mix. 5: Using the above recipe as a guide you can increase the amounts to make any number of packages. 6: Taco Filling: Brown 1 lb lean ground beef in a medium skillet over medium-high heat; drain the excess grease. Add 1/2 cup water and the seasoning mix. 7: Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. 8: Makes filling for 8 to 10 tacos. 9: Hope this is what you are looking for.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2606,"Taffy Apple Salad 11","PT1H","PT25M","PT1H25M","Make and share this Taffy Apple Salad 11 recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",5.0,1.0,3237.0,171.8,66.2,211.5,255.7,398.4,36.9,310.5,71.8,"0.0","Taffy Apple Salad 11 Recipe Instructions:  1: This takes two days to prepare. 2: First day: 3: Drain the pineapple and reserve the juice.  Combine the pineapple  with the marshmallows. 4: Refrigerate overnight. 5: Cook and stir the pineapple juice,  sugar, vinegar, flour, and well beaten egg until thick. 6: Refrigerate mixture. 7: Second day:  Mix cocktail peanuts and diced apples. 8: Add to the two mixtures from the first day. 9: Add Cool Whip.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2607,"Tamarillo Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","This one goes well grilled or roast chicken also good with pork and ham. I leave the five spice out because I don''t like it.","New Zealand",5.0,1.0,483.0,0.4,0.2,0.0,708.4,121.5,0.0,120.1,2.2,"0.0","Tamarillo Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel and chop tamarillos, combine with sugar and water in pan, simmer, covered, about 5 mins. 2: or until tamarillos are soft.  Blend or process mixture; strain. 3: Return mixture to pan, stir in stock, spice, extra water and extra sugar, simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes. 4: Freezes well. 5: Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 6: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2608,"Tame Kimchi","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Tame Kimchi recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",3.5,2.0,76.9,4.9,0.4,0.0,4757.2,7.9,1.8,4.0,1.6,"6.0","Tame Kimchi Recipe Instructions:  1: In large bowl, combine the red onion, carrots, cabbage, and salt. Add just  enough water to cover the vegetables. 2: Let them sit at room temperature  overnight.  The next day, drain the vegetables. 3: Add the remaining ingredients,  and toss well. 4: Chill the salad for at least 1 hour before serving. 5: It will keep  in a sealed container in the refrigerator for up to 7 days. 6: Variation: This kimchi doesn''t undergo a fermenting process, as real kimchi  does. 7: If you''d like to ferment this kimchi, omit the oil, and put the mixture  into a large sterilized jar. 8: Let the kimchi stand at room temperature for 2-4  days, opening the jar once a day to let out the gases that build up. 9: Store the  kimchi in the refrigerator after this period. 10: It will keep for several weeks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2609,"Tangerine Creme Brulee","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Tangerine Creme Brulee recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,2.0,612.5,49.3,29.6,355.6,64.2,39.4,0.8,34.2,5.5,"0.0","Tangerine Creme Brulee Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat the cream and half n half just to the simmer. 2: Remove the zest from the tangerine and place it in the cream. 3: Let it steep for about 1/2 hour. 4: Squeeze in about 1 tablespoon of the juice. Beat the egg yolks until light and pour the hot cream over them whisking the entire time.  Add the vanilla and strain the mixture though a fine sieve. Fill ramekins with the mixture, place them in a large baking dish and fill the dish with hot water to a depth of 1 inch. 5: Bake for about 40 minutes at 300 degrees or until the custards are set. They will continue cooking after you remove them, so they can still have a small amount of movement in the center. 6: Chill completely. 7: Sift the brown sugar and place a light coating over each ramekin. 8: Either place under your broiler or, in my case, I use my propane torch until the sugar has melted. 9: *  I usually halve this recipe since we are two. 10: If a make it any larger than this recipe (which really only serves 6 with my size ramekins) I will add an extra yolk.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2610,"Taste of Home Chunky Blond Brownies","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Taste of Home Chunky Blond Brownies recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",5.0,3.0,233.8,11.9,5.9,27.4,112.2,30.0,1.2,22.3,2.5,"0.0","Taste of Home Chunky Blond Brownies Recipe Instructions:  1: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars. 2: Add the eggs and vanilla: mix well. 3: Combine flour, baking powder and salt: add to creamed mixture and mix well. 4: Stir in vanilla chips, chocolate chunks and 1/2 cup nuts. 5: Spoon into a greased 13 in by 9 in by 2 in pan,  spread to evenly cover bottom of pan. 6: Sprinkle with remaining nuts. 7: Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown. 8: cool on wire rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2611,"Teriyaki Chicken W/pecans","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Teriyaki Chicken W/pecans recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",3.0,2.0,487.1,36.1,7.4,126.8,1140.8,10.5,2.2,4.7,30.4,"0.0","Teriyaki Chicken W/pecans Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine teriyaki sauce, ginger and garlic powder. 2: Pour into large plastic bag with chicken pieces. 3: Press air out, tie top securely. 4: Turn over several times to coat chicken pieces. 5: Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.  Remove chicken, reserving marinade. Combine egg and 2 tablespoons of reserved marinade, set aside. Combine pecans and flour on large plate. Dip chicken pieces into egg mixture, then roll in pecan mixture, coating all sides. 6: Place chicken pieces, skin side up, on rack placed in large baking pan. 7: Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes, or until chicken is tender. 8: Cool slightly, then serve. Or, chill in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight. Wrap in foil, and transport packed in ice cooler to your picnic! Yields 8 servings.");
