INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2635,"Walnut Creme Pie","PT10M","PT25M","PT35M","GRANDMA DUNKIN''S WALNUT CREME PIE (In Memory Of Lucy Dunkin).  It is also lovely topped with meringue.","Pie",0.0,0.0,349.2,15.5,4.2,8.5,166.0,49.9,0.9,34.5,4.7,"0.0","Walnut Creme Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375°F. 2: Line pie pan with prepared pie crust, prick bottom evenly with a fork to prevent bubbling up and bake for 20- 25 minutes, checking occasionally to make sure it''s browning evenly. 3: Filling: Whisk sugar, flour, and milk together in a large saucepan. 4: Add egg yolks and walnuts. 5: Bring mixture to a simmer over medium heat, whisking regularly, 8- 10 minutes, until thickened. 6: Pour into baked pie shell.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2636,"West Indian Bread Pudding","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this West Indian Bread Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,1.0,458.2,4.9,1.1,1.0,838.3,87.2,4.5,17.3,16.2,"9.0","West Indian Bread Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine the bread cubes and raisins. 2: In a separate bowl, combine the remaining ingredients, and pour over the bread cubes. 3: Stir gently to mix, and let the mixture sit for 10 minutes. 4: Coat a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray. 5: Spread the bread mixture evenly in the dish, and bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 60 minutes, or until a sharp knife inserted in the center comes out clean. 6: Let stand for 10 minutes. 7: Serve warm, and refrigerate any leftovers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2637,"White Bread or Rolls","PT50M","PT30M","PT1H20M","Make and share this White Bread or Rolls recipe from Food.com.","Yeast Breads",4.5,5.0,2458.3,57.1,13.7,0.0,5840.9,424.3,16.7,39.1,56.5,"1.0","White Bread or Rolls Recipe Instructions:  1: Sprinkle yeast in 1/4 cup warm water with a pinch of sugar. 2: Let rest 5 minutes. 3: Mix in remaining ingredients and 1/2 the flour. 4: Beat well with wooden spoon, slowly stir in remaining flour.  (When adding flour I start with a full cup, as the dough takes shape I only add a 1/2 cup at a time.  Too much flour at once can make for very dry tough bread.) 5: Knead 8 minutes and add more flour if sticky. 6: Let rise until double in bulk (about 2 hour). Punch down. 7: Let rest 5 minutes. 8: Shape into loaves or rolls and place in 2 greased medium (8.5 inch x 4.5 inch) bread pans or 2 round 8\ 9: Let raise until double in bulk (about 1 hour). Bake at 350''F 35 for rolls or 45-50 minutes for bread. 10: Brush crust with butter while still warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2638,"Whole Wheat Pizza Dough & Pizza Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Whole Wheat Pizza Dough & Pizza Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Sauces",4.0,5.0,1753.4,47.7,6.6,0.0,5118.1,299.5,35.2,59.2,51.5,"0.0","Whole Wheat Pizza Dough & Pizza Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water. 2: Let stand 5 minutes Stir in oil, flours  and salt with bread hooks on mixer. 3: Add about 1 cup additional unbleached flour. 4: Work into dough. 5: Grease pan and sprinkle with cornmeal Let raise 1 hour. 6: Top  with Sauce and bake at 450. 7: Pizza Sauce: Saute onions in oil until onions are clear. Add remaining ingredients. 8: Simmer  for 10- 20 minutes. 9: Top your pizza Enjoy Barbara");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2639,"Wild Mushroom Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Wild Mushroom Pie recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,387.1,29.1,17.5,160.2,398.0,19.3,1.0,1.3,13.3,"8.0","Wild Mushroom Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: FOR CRUST: 2: Mix flour and salt in medium bowl. 3: Add butter and rub with fingertips until mixture forms coarse meal. 4: Mix in enough water by Tbsp to form moist clumps. 5: Gather dough into ball; flatten into disk. 6: Wrap in plastic and chill until firm, about 45 minutes. 7: (Can be prepared 2 days ahead; keep refrigerated.) Roll out dough on lightly floured surface to 13-inch round. 8: Transfer to 9-inch glass pie plate; crimp edges. 9: Refrigerate 30 minutes. 10: Preheat oven to 375 F. 11: Line pie crust with foil. 12: Fill with dried beans or pie weights. 13: Bake 10 minutes. 14: Remove foil and beans. 15: Bake until crust is set and begins to color, piercing bottom with fork if puffy, about 15 minutes more. Transfer to rack and cool. 16: FOR FILLING: Place porcini in small bowl. 17: Add enough hot water to cover. 18: Let soak 30 minutes. 19: Drain mushrooms. 20: Melt butter in heavy large skillet over high heat. Add shallots and garlic and saute 1 minute. Add fresh mushrooms and saute until tender and liquids evaporate, about 5 minutes. 21: Add porcini and saute 2 minutes. 22: Season to taste with salt and pepper. 23: Set aside. Whisk eggs, half and half, basil and thyme in medium bowl until blended. 24: Season with salt and pepper. 25: Sprinkle half of cheese on crust. Top with mushroom mixture and remaining cheese. Carefully pour egg mixture over mushrooms. 26: Bake until center is set, about 40 minutes. 27: Transfer to rack and cool slightly. 28: Garnish with parsley. 29: Cut into wedges and serve. NOTE: such as crimini, chanterelles and/or stemmed Shiitake, thickly sliced");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2640,"Yeast Biscuits","PT12M","PT2H","PT2H12M","These biscuits work every time and are really good for making ham biscuits or other ''sandwiches''. They hold up well and yet are tender with a wonderful flavor. Prep time includes rest time.","Yeast Breads",5.0,64.0,142.5,6.8,1.7,0.6,224.3,17.6,0.7,2.4,2.8,"16.0","Yeast Biscuits Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve yeast in water, set aside. 2: Mix dry ingredients in order given; cut in  shortening until the size of small Lima beans. 3: Stir in buttermilk and yeast mixture. 4: Cover bowl with towel and let sit until ready to use. (At least 1 hour, but it is fine if it sits for a couple hours.) Dough will be very sticky. 5: Scrape out onto well floured board. 6: Flip over and knead lightly (4-6 times). 7: Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter. 8: Place on greased pan and let raise slightly (10-30  minutes). 9: Bake at 400 F until light brown, 10-12 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2641,"Yoghurt Wholemeal Scones","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Yoghurt Wholemeal Scones recipe from Food.com.","Scones",4.0,3.0,1038.6,30.7,8.3,19.9,2018.0,170.3,24.0,8.1,35.1,"1.0","Yoghurt Wholemeal Scones Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix together flour, salt, and baking powder..Rub in margarine. Form into a stiff dough with the yoghurt. Turn onto a floured board and shape with the hands until 2 cm/3/4 inch thick. 2: Cut into rounds with a pastry cutter. 3: Place on a lightly greased baking tray and bake in a moderately hot oven,Gas 6, 400 F, 200 C, for 10 to 12 minutes. 4: Serve hot with butter.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2642,"Nanna''s Yorkshire Pudding","PT20M","PT5M","PT25M","These are my nanna''s and mother''s Yorkshire pudding recipes. I guess the problem with traditional recipes is that they are seldom very accurate. This does not  produce a &quot;popover&quot; style Yorkshire pudding like I have found in North American  restaurants. The result of the recipes below is the more traditional  style--slightly eggy, and &quot;fallen.&quot; My siblings and I MUCH prefer it this way.  Batter resting time not included in preparation time.","European",5.0,7.0,127.5,8.0,3.8,81.3,43.5,9.2,0.3,0.1,4.4,"6.0","Nanna''s Yorkshire Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: In a bowl combine flour and salt. 2: With a handheld mixer add the milk, in a stream, until smooth. 3: Add water and eggs and beat until combined well and bubbly. 4: Let stand, covered, at room temperature for 1 hour. 5: Preheat oven to 450°F 6: Divide drippings among six muffin pan cups. 7: Heat the cups in the oven until almost smoking. 8: Beat batter until bubbly and divide among muffin cups. 9: Bake 10 minutes in lower third of the oven without opening the oven door. 10: Reduce oven temperature to 350 degrees F and continue to bake for another 10 minutes until puffed, crisp and golden brown. 11: Serve immediately. 12: MUM''S YORKSHIRE PUDDING 1 cup flour 1 cup milk 2 eggs salt & pepper Put fat from roast into glass pie plate or use vegetable oil. (Be generous.) Mix listed ingredients together. Cook in 450F oven for 25 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2643,"Yummy Vegetable Fritters","PT15M","PT15M","PT30M","Make and share this Yummy Vegetable Fritters recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",4.0,2.0,596.6,3.7,0.8,0.0,420.6,132.2,22.7,29.0,19.8,"0.0","Yummy Vegetable Fritters Recipe Instructions:  1: Batter:- 3 eggs 1 Tbsp flour 1 tsp baking powder oil for frying Squeeze all the excess moisture from the grated vegetables. 2: Mix together well the vegetables, herbs and spices. 3: Lightly beat the eggs and mix in the flour and baking powder. 4: Stir into the vegetables and let stand 30 minutes. 5: If there is any excess liquid on top, scoop it off with a spoon. 6: Heat oil in a frypan (about 1 Tbs) add large spoonfuls of the fritter mixture, allowing enough space to expand. 7: Don''t flatten the fritters. 8: Cover with a lid and cook around 10 minutes over a medium heat.  Turn and cook the other side, until golden. 9: Drain on absorbent paper. 10: Serve with chutneys of your favourite sauce. Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 11: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2644,"Zesty Beef and Bean Wedges","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Zesty Beef and Bean Wedges recipe from Food.com.","Beans",5.0,1.0,290.9,22.7,8.7,80.5,77.0,0.8,0.2,0.2,19.6,"4.0","Zesty Beef and Bean Wedges Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 375. 2: Combine beef, beans, mix, juice and pepper in large bowl,  mixing lightly but thoroughly. 3: Spread mixture evenly in 12-: pizza pan. 4: (Recipe can be prepared in a 13 x 9\ 5: ,  6: ,  7: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2645,"Zucchini Bars","PT25M","PT10M","PT35M","This time of year it seems we all have extra-large zucchini, which makes great bread and stuff.  Here is a recipe to help you that is yummy for bars.  Hope you enjoy!","Bar Cookie",5.0,28.0,599.7,29.8,4.7,60.7,541.2,79.4,0.9,58.5,5.1,"0.0","Zucchini Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F and grease/flour a 13x9-inch baking pan. 2: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil. 3: Add the zucchini and vanilla; stir to mix well. 4: Sift the dry ingredients together and add to the egg mixture. 5: Pour batter into prepared pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until done. 6: While the bars are baking, whip the butter and cream cheese until light; add vanilla and powdered sugar. 7: Beat until fluffy, adding a *little* milk as needed if frosting is too thick. 8: Spread frosting on top of the bars when they are cooled.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2646,"Zucchini Pizza","PT20M","PT15M","PT35M","Make and share this Zucchini Pizza recipe from Food.com.","< 60 Mins",4.0,1.0,93.3,6.4,3.8,22.4,180.6,2.4,0.6,1.2,6.8,"8.0","Zucchini Pizza Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare your dough ( use my  dough recipes from my web page or from Dave''s recipe archives) Place dough to fit 12 inch pan. 2: Brush dough with olive oil, mince over garlic.  Lay on sliced tomato, sprinkle on spices. Scatter on zucchini evenly. 3: Sprinkle on cheeses. 4: Bake in a hot oven (400-425°F) about 20 minutes or until dough is  done and cheese has melted.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2647,"Apple and Cheddar Corn Muffins","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apple and Cheddar Corn Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",4.5,3.0,206.6,8.0,1.1,47.6,143.4,29.2,1.9,9.8,5.3,"12.0","Apple and Cheddar Corn Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400. 2: Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups. 3: In large  bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, and baking powder. 4: Add apples, corn, cheese,  sugar, cinnamon, nutmg, stir to combine.  In small bowl, beat eggs and oil; stir into flour mixture (don''t over beat...the mixture will be stiff).  Fill baking  cups and bake for 15 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2649,"Hot Jalapeno Pepper Jelly","PT20M","PT30M","PT50M","Make and share this Hot Jalapeno Pepper Jelly recipe from Food.com.","Jellies",5.0,25.0,51.6,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.3,13.2,0.0,13.1,0.0,"80.0","Hot Jalapeno Pepper Jelly Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash hot peppers, cut off stem and halve the peppers, remove membrane and seeds. 2: Put peppers in food processor and process off and on a couple of times until the peppers are coarsely chopped. 3: In a medium saucepan combine peppers, cranberry  juice, and vinegar. 4: Bring to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer for about  10 minutes. 5: In a 4 quart pot combine the pepper mixture and sugar. 6: Bring to  a full rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly. 7: Stir in pectin. 8: Return to a full rolling boil; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. 9: Remove  from heat and quickly skim off foam with a metal spoon. 10: Pour at once into hot,  sterilized half-pint jars, leaving a 1/4\ 11: ,  12: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2650,"Hot Pizza Dip","PT10M","PT10M","PT20M","Make and share this Hot Pizza Dip recipe from Food.com.","< 30 Mins",5.0,47.0,202.5,16.8,9.8,55.2,309.8,3.5,0.5,1.7,9.6,"10.0","Hot Pizza Dip Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine cream cheese and seasonings. 2: Spread  in the bottom of a 9 inch pie  plate. (I used a round cake pan). Combine  cheeses and sprinkle half over the  cream cheese layer. 3: Spread sauce over  that. Sprinkle remaining cheese on  top.Bake 350 for 20 minutes. 4: Serve  warm with breadsticks or tortilla chips. 5: (I  used pita triangles).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2651,"How to Toast Pecans","PT5M","PT1M","PT6M","Make and share this How to Toast Pecans recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,10.0,753.2,78.5,6.7,0.0,0.0,15.1,10.5,4.3,10.0,"0.0","How to Toast Pecans Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Lightly spritz baking sheet with cooking spray. 3: To toast pecans, put them on a baking sheet and toast them just until they become aromatic, about 5 minutes. 4: You have to watch them carefully as they are easily scorched.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2652,"Kidney With Spring Onions &amp; Cauliflower","PT15M","PT20M","PT35M","Make and share this Kidney With Spring Onions &amp; Cauliflower recipe from Food.com.","Beef Organ Meats",0.0,0.0,125.9,7.1,0.9,0.0,857.3,8.2,1.9,3.1,2.2,"4.0","Kidney With Spring Onions &amp; Cauliflower Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash and core the kidneys, slice them thinly and soak in the sherry. 2: Break the cauliflower into very small florets and cook in salted boiling water 3 minutes. 3: Drain. 4: Cut the spring onions into 2 1/2cm lengths. 5: Heat the oil and fry the kidneys and onions with the cauliflower for 2 minutes. 6: Mix the cornflour to a smooth paste with the soy sauce, 2 Tbsp water, sugar, the remaining sherry and salt.  Add to the pan and cook gently 3 minutes, stirring all the time.  Serve immediately. 7: Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui,  New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2653,"Kumara and Red Lentil Soup","PT30M","PT15M","PT45M","Make and share this Kumara and Red Lentil Soup recipe from Food.com.","Lentil",5.0,3.0,1505.4,19.0,2.8,1.2,3784.4,278.5,45.4,36.4,64.4,"0.0","Kumara and Red Lentil Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oil in pan, add onion, coriander and cumin; cook, stirring, until onion is  soft.  Add kumara, lentils, water and crumbled stock cubes. 2: Bring to the boil  and simmer, covered, for about 30 minutes or until kumara is tender. 3: Blend  soup, in batches, until pureed. 4: Return to pan, stir over heat until heat until  hot.  Stir in soy sauce.  Serve with a dollop of sour cream or yoghurt. 5: Cheers,  Doreen. Doreen Randal,  Wanganui, New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2654,"Lamb Chops with Mandarins","PT35M","PT10M","PT45M","I have cheated making this and used canned mandarins, must admit though, if you have enough of the fruit it''s nicer.","Lamb/Sheep",4.0,1.0,36.5,0.1,0.0,0.0,1.6,5.4,0.4,4.0,0.3,"6.0","Lamb Chops with Mandarins Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim the chops so the are neat and free from any excess fat. Roll the tails up so the chops make a round, if necessary secure with a toothpick. 2: In a large pan, heat just enough butter to cover the bottom of the pan and brown the chops on both sides. 3: Season lightly with salt and pepper. 4: Add the wine and mandarin juice.  Cover, lower heat and simmer until the meat is quite tender--About 30 mins. 5: When it is cooked, lift the meat on to a serving plate and keep warm. 6: Mix the cornflour and water to a smooth paste and stir into the pan juices. 7: Cook quickly with regular stirring until they thicken slightly. 8: Add the mandarin segments to the sauce and cook about 1 minute.  Pour the sauce over the chops and garnish with parsley. 9: Serves 6. 10: N.B.---- To make mandarin juice, crush mandarin segments and strain the juice from them. 11: Cheers, Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 12: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2655,"Lavash Armenian Thin Bread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lavash Armenian Thin Bread recipe from Food.com.","Breads",5.0,4.0,1272.6,32.0,5.5,8.5,2367.7,214.0,7.7,19.5,29.3,"0.0","Lavash Armenian Thin Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Place the tepid water in your electric mixing bowl and add the olive oil, sugar, and yeast. Using the batter blade let the electric mixer blend these very well. 2: It will take about 5 minutes on low speed. 3: Stir in the salt. Gradually add 2  cups of the flour and beat on low speed until a thick and smooth batter forms. 4: Change the blade to a bread dough hook and knead in the additional 2 cups of  flour. 5: If you do not have a heavy mixer such as a KitchenAid, incorporate the  flour with a wooden spoon and finish the kneading by hand. 6: Kneading should take  about 10 minutes in the machine, 20 minutes by hand. 7: Place the dough on a plastic countertop and cover with a large stainless-steel  bowl. 8: Allow the dough to rise until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours. 9: Punch the dough down and divide into 8 pieces. 10: Let stand, covered, 15 minutes. 11: Roll out  each piece of dough into a 12-inch-diameter circle. Working with 2 pieces of  dough at a time, arrange breads on ungreased baking sheets. 12: Brush with milk and  sprinkle sesame seeds over tops. 13: Pierce with a fork many times, all over. 14: Bake on the lowest racks in the oven, at 375F, for 8-10 minutes, or until light brown. 15: Rotate the pans in the oven from top to bottom, to insure even browning. 16: Serve dry or wet. (To wet, hold the cracker under running water until lightly  moistened all over, and then wrap in a moist towel for 10-15 minutes.) If the  cracker is too dry to roll, it will crack. 17: Sprinkle with a little more water and let stand a few minutes. 18: If it is too wet, cover with a dry towel and let it  stand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2656,"Layered Berry Parfaits","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Layered Berry Parfaits recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,694.3,22.8,5.6,0.0,351.9,114.2,10.0,21.6,6.9,"4.0","Layered Berry Parfaits Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large bowl, combine blueberries, strawberries, currants, blackberries, and wine or apple juice. Let stand for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. 2: Meanwhile, puree raspberries and syrup in a blender or food processor until smooth. 3: To assemble dessert, spoon a layer of mixed berries into the bottom of 4 parfait glasses or wine glasses. 4: Top with a drizzle of raspberry puree, then vanilla wafer crumbs. 5: Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with a drizzle of raspberry puree.  Garnish each serving with a sprig of mint. If desired, chill parfaits for 1 hour before serving. 6: Variation: Substitute any other fresh berries for those listed above.  Helpful Hint: You may substitute frozen berries for fresh, if desired, but frozen berries will exude more juice than fresh berries.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2657,"Lemon Chicken and Potatoes with Garlic Sour Cream","0","PT0S","PT0S","This is a chicken substitution for a similar lamb dish we tried in a  Greek restaurant in Toronto a few years back.","Chicken Breast",3.0,2.0,438.4,27.6,9.5,100.8,167.1,21.9,2.2,2.0,25.6,"8.0","Lemon Chicken and Potatoes with Garlic Sour Cream Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, threebe, salt and pepper well & let stand 10 minutes; pour over chicken. 2: Let Marinade 1-1/2 hours refrigerated. 3: Bake at 400F for ~ 1 hour or until done. Serve with potatoes. 4: Arrange potatoes in glass baking dish (multiple layers). 5: Pour mixture of stock, lemon juice, garlic, threebe, salt and pepper over potatoes & bake at 400F until slightly golden brown on  top 6: Fold garlic into sour Cream Cover and let stand 1 hour refrigerated. 7: Serve as a dip/accompaniment for potatoes");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2658,"Lemon Jello Cake","PT35M","PT10M","PT45M","Make and share this Lemon Jello Cake recipe from Food.com.","Gelatin",5.0,28.0,456.9,22.2,4.3,68.0,362.1,61.2,0.5,44.9,4.6,"0.0","Lemon Jello Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix cake ingredients together for 4 minutes. 2: Bake in metal non stick 9x13 inch pan @350 for 40 minutes. 3: or,if using a glass baking dish bake @325 for 45 minutes. 4: Poke holes all over the cake while hot. 5: Mix together icing: powdered sugar and lemons (grated rind and juices). 6: Pour this over the cake immediately, while it is still hot from the oven. 7: Serve warm or cold.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2659,"Lemon Sherbet","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lemon Sherbet recipe from Food.com.","Frozen Desserts",0.0,0.0,1475.8,1.2,0.2,0.0,78.4,383.2,5.6,360.0,6.4,"0.0","Lemon Sherbet Recipe Instructions:  1: In a saucepan combine the sugar, the rind, and 2 cups water, bring the mixture to a boil, stirring until the sugar is dissolved, and simmer the syrup for 5 minutes. 2: Let the syrup cool, strain it into a bowl, and stir in the lemon juice. Chill the syrup, covered, for 2 hours, or until it is cold. 3: (The syrup may be made up to one day in advance and kept covered and chilled.)  Freeze the syrup in an ice cream freezer according to the manufacturer''s instructions until it is almost frozen but still mushy. 4: In a bowl beat the egg white until it holds soft peaks, add it to the sherbet, and freeze the sherbet again in the ice-cream freezer until it is frozen but not firm. 5: Remove the dasher and freeze the sherbet, covered, until it is firm. 6: (The sherbet may be made up to 3 days in advance and kept covered tightly and frozen.)  Yield: 1 quart");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2660,"Refreshing Lemon Sorbet","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Refreshing Lemon Sorbet recipe from Food.com.","Frozen Desserts",4.5,3.0,181.5,0.1,0.0,0.0,19.0,46.3,0.1,44.6,1.0,"4.0","Refreshing Lemon Sorbet Recipe Instructions:  1: Place the lemon rind in a large saucepan with the sugar and water. 2: Dissolve the sugar slowly, then bring to the boil and boil for 10 minutes. 3: Remove the saucepan from the heat and allow the syrup to cool completely. 4: Add the strained lemon juice, mix and pour into a suitable container. 5: Cover and place in the freezer until the mixture is thick and slushy. 6: Beat the egg white until stiff and fold into the mixture.  Return the mixture to the freezer and freeze until stiff. 7: Remove the sorbet from the freezer 10 minutes before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2661,"Lemonade Cake #3","PT40M","PT25M","PT1H5M","Adopted recipe. I have made this once and it didn''t turn out as it had been written so I have changed a few things. Be sure to grease and flour your pan very well. I have changed the glazing step to hopefully prevent the cake from sticking in the pan. If your cake mix calls for more than 1/4 cup applesauce as the substitution for oil, by all means do that. The cake mix I used only called for 1/4 cup so that is how I rewrote this. I hope the tweaks fix the problems and that you like it!","Dessert",0.0,1.0,286.7,7.8,1.5,75.4,406.2,49.0,0.6,29.5,5.4,"10.0","Lemonade Cake #3 Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: Grease and flour a Bundt pan. 3: Dissolve Jello in hot water and set aside to cool. 4: DO NOT  JELL. 5: In a large bowl, mix cake mix, eggs and applesauce. 6: Add cooled Jello. 7: Beat until well mixed. 8: Turn into Bundt pan. 9: Bake 40-45 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. 10: Meanwhile: Mix lemonade concentrate and sugar and let  set,optional. 11: While cake is still warm, loosen it from edges of pan. 12: When completely cooled, turn out onto serving plate. 13: You can top with the lemonade concentrate glaze or Cool Whip or just dust with the powdered sugar.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2662,"Banana Rice Pudding Served with a Raspberry Coulis","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Banana Rice Pudding Served with a Raspberry Coulis recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,1.0,1073.4,23.6,12.7,75.3,150.8,211.2,34.0,126.5,17.5,"1.0","Banana Rice Pudding Served with a Raspberry Coulis Recipe Instructions:  1: Place milk into saucepan with vanilla pod, bring to the boil. 2: Pour in  rice and sugar and stir. 3: Add a pinch of cinnamon. 4: Grease an ovenproof dish and pour in  rice pudding then grease a small  circle of greaseproof paper (this will stop a  skin from forming).  Put in a preheated oven 160C for 2 hours. 5: Raspberry sauce: Place raspberries in a food processor with the icing sugar and blend to a smooth pouring consistency. 6: Strain the sauce to remove the seeds and put aside.  Take  the pudding out of the oven and mix in the creme fraiche.  Mash the  banana and  mix with the pudding. 7: Add honey and crushed nuts and mix. 8: Then pack pudding  into a ramekin dish, sprinkle the top with brown sugar  and place under the  grill. 9: Place ramekin on to a plate and decorate with the sauce.  Garnish with   fresh sprigs of mint.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2663,"Lomo de Cerdo","0","PT0S","PT0S","In my recipe book, The Complete Spanish Cookbook, by Jacki Passmore, there is a recipe for  LOMO DE CERDA, Loin of Pork.  It is a substantial tapa, or snack which is served in a small pottery dish with a sliced roll to mop up the juices.  Here is the recipe she gives:","Lunch/Snacks",4.5,3.0,128.6,8.3,1.4,24.6,29.8,5.1,1.3,2.5,8.7,"6.0","Lomo de Cerdo Recipe Instructions:  1: Remove the rind from the pork(if there is one)  Brown the pork in the olive oil, then brown the carrot and onion. 2: Place in a saucepan with the bay leaves,  garlic, tomatoes, peppercorns and rosemary. 3: Add water to cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, adding the vinegar in the final few minutes of cooking. 4: Lift out and thinly slice the pork. 5: Place in a dish with the vegetables and sauce to cover.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2664,"Louisiana Grilled Shrimp with Grits Cakes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Louisiana Grilled Shrimp with Grits Cakes recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,7623.3,186.1,100.8,486.9,3928.8,1326.0,33.1,202.4,206.5,"0.0","Louisiana Grilled Shrimp with Grits Cakes Recipe Instructions:  1: For the Grit Cakes: Roast one poblano pepper over open flame on  gas stove until completely charred, then cool and dice. Add pepper  and cheese to grits. 2: Stir to incorporate and spread in pan  approximately 2 to 3 inches thick. 3: Let sit and refrigerate until it is  cold. 4: Remove from refrigerator and cut with biscuit cutter to create  cakes. 5: Bread the cakes in flour, egg wash and bread crumbs. 6: Keep  in refrigerator until you are ready to cook the dish. 7: For the Pepper Jelly: Saute diced red peppers and remaining 1  poblano in 1 tablespoon peanut oil for 1 minute. Deglaze with  Grand Marnier and add Karo syrup. 8: Cook at moderate heat  approximately 20 minutes, liquid should reduce by 2/3. 9: Remove  from heat and cool slightly. 10: For the Rouille: Combine anchovies, capers, pepper sauce, garlic  and lemon juice in a blender until smooth. 11: Fold in mayonnaise and  refrigerate. For plating: Deep fry the cakes. 12: Place Pepper Jelly on the bottom  of the plate. Grill shrimp only until firm and pink. 13: Do not overcook. 14: Briefly place fried cake on grill to score and flavor, being careful not  to burn breading. 15: Place cake on Pepper Jelly and top with 2 shrimp  per person. 16: Drizzle Rouille on top and sprinkle with scallions. 17: Options: Top the cake with a teaspoon of salmon caviar, which will  add texture and richness.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2665,"Louisiana Turkey Pepper Links","0","PT0S","PT0S","This colorful grilling sausage makes a nice change from pork sausages. For the best flavor and texture, we do not recommend freezing this sausage.","Poultry",0.0,0.0,896.1,49.2,16.4,322.2,581.7,22.1,1.7,4.0,85.5,"0.0","Louisiana Turkey Pepper Links Recipe Instructions:  1: Have the meat, fat, cream, and milk chilled to near the freezing point, 32 F (0  C). Grind the turkey meat and fat through a 3/16 in. 2: (0.5 cm) plate. Add the  salt, pepper, Cajun spices, bread crumbs, and Prague powder # l to the  force-meat and mix lightly by hand. 3: Using a vertical cutting machine, mix and  finely cut the forcemeat for 4 minutes Alter- natively process by batches in a  food processor.Turn the forcemeat into a tub or mixing machine. Mix in the milk, cream, and stock. 4: Fold in the diced bell peppers and mix until the ingredients  are uniformly blended. 5: Pack into shallow pans, cover, and refrigerate for at  least 1 1/2 hours. 6: Stuff the prepared casings but not too tightly. 7: Tie into 4  in. 8: (10 cm) links. 9: SMOKING Preheat the smoker to 110 F (43 C). Hang the sausages on sticks to dry in the  smoker with the dampers wide open for I hour. 10: When the sausages are uniformly  dry, increase the temperature every 15 minutes until it reaches 160 F (71 C).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2666,"Low-Fat Beef &amp; Lentil Soup (High Fiber)","PT55M","PT10M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Low-Fat Beef &amp; Lentil Soup (High Fiber) recipe from Food.com.","Lentil",4.0,1.0,116.1,2.6,0.4,0.0,699.5,17.6,5.7,3.9,7.5,"4.0","Low-Fat Beef &amp; Lentil Soup (High Fiber) Recipe Instructions:  1: In Dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat until hot. Add onion and garlic; cook and stir 3 to 5 minutes or until tender. 2: Add water, broth, picante sauce and lentils. 3: Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low. 4: Cover tightly and simmer 35 to 45 minutes or until lentils are tender. 5: Meanwhile trim fat from beef steaks. 6: Stack steaks and cut lengthwise in half and then crosswise into 1-inch strips; set aside.  Increase heat to medium; bring to a boil. 7: Stir in beef and escarole. Immediately remove from heat. Cover and let stand 5 minutes before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2667,"Banana Sultana Muffins","PT25M","PT10M","PT35M","Make and share this Banana Sultana Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,1.0,1937.9,18.7,3.2,4.9,2264.9,417.6,19.1,192.8,40.3,"0.0","Banana Sultana Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375F and prepare muffin pans by either lining with cupcake papers or a light spritz with cooking spray. 2: Combine raisins and juice, let stand for 5 minutes. 3: Add buttermilk, egg whites, oil, and honey; whisk until smooth. 4: Sift flour, cornmeal, baking powder, baking soda together; add brown sugar and spices, whisk until mixed. 5: Add bananas and toss lightly. 6: Combine wet and dry ingredients and stir ''just to mix'' (it will be lumpy). 7: Pour into prepared muffin tin, bake for 25 minutes (or until done).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2668,"Low-Fat Potato-Vegetable Chowder","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Low-Fat Potato-Vegetable Chowder recipe from Food.com.","Chowders",5.0,3.0,62.2,0.3,0.1,0.0,606.4,14.0,2.7,4.5,2.1,"8.0","Low-Fat Potato-Vegetable Chowder Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring liquid to boil in a deep soup kettle. Add all vegetables and seasonings. 2: Turn down heat to simmer and partially cover the pot. Simmer until vegetables are tender. 3: Serve hot with crusty whole wheat bread and a light fruit dessert. Variation: Almost any vegetable but onions, tomatoes, and the potatoes can be substituted for another vegetable. Don''t use the cabbage family because the flavor is too radically changed. 4: Green peas and baby lima beans are a great addition, as is 1/2 cup of corn kernels.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2669,"Low-Fat Swiss Muesli","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Low-Fat Swiss Muesli recipe from Food.com.","Swiss",0.0,0.0,225.8,1.6,0.3,0.0,4.6,53.5,6.3,27.0,3.8,"6.0","Low-Fat Swiss Muesli Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine oats, water, shredded apples, prunes, honey, lemon juice and cinnamon. 2: Cover and refrigerate overnight.  In the morning, spoon some of the muesli into  a cereal bowl. 3: Top with your choice of fresh fruits and nuts. 4: Serve with a  dollop of plain yogurt or milk, if desired. 5: Muesli can be stored in covered  container in refrigerator for several days.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2670,"M&amp;M Cookies","PT8M","PT0S","PT8M","Make and share this M&amp;M Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",4.5,16.0,108.0,4.6,2.8,18.3,92.8,15.5,0.3,10.0,1.2,"0.0","M&amp;M Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375°. 2: Mix brown sugar, butter or margarine, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl until blended. 3: Stir in remaining ingredients. 4: Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful about 3\ 5: ,  6: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2671,"Guacamole With Sour Cream","0","PT10M","PT10M","My guacamole is very free-form, but here are the basics:  Figure about 1/2 large avocado per person. I don''t care whether I''m using Haas or regular avocados - some people do. Pick ones that give to mild pressure but are not mushy. If you can''t find any that are ripe, get hard ones and keep them in a paper bag for a couple of days until they ripen.","Fruit",5.0,96.0,227.3,20.4,4.0,6.2,87.3,12.7,8.5,1.9,3.0,"2.0","Guacamole With Sour Cream Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut the avocado in half, scoop out the flesh with a spoon; mash 3/4 of it well and chop the remaining 1/4 coarsely (I do this with the spoon, in the  avocado shell, before scooping the last bit out). 2: Mix it into the mashed portion. 3: Mix all remaining ingredients together. 4: Serve immediately, or cover with plastic wrap, pressing wrap firmly to surface of guacamole (or it will turn  color due to oxidation) and refrigerate up to 4 hours before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2672,"Guacamole -Rancho De Chimayo Dip","0","PT20M","PT20M","Make and share this Guacamole -Rancho De Chimayo Dip recipe from Food.com.","Mexican",0.0,0.0,350.8,30.4,4.4,0.6,624.1,22.2,14.4,3.8,5.0,"0.0","Guacamole -Rancho De Chimayo Dip Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel and mash avocados. 2: Next, add all ingredients. 3: Cover the dip with plastic  wrap until serving time. This will help keep the dip from turning funny colors. 4: If the dip hasn''t been eaten all, recover it with plastic  until later use.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2673,"Half-Time Shredded Beef Sandwiches","PT2H","PT30M","PT2H30M","Make and share this Half-Time Shredded Beef Sandwiches recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",4.5,2.0,321.7,8.5,3.1,117.3,580.1,25.0,2.1,5.9,36.8,"12.0","Half-Time Shredded Beef Sandwiches Recipe Instructions:  1: In Dutch oven, place beef, onion, garlic, salt and pepper. 2: Combine water and tomato paste; pour over beef mixture. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low. 3: Cover tightly and simmer 1 3/4 to 2 hours or until beef is tender. 4: Remove beef from cooking liquid; cool slightly. 5: Meanwhile skim fat from cooking liquid, if necessary. 6: Trim and discard excess fat from cooked beef. 7: Shred beef with 2 forks. 8: In Dutch oven, combine 2 cups cooking liquid, steak sauce, brown sugar and cornstarch mixture. Bring to a boil; cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes or until slightly thickened. 9: Add shredded beef; mix well. 10: Continue to cook until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally. 11: Place equal amounts of beef mixture on bottom half of each bun. 12: Sprinkle with green onions and close with top half of bun. 13: Serve with additional steak sauce, if desired. 14: Makes 12 servings (serving size: 1 sandwich).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2674,"Ham and Cheese Puffs","PT3M","PT10M","PT13M","Make and share this Ham and Cheese Puffs recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",0.0,0.0,200.0,13.3,5.0,82.1,1057.2,6.3,0.1,1.2,13.8,"4.0","Ham and Cheese Puffs Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix the first six ingredients together and spread onto bread rounds. 2: Mix the next four ingredients together; spread over the top of the ham mixture and place on a baking sheet. 3: Preheat broiler; broil until cheese is melted (take caution as this will scorch quickly).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2675,"Baked Fish With Orange","PT30M","PT15M","PT45M","Make and share this Baked Fish With Orange recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",5.0,5.0,379.0,15.1,8.1,92.1,478.0,36.5,2.8,5.9,23.3,"4.0","Baked Fish With Orange Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt the butter in frying pan, add the crumbs, garlic and grated orange rind. 2: Stir until crumbs have absorbed all the butter. 3: Place fish portions in a buttered ovenproof dish, sprinkle with the breadcrumbs, then pour over the orange juice. 4: Bake uncovered for 20-30 minutes in moderate oven.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2676,"Easiest Hamburger Soup","PT1H","PT20M","PT1H20M","Make and share this Easiest Hamburger Soup recipe from Food.com.","Clear Soup",5.0,21.0,476.9,13.5,5.1,76.1,1616.0,60.5,10.1,20.6,32.0,"4.0","Easiest Hamburger Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off fat and add vegetables. 2: Cook 5-10 minutes to soften vegetables. 3: Add tomato juice and soup mix. 4: Let simmer 1 hour.Season as desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2677,"Hard Apple Cider","PT2784H","PT0S","PT2784H","Make and share this Hard Apple Cider recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",5.0,5.0,306.2,0.5,0.1,0.0,14.2,76.7,0.6,72.8,0.5,"0.0","Hard Apple Cider Recipe Instructions:  1: crush and dissolve campden tablets in a cup of warm water and mix well with the FRESH apple juice in your primary fermenter. 2: Let stand over-night. Mix in all other ingredients except yeast making sure everything is dissolved, then sprinkle yeast over top of juice and cover with plastic sheet and ferment 3 to 5 days. 3: Rack (siphon) into secondary fermenter and attach air lock. 4: Rack again in 3 weeks. 5: When all fermentation is finished, rack into a clean vessel and add 2 oz of white sugar and gently stir well. 6: (I usually put the sugar into a bit of water and dissolve it first by boiling it in the microwave) When sugar is well mixed, bottle and age 3 months. 7: This will give you a crisp, carbonated hard cider. 8: * the more sugar you add, the more alcohol you will get, but the longer it will take to ferment. I would recommend from 1/2 to 1 pound per gal/4.5 l and not more than 2 lbs.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2678,"Harvard Beets II","PT20M","PT20M","PT40M","Make and share this Harvard Beets II recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,133.5,2.5,0.6,0.0,243.4,26.4,3.8,21.6,3.3,"0.0","Harvard Beets II Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt shortening on top of double boiler directly over heat. Add flour and let bubble for 3 minutes. 2: Add boiling water slowly and stir until smooth. 3: Add sugar, vinegar, seasonings, spices until blended well. 4: Add beets and let it stand over the boiling water until the whole dish is very hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2679,"Harvest Bean Soup","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Harvest Bean Soup recipe from Food.com.","Beans",0.0,0.0,164.6,4.3,2.3,21.2,736.1,21.0,4.2,1.8,11.0,"6.0","Harvest Bean Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Rinse beans. 2: In a Dutch oven combine beans and enough water to   cover. 3: Bring to boiling. 4: Reduce heat and simmer for 2 minutes. 5: Remove from heat. Cover and let stand for 1 hour, or cover beans with   water and soak over- night.    Drain off the water. 6: Rinse and return the beans to the Dutch   oven. 7: Stir in the 3 1/2 cups water, the bite-size pieces of ham or   sausage, chopped carrots, potato, onion, salt, oregano, sage and   pepper. 8: Bring to boiling. 9: Reduce heat.  Cover and simmer for 2 to 2   1/2 hours or till beans are tender, adding more water, if necessary. 10: Stir the milk into the bean soup. 11: Cook the soup until heated   through, stirring occasionally. 12: Season to taste with salt and pepper.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2680,"Hash Browns Casserole","PT40M","PT10M","PT50M","Make and share this Hash Browns Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",4.5,9.0,1259.3,81.4,34.9,125.2,2381.1,107.5,8.9,9.0,27.4,"4.0","Hash Browns Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Sauté onion, bell peppers and celery in butter until soft. 2: Mix all ingredients  except corn flakes and spread into an oiled baking dish. 3: Top with corn flakes. 4: Bake 40 minutes at 350°F.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2681,"Hash Browns Casserole II","PT1H10M","PT10M","PT1H20M","Make and share this Hash Browns Casserole II recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",4.5,7.0,216.4,3.4,1.8,12.1,361.9,32.4,2.2,3.6,14.6,"8.0","Hash Browns Casserole II Recipe Instructions:  1: Coat a medium saucepan with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot. Add onion, and saute 3 minutes or until tender. 2: Add flour, mustard, and salt; stir well, and cook an additional minute. Remove form heat; gradually add milk and broth, stir in with a wire whisk until blended. 3: Cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly. 4: Remove from heat; add cheeses an pepper, stirring until cheeses melt. Stir in sour cream. 5: Combine cheese mixture and potatoes; stir well. 6: Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2\ 7: ,  8: ,  9: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2682,"Hawaiian Bread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Hawaiian Bread recipe from Food.com.","Yeast Breads",5.0,1.0,3257.5,160.2,76.3,264.4,3079.1,389.1,18.1,86.2,65.7,"0.0","Hawaiian Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Place all ingredients in bread machine on sweet bread setting,  using darker than normal crust setting. 2: Dough will appear dry until  the cream cheese and pineapple become well blended.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2683,"Hawaiian Fruit Dip","0","PT0S","PT0S","This is really flavorful; I have served with pineapple chunks, sliced apples & grapes. I make this with skim milk & low-fat sour cream. I added the food coloring in response to a previous reviewer saying it looked like just vanilla pudding.
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2684,"Hawaiian Papaya Chutney","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Hawaiian Papaya Chutney recipe from Food.com.","Chutneys",0.0,0.0,6368.5,80.6,7.1,0.0,28730.7,1467.0,86.7,1186.4,66.7,"0.0","Hawaiian Papaya Chutney Recipe Instructions:  1: Pare the papayas and cut into pieces. 2: Simmer sugar and vinegar together for about 20 minutes to form a syrup. 3: Add the salt and all other ingredients. 4: Simmer in a heavy kettle, stirring constantly, for about 1 hour, or till papaya is soft and the mixture is as thick as jam. 5: Seal in hot sterilized jars. 6: Let stand for some days before using.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2685,"Baked French Toast","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Baked French Toast recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",5.0,6.0,157.8,3.2,1.1,56.2,341.6,21.7,1.9,8.2,11.0,"4.0","Baked French Toast Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 425. 2: In a food processor or blender, whirl the cottage cheese,  milk, sugar, egg, egg white, and vanilla for about 1 minute or until smooth. 3: Transfer the mixture to a shallow dish, place the bread in it, and let stand for 10 minutes. 4: Spray a baking sheet with cooking spray generously. 5: Place  it in  the preheat oven for about 7 minutes. 6: Remove the baking sheet from the oven, place the bread on it, and bake for 6  minutes. 7: Turn the bread over and bake 5 to 6 minutes longer or until golden  brown. 8: Serve with no sugar added jam.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2686,"Healthy Pumpkin Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","I''ve been experimenting with recipes for a diabetic friend.  This pie is  delicious, sugar-free and cholesterol-free.  I really can''t tell the difference! Enjoy,Robb in Cleveland                        Healthy Pumpkin Pie","Pie",0.0,0.0,395.1,18.7,2.5,0.1,587.6,52.9,1.8,23.2,4.6,"6.0","Healthy Pumpkin Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. 2: Pastry: Mix flour and salt together in medium mixing bowl. 3: Measure oil. 4: Add milk to  oil but do not stir. 5: Add liquid all at once to flour mixture.  Stir lightly  with fork until well-mixed. 6: Press dough into smooth ball. 7: Roll between sheets  of waxed paper and fit into pie plate, or press pastry into pie plate with  fingers. 8: Set aside. Filling: In large mixing bowl, blend pumpkin, salt, spices and sugar substitute until  thoroughly combined. 9: Add egg substitute and whisk together. 10: Add evaporated  milk in three increments, whisking thoroughly after each addition. 11: Pour into  prepared pie shell. 12: Bake 15 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350 degrees F. 13: Bake about 45 minutes longer, until metal knife inserted near center comes out  clean.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2687,"Herbed Pecan Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Herbed Pecan Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",5.0,1.0,1389.4,145.2,23.7,33.3,808.8,10.5,4.8,2.0,19.6,"0.0","Herbed Pecan Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Place cheese in food processor; process, using on/off motion, until finely chopped. 2: Add spinach, pecans, parsley and basil, garlic, and salt; process until evenly chopped. 3: With motor running, gradually add oil; process until mixture is smooth. 4: Serve at room temperature or chilled; or spoon into saucepan and heat, stirring over low heat until hot. 5: Notes: * fresh, firmly packed - washed and dried");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2688,"Herbed Polenta","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Herbed Polenta recipe from Food.com.","European",4.0,2.0,328.1,24.5,6.8,27.1,38.0,25.6,3.0,0.4,3.6,"4.0","Herbed Polenta Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring small pot of water to boil. 2: Add herbs and blanch 5 seconds. 3: Drain. 4: Refresh under cold water and drain. 5: Place herbs and oil in blender and puree. Cover; chill. 6: (Can be made 1 day ahead.) Bring water to boil in heavy medium saucepan over medium heat. Gradually whisk in cornmeal. 7: Cook until thickened, stirring often, about 5 minutes. 8: Add cream. 9: Stir in 1/4 cup herb puree. Season polenta with salt and cayenne. Serves: 4 Source: Bon Appetit Serve With: meats, roasts");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2689,"Homemade Mayonnaise II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Variations: Aioli---add chopped garlic, Basil---chop basil and add, Cilantro---add chopped cilantro and fresh lime juice, Sun-dried Tomato---soak first in hot water; drain, chop and  add, Tartar Sauce---add chopped pickle, onion and roasted red  peppers, Thousand Island---make like Tartar Sauce but add catsup and  hard cooked egg","European",4.0,1.0,2025.1,225.2,32.0,332.0,312.8,3.2,0.2,0.8,5.0,"1.0","Homemade Mayonnaise II Recipe Instructions:  1: (If you use a food processor, you will no doubt have the perfect mayonnaise--a  mixing bowl takes more effort.)  Place all ingredients, except the oil, in the food processor. 2: Start the motor. 3: SLOWLY, drip by drip, add the oil. 4: Once an emulsion starts (it starts to  thicken), you can add the oil more generously. 5: Adjust seasonings--more salt,  pepper, lemon. 6: This will last 5-7 days in the refrigerator.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2690,"Honey Jam Bars","PT30M","PT15M","PT45M","Make and share this Honey Jam Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",5.0,3.0,95.2,3.7,0.9,7.0,36.8,15.1,0.3,8.6,0.9,"30.0","Honey Jam Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream shortening and honey well. 2: Combine dry ingredients and mix into creamed  mixture with egg. 3: Grease a 8-inch square pan. 4: place 1/2 batter in pan. 5: Top with seedless raspberry jam or preserves. 6: Cover with remaining batter. Bake in a 400°F oven about 30 to 35 minutes or until done. Cool completely and cut into bars.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2691,"Honey-Cheddar-Chutney Scones","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Honey-Cheddar-Chutney Scones recipe from Food.com.","Scones",2.0,1.0,84.1,4.6,2.9,12.6,163.7,8.2,0.3,0.7,2.5,"10.0","Honey-Cheddar-Chutney Scones Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. 2: Into large bowl, sift together 3/4 cup flour,  baking powder, baking  soda and salt.  Sift mixture again. 3: Add butter; mix just until crumbly. 4: Add cottage cheese, chutney, Cheddar cheese, honey and 1  tablespoon  buttermilk. 5: Combine briefly, just to mix ingredients. 6: If dough is  too  crumbly, add additional 1 tablespoon buttermilk. 7: Knead only 5 times. 8: (Dough should be soft and satiny.)     Lightly flour board and roll out dough  into 8- by 5-inch rectangle.   Cut into rounds with 2-inch biscuit cutter,  rerolling and cutting scraps. 9: Place on oiled baking sheet.  Bake 7 to 10  minutes, until just golden. 10: Yields 10 to 12 scones. 11: Recipe Source: St. Louis Post-Dispatch - 09-28-1998 By Mary Carroll Alan Hewitt     The UK Recipe Archive recipes on-line in Mastercookand Mealmaster formats. 12: http://recipes.reedsweb.net/");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2692,"Hono Bread - Honokakor","0","PT0S","PT0S","There are many variations of this bread which is often baked on the islands off the West Coast of Sweden.","Yeast Breads",0.0,0.0,127.4,3.0,1.7,7.9,174.2,21.7,1.2,0.6,3.4,"0.0","Hono Bread - Honokakor Recipe Instructions:  1: Crumble the yeast in a mixing bowl. 2: In saucepan, melt the butter and then add the milk. 3: Heat to 99M-0F/37M-0C or lukewarm. 4: Dissolve the yeast in a little of the warm milk. 5: Add the rest of the liquid, syrup, salt, aniseed, fennel, and rye flour to the yeast. Stir together and add the all-purpose flour. 6: Work the dough until smooth and shiny. 7: Cover and let rise for 20 - 30 minutes. 8: Turn the dough out onto a floured surface and knead well. 9: Divide into 8 - 10 sections and roll each section into a smooth ball. 10: Cover and let rise under a baking cloth in a warm room for 25 - 30 minutes. 11: Then, with a rolling pin, roll out large rounds of bread, about 10\ 12: ,  13: ,  14: ,  15: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2693,"Baked Ham With Walnut Peach Sauce","PT1H30M","PT15M","PT1H45M","Make and share this Baked Ham With Walnut Peach Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",0.0,0.0,132.4,3.4,0.2,0.0,73.8,24.5,0.9,15.3,1.9,"12.0","Baked Ham With Walnut Peach Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 325°F. 2: Put the ham in a shallow baking pan. 3: With a sharp knife, score the ham in a diamond design. 4: Add 1 cup of water to the bottom   of  the pan. 5: Cover pan securely with foil and bake for 1 hour. 6: Uncover the   ham and brush with 1/2 cup of peach preserves. 7: Bake uncovered, 30 minutes longer, basting occasionally. 8: Meanwhile make the sauce: In a medium saucepan,  combine the nectar,   chicken broth and cornstarch and stir until smooth. 9: Add  remaining 1/2 cup peach preserves and the brown sugar and bring to a boil,  whisking occasionally. 10: Simmer the sauce until thickened. 11: Add the walnuts and peaches and simmer 1 minute longer. 12: Whisk in the mustard, lemon juice and   salt and pepper to taste.   Serve the ham sliced with the sauce on the side.  From Gourmet, March 1999.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2694,"Jaegerschnitzel","PT20M","PT15M","PT35M","Make and share this Jaegerschnitzel recipe from Food.com.","Veal",5.0,9.0,382.2,18.6,7.0,198.8,427.4,16.4,2.0,4.2,31.0,"4.0","Jaegerschnitzel Recipe Instructions:  1: Preparation of meat:  pound cutlets and rub in salt and pepper. 2: Let stand for about 10 minutes. 3: Dip the cutlets in beaten egg and then in crumbs. 4: Brown in a small amount of oil over a low heat for about 10 minutes on each side.  Preparation of gravy Whilemeat is browning, saute bacon and onions until golden brown. 5: Add tomato paste and mushrooms, and saute over a low heat. Add wine, water and seasonings; let simmer for about 5 minutes. 6: Stir in the sour cream. 7: Pour over Schnitzel.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2696,"Joans Easy Broccoli Soup","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Joans Easy Broccoli Soup recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,433.5,13.3,3.9,12.2,7623.1,19.8,0.3,5.1,59.2,"0.0","Joans Easy Broccoli Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Rinse florets and cover with water Add chopped onion. 2: Cook uncovered until  broccoli is tender. 3: Drain and reserve cooking water. 4: Remove florets/onion to a  large cooking pot.  Add enough stock to cover. 5: Or don''t drain vegetables and use broccoli water and add some chicken bouillon if desired.. 6: With a hand blender,  finely chop broccoli but not puree. Heat well, season to taste. Add the cream if desired. 7: If  extra thickening is desired add pasta. 8: Serves 8 to 10  Garnish soup bowls with dabs of sour cream or a sprinkle of fresh herbs. 9: * Note:  You can use more or less  stock/water making the soup thicker or thinner as desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2697,"Ken''s Hamburgers","PT10M","PT10M","PT20M","Make and share this Ken''s Hamburgers recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.0,5.0,273.2,15.2,6.2,98.2,164.0,1.4,0.1,0.5,30.4,"1.0","Ken''s Hamburgers Recipe Instructions:  1: Allow 1/3 lb. lean ground beef per burger. 2: To each burger, add 1 1/2 teaspoons barbeque sauce and 1/4 teaspoon dehydrated minced onion. 3: Cook on broiler, turning about every 4 minutes. 4: Also great on the grill. 5: Serve with more barbeque sauce, not catsup.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2698,"Kfc Fried Chicken","PT10M","PT15M","PT25M","Notes: MSG stands for MonosodiumGlutamate.  It is a spice, found in your grocery store.  It can be sold as MSG or under the brand name &quot;Accent&quot;.  Some people are extremely allergic to MSG, over 98% of the population is not.  It serves to make flavors stronger, and almost pop right out at you.  This recipe used to call for Fines herbs, but most people have difficulty in obtaining them.  Fines herbs used to be used more frequently many years ago.    Fines herbs was a poultry seasoning.  Since so many people have difficultly in obtaining the herb, it has been removed from the recipe.  If you can access Fines herbs add 2 teaspoons to the flour mixture.","Whole Chicken",5.0,1.0,408.7,23.3,6.7,115.0,1274.7,16.6,0.7,0.1,30.8,"6.0","Kfc Fried Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Cover chicken with mixture of water and salt. Chill in bowl for least 1 hour. 2: Combine herbs, onion powder, seasoned salt, instant chicken broth, and pepper in a blender and mix well. 3: Place this mixture in a bowl. 4: Add the flour to this  bowl. 5: Mix flour and seasonings well. 6: Remove chicken from water, and dip it  into the flour mixture coat well. 7: Place coated pieces on a plate for 5 minutes. 8: Pressure cook 10 psi 10 minutes  Note: Find the Fines Herbs if you can. 9: It makes a great deal of difference. Steve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2699,"KFC Pecan Pie","PT35M","PT10M","PT45M","Make and share this KFC Pecan Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",0.0,0.0,548.5,28.9,9.1,161.3,367.8,69.4,2.2,26.7,7.1,"0.0","KFC Pecan Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 325°-350°F. 2: Mix together the first seven ingredients. 3: Stir in pecan halves. 4: Pour the mixture into an unbaked pie shell Bake 35-40 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2700,"Balkan Spaghetti","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Balkan Spaghetti recipe from Food.com.","Spaghetti",3.5,2.0,1966.0,111.7,27.1,76.0,695.3,198.7,9.5,28.4,44.6,"1.0","Balkan Spaghetti Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook spaghetti until al dente.  Return the spaghetti to the still-hot saucepan  and toss it, with two forks, with a tablespoonful of butter. 2: See that every  strand of spaghetti is coated with the butter. 3: In a small pan, heat the oil and fry the chopped garlic in it for a minute or two, then add the tomato paste, and season with salt and a good grate of black pepper. 4: Take the pan off the heat,  add the yogurt and pour the mixture over the spaghetti.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2701,"Lemonade Cake Trifle","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lemonade Cake Trifle recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,3388.0,31.0,7.4,0.0,5808.0,766.2,25.6,117.8,27.8,"1.0","Lemonade Cake Trifle Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine fruits and reserve a small amount for garnish. 2: Spread approximately 1/2 of cake into bottom of trifle dish. 3: Then place a layer of 1/2 of combined fruits. 4: Follow with a layer 1/2 of pudding. 5: Repeat the cake layer, fruit layer and pudding layer Top with a layer of Cool Whip and garnish with reserved fruit.  Lemonade Cake You will need: 1 - 3 oz pkg lemon Jello 3/4 cup hot tap water 1 lemon cake mix 4 eggs 3/4 cup oil 1 can frozen lemonade concentrate 1 cup sugar Preheat oven to 300. 6: Grease and flour a Bundt pan. 7: Dissolve Jello in hot water  and set aside - DO NOT JELL. 8: In a large bowl, mix next 3 ingredients. 9: Add Jello  and beat together 3 minutes. 10: Turn into Bundt pan. 11: Bake 1 hour or until inserted  knife comes out clean. 12: Meanwhile: While cake is baking mix next 2 ingredients and let sit. While cake is still warn, loosen it from edges of pan but leave cake in pan. 13: Pour lemonade mixture over cake allowing it to run down the sides. 14: Save some lemonade mixture. When you turn your cake out onto your, rack put some wax paper under rack and pour saved lemonade mixture over top of cake. This cake is simply divine.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2702,"Lemony Fish Fillets","PT6M","PT4M","PT10M","Make and share this Lemony Fish Fillets recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",3.0,1.0,152.5,2.0,0.5,78.2,133.4,0.9,0.3,0.5,30.9,"4.0","Lemony Fish Fillets Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 450. 2: Spray a 2 quart rectangular baking dish with cooking  spray. 3: Place fish in baking dish. 4: Sprinkle with lemon pepper. 5: Place tomato  slices on top of fish. 6: Sprinkle with green onion and basil. 7: Bake for 4 to 6  minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2703,"Lentil Loaf","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lentil Loaf recipe from Food.com.","Lentil",3.5,3.0,1132.3,36.7,19.8,258.7,1195.1,130.4,22.0,5.3,76.0,"1.0","Lentil Loaf Recipe Instructions:  1: Put lentils, water and bay leaf into saucepan and simmer, uncovered, until lentils are tender, all liquid absorbed - about 20 mins. 2: Remove bay leaf. 3: Oven to Gas Mark 5. 4: Grease loaf tin with butter, sprinkle with dried crumbs. 5: Add cheese, onion, mushrooms, breadcrumbs, parsley, lemon juice and egg to lentils. 6: Mix well. 7: Season well. 8: Bake in tin, uncovered for 45-60 mins. until firm and golden brown on top. 9: Hope you like it! Eve");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2704,"Linda''s Enchiladas","PT25M","PT0S","PT25M","Make and share this Linda''s Enchiladas recipe from Food.com.","Mexican",4.5,8.0,2651.9,135.1,64.7,532.1,5571.9,197.1,30.1,20.3,168.2,"1.0","Linda''s Enchiladas Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown meat and onion in large frying pan. 2: Drain. 3: Combine with olives and cheese in large bowl. 4: Mix well. 5: Combine sauces in frying pan and keep on low heat.  Immerse tortilla in hot sauce mixture holding carefully by edge being careful not to burn fingers. 6: Leave in for 30 seconds. 7: Remove tortilla and place on plate.  Spoon small amount of meat mixture (about 1/3 cup) along edge of tortilla. 8: Roll up and place seam side down in 13 x 9 pan. 9: Repeat until all tortillas have been used. 10: Top with remaining sauce and any left-over meat mixture.  Sprinkle cheese on top and lightly cover. 11: Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. 12: Serve with sour cream and guacamole. I got this recipe from a Mexican lady in California who could not speak a word of English. 13: We did a lot of hand signals.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2705,"Linzertorte","PT45M","PT2H","PT2H45M","Make and share this Linzertorte recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,618.4,32.9,16.5,194.8,37.4,74.7,2.8,42.4,7.7,"8.0","Linzertorte Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift flour, cloves and cinnamon together into a deep mixing bowl. 2: Add ground almonds, sugar, lemon peel and mashed egg yolks. 3: With a wooden spoon, beat in butter, raw egg yolks and vanilla. 4: Continue beating until smooth and doughy. 5: Form dough into ball. 6: Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate at least 1 hour or until firm. 7: Remove about 3/4 of dough and return rest to refrigerator. 8: Lightly butter round cake pan (spring-form, if available). Add dough, and press out to form a 1/4-inch thick shell. 9: Spoon in raspberry jam and spread out evenly with spatula. 10: With floured rolling pin on a floured surface, roll out remaining dough 1/4-inch thick. 11: Cut 1/2 inch wide strips, 2 of them 9-inches long and the rest 8-inches. 12: Lay atop jam in lattice; run knife around sides of pan and press dough at sides down to form a 1/4-inch border. 13: Lightly beat whole egg and cream and coat exposed pastry. 14: Refrigerate 1/2 hour. 15: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 16: Bake torte 45 to 50 minutes until lightly brown. 17: Let cool 5 minutes and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2706,"Little Fish Balls","PT12M","PT0S","PT12M","Make and share this Little Fish Balls recipe from Food.com.","Free Of...",3.0,1.0,30.3,1.3,0.4,52.9,18.4,3.0,0.4,1.3,1.8,"4.0","Little Fish Balls Recipe Instructions:  1: Steam or boil boneless fish. 2: Drain and cool. 3: Chop onions finely and mix with fish. 4: Mix in eggs, salt and pepper and little evaporated milk. 5: Make into golf ball size, squeezing out surplus liquid. 6: Fry in deep hot oil or fat quickly until golden. 7: Also very good cold.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2707,"Little Individual Pizzas","0","PT0S","PT0S","This is a recipe my sister got when she was in high school.  My sisters and I always loved them and my mom enjoyed making them because they were quick and easy.   Little Individual Pizzas","Broil/Grill",0.0,0.0,1924.1,93.1,54.4,217.7,5329.3,180.1,7.2,12.9,89.8,"1.0","Little Individual Pizzas Recipe Instructions:  1: Turn the oven on broil - Put bread slices on cookie sheet to brown. 2: When browned, turn over. 3: Place one slice of spam diagonally across the bread, take a half piece of cheese and cross over the spam. 4: Put a dab of mustard on top. 5: Put back under the broiler to melt cheese.  In a sauce pan, put the tomato sauce and oregano to taste, warm. 6: Remove pizzas from oven and put some sauce on top of each. 7: ENJOY");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2708,"Veal Liver Alla Veneziana","PT10M","PT1H","PT1H10M","Make and share this Veal Liver Alla Veneziana recipe from Food.com.","Beef Organ Meats",0.0,0.0,46.4,0.1,0.1,0.0,9.4,10.6,1.9,4.8,1.2,"6.0","Veal Liver Alla Veneziana Recipe Instructions:  1: Add vinegar to water. 2: Slice liver and marinate in acidulated water for at least one  hour. 3: Drain and pat dry. 4: While the liver is marinating, slice the onions and brown them slowly in butter and oil. 5: Add sliced liver and cook on a lively flame. 6: Add salt when  they are nearly done, sprinkle it with finely chopped parsley and serve. 7: Buon appetito!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2709,"Mabo Dofu - Tofu with Beef","PT20M","PT0S","PT20M","This recipe comes from an English-language Chinese cookbook of my mother''s. I have made it...easy and delicious, and better than in the Chinese restaurants. As most Chinese dishes, it is best as part of a meal of a variety of dishes and a group of people. Accompany with Oriental boiled rice.  Mabo Dofu (Bean Curd with Ground Beef and Chili Peppers)","Soy/Tofu",4.5,4.0,795.3,58.2,10.2,38.6,1084.2,25.9,2.7,6.1,51.3,"2.0","Mabo Dofu - Tofu with Beef Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut bean curd into bite-sized squares and set aside. Heat oil and fry garlic,  chili peppers and chopped leek. 2: Add meat. When meat changes color, lightly stir  in bean curd, soy sauce and = sugar. 3: Cover with lid and cook for 10 min. 4: Add cornstarch mixture, allowing it  to thicken for a few minutes. 5: Turn out into serving dish, sprinkle with the  sesame oil and serve hot. EmmaDeer");
