INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2723,"Microwave Spicy Spaghetti","PT4H","PT15M","PT4H15M","Make and share this Microwave Spicy Spaghetti recipe from Food.com.","Spaghetti",0.0,0.0,406.7,11.8,1.7,0.0,270.3,64.6,3.6,11.2,11.2,"4.0","Microwave Spicy Spaghetti Recipe Instructions:  1: Rinse the spaghetti under running water and drain well. 2: Place the oil, spices, garlic and onions in microwave safe bowl, cover and cook on HIGH for 2 minutes, or until onions are slightly softened, stirring twice.  Add the hot stock and sultanas and cook on HIGH 4 - 5 minutes, or until the onions are tender, stirring once. Add onion mixture to spaghetti with parsley, pine nuts (if using) and pepper to taste and toss to blend. 3: Leave at room temperature for 3 - 4 hours to allow flavours to blend. 4: Toss again before serving. 5: Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 6: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2724,"Minted Summer Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Minted Summer Salad recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",5.0,2.0,133.7,1.3,0.3,0.0,30.6,30.2,7.4,18.0,6.3,"0.0","Minted Summer Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: MINT DRESSING 2 Tbs finely chopped mint 1/3 cup white vinegar 1/4 cup oil salt and pepper Cut pineapple slices into large pieces. 2: Score cucumber with a fork and slice thinly. 3: Put tomatoes, pineapple and cucumber in a bowl. 4: Pour over prepared dressing; toss well. 5: Refrigerate. Before serving sprinkle over with chopped mint. Mint Dressing:- Put mint and vinegar in a small saucepan; bring to the boil. 6: Reduce heat and simmer 1 minutes. 7: Remove from the heat and allow to cool. 8: When cold, strain into a screw-top jar, add oil, and season to taste with salt and pepper. 9: Shake well.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2725,"Mississippi Mud Cake II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Hello, I have made this cake since the ''70s when it first appeared in the Food section of the DALLAS Times Herald.","Dessert",5.0,4.0,9427.9,471.6,251.6,1586.6,4016.5,1270.2,61.4,959.0,106.5,"0.0","Mississippi Mud Cake II Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter and cocoa together, remove from heat.  Stir in sugar and eggs and mix well. 2: Add flour, salt, nuts, coconut and vanilla. 3: Mix well. 4: Bake in 13x9x2 inch pan at 350 degrees for 35 to 45 minutes (check with the toothpick method).  Remove from oven, spoon marshmallow cream over the cake while still very hot. 5: Icing  Melt butter and cocoa together, add the rest of the ingrediants. 6: Spread over marshmallow layer. 7: Swirl into marshmallow cream to resemble mud.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2728,"Barbecued Catch of the Day","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Barbecued Catch of the Day recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,2195.2,77.8,12.3,357.0,4008.9,105.7,37.8,13.7,291.5,"1.0","Barbecued Catch of the Day Recipe Instructions:  1: Squeeze lemon juice over fish and refrigerate for a few hours. 2: Remove and drain well. 3: Place fish and all other ingredients on a large piece of aluminum foil. 4: Close securely and bake at 350 degrees for about one half (1/2) hour. 5: Also try this on barbecue grills and camp fires.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2729,"Moghlai Chicken","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Moghlai Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",0.0,0.0,536.8,42.6,14.2,150.4,536.4,6.1,0.6,4.5,31.8,"6.0","Moghlai Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Remove skin from chicken. 2: Cut into serving pieces, cutting whole legs into two pieces and whole breasts into 6 pieces. 3: Spread chicken in single layer and sprinkle with 1/4 tsp salt and pepper to taste; pat into chicken to help it adhere. Turn chicken over and repeat with another 1/4 tsp salt and pepper to taste. Heat oil and butter in large skillet, preferably non stick, over medium-high heat. When hot, add cardamom, cloves, cinnamon, bay leaves and as many chicken pieces as pan will hold in single layer. 4: (Do not crowd.) Brown chicken on both sides; transfer with slotted spoon to ovenproof casserole. Repeat with remaining chicken. 5: Add almonds to hot oil in skillet and stir. 6: As soon as they begin to brown, about 1 minute, stir in raisins. 7: Immediately pour contents of skillet, fat and all over chicken. 8: In small bowl, stir together yogurt, cumin, cayenne, remaining salt and black pepper to taste. Pour over chicken; mix well. 9: Cover casserole; place in preheated 350F oven 20 minutes. 10: Turn chicken pieces over; baste with juices. 11: Cover, return to oven 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is tender. 12: Just before serving, if necessary, reheat chicken over low heat. Remove chicken pieces; transfer to warm serving dish. 13: Spoon off most fat left in casserole; discard. 14: Place remaining sauce in casserole over medium-high heat and boil until thickened, about 5 minutes. 15: Pour thickened sauce over chicken.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2730,"Moms Chocolate Zucchini Cake","PT45M","PT45M","PT1H30M","Make and share this Moms Chocolate Zucchini Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,18.0,138.8,6.8,1.6,10.7,76.2,18.7,0.7,11.4,1.7,"0.0","Moms Chocolate Zucchini Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: There are many versions of this recipe, this one we like the best for our  family! Beat margarine,oil and sugar well. 2: Beat in eggs, vanilla and sour milk. 3: Sift dry ingredients and beat into mixture. Stir in zucchini. 4: Pour batter into a greased  and floured tube or Bundt pan. 5: Sprinkle top of batter with chips ( Or could stir into batter if you wish ) Bake in a 325F oven 40 to 45 minutes or tested done.  Cool in pan 15 minutes and carefully remove to finish cooling.Sprinkle with  powder sugar if desired. 6: Freezes well and tastes wonderful!");
