INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2756,"Pacifist Pesto","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pacifist Pesto recipe from Food.com.","European",5.0,1.0,1302.2,135.0,17.5,0.0,623.9,24.5,7.4,4.6,10.9,"0.0","Pacifist Pesto Recipe Instructions:  1: Put chick peas, lemon juice, 1/4 cup of olive oil, garlic and miso (or Parmesan cheese) in a blender or food processor and process until smooth. 2: Add one cup of basil leaves and the remainder of the oil and process again until well-blended. 3: Add the remainder of the basil leaves and process again until smooth. 4: Last, add the walnut pieces and mix briefly. 5: Suggestions  Serve on top of pasta with tomato sauce or as a spread on bruschetta (toasted slices of French bread rubbed with garlic). Miso can be found in many health food stores and Oriental groceries.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2757,"Parmesan Dill Potatoes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Parmesan Dill Potatoes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",4.0,2.0,850.0,41.1,5.8,0.0,39.1,111.6,14.1,5.0,12.9,"1.0","Parmesan Dill Potatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil Potatoes for 10-15 minutes checking them for softness with a fork. 2: You  want them to be soft, but not falling apart or fully cooked. 3: Cube the potatoes  into approx. 4: 1/2 to 1 inch cubes, not to thick or thin. 5: Spread 2-3 tablespoons  of the oil onto a nonstick cookie sheet. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 6: Put  potatoes on sheet spreading them around in the oil, but keeping them away from  direct contact with the side of the sheet.  Season with garlic salt, onion salt  and dill. 7: (This should be over all potatoes, but depending on how much you want to flavor them, it is variable.. 8: I moderately-generously season them). Pepper to taste.  Cook for 25-30 minutes or until done.  Slightly golden brown. 9: Halfway  through check potatoes and stir around on sheet.  If oil has cooked out, add the remaining oil, keeping potatoes moist but not saturated. 10: After done, remove  from oven and place in bowl, generously sprinkling Parmesan cheese over them. 11: Stir well and serve, making sure each potato has some Parmesan cheese on it!!!   Enjoy!!! Sarah Smith");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2758,"Pasta and Beans","0","PT2H","PT2H","Make and share this Pasta and Beans recipe from Food.com.","Weeknight",5.0,1.0,1767.9,11.6,3.0,168.0,89.1,324.1,51.5,8.7,97.7,"1.0","Pasta and Beans Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook the beans over gentle heat for 45 minutes or an hour at the most (an hour-and-a-half if they are dried, after soaking in water, together with the herbs and garlic, for a couple of hours). In either case, do not add salt which tends to harden the skins. 2: Purie by putting through a vegetable mill, carefully eliminating the husks. 3: Put the garlic, rosemary, sage and cubed bacon to sauti briefly in a saucepan with 4 tablespoons of oil. 4: Pour on the bean purie. Season lightly with salt and the red hot pepper to taste. Stir to blend the flavours and bring slowly to the boil. 5: Throw the pasta into the purie and cook until firm, diluting with a little of the bean cooking water, but only if necessary - the soup must be thick and rather solid. 6: It is excellent hot, but is absolutely delicious if heated up with the addition of a drop of first-rate olive oil. 7: If you prefer, leave a few beans whole and add them to the saucepan with the purie. Some cooks hold that a carrot is not out of place in the mirepoix (but then cut out the bacon), or that the soup loses nothing if you add a little tomato, even tomato concentrate (paste).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2759,"Pasta Salad with Sweet Peppers and Dill","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pasta Salad with Sweet Peppers and Dill recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",3.0,1.0,83.4,3.0,0.4,7.0,24.2,12.4,1.9,3.8,2.2,"10.0","Pasta Salad with Sweet Peppers and Dill Recipe Instructions:  1: In large saucepan of boiling water, cook pasta until al dente (tender but  firm-start tasting 2 minutes for fresh pasta, 5 minutes for dry); drain, rinse  under cold running water and drain again. 2: Blanch mangetout or green beans in  boiling water for 2 minutes. 3: Drain; rinse under cold running water and drain  again. 4: Cut diagonally into 2 inch/5 cm lengths. 5: In large bowl, combine  cauliflower, carrots, peppers, spring onions, dill, mangetout and pasta; toss to mix. 6: Dressing: in food processor or bowl, combine garlic, vinegar and sugar; mix well. 7: While whistling or processing, gradually add oil and water; mix well. 8: Pour over salad and toss to mix. 9: Add salt and pepper to taste.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2760,"Pasta with Blue Cheese Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pasta with Blue Cheese Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",4.0,2.0,475.8,6.2,2.9,13.7,703.5,82.3,5.7,8.8,16.1,"2.0","Pasta with Blue Cheese Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: Roast onion in oven for half an hour or until tender. 3: Allow to cool. 4: Peel and quarter. 5: In blender, blend onion, blue cheese, cream cheese and sherry till very smooth. 6: Cook pasta (gnocchi works well) in salted boiling water till done. Drain & toss with tomatoes, herbs, salt and pepper. 7: Stir in sauce and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2762,"Pasta with Peperoni (Sweet Green Peppers)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pasta with Peperoni (Sweet Green Peppers) recipe from Food.com.","Low Cholesterol",0.0,0.0,420.2,2.5,0.4,0.0,36.4,93.4,13.7,1.6,9.1,"5.0","Pasta with Peperoni (Sweet Green Peppers) Recipe Instructions:  1: Put some water in a large pan for the pasta and put some salt in it. Now take a  smaller pan and put a drop of olive oil it, then add the pepperoni with a little pinch of salt. Stir them gently and after a while add the olives (without the  brine of course). When the pasta water is boiling put in the pasta and wait for  it to cook. 2: Don''t cook it to much, but drain it when it is still ''al dente'' (not to soft). Put the peperoni in a large bowl and put the drained pasta on top. 3: Mix and add a little oil. 4: You can serve it with some Parmigiano cheese.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2763,"Pasta With Szechuan Peanut Dressing","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Pasta With Szechuan Peanut Dressing recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",5.0,1.0,423.4,18.8,2.8,0.0,198.7,51.9,4.0,5.0,14.7,"0.0","Pasta With Szechuan Peanut Dressing Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring large pot of water to boil; cook pasta until al dente. While pasta  is cooking, steam broccoli florets. 2: In a med mixing bowl, whisk together peanut butter and stock or water  until smooth. 3: Stir in remaining dressing ingredients. 4: When pasta is done, drain well. 5: Pour sauce over pasta; toss to coat well. 6: Add broccoli and tomatoes; toss again. 7: Garnish with chopped scallions. 8: 4  - 6 Servings   VARIATIONS: - add more red pepper to taste - try Szechwan Peanut Dressing as a warm topping on steamed vegetables, especially on green  beans,broccoli, or cauliflower - make extra dressing to refrigerate and  serve later on chilled steamed green beans or broccoli Alan Hewitt     The UK Recipe Archive recipes on-line in Mastercookand Mealmaster formats. 9: http://recipes.reedsweb.net/.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2764,"Pastrami","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pastrami recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.0,2.0,73.7,1.1,0.1,0.0,7553.9,17.5,3.5,9.2,1.5,"0.0","Pastrami Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim the beef. 2: Combine the salt, pepper, sugar, ginger, garlic, and coriander. 3: Working on a clean, nonporous surface, rub the seasoning mixture into all  surfaces of the beef. 4: Place the beef with all the seasonings into a heavy:-duty  sealable plastic bag. 5: Expel the excess air, and carefully tie and seal the bag. 6: Put the bag in the cooler. 7: Rotate and lightly massage the sealed bag at least  once a day for 12 days. 8: SMOKING Preheat the smoker to 650F (180C). Adjust the dampers to wide open. 9: Remove the beef from the plastic bag. 10: Using a trussing needle and strong cord,  provide a secure loop to hang the meat on a smoke stick. 11: Place into the smoker  Allow to air dry with no smoke for a full 24 hours. 12: Remove the meat from the  smoker and cover loosely. 13: Set the temperature at 1''3()0F (540C) with the dampers wide open. 14: Return the meat to the smoker and hold at this setting for 2 hours. 15: Adjust the dampers to one-half open. 16: Monitor the temperature and raise the  tempera ture gradually over the next several hours. 17: Remove the pastrami when its internal temperature reaches 1200F (490C). Do not shower with cold water. 18: Apply  a finishing rub of cracked pepper. 19: Cool quickly and wrap tightly. 20: Refrigerate  for 2 days before using. 21: To cook, unwrap the chilled pastrami and place in a  large quantity of white beef stock. 22: Bring quickly to a full boil, reduce the  heat, and simmer for 2 or more hours until tender. 23: Store the pastrami tightly  wrapped and well-chilled at all times.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2765,"Patatas Brava","PT45M","PT15M","PT1H","Make and share this Patatas Brava recipe from Food.com.","Spanish",5.0,2.0,517.4,27.1,3.9,15.3,475.5,62.8,5.3,8.8,8.5,"4.0","Patatas Brava Recipe Instructions:  1: Grease a roasting pan and arrange the potatoes in one layer. 2: Brush with olive oil,sprinkle with salt and bake at 375  for about 45 minutes or until golden brown. 3: Prepare the tomato sauce by heating the oil in a new skillet.  Saute the onions and garlic until the  onion is wilted. 4: Add the tomatoes and saute for another few minutes Stir in the tomato paste,wine water, parsley,chili pepper,Tabasco, bay leaf,sugar salt and pepper. 5: Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. 6: Strain. 7: The sauce should should not be too thick-thin with water if necessary To serve, arrange the potatoes in a bowl or on the dish. 8: Spoon on several tablespoons of the tomato sauce , then if you wish 3 or 4 tablespoons of the aioli. 9: Generally we eat either the potatoes with only the tomato sauce  or a separate dish potatoes aioli with just the aioli sauce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2766,"Fresh Peach Cobbler With Almond Crunch Topping","PT30M","PT30M","PT1H","Make and share this Fresh Peach Cobbler With Almond Crunch Topping recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,2.0,483.3,14.8,5.5,21.1,224.6,84.5,6.2,55.3,8.6,"6.0","Fresh Peach Cobbler With Almond Crunch Topping Recipe Instructions:  1: For Cobbler:  In food processor, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.  Pulse  to combine.  Add cold butter and pulse until mixture is crumbly. 2: Drizzle  most of buttermilk /cream over flour mixture, pulse to combine. If mixture seems dry, add a little more.  Dough should be just moist.  Gather the dough and  spread out onto lightly floured parchment or waxed  paper. 3: Patting into a Disc  a little less than 1/2-inch thick chill for  1/2 hour. 4: For Fruit:  Slice  peaches into wedges, toss with lemon juice.  In a small bowl, combine  cornstarch, spices, pinch of salt and lemon zest.  Toss with the peaches and  pour unto lightly greased 8-inch baking dish. 5: To assemble:  On a lightly  floured surface, using a fluted cutter or any shaped cutter, cut out biscuits. 6: Gently re-roll scraps and arrange over fruit, slightly overlapping. 7: Brush  biscuits with cream. 8: In a small bowl, combine almonds, brown sugar and  cinnamon. 9: Sprinkle over dough. 10: Place in the oven and cook until fruit is  bubbling, biscuits are golden,  and a skewer poked into the center of the  biscuit dough comes out clean. 11: Serve warm with ice cream, heavy cream or creme anglaise.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2767,"Peach Sour Cream Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Peach Sour Cream Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,1.0,1966.4,90.3,43.6,478.8,2008.4,277.8,7.9,202.8,22.3,"1.0","Peach Sour Cream Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Blend sour cream, orange juice, brown sugar, salt and egg yolks. 2: Sprinkle pie  shell with 1 Tbsp flour. 3: Pour in peaches and sprinkle with remaining flour. 4: Pour sour cream mixture over peaches. 5: Bake 425F for 15 minutes, then 350F for 30  minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2769,"Battenburg Cake","PT35M","PT15M","PT50M","Make and share this Battenburg Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,3.0,619.9,29.4,11.2,111.2,276.1,84.4,3.4,57.2,9.7,"12.0","Battenburg Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar together. 2: Beat in 3 eggs, one at a time. Mix in  vanilla. 3: Stir in flour, baking powder and salt gently. 4: Add milk if needed. 5: Divide batter into 2 equal parts. 6: Add food coloring to 1 part to make a deep  pink color. 7: Grease two 7-inch square pans. 8: Spread batters into pans. 9: Bake at 350°F until an inserted wooden pick comes out clean, about 25-30 minutes. 10: Let stand in pans 5 minutes. 11: Turn out on racks to cool. 12: Trim edges from both cakes. 13: Cut  each cake lengthwise into 4 strips as wide as the cake is thick. 14: Trim to make  strips match. 15: Heat jam slightly. 16: Spread on sides to glue 2 pink and 2 white  strips together checkerboard fashion. 17: Spread all 4 sides of completed cake with  jam. 18: Repeat with remaining pink and white stripes. 19: Makes 2 cakes. 20: To make  almond paste: Mix almonds, confectioners'' sugar, egg, lemon juice and almond  extract together. 21: Knead until smooth, adding a bit of lemon juice or water if  too dry to roll. 22: Add only 1/2 teaspoon at a time. It will be stiff. 23: Divide into  2 equal parts. 24: Roll 1/2 of paste 1/8 inch thick on a surface lightly dusted with  confectioners'' sugar. 25: Cut to fit length of cake and long enough to cover 4 sides leaving ends uncovered. 26: Lay cake on one end of paste. Wrap completely to enclose all 4 sides of cake pinching paste to seal. 27: Roll in granulated sugar. 28: Place with seal underneath on serving plate, or store in plastic bag. 29: repeat for second  cake. Chill. 30: Slice thinly to serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2770,"Peachy Cheesecake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Peachy Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",0.0,0.0,169.5,0.2,0.0,0.0,12.8,42.0,1.7,32.9,0.9,"0.0","Peachy Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine sugar and Fruit-Fresh; add peaches and toss well to coat each slice.  Cover and refrigerate. Thaw cheese cake according to package directions. 2: Melt preserves over low heat; add almond extract. Cool. 3: Drain peaches well and arrange on top of cake. Glaze with preserves. 4: Refrigerate until serving time. Makes 4-5 servings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2771,"Pecan Honey Butter","0","PT5M","PT5M","Make and share this Pecan Honey Butter recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",5.0,3.0,113.1,11.2,6.0,24.4,65.5,3.9,0.3,3.6,0.4,"20.0","Pecan Honey Butter Recipe Instructions:  1: Slowly beat the honey into the butter or margarine until well blended. 2: Stir in chopped pecans. 3: Pack in gift containers and refrigerate. Bring to room temperature before serving on biscuits, rolls, or other bread.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2772,"Perfect Fish & Chips","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Perfect Fish & Chips recipe from Food.com.","Healthy",5.0,1.0,542.6,9.7,1.9,153.4,1044.3,52.2,2.5,0.3,52.2,"2.0","Perfect Fish & Chips Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash fillet in lemon and water. 2: Season with salt and pepper. 3: Chill while you  prepare the  batter. 4: Sprinkle yeast over warm water. 5: Let stand until  dissolved. 6: Place flour in a bowl with the salt and sugar. 7: Make a well in  the   center. 8: Add the dissolved yeast, oil and 2/3 of the beer. 9: Stir with  a  wooden spoon just to combine.  Stir in remaining beer. 10: Let the batter stand, covered,  in a warm place for 30-35  minuted,  until it has thickened and become frothy. 11: Dry fish with paper towels and cut each fillet diagonally into 2  pieces. 12: Heat  the oven to warm. 13: Stir together remaining flour, pepper and salt in a plate.  Heat the oil. 14: Whip egg white until it forms soft peaks and fold into batter. 15: Coat fish with seasoned flour, patting so they are evenly  coated. 16: Shake off  excess flour. 17: Using a 2 pronged fork, dip the fish into the batter. 18: Lift it out and hold it over bowl 5 seconds to drip off excess batter. 19: Carefully lower the  piece of fish into the hot oil and deep fry,  turning once, until golden crisp. 20: Fry 1-2 pieces at a time, transferring to paper towels as you  go.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2773,"Pickled Onions","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pickled Onions recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",0.0,0.0,3249.2,15.1,1.4,0.0,268.8,695.6,43.4,522.3,35.1,"0.0","Pickled Onions Recipe Instructions:  1: Sprinkle the onions with the salt. Cover with cold water and let stand 6-8 hours or overnight. Rinse thoroughly with cold water, and drain well. 2: Combine the vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, and horseradish in a pot and simmer for 10 minutes. 3: Spoon the onions into hot, sterilized jars, adding a few peppercorns, a bay leaf, and some pimiento slices to each jar. 4: Pour the boiling hot vinegar mixture over the onions, leaving 1/4-inch headspace, and seal. 5: Or close the jars and process in a boiling-water bath for 10 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2774,"Pina Colada Cake","PT35M","PT10M","PT45M","Make and share this Pina Colada Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,22.0,424.3,18.5,9.5,33.7,308.6,60.9,1.2,50.9,5.1,"15.0","Pina Colada Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: Grease and flour a 9x13-inch pan. 3: Prepare cake as directed on package, but use 2 eggs instead of the number the recipe calls for. 4: Bake as directed. 5: While cake is baking, combine cream of coconut and sweetened condensed milk. 6: When the cake is done, remove from oven and, while it is still hot, punch holes in the top (the handle of a wooden spoon works well). Pour the cream of coconut/condensed milk mixture over top and into all the holes. 7: Let cake cool thoroughly (can be refrigerated to cool). When ready to serve, cover cake with whipped topping and sprinkle coconut flakes on top. 8: Serve thoroughly cooled.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2775,"Pineapple Cheese Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pineapple Cheese Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",0.0,0.0,1841.8,118.4,68.4,733.5,1325.4,157.9,6.9,107.3,39.0,"1.0","Pineapple Cheese Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter. 2: Mix well and press evenly into bottom of 9-inch pie pan. 3: Cream cream cheese. Add eggs and mix until smooth. 4: Add orange juice, sugar, flour, vanilla, orange rind and salt. Mix until smooth. 5: Pour into crumb crust. Bake at 3500 for 20 - 30 minutes or until filling is set. Chill. 6: To prepare topping drain pineapple juice into a saucepan. 7: Soften gelatin in juice and warm gently until it dissolves. 8: Chill until mixture begins to thicken. 9: Arrange pineapple tidbits over baked pie filling. 10: Pour gelatin mixture over all. 11: Chill 1 hour or until firm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2776,"Pink Lady Punch","PT4H","PT20M","PT4H20M","Make and share this Pink Lady Punch recipe from Food.com.","0",4.0,1.0,894.5,1.6,0.1,0.0,190.2,223.4,2.6,214.4,6.1,"0.0","Pink Lady Punch Recipe Instructions:  1: Make up Koolaid  according to package directions and heat to simmer.. 2: This  removes the koolaidy taste when punch is all made up.. 3: All fruit juices and  koolaid are to be mixed together 4 hours before serving. 4: Add Ginger Ale just  before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2777,"Pizza Fondue","PT10M","PT15M","PT25M","Make and share this Pizza Fondue recipe from Food.com.","< 30 Mins",5.0,19.0,522.5,38.4,22.0,135.2,656.3,8.5,0.9,1.8,34.9,"0.0","Pizza Fondue Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown the chopped onion and beef together; drain grease off. 2: Add remaining ingredients and cook until cheese is melted. 3: Place in fondue pot and serve with toasted cubes of French bread.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2778,"BBQ Portabella","PT10M","PT0S","PT10M","Make and share this BBQ Portabella recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,9.0,494.3,42.4,13.4,38.6,499.5,14.1,3.3,4.3,17.9,"1.0","BBQ Portabella Recipe Instructions:  1: Clean off the portabella cap, and cut stem close to cap, chop stem. 2: Gently heat the olive oil in a saute pan, then add the peppers, onion, and stem ( I''ve added cubed tofu at this stage too) Saute all together until just tender Set the peppers, etc. aside for a moment and use a pastry brush dipped in the flavored olive oil in the bottom of the pan to oil the portabella cap ( both sides) Then, with the top side of the cap down, put all the peppers, etc. on the underside (up), transfer to the grill and cook for about 3-4 minutes. 3: Put the cheese onto of the peppers, and grill until melted. 4: Really good, I even like this, and I''m a confirmed carnivore! Vickie.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2779,"Pizza Pockets","PT30M","PT20M","PT50M","Make and share this Pizza Pockets recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,24.0,421.1,17.7,6.9,29.1,1148.2,50.6,3.6,4.4,15.2,"6.0","Pizza Pockets Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix 1 1/4 cups flour, yeast and salt in bowl. 2: Stir  in warm water. 3: Beat on low  speed for 1/2 minute.  Scrape bowl constantly. 4: Beat 3 minutes on high speed. 5: Stir in  remaining flour with a spoon. 6: Turn dough out on floured  surface. Knead 6 to 8 minutes. 7: Cover dough; let rest for 10  minutes. 8: Divide into 6 parts. 9: (Dough is also excellent pizza  dough.) Filling instructions: Brown and drain sausage, green pepper and  onion. 10: Add  chopped tomatoes and tomato paste, spices and  water. 11: Cook 5 minutes. 12: Roll each  portion of pizza pocket  dough into rounds. 13: Spoon 1/6 of filling and 1/6 of  cheese onto  each pizza pocket round. 14: Fold dough in half and close with fork   tines. 15: Brush with beaten egg. 16: Bake at 375 degrees for 30 to  35 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2780,"Pork with Orange and Apricots","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pork with Orange and Apricots recipe from Food.com.","Pork",0.0,0.0,1019.6,48.7,19.7,306.7,336.6,59.6,8.7,45.3,86.8,"1.0","Pork with Orange and Apricots Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt the butter in a frying pan. 2: add the chops and fry on both sides until evenly browned. 3: Transfer to a shallow ovenproof dish, using a slotted spoon. 4: Sprinkle with orange rind. 5: Add onion and pepper to the fat remaining in the pan and fry until soft.  Stir in the stock. 6: Blend the cornflour with the orange juice and add to the pan. 7: Heat, stirring, until the sauce thickens. 8: Add the sugar and salt and pepper to taste.  Arrange the apricots on top of the pork and pour the sauce over. 9: Cover with foil and cook at 180 C for 1-1 1/4 hours. 10: Serve hot garnished with watercress sprigs.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2781,"Pork With Orange Sauce","PT15M","PT0S","PT15M","Make and share this Pork With Orange Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Pork",4.0,4.0,75.9,4.5,1.6,5.1,70.3,8.8,0.8,5.3,0.8,"6.0","Pork With Orange Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Dust steaks  with seasoned flour. 2: Saute in oil and butter approximately 8 minutes. 3: Remove from pan and keep warm. 4: Drain excess fat from pan. 5: Add juice, mustard, sauce and garlic and simmer for 3 minutes. 6: Add slices of orange and reheat with pork, coating well with sauce.  Serve sprinkled with parsley.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2782,"Potato Candy","PT20M","PT20M","PT40M","Make and share this Potato Candy recipe from Food.com.","Candy",4.5,6.0,2656.9,65.6,13.4,0.0,606.9,506.8,11.5,457.5,35.8,"0.0","Potato Candy Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel hot potato and smash it up real good with a fork, about 1/2 cup mashed. 2: Add 1/4 teaspoon vanilla. 3: Add enough powdered sugar to create a stiff dough. You may need more sugar. 4: Roll out on powdered sugar, spread with  peanut butter. 5: Roll up from  one end, pinwheel fashion, slice into 1/4 inch  slices.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2783,"Potato Cauliflower Soup","0","PT1M","PT1M","Make and share this Potato Cauliflower Soup recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,14.0,257.6,16.5,7.6,40.8,458.6,24.9,4.2,3.8,4.8,"8.0","Potato Cauliflower Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: In a 4-quart soup pot, heat the oil and saute the onions, dill weed, and thyme until tender and beginning to brown. 2: Add cauliflower and cook a few minutes more.  Add stock or water and potatoes. 3: Cover and cook on medium heat until tender (approximately 30 minutes.) Remove from heat, and in a blender puree approximately half the soup (or 6 cups), 2 cups at a time.  Return puree to soup pot.  Simmer on lowest heat, and add bay leaves, salt, pepper, and tamari. 4: Cook approximately 20 minutes more uncovered, stirring occasionally. 5: Mix cream with flour and stir to smooth out lumps. 6: Turn off heat and add to soup along with parsley. 7: Check seasoning. 8: Thin with water or milk if the soup has gotten too thick after sitting. 9: Reheat if necessary and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2784,"Potato Salad with Cooked Dressing","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Potato Salad with Cooked Dressing recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,7.0,1925.4,71.3,41.2,565.7,472.6,284.7,29.4,66.2,42.5,"0.0","Potato Salad with Cooked Dressing Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix together and let come to a boil. 2: Cook until thick. 3: Add 1/2 cup cream or you can use 1/2 cup mayonnaise.  Pour dressing over potato mixture.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2785,"Potato-Crusted Meatloaf","PT1H","PT20M","PT1H20M","I have had this recipe for a long time and do not know where I got it other than it was from a magazine.","Potato",4.0,1.0,665.2,27.3,10.4,170.6,1479.2,50.2,6.3,7.5,53.0,"0.0","Potato-Crusted Meatloaf Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat the broiler. 2: Place the onion, bell peppers and garlic cloves on a baking sheet.  Broil 3 inches from heat for 7 minutes or until blackened, turning frequently. 3: Transfer to a paper bag, close tightly and let stand 15 minutes or until soft.  Scrape off outside skins. 4: Chop the onion and garlic; seed and chop the peppers. 5: (You will have about 2 cups of vegetables). Preheat oven to 350 and spray a 13x9x3\ 6: ,  7: Mix with your hand until well combined. 8: Transfer to the baking dish and pat into a 12x7\ 9: ,  10: ,  11: ,  12: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2786,"Potato-Stuffed Green Bell Peppers","PT25M","PT40M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Potato-Stuffed Green Bell Peppers recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,3.0,143.2,0.7,0.2,0.0,652.3,32.9,6.9,11.4,4.9,"4.0","Potato-Stuffed Green Bell Peppers Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: Slice away pepper tops below stems. 3: Remove seeds and interior spines. 4: Gently parboil peppers about 5 minutes. 5: Drain upside down. 6: Set peppers aside. Saute onions and red pepper until soft. Add seasonings and mix well into mashed potatoes. 7: Carefully stuff peppers, set them in a deep- sided baking dish. 8: Pour tomato sauce around base of peppers. 9: Bake at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes covered. 10: Uncover, and bake 5 minutes longer. 11: Serve warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2787,"Pound Cake Supreme","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pound Cake Supreme recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,1851.2,54.1,14.1,174.0,1307.1,324.1,6.6,0.0,17.8,"1.0","Pound Cake Supreme Recipe Instructions:  1: Split cake into 3 layers. 2: Put 1/2 can of blueberry pie filling on first layer and put cherry pie filling on second layer. 3: Cover entire dessert with thawed cool whip. 4: You may make a small indentation in the cool whip on top and add a few cherries. 5: Service with the leftover pie fillings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2788,"Praline Pudding Cake","PT35M","PT0S","PT35M","Make and share this Praline Pudding Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,259.4,5.8,2.0,7.5,221.2,50.2,0.9,35.4,2.8,"9.0","Praline Pudding Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: Combine brown sugar and 1 tablespoon flour in a bowl, mix and set aside.  Combine 1 1/4 cups flour with the granulated sugar, pecans, baking powder and salt in a bowl, make well in the center. 3: Combine milk, margarine, and vanilla and add to flour mixture, stir until moist. Spread batter into an 8 inch square baking pan, sprinkle top with brown sugar mixture.  Pour boiling water over batter, do not stir. 4: Bake at 350 for 35 minutes or until pudding is bubbly and cake springs back when lightly touched in center. 5: Serve warm with whipped cream topping. 6: Garnish with pecans if desired. 7: I made this cake this past weekend, it is not too heavy as I got it from Cooking Light Magazine.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2789,"Prawns (Shrimp) on the Barbie Aussie Style","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Prawns (Shrimp) on the Barbie Aussie Style recipe from Food.com.","Very Low Carbs",5.0,1.0,233.2,9.6,1.4,242.5,243.3,2.2,0.1,0.0,32.6,"4.0","Prawns (Shrimp) on the Barbie Aussie Style Recipe Instructions:  1: These are prepared using a kettle bbq, with a direct fire, the lid off, and 2: using the wok. 3: Heat the wok and add the oil. 4: Fry the prawns with the garlic,  ginger and chilli, tossing them well until the prawns turn pink and are cooked  through. 5: Add the coriander and serve the prawns as an entree.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2790,"Prize Winning Zucchini Relish","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Prize Winning Zucchini Relish recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,5.0,693.6,1.7,0.4,0.0,4221.2,165.8,6.3,154.1,5.7,"0.0","Prize Winning Zucchini Relish Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large container, combine zucchini, onion, pepper, chilies and salt; stir well. 2: Chill overnight. Rinse thoroughly; drain. 3: In a large kettle, combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. 4: Add zucchini mixture; simmer for 10 minutes. 5: Ladle hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch  headspace. Adjust lids. 6: Process for 10 minutes in a boiling-water bath. 7: Serving suggestion: Mix into tuna or macaroni salad. 8: (Country Woman July/Aug 1995)");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2791,"Queen''s Speech Peach Trifle","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Queen''s Speech Peach Trifle recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,1.0,1302.8,4.9,2.9,22.1,1553.1,268.4,2.0,198.0,32.4,"1.0","Queen''s Speech Peach Trifle Recipe Instructions:  1: Pour the yogurt into a coffee filter set in a colander over a bowl and let drain for 5 to 10 minutes. 2: In a large bowl, whisk together the pudding mix and milk  until well blended. 3: Add the drained yogurt and stir to combine. Set aside.  In a small bowl, mix the jam and sherry. 4: Set aside.  In a large deep glass bowl,  arrange half of the cake cubes. 5: Spread half of the pudding mixture over them. 6: Spoon half the jam mixture over the pudding, and top with half the peaches. 7: Repeat layers in the same order with remaining ingredients. 8: Granish with the  reserved peach slices and mint.  For a change, this trifle is also delicious when made with a 15 ounce (425g)  package of frozen unsweetened raspberries, sweetened with 1 tbsp granulated  sugar, instead of the peaches.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2792,"Quick and Cheap Pasta","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Quick and Cheap Pasta recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.0,1.0,176.5,11.9,7.4,30.5,614.5,17.3,3.6,10.2,3.5,"1.0","Quick and Cheap Pasta Recipe Instructions:  1: Have some boiling water, with salt and one of those chicken  stock cubes in it and a tablespoon of butter. 2: When it starts to boil, add the  Spaghetti or any other type of pasta. 3: After about 10-15 minutes, the pasta  should be cooked (try it and see if its not hard) Remove the water, stir a  little bit with a fork (don''t squish it!) and let it dry for about one minute.   You can eat the pasta like this it''s good, but you''ll be fed up with it in no  time, so, the solution I found is to add some nice sauce: Start making the sauce about 5 minutes after the pasta''s been boiling Have some  oil or olive oil on a frying pan or a small pan. 4: Add half an onion cut into  little pieces. 5: When the onion starts to get transparent and soft add a little  bit of concentrated tomato, just about 4-5 table spoons. 6: Stir (have the fire set to LOW) Add half a cup of water and stir again. 7: Add salt, pepper, nutmeg,  mustard, lemon juice, and any sort of seasoning you like, and let it cook for a  couple of minutes. 8: And there, you have your basic sauce recipe, if you''re vegan, just pour it over  the pasta, it''s very tasty. 9: If you''re not vegan you''ll soon get fed up with this to, to solve that problem, simply add whatever you want to the sauce, it''s  excellent with canned tuna, mushrooms, fish leftovers, meat, ham, really  ANYTHING you like! And the great thing is that the sauce has a completely  different taste depending on what you add to it. I hope this helps :)");
