INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2846,"Carrot Walnut Cake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Carrot Walnut Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,2.0,526.8,23.8,10.9,102.7,454.7,74.4,3.4,44.0,7.8,"12.0","Carrot Walnut Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: CREAM CHEESE GLAZE  8 oz Cream cheese, softened  1 Tbsp Lemon juice  1 tsp Grated lemon peel  1 1/2 cup Confectioners sugar  1/2 cup Coarsely chopped walnuts  This is billed as the richest carrot cake recipe ever. 2: Lightly grease and flour a 10-by-4-inch tube pan. 3: Sift flour with baking powder,  soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside. Wash and pare carrots; grate on medi  um  grater or use coarse blade of food processor. 4: Should measure 4 cups. 5: Preheat  oven to 350F. 6: In large bowl of mixer, at high speed, beat butter and brown and  granulated sugars, occasionally scraping side of bowl with rubber scraper, until  light and fluffy-about 4 minutes. 7: Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each  addition until smooth and light. In measuring cup, combine lemon and orange  peels and juices. 8: At low speed, beat in flour mixture (in fourths), alternately  with lemon-orange mixture (in thirds), beginning and ending with flour mixture.  Beat just until smooth-about 1 minute. With wooden spoon, stir in grated carrot,  nuts and raisins; mix well. 9: Turn into the prepared tube pan; spread evenly. 10: Bake  60 minutes, or until a cake tester inserted in center of the cake comes out  clean. 11: Cool in pan on wire rack 20 minutes, to cool slightly. 12: Meanwhile, make  cream-cheese glaze: In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, lemon juice, lemon  peel and confectioners'' sugar. 13: With portable electri  c mixer at high speed, beat  mixture until smooth. 14: Set aside. Gently loosen edge of cake with spatula. 15: Turn  out of pan onto rack. 16: Spread glaze over top of the warm cake, letting it run  down side of cake. Carefully remove cake to cake platter. 17: Sprinkle chopped  walnuts around top edge of cake. Serves 12.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2847,"Carrot Cake with Lemon Frosting","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Carrot Cake with Lemon Frosting recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,830.7,46.4,17.5,115.9,512.8,99.7,2.6,77.2,7.9,"16.0","Carrot Cake with Lemon Frosting Recipe Instructions:  1: For Cake:  Preheat oven to 350 deg. 2: Butter three 9-inch-diameter cake pans with 1 1/2-inch-high sides. 3: Line bottoms with waxed pape r. 4: Butter paper. 5: Mix together oil, pineapple, eggs, vanilla and carrots. 6: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt in medium bowl. 7: Stir into oil mixture.  Mix in walnuts. 8: Divide batter among prepared pans. 9: Bake until tester inserted into center comes out clean, about 35 minutes. 10: Cook cakes in pans on racks. 11: For Frosting:  Using electric mixer, beat cream cheese, butter, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy. 12: Gradually beat in sugar. 13: Chill until firm but spreadable, about 1 hour. 14: Turn cakes out of pans; peel off waxed paper. 15: Place 1 cake on platter. 16: Spread 3/4 cup frosting over. 17: Top with second cake. Spread 3/4 cup frosting over. 18: Top with third cake.  Spread remaining frosting over top and sides of cake.  (Can be prepared 1 day ahead. 19: Cover with cake dome and refrigerate.  Let stand 3 hours at room temperature before serving.)  Garnish cake with flowers. 20: ** Actual recipe calls for carrots to be cut into 1/2-inch pieces and cooked in a large pot of boiling salt ed water until tender, about 12 minutes. 21: Drain. 22: Puree in processor, stopping occasionally to scrape down sides of bowl. 23: Transfer to large bowl and cool. 24: I prefer to use the shredded carrots and have had very good results. 25: I have also baked this in a large sheet cake size pan and adjusted the cooking time.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2848,"Banana Bread II","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","Make and share this Banana Bread II recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,21.0,417.2,0.8,0.2,0.0,366.4,96.2,3.9,43.2,8.1,"6.0","Banana Bread II Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°. 2: Spray a 9 x 5 loaf pan with non-stick cooking spray. 3: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon and set aside. 4: In a large bowl, whisk together applesauce, sugar, egg whites, banana and vanilla. 5: Add flour mixture all at once and stir gently to blend. 6: Pour batter into prepared loaf pan and bake for 50-60 minutes or until knife inserted  comes out clean. 7: Cool bread completely before slicing.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2849,"Best Banana Bread","PT1H","PT10M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Best Banana Bread recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,2273.0,272.8,10.5,6.2,61.6,338.3,42.5,1.4,24.4,3.7,"10.0","Best Banana Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Remove odd pots and pans from oven. 2: Preheat oven to 350º / 180º. 3: Cream together butter and sugar. 4: Add eggs and crushed bananas. 5: Combine well. 6: Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture. Add vanilla. 7: Mix just until combined. Do not overmix. 8: Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. 9: Bake at 350º / 180º for 55 minutes. 10: Keeps well, refrigerated.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2850,"Barbecue Sauce Marinade","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Barbecue Sauce Marinade recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,261.6,7.5,1.0,0.0,1364.3,39.3,2.8,26.9,2.6,"0.0","Barbecue Sauce Marinade Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute onion flakes in vegetable oil. 2: Stir in garlic, salt, chili powder, dry mustard, brown sugar;add the  Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce, and wine and stir well. 3: Bring mixture to boil and then simmer for 5 minutes. 4: Cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2851,"Vanilla Cake II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Vanilla Cake II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",3.0,1.0,5699.9,220.6,130.6,1452.2,6151.6,856.7,10.2,552.8,83.7,"1.0","Vanilla Cake II Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. Mix vanilla with  butter or margarine. Gradually blend in sugar. 2: Beat in 1 egg yolk. 3: Add flour  mixture alternately with milk. 4: Beat 4 of the egg whites until they stand in  soft, stiff peaks. 5: Fold into mixture. Divide batter into 2 equal parts and blend  4 egg yolks and yellow food coloring into 1 part. Drop white and yellow batters  alternately into well-greased, lightly floured 10 x 4-inch tube pan. 6: Bake in  preheated oven at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cak  e tester  inserted in center comes out clean. 7: Remove from oven. 8: Cool in pan 20 minutes. 9: Turn out onto cake rack to finish cooling. 10: Frost top and sides with Easy Vanilla  Frosting. 11: Easy Vanilla Frosting: Place all ingredients in small deep bowl of  electric mixer. 12: Beat with mixer at high speed until very stiff. 13: Spread over top");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2852,"White Cake with Coconut Pecan Frosting","PT40M","PT1H","PT2H","Make and share this White Cake with Coconut Pecan Frosting recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,3.0,9973.8,632.4,305.3,2260.4,4608.6,1021.5,31.1,794.5,107.5,"1.0","White Cake with Coconut Pecan Frosting Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. 2: Add eggs, one at a time and mix. 3: Add flour, baking soda and buttermilk; mix well. 4: Add oil. 5: Bake in layer cake pans for 40  minutes at 350 degrees F until done. 6: Frosting: Mix all ingredients together well and frost cake.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2853,"Pasta Fruit Salad","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Pasta Fruit Salad recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",0.0,0.0,196.2,1.4,0.6,3.2,14.4,42.7,3.0,18.9,5.2,"10.0","Pasta Fruit Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook pasta; rinse in cold water and drain very well. 2: Place in a large bowl; add the fruit. 3: Combine the yogurt and orange juice concentrate; pour over salad and toss to  coat. 4: Cover and chill for several hours.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2854,"Potluck Pasta Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Potluck Pasta Salad recipe from Food.com.","Potluck",5.0,7.0,278.0,16.6,3.6,9.9,525.5,25.0,4.0,4.6,9.4,"12.0","Potluck Pasta Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook pasta according to package directions except add crushed red pepper to the  cooking water. 2: Rinse with cool water and drain thoroughly. 3: Cool pasta to room  temperature.  In a large mixing bowl combine pasta, sweet red pepper, yellow squash or  zucchini, peas, olives, cheese, almonds, green onions and herb. 4: Add dressing to  pasta mixture. Toss gently to mix. 5: Cover and chill for 2 hours or up to 24  hours.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2855,"Spinach Pasta Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Spinach Pasta Salad recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.0,2.0,141.1,9.9,2.9,14.7,166.0,9.4,0.9,0.7,4.2,"12.0","Spinach Pasta Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large saucepan cook tortellini. 2: drain. 3: Rinse. Drain. 4: In a large salad bowl toss together tortellini, spinach, cabbage, bacon and  green onion. 5: Cover and chill. 6: Just before serving, shake dressing well. 7: Toss with tortellini mixture.   - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2856,"Streusel-Topped Pumpkin Pie","PT55M","PT10M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Streusel-Topped Pumpkin Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,1.0,504.4,26.8,8.8,82.3,441.4,60.3,2.6,48.4,11.3,"0.0","Streusel-Topped Pumpkin Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 425. 2: With mixer or wire whist, beat pumpkin, sweetened condensed  milk, egg, 3/4 tsp cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Pour into crust bake 15  minutes meanwhile, combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoons. 3: cinnamon; cut in butter  until crumbly. 4: Stir in walnuts. 5: Remove crust from oven. 6: Reduce oven to 350. 7: Sprinkle streusel mixture over pie. Bake 40 minutes or until set. Cool. 8: Serve  warm or at room temperature. Refrigerate leftovers. 9: TIP: Top with whipped cream if desired.");
