INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2897,"Christmas Puddings","PT6H","PT15M","PT6H15M","Make and share this Christmas Puddings recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,1.0,403.7,10.0,4.5,40.4,127.5,50.7,2.0,21.7,6.2,"12.0","Christmas Puddings Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift flour, salt and spices together. 2: Put suet, breadcrumbs, sugar, eggs, stout and golden syrup, almond essence and juice into bowl. 3: Mix well. 4: Stir in nuts and fruit. 5: Add dry ingredients and mix well. 6: Turn batter into thoroughly greased 2-quart mold. 7: Cover tightly with greased cover or aluminum foil, waxed paper or parchment. 8: Place mold on trivet or rack in steamer or deep kettle. 9: Pour boiling water into steamer about half the height of mold. 10: Cover and steam pudding for six hours. 11: Add more boiling water if necessary during steaming.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2898,"Balkenbrij (Liverwurst)","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","I live in Holland, Michigan and these are just a few of the &quot;traditional&quot;  recipes I''ve collected from people I know who probably brought them from &quot;the  old country.&quot; Enjoy!     Balkenbrij (Liverwurst)","Beef Organ Meats",2.0,2.0,749.0,17.6,5.7,879.7,818.1,53.5,6.0,2.1,92.4,"12.0","Balkenbrij (Liverwurst) Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim and cook liver in separate kettle, keep broth. 2: Remove veins. 3: Trim fat and  veins from heart, cook, keep broth. 4: Trim fat from roast and cook, keep broth. 5: When all meats are cooked, put through food grinder using coarse cutter. 6: Put  all ground meat and broth in 8 quart kettle. Add salt and pepper. 7: Bring to  boiling, adding buckwheat flour a little at a time to mix well. 8: Mixture will  become very thick. 9: Spoon and press into 4 to 5 loaf pans. 10: Refrigerate or  freeze.  To serve, slice and brown on both sides, with a slice of cheese if desired, or  with syrup.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2900,"Barbecued Pork Strips","PT8H","PT5M","PT8H5M","Make and share this Barbecued Pork Strips recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",4.0,5.0,188.8,5.2,1.8,53.5,656.5,13.4,0.3,11.7,20.6,"15.0","Barbecued Pork Strips Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients except pork strips in crock pot and stir well. 2: Add pork and stir to coat. 3: Cook on LOW, covered, for 8-10 hours.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2901,"Medallions of Pork with Riesling Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","This is a recipe that I adopted that sounds really delicious!  The recipe is going to require a bit of editing to figure it out - I hope to prepare it soon.","Pork",0.0,0.0,467.2,31.9,16.0,116.3,254.7,21.7,1.6,14.2,20.1,"4.0","Medallions of Pork with Riesling Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Season pork with salt and pepper. 2: Coat with flour; shake off excess. 3: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat.  Add onions and garlic and saute until golden brown, about 5 minutes; transfer mixture to bowl. 4: Melt remaining 2 tablespoons of butter in same skillet over medium-high heat, and add pork and saute about 4 minutes per side about 16 minutes. 5: Transfer pork to platter; tent with foil to keep warm. 6: Add onion mixture, Riesling, raisins, vinegar, peppercorns and herbs to the same skillet and simmer until sauce thickens, about 4 minutes. 7: Add browned pork to skillet and heat through. 8: Slice and divide pork among plates. 9: Add remaining 1/4 cup butter to sauce in skillet and whisk just until melted; mix in pine nuts. 10: Spoon sauce over pork and serve.  Goes well with wild rice pilaf and asparagus or green bean almondine.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2902,"Peachy Pork Picante","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Make and share this Peachy Pork Picante recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,4.0,383.6,18.2,6.2,76.0,463.7,31.6,1.5,21.4,22.6,"0.0","Peachy Pork Picante Recipe Instructions:  1: Coat pork cubes with taco seasoning. 2: Heat oil in a heavy nonstick skillet over  medium high heat. Saute pork 2-3 minutes, stirring occasionally  until browned on all sides. 3: Add salsa and preserves. 4: Reduce heat  to low, cover and simmer 15-20 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2903,"Lemon Sherbet Punch","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Lemon Sherbet Punch recipe from Food.com.","Punch Beverage",5.0,13.0,32.6,0.0,0.0,0.0,3.9,8.4,0.0,4.4,0.0,"40.0","Lemon Sherbet Punch Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix Lemonade in very large punch bowl. 2: Add soda and frozen fruit. 3: Open  sherbet and dump the entire package of it into punch (it will float on the  top). 4: Due to the frozen fruit and Sherbet, there is really no need for ice until later, or unless it it very hot.");
