INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2905,"Strawberry Punch #1","PT6M","PT0S","PT6M","Make and share this Strawberry Punch #1 recipe from Food.com.","Punch Beverage",4.0,2.0,43.3,0.1,0.0,0.0,6.4,11.0,0.5,10.1,0.2,"12.0","Strawberry Punch #1 Recipe Instructions:  1: Allow strawberries to thaw for a couple of hours in refrigerator. 2: Prepare  lemonade  and chill. 3: Combine all just before serving and mix until sherbet is  dissolved. 4: Place ice ring in to keep punch cold.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2906,"Apple Bread Pudding","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apple Bread Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,10.0,1577.7,25.1,6.4,93.6,1664.4,301.4,22.9,59.4,44.9,"0.0","Apple Bread Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: In large bowl, toss bread cubes and apples  together. 3: In separate bowl, whisk together brown sugar and eggs. 4: Add evaporated  milk, skim milk, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and whisk again. 5: Pour egg/milk  mixture over bread cubes and apples. 6: Stir well and let stand 5 minutes for bread to absorb liquid. 7: Transfer mixture to an 8 x 8\ 8: ,  9: A knife inserted in the centre  should come out clean.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2907,"Apple Chutney","PT2H","PT30M","PT2H30M","Make and share this Apple Chutney recipe from Food.com.","Chutneys",5.0,4.0,4047.0,5.3,1.1,0.0,378.4,1019.0,50.8,888.1,23.1,"0.0","Apple Chutney Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel, core and chop apples. 2: Combine with tomatoes, onions, ginger, garlic, chilies, raisins, juices, brown sugar and vinegar in a large deep heavy-based pan. 3: Stir over low heat until sugar is completely dissolved. 4: Increase heat, stirring occasionally until mixture boils. 5: Simmer, uncovered, 2 hours or until fruit and vegetables are tender and chutney is thick. 6: Stir occasionally. 7: Allow to stand 5 minutes. 8: Using a jug, pour into warm sterilised jars and seal immediately. 9: Label and date jars when cool. 10: Store in a cool place for up to 12 months. 11: Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 12: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2908,"Apple Fantasy","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apple Fantasy recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",4.0,1.0,77.6,0.3,0.0,0.0,1.8,20.3,3.0,14.7,0.7,"4.0","Apple Fantasy Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve rice syrup into pineapple juice; then combine all ingredients but the strawberries in a bowl. 2: Let stand for a few minutes, mix again. 3: Set fruit mixture in individual dishes, garnish with berries. 4: Serve at once.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2909,"Cereal Apple Pie Bars","PT50M","PT1H","PT1H50M","A Land-O-Lake classic recipe. I''ve learned the hard way not to roll the crust out on waxed paper. Just make sure you flour the counter extremely well. The easiest way for me to move the crust from the counter to the pan is to fold it over, flour the top if necessary and fold it over again.","Bar Cookie",5.0,5.0,136.9,5.6,3.4,18.9,120.0,21.1,1.0,12.5,1.4,"0.0","Cereal Apple Pie Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: For crust, add enough milk to egg yolk to measure 2/3 cup; set aside. In medium bowl, combine flour and salt. Cut in butter until crumbly. 3: With fork, stir in milk mixture until dough forms a ball. You may need to add a few teaspoons more of milk if dough is still too dry. Divide into halves. 4: Roll out half of the dough, on lightly floured surface, into a 15x10-inch rectangle. Place on bottom of ungreased 15x10x1-inch jelly-roll pan. 5: For Filling, sprinkle cereal over top of crust; layer apples over cereal. In small bowl, combine 1 cup granulated sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon and nutmeg. Sprinkle over apples. 6: Roll remaining half of dough into a 15 1/2-10 1/2-inch rectangle; place over apples. 7: In small bowl, beat egg white with fork until foamy; brush over top crust. In another small bowl, stir together 2 tablespoons granulated sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle over top crust. Bake for 45 to 60 minutes or until lightly browned. 8: For Glaze, in small bowl, stir together all glaze ingredients. Drizzle over top crust while still warm. Cut into bars.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2910,"Strawberry Punch #2","0","PT2M","PT2M","Make and share this Strawberry Punch #2 recipe from Food.com.","Punch Beverage",0.0,0.0,2538.2,24.1,13.7,0.0,732.1,571.2,39.1,475.0,14.1,"0.0","Strawberry Punch #2 Recipe Instructions:  1: Put the sherbet in a bowl and pour the 7-Up over the sherbet. 2: Stir until the  sherbet is melted. 3: This makes a pretty pink punch.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2911,"Apple-Raisin Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apple-Raisin Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",0.0,0.0,349.4,14.3,4.7,7.6,270.2,55.4,4.1,29.8,3.2,"8.0","Apple-Raisin Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400 deg. 2: Roll out half the chilled pastry to a thickness of 3: 1/8-inch. 4: press into an 8-inch pie plate, and chill. 5: Roll out remaining pastry  with very sharp knife and make several vents in center. 6: Place top pastry on  parchment-lined baking sheet and chill. 7: Put apple slices and raisins in a  mixing bowl. 8: Sprinkle with sugar, and toss to mix well. 9: Pour this mixture into  the chilled bottom crust and dot with butter. 10: Carefully cover the apples with  the top pastry, trim and crimp edges to seal. 11: Bake 45-50 min. 12: or until pastry  is nicely browned and juices in center are bubbling. 13: Let cool slightly on wire  rack before serving. 14: -----");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2912,"Sour Cream Raisin Pie From Blue Gentian Restaurant","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sour Cream Raisin Pie From Blue Gentian Restaurant recipe from Food.com.","Pie",0.0,0.0,236.3,12.0,5.4,71.8,22.3,30.8,1.1,24.4,3.4,"10.0","Sour Cream Raisin Pie From Blue Gentian Restaurant Recipe Instructions:  1: Place all ingredients in a double boiler and stir until well mixed. 2: Cook until 3: the mixture is the consistency of a heavy cream filling and turns dark in color. 4: Stir occasionally. 5: Put the filling in a baked pie shell and top with meringue.  Bake until the meringue darkens.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2913,"Old Fashioned Raisin Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Old Fashioned Raisin Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,3.0,635.2,24.3,6.0,10.2,171.9,107.2,5.0,73.5,7.1,"6.0","Old Fashioned Raisin Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Divide the pastry almost in half and roll out the  larger half, on a lightly floured surface, to a 13-inch circle. Line  a 9-inch pie plate with the pastry and trim the pastry 1/2 inch beyond  the rim of the pie plate. Combine the raisins, brown sugar, corn  starch and drink mix in a 3-quart saucepan. 2: Stir in the water and lemon  juice. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture boils  and thickens. 3: Remove from the heat and stir in the walnuts. 4: Turn the  mixture into the pastry-lined pie plate and dot with the butter. 5: Roll out the remaining pastry to an 11-inch circle. Place the top crust  over filling and trim the edge to 1-inch beyond the rim. 6: Fold the top crust  under the bottom crust and form a ridge. Flute the edge and cut steam  vents in the top crust. Bake in a preheated 400 degree F. 7: oven for 30  minutes or until the crust is a golden brown and the filling is bubbly. 8: Cool  on a wire rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2914,"Raisin Pie (Rosina Pie, "Funeral Pie")","PT40M","PT3H","PT3H40M","This is an adopted recipe from the Great Recipezaar Adoption Programme. I''ve read a lot about the Funeral Pie and when it was up for adoption, I grabbed it.","Pie",0.0,0.0,1802.3,5.9,1.7,186.0,688.0,446.3,9.1,387.4,14.8,"0.0","Raisin Pie (Rosina Pie, "Funeral Pie") Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash raisins and soak in cold water for 3 hours.  Drain. 2: Combine the 2 cups water, the raisins, sugar and flour which have  been mixed together, salt, lemon juice and rind, and the egg.  Mix thoroughly and cook over hot water for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. 3: Cool. Pour into pastry-lined pan. Cover with narrow strips of dough, crisscrossed. 4: Bake at 450-F for 10 minutes. 5: Reduce heat to 350-F and bake 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2915,"Spaetzle (Homemade Noodles)","PT30M","PT0S","PT30M","Make and share this Spaetzle (Homemade Noodles) recipe from Food.com.","German",0.0,0.0,1710.4,56.0,15.0,1116.0,3448.6,223.9,8.7,4.4,69.5,"0.0","Spaetzle (Homemade Noodles) Recipe Instructions:  1: Place flour and salt in mixing bowl, add eggs and beat with a large  spoon. 2: Add water, as needed, mixture should be stiff. 3: (beat from  bottom to top to put air in dough) season with marjoram and let rest. 4: Bring a saucepan of salted water to a boil, reduce the heat, and maintain a simmer.  Place a colander over the pan, pour about 1/4 of the batter into the colander, and press through the holes with a plastic spatula into the hot water. 5: When the spaetzle starts to float to float to the surface, cover the pan and keep covered until the spaetzle appears to swell and is fluffy. Remove the dumplings and repeat the procedure with the remaining batter.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2916,"Spaetzle II","PT15M","PT20M","PT35M","Basic Spaetzle and how to serve     while you make the schnitzel. We have a spaetzle press that is similar  to a potato ricer with a little larger holes. My mother-in-law would  put dough on a smooth rim plate and tip the plate till it started to  slide off and cut off the dough in slivers with a butter knife into the  boiling water. When they float they are done and can be skimmed off and  put in a bowl. Melt the margarine in a pan and stir in breadcrumbs,  pour mixture over spaetzle. (posted by John Reynolds)","German",5.0,5.0,528.0,6.1,1.8,186.0,657.3,96.0,3.5,0.6,19.2,"0.0","Spaetzle II Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift flour into large bowl, make a depression in the center, and into it  break the eggs. 2: Add salt, pepper and nutmeg, and 1 cup water, or enough  to make a medium batter. 3: Beat the batter only until it is smooth. 4: Pour  the batter into a colander with large holes and let the Spaetzle fall  directly into a pot of simmering stock. 5: Stir gently so that they do not  stick together. 6: When the Spaetzle rise to the surface they are  sufficiently cooked. 7: Drain the Spaetzle well, put them in a heated  vegetable dish, and pour 1/2 cup melted butter over them.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2917,"Spaetzle (Tiny Dumplings)","PT10M","PT10M","PT20M","Make and share this Spaetzle (Tiny Dumplings) recipe from Food.com.","German",0.0,0.0,2241.8,38.2,13.6,880.2,3523.1,376.8,15.0,9.2,86.3,"0.0","Spaetzle (Tiny Dumplings) Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine the flour, 1/2 the salt, and the nutmeg in a large mixing bowl. 2: Beat the eggs into the flour mixture. 3: Add the milk in a thin stream, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon and continue to stir until the  batter is smooth. 4: Bring 2 quarts (2 L) of water with the remaining salt  to a boil in a 4 to 5 quart (4-5 L) saucepan over high heat. 5: Place a  large colander (with large holes) over the saucepan and press a few  tablespoons of batter at a time through the holes with a spoon or rubber spatula.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2918,"Kasespaetzle (Cheese Spaetzle)","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Make and share this Kasespaetzle (Cheese Spaetzle) recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",0.0,0.0,1592.4,84.3,47.6,478.8,2062.8,113.4,4.9,6.2,92.0,"0.0","Kasespaetzle (Cheese Spaetzle) Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare spaetzel: Combine the dry ingredients (add a bit of nutmeg to taste if doing it for German Cooking, omit if for Hungarian) 2: Add the milk and egg and mix together into a batter of sorts. 3: Meanwhile, have a wide pan of water with salt boiling. 4: Take the batter and put it into a spaetzle maker, or I used a French  fry basket, and rubbed it with the bottom of a spatula to break it up. 5: When the Spaetzle float, remove with a slotted spoon and put them into a colander. 6: Fry onion in a little oil until very brown and crispy.Set aside. 7: In heavy (preferably non-stick) skillet, heat spaetzle in a little butter. 8: Grate cheese and toss into spaetzle. 9: When cheese melts, transfer to large bowl and sprinkle with onion. 10: Serve hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2919,"Twice-Baked Potatoes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Twice-Baked Potatoes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",0.0,0.0,226.8,10.6,6.7,30.1,144.2,27.7,2.5,1.3,6.2,"2.0","Twice-Baked Potatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: Scrub baking potatoes with a brush. 2: Prick with a fork in several   places. 3: Place potatoes in a shallow baking dish. 4: Micro-cook,   uncovered, on 100% power for 6 to 8 minutes or till potatoes are   tender. 5: Cut a lengthwise slice from the top of each potato. 6: Discard   the skin from the lengthwise slices, place the potato portions from   the lengthwise slices in a mixing bowl. 7: Scoop out the insides of the   potatoes leaving two 1/4-inch thick shells; reserve the shells. 8: Add   the insides of the potatoes to the mixing bowl containing the potato   portions from the top slices; mash. 9: Stir in shredded cheddar cheese,   butter or margarine and sliced green onion. 10: Beat in enough milk to   give the mixture a stiff consistency. 11: Season to taste with salt and   freshly ground pepper. 12: Pile the mashed potato mixture into the   reserved potato shells. 13: Return to the shallow baking dish. 14: Micro-cook, uncovered, on 100% power for 2 to 3 minutes or till   potato mixture is heated through. 15: Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2920,"Light Twice-Baked Potatoes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Light Twice-Baked Potatoes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",2.0,1.0,152.9,8.3,5.1,16.8,79.8,17.6,1.4,1.9,2.7,"8.0","Light Twice-Baked Potatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 400 degrees. 2: Prick potatoes with fork to allow steam to   escape Bake for 60 to 75 minutes or until fork tender. 3: Reduce oven   temperature to degrees. 4: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; let cool   about 15 minutes. 5: Using spoon, scoop out inside of potatoes, leaving a   shell; set aside shells. 6: In large mixer bowl, combine potatoes, sour   cream, butter, 1 T chives, salt an pepper (if desired). Beat at   medium speed until smooth (1 to 2 minutes). shells with potato   mixture. Place on coo kie sheet. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until   heated through. 7: Sprinkle with chopped chives and paprika if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2921,"Marks Twice Baked Potatoes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Marks Twice Baked Potatoes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,6.0,451.3,30.7,18.5,94.3,496.0,31.2,3.1,2.4,14.3,"4.0","Marks Twice Baked Potatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: Bake potatoes until slightly softened or microwave 12 minutes. 2: Slice in two lengthwise. Mix shredded cheese and remaining   ingredients together in a mixing bowl, reserving 1 tablespoon of   Parmesan and the paprika. 3: Scoop out potatoes and put hot scoops in   with cheese mixture. Cut in well with a knife until well blended. 4: Fill potato shells with mixture, top with remaining Parmesan and   paprika. 5: Place in a well greased casserole dish and bake at 350 for   30 minutes or until browned. 6: MMMMM  MMMMM----- Recipe via Meal-Master (tm) v8.06");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2922,"Twice-Baked Potatoes II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Twice-Baked Potatoes II recipe from Food.com.","Potato",4.0,1.0,237.2,10.1,5.7,28.1,732.9,29.6,2.5,1.8,7.8,"2.0","Twice-Baked Potatoes II Recipe Instructions:  1: Between 2 layers of paper towel, cook bacon 1 1/2 minutes on High   until crisp. 2:  3: Crumble bacon coarsely; set aside 4: With fork, pierce   potatoes in several places. 5: Cook, on clean paper towel, on High 6-8   minutes; (turn potatoes over halfway through cooking. 6: Cut off top   fourth of each potato; scoop out potato from shells and tops;   reserve shells. 7: In medium bowl, mash potato with milk, sour cream,   onion and salt/pepper. 8: Spoon mixture back into shells. 9: Top each   with cheese and bacon. 10: Cook on High 2-3 minutes until hot and cheese   melts.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2923,"Pickled Apples","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pickled Apples recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,2379.6,4.1,0.9,0.0,38.2,592.5,25.8,552.3,3.3,"4.0","Pickled Apples Recipe Instructions:  1: Take ripe, hard, sweet apples. 2: Peel evenly, and if the apples are perfect leave  them whole, otherwise cut into quarters. 3: To a peck of apples take about two  quarts of vinegar and four pounds of sugar, half an ounce of mace, half an ounce  of cloves and the same amount of allspice, all unground, one teaspoonful of  mustard seed, a few pepper grains and a little salt. Heat the vinegar and sugar  together until it boils, skim well, put the spices into a thin muslin bag and  add to the vinegar, then put in the apples. 4: Place over the fire, and stew slowly  until the apples are soft. Then take out the apples, let the vinegar boil down  and pour over the fruit; cover and put away.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2925,"Pickled Peaches or Pears","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pickled Peaches or Pears recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,269.1,0.3,0.0,0.0,0.6,67.5,1.7,66.2,1.0,"4.0","Pickled Peaches or Pears Recipe Instructions:  1: place all the sugar and vinegar over the fire till it comes to a boil 2: add a layer of fruit and cook until soft enough to easily run a fork through 3: then remove the fruit, and fill the same way until all are done. 4: The syrup needs no more cooking. 5: Stick cloves in the fruit before cooking and add cinnamon to the syrup, if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2926,"Pickled Watermelon Rind","PT30M","PT36H","PT36H30M","--Adopted Recipe--       I used to make watermelon rind pickle, but my recipe is in the group of my recipes that is &quot;hiding&quot; from me.  I will try to figure out how much rind, but I am guessing it is the peeled rind of one melon, and have changed the directions to reflect this.  I have also added the step of soaking overnight in salt water.  Amount of salt is approximate, but I never made any kind of pickle without any salt, as this recipe originally was written.  Everything in this recipe is subject to change when I find my recipe.  I have simply made some changes to try to make the recipe a little clearer, because I don''t want someone to waste time and ingredients on a recipe that really seemed to be missing some ingredients and some steps.  Preparation time includes standing time.","Melons",3.0,2.0,117.7,0.3,0.1,0.0,570.9,29.7,1.8,26.6,0.2,"50.0","Pickled Watermelon Rind Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel the hard rind from the outside of the watermelon, and scrape off most of the pink from the inside.  Chop into 3/4-1 inch pieces. 2: Add salt to water and pour over watermelon rind in a large glasss or ceramic bowl.  Soak overnight in the refrigerator. 3: In the morning, pour off the salt water and rinse well. 4: Add three pounds of brown sugar to the vinegar in a cooking pan. Bruise the spices, tie in a muslin bag and boil with the vinegar for five minutes. 5: Then pour over the rind and let it stand twenty-four hours at room temperature. 6: The next day, drain and save the liquid and, after heating it to a boil again, pour it over the rind again and let stand another twenty-four hours at room temperature. 7: The last morning, bring to a full boil and boil all together for 10 minutes, then pour into sterilized jars and process according to the directions in a reputable canning guide.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2927,"Pickled Muskmelon","PT30M","PT15M","PT45M","Make and share this Pickled Muskmelon recipe from Food.com.","Melons",0.0,0.0,816.8,0.0,0.0,0.0,6.8,200.1,0.0,199.7,0.0,"4.0","Pickled Muskmelon Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil vinegar and sugar together for five or ten minutes. 2: Drop in the sliced muskmelon and boil until tender. 3: Last of all, drop in whole cloves and cinnamon bark. Let all boil a few minutes longer, then put in jars and seal, and you have as nice a pickle as peaches.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2928,"Bibby''s Yellow Squash Bake","PT45M","PT5M","PT50M","Make and share this Bibby''s Yellow Squash Bake recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",4.0,1.0,150.6,8.7,4.5,121.0,101.2,14.3,3.1,8.8,6.4,"0.0","Bibby''s Yellow Squash Bake Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute onion in butter. 2: Add sliced squash. 3: Cover and cook  slowly until just tender. 4: Beat eggs with sugar and seasonings. 5: Combine with squash in buttered casserole. Sprinkle top with bread  crumbs, crushed potato chips, etc. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2929,"Crookneck Yellow Squash","PT30M","PT20M","PT50M","Make and share this Crookneck Yellow Squash recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,253.3,6.6,2.1,143.9,365.7,36.9,5.4,4.1,12.2,"0.0","Crookneck Yellow Squash Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook squash with onion until tender in a very little salted, boiling water. 2: Mix the American cheese and eggs into a white sauce. 3: Drain squash and combine with white sauce. 4: Turn into a greased baking dish;  sprinkle with crumbs and Parmesan cheese. 5: Bake at 350F for about 30 minutes until browned.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2932,"Marlin (or Shark) Espanole","0","PT0S","PT0S","Marlin is very firm fleshed so you can use your favourite tuna or swordfish recipe. It  grills very nicely.","Canadian",5.0,2.0,44.7,2.4,0.3,0.0,422.8,5.7,1.4,3.3,1.0,"6.0","Marlin (or Shark) Espanole Recipe Instructions:  1: Place fish in glass baking dish. 2: Heat oil in skillet; add onion and 3: green pepper: saute 2-3 minutes. 4: Add remaining ingredients and pour   sauce over steaks. 5: Bake at 350 F for 15 minutes, or until fish flakes   easily when tested with a fork.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2933,"Pacific Blue Marlin (Kajiki)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Marlin is very  firm fleshed so you can use your favourite tuna or swordfish recipe. It  grills very nicely.","< 15 Mins",5.0,4.0,111.2,11.1,6.5,98.8,160.0,0.5,0.1,0.2,2.7,"5.0","Pacific Blue Marlin (Kajiki) Recipe Instructions:  1: Lightly season fish with garlic salt and pepper. 2: Then dust in flour  and roll in egg. 3: Next roll in bread crumbs. 4: Heat skillet and melt butter. 5: Squeeze lemon juice in and add about   1/2 the capers. 6: Cook 1/2 the fish then add the rest of the capers and   cook the other half. 7: Be careful to not overcook as Marlin is easy to   turn into leather if you do!   Capers: Sort of like little olives. 8: Expensive but it only takes a   bit in a dish so worth it. If you don''t have any, you might try green   olives for a similar effect but use more and chop fine.");
