INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2940,"Caraway Cabbage Soup with Lemon Dill Spaetzle","PT1H","PT10M","PT1M","Make and share this Caraway Cabbage Soup with Lemon Dill Spaetzle recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.0,1.0,374.6,5.6,2.1,129.7,1005.7,65.7,3.9,3.2,14.2,"6.0","Caraway Cabbage Soup with Lemon Dill Spaetzle Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine cabbage, onions, caraway seeds, diced tomatoes, carrots, and 1  teaspoon chopped dill. 2: Spaetzle: Sift flour and salt into bowl. 3: Make a well in the center. 4: Combine lukewarm milk and water with eggs and pour into the well. 5: Stir  in flour, lemon, and remaining dill. 6: Beat dough until bubbles start to  form. 7: Force through colander into boiling salted water. 8: When spaetzle  noodles float, remove them from the boiling water and cool. 9: Soup: Heat ham stock in large pot. Add garnish to soup stock and simmer  for one hour. 10: Add spaetzle and serve");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2942,"Pork Medallions with Herbed Spaetzle - Emeril","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pork Medallions with Herbed Spaetzle - Emeril recipe from Food.com.","Pork",0.0,2.0,300.0,13.1,2.1,46.5,215.9,37.4,1.9,1.8,7.6,"4.0","Pork Medallions with Herbed Spaetzle - Emeril Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: Pound pork medallions to 1/2-inch  thickness, if necessary. 3: Season pork medallions with about 1 tablespoon  Bayou Blast. Season the flour, egg wash and bread crumbs with 1  tablespoon Creole seasoning each. 4: Dredge pork in seasoned flour, dip in  egg mixture, then coat thoroughly with crumbs, shaking off excess after  each layer. 5: Refrigerate while you prepare Herbed Spaetzle. In an  ovenproof saute pan heat oil, add pork and cook until first side is  golden. 6: Turn medallions and transfer pan to oven to finish cooking. 7: Serve pork on top of Herbed Spaetzle.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2943,"Roasted Pork Loin with Bacon and Onion Spaetzle","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Roasted Pork Loin with Bacon and Onion Spaetzle recipe from Food.com.","Pork",1.5,2.0,1185.8,93.5,29.6,213.3,1051.1,19.4,4.6,3.7,60.7,"4.0","Roasted Pork Loin with Bacon and Onion Spaetzle Recipe Instructions:  1: Prehaet the oven to 400 degrees. 2: For pork loin: Season the entire loin  with olive oil and salt. In a hot saute pan, sear the loin for 1-2  minnutes on each side. Remove from pan and crust the loin with cracked  black pepper. 3: Place in a roasting pan. 4: Roast the loin for 25 to 30  minutes for medium. 5: Remove from the oven and allow to rest for 10  minutes. 6: For the spaetzle: In a hot large pan, render the bacon until  crispy, remove the bacon from the pan. 7: In the bacon fat, saute the  onions for 2-3 minutes. 8: Stir in the bacon. 9: Season.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2944,"Sea Bass in a Sesame Seaweed Spaetzle Crust","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sea Bass in a Sesame Seaweed Spaetzle Crust recipe from Food.com.","Bass",0.0,0.0,549.6,17.5,5.3,175.7,185.3,57.4,2.3,0.5,38.0,"4.0","Sea Bass in a Sesame Seaweed Spaetzle Crust Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix flour, milk and eggs until a sticky batter is formed. 2: Crush Nori  and mix with sesame seeds and add to batter. 3: Push batter through  colander holes over boiling, salted water. 4: When droplets float to the  top, remove and drain. 5: Spread mashed potato on one side of each filet  and press spaetzle into potato. 6: Heat oiled skillet and place fish,  spaetzle side down. 7: Cook until golden brown, about 2 to 3 minutes. 8: Flip  over and place skillet in a preheated 400 degree oven until fish is  cooked, about 4 to 5 minutes. 9: Drizzle with Lemongrass Dressing. 10: LEMONGRASS DRESSING: Blend all ingredients in a blender and pass through  a strainer. 11: Serve over bass.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2945,"Yellow Squash Casserole","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Yellow Squash Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",5.0,6.0,1473.4,105.5,46.5,168.4,3112.6,89.8,11.7,39.4,52.4,"0.0","Yellow Squash Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil squash. 2: Saute onion and pepper in butter. 3: Make  white sauce and add cheese. Mix squash, onion, pepper and  pimiento with cheese sauce. Put buttered cracker crumbs on  top. 4: Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2946,"Stuffed Yellow Squash","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Stuffed Yellow Squash recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,2.0,2256.8,141.7,38.2,255.2,2588.9,156.5,27.9,60.5,104.2,"0.0","Stuffed Yellow Squash Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt margarine in frying pan, add rice, salt, pepper,  garlic powder and steak that has been cut into small cubes. 2: Mix thoroughly. 3: Wash squash, cut necks off and set aside.  With a teaspoon, scoop the pulp (seeds) from bottom of the  squash, making a shell. 4: Discard pulp and seeds. 5: Fill shells with rice-steak mixture and put 2 toothpicks  crisscross across top to hold filling in shells. 6: Put shells and  tops in Dutch oven. 7: Run tomatoes through blender, then pour  over squash. 8: Bring to boil, then simmer for about 1 hour, or  until rice is tender.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2947,"Chicken Enchiladas","PT25M","PT20M","PT45M","Make and share this Chicken Enchiladas recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",4.0,2.0,349.7,13.4,5.2,61.3,1060.4,33.2,1.4,3.5,24.5,"8.0","Chicken Enchiladas Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine chicken, 1/2 cup picante sauce, soup, yogurt, green pepper and  seasonings; mix well. 2: Fill tortillas. 3: Top with remaining picante sauce. Cover  with foil and bake at 350F for 25 minutes. 4: Remove foil and top with cheese;  let stand 5 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2948,"Numero Uno Chili Con Carne With Beans","PT2H20M","PT20M","PT2H40M","Make and share this Numero Uno Chili Con Carne With Beans recipe from Food.com.","Tex Mex",5.0,4.0,1627.8,133.1,51.3,276.8,1962.2,42.6,14.6,11.4,67.0,"6.0","Numero Uno Chili Con Carne With Beans Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large skillet, over med. 2: heat, warm the oil. 3: Add onions and cook,  stirring occasionally, until tender, about 20 minutes. 4: Meanwhile in a 4  to 5 quart heavy flameproof casserole or Dutch oven over med. heat, combine  beef and pork. 5: Season with salt and cook, stirring often, until meat has  lost all its pink color and is evenly crumbled, about 20 minutes. 6: Scrape  onions into casserole with meats. 7: Stir in chili powder, cumin, oregano,  cocoa, cinnamon and cayenne pepper. 8: Cook, stirring, 5 minutes. 9: Stir in  tomato juice and beef stock. 10: Bring to a boil then lower heat and simmer,  uncovered, for 1 hour. 11: Taste, correct seasonings and simmer another 30  minutes or until chili is thickened to your liking. 12: Stir in garlic. To  thicken chili further or to bind any surface fats, stir in the optional  cornmeal. 13: Stir in the beans and simmer another 5 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2949,"Senator Barry Goldwater''s Expert Chili Con Carne With Beans","PT5H","PT20M","PT5H20M","Make and share this Senator Barry Goldwater''s Expert Chili Con Carne With Beans recipe from Food.com.","Tex Mex",3.0,1.0,833.2,55.6,22.6,74.9,323.9,60.3,15.3,7.7,25.0,"6.0","Senator Barry Goldwater''s Expert Chili Con Carne With Beans Recipe Instructions:  1: Soak beans in water overnight. 2: In a large Dutch oven, cook beef until browned, stirring to keep crumbly. 3: Drain off drippings, if needed. 4: Add tomato paste, onions and drained beans. 5: Mix chili powder, cumin and season to taste with salt. 6: Stir into mixture. 7: Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer until beans are tender, about 5 hours.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2950,"Spicy Pork and Black Bean Chili","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Spicy Pork and Black Bean Chili recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,22.0,353.7,17.8,5.3,58.8,163.6,24.9,7.8,4.8,24.4,"8.0","Spicy Pork and Black Bean Chili Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large pot, cover beans with water and bring to boil; cook for 2  minutes. 2: Cover and remove from heat.  Let stand 1 hour. 3: Drain liquid and cover with 8 cups of cold water. 4: Bring to  a boil, reduce heat and let simmer for about 1 1/2 hours or until beans are  tender. 5: Drain and reserve. Meanwhile, heat oil in a large saucepan on high  heat and brown meat cubes on all sides. 6: Remove from pan and set aside. Add  onions and garlic to pan; cook on medium heat until tender about 5 minutes. 7: Add chili powder, paprika, oregano, cumin and chili pepper flakes; cook,  stirring for 1 minute. Return meat to pan along with tomatoes, including  juice, stock and vinegar. 8: Bring to boil, let simmer, partly covered, for 1  1/2 hours or until meat is tender. 9: Add beans and peppers; season with salt  and pepper. 10: Cover and cook 15 minutes more or until peppers are tender. 11: Add  chopped parsley or chopped coriander.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2951,"Wendy''s Chili","PT3H","PT15M","PT3H15M","Make and share this Wendy''s Chili recipe from Food.com.","Tex Mex",4.5,4.0,975.9,84.0,34.0,112.4,1375.9,37.3,10.0,14.5,19.8,"6.0","Wendy''s Chili Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown beef in oil. 2: Break meat into tiny rice size pieces. 3: Place onion soup and half of cooked beef into a blender and process on high speed until it resembles cement mortar. 4: Place with unblended beef into 2-1/2 qt saucepan. 5: Add remaining ingredients and simmer until flavors are blended.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2952,"Emerald Fried Rice","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Emerald Fried Rice recipe from Food.com.","Rice",5.0,1.0,1025.1,23.1,4.1,168.4,1502.9,174.9,3.3,0.5,23.5,"4.0","Emerald Fried Rice Recipe Instructions:  1: Sprinkle the finely shredded greens with 1 teaspoon salt and leave for 10  minutes, then squeeze out the liquid and chop finely. 2: Heat 1 tablespoon of oil  in a frying-pan or crepe pan. 3: Pur in the beaten egg and allow to spread thinly  over with a palette knife and cook the other side gently. 4: Remove the omelette  and cut into fine shreds. 5: Heat another tablespoon of oil in the frying-pan and  add the finely chopped greens. 6: Stir-fry for about 30 seconds, then remove from  the pan. 7: Heat the remaining oil in a wok until it is smoking. 8: Add the spring  onions, then the rice, and toss well together until the rice is heated through. 9: Add the remaining salt with the MSG, greens, omelette shreds and ham. 10: Toss all  together and serve hot on a serving dish.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2953,"Classical Chinese Fried Rice - Yang Zhou Chao Fan","PT10M","PT10M","PT20M","Make and share this Classical Chinese Fried Rice - Yang Zhou Chao Fan recipe from Food.com.","Rice",5.0,3.0,2504.8,110.5,20.9,855.4,993.4,95.7,1.7,0.2,262.0,"4.0","Classical Chinese Fried Rice - Yang Zhou Chao Fan Recipe Instructions:  1: Break up the lumps in the cooked rice (the goal is to try to separate cooked rice into individual grains). 2: Dice  roast pork. 3: Beat eggs. 4: Heat iron wok till smoking hot. 5: Swirl a ladle of cold oil in  the wok to coat the inside evenly. 6: Pour off the oil 7: Add 2 Tbsp oil to wok. 8: Pour the beaten egg into the hot wok. 9: Before the eggs are completely set, put in the rice, then the  roast pork and the fresh coriander. 10: Toss and turn the rice very quickly for about ten seconds with spatula. 11: Add the salt, light and dark soy sauce. 12: Toss and turn  the rice very quickly for about another ten seconds. 13: When you see some the rice  grains jumping up and down in the work (meaning the rice is really hot), add half  the broth. 14: Toss quickly for another ten seconds, and add the other half of the  broth. 15: Add another Tbsp oil and toss for a further 3 seconds.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2954,"Fried Rice Shoyu","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Fried Rice Shoyu recipe from Food.com.","Rice",0.0,0.0,611.5,3.8,0.8,43.2,80.1,127.5,3.5,1.4,12.9,"5.0","Fried Rice Shoyu Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oil in skillet; add beaten egg and scramble briefly. 2: Add all remaining  ingredients except shoyu. 3: Cook over medium heat 4 or 5 minutes, stirring gently. 4: Add shoyu; mix thoroughly. 5: Cook 2 minutes. 6: Serving Serves 5 people");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2955,"Nectarine Tart","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Nectarine Tart recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,2738.5,98.3,60.3,246.2,2355.7,460.6,19.1,318.9,23.7,"1.0","Nectarine Tart Recipe Instructions:  1: For crust, flour, sugar, nutmeg and salt into food processor and process  for 5 seconds. 2: Add butter and pulse until pea-size pieces form. 3: Use pulse  button to incorporate cold water until dough comes together. 4: Gather dough  into ball, flatten slightly and wrap in plastic wrap. 5: Chill one hour  before using. 6: Spray ceramic pie plate with cooking spray and set aside.  Between sheets of plastic wrap that have been lightly floured, roll out  dough into a 14-inch round. 7: Remove top sheet and turn dough oven into the  pie plate and gently press dough against bottom and side. Remove second  sheet of plastic (chilling for few minutes if sticky). There should be  about a 3-inch dough hangover. 8: Chill for 30 minutes. 9: Heat oven to 375 degree. Slice nectarines and stir in sugar, cornstarch  and nutmeg. 10: Let set 15 minutes. 11: Pour mixture into tart shell. 12: Fold up  dough to cover edges of tart leaving 4-inch opening in center. 13: Brush dough  with 1 Tbsp milk and sprinkle with 1 Tbsp sugar. 14: Place on baking sheet and bake  35-40 minutes until golden and bubbly. 15: Cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2956,"Pear Croustade","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pear Croustade recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,453.3,22.1,13.7,58.6,232.9,60.8,4.3,26.2,5.4,"4.0","Pear Croustade Recipe Instructions:  1: Make crust by mixing flour, sugar and salt in processor. 2: Add butter using  on/off turns until mixture resemble coarse meal. 3: Transfer to large bowl. 4: Mix egg yolk and ice water in small bowl. 5: Use fork to blend enough yolk  mixture, 1/2T at a time into flour mixture to form moist clumps. 6: Gather  dough into ball, flatten into disk, wrap in plastic and chill until firm,  about 1 hour. 7: Then position rack in center of oven and preheat to 400  degrees. 8: Roll out dough on floured parchment paper to 10-inch round. 9: Transfer dough on the paper to large baking sheet. For filling: Toss  pears, sugar, flour, lemon juice and allspice in large bowl. 10: Overlap pear  slices atop dough, leaving 2-inch board. 11: Fold dough border over fruit,  pleating loosely and pinching to seal any cracks. 12: Brush dough with egg  white. Drizzle cream or milk over filling. 13: For topping: Mix flour and  sugar in small bowl. 14: Rub in butter with fingers until small clumps form. 15: Sprinkle topping over filling. 16: Then bake start until crust is golden and  filling bubbles, about 40 minutes. 17: Transfer to rack and cool slightly,  about 15 minutes. 18: Slide metal spatula under crust to free from parchment.  Serve warm or at room temperature.  --Bon Appetit");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2957,"Apricot Custard Tart","PT25M","PT45M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Apricot Custard Tart recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,2997.3,148.1,50.0,531.9,1733.9,361.1,16.9,190.1,37.9,"1.0","Apricot Custard Tart Recipe Instructions:  1: For crust blend flour sugar and salt in processor 5 seconds. 2: Add butter,  cutting in using on/off turns until mixture resembled coarse meal. 3: Mix in  vanilla and enough water to form moist clumps. 4: Knead dough briefly on  work surface to combine and flatten into disk. 5: Cover with plastic and  chill until firm --at least two hours or 1/2 hour in freezer. 6: Preheat oven to 375 . 7: Roll out dough on lightly floured surface to 13-inch  round. 8: Transfer to 11-inch diameter tart pan with removable bottom. 9: Gently press dough into pan, trimming excess dough. 10: Freeze 30 minutes. 11: Place pan on baking sheet and bake until light golden about 25 minutes. 12: If crust bubbles, prick with tooth pick. 13: Cool crust.  For filling: Combine cream, 1/4 cup sugar, flour, brandy, yolk and  vanilla in processor and blend until smooth. 14: Arrange apricot pieces cut  side down in cooled crust. Pour custard over fruit. Sprinkle with  remaining 3 Tbsp of sugar. 15: Bake tart on baking sheet until apricots are  tender and filling is puffed and set --anywhere from 30 to 60 minutes. 16: Test with tooth pick. 17: Cool to room temper- ature. Brush pan bottom up to  free tart and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2958,"Lemon Chicken Skewers","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lemon Chicken Skewers recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",4.0,1.0,255.2,15.1,2.1,65.8,369.1,2.8,0.4,0.6,26.6,"8.0","Lemon Chicken Skewers Recipe Instructions:  1: In a medium bowl, combine 1/2 cup of the lemon juice, the oil, garlic,  salt and black pepper; mix well. 2: Add chicken; cover and marinate in the  refrigerator 1 hour. 3: Meanwhile, soak wooden skewers in the remaining 1/4  cup lemon juice 30 minutes. 4: Thread chicken equally onto each skewer. 5: Discard leftover marinade. Preheat grill to medium-high heat. Place  parsley in a shallow dish and roll skewered chicken in parsley, coating  completely. 6: Grill chicken skewers 2 to 3 minutes per side, or until no  pink remains.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2959,"Lemon Herbed Salmon","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lemon Herbed Salmon recipe from Food.com.","High Protein",4.0,2.0,281.4,13.3,6.9,44.5,558.1,25.6,1.9,2.2,14.5,"8.0","Lemon Herbed Salmon Recipe Instructions:  1: In a bowl, combine bread crumbs, garlic, parsley, Parmesan cheese, thyme,  lemon peel and salt; mix well. 2: Add 4 Tbsp butter and toss lightly to  coat; set aside. Pat salmon dry. 3: Place skin side down in a greased baking  dish. 4: Brush with remaining butter; cover with crumb mixture. Bake at 350F  for 20-25 minutes or until salmon flakes easily with a fork.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2960,"Benigno Family Biscotti","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Benigno Family Biscotti recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,731.9,35.7,7.2,139.5,616.9,90.6,3.2,38.5,14.4,"8.0","Benigno Family Biscotti Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter; add eggs. 2: Add sugar, and beat well. 3: Sift flour and 4: baking powder together; add to bowl gradually, beating at med/low  speed. 5: Add nuts and Anisette; mix well. 6: Using two (2) cookie sheets, spoon dough out into four (4) straight  lines (loaf-style). Bake at 375 for 25 minutes. 7: Cool for 10 minutes,  then slice into 1\ 8: Keeps well for up to 6 weeks, or can be frozen. 9: I use my KitchenAid to do this dough - makes it a snap!  ---------- Recipe via Meal-Master (tm) v8.02");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2961,"Biscotti Del Laggaccio","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Biscotti Del Laggaccio recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,2318.6,51.6,29.9,122.0,1190.8,416.3,13.9,100.9,46.5,"1.0","Biscotti Del Laggaccio Recipe Instructions:  1: In the bowl of an electric mixer proof the yeast in the water  for 5 minutes, or until the mixture is foamy. 2: Whisk in the flour and let the  sponge stand, covered with plastic wrap, for 30 minutes or until it is foamy. 3: To the sponge, add the sugar, the water and the butter and stir the mixture  until it is combined well. 4: Add the flour, the aniseed, and the salt and with the  electric mixer fitted with the dough hook knead the dough for 3 minutes, or  until it is smooth but still sticky. 5: Transfer the dough to a lightly oiled bowl,  turning it to coat it with the oil, and let it rise, covered tightly with  plastic wrap, for 1 1/2 hours, or until it is double in bulk. 6: Turn the dough  out onto a lightly floured surface, halve it, and with floured hands form each  piece of dough into a flattish log 15 inches long and 2 inches wide. Transfer  the logs to a buttered and floured baking sheet and let them rise, covered with  a kitchen towel, for 2 hours, or until they are double in bulk. 7: Bake the logs  in the middle of a preheated 350F oven for 30 minutes, or until they are golden  brown, and let them cool on the baking sheet on a rack for 10 minutes. 8: On a  cutting board cut the logs crosswise on the diagonal into 1 inch thick slices,  arrange the biscotti, cut sides down, on the baking sheet and bake them in the  350F oven for 10 minutes on each side, or until they are pale golden. 9: Transfer  the biscotti to racks to cool and store them in airtight containers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2962,"Chocolate-Covered Biscotti","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chocolate-Covered Biscotti recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,702.7,39.0,17.0,109.8,160.0,83.2,5.7,49.2,12.0,"8.0","Chocolate-Covered Biscotti Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large mixing bowl, stir together the sugar and melted butter. 2: Add the 3: Pernod, bourbon and anise seed. 4: Beat in the eggs, then stir in the nuts. 5: Sift  the dry ingredients together. 6: Gently stir in the dry ingredients until well  incorporated. 7: Cover with plastic wrap and chill for about three hours. 8: Preheat  the oven to 375 F. 9: Butter two cookie sheets. 10: Shape the dough on cookie sheets  into three loaves, well spaced. 11: Each loaf should be about two inches wide and  1/2\ 12: Bake for about 20 minutes, until the loaves puff up and brown. 13: When the loaves are cool enough to touch, cut each loaf into diagonal slices  about 1/2\ 14: ,  15: ,  16: ,  17: ,  18: ,  19: ,  20: Holding each cookie by  its bottom, gently dip the tops into chocolate. Turn immediately and allow to  dry, uncoated side down, on wax paper. 21: Repeat until all are done.   ---*The Cereal Murders*   Diane Mott Davidson  ---------- Recipe via Meal-Master (tm) v8.02");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2963,"Chocolate Biscotti","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chocolate Biscotti recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",3.0,2.0,52.4,0.4,0.2,0.0,48.1,12.2,1.0,5.6,1.2,"0.0","Chocolate Biscotti Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and baking baking powder. 2: Separately, mix  flavoring and eggs. 3:  4: Combine. Add splash of liquor or water as needed to have a  sticky consistency. 5: If the mixture is too stiff, it won''t spread out properly. 6: Put this glob on a greased cookie sheet and arrange it into a log about 15 inch  es long and 1 1/2 - 2\ 7: ,  8:  slices. 9: I got 18  pieces from mine. Place the slices on their side and put back in the oven (300  degrees) for 15 minutes. 10: Turn over and cook another 10-15 minutes. 11: If you can afford the fat, a small drizzle of semisweet chocolate is  wonderful on these when cooled. 12: I used about 2 Tbsp. for all the cookies,  which added about 6 g. fat to the recipe or 1/3 g. fat each one.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2964,"Queen''s Biscuits (Biscotti Di Regina)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Queen''s Biscuits (Biscotti Di Regina) recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,1.0,73.4,3.9,0.9,6.1,26.3,8.6,0.4,2.8,1.2,"72.0","Queen''s Biscuits (Biscotti Di Regina) Recipe Instructions:  1: Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets. 2: Sift together in a bowl the flour, sugar, baking 3: powder and salt. Cut in with pastry blender or two knives until pieces are size  of small peas. 4: Add shortening and stir in eggs and milk. 5: Make a soft dough. 6: Mix  thoroughly together. 7: Break dough into small pieces and roll each piece between  palms of hands to form rolls about 1-1/2-\ 8: ,  9: ,  10:  apart. Bake at 375~  for 12-15 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2966,"Blinde Vinken","PT1H10M","PT10M","PT1H20M","Make and share this Blinde Vinken recipe from Food.com.","Veal",4.0,1.0,300.9,13.6,2.9,115.6,293.2,33.4,0.6,0.9,11.8,"6.0","Blinde Vinken Recipe Instructions:  1: Sprinkle the veal cutlets with salt, and allow to stand in the refrigerator  for about 15 minutes. 2: Beat the egg yolks and soak the bread slices in  them. 3: Add the ground veal, peppers, nutmeg and the lemon juice. Mix  thoroughly. 4: Divide this evenly among the 8 cutlets and spread on each. 5: Roll the mixture inside the cutlets and secure each roll with a toothpick. 6: Beat the egg whites with a little water and brush this mixture over each of  the veal rolls. 7: Cover each roll with Dutch rusk crumbs. 8: Heat the  margarine in a large frying pan. 9: Brown each of the veal rolls, turning  them occasionally. 10: Remove them from the pan and set aside. Add a little  water to the pan and stir. 11: Put the veal rolls back into the pan and  add the lemon slices. 12: (You may have to add some more margarine at this  point) 13: Simmer the veal rolls, covered, for about 40 minutes, until they  are done. Remove veal rolls to a heated plate. Remove toothpicks. 14: Remove  the lemon slices and pour the gravy over the veal rolls. 15: Garnish with  parsley and serve with rice and beans.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2967,"Caribbean Coffee","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Caribbean Coffee recipe from Food.com.","Caribbean",5.0,2.0,37.8,1.2,0.8,4.9,27.4,4.4,0.0,4.7,2.2,"8.0","Caribbean Coffee Recipe Instructions:  1: Note: You can replace the coconut with packaged coconut and coconut milk,  but it won''t be as much fun to prepare.  Drive two holes into the coconut with a hammer and nail. 2: Drain the coconut liquid into a saucepan. 3: Bake whole coconut at 300 F. 4: for thirty minutes to release  coconut meat from hard shell. 5: Grate fresh coconut (about one cup).  Place saucepan over low heat and combine grated coconut, coconut liquid, and  milk. 6: Heat until creamy. 7: Strain, reserving both grated coconut under  broiler or in fry pan on top of range.In warmed mugs, blend hot coconut milk  with equal amounts of hot coffee. Sweeten with sugar. 8: Sprinkle with  toasted coconut.  Serves 8.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2968,"Chocolate Coffee II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chocolate Coffee II recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",5.0,1.0,136.4,6.9,4.3,17.1,88.4,15.8,0.8,8.4,4.7,"6.0","Chocolate Coffee II Recipe Instructions:  1: In saucepan combine coffee, sugar, salt, chocolate, and water; stir over  low heat until chocolate has melted. 2: Simmer 4 minutes, stirring constantly. 3: Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until heated. 4: When piping hot,  remove from heat and beat with rotary beater until mixture is frothy. 5: Pour  into cups and sail a dollop of whipped cream on the surface of each.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2969,"Cafe Borgatta","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Cafe Borgatta recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",4.0,1.0,82.7,3.5,2.1,10.6,52.1,11.6,0.9,10.0,2.9,"0.0","Cafe Borgatta Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat milk in a small saucepan. 2: Sift cocoa and sugar into milk and whisk to  blend. 3: Stir in espresso. 4: Divide equally into four small espresso or demitasse  cups. 5: Top with whipped cream and grated orange. Makes 4 servings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2970,"Cafe Au Lait","PT15M","PT5M","PT20M","Make and share this Cafe Au Lait recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",5.0,2.0,39.2,2.2,1.4,8.5,32.6,2.8,0.0,0.0,2.0,"0.0","Cafe Au Lait Recipe Instructions:  1: Brew coffee. Heat milk, almost to a boil. 2: Pour coffee and hot milk,  preferably simultaneously, into large cups or mugs. 3: Sweeten to taste.  If you like the frothy finish that traditional steam infusers give to cafe au  lait, whirl the hot milk in a blender (or use a whisk or hand mixer) before  filling cups.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2971,"Cafe Mexicano II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cafe Mexicano II recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",4.0,1.0,46.9,1.0,0.6,0.0,11.4,9.9,0.5,9.0,0.3,"8.0","Cafe Mexicano II Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat water, brown sugar, chocolate, cloves, and cinnamon to boiling in  3-quart saucepan; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes. 2: Stir  in coffee. Remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes. 3: Stir in  vanilla. 4: Strain coffee through 4 thicknesses of cheesecloth.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2972,"Lemony Salmon Patties","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lemony Salmon Patties recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,18.0,302.7,15.4,7.1,123.0,548.1,12.6,0.4,0.8,27.4,"8.0","Lemony Salmon Patties Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine the first nine ingredients; mix well. 2: Spoon into eight greased  muffin cups, using 1/4 cup in each. 3: Bake at 350 for 45 minutes or until  browned. 4: Meanwhile, melt butter in a saucepan; stir in the flour to form  a smooth paste. Gradually stir in milk; bring to a boil over medium heat,  stirring constantly. 5: Cook for 2 minutes or until thickened. 6: Remove from  the heat; stir in lemon juice, salt and cayenne. Serve over patties.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2973,"No-Bake Cereal Bars","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this No-Bake Cereal Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",4.5,10.0,5508.5,242.8,89.2,0.0,2394.4,855.5,52.6,507.2,98.1,"1.0","No-Bake Cereal Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan. 2: In large saucepan, combine corn syrup and sugar. 3: Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. 4: Cook until sugar is dissolved;  remove from heat. Add peanut butter; stir until mixture is smooth. 5: Add cereal;  mix well. 6: Immediately press into greased pan. 7: In medium saucepan over low heat,  melt chocolate chips, stirring constantly. 8: Spread evenly over bars. 9: Refrigerate  10 to 15 minutes, or cool completely at room temperature until chocolate is  set. Cut into bars.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2974,"Chocolate Mint Bars","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chocolate Mint Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",0.0,0.0,228.9,13.0,5.7,15.3,52.6,25.6,2.0,18.4,4.5,"0.0","Chocolate Mint Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350-F degrees and set aside a 9-inch by 13-inch cake pan. 2: In a  large mixing bowl, cream together the shortening, sugar, cocoa, and egg until  smooth. 3: Sift in the flour and mix until well blended. 4: Press the mixture firmly  into the bottom of the cake pan. 5: Bake for about 10 minutes, or until dry. 6: To  prepare the topping, combine the coconut, almonds, and mint chips in a bowl,  then sprinkle over the baked chocolate base.  In a separate mixing bowl, combine the sweetened condensed milk and peppermint extract. Pour the mixture evenly  over the top of the nuts and coconut.  Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until  golden. 7: Cool, then cut into bars.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2975,"Chocolate Chip Turtle Bars","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chocolate Chip Turtle Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",0.0,0.0,200.7,5.3,2.5,9.1,185.0,38.0,0.9,27.9,2.5,"0.0","Chocolate Chip Turtle Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 350 F (180 C). Grease a 9 x 13-inch (23 x 33 cm) pan with  shortening. 2: Place cooling rack on countertop. 3: Combine shortening, brown  sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. 4: Beat at medium speed of electric  mixer until well blended. 5: Beat egg into creamed mixture. Combine flour,  salt and baking soda. 6: Mix into creamed mixture just until blended. 7: Stir in  Hershey''s Chipets- small chocolate chips. 8: Divide dough into thirds. 9: Pat  2/3 of dough into the bottom of the prepared pan. 10: Combine caramels and  water in small saucepan. 11: Place on very low heat. Stir constantly until  caramels melt. Spread caramel mixture over dough in pan to within 1/2 inch  (1 cm) of edge. Divide remaining dough into measuri ng teaspoonfuls (5 mL)  and drop evenly over the caramel layer. 12: Bake at 350 F (180 C) for 25 to 30  minutes or until golden brown. 13: DO NOT OVERBAKE. 14: Loosen from sides of pan  with knife. Cool completely on rack. 15: Cut into bars.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2976,"Cr&egrave;me De Menthe Bars","PT30M","PT0S","PT30M","This recipe is an adoptee from the now-mostly-empty recipezaar account. As the commentator below notes, there were once serious problems with this recipe. I have worked with it a bit to come up with something that should work and should even, darn it, be good! Enjoy!","Bar Cookie",0.0,1.0,455.6,25.4,15.2,98.4,305.8,53.3,1.4,39.5,3.9,"18.0","Cr&egrave;me De Menthe Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease one 9x13-inch baking dish. 2: Beat the white sugar with 1 cup of the butter or margarine until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs. Then stir in the flour, salt, chocolate syrup and vanilla. Mix until combined. 3: Pour batter into the prepared pan and bake at 350° (175°C) for 30 minutes. Let cool then frost with Crème de Menthe Frosting (See below for recipe). Refrigerate until set. Then spread Melted Chocolate topping (see below) over top. Let sit until set and cut into bars. 4: To Make Crème de Menthe Frosting: Combine the confectioners'' sugar, 1/2 cup butter or margarine and crème de menthe. Mix until smooth. 5: # To Make Melted Chocolate Topping: Melt the chocolate chips and 6 tablespoons butter together. Stir until smooth and spread evenly over the top of the cooled filling. 6: Let set and cut into bars.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2977,"Key Lime Bars","PT45M","PT20M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Key Lime Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",4.0,5.0,132.0,5.8,3.4,37.1,58.7,19.0,0.2,12.8,1.6,"36.0","Key Lime Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: For CRUST: Mix 1 cup butter, 1/2 cup confectioners'' sugar & 2 cups of flour and pat into a 9x12-inch pan. 2: Bake at  350 degrees for 20 minutes. 3: Watch carefully! Beat together the eggs, sugar, and lime juice. Add the 4 Tbsp flour, salt, and baking powder. 4: Mix  and pour on top of the crust. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. 5: Sprinkle the top with confectioners'' sugar and cut into bars.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2978,"Hello (Aloha) Dollies","PT30M","PT10M","PT40M","Make and share this Hello (Aloha) Dollies recipe from Food.com.","< 60 Mins",5.0,2.0,150.8,11.2,5.9,12.9,53.2,12.4,1.1,11.1,1.9,"30.0","Hello (Aloha) Dollies Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 inch oblong baking pan. 2: Sprinkle the crumbs evenly over the butter to form the crust. 3: Evenly distribute in the order listed, the next ingredients (except for the milk), over the crust. 4: Remove the entire top of the can of condensed milk, and gently stir in the rum flavoring. 5: Drizzle the milk over the top of the last layer (coconut). 6: Bake at 350 for 30 minutes. 7: Cool before cutting into squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2979,"Five Layer Bars","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Five Layer Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",2.0,1.0,148.9,8.7,4.2,13.9,93.7,17.4,1.0,13.1,2.3,"36.0","Five Layer Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. Place butter in 13x9x2-inch baking 2: pan. 3: Heat in oven until melted; remove pan from oven. 4: Stir together  crumbs, cocoa and sugar; sprinkle evenly over butter. 5: Pour sweetened  condensed milk evenly over crumb mixture. Sprinkle with chocolate chips  and raisins. 6: Sprinkle nuts on top; press down firmly. 7: Bake 25 to 30  minutes or until lightly browned. 8: Cool completely in pan on wire rack. 9: Cover with foil; let stand at room temperature 6 to 8 hours. 10: Cut into  bars. 11: About 36 bars. 12: Variation:  Golden Bars: Substitute 1 cup Reese''s Peanut Butter Chips for chocolate  chips. 13: Sprinkle 1 cup golden raisins or chopped dried apricots over chips. 14: Proceed as above.  Hershey''s is a registered trademark of Hershey Foods Corporation. 15: Recipe  may be reprinted courtesy of the Hershey Kitchens. 16: Meal-Master compatible format by: Karen Mintzias  -----  ---------- Recipe via Meal-Master (tm) v8.04");
