INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2985,"Chicken a la King IV","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chicken a la King IV recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",4.0,1.0,647.6,12.7,4.6,90.9,1555.1,92.5,3.6,2.8,37.8,"4.0","Chicken a la King IV Recipe Instructions:  1: In 10 inch skillet, heat margarine, over med heat, until bubbly; add  onions and saute until translucent. 2: Add mushrooms and saute 1 min.  longer. 3: Add disolved flour (2 tbsp. water) and stir constantly, until  mixture smooth. 4: Stir in salt, paprika and pepp constantly, until  mixture begins to boil. 5: Reduce heat to low and stir in chicken  (shinned,boneless,diced), peas and pimientos. 6: Cook stirring  occasionally, until chicken and peas are thoroughly heated. 7: Serve hot.  Optional: Serve over 1/2 cup of rice per serving");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2986,"Chicken a la King V","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chicken a la King V recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",5.0,1.0,347.4,27.8,16.8,148.1,458.7,14.0,1.0,1.6,6.1,"5.0","Chicken a la King V Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter in top of double boiler. 2: Add flour and cook one minute. 3: Add chicken broth and cream. 4: Bring to a boil. 5: Set over hot water and  cook for 15 minutes. 6: Remove from heat and add beaten egg yolks,  pimento, mushrooms, green peppers, and chicken. 7: Season with sherry,  salt, pepper, and paprika to taste.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2987,"Chicken a la King Microwave","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chicken a la King Microwave recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",0.0,0.0,141.1,11.2,6.9,32.1,653.4,8.5,1.1,1.0,2.7,"4.0","Chicken a la King Microwave Recipe Instructions:  1: You can use puff pastry shells or muffins. 2: To Serve:  Place margarine in bowl (medium). Microwave at High 30 seconds, blend in flour, salt, and pepper. 3: Gradually stir in halfand half, water and instant bouillon. 4: Micro Medium High until thick, 4 to 6 minutes, stirring once.  Stir in chicken, mushrooms and pimientos. 5: Micro at Medium High 5 to 8 minutes, stirring once. Serve over muffins or pastry shells.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2988,"Sweet Potato Pie III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sweet Potato Pie III recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,2931.5,61.0,32.0,975.4,994.1,556.3,12.0,469.4,47.7,"1.0","Sweet Potato Pie III Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine sweet potatoes, milk, eggs, and sugar. 2: Beat at  high speed until mixed. 3: Add flavoring. 4: Mix baking powder  with 1 tablespoon of milk and add to potatoe mixture. Line  two 9-inch pie pans with your favorite pie crust, pour in mixture  and bake 1 hour at 375 degrees. 5: Serve with Cool Whip.");
