INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2998,"Mom''s Pizzelles","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Mom''s Pizzelles recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,292.9,20.4,4.5,89.3,247.1,25.2,0.2,24.7,3.3,"25.0","Mom''s Pizzelles Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat eggs and sugar until light and foamy. 2: Add melted margarine a little at a time. Add anise seed, anise flavoring, vanilla, grated rind and orange juice. Gradually add flour to make very light dough, light enough to drop on the pizzelle maker with a spoon. 3: Preheat pizzelle maker and grease with margarine just before using. 4: Use a knife to push down off from spoon. 5: (You can halve this recipe.).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(2999,"Greek Pastitsio","PT40M","PT20M","PT1H","Make and share this Greek Pastitsio recipe from Food.com.","Greek",4.5,4.0,1163.7,96.2,42.2,245.0,708.2,47.2,2.9,4.8,26.6,"6.0","Greek Pastitsio Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare macaroni according to directions. 2: Rinse with cold water; drain. 3: Stir flour into melted butter in a heavy saucepan. 4: Gradually stir in milk and cook until thickened, stirring occasionally. 5: Cover & cool the white sauce.  Brown the ground beef and onion in a large fry pan. 6: Pour off drippings. 7: Sprinkle salt, pepper, cinnamon, and oregano over beef. 8: Stir in tomato puree and cook slowly for 10 minutes. 9: Beat together egg, and 1/3 cup of Parmesan  cheese.  Gently stir in macaroni. 10: Gradually stir in 2 cups of the white sauce into the macaroni mixture. Place 1/2 macaroni mixture into a buttered 11-3/4 x 7-1/2 inch baking dish. 11: Spoon beef mixture in an even layer over macaroni. 12: Place remaining macaroni mixture over the beef. 13: Pour remaining white sauce over the top. 14: Bake in moderate 375* degree oven for 20 minutes. 15: Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese, and continue baking 20-25 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. 16: Let stand 15 minutes before cutting into squares. 17: **Can be doubled** From: Nancy and wwrecipes.com");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3000,"Creole Black Beans and Rice","0","PT0S","PT0S","This one of my favorite recipes. It is a crockpot recipe but I''m sure you  could cook it on the stovetop also. It''s pretty spicy.","Rice",5.0,12.0,480.1,22.6,7.4,46.4,1012.1,46.4,16.1,5.5,24.5,"0.0","Creole Black Beans and Rice Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown sausage in a skillet over med. 2: heat. Drain fat and transfer to  crockpot. Combine remaining ingredients in crockpot. Cover and cook on low 8  hrs. 3: or on high 4 hrs. 4: Remove bay leaves. 5: Serve over cooked rice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3001,"Salt Rising Bread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Salt Rising Bread recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",0.0,0.0,2066.2,36.9,13.3,32.5,921.2,368.4,13.3,22.6,57.3,"0.0","Salt Rising Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Scald 1 cup milk and pour over corn meal. 2: Let stand in warm place to  ferment, almost 24 hours. 3: Heat 3 cups milk until lukewarm, with salt,  sugar and Crisco. 4: Stir in 3 1/2 cups flour, then corn meal mixture. Place  bowl containing these ingredients in pan of lukewarm water for about 2  hours or until bubbles work up from the bottom. 5: Then stir in 5 cups flour  and knead in 2 1/2 cups. 6: Place dough in three 5 x 10-inch pans until it  has doubled in size. Bake in moderate oven for about 10 minutes; then  increase heat to moderately hot oven gradually. 7: Bake bread for 45 to 60  minutes in all. 8: Do not attempt to bake bread in cold damp weather, unless  house is warm. 9: Be sure to protect batter from drafts.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3002,"Mom Gourley''s Salt Rising Bread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Mom Gourley''s Salt Rising Bread recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",0.0,0.0,1723.3,111.9,31.3,34.2,9478.8,174.4,6.5,114.2,14.2,"0.0","Mom Gourley''s Salt Rising Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel potato and slice thin. 2: Add potato to the boiling water to which the 1 tablespoon sugar, meal and 1 tablespoon salt have been added. 3: Keep this mixing warm overnight or until ferments and smells. 4: Take out the slices of potato and add the cup of scalded milk and enough flour to make a stiff batter. 5: Keep warm until it rises. 6: Then add the warm water, shortening, 1 teaspoon salt and enough flour to make consistency of bread dough. 7: Put in greased pan and let rise. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3003,"Japanese Cabbage Salad II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Japanese Cabbage Salad II recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,3724.5,304.2,48.8,0.0,5965.1,233.5,36.1,85.7,42.9,"0.0","Japanese Cabbage Salad II Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix dressing and marinate sliced cabbage and chopped  onions for approximately 4 hours. 2: Toast sesame seeds, almonds  and Ramen noodles on cookie sheet at 400 degrees. 3: Toss toasted items  into marinated cabbage just before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3004,"Japanese Cabbage Salad III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Japanese Cabbage Salad III recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,352.6,28.0,4.7,0.0,375.5,23.2,3.7,8.5,4.4,"10.0","Japanese Cabbage Salad III Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix all ingredients 1/2 hour before serving. 2: Break noodles up. 3: Add dressing 10  minutes before serving. 4: Dressing:  4 Tbsp. sugar  1/2 cup sesame oil  1 tsp. pepp  er  6 Tbsp. vinegar  1/2 cup salad oil  salt to taste 5: Combine dressing items in a jar. 6: Add seasoning packets from Ramen noodles. 7: Add  boiled chicken breast for a main luncheon dish.");
