INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3007,"Turkey Sausage Quiche","PT25M","PT20M","PT45M","Make and share this Turkey Sausage Quiche recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",3.0,1.0,197.6,13.4,6.6,106.8,472.4,5.2,0.1,2.6,13.5,"0.0","Turkey Sausage Quiche Recipe Instructions:  1: Spray 9 x 13-inch dish with Pam. 2: Trim crust from bread. 3: Place crusts in blender and blend until crumbled. 4: Place bread  over bottom of dish. 5: Brown sausage and drain. 6: Layer over  bread. 7: Mix bread crumbs with remaining ingredients and pour  over bread and sausage. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes, or  until puffed and firm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3008,"Homemade Baked Ziti","PT1H","PT30M","PT1H30M","Make and share this Homemade Baked Ziti recipe from Food.com.","European",5.0,2.0,679.4,32.5,12.8,93.8,1524.4,62.6,5.8,11.6,35.0,"0.0","Homemade Baked Ziti Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F 2: To make the sauce: First, brown the ground beef and Port. Sausage in separate frying pans over medium heat.  Make sure the beef is in a large frying pan, and drain the fat. When the sausage is done, pat it dry with paper towels to remove the grease.  When the beef is just about done, grind the pepper over the beef, probably about 1 Tbsp worth. 3: Add about 1/2 to 1 Tbsp soy sauce and mix it in to  the beef. 4: You can replace the soy sauce with salt, but it adds a nice zing to the flavor. 5: At this point, I usually cut the onion into chunks and throw it into my Cuisinart with the garlic, and shred them to bits, and toss them in . 6: But sliced into small bits works well also. 7: Add the onion and garlic, and let cook down (covered) until the onion gets a little clear. 8: I add a little oil here sometimes, depending on how much fat was in the meat. Add the tomato paste, and mix it in . 9: I do the paste first because it makes it faster and easier to get the consistency right when the sauce comes in . 10: Add the sauce and mix it well. 11: Add generous amounts of the oregano and Italian Seasoning. 12: Don''t go overboard on the basil though. 13: Add the bay leaves. 14: Let it simmer. 15: Mix it, and let it simmer longer. 16: Start the water boiling for the ziti. 17: Add some salt and oil to the water to make it boil quicker, and to help keep the zitis from sticking. 18: Throw the green pepper, sausage, and mushrooms into the sauce. Next stir about 4 or 5 Tbsp Parmesan cheese in to the sauce. When the ziti is done, drain them and dump into a large rectangular Pyrex. 19: I don''t remember the exact size, but I think its around 9x18. 20: You may have a touch too many zitis, but they are delicious plain, so eat any extras. 21: Once the Parmesan has melted into the sauce and made it stringy, and the sauce has thickened, stir the sauce into the zitis. 22: Mix it all well. 23: Now, lay the sliced mozzarella over the ziti like shingles on a roof. 24: Sprinkle over some more Parmesan, maybe a tablespoons. 25: Bake at 350°F for 45 minutes to 1 hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3009,"Fig Preserves","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Fig Preserves recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",0.0,0.0,1215.0,1.4,0.3,0.0,1542.6,314.2,13.2,300.3,3.4,"0.0","Fig Preserves Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash figs in warm water with baking soda. 2: Rinse. Cut off stems. 3: Combine sugar,  lemon juice and water in heavy pot. Drop figs into syrup. 4: Cook until figs are  clear looking and syrup is thick (2 to 3 hours). Add lemon slices 1/2 hour  before figs are done. Seal in jars.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3010,"Dried Figs","PT72H","PT12H","PT84H","Make and share this Dried Figs recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",0.0,1.0,2322.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,7025.1,599.9,0.0,598.8,0.0,"0.0","Dried Figs Recipe Instructions:  1: Place figs in 1 quart of water in which salt has been dissolved. 2: Let stand  overnight. Drain. 3: Make a syrup of the sugar and 1 pint water. 4: Add figs and cook  gently until the syrup is m  ostly absorbed. 5: While cooking, watch carefully! Do  not stir, but lift kettle and shake figs. 6: Put on plates and turn daily until  dry. 7: Pack in powdered sugar.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3011,"Cuccidatti (Fig Cookies)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cuccidatti (Fig Cookies) recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,43.2,2.0,0.5,2.5,27.9,5.8,0.3,3.0,0.6,"0.0","Cuccidatti (Fig Cookies) Recipe Instructions:  1: Remove hard knob on one end of figs and discard. 2: Soak figs, raisins and dates in hot water for 1 hour. 3: Drain. 4: Put figs, dates and raisins through food grinder; add remaining ingredients, put through blender to puree. Mix well, it''s easier to prepare the fig filling one day and proceed the next day. 5: Refrigerate filling. 6: Sift flour, salt, granulated sugar and baking powder together in large bowl or kettle. Cut Crisco and margarine in with pastry blender (as for  pie crust). Make a well in center, add eggs, vanilla and milk. 7: Blend thoroughly using hands. 8: Roll out on floured surface into 3 x 10-inch rectangle about 1/8-inch thick. 9: Place filling in center, fold long edges to center and pinch edges to seal. 10: Cut 1 1/2-inch slices. 11: Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 350 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes. 12: Continue until dough and filling are used up. 13: Frost with a plain frosting: powdered sugar, milk and vanilla. 14: Garnish with sprinkles or jimmies. 15: Recipe can be divided in half. 16: Do not overcook. 17: Should be light in color.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3012,"My Favorite Roll out Sugar Cookies","PT7M","PT0S","PT7M","Make and share this My Favorite Roll out Sugar Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,25.0,74.1,4.0,0.8,3.9,72.3,8.8,0.2,3.7,0.8,"48.0","My Favorite Roll out Sugar Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream sugar and margarine; add egg and flavorings and mix well. 2: Stir dry ingredients; mix into sugar and margarine mixture. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. 3: Heat oven to 375°F. 4: Roll out 3/16-inch thick. 5: Bake 7-8 minutes until delicately brown. 6: Let cool. 7: Icing for Roll Out Sugar Cookies:  2 cups powdered sugar, milk and 1/2 tsp vanilla 8: Icing for Roll Out Sugar Cookies: In a mixing bowl, sift powdered sugar. 9: Gradually add milk, stirring continuously until mixture is the consistency of a thin glaze. Add vanilla. 10: Blend well. 11: Food coloring may be added, if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3013,"Pizzelles","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pizzelles recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,49.6,2.4,0.4,11.8,11.5,6.1,0.1,2.5,0.8,"0.0","Pizzelles Recipe Instructions:  1: Crack eggs into a large bowl and beat lightly by hand. 2: Add sugar and stir. 3: Add  oil and stir. 4: Next, stir in salt, vanilla and aniseeds. 5: Continue stirring and  add anise extract. Gradually add 6 cups of flour, mixing well after each cup. 6: Combine 1 cup flour with all of the  baking powder and add to dough. 7: The  addition of the last cup of flour will depend on the consisteny that you desire. A firmer dough  will produce a firmer/harder cookie. A thinner/stickier dough  will produce a thinner and crispier  cookie. This is a matter of personal  preference.  To bake pizelle: Heat a well-seasoned, pizelle iron. 8: The iron must be  well-seasoned to prevent cookies from  sticking. 9: Place a scant 1 tabl espoon of  dough to each section of the iron and \ 10: . 11: The amount of  baking time  required will depend on the pizelle maker. 12: The usual time is between 20 and 40   seconds. 13: Take care not to burn the cookie. Turn each cookie out onto a flat  surface to cool. 14: Cool thoroughly and store in an air-tight container.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3014,"Paella","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Paella recipe from Food.com.","Mussels",4.5,18.0,677.8,35.1,8.1,90.9,1506.5,53.2,4.1,6.0,36.1,"8.0","Paella Recipe Instructions:  1: In a bowl, combine olive oil, oregano, dry basil, garlic, salt and pepper. 2: Place  chicken and shrimp in another bowl; pour over marinade. Cover and refrigerate  overnight. Heat about 1 tablespoon marinade in frypan over medium heat. Remove  chicken and drain; add to pan and cook until lightly brown. 3: Remove from pan; set  aside. Add sausage to pan; cook over medium heat until well browned. 4: Add onions  and green pepper to pan; raise heat to medium-high; cook until vegetables are  soft. Stir in rice; brown slightly. 5: Add broth, tomatoes, saffron, coriander,  chicken and sausage; boil, cover, heat and simmer for 25 minutes, stirring  occasionally until rice is tender. 6: Add peas and scallops; toss gently. 7: Transfer  Paella to large ovenproof 6-quart baking dish or paella pan. 8: Drain shrimp; push  into rice mixture along with clams. 9: Bake, covered, in 350 degrees oven for 15 to  20 minutes, or until shrimp are pink and clams open. 10: Garnish with pimento  strips, if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3015,"Paella Los Porches","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Paella Los Porches recipe from Food.com.","Medium Grain Rice",5.0,1.0,747.9,15.1,2.3,0.0,91.5,136.8,10.4,6.1,17.5,"4.0","Paella Los Porches Recipe Instructions:  1: In a 14-inch paella pan or a skillet or casserole at least 14-inches in diameter and 2 to 2 1/2-inches deep, heat the oil over moderate heat. Add all the  vegetables and, stirring frequently for 1 minute. Add rice, salt, pepper and  water (saffron added to the boiling water before adding to casserole). Preheat  the oven to 400 degrees. 2: Set the pan on the floor of the oven and bake uncovered for 20 minutes or until liquid has been absorbed by the rice and vegetables. 3: At  no point should the paella be stirred after it goes in the oven. 4: When the paella is done, let it rest for 5 to 8 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3016,"Mashed Potatoes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Mashed Potatoes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",4.5,19.0,211.0,4.8,3.0,13.0,56.5,38.2,4.7,1.7,5.0,"6.0","Mashed Potatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil potatoes. 2: Drain and mash them with all the other ingredients to the consistency desired. 3: In general, the quantity of milk must be enough to obtain creamy mashed potatoes, but not too much ''as to make a soup. 4: So 1/2 cup of milk for 6 potatoes will be O.K. 5: I apologize because my English is not so good. 6: Greetings,                                Karina.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3017,"Crab-Stuffed Mushroom Bake","0","PT0S","PT0S","This recipe came from Southern Living Magazine years ago.....make copies of  it to take with you wherever you serve it!  They will ask for it","Crab",4.5,15.0,151.0,11.4,3.7,64.5,185.2,5.0,0.6,1.6,8.0,"6.0","Crab-Stuffed Mushroom Bake Recipe Instructions:  1: Gently rinse mushrooms, and pat dry. 2: Remove stems. 3: Brush caps with salad  oil, and place upright in a buttered baking dish. 4: Combine the egg, crab,  mayonnaise, onion, and lemon juice with 1/4 cup breadcrumbs. 5: Stuff the caps  with the mixture.  Combine the remaining 1/4 cup breadcrumbs  with the melted  butter. 6: Sprinkle over crab mixture.  Bake at 375 for 15  minutes. 7: They should  be a golden brown on the breadcrumb/butter topping. 8: Serve immediately. 9: Also, caution when they   are served. 10: There will be juice in the cap under the mixture which will be  VERY hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3018,"Japanese Hamburger Dish","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Japanese Hamburger Dish recipe from Food.com.","Japanese",4.0,2.0,737.3,68.8,27.4,99.9,483.1,18.3,4.1,0.7,13.1,"4.0","Japanese Hamburger Dish Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute almo  nds in butter or margarine in skillet until lightly browned. 2: Remove  from pan and set aside. Brown beef well in butter remaining in skillet. Stir in  water and salt and bring to a boil. 3: Stir in noodles. 4: Cover and simmer for 2  minutes. 5: Add vegetables. 6: Bring to a full boil over medium heat, separating  vegetables with a fork and stirring frequently. 7: Cover and simmer for 3 minutes. 8: Stir in soy sauce and sprinkle with almonds.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3019,"Chinese Chicken Noodle Soup","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chinese Chicken Noodle Soup recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,5.0,154.1,7.3,2.0,71.2,1014.6,4.3,1.0,1.8,17.0,"4.0","Chinese Chicken Noodle Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: This soup changes as the ingredients are available in my refrigerator or on my  cupboard shelves. 2: Takes about 20 minutes from start to table. Start 2 cups of  water to boil; add chicken broth. 3: After stock boils, add the packet of seasoning supplied with Top Ramen. 4: While broth is boiling, add 1 raw chicken breast (cut  in small pieces), the chopped vegetables and the raw egg. 5: The egg will cook into threads. 6: Just before serving, add the noodles and the peas, then the sesame oil  and scallions. 7: Don''t let soup sit around for long time because vegetables need  to be a bit crunchy,  cooked soft. If using leftover meat in your soup, just add  at the end because it only needs to warm up again. 8: You can always add another  can of chicken broth if soup is too thick or you like more broth. 9: You may vary  the soup with different Chinese type vegetables available. Add some garlic and a dash of hot Chinese mustard. 10: If using strong vegetables such as broccoli, cut  small and don''t overcook to avoid the strong flavor. 11: Remember the noodles are  already cooked and they do not need to be cooked, only to absorb the moisture  from the broth, which does thicken the soup.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3020,"Daisy Mae''s Fried Apples","0","PT0S","PT0S","each fall, I use these with pork chops, pork roast - whatever.  They are wonderful, and so easy to make, from my Grandma Daisy''s kitchen.","Apple",5.0,33.0,175.1,7.9,4.9,20.3,56.1,28.4,3.7,22.8,0.5,"6.0","Daisy Mae''s Fried Apples Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.  Add apples. 2: Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. 3: (If you''re using sweet apples, like Delicious, Fuji or Gala, add the lemon juice.  For tart apples, like Jonathans, omit it.)  Stir until apples are blended with sugar/cinnamon. 4: Cover and cook for approx 15-20 minutes, frequently stirring gently. 5: Serve them warm, right on the pork chop or pork roast.  They also double for a dessert dish served over vanilla ice cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3021,"Shepherd''s Cheddar Pie","0","PT0S","PT35M","Make and share this Shepherd''s Cheddar Pie recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",4.0,4.0,1057.9,87.7,37.7,131.8,1164.2,49.7,7.5,3.2,19.1,"4.0","Shepherd''s Cheddar Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Make topping by combining 1/2 can condensed soup with hot mashed potatoes; set  aside. In non-stick frypan, brown ground beef at medium-high heat until coo ked  through. 2: Drain excess fat. Meanwhile, cook mixed vegetables according to package directions; add to frypan and stir into beef with  remaining soup,  Worcestershire sauce and pepper. 3: Spoon meat mixture into 8 x 8 x 2 in. (20 x 20  x 5 cm) square baking pan. 4: Spread reserved potato mixture evenly over surface.  Bake at 400 F (200 C) for 20 minutes or until topping is light golden.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3022,"Low-Carb Stuffed Cabbage Hotdish","0","PT0S","PT1H40M","Make and share this Low-Carb Stuffed Cabbage Hotdish recipe from Food.com.","Pork",4.5,29.0,415.2,14.3,5.9,58.4,1044.1,53.6,10.1,16.8,21.9,"6.0","Low-Carb Stuffed Cabbage Hotdish Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350. 2: In a large pot, steam the cabbage for 10 minutes or until  the leaves are softened enough to peel away. 3: Cool and separate leaves, gently  shake off moisture, and set aside. Melt butter in a skillet and saute onions  until they are golden. 4: Remove half the onions to a bowl containing the ground  beef and pork sausage. Mix in the rice and allspice gently with your hands. 5: To  the remaining onions in the skillet, add the tomatoes and juice, tomato sauce,  tomato paste,  salt and seasonings. 6: Simmer for 15 minutes. 7: Place a small amount  of  meat mixture on each cabbage leaf. 8: Fold leaf over to enclose meat and starting at the stem end, roll up. 9: Place rolls, seam side down in a buttered baking dish. 10: Cover with tomato mixture and bake, uncovered for 1 hour. 11: Serve with sour cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3023,"King Arthur''s Apple Cinnamon Breakfast Bread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Use your bread machine''s timer for this one - it''s wonderful to wake up to the aroma of cinnamon, apples and hot bread !","Breads",0.0,0.0,2632.3,54.0,29.0,122.6,3974.9,463.5,25.4,62.6,74.3,"0.0","King Arthur''s Apple Cinnamon Breakfast Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: *Use the lesser amount in the summer, the greater amount in the winter, and something in between in the spring and fall. 2: Place all of the ingredients into the pan of your bread machine in the order recommended by the manufacturer. 3: Program for basic white bread, and press Start.  Check the dough''s consistency about 7 min. 4: after the kneading cycle begins, adding additional water of flour to form a smooth, soft ball of dough. 5: Allow the machine to complete its cycle.  Remove the b read when it''s done, and let it cool completely before slicing. 6: Note: This bread makes great toast!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3024,"Delicious Lamb Stew","PT2M","PT20M","PT22M","Make and share this Delicious Lamb Stew recipe from Food.com.","Stew",4.0,1.0,595.1,46.8,18.2,127.3,179.0,9.0,1.6,3.7,30.4,"8.0","Delicious Lamb Stew Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut the meat into 2 inch pieces, discarding any skin and fat.  Peel and chop the onions; peel and slice the carrots. 2: Heat the oil in a large saucepan and fry  the onions 5 minutes, add the carrots and fry 5 minutes longer. 3: Remove the  vegetables to a plate, draining as much oil as possible back into the pan. 4: Add  the meat to the pan and cook over a high heat, turning it all the time to brown  it on all sides. 5: Pour the wine into the pan, return the vegetables and season  the mixture with salt and pepper, add the parsley, thyme, marjoram and garlic.   Cut the bacon into small pieces and add to the pan. 6: Bring to the boil, then simmer for 2 hours. 7: Allow to cool,  then place in the refrigerator overnight,   Next day remove the layer of solidified fat from the top. 8: Reheat, check the  seasoning, and serve.  Serve with mashed potato. 9: You may cook this the oven (I usually do).  Cook it at 300-325°F about 2 - 2 1/2 hours or until tender. 10: It freezes well too. 11: Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 12: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3025,"Greek Lamb Chops","PT1H10M","PT15M","PT1H25M","Coming from &quot;Greek Roots&quot; I have been indulging myself for years cooking dishes from the &quot;Old World&quot; and creating my own along the way.  Here is my latest creation, so good and easy to make.","Lamb/Sheep",5.0,9.0,545.7,28.8,4.0,0.0,672.8,67.8,16.6,13.7,12.1,"0.0","Greek Lamb Chops Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large skillet, medium coat lamb chops with the Greek seasoning and brown with the olive oil. 2: Remove chops and add the diced tomatoes, tomato sauce, cinnamon, parsley and the remainder of the Greek seasoning (do not drain the olive oil). Stir and sauté sauce mixture for approx 10 min on low-med heat uncovered. 3: Return chops to the center area of pan  and spoon on sauce mixture. Note: It is important that you turn the chops 3 or 4 times during the whole process keeping them heavenly coated with sauce.  Reduce heat to low temp and cover. 4: Simmer 1 hour stirring periodically. 5: Remove chops again and add rice and green beans, mixing together well. 6: Return chops and simmer for another =hour or until meat is very tender and easy to pull from bone. 7: Enjoy with a nice Greek salad!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3026,"Enzo''s Penne a la Vodka","0","PT0S","PT0S","Rigatoni a la Vodka  Penne Ala Vodka and Smoked Salmon  Pennestroika Penne with Vodka and Spicy Tomato  Penne in Vodka Sauce  A Healthier Penne with Vodka  Penne Ala Vodka  Penne With Creamy Mushroom And Vodka Sauce","Penne",4.0,1.0,1520.9,72.6,36.1,185.9,231.0,205.0,30.6,12.9,23.4,"2.0","Enzo''s Penne a la Vodka Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute onions in butter and olive oil until transparent. Add shredded 2: or pureed tomatoes with juice. Cook over medium heat 20 to 25 minutes or until all liquid content is reduced. 3: Meanwhile in separate saucepan, cook pasta according to package directions,  drain very well and set aside. When tomato sauce is ready, stir in heavy cream. 4: Bring to a near boil, reduce heat and cook 2 to 3 minutes until cream and tomatoes are well blended. 5: Stir in sauce and pepper vodka, mix, stir in hot cooked penne pasta. 6: Stir together to blend. 7: Liberally sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.          -Rosalind Beck  CHEF''S NOTES: Pepper vodka is a commercial item available at many liquor stores, but chef Enzo Perlini prefers the flavor of a homemade version: stir 1/4 tsp. 8: red crushed pepper in 4 Tbsp Vodka. 9: Marinate 3 hours or overnight. Using coffee  filter or fine cloth napkin, allow peppered vodka to filter 3 hours. 10: Remove and  discard filter and set peppered vodka concentrate aside. Penne is large straight tubes of macaroni cut on the diagonal.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3027,"English Flapjack","PT35M","PT5M","PT40M","This is my recipe for Flapjack, inherited from my English mother. It doesn''t have golden syrup in it, but you could try using 3 oz of Lyles with 3 oz brown sugar and seeing how it turns out. I''m sure it would work quite well.","European",5.0,11.0,272.6,15.3,9.0,36.6,143.1,32.0,2.3,16.7,3.1,"0.0","English Flapjack Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter in saucepan over very gentle heat.Mix in the sugar, oats and salt.Stir well and turn mixture into greased swiss roll tin and press lightly together. 2: Smooth top surface with the back of a metal spoon and bake at 190C for 30-35 mins in centre of oven. 3: When golden brown remove from oven and allow to cool for a few minutes before cutting into square slices. 4: Cool completely before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3028,"Crispy Baked Orange Roughy","PT9M","PT7M","PT16M","Make and share this Crispy Baked Orange Roughy recipe from Food.com.","Orange Roughy",4.5,8.0,321.7,8.4,3.1,253.2,489.2,11.6,0.8,1.2,47.3,"2.0","Crispy Baked Orange Roughy Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut fish into serving-size pieces. 2: Beat egg in small shallow bowl. 3: Combine remaining ingredients in second shallow bowl. 4: Dip fish into  egg and then into crumb mixture, coating completely. 5: Place on  foil-lined baking sheet tucking tail under if needed. 6: Bake at 450  degrees F oven for 6-8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3029,"Butter Pecan Cookies III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Butter Pecan Cookies III recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,115.2,8.6,3.0,15.2,98.3,9.2,0.7,4.7,1.2,"0.0","Butter Pecan Cookies III Recipe Instructions:  1: Place chopped pecans and 1 tablespoon butter in a baking pan. 2: Bake at 325  degrees for 5-7 min. or until toasted and browned, stirring frequently. 3: Set  aside to cool. 4: In a mixing bowl, c  ream brown sugar and 1 cup butter. 5: Beat in egg  yolk and vanilla. 6: Gradually add flour. 7: Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour or until  easy to handle. Roll into 1\ 8: ,  9:  apart onto ungreased cookie sheets. 10: Beat egg white until  foamy. 11: Dip pecan halves in egg white, then gently press one into each ball. 12: Bake  at 375 degrees for 10-12 min. or until golden brown. 13: Cool for 2 min. before  removing to wire racks. 14: NOTES : * As a substitute for each cup of self-rising flour, place 1 1/2  teaspoons baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a measuring cup. Add  all-purpose flour to measure 1 cup.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3030,"Pecan Snaps","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pecan Snaps recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,70.3,5.4,2.7,13.9,14.1,5.3,0.2,3.4,0.5,"30.0","Pecan Snaps Recipe Instructions:  1: Lightly grease a cookie sheet or line with foil. 2: In a small bowl stir together  brown sugar, melted butter, corn syrup and coffee. Stir in pecan s and flour  until combined. 3: Drop batter by level teaspoon 3\ 4:  apart, onto prepared cookie sheet. (Bake only 4 or 5 cookies at a time.) Bake at 350 degrees for 7-8 min. 5: for smaller cookies and 8-10 min,  for larger cookies. 6: or until cookies are bubbly and a deep golden brown. 7: Cool  cookies on the cookie sheet for 1-2 min. 8: or until set. Quickly remove 1 cookie;  roll cookie around a metal cone or the greased handle of a wooden spoon. 9: when  cookie is firm, slide the cookie off the cone or spoon and cool completely on a  wire rack. 10: Repeat with remaining cookies, 1 at a time. (If cookies harden before you can shape them, reheat them in the oven about 1 min. 11: or until softened.) If  desired, carefully brush the top edge of each one with melted semisweet  chocolate. (Use a light touch, as the cookies are fragile and will break.) Up to 30 min. 12: before serving, in a large mixing bowl beat whipping cream, powdered  sugar and espresso powder with an electric  mixer on low speed until stiff peaks  form. 13: Pipe or spoon some of the whipped cream into each cookie. If desired,  sprinkle with grated chocolate.                    - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  NOTES : To make ahead: Bake, shape and cool cookies as directed. 14: Arrange in a  single layer in a freezer container and freeze for up to 1 month. 15: To serve, thaw frozen cookies for 15 min. 16: Prepare whipped cream mixture and fill the cookies as directed .");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3031,"Raspberry-Pecan Bars","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","Make and share this Raspberry-Pecan Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",0.0,0.0,210.9,11.4,4.9,39.3,70.5,25.8,1.0,13.3,2.2,"20.0","Raspberry-Pecan Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Oven rack in center. 2: Oven 325°F. 3: Butter an 11 x 7 baking pan. 4: Stir  together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a bowl. 5: Beat butter in  large bowl until creamy, about 1 minute. 6: Gradually beat in sugars and continue to  beat until light and fluffy, 1-2 minute. 7: Beat in egg yolks and vanilla. 8: With a spoon, stir in dry ingredients. 9: Reserve 3 Tbsp pecans; stir the remaining  pecans into the dough. 10: Stir together jam and lemon juice in small bowl. 11: Press half of the dough, about 1 1/2 cups, evenly in bottom of prepared pan. 12: Spread with jam mixture. Crumble remaining dough evenly over top (dough is sticky so  this is a bit of work, but persist). Sprinkle top with reserved 3 Tbsp pecans. 13: Bake 325° for 60 minutes. 14: Cool in pan on wire rack. 15: Cut lengthwise down center and then crosswise into 10 equal widths to make 20 bars.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3032,"Strawberry Pecan Cookies","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Strawberry Pecan Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",1.0,1.0,65.2,3.6,0.8,5.4,39.8,7.8,0.3,4.0,0.8,"78.0","Strawberry Pecan Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar. 2: Add eggs, one at a time, beating  well after each addition. 3: Beat in puree just until blended. 4: Combine flour, salt  and baking soda; gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in pecans and add some  red food coloring if desired. 5: Drop by tablespoonfuls 2\ 6: ,  7: ,  8: ,  9: , ");
