INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3035,"Carrot Marmalade II","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Carrot Marmalade II recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",2.0,1.0,2460.6,1.0,0.1,0.0,206.3,635.2,10.4,613.8,3.7,"0.0","Carrot Marmalade II Recipe Instructions:  1: Squeeze the oranges and lemons, save juice. 2: Grind the rinds and cook until tender (about 30 minutes) in water to cover. 3: Add carrots and cook until tender (about 20 minutes). 4: Add orange and lemon juice. 5: Measure mixture and add equal amount of water for each cup of mixture. 6: Then add 1/2 cup sugar for each cup of all that mixture. 7: Boil to jelly stage, about 1 hour, stirring often to keep from scorching.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3036,"Beef and Kidney Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Beef and Kidney Pie recipe from Food.com.","Beef Organ Meats",0.0,0.0,477.2,37.6,17.0,124.7,536.0,3.8,0.5,1.6,29.6,"6.0","Beef and Kidney Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Season beef and kidney cubes with salt and pepper. 2: Dredge with flour. 3: Saute in butter until brown on all sides. 4: Add onions, brown lightly. 5: Add bay leaf, beef stock, and  Worcestershire. Simmer covered over low heat 2 hours. 6: Pour in  casserole while hot. Place biscuits on top. 7: Bake at 375 degrees  until golden brown. 8: ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3037,"Steak and Kidney Pie II","PT1H30M","PT10M","PT1H40M","Make and share this Steak and Kidney Pie II recipe from Food.com.","Beef Organ Meats",0.0,0.0,1176.1,86.0,27.2,204.5,1153.4,49.0,3.9,2.2,49.5,"0.0","Steak and Kidney Pie II Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim beef to remove fat. Cut away white tissues from kidney and cut into small pieces. 2: Cube the beef. 3: Brown meat in oil. 4: Add onion and cook 5  minutes. 5: Stir in flour; add beef broth slowly. 6: Season with salt and pepper. 7: Add Worcestershire sauce and bay leaf. 8: Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally and adding water if necessary. 9: Place in pie crust. Cover with top crust. Brush with egg yolk and milk glaze. Bake in 350 degrees oven until golden brown, about 1 hour, more if necessary.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3039,"Coconut Bread III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Coconut Bread III recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",0.0,0.0,231.9,10.5,5.3,20.5,206.5,31.4,1.7,13.1,3.8,"12.0","Coconut Bread III Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350. 2: Mix coconut, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. 3: In separate bowl, mix egg, oil, milk, and vanilla. 4: Add wet mixture to dry mixture and stir until blended. 5: Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and bake one");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3040,"Coconut Bread Trinidad","0","PT0S","PT0S","I have used packaged coconut instead of the fresh but found a little more liquid was needed.  Also the flavor was not quite as good but still passable. Nice toasted for breakfast but watch since it burns easily.","Quick Breads",0.0,0.0,329.1,14.4,10.0,44.0,317.0,45.0,2.0,17.6,5.7,"12.0","Coconut Bread Trinidad Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.  Stir in coconut.  Combine egg, milk,  vanilla and  butter. 2: Make a well in the dry ingredients. 3: Pour liquid into the  well. 4: Stir lightly but thoroughly and pour into 2 greased 8 or 9 inch loaf pans, filling pans about 2/3 full. 5: Sprinkle the top of the batter with sugar. 6: Bake at 350 F for about 55 minutes or until they test done.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3041,"Hobo Cake","PT1H","PT10M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Hobo Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,562.6,3.9,1.4,1.8,312.1,130.7,3.4,83.6,6.6,"0.0","Hobo Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix sugar, water, shortening, and raisins and boil for 5 minutes. 2: Cool mixture You can put into refrigerator until cooled. 3: Dissolve the baking into a small mixture that was prepared above. Then add to the cooled mixture. Next, add all dry ingredients and mix well. 4: Put into a well greased tube pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°. 5: NOTE: You can add nuts and dried fruits for a variety taste. Great when sliced warm and drizzled with honey or maple syrup.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3042,"Tuna-Riffic Pasta Salad","PT25M","PT0S","PT25M","Make and share this Tuna-Riffic Pasta Salad recipe from Food.com.","Tuna",4.0,4.0,362.5,2.9,0.7,22.2,349.9,56.7,5.3,8.8,26.1,"4.0","Tuna-Riffic Pasta Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook pasta shells according to package directions. 2: Drain and set aside.  In a  small saucepan, cook the peas according to package directions. 3: Drain and set  aside.  In a large bowl, combine tuna, green onions, mayonnaise, yogurt,  mustard, garlic, salt and pepper. 4: Mix lightly. 5: Add the cooked pasta and peas and toss all ingredients together. 6: Cover and refrigerate until serving time.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3043,"Butter Fluff Icing","PT25M","PT5M","PT30M","Make and share this Butter Fluff Icing recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",3.0,2.0,938.4,68.0,35.1,111.9,258.1,80.2,0.3,66.8,4.3,"0.0","Butter Fluff Icing Recipe Instructions:  1: Thicken milk and flour over medium heat. Once thickened, remove to cool. 2: Next, mix sugar, shortening, vanilla with the flour/milk mixture. Beat until fluffy and creamy.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3044,"Braised Beef Liver With Vegetables","PT1H","PT10M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Braised Beef Liver With Vegetables recipe from Food.com.","Beef Organ Meats",0.0,0.0,1004.2,33.3,11.9,1120.4,779.2,82.5,10.1,7.9,90.4,"0.0","Braised Beef Liver With Vegetables Recipe Instructions:  1: On a deep dish plate, add flour, salt and pepper; mix well. 2: Next, dredge your liver on both sides. 3: Brown it in the bacon drippings w/ the onion and celery. 4: In a greased casserole dish, add the liver, stock, salt, pepper. 5: Cook covered in 350° oven for 30 minutes. 6: Remove the pan and add carrots and potatoes. 7: Return back to oven and cook for 45 minutes more. Remove and add the bacon strips and put back into oven until bacon is crispy.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3045,"Olive-Nut Spread","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Olive-Nut Spread recipe from Food.com.","Spreads",4.0,5.0,174.7,17.2,5.7,24.5,67.0,2.9,1.0,0.4,4.1,"4.0","Olive-Nut Spread Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix all ingredients together. 2: Refrigerate until set. 3: Serve w/ crackers. 4: Great when used as a spread for finger sandwiches as well.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3046,"Tortilla Lasagna","PT20M","PT30M","PT50M","Make and share this Tortilla Lasagna recipe from Food.com.","European",4.0,2.0,440.1,20.6,8.8,83.6,1580.4,38.9,3.1,9.1,25.4,"8.0","Tortilla Lasagna Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. 2: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish Heat vegetable oil in large skillet over medium heat.  Add meat; cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 6 minutes or until no longer pink: drain. 3: Stir in onion, bell peppers,  chilies and  seasoning mix. 4: Reduce heat to low; cook, stirring occasionally,  for 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are slightly tender. 5: Spread 1/ 2 cup of  taco sauce over bottom of prepared baking dish. 6: Cover with 5 tortillas. 7: Spread  with half of meat mixture a nd 1/ 2 cup taco sauce.  Sprinkle with 1 cup of  cheese. Repeat with remaining ingredients  Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until  heated through and cheese is melted.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3047,"Old Fashioned Shepherd''s Pie","PT1H30M","PT30M","PT2H","I do not have the exact measurement of the ingredients, but my Mom made it like this and before her my grand-maman made it the same way, so here it is if you care to try.  PATE CHINOIS  (our shepherd''s pie)","Low Cholesterol",3.5,3.0,2738.0,99.3,43.0,370.2,1760.9,345.9,42.0,29.8,128.5,"1.0","Old Fashioned Shepherd''s Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: In a frying pan that can go in the oven, saute the onions and the garlic until  wilted, remove. Add the beef to the pan and cook  it until done.  Remove the  fat.  Return the onions and the garlic, add salt, pepper and thyme,  add the  gravy and stir evenly. 2: Cover the whole thing with corn. 3: Spread the hot mashed  potatoes on top of the corn, making grooves. 4: put little dashes of butter all  over and sprinkle some paprika all over. 5: Set in the  oven about 1 hour at 300F or until the potatoes are all brown and crispy all around the rim We use an iron  frying pan and it''s just great. 6: The longer you leave it in the oven, the better because all the flavours marry and it is just nice. You can lower the heat in  order to leave it in longer.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3048,"Steak and Kidney Pie IIi","PT1H30M","PT10M","PT1H40M","Make and share this Steak and Kidney Pie IIi recipe from Food.com.","Beef Organ Meats",4.0,2.0,590.0,36.3,9.3,0.0,906.8,55.5,2.6,3.1,10.6,"0.0","Steak and Kidney Pie IIi Recipe Instructions:  1: Core and dice the kidneys, cut the steak into 2 1/2cm cubes. 2: Put in a  saucepan. 3: Add stock and chopped onions, simmer, covered, 1 - 1/2  hours or until meat is tender. 4: Season with salt and pepper. 5: Blend  the flour with extra water, add to steak, stir until the mixture boils  and thickens; cool. 6: Pour into a pie dish. 7: (If you want a darker  gravy, add a couple of teaspoons of soy sauce). Roll out pastry to an  oblong, or circle, (depending what shape dish you are using) slightly  larger the d  ish. 8: Cut thin strips from the ends and fit round moistened edge of the  dish. 9: Brush pastry rim with water and place the top on. 10: Press edges  together, trim off excess pastry, using a sharp knife. Make 2 slits  in centre to allow the steam to escape. Glaze with beaten egg yolk. 11: Bake in a hot oven 20 - 25 minutes. 12: Reduce heat to moderately hot,  bake a further 25 - 30 minutes or until pastry is golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3049,"Steak and Kidney Pie Iv","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","Make and share this Steak and Kidney Pie Iv recipe from Food.com.","Beef Organ Meats",0.0,0.0,370.3,12.7,5.5,412.2,952.7,12.3,0.9,1.9,49.0,"0.0","Steak and Kidney Pie Iv Recipe Instructions:  1: Take the fatty bit out of the kidney and dice.  In a large saucepan melt butter and fry the onion and garlic gently for 5 minutes. 2: Mix the flour, salt and pepper together and toss the  meat in, coating them thoroughly. 3: Add to the onion and brown over a moderate heat.  Add stock, wine, mustard and sauce and bring to the boil. 4: Cover and simmer 40 - 45 minutes. 5: Set aside. Roll out pastry to form lids for individual dishes or one large one.  Spoon filling into the dishes and cover with pastry lids. 6: Bake at 190 C for Shortcrust pastry - OR - 220 C for Puff pastry.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3051,"Crispy Corn Toasts","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Crispy Corn Toasts recipe from Food.com.","Corn",0.0,0.0,203.5,9.0,5.6,34.2,348.8,23.6,0.1,11.8,8.3,"1.0","Crispy Corn Toasts Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring the milk to boil. 2: Mix some cold milk with the custard powder and add to  the boiling milk, stirring constantly. 3: Add the rest of the ingredients and cook  for a further 5 mins over a slow flame.  Serve hot or chilled over crisp toasted bread slices.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3052,"Quiche Lorraine","PT30M","PT10M","PT40M","Make and share this Quiche Lorraine recipe from Food.com.","Savory Pies",4.5,7.0,442.8,36.6,15.2,138.3,494.4,11.9,0.9,0.3,16.2,"6.0","Quiche Lorraine Recipe Instructions:  1: Line an 18-cm(7-in) flan tin or sandwich cake tin with the pastry. 2: Place a layer of cheese on the pastry, then a layer of bacon, and repeat until both ingredients have been used up. 3: Mix the eggs with the cayenne pepper, nutmeg, and cream or milk. 4: then pour over the cheese and bacon mixture in the flan case. 5: Bake near the top of the oven at 200C(400F) Gas mark 6 for about 30 minutes, until the pastry is golden brown and the filling set. 6: Serve hot or cold.");
