INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3057,"Confectioner''s Sugar Cookies","PT6M","PT0S","PT6M","Make and share this Confectioner''s Sugar Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,16.0,59.3,3.2,2.0,11.7,44.1,7.0,0.1,3.0,0.7,"60.0","Confectioner''s Sugar Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar. 2: Beat until light.  Add egg and vanilla. 3: Beat until fluffy. 4: Add dry ingredients.  Stir just until mixed. 5: Refrigerate.  Roll, cut and bake for 6 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet. 6: Cool, frost and decorate. 7: Variations: Spread unbaked shapes with egg white and decorate with  sprinkles-then bake.  Add 1 cup chopped nuts (walnuts or pecans here in Texas).  Roll in 1\ 8: ,  9:  balls. 10: Bake, cool and toss in paper bag with sugar/cinnamon  mixture to coat.  Add 1 cup of candied fruits to dough. 11: Roll in 1\ 12: ,  13: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3058,"Mock Devonshire Cream Substitute II","0","PT10M","PT10M","Real Devonshire Cream or clotted cream is a natural product, but in the 1951 Fannie Merritt Farmer Cookbook  Little,Brown and Company Boston there is the following recipe.","Very Low Carbs",5.0,1.0,707.4,73.7,46.1,256.6,297.0,5.6,0.0,0.3,8.9,"0.0","Mock Devonshire Cream Substitute II Recipe Instructions:  1: Mash cheese and heat in the cream. 2: Beat until smooth. 3: Serve with hot scones  and raspberry jam or on fresh or stewed fruit.   Anything you like Enjoy        Ken.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3059,"Chicken Loaf","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chicken Loaf recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",0.0,0.0,169.8,17.1,7.7,88.0,110.3,2.0,0.7,0.4,3.2,"8.0","Chicken Loaf Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat the broth until boiling, and pour a little into the beaten eggs,  stirring constantly. 2: Pour egg mixture into broth and cook over very  low heat until thick and smooth (do not boil or it will separate). Stir  in gelatin mixture. Chill until mixture is congealed; then fold in the  chicken, nuts, and whipped cream. 3: Turn into mold and chill. 4: Unmold on a chilled platter and garnish with lettuce, tomatoes and  olives. 5: Serve with mayonnaise.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3060,"Turkey and Black Bean Stew","PT2H","PT1H","PT3H","This recipe is a little bit of work, but I think it''s worth it for good food.  Serve with cooked rice and chopped scallions for garnish.","Stew",5.0,1.0,186.1,2.3,0.6,25.6,198.6,23.8,4.8,4.4,17.7,"8.0","Turkey and Black Bean Stew Recipe Instructions:  1: Place the beans in a large saucepan and cover with cold water.  Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.  Remove from the heat and set aside 1 hour. 2: Meanwhile, coat a non-stick Dutch oven with cooking spray.  Warm over medium high heat.  Add the onions, carrots, green peppers, sweet red peppers, oregano, cumin and garlic. 3: Reduce the heat to medium and cook, stirring, 4 to 6 minutes, or until the onions start to soften.  Remove the vegetables and set aside. 4: Drain and rinse the beans.  Add the beans to the Dutch oven.  Add the chicken or turkey stock.  Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.  Reduce the heat to medium-low.  Partially cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 1 1/2 hours, or until the beans are nearly tender. 5: Add the reserved vegetables and simmer for 30 minutes, or until the beans are tender. 6: Add the diced turkey, tomatoes, jalapeno peppers, vinegar, salt and freshly ground black pepper.  Simmer for 5 minutes, or until or until the turkey is cooked.  Remove from the heat and stir in the basil.  Let stand 5 minutes to allow the flavors to blend.  Enjoy!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3061,"Chicken With Cashew Nuts","PT12M","PT10M","PT22M","Make and share this Chicken With Cashew Nuts recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",2.0,1.0,841.6,64.0,10.1,75.5,2801.4,37.8,5.7,7.1,33.9,"0.0","Chicken With Cashew Nuts Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oil and fry garlic, add chicken, salt, pepper, carrot, chestnut and stir  fry for 5 minutes or until chicken is fully cooked, remove and set aside. Add  corn starch, light sauce, sesame oil and bring to a boil. 2: Put back chicken and vegetable, stir fry for 30 seconds. 3: Add cashew nuts, give  it a few stirs. 4: Dish up and garnish with cilantro leaves. 5: Serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3062,"Indonesian Chicken","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Indonesian Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",5.0,1.0,459.9,27.3,13.2,86.2,400.4,30.9,0.8,28.1,23.0,"8.0","Indonesian Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash and cut up chicken. 2: Broil for 10 minutes until golden brown. 3: Pound spices  until fine. Simmer coconut milk with spices and put  in lime juice and rinds. 4: Pour over chicken and broil for another 20  minutes or until tender. 5: Baste  frequently with gravy.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3063,"Adobong Manok","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Adobong Manok recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",0.0,0.0,622.6,39.9,15.2,170.1,896.5,19.6,0.1,18.2,43.3,"6.0","Adobong Manok Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat 2 Tbsp. of oil and fry garlic until brown. 2: Add chicken, vinegar, water,  salt, bay leaf,  peppercorns, food coloring, soy sauce and coconut milk. 3: Bring to a boil then  simmer for 30  minutes. 4: Remove chicken and let cool. 5: Heat sauce and reduce liquid until sauce  thickened. 6: Heat oil and fry chicken pieces until brown on all sides. 7: Serve with sauce and  steam rice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3064,"Chicken Drumsticks in Ginger Wine","PT1H","PT5M","PT1H5M","This is an adopted recipe of mine. I have added a few ingredients, lengthened the cooking time, and I thnk it''s great!","Chicken Thigh & Leg",5.0,1.0,320.4,19.5,4.4,118.3,875.7,5.3,0.2,3.4,29.3,"4.0","Chicken Drumsticks in Ginger Wine Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oil in a pan and fry chicken until browned a little. 2: Combine all other ingredients in a saucepan; add the chicken . 3: Bring to the boil, then simmer until chicken is tender and sauce is reduced and thickened (about i hour). 4: Add a little more water to the saucepan if the sauce reduces too much before you think your chicken is cooked.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3065,"Braised Coriander Chicken","PT35M","PT25M","PT1H","Savory coriander, sweetened stirfried chicken.  Simple and delicious!!  Prep time includes marination.  An adopted recipe.","Whole Chicken",5.0,1.0,354.3,20.0,4.7,90.8,849.4,11.1,0.9,8.1,31.6,"4.0","Braised Coriander Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: In a plastic container with lid or Ziplock bag, combine soy sauce, coriander, sugar, salt, and pepper to make marinade. 2: Add chicken pieces, cover or close, shake, and marinade for for 20 minutes in refrigerator, turning occasionally. 3: In a heavy skillet over medium temperature, heat oil and fry onion and garlic until soft but not brown, about 7 minutes. 4: Add chicken together with marinade and stirfry until chicken is well coated and brown, about 7 minutes. 5: Add water and simmer for 20 minutes, turning occasionally. 6: Adjust seasoning and serve with French bread or rice.  Garnish with chopped green onions.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3066,"Chicken with Lemon Curry Sauce","PT40M","PT30M","PT1H10M","This dish is excellent served with Basmati rice since there will be a little extra sauce to spoon over the chicken and to flavor the rice nicely. This recipe is courtesy of the "Spice of Life Cookbook" by Treva Davis (no longer in print).","Curries",4.5,10.0,298.6,13.7,3.9,92.8,94.1,11.3,1.0,7.0,30.8,"4.0","Chicken with Lemon Curry Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients, except chicken and honey, in a medium skillet. Mix thoroughly. 2: Place chicken in the pan and turn several times to coat. Cover and marinate for 30 minutes 3: Turn on heat and simmer for 25 minutes, turning chicken every 10 minutes. 4: Add honey, stir and cook for 10 minutes more, or until chicken is throughly cooked. 5: Serve along side Basmati rice and enjoy!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3067,"Red Cooked Chicken","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Red Cooked Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",0.0,0.0,458.8,32.2,7.8,115.0,447.5,7.1,0.4,4.9,29.4,"6.0","Red Cooked Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Stuff ginger and scallions inside chicken. 2: Sew up cavity with thread. 3: Blend all  other ingredients and bring to a boil. 4: Add chicken cover and simmer for 40  minutes, turn chicken frequently. 5: Carve into slices and pour gravy over.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3068,"Rice Paper Wrapped Chicken","PT10M","PT10M","PT20M","This is an adopted recipe. I shall be trying it out and then post any additional information if needs be. Feel free to try it out first and share your comments!","Lunch/Snacks",0.0,0.0,1755.2,97.8,26.1,581.1,2389.5,16.8,1.0,9.2,191.2,"0.0","Rice Paper Wrapped Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Marinate chicken in seasoning ingredients for 30 minutes. 2: Place a piece of  chicken on one sheet of paper and wrap up firmly. 3: Preheat oil to 375F, then deep fry.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3069,"Chicken With Honey Lemon","PT50M","PT1H","PT1H50M","Make and share this Chicken With Honey Lemon recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",4.0,2.0,743.1,54.6,7.1,0.0,2333.1,70.5,1.4,65.9,0.8,"0.0","Chicken With Honey Lemon Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix oil, lemon juice, pepper, honey, salt and sugar. 2: Marinate chicken with  mixture for 1 hour. 3: Preheat oven to 300 degrees, and roast chicken for 40  minutes basting frequently. 4: Broil chicken at the last 10 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3070,"Red Hot Curried Chicken","PT30M","PT10M","PT40M","A good party dish. The chicken is marinated the night before, so all you have to do on the day is to cook it in a very hot oven and serve with wedges of lemon and a green salad.","Curries",0.0,0.0,729.2,54.8,15.1,219.2,800.7,4.7,0.7,2.3,52.1,"4.0","Red Hot Curried Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Skin the chicken pieces and cut two slits into each piece. 2: Arrange them single layer in a glass or ceramic dish and pour the lemon juice over them. 3: Combine the remaining ingredients and pour the sauce over the chicken pieces, turning them to coat throughly. 4: Cover with plastic wrap and chill overnight. 5: Preheat the oven to 425°F. 6: Remove chicken from the marinade and arrange single layer on a baking sheet. 7: Bake for 15 minutes, turn over and bake for another 15 minutes, or until tender. 8: Serve with a fresh garden salad and enjoy!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3071,"Broiled Balanese Chicken","PT30M","PT30M","PT1H","This was adopted way back in 2005 or so. I haven''t tried it but intend to in the next couple of weeks. Looks very good.","Whole Chicken",0.0,0.0,448.4,33.4,8.5,121.9,564.2,6.3,0.9,3.8,29.7,"8.0","Broiled Balanese Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Fry chicken pieces in oil until golden brown. 2: Remove and place on a rack. 3: Pound  together onion, chilies, garlic and ginger, fry them in remaining oil until  fragrant. Mix with tomato paste, sugar and soy sauce and marinate chicken  pieces in mixture for an hour. 4: Broil chicken on rack, basting frequently with  marinade and bruised lemon grass. 5: Broil for 25 minutes, turning over once and  squeeze lemon juice over before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3072,"Broiled Chicken (Malay)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Broiled Chicken (Malay) recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",0.0,0.0,280.7,19.7,7.0,86.2,523.8,3.0,0.6,1.6,21.9,"16.0","Broiled Chicken (Malay) Recipe Instructions:  1: Pound spices until fine and set aside. Rub chicken with salt and set aside. Mix  coconut milk with 1 cup of water, add spices then bring to a boil. 2: Add chicken  pieces and simmer for 10 minutes. 3: Remove chicken and place on a broiling rack. 4: Broil for 10 minutes on each side basting with gravy.");
