INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3077,"Chicken and Spinach Veloute","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chicken and Spinach Veloute recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",0.0,0.0,910.8,42.5,21.6,137.4,1547.9,94.4,6.0,16.2,38.0,"1.0","Chicken and Spinach Veloute Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring the stock to a boil. 2: Add cream of wheat, mix well and bring to a boil. 3: Add spinach to soup stock and boil for 5 minutes. 4: Stir in the cream and serve  immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3078,"Chicken Armenian","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chicken Armenian recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",5.0,4.0,4577.6,323.7,108.6,1502.0,4686.8,30.8,4.5,16.3,347.0,"1.0","Chicken Armenian Recipe Instructions:  1: Fry chicken in butter until brown. 2: Place chicken skin down in casserole. Fry the  onion in the remaining butter until golden then add garlic, tomato juice,  paprika and sherry to the pan, bring to a boil then pour over chicken. 3: Sprinkle  chicken with salt and pepper. 4: Bake uncovered in a 400 oven for 1 hour, tur  n  chicken over after 30 minutes. 5: Baste frequently with pan juice. Serve with rice  pilaf.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3079,"Chicken Biryani","PT1H15M","PT15M","PT1H30M","Biryani is a combination of rice with meat, chicken, shrimp, vegetables or fish. It is a meal within itself. Don''t be put off by the long list of ingredients, it is really an easy dish to prepare and tasty too.","One Dish Meal",4.0,2.0,763.3,32.6,7.5,114.2,437.1,72.2,6.8,9.8,45.9,"4.0","Chicken Biryani Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat the oven to 375°F. 2: Bring a pan of water to a boil and add the rice, salt, cardamom pods, cloves and cinnamon stick; boil for two minutes and then drain, leaving the whole spices in the rice. 3: Heat the oil in a pan and fry the onions for about 8 minutes, until browned. 4: Add the chicken, followed by the ground cloves, cardamom, chilies, cumin, coriander, black pepper, garlic, ginger and lemon juice; stir-fry 5 minutes. 5: Transfer the chicken mixture to a casserole and lay the sliced tomatoes on top. 6: Sprinkle on the cilantro, spoon on the plain yogurt and top with drained basmati rice. 7: Drizzle the saffron and milk over the rice and pour on 2/3 cup water. 8: Cover tightly and bake in the oven for 1 hour. 9: Transfer to a warmed serving platter and remove the whole spices from the rice. 10: Garnish with toasted almonds and freshly chopped cilantro and serve with plain yogurt.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3080,"Grand Marnier Garlic Chicken","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Grand Marnier Garlic Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",0.0,0.0,543.9,34.7,9.9,172.5,633.0,11.9,0.4,6.6,44.1,"4.0","Grand Marnier Garlic Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: First, preheat your oven to 350 degrees F (about 175 degrees C). 2: Rub a pinch of salt and slight sprinkling of pepper into the chicken pieces and set it aside whilst preparing the marinade 3: Marinade:  use a food processor or pestle and mortar to  pound/blitz the peeled garlic and black peppercorns to a rough dry paste.  Add in the salt and continue to blitz/pound as paste becomes moist.  Add in Grand Marnier, marmalade, sugar, honey, soy, mint sauce and tomato ketchup and mix well. 4: Pour this marinade over the prepared chicken, rubbing the marinade well into the meat and set aside for at least 2 hours. 5: Line baking/roasting tin in foil and place chicken together with marinade in tin. 6: Cover with foil and pierce the cover to allow steam to escape. Bake at 350 degrees F for 40 minutes; remove the foil cover from the chicken, increase the heat of the oven to 400 degrees F and bake a further 10 minutes or till golden brown. 7: Skim fat off the drippings and serve as an accompanying sauce. 8: Serve chicken hot, garnished with a fresh sprig of parsley or rosemary. 9: Garlic cooking tip: about peeling garlic, Julia Child writes, \ 10:  From \ 11: ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3081,"Salt Rising Bread II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Salt Rising Bread II recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",0.0,0.0,1726.9,24.7,13.5,64.7,2539.7,321.8,11.2,13.7,48.1,"0.0","Salt Rising Bread II Recipe Instructions:  1: Add the salt, sugar, corn meal, and butter to the milk. 2: Place this in 3: a glass fruit jar or a heavy crockery pitcher and surround it with  water at about 120 F. 4: Allow it to stand 6 to 7 hours or until it  starts to ferment. If it has \ 5:  enough, the gas can be heard as  it escapes. 6: This leaven contains enough liquid for 1 loaf. 7: If more  loaves are wanted, add 1 cup water, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 Tablespoon  sugar, and 1 Tablespoon butter for each additional loaf. 8: Make a soft  sponge by adding 1 cup flour to each loaf to be made. Beat well. 9: Put  the sponge to rise again at 120 F. 10: When it is very light, add more  flour (2 cups flour for each loaf) gradually so tha  t the dough can be  kneaded and not stick to hands. 11: Knead 10 to 15 minutes. 12: Put in a  greased pan. 13: Let rise until 2-1/2 times its original size. Bake in  hot oven 15 minutes and then a moderate one for 45 more.  Notice that there is no yeast in this bread except the wild yeast that  comes from the air. 14: While it is baking there is a disagreeable odour  that disappears when the bread is baked. 15: It always has a peculiar  flavour, disliked by some and prized by others. 16: It is never so light as bread made with yeast. A loaf made with 1 cup  liquid will not rise to the top of a standard-sized bread pan. 17: Do not  try to keep this fine-grained white bread for long as it dries out.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3082,"Seafood Lasagna With Brandied-Basil Cream Sauce","PT45M","PT15M","PT1H","Make and share this Seafood Lasagna With Brandied-Basil Cream Sauce recipe from Food.com.","< 60 Mins",5.0,1.0,956.4,57.9,35.1,354.8,1340.4,38.6,1.4,1.8,68.5,"12.0","Seafood Lasagna With Brandied-Basil Cream Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: This recipe should make 3 layers. 3: In a  bowl, mix together ricotta, Parmesan, shredded provolone, eggs, basil  and black pepper. 4: Add a layer of noodles. 5: Spread a thin layer of cheese mixture  to cover noodle layer and top with a layer of shrimp, crabmeat and  scallops. 6: Repeat steps again, ending with a layer of noodles until  you have completed the process 3 times. 7: Arrange provolone cheese  slices on top of lasagna. 8: Bake for approximately 1 hour or until  golden brown and bubbly. 9: To serve, cut into portions and place lasagna on a plate. Generously  spoon Brandied-Basil Cream Sauce over the top and garnish with fresh  basil. 10: Brandied-Basil Cream Sauce:  Bring heavy cream, cognac, basil leaves and stock to a boil. 11: Reduce mixture to preferred consistency. 12: Add Parmesan cheese, stirring to melt, and remove from the heat. 13: Use shrimp base to make the shrimp stock or make your own shrimp stock by boiling together and reducing by 2/3  the following ingredients:  shells from 5 pounds of shrimp, 1 peeled Bermuda onion studded with 8 whole cloves, 3 bay leaves, 2 tablespoons whole black peppercorns, and 5 quarts of water.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3083,"White Sauce Seafood Lasagna","PT50M","PT10M","PT1H","Make and share this White Sauce Seafood Lasagna recipe from Food.com.","European",5.0,16.0,471.8,22.3,13.1,70.2,813.2,44.1,1.8,2.6,21.3,"8.0","White Sauce Seafood Lasagna Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat butter in a large saucepan over low heat until melted. 2: Add  garlic. 3: Stir in flour and salt. Cook,stirring constantly until  bubbly. 4: Remove from heat. Stir in milk, broth and white wine. Return  to stove and heat to boiling, stirring constantly. 5: Boil for 1 minute.  Add mozzarella cheese,onions, basil and pepper. 6: Cook over low heat  until cheese is melted, stirring constantly. 7: Spread about 1 1/2 cups  of the sauce in an ungreased 9X13 pan. 8: Top with UNCOOKED lasagna  noodles, overlapping as needed. 9: Spread the cottage cheese over the noodles. 10: Spread with another 1 1/2 cups of sauce and then top with another 5  lasagna noodles. 11: Spread seafood over this layer and top with another  1 1/2 cups of sauce. Cover with the last 5 lasagna noodles and top  with all of the remaining sauce. If desired, top with 1/2 cup grated  Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered at 350~F for 35 - 45 minutes or  until the noodles are tender. 12: Let stand for 15 minutes before  cutting. 13: Hope you love this as much as we do!!!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3084,"Tiramisu - Olive Garden","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Tiramisu - Olive Garden recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",3.5,9.0,624.0,38.9,21.9,125.0,365.6,54.6,0.0,53.5,6.8,"6.0","Tiramisu - Olive Garden Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut across the middle of the sponge cake to form two disks, about  1\ 2:  thick, each. 3: Blend the coffee or espresso and liqueur together. 4: Sprinkle the bottom half of the cake with the coffee  liqueur blend, enough to flavor it strongly, but don''t saturate the cake so much that it will collapse. 5: Mix the cream cheese or  mascarpone with the sugar and beat the cheese until the sugar is  completely dissolved and the cheese is light and spreadable. 6: Spread  the bottom half off the cake with half of the creamy cheese, in a  fairly thick layer. 7: Set the second half of the cake on the bottom  half and repeat the process ~ sprinkle the coffee/liqueur blend and  spread with the remaining cream cheese. 8: Put the cocoa powder into a  wire strainer and coat the top layer of cream cheese completely with  cocoa. 9: Refrigerate the cake for at least two hours before cutting and  serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3085,"Classic Tiramisu","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Classic Tiramisu recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,1.0,116.6,7.4,4.6,27.2,9.5,7.7,0.2,6.4,0.6,"12.0","Classic Tiramisu Recipe Instructions:  1: *If unavailable, substitute 8 ounces cream cheese, blended with 1/4 2: cup whipping cream and 2 1/2 tablespoons sour cream. 3: Layer biscuits in the bottom of a 13X9X2\ 4: ,  5: ,  6: ,  7: ,  8: ,  9: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3086,"Tiramisu III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Tiramisu III recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,441.4,30.0,17.1,323.2,75.2,38.1,2.7,12.7,8.1,"8.0","Tiramisu III Recipe Instructions:  1: In bowl, beat egg yolks with sugar till light about 5 minutes. 2: Whisk  in 1/2 cup coffee and 1 Tbsp brandy or almond extract. Transfer to  double boiler, over gently simmering water, whisk for about 7  minutes, till thickened. 3: Let cool. 4: Beat cheese till smooth, fold into  egg mixture. Whip cream, stir 1/4 into egg mixture. Fold in remaining  cream. 5: Combine remaining strong coffee and 1 Tbsp brandy or almond  extract. Arrange 1/2 of ladyfingers in 11X7\ 6: Top with chocolate. Cover and refrigerate overnight.  Can be frozen for up to 2 weeks, let defrost in refrigerator for   24 hours. 7: the amount of liquor in this recipe has been reduced.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3088,"Espresso Tiramisu","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Espresso Tiramisu recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,273.8,12.6,7.6,90.8,128.7,34.1,0.1,17.9,2.1,"10.0","Espresso Tiramisu Recipe Instructions:  1: In a medium bowl, using an electric mixer set on medium speed, beat 2: together the mascarpone cheese, 1 c up of the confectioner''s sugar and the Marsala until well blended. 3: Add the cream and beat until fluffy, about 1 minute. Set aside. In a small, heavy saucepan over high heat, combine the water, the remaining 1/2 cup confectioners'' sugar and the espresso or coffee powder. 4: Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. 5: Remove from the heat and let cool. 6: Using a long serrated knife, cut the cake crosswise into slices 1/4- 1/3 inch thick. 7: Select a 2 1/2-qt oval or rectangular glass or ceramic dish about 11 inches in diameter and 2 inches deep. 8: Arrange enough of the cake slices in a single layer over the bottom of the dish to cover completely, trimming to fit as needed. 9: Brush half of the cooled espresso syrup over the cake. Spread half of the cheese mixture evenly over the top. 10: Top with enough of the cake slices in a single layer to cover completely, trimming to fit as needed. 11: Brush the remaining cooled espresso syrup evenly over the top. 12: Then spread the remaining cheese mixture over the top. 13: Cover with pla stic wrap and refrigerate up to 2 days. 14: Using a fine-mesh sieve, sift cocoa evenly top just before serving. 15: Using a large spoon, scoop the tiramisu onto individual plates.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3089,"Charcoal Grilled Duck","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Charcoal Grilled Duck recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",0.0,0.0,5530.8,526.5,171.2,964.0,5624.9,43.0,0.6,40.0,146.6,"1.0","Charcoal Grilled Duck Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash duck and dry thoroughly. 2: Combine marinade ingredients and rub all over 3: Refrigerate for 1 hour. 4: Drain duck and keep marinade as a basting liquid. 5: Grill duck over hot charcoal for 20 minutes each side turning over frequently 6: Heat remaining marinade gently and thicken with cornstarch mixed in cold water. 7: Pour over duck and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3090,"Braised Duck with Glutinous Rice","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Braised Duck with Glutinous Rice recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",0.0,0.0,6187.6,527.2,171.7,963.7,7514.2,183.4,6.7,28.0,162.8,"1.0","Braised Duck with Glutinous Rice Recipe Instructions:  1: Steam duck for 30 minutes. 2: Remove and cool. 3: Mix rice with shrimps, salt, 1 Tbsp. 4: of soy sauce, sesame oil, Chinese wine, pepper and scallions. 5: Stuff duck with  mixture and sew up cavity with thread. 6: Place in casserole with water and simmer  for 30 minutes or until tender. 7: Remove and reserve liquid. 8: In a clean wok add  soy sauce, sugar, sherry and 4 Tbsp. 9: of broth and simmer until thick. 10: Add duck  and glaze all over. 11: Serve hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3091,"Maple Pecan Cheesecake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Maple Pecan Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",0.0,0.0,1019.2,68.5,35.1,233.3,899.5,89.9,2.6,51.0,15.9,"8.0","Maple Pecan Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: In a bowl stir together the gingersnap crumbs and the butter until the  mixture is combined well and press the mixture onto th  e bottom and  halfway up the side of a 9-inch springform pan. 2: Make the filling In a large bowl with an electric mixer cream together the cream  cheese and the brown sugar until the mixture is light and fluffy and beat in the  maple syrup. 3: Add the egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition,  and beat in the sour cream, the salt, the vanilla, the maple extract, and the  pecans. 4: In a bowl with the electric mixer, beaters cleaned, beat the egg whites  with a pinch of salt until they just hold stiff peaks, whisk about one fourth of  them onto the cream cheese mixture, and fold in the remaining whites gently but  thoroughly. 5: Pour the filling into the prepared crust and bake the cheesecake in  the middle of a preheated 350 F. oven for 1 hour. 6: Turn off the oven, let the  cheesecake cool completely in the oven with the door ajar, and chill it,  covered, overnight.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3092,"Chocolate-Caramel-Pecan Cheesecake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chocolate-Caramel-Pecan Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",0.0,0.0,758.2,47.0,20.6,133.3,454.2,77.4,2.7,60.0,11.3,"8.0","Chocolate-Caramel-Pecan Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter, stirring well. 2: Press mixture evenly onto bottom and 1 inch up sides of a 9-inch springform pan. 3: Unwrap caramels; combine with milk and heat over low heat until  caramels are melted, stirring often. 4: Pour over graham cracker crust;  sprinkle chopped pecans evenly over caramel layer and set aside. 5: Beat  cream cheese at high speed until light and fluffy; gradually add  sugar, mixing well. 6: Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each  one. Stir in vanilla and chocolate; beat until blended. 7: Spoon over  pecan layer. 8: Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. 9: Remove from oven,  and run knife around edge of pan to release sides. 10: Let cool t  o room  temperature on a wire rack; cover and chill at least 8 hours before  serving. 11: Top with pecan halves and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3093,"Caramel Pecan Cheesecake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Caramel Pecan Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",5.0,3.0,406.6,27.6,13.4,94.5,310.3,36.5,0.8,27.2,5.6,"12.0","Caramel Pecan Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix together butter, crumbs and 2 Tbsp sugar. 2: Pat in bottom of 3: springform pan. 4: Melt caramels and milk together. 5: Stir in pecans and  spread over crust. Beat well cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs. 6: Pour over caramel. 7: Bake at 350 for 40 minutes. 8: Cool and refrigerate  for 3 hours.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3094,"No Bake Chocolate Pecan Cheesecake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this No Bake Chocolate Pecan Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",0.0,1.0,417.5,35.8,18.9,113.3,173.5,25.2,4.1,14.0,7.3,"12.0","No Bake Chocolate Pecan Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Crust: Combine crumbs, pecans, sugar and butter . 2: With the back of a spoon,  press mixture to the bottom of a lightly greased 9 inch springform pan. 3: Bake in  325 oven for 8 minutes. 4: Cool. 5: Filling: Beat cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar with electric mixer until smooth. 6: Beat in egg yolks and vanilla, mixing well. 7: Blend in melted chocolate.  In another bowl, beat egg whites to soft peaks. 8: Add  remaining sugar and beat until stiff peaks form. 9: Fold egg whites and whipped  cream into chocolate mixture.  Stir until well blended. 10: Pour over crust.  Garnish: Sprinkle with chopped pecans and drizzle with melted chocolate. Cover  with foil. 11: Freeze cheesecake for 3  hours or until firm. 12: When frozen solid,  remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3095,"Taco Rice","0","PT0S","PT0S","Here is the version of Taco Rice that we have  made at our house. It came out of the freezer and tasted better  than the day we made it I thought. I also boiled  the ground beef. I made  it because it was a recipe that my sister-in-law wanted to make when we  were cooking together. My family liked it and so did I. I will  definitely  make this again.  Khandi                            Taco Rice","Brown Rice",4.5,14.0,566.9,24.3,12.5,91.0,293.0,56.3,3.1,3.3,28.6,"6.0","Taco Rice Recipe Instructions:  1: ASSEMBLY Brown meat and drain. 2: Combine meat, onion,  taco seasoning packe t,  cooked rice and tomatoes in saucepan. 3: Simmer  until thick - about 30 minutes. 4: FREEZING & COOKING Cool, label, and freeze in bags or rigid  containers. 5: Also  freeze a ziptop bag with 2 cups of shredded cheese for  each meal. 6: TO SERVE: Thaw completely. 7: for taco salad, warm over  medium heat. Serve with  lettuce, taco chips, tomatoes, sour cream and  the enclosed cheese.          - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -    NOTES : I made with Uncle Ben''s Rice. My  kids rolled it up in warm tortillas to eat. I ate with fat free sour cream and salsa. 8: It can also be used as a burrito filling. 9: It was better than I expected.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3096,"Shepherd''s Pie II","0","PT0S","PT0S","I prefer stew meat instead of ground beef, but either could be used. Frozen mixed vegetables can reduce preparation time.  I usually make extra mashed potatoes for a meal the day before and save them for this.","Meat",4.5,2.0,1794.9,52.5,27.2,398.4,5458.2,183.3,17.0,21.8,148.2,"1.0","Shepherd''s Pie II Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown meat over medium high heat.  Add garlic and saute 30 seconds (if  vegetables to be used cook quickly, add onion with garlic and saute until  tender).   Add broth and spices to meat and simmer covered for 30 min. 2: Chop  veggies. 3: Add onions and veggies (peas, carrots, green beans, celery, corn,  your choice), simmer until tender. 4: You may have to add vegetables at different  times so that they are all done at the same time depending on the vegetables  chosen. 5: Mix 1/2 cup water and gravy mix in bowl. 6: Add to mixture and simmer 5 min. 7: Mix chives and taters. 8: Place meat mixture in bottom of 2 1/2 quart  casserole dish. 9: Top with taters. 10: Sprinkle with cheese  and bake at 375: for 10  min. 11: Note: This can be cooked in one dish if you use a cast iron chicken fryer or  Dutch oven. 12: Also tastes good with elk meat.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3097,"Wild Rice Stuffed Morels","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Wild Rice Stuffed Morels recipe from Food.com.","Rice",4.0,1.0,59.9,1.8,0.7,2.6,136.8,8.7,1.0,1.0,2.2,"0.0","Wild Rice Stuffed Morels Recipe Instructions:  1: Soak rice in water to cover for 30 minutes. 2: Drain. 3: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 4 1/2 cups water, add pepper and bring to a boil. 4: Add rice slowly, so water doesn''t stop boiling, turn down heat and simmer, covered, over low heat for 45 minutes. 5: Let sit off heat 15 minutes. 6: Drain off excess water. 7: In a skillet heat oil and butter. 8: Saute celery and onion until translucent, about 5 minutes. 9: Turn off heat and add thyme, parsley, garlic and salt and pepper to taste.         Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 10: Prepare morels by brushing them off with a damp paper towel. 11: Trim off stems and, if necessary, enlarge the opening into the cap with a paring knife. Spread half the rice mixture in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole and top with butter. 12: Fill morels with as much of the rice mixture as each will hold. 13: Mound rice on top of each morel, and stand upright in the casserole. Repeat with remaining morels. 14: Drizzle with white wine and dust with Parmesan cheese if desired. 15: Cover and bake at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes. 16: Lower heat to 300 and bake until morels are resilient, but tender, about another 25 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3098,"Creamy Ham and Cheese Quiche","PT50M","PT10M","PT1H","Make and share this Creamy Ham and Cheese Quiche recipe from Food.com.","Savory Pies",4.5,4.0,530.3,35.5,12.9,259.4,1467.9,26.9,2.0,2.1,25.2,"4.0","Creamy Ham and Cheese Quiche Recipe Instructions:  1: Whisk together condensed soup and eggs. 2: Stir in ham, green pepper and Cheddar  cheese. 3: Pour mixture into unbaked pastry shell (placed on baking sheet). 4: Bake in preheated 350F (180 C) oven for 50 minutes or until set and golden. 5: Cut into  wedges; serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3099,"South Pacific Islands Rum Punch","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this South Pacific Islands Rum Punch recipe from Food.com.","Punch Beverage",0.0,0.0,446.4,0.3,0.1,0.0,8.2,27.9,5.2,16.3,1.7,"0.0","South Pacific Islands Rum Punch Recipe Instructions:  1: Pour rums into container. 2: Add sugar and vanilla beans. 3: Stir until sugar is  dissolved. 4: Cut the citrus fruits in half. 5: Squeeze juice into the rum; then toss  in the shells. 6: Peel and slice the bananas. 7: Peel and slice the pineapple. Add  banana and pineapple to rum. 8: Cover container and let stand in a cool place for  two to three days. 9: Stir several times during each day. 10: On the day of the  celebration, remove pulp, vanilla beans and citrus rinds. 11: Pour rum mixture over  ice in a large punch bowl and let chill fo r a few hours. 12: Just before serving add chilled white wine. Decorate bowl with sliced citrus fruits and float a few  slices in the punch. 13: If you don''t have a large punch bowl, add ice to the  container; let chill. 14: Add wine just before serving - float citrus slices in the  punch. 15: ----------- Notes: I recommend a new 15 gallon plus plastic garbage can with cover. 16: Wash and rinse well before using. 17: A new canoe paddle makes an excellent stirring device. (The bonus is they can be saved and used for this again, or can be used for their original purpose.)  DO NOT USE a metal container (unless it is stainless steel). Due to the interaction of the rum and citric acids on metal - it would ruin the punch with a metallic flavour and the dissolved metals could poison your guests.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3100,"Caribbean Vegetable & Chicken Curry","0","PT0S","PT0S","For a vegetarian version, omit first 4 ingredients.   This dish is much better the next day as it gives time for the flavours to  blend.","Chicken Breast",4.0,5.0,264.7,5.9,1.0,56.6,184.6,32.1,5.4,8.3,22.4,"8.0","Caribbean Vegetable & Chicken Curry Recipe Instructions:  1: Pat chicken dry. 2: In small bowl, combine mustard, sesame oil and 1 tbsp. curry  powder. 3: Preheat barbecue or broiler and grill chicken  for 5 minutes per side (chicken will not be completely cooked). Cut into 2-inch  chunks. 4: Reserve. Heat oil in large, deep skillet or Dutch oven. 5: Add garlic,  ginger and hot chile pepper. 6: Cook for 30 seconds. 7: Add remaining 2 tbsp. curry  powder, allspice, cinnamon and nutmeg. 8: Cook for 30 seconds longer. 9: Add onion,  leek and stock. 10: Cook until liquid evaporates. 11: Add pureed tomatoes and bring to  boil. 12: Add potatoes and sweet potato and cook, covered, for 10 minutes. 13: Add  carrots, squash, pineapple juice, plantains, chickpeas and chicken and cook,  covered, for 30 minutes longer. 14: Taste and adjust seasonings if necessary. 15: To  serve, sprinkle with cilantro.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3101,"Tiki Torch Chicken Satays","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Tiki Torch Chicken Satays recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",3.0,2.0,37.9,0.8,0.2,18.2,95.9,1.3,0.1,1.1,6.2,"0.0","Tiki Torch Chicken Satays Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large bowl, combine the curry, garlic, soy sauce, lemon juice, honey and  water. 2: Add the chicken strips and marinate in the refrigerator for 1 hour. 3: Thread 1 chicken strip on each skewer and grill on medium high heat 4 minutes  per side until chicken is cooked through.");
