INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3133,"Old-Fashioned Porridge Bread","0","PT0S","PT0S","I have varied the following recipe to utilize 5, 7 and 10-grain cereals, substituting them for the rolled oats. I also substitute a cup of whole or cracked-wheat flour for a cup of the "additional" flour. I also sprinkle some multi-grain on the loaf tops before the rising stage in the loaf pans. The term Porridge Bread comes from the fact that the cereal is softened in hot water. This is really an Oat Bread. This old recipe is in the narrative style.","Yeast Breads",0.0,0.0,1360.3,18.2,4.1,0.0,2361.0,264.0,11.8,34.5,32.6,"0.0","Old-Fashioned Porridge Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Pour 3 cups boiling water Over 2 cups rolled oats 1/4 cup shortening. Stir  until shortening melts and let stand for about 20 minutes, stirring  occasionally. 2: Meanwhile, dissolve  2 teaspoons sugar in  1 cup lukewarm water  (100 F)  Over this sprinkle  2 envelopes active dry yeast  Let stand for 10  minutes. 3: Then stir briskly with a fork. 4: Stir into partially cooled rolled oat  mixture  2/3 cup table molasses  4 teaspoons salt  Cool to lukewarm. 5: Add  softened yeast to the lukewarm rolled oat mixture. Stir Beat in  2-1/2 cups All  Purpose flour  Beat vigorously by hand or with electric mixer. 6: Then gradually  beat in with a spoon an additional  5-1/2 to 6 cups All Purpose flour  Work in  last of flour with a rotating motion of the hand. 7: Turn dough onto a floured  surface and knead 8 to 10 minutes. 8: Shape into a smooth ball and place in a  greased bowl, rotating dough to grease surface. Cover and let rise until doubled (about 1-1/2 hours). Keep in a warm place. Punch down and shape into 4 loaves. 9: Place in greased 8-1/2 x 4-1/2 inch loaf pans, grease tops, cover and let rise  again until doubled (about 1 hour). Bake in preheated 400F oven for  30 to 35  minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3134,"Kettle Corn","PT10M","PT0S","PT10M","I found this recipe at www.jollytime.com. I hope it is helpful.  Sugar Corn or &quot;Kettle Corn&quot;","Corn",5.0,22.0,29.3,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.1,7.6,0.0,7.5,0.0,"0.0","Kettle Corn Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oil in medium saucepan until hot. 2: Add pop corn and sprinkle all of the sugar over it. 3: Cover and shake continuously until popped.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3135,"Seven Layer Mexican Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Seven Layer Mexican Salad recipe from Food.com.","Mexican",0.0,0.0,5226.5,336.4,181.9,1226.3,8124.0,228.8,62.5,29.0,328.5,"0.0","Seven Layer Mexican Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown hamburger with chopped onion. 2: Drain. 3: Add taco seasoning. 4: Layer refried beans at bottom of oblong pan followed by browned hamburger mix. 5: Next mix the three jars of salsa and pour over hamburger. 6: Spread on top of that the shredded cheese, and then the sour cream. 7: Chop the lettuce fine and sprinkle on top of the sour cream leaving a large hole in the middle.  The chopped tomatoes go inside the hole, still leaving room for the chopped green onions. 8: Serve with the Tostitos chips.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3136,"Salmon with Avocado Wild Rice","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Salmon with Avocado Wild Rice recipe from Food.com.","Rice",5.0,3.0,466.5,18.9,3.9,111.0,643.4,21.8,3.5,2.6,51.1,"8.0","Salmon with Avocado Wild Rice Recipe Instructions:  1: In a medium saucepan combine water, butter, and wild rice mix. 2: Bring to a boil;  cover and simmer until the liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes. 3: Remove from  heat and stir in peeled, sliced avocado and chopped red bell  pepper. 4: In a small bowl combine mayonnaise, chopped cilantro, and  prepared brown mustard. 5: Stir  until thoroughly combined. 6: Cover and  refrigerate. Place salmon filets in a  large skillet. Sprinkle with salt. Place  thinly sliced onion on top. 7: Add  chicken broth and peppercorns. 8: Heat until  the mix ture slightly simmers. 9: Reduce  heat and cook slowly for 10 minutes or until the salmon flakes easily with a  fork. 10: Discard the broth, onion, and  peppercorns. 11: Serve salmon over rice. Top  with the mayonnaise mixture.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3137,"Racks of Lamb with Almond Crust and Orange Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Racks of Lamb with Almond Crust and Orange Sauce recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,203.5,12.7,5.3,20.3,169.6,18.6,1.8,9.9,3.4,"0.0","Racks of Lamb with Almond Crust and Orange Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim the lamb of any excess fat.  You want the racks to be really fat free.  Combine orange juice, white wine and black pepper.. 2: Place in a shallow dish and  add racks of lamb. 3: Arrange lamb so that the meaty part is in the marinade.   Refrigerate and allow to marinate for 1 - 2 hours. 4: Remove the racks from the  marinade and reserve the marinade for the sauce.  Combine parsley, breadcrumbs,  almonds, marmalade, orange rind and butter and mix well. 5: Press mixture over  meaty part of each rack. 6: Place la mb, crumb side up in a baking dish and bake at  200 C for 20 - 25 minutes or until lamb is cooked to your liking. 7: Remove lamb  from oven and cover with foil and allow to rest in a warm place for 10 minutes  before serving with the sauce. Add water, honey and cornflour to reserved  marinade. Bring to the boil; simmer 1 minutes until thickened.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3138,"Fried Chicken","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Fried Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",4.0,3.0,247.2,17.3,5.0,86.2,80.5,0.0,0.0,0.0,21.4,"8.0","Fried Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut up a chicken or two, or get the chicken already cut up. 2: Rub some lemon juice on each piece. Sprinkle some freshly ground black pepper on the chicken to taste.  Let sit for 30 minutes. 3: Now put about 2 inches of peanut oil in a cast iron skillet. Now heat the oil. 4: Pat the chicken dry, now dip the chicken pieces in flour, and salt to taste. Add to the hot oil. 5: Turn chicken after about 15 minutes, and continue cooking for an additional 10 minutes or so, or until done. I really like how the chicken turns out.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3141,"Macaroni Crab Casserole","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Macaroni Crab Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Crab",0.0,0.0,390.4,9.8,3.3,99.3,1544.3,42.5,3.9,4.6,31.5,"0.0","Macaroni Crab Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook macaroni according to package directions. 2: Drain and rinse  with hot water. 3: Drain. 4: Add milk to mushroom soup and heat until  hot. Add peas, all seasonings, then add crab meat, mixing lightly  with fork. 5: Put in greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. 6: Cover with  bread crumbs. 7: Bake in 350 degree oven about 20 to 25 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3142,"Fried Cornbread III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Fried Cornbread III recipe from Food.com.","Breads",5.0,3.0,546.6,10.6,3.0,218.1,1763.7,94.0,8.2,8.2,21.8,"0.0","Fried Cornbread III Recipe Instructions:  1: I use a self rising cornmeal mix for this. 2: I use about 1 cup of cornmeal mix, about 2/3 to 3/4 cup of buttermilk, and 1 egg. 3: You can adjust the amount of milk depending on how thick or thin you would like them to be. And then you just fry them just like pancakes. 4: It''s really simple. Also, sometimes my mom would add some chopped onion to these. Alicia Goodman");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3143,"Vanishing Oatmeal Raisin Cookies","PT10M","PT10M","PT20M","Make and share this Vanishing Oatmeal Raisin Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",5.0,196.0,109.7,4.5,2.6,17.9,89.3,16.3,0.9,8.4,1.6,"0.0","Vanishing Oatmeal Raisin Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 350°F. 2: Beat together margarine and sugars until creamy. 3: Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. 4: Add combined flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; mix well. 5: Stir in oats and raisins; mix well. 6: Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto  ungreased cookie sheet. 7: Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. 8: Cool 2  minutes on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack. 9: Makes about 4 dozen.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3144,"Seven Layer Salad IIi","PT8H","PT15M","PT8H15M","Make and share this Seven Layer Salad IIi recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,303.3,24.7,6.1,28.7,583.2,16.1,1.3,4.5,5.6,"10.0","Seven Layer Salad IIi Recipe Instructions:  1: Arrange in bowl in alternate layers in order given-- lettuce, peas, onion,bell  pepper, and cheese. 2: On top layer, spread mayonnaise to edge of bowl to seal. 3: Sprinkle with bacon bits. 4: Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3145,"Seven Layer Salad IV","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Seven Layer Salad IV recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,2.0,247.1,18.3,5.7,27.9,376.1,14.7,2.4,5.1,7.0,"0.0","Seven Layer Salad IV Recipe Instructions:  1: Layer in the following order in a large 4-qt bowl: Lettuce, celery onion,  peas,bacon, cheese and spre  ad the mayonnaise mixture over all, sealing the  entire top to the edges. 2: Refrigerate overnight without covering. 3: Toss before  serving. 4: Reduce the fat and calories by using no-fat mayonnaise,  reduced-fat cheese, and imitation low-fat bacon bits.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3146,"Banbury Tarts","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Some folks use Craisins in place of raisins as done in the Banbury Tart recipe.  It is also great as a filling for cinnamon rolls. I have included three filling  combinations - and I will vouch for the Orange-Craisin combination. Hope these  are useful.","Dessert",0.0,1.0,255.3,7.3,2.8,30.2,122.9,47.7,0.8,36.6,2.1,"0.0","Banbury Tarts Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat the oven to 350°F. 2: Combine raisins through lemon juice and rind. 3: Roll out the pastry dough to  about 1/8-inch thickness. 4: Cut into 3-inch squares. 5: Place a scant tablespoon of  raisin mixture in the centre of each square. Fold the square in half, forming a  triangle. Seal the edges by brushing wi  th water. 6: Cut a small X in the top with  a sharp knife. Bake for 20 minutes or until browned. 7: Notes: Puff pastry can be used instead of pie crust. If so bake at 400 F for 15  minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3147,"Bruschetta II","PT15M","PT20M","PT35M","Make and share this Bruschetta II recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,3.0,309.1,11.5,2.9,7.3,589.6,41.0,2.6,1.1,10.2,"6.0","Bruschetta II Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix fresh pressed garlic and olive oil in a bowl. 2: Cut baguette or sourdough  loaf into individual slices. 3: Using basting brush, brush oil mixture onto one  side of each slice.  Place a slice or two of Roma tomato onto the oiled side of  each piece of bread. 4: Sprinkle fresh shredded Parmesan cheese over top. 5: Add  Italian seasoning to taste.  Place all slices of bread on a cookie sheet or  toaster oven pan & broil until cheese is bubbling. 6: *I''ve also used chopped roma tomatoes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3148,"Chicken Mole II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chicken Mole II recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",5.0,1.0,1090.0,73.3,20.4,230.9,1223.0,41.4,7.8,22.1,67.9,"0.0","Chicken Mole II Recipe Instructions:  1: Chicken: In a large bowl or plastic bag, combine flour, 1 measuring tablespoon chili powder, the salt and pepper. 2: Add chicken pieces (2 to 3 at a time); coat well. 3: Heat oil in a large skillet; brown half the chicken pieces on all sides over medium heat. Drain thoroughly on paper towels. 4: Repeat with remaining chicken. 5: In small skillet, saute onion and garlic until golden. 6: Return chicken to skillet. Add the water; simmer, covered, over medium heat about 35 to 40 minutes or until chi cken is tender. 7: Transfer to a serving platter and top with Chocolate Mole Sauce. Garnish each serving with chopped peanuts. 8: Chocolate Mole Sauce: In a small saucepan combine tomatoes and green chilies, tomato puree, semi-sweet chocolate morsels, remaining chili powder and bouillon. 9: Cook over low heat until morsels melt and sauce is heated through. 10: Makes 6 to 8 servings and 3 1/2 cups sauce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3149,"Herbed Gougere Puffs","PT50M","PT25M","PT1H15M","This is an adopted recipe that I''ve not yet had the chance to try, although it looks wonderful. Any reviews by those who make this recipe before I do (or after, of course) would be appreciated. Thanks!","European",4.5,2.0,86.5,6.2,3.7,46.2,94.9,4.3,0.1,0.1,3.2,"0.0","Herbed Gougere Puffs Recipe Instructions:  1: In 2-quart saucepan, heat 1 cup water, butter and salt to a boil. 2: Remove from  heat and add flour  all at once, beating until smooth. 3: Return saucepan to medium heat; cook, stirring constantly,  until dough becomes stiff and pulls away from  sides of pan, about 5 minutes. 4: Remove from heat  and beat in eggs, one at a  time. Stir in 2/3 cup Swiss cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley, dill  and chives. 5: Lightly grease one or two baking sheets. 6: Drop heaping tablespoon of dough onto   baking sheet, forming one 15 inch or two 8-inch rings, with dough barely  touching. 7: Sprinkle with  rema ining 1/3 cup Swiss cheese. Bake at 425 degrees F  25 minutes or until puffed and golden  brown. 8: Serve warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3150,"Pa Pot Roast","PT2H","PT10M","PT2H10M","Adopted recipe. This smells great when it is cooking. It also lends itself well to adding whatever seasonings you prefer. You could very easily make this is a crockpot/slow cooker too.","Roast",4.0,1.0,278.3,10.8,4.3,99.8,580.7,6.2,0.9,2.5,32.4,"6.0","Pa Pot Roast Recipe Instructions:  1: Sprinkle meat with salt, seasoning salt and freshly ground black pepper. 2: Heat oil in large, heavy skillet. 3: Brown beef on all sides. 4: Place carrots, celery, onion, bay leaves and parsley in bottom of heavy casserole or dutch oven, just large enough so roast fits snugly. 5: Add wine, Worcestershire sauce, liquid smoke and beef broth to cover meat. 6: Cover with lid or heavy foil and bake (braise) at 350°F for 1-1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is very tender. 7: Let meat stand in braising liquid until ready to serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3151,"Silver and Gold Salad","0","PT10M","PT10M","I adopted this recipe in the February 2005 recipe adoption.  This one may end up being my problem child; I just don''t know what to do with it.  I made this as directed in the recipe, but just can''t see eating it plain as a salad.  So I spread it on a torilla with some lettuce, sliced tomato and sliced avocado for a veggie wrap sandwich.  It was actually quite good.  My other ideas are to 1) pack into a measuring cup and turn out onto a green salad, or 2) add to pasta and Italian dressing for a pasta salad, or 3) Add as a topping on a hearty sandwich, like roast beef and pumpernickel.  If anyone has any other ideas, I''d love to hear them!","High In...",0.0,0.0,182.6,13.3,7.9,40.5,323.1,5.7,1.1,2.4,10.7,"6.0","Silver and Gold Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: In medium bowl, combine dressing and sour cream. 2: Add alfalfa sprouts, carrots,  Swiss and  Cheddar cheeses; toss lightly. 3: Serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3152,"Walnut Brownie Cheesecake","PT1H10M","PT25M","PT1H35M","This recipe is one of my Adoptees. After making it, I felt it needed something to perk it up a bit and Chocolate Fluff Icing recipe#81988 was a perfect addition. This cheesecake has a different texture than traditional cream cheese cheesecakes but delicious none the less. Enjoy!","Cheesecake",5.0,2.0,380.6,18.8,7.6,90.8,280.3,40.2,1.6,28.4,15.5,"10.0","Walnut Brownie Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Lightly grease sides of 8 or 9-inch springform pan. 2: Combine crust ingredients;  mix well. 3: Press  evenly over bottom of pan. 4: Chill while preparing filling. 5: In  bowl of electric mixer, combine Ricotta cheese, brown sugar, cocoa,  half-and-half, flour, vanilla and salt; beat until smooth. 6: Add eggs,  one at a  time; beat until smooth. 7: Stir in walnuts. 8: Pour batter over crust. Bake at 350 F  1 hour  and 10 minutes or until center is just set. Turn off oven; cool in oven  with  door propped open 30  minutes. 9: Remove to wire cooling rack; loosen cake  from rim of pan with metal spatula. 10: Cool  completely; chill at least 4 hours. 11: If desired, sift confectioners sugar over cheesecake immediately before serving, or ice with suggested icing and garnish with chocolate curls and whole walnuts.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3153,"Jicama Salad","PT2H","PT10M","PT2H10M","Make and share this Jicama Salad recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",3.0,1.0,194.6,1.0,0.2,0.0,33.8,47.2,15.0,21.7,5.0,"0.0","Jicama Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large bowl combine jicama, cucumber and orange. 2: Sprinkle with lemon juice  and chili powder; toss. 3: Cover and chill at least 2 hours. 4: Just before serving,  sprinkle lightly with salt.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3154,"Sweet and Sour Chicken","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sweet and Sour Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",0.0,0.0,146.5,3.6,1.0,24.2,90.1,19.9,1.7,14.7,8.8,"0.0","Sweet and Sour Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut chicken; set aside. Prepare pineapple, onion, green pepper and jicama; set  aside. Combine brown sugar and corn- starch, stir in vinegar, pineapple juice,  soy sauce, pepper sauce and salt to taste; set aside. In a 2 quart glass  casserole dish put chicken pieces. 2: Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes stirring  every 2 minutes until chicken is done. Add vinegar mixture and cook on High for  4 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes. 3: When sauce is clear and boiling, add  pineapple, onion, green pepper and jicama; mix well. 4: Cook 1 to 2 minutes until  vegetables are desired doneness. 5: ENSALADA DE NOCHE BUE  NA  1 (20 oz.) can pineapple chunks  2 medium bananas  1 (16 oz.) can sliced beets, drained  1 jicama, peeled and sliced (optional)  1 stick sugar cane, peeled and chopped (optional)  lettuce  mayonnaise  2 large oranges  1 large apple  1/2 cup peanuts  milk  Drain pineapple, reserve juice. Peel and section oranges, peel and slice  bananas, core and slice apple. Toss apple and bananas with orange sections and a  little pineapple juice. Drain fruits and beets. 6: Arrange pineapple, beets,  bananas, oranges, apple, jicama and sugar cane on large let- tuce-lined  platter. 7: Sprinkle with peanuts. 8: Thin mayonnaise with little milk to make  drizzling consistency. 9: Serve with salad. 10: Makes 6 to 8 servings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3155,"Mushroom Bruschetta","0","PT0S","PT0S","Here''s a very tasty and different bruschetta served in Tulio Ristorante in Seattle  MUSHROOM BRUSCHETTA (Bruschetta Mista)","European",0.0,0.0,337.5,16.4,2.5,0.0,364.1,39.6,4.6,4.7,12.2,"1.0","Mushroom Bruschetta Recipe Instructions:  1: Brush bread lightly with olive oil and grill both sides until lightly toasted. 2: Quickly saut mushroom in preheated pan with olive oil until lightly browned. 3: Remove from heat and  stir in remaining ingredients. 4: Spoon mushrooms over slices of bread --Tulio Restaurant");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3156,"Stuffed Jalapeno Peppers -Armadillo Eggs","PT30M","PT15M","PT45M","Make and share this Stuffed Jalapeno Peppers -Armadillo Eggs recipe from Food.com.","< 60 Mins",5.0,2.0,221.9,10.5,4.2,27.8,657.1,23.5,2.7,2.6,8.3,"15.0","Stuffed Jalapeno Peppers -Armadillo Eggs Recipe Instructions:  1: For the stuffing I like to use Stove Top stuffing for pork. 2: Cook stuffing mix according to package directions. 3: Combine sausage with stuffing. 4: Cut stem and seeds from jalapenos, fill with cheese. Add egg to sausage and stuffing mixture. Mold mixture in egg shape around jalapenos. 5: Roll in bread crumbs until covered well. 6: Bake in a 400 degree farenheit preheated oven for 30 minutes or until brown. 7: More recipes at: http://maxpages.com/recipegallery.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3157,"Cranberry Apple Pie with Soft Gingersnap Crust","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cranberry Apple Pie with Soft Gingersnap Crust recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,2.0,208.8,5.2,1.2,0.0,167.6,40.5,2.8,23.5,1.6,"0.0","Cranberry Apple Pie with Soft Gingersnap Crust Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375F. 2: Place gingersnaps and margarine in food processor;  process until finely ground. 3: Press gingersnap mixture into 8\ 4: ,  5: ,  6:  pie plate or casserole dish. 7: Sprinkle with granulated sugar. 8: Bake 35 min or until tender. 9: Spoon filling  into gingersnap crust and serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3158,"Lemon Cranberry Pie","PT30M","PT15M","PT45M","Make and share this Lemon Cranberry Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",4.0,1.0,417.3,14.0,5.4,88.8,210.0,68.3,1.0,54.1,6.7,"8.0","Lemon Cranberry Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 325 degrees. 2: Prepare pastry. 3: In small sauce pan, combine  cranberry sauce, cornstarch, and sugar over medium heat until thickened and  bubbly. 4: Spoon into pastry shell. 5: In small mixing bowl, beat the condensed milk, lemon, and egg yolk until well-blended. Spoon evenly over cranberry mixture. 6: Bake 30 minutes, cool, then chill thoroughly before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3159,"Cape Cod Cranberry Velvet Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cape Cod Cranberry Velvet Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,2.0,792.0,50.1,24.5,127.7,464.4,79.3,1.9,39.4,8.1,"8.0","Cape Cod Cranberry Velvet Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. 2: In small mixer bowl, beat whipping cream, sugar and vanilla until soft peaks form. 3: Gradually add to cream cheese, beating until smooth and creamy. 4: Set aside a few whole cranberries from sauce for garnish. 5: Fold remaining sauce into whipped mixture. Spoon into pi e crust. Freeze 4 hours until firm. 6: Garnish with reserved berries. 7: Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3160,"Salpicon de Choros (Smoked Mussel Salad)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Salpicon de Choros (Smoked Mussel Salad) recipe from Food.com.","Mussels",0.0,0.0,1428.0,60.0,11.6,742.0,1496.0,156.5,42.2,33.2,91.0,"0.0","Salpicon de Choros (Smoked Mussel Salad) Recipe Instructions:  1: Soak mesquite chips in water for a few hours; heat them in a large Dutch  oven or heavy roaster. 2: Meanwhile, scrub the mussels and place in a dish  that fits inside the roaster. 3: When the chips smoke, place the mussels on  top, splash water around for steam, cover tightly and heat for 2-3 minutes. 4: Remove from heat and leave covered for 1 hour. 5: Discard unopened mussels. 6: Shred lettuce; scrape carrot, cut in juliennes and blanch; peel, seed and  dice tomatoes; peel and dice avocado; peel and slice eggs. 7: Mix mussels and vegetables, toss with dressing and le  t stand for a few  minutes. 8: Serve in bowls, garnished with egg slices.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3161,"Empanadas de Honoro (Beef Turnovers)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Empanadas de Honoro (Beef Turnovers) recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.0,3.0,690.4,39.2,10.5,169.4,348.3,61.5,4.0,4.5,24.2,"8.0","Empanadas de Honoro (Beef Turnovers) Recipe Instructions:  1: Marinate beef in a glass bowl with the juice of lemon and lime, 2-3 sprigs of  oregano and chili to taste for at least 4 hours, or overnight.  Sift flour with  baking powder and salt; beat eggs, warm the milk, melt the shortening and add. 2: Mix to make a stiff dough, cut into 20 pieces and roll each into a small circle. (Alternately, use frozen pastry.)  Chop (not grind) the meat. Chop the onions  and fry in the oil; mix in spices, salt to taste, and beef. 3: Saute until meat  turns grey. 4: Place a spoonful of mixture on each dough circle; add slices of  egg, olive and raisins. 5: Fold in two, brush edges with milk and seal. 6: Bake in a  400 degree F oven until lightly browned.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3162,"What-to-Do-with-All-the Egg-Yolks Bread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this What-to-Do-with-All-the Egg-Yolks Bread recipe from Food.com.","Breads",5.0,7.0,531.9,31.9,6.4,98.7,360.8,53.3,3.6,7.3,9.6,"8.0","What-to-Do-with-All-the Egg-Yolks Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Butter a 10\ 2: ,  3: ,  4: ,  5: ,  6: ,  7: ,  8: Put the dough back in the bowl, cover the bowl and let the dough  rise at room temperature until it is doubled in bulk. 9: Using a wooden spoon,  beat down the risen dough for about a minute.  Place the dough into the buttered tube pan and allow it to rise at room  temperature until it is doubled in bulk. 10: Preheat the oven to 375 . 11: Bake the bread for 45-50 minutes or until it is  dark golden brown and sounds hollow when tapped. 12: Place on a rack to cool or  serve warm. 13: Once cooled, the bread is also excellent sliced and toasted. 14: Recipe By : Diane Mott Davidson, Killer Pancakes");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3163,"Cranberry Coconut Muffins","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Make and share this Cranberry Coconut Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",4.5,4.0,147.5,5.2,1.9,24.2,198.9,22.5,0.8,11.1,2.8,"0.0","Cranberry Coconut Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: In bowl, stir together flour, sugar, 1/2 cup of the coconut, baking  powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. 2: Whisk buttermilk, eggs, oil and vanilla; stir into flour mixture along with cranberries just until blended. 3: Spoon into lightly greased muffin tins, filling three-quarters full;  sprinkle with remaining coconut. 4: Bake in 400F oven for about 20  minutes or until golden and firm to the touch.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3164,"Holiday Season Cranberry Bread","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","We always have a lot of people visiting during the holiday season and it''s always nice to have a little something homemade on hand to offer.  This bread is nice to give away as gifts during the holidays.  Delicious plain, with butter or with cream cheese (&lt;-- my personal favorite).  Thank you mom for this recipe. :)","Quick Breads",5.0,12.0,362.6,13.4,3.0,34.1,322.9,56.4,3.0,28.4,6.5,"8.0","Holiday Season Cranberry Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda into large bowl and set aside. 2: Add 2 tablespoons melted butter to 3/4 cup freshly squeezed orange juice. 3: Add beaten egg to orange mixture and add to dry ingredients. 4: Mix until dry ingredients are moistened. 5: Stir in chopped nuts and cranberries. 6: Turn into (greased and floured) 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pan. 7: Bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes to 1 hour. 8: Let stand 24 hours before slicing. 9: This recipe freezes very well - I usually wrap first in Saran Wrap, then wrap it in aluminum foil and then place in zip-lock bags - I generally take out of the freezer the night before serving, if possible. 10: Delicious plain or with butter or cream cheese spread on it.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3165,"Pineapple Roll Using Splenda","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pineapple Roll Using Splenda recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,165.7,1.6,0.3,20.8,426.7,34.4,1.3,8.8,3.6,"8.0","Pineapple Roll Using Splenda Recipe Instructions:  1: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.  Rub margarine into flour(reserve 2: 4 tsps flour) and stir in Splenda. 3: Beat egg yolk with 2 tsps lemon juice   and water and add to flour. 4: Combine to form a firm dough. 5: Knead lightly   and refrigerate 30 mins. 6: Sprinkle work surface with reserved flour & roll out to a  large rectangle.  Mix softened honey into pineapple & apple, spread over pastry and roll Swiss roll style.  Spray baking dish   with cooking spray and place roll in prepared dish. 7: Sprinkle with   brown sugar. 8: Bake 400F 30 mins till cooked. 9: Heat pineapple juice,   made up to 1 1/4 cups with water, till boiling. 10: Blend cornstarch with   a little water and add to mixture.  Cook, stirring till mixture boils,   then simmer 1 min. 11: Stir in remaining lemon juice and pour over warm   roll. 12: MMMMM");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3166,"Grandma Hornsby''s Popcorn Balls","0","PT25M","PT25M","Make and share this Grandma Hornsby''s Popcorn Balls recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",3.0,2.0,998.5,22.6,5.1,8.7,1379.3,205.7,3.6,160.8,3.3,"0.0","Grandma Hornsby''s Popcorn Balls Recipe Instructions:  1: Put sugar, brown sugar, syrup, and water into a sauce pan--stirring  until all sugar is dissolved. 2: Add the butter--continue to cook but  without stirring, until it reaches the temperature of 240F (Use a  candy thermometer.). 3: Put the popped corn into a large mixing bowl and add the salt to it. 4: Pour the candied mixture over the pop corn and mix well. 5: Shape into small balls and then wrap in wax paper.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3167,"Chunky Fruit and Nut Relish","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chunky Fruit and Nut Relish recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",0.0,0.0,2867.0,81.6,7.1,0.0,28.1,559.6,57.4,456.5,22.4,"1.0","Chunky Fruit and Nut Relish Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large saucepan, bring cranberries, sugr and orange juice to a boil,  stirring occasionally. 2: Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered for 8-10 minutes  or until the berries burst. Remove from the heat; stir in peaches,  pineapple, pecans and raisins. 3: Cool. 4: Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3168,"Cranberry Star Mold","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cranberry Star Mold recipe from Food.com.","Gelatin",4.0,3.0,183.2,11.1,6.9,40.8,61.8,20.7,2.3,16.4,2.0,"0.0","Cranberry Star Mold Recipe Instructions:  1: Drain one 9-ounce can (1 cup) crushed pineapple, reserving syrup. 2: Add  boiling water to syrup to make 1 1/4 cups. 3: Dissolve 1 package raspberry  flavored gelatin in the hot liquid; chill till partially set. Fold in one  cup drained orange sections (membrane removed), and the pineapple. Whip 1  cup heavy cream; fold in. 4: Pour into 1 1/2 mold. 5: Chill till set. Unmold; top  with whipped cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3169,"No Cook Cranberry Relish","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this No Cook Cranberry Relish recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",5.0,1.0,402.5,0.2,0.0,0.0,59.2,104.3,7.9,75.3,1.0,"0.0","No Cook Cranberry Relish Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash cranberries and discard any soft berries. 2: In food processor, chop  cranberries. 3: Add jam and marmalade and pulse just to combine.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3170,"Paradise Jelly","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Paradise Jelly recipe from Food.com.","Jellies",0.0,0.0,4558.7,12.6,1.4,0.0,101.8,1203.9,186.0,846.8,41.2,"0.0","Paradise Jelly Recipe Instructions:  1: The apples and quince must be  washed, the stem and blossom ends scooped out, and each one quartered. 2: Remove any bruises to clean flesh. 3: Pick over the  cranberries, discarding any less than perfect. Place all in non aluminum pot and barely cover with water Boil until they are quite soft. Strain through jelly  bag. 4: Slice vanilla beans once lengthwise, and place in clean pot. Add strained  liquid and boil gently for 12 minutes. 5: Set beans aside. Measure juice, using 1  cup juice to 1 cup sugar, and cooking no more than 4 cups at a time. Place in  clean pot. Boil until jelly sheets from spoon. 6: Pour into 1/2 pint sterilized  jars and seal. 7: Process 5 minutes in boiling bath. 8: NOTE: Cheat if you like, and add more water to the fruit after the first straining. 9: Boil and strain that, combine with the first liquid and continue as directed. 10: There''s so much pectin in the fruit you can get away with it. Of course if you''re going for the top prize at the fair, you might want to forego that this time. Use the vanilla beans in the water you  boil for your next few pitchers of herbal iced tea. 11: Recipe By : DDMmom");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3171,"Iced Chai","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Iced Chai recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",4.0,1.0,546.6,9.0,5.6,34.2,175.5,116.8,0.5,103.6,8.6,"1.0","Iced Chai Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring water to a boil in a saucepan. 2: Add tea, ginger, vanilla, cinnamon, and  bay leaves. 3: Simmer for 5 minutes, adding milk near the end of the simmering  time. Stir in honey. 4: Remove from heat, cover, and steep for 3 minutes. 5: Strain  through a sieve to remove spices. 6: Chill. 7: Serve over ice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3172,"Layered Salad","PT24H","PT15M","PT24H15M","Make and share this Layered Salad recipe from Food.com.","Easy",5.0,1.0,450.6,32.5,9.4,53.3,880.5,26.3,3.3,8.5,15.3,"0.0","Layered Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Layer the bowl with all ingredients in order--the mayonnaise should be the  sealer for the layers. 2: Seal in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 24  hours. 3: Toss before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3173,"Applesauce Cake in Jars","0","PT0S","PT0S","Recipes for Cakes Baked In Jars      Ever baked cakes in canning jars? It''s neat! ANY quick bread-type cake can be  baked in canning jars. Lighter cakes tend to fall once the jar seals. I usually  bake one jar first -- you have to know how high the batter rises. I usually fill  ONE jar 1/2 full then bake it to see how high it rises, then go from there. You  don''t want the cake to come out of the top of the jar, only to within 1/4 to 1/2  inch from the lip of the jar. Write it down on your recipe (how far you filled  the jars)! Once you''ve established how high the cake rises, you can go from  there. The first time around is a bit tricky because you won''t know how many  jars you''ll need. MOST of the recipes I''ve tried I end up using around 8.    Sterilize as many jars as you think you''ll need and go from there. Make sure  your LIDS are new, the rings don''t ha  ve to be As the jars do seal, the cakes are  as moist as the day you put them into the jars--sometimes MORE SO. The baking  times will v","Dessert",0.0,0.0,5491.4,162.3,41.6,744.0,6643.1,959.9,20.3,535.0,69.4,"1.0","Applesauce Cake in Jars Recipe Instructions:  1: Sterilize 8 (12 oz Ball Quilted Crystal - #14400-81400) canning jars, lids and 2: rings by boiling for 10 minutes. 3: Remove the jars and allow to air-dry and cool. 4: Leave the lids and rings in the hot water until ready to use. Once the jars are  cool enough to handle, grease them (use a pastry brush) with shortening (DO NOT  use Pam or Baker''s Secret); set aside. Cream together the shortening and sugar. 5: Beat in the eggs, one at a time, until the mixture is light and f  luffy. 6: Add the  applesauce and water; set aside. In another bowl, sift together the flour,  baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves. 7: Blend dry ingredients  into the applesauce mixture. Fold in the nuts. 8: Pour batter into the jars,  filling them about 1/2 full. 9: Place jars onto a cookie sheet or they''ll fall  over. 10: Bake in a preheated  325-degree oven for 35-40 minutes or until a pick inserted deep into the center  of each cake comes out clean. 11: Remove jars from the oven, one-at-a-time (use  HEAVY-DUTY MITTS, the jars ARE HOT!); place a lid, then a ring on top and screw  down tightly.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3174,"Apple Cake in a Jar With Lemon Sauce","PT1H5M","PT20M","PT1H25M","Ever baked cakes in canning jars? It''s neat! ANY quick bread-type cake can be  baked in canning jars. Lighter cakes tend to fall once the jar seals. I usually  bake one jar first -- you have to know how high the batter rises. I usually fill  ONE jar 1/2 full then bake it to see how high it rises, then go from there. You  don''t want the cake to come out of the top of the jar, only to within 1/4 to 1/2  inch from the lip of the jar. Write it down on your recipe (how far you filled  the jars)! Once you''ve established how high the cake rises, you can go from  there. The first time around is a bit tricky because you won''t know how many  jars you''ll need. MOST of the recipes I''ve tried I end up using around 8.    Sterilize as many jars as you think you''ll need and go from there. Make sure  your LIDS are new, the rings don''t ha  ve to be As the jars do seal, the cakes are  as moist as the day you put them into the jars--sometimes MORE SO. The baking  times will vary.","Dessert",4.0,3.0,945.9,33.0,8.9,115.0,1069.0,156.2,4.8,105.1,12.0,"0.0","Apple Cake in a Jar With Lemon Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix the ingredients together in the order given. 2: Sterilize 7 to 9 wide mouth  pint jars and lids. 3: Grease them with shortening. 4: Fill the jars half full and  bake on the middle wire wire rack in the oven. 5: Bake for 45 minutes at 325  degrees. 6: As soon as the cake is done, remove the bottles from the oven one at a  time. Wipe the rim of the bottle clean with cloth and put on the hot sterilized  Lids. 7: Screw down the bands and let cool. 8: Important-- do not use small mouth  jars. 9: Do not add any other ingredients. 10: As the cake cools in the sealed jar, it  will pull away from the sides of the jar and come out easily when ready to  serve. Slice and serve with lemon sauce. 11: In a pan, thoroughly stir together the corn starch, sugar, and salt. gradually  stir in the boiling water, stirring constantly to keep it smooth. 12: Continue  stirring and cook over moderate heat until boiling. 13: Boil gently for about 20  minutes. 14: Remove from heat, add butter, lemon rind and juice. stir thoroughly. 15: Serve hot over apple cake in a jar. 16: This sauce is thicker and more tart than the usual lemon sauce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3175,"Pumpkin Spice Cake in Jars","PT35M","PT15M","PT50M","Recipes for Cakes Baked In Jars      Ever baked cakes in canning jars? It''s neat! ANY quick bread-type cake can be  baked in canning jars. Lighter cakes tend to fall once the jar seals. I usually  bake one jar first -- you have to know how high the batter rises. I usually fill  ONE jar 1/2 full then bake it to see how high it rises, then go from there. You  don''t want the cake to come out of the top of the jar, only to within 1/4 to 1/2  inch from the lip of the jar. Write it down on your recipe (how far you filled  the jars)! Once you''ve established how high the cake rises, you can go from  there. The first time around is a bit tricky because you won''t know how many  jars you''ll need. MOST of the recipes I''ve tried I end up using around 8.    Sterilize as many jars as you think you''ll need and go from there. Make sure  your LIDS are new, the rings don''t ha  ve to be As the jars do seal, the cakes are  as moist as the day you put them into the jars--sometimes MORE SO. The baking  times will vary.","Dessert",5.0,3.0,377.9,19.8,2.8,46.5,327.0,48.1,2.4,31.6,4.9,"16.0","Pumpkin Spice Cake in Jars Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 325°F. 2: Sterilize 8 (12 oz) Ball Quilted Crystal Canning Jars (14400-81400), lids and rings by boiling them for 10 minutes. 3: Leave the  lids and rings in the hot water until you''re ready to use them; remove jars and  allow the jars to air-dry and cool. 4: Prepare the batter in the meantime. 5: Using a pastry brush, brush the inside of the cooled jars with shortening (DO NOT use  Pam or Baker''s Secret); set aside. 6: Coarsely chop the raisins and walnuts; set  aside. 7: Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cloves,  cinnamon and ginger in a large bowl. 8: Add raisins and walnuts; toss to lightly  combine. 9: In another large bowl, beat eggs at high speed until thick and yellow  (2-3 minutes). 10: Gradually beat in the sugar until thick and light. 11: At low speed,  beat in the oil and pumpkin; blend well. 12: Gradually stir in the flour mixture until well blended. 13: Divide among the 8 canning jars (should be slightly less  than 1/2 full. 14: Wipe the sides of the jar off (inside/ outside) in case you slop  or it''ll burn. 15: Place jars onto a cookie sheet or they''ll tip over. 16: Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until a pick inserted into the center of each jar comes out clean. 17: Have your lids and rings ready. 18: Take one jar at a time from the oven; place a  lid and ring on and screw down tightly. 19: Use HEAVY-DUTY mitts--the jars are HOT!  Place the jars onto your counter top too cool. 20: You''ll know when they''ve sealed,  you''ll hear a \ 21: .");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3176,"Gingerbread Men","PT12M","PT10M","PT22M","Make and share this Gingerbread Men recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,41.0,84.2,3.1,1.2,6.1,63.7,13.1,0.3,5.4,1.1,"0.0","Gingerbread Men Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix together the shortening, sugar, and molasses. 2: Next, add egg and  beat completely. 3: Combine all dry ingredients and add to the creamed  ingredients--using 1/2 cup increments. 4: Beat well after each addition. 5: Refrigerate the dough until cold. 6: Roll out until the dough is about  1/4 inch thick. 7: Use cookie cutters to form the figures. 8: Place in a 350° oven and bake for 10 - 12 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3177,"Wine and Cheese Bread Pudding","0","PT0S","PT0S","This is an adopted recipe. I shall be trying it out and then post any additional information if needs be. Feel free to try it out first and share your comments!","Dessert",0.0,0.0,483.9,11.5,6.7,27.8,491.0,78.5,2.4,32.7,13.2,"8.0","Wine and Cheese Bread Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Place bread slices on baking sheet and toast under broiler until light brown. 2: Tear into bite-size  pieces; spread in even layer in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking  dish. 3: Drizzle wine over bread so all is  moistened. 4: Sprinkle raisins evenly over bread, then sprinkle evenly with Monterey Jack cheese;  set aside. In 2-quart  heavy saucepan, cook sugar over medium heat without stirring until sugar begins  to  melt at edge. Start stirring with wooden spoon and stir until sugar melts  completely and turns  straw-colored. 5: Reduce heat; stir constantly until sugar is color of dark honey. 6: Remove from heat;  add water very gradually, stirring  constantly. 7: Mixture will boil up . 8: If lumps of hard caramel  develop, return pan  to heat; boil until mixture is smooth. 9: Remove from heat; stir in cinnamon and   butter. 10: Pour evenly over bread. 11: Cover with foil; bake at 350 F 30 minutes. 12: Remove foil; cool 10  minutes. 13: Serve warm with whipped cream. 14: Sodium 270 mg.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3178,"Golden Gate Quesadilla","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Golden Gate Quesadilla recipe from Food.com.","Mexican",0.0,0.0,115.0,4.1,2.2,8.8,145.3,12.8,0.7,4.6,3.1,"32.0","Golden Gate Quesadilla Recipe Instructions:  1: Spread one side of each tortilla with butter. 2: Turn over onto wax paper; spread  other side with  marmalade. Combine Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheeses; sprinkle evenly over  tortillas. 3: Top  with apple and raisins. 4: Fold tortillas in half; place on ungreased baking  sheets. 5: Bake at 350 F  12 minutes or until cheese is melted and tortillas are golden brown. 6: Combine  yogurt and  cinnamon. 7: Cut each tortilla in half; serve with yogurt mixture for dipping.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3179,"Savory Crab Cheesecake","PT40M","PT30M","PT1H10M","I adopted this recipe in after a previous member left the site.  I haven''t had a chance to prepare it, but this is what the previous owner had to say: &quot;Hmmmm, this is a recipe I adopted -- I looked it over and made some major corrections (it called for a cup of dijon mustard - Oh my!) but I still have yet to make it myself.  I will update as soon as I have the chance to get to it...Caveat Emptor!&quot;","Crab",4.0,1.0,126.5,7.2,4.1,71.2,167.0,5.3,0.3,0.7,10.0,"10.0","Savory Crab Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: In small skillet, cook onion and garlic in butter about 5 minutes or until  tender; cool. 2: With electric mixer, blend Ricotta cheese, half-and-half,  mustard and flour until smooth. 3: Add  eggs, one at a time, blending until smooth. 4: Stir in crab meat, green onions, 1/2 cup Parmesan  cheese, andcooled onion mixture. 5: Pour batter into lightly greased 9-inch springform pan;  sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.   Bake at 350º F 40 minutes or until center is set.  Cool on wire rack to room temperature; chill. 6: Let stand at room temperature 30  minutes before serving. 7: Serve as a spread on crackers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3180,"Focaccia with Tomato & Cheese","0","PT0S","PT0S","This is an adopted recipe. I shall be trying it out and then post any additional information if needs be. Feel free to try it out first and share your comments!","Cheese",5.0,1.0,1930.8,43.8,12.9,231.5,2251.0,315.7,16.4,18.1,64.2,"1.0","Focaccia with Tomato & Cheese Recipe Instructions:  1: DOUGH SETTING Special instructions: If dough is too sticky because of oil; add 2: up to 1/2 cup flour by Tablespoons until you reach the correct consistency. 3: After the dough has completed the first rising,remove from b/m and punch down. 4: Cover on lightly floured board and allow to rest 5-10 minutes. 5: Spray a 9x13x2  pan with Pam, or brush with olive oil. 6: Briefly knead dough and spread i  nto pan,  using hands to achieve a \ 7: . 8: Form a low ridge around the edge of  the dough. 9: Push dough into corners. 10: The bumps and ridge will allow the topping  to stay in place. Brush surface with olive oil. 11: You can cover and allow to  rise, and bake at this stage, or continue on for Tomato & Cheese topping. 12: TOPPING: Combine tomato paste and spaghetti sauce. Spread on dough. 13: Combine  remaining ingredients. 14: Spread evenly over sauce. Press gently into dough. 15: Cover & allow to rise until doubled. 16: Preheat oven to 375. 17: Bake 25 minutes. 18: Slide  out of pan onto cutting board. 19: Cut into small pieces for appetizers or large  wedges for dinner. 20: This bread rose almost to the top of the 2\ 21: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3181,"Crispy Olive & Herb Focaccia","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Crispy Olive & Herb Focaccia recipe from Food.com.","Breads",4.0,1.0,168.7,4.2,0.6,0.0,79.6,29.2,2.1,0.1,3.8,"10.0","Crispy Olive & Herb Focaccia Recipe Instructions:  1: Stir the yeast into a large mixing bowl with the water & let proof for 10  minutes. 2: Stir in the olive oil, rosemary, sage, olives & garlic. Using a wooden  spoon, mix in the flours & salt & stir until the dough is thick & smooth. 3: Knead  by hand for 8 to 10 minutes until the dough is firm & elastic. Set the dough in  a lightly oiled container, cover with plastic wrap & let rise until doubled. 4: Turn the dough onto an oiled 10 1/2\ 5:  baking pan & stretch it to fit.  If it won''t fit, let it rest for 10 minutes & try again. 6: Cover with a towel & leave until it has half risen, about 30 minutes. 7: 30 minutes before baking,  preheat oven to 400F. 8: Just before baking, dimple the top of the dough with your  fingerti  ps & sprinkle with some extra salt & 2 tsp of oil. 9: Bake for 25 to 30  minutes until golden. 10: Slide off baking sheet onto a rack & let cool for a few  minutes before eating warm or at room temperature. 11: VARIATION: Focaccia Dolce. Substitute 2 oz raisins & 1 oz pine nuts for the  olives, herbs & garlic. Soak the raisins in warm water for 30 minutes before  using & toast the pine nuts.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3182,"Focaccia with Rosemary & Olives","PT20M","PT20M","PT40M","This is a simple and basic Focaccia recipe.  Focaccia is an Italian flat bread which is used as a side to many meals, as a base for pizza or as sandwich bread.","Breads",4.5,3.0,187.1,16.6,4.8,16.5,352.8,2.5,0.5,0.2,7.5,"4.0","Focaccia with Rosemary & Olives Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 450F. 2: Place dough in a bowl. 3: Add 1 Tbsp olive oil and minced rosemary. 4: Season with salt & freshly ground black pepper, to taste. 5: Knead dough until all ingredients are combined. 6: Roll dough out on to a lightly floured baking sheet and press dough into 12x9\ 7: ,  8: ,  9: Bake until bread is almost cooked through and cheese begins to brown, about 12 minutes. 10: Arrange olives, tomatoes and garlic atop bread. 11: Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan over bread. 12: Drizzle remaining 1 Tbsp olive oil over. 13: Top with rosemary sprigs. 14: Continue baking until cheese melts and bread is cooked through, about 5 minutes. 15: Cut into squares or wedges and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3183,"Focaccia","PT30M","PT1H","PT1H30M","Make and share this Focaccia recipe from Food.com.","Breads",5.0,3.0,380.6,11.0,1.5,0.0,585.8,60.6,2.6,0.5,8.8,"4.0","Focaccia Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve yeast in warm water with olive oil, 1 teaspoons salt, and sugar. 2: Stir in  the flour a little at a time; when you can no longer stir, turn the dough onto a  floured board and knead till the dough is smooth and elastic. 3: Place dough in  an oiled bowl and let rise till it has doubled in size, about 30-40 minutes. 4: Shape the dough into an oval 1/2 inch thick with a rolling pin. 5: Make decorative  cuts on the top of the loaf with a sharp knife. Place the loaf on an oiled  baking sheet, brush with olive oil, and sprinkle with coarse salt(also sprinkle  with optional chopped olives or chopped onions, if desired).Let rise 20  minutes. 6: Preheat oven to 450F degrees. 7: Bake loaf for 20-30 minutes, until bread  is nicely browned. 8: Serve hot from the oven.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3184,"Focaccia With Fresh Herbs","PT25M","PT1H30M","PT1H55M","This is one of my adopted recipes. It''s actually very good and makes a nicely textured focaccia - you can vary the toppings - it''s a great bread you can be creative with....I highly recommend using a heavy cast iron skillet that has been lightly oiled. It makes an excellent crust!","Yeast Breads",4.5,4.0,217.9,7.2,1.0,0.0,292.5,33.1,1.2,0.4,4.5,"8.0","Focaccia With Fresh Herbs Recipe Instructions:  1: Sprinkle yeast and sugar into 1/2 cup of the water - do not stir. 2: Let stand 10 minutes or until the surface becomes bubbly. 3: In large bowl, combine flour and table salt. 4: Make a well in the center of the flour and pour in yeast mixture and 1 tablespoon olive oil. 5: Stir with wooden spoon or electric mixer, and slowly add remaining 1/4 cup water - dough will be soft and slightly sticky. 6: Turn dough onto lightly floured surface. Knead for 10 minutes, adding small spoonfuls of flour if necessary. 7: If you are using a stand mixer, you may continue using the dough hook setting rather than turning out on the board as mentioned in step 6. 8: When dough is smooth and elastic, place in bowl and cover with plastic wrap or damp cloth. 9: Let rise in a warm place- about 80-85 degrees - until doubled in bulk, for 1 hour. 10: Turn onto lightly  floured surface. Knead gently several times. 11: Flatten into 10-inch circle. Place on an oiled baking stone, pizza pan or heavy cookie sheet (I use a large cast iron skillet). Press indentations into the surface of the dough with fingers to make \ 12:  Loosely cover and let rise about 15 minutes, or until doubled in size. Preheat oven to 425°F. 13: In a blender or mortar and pestle, combine remaining 3 Tbsp olive oil and herbs until leaves are broken up and oil  is fragrant. 14: Pour over dough. Rub gently into surface. Sprinkle with kosher salt. 15: Bake 15 minutes, reduce heat to 400°F. 16: Bake 5 minutes more, or until golden brown. 17: Let cool and cut into wedges.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3185,"Spicy Cheese &amp; Mushroom Quesadillas","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","This is an adopted recipe I have not yet tried. Having made a good number of quesadillas in my day, though, I''ve probably made this combination or something close to it before and would be willing to bet that it will work just fine. Please review if you try it! Any suggestions will be appreciated.","Cheese",5.0,3.0,526.7,33.2,19.2,92.2,1337.0,37.4,2.5,5.5,20.3,"4.0","Spicy Cheese &amp; Mushroom Quesadillas Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt 1 tablespoons butter in a large skillet over medium heat. 2: Add onion; cook 3  minutes. 3: Add  mushrooms, garlic, thyme, salt and pepper; cook 5 to 7 minutes or  until liquid evaporates. 4: Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter; brush half of butter  over one side of 4 tortillas. 5: Arrange tortillas,  buttered side down, on large  baking sheet; top with 3/4 cup cheese. 6: Arrange mushroom mixture  over cheese;  top with 3/4  cup cheese. 7: Place remaining 4 tortillas over cheese; press lightly. Brush remaining butter over tops of tortillas. 8: Bake at 450 F for 5 to 6 minutes or until top tortillas are golden brown. 9: Turn quesadillas over;  continue to  bake 4 minutes. 10: Sprinkle quesadillas with remaining 1/2 cup cheese; continue to  bake 1 minute or until quesadillas are golden brown and cheese is melted. 11: Cut  into wedges;  serve with toppings as desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3186,"Salmon Croquettes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Salmon Croquettes recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.0,3.0,71.9,3.3,1.0,14.7,79.7,8.7,0.3,0.3,1.8,"0.0","Salmon Croquettes Recipe Instructions:  1: Remove all bones and skin from salmon and mix with cracker crumbs, onion and  egg. 2: Shape into croquettes and skillet fry. 3: Serve with white sauce. White Sauce: Combine cornstarch, margarine, milk and stir until smooth. 4: Add salt and pepper  and bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. 5: Boil for 1 minute and  pour over salmon croquettes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3187,"Shrimp Newburg II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Shrimp Newburg II recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.0,1.0,129.9,6.0,3.7,19.2,105.2,10.6,3.1,3.5,7.5,"8.0","Shrimp Newburg II Recipe Instructions:  1: Bake patty shells according to package directions. 2: Combine soup and milk; heat. Add shrimp and peas and continue  to heat, stirring, until just simmering. 3: Cook slowly about 5  minutes. 4: Stir in the sherry and half the cheese. Sprinkle  remaining cheese in baked patty shells. 5: To serve, spoon sauce  into patty shells.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3188,"Apples ''N Cheese Casserole","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apples ''N Cheese Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",4.0,2.0,2646.8,144.5,92.1,431.8,4043.3,296.4,2.5,218.3,49.2,"1.0","Apples ''N Cheese Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Place apples in a greased casserole dish. 2: Cream butter, sugar and flour. 3: Add grated or cut up cheese to creamed mixture. Mix well and spread over apples. 4: Pour milk on top. 5: Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3189,"Dirt Cake","PT15M","PT15M","PT30M","Make and share this Dirt Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,235.4,4.4,1.4,0.6,382.7,47.2,1.7,25.6,2.5,"8.0","Dirt Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine cookie crumbs and NesQuik in medium bowl; reserve 1/4 cup. 2: Layer half of remaining crumb mixture, half of pudding and half of whipped  topping in a large bowl or 8 small bowls. 3: Repeat layers. 4: Sprinkle with reserved  crumb mixture; top with gummy worms.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3190,"Lazy Cabbage Roll Casserole","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lazy Cabbage Roll Casserole recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.5,3.0,277.4,10.7,3.7,38.6,833.5,31.3,4.8,8.2,15.0,"0.0","Lazy Cabbage Roll Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Place rice in small saucepan; cover with water and bring to boil. 2: Simmer 5  minutes; drain. 3: Heat oil in Dutch oven or large skillet over medium-high heat;  add beef (or beans) and onion and cook until beef is no longer pink and onions  are softened. 4: Drain off excess fat.  Stir in rice, cabbage, tomato sauce, salsa if using, water, salt and pepper. 5: Pour into a casserole dish; cover and bake in preheated 375 F oven about 1 hour. 6: Stir and add 1/2 cup more water if  necessary. 7: Cook  1 hour longer or until cabbage is very tender. 8: Makes 8 generous servings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3191,"Country Fried Steak","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Country Fried Steak recipe from Food.com.","Meat",5.0,5.0,681.3,49.7,24.7,199.1,225.8,17.1,0.4,0.2,39.8,"4.0","Country Fried Steak Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim visible fat from meat and cut into 4 equal serving pieces. 2: Mix flour,  salt, and pepper in a shallow, wide bowl and dredge each piece of meat in it,  coating well on both sides. 3: Heat grease or oil until hot but not smoking in a  heavy, wide skillet with a lid. 4: Brown the meat pieces on both sides, turn heat  down a bit, cover and let steak fry like chicken for 15 to 20 minutes, until  done. Remove cover and let steak crisp for about 5 minutes. 5: Take steak from the  pan and drain. 6: Leave about 2 Tbsp of drippings and all the browned flecks of  crust in the pan. 7: Turn the heat a bit lower, sprinkle Wondra  flour int o the  drippings and stir to keep from lumping while it browns. 8: Slowly add half and  half, stirring. 9: Let it cook until thick, about 3 to 5 minutes. 10: Taste and add  seasoning, if needed. 11: Return the steaks to the gravy and cook an additional 5  mins or so. 12: Serve on plate, Mashed potatoes, maybe some green beans with country ham.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3192,"Stromboli","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Stromboli recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,6.0,462.1,35.9,17.4,113.2,1649.7,2.1,0.0,0.6,31.5,"20.0","Stromboli Recipe Instructions:  1: Divide each loaf of bread into 4 pieces. 2: Roll out to  about 1/8-inch thick. 3: Alternate layers of meat and cheese.  Add peppers if desired. 4: Wrap bread dough around meat and  cheese. Tuck ends under well (to prevent leaking of juices).  Place on greased cookie sheets. 5: Brush stromboli with lightly  beaten egg white. Place in 350 degrees oven for 20 minutes or until  golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3193,"Homemade Stromboli","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Homemade Stromboli recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,4.0,440.8,18.4,8.2,59.4,1621.3,44.1,2.2,3.2,23.4,"12.0","Homemade Stromboli Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve yeast in warm water. 2: Add salt, sugar and 1/2 of the flour, mix well. 3: Add rest of flour, turn onto floured boa rd and knead until smooth. 4: Place in buttered bowl. 5: Cover and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours in warm place. Punch down, divide into 12 pieces for stromboli or shape into 2 loaves for bread. 6: Bake bread 30 minutes at 400 degrees. 7: Roll out each dough into a circle; place in center of each dough a few slices of ham, pepperoni, grated cheese and a little sauce. Fold in half and pinch edges well to seal. 8: Brush with egg white mix. 9: Place on greased sheet pan. 10: Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400 degrees until lightly brown. 11: May be reheated. 12: Serve with extra tomato sauce to dip in.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3195,"My Sin (Dessert)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this My Sin (Dessert) recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,1.0,14945.6,1204.8,714.2,3554.0,9855.6,921.8,12.9,634.8,185.4,"1.0","My Sin (Dessert) Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix flour and nuts with brown sugar and butter. 2: Mix still smooth spread mixture in baking dish and bake at 350 for 20  minutes..let cool for 2 hours. 3: Blend  cream cheese with 1 cup whipped topping and sugar. 4: Spread mixture on top of  crust and chill 1 hour. 5: Make pudding according to pie directions on box spread  on top of cream  cheese.  Spread remainder of whipped topping on top and chill 5 hours..can be made the day  before.  Very rich and just as good..indulge.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3196,"Yakisoba","PT10M","PT15M","PT25M","Make and share this Yakisoba recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.5,4.0,653.1,34.7,12.3,57.8,852.2,61.0,5.7,0.0,26.1,"4.0","Yakisoba Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut semi-frozen steak into thin bite size pieces and stir-fry over medium heat  until thoroughly browned, heat 2 quarts water to rapid boil while stir-frying  meat. 2: Add 1 to 2 seasoning packets of seasoning mix from noodles to steak. 3: Add  Ramen noodles to water and boil 3 minutes. 4: While cooking noodles, add vegetables  and soy sauce to taste to steak and heat thoroughly. 5: When noodles are done,  drain and add to steak and vegetable mixture. 6: Salt and pepper to taste. 7: Note:  Chicken, pork or shrimp can be substituted for steak.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3197,"Sylvia''s Smothered Chicken","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sylvia''s Smothered Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",0.0,0.0,761.0,48.7,11.8,172.5,484.1,31.2,2.5,2.6,47.1,"8.0","Sylvia''s Smothered Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim the excess fat from the chicken pieces and sprinkle them with 1 teaspoon each of the salt and pepper. 2: Season 2 cups of the flour with the remaining 1 tablespoon each of salt and pepper. 3: Dredge the chicken pieces in the flour until coated on all sides. 4: Shake off any excess flour. 5: Heat the vegetable oil in a heavy deep skillet (cast-iron is perfect) over medium heat until the edge of a chicken piece dipped into the oil gives off a lively sizzle. Add as many chicken pieces to the skillet 4 as will fit without touching. 6: Fry until the pieces are browned on all sides, about 6 min utes. 7: Adjust the heat as necessary during frying to keep a lively sizzle without over-browning. 8: Remove the fried chicken to drain and repeat with the remaining pieces. 9: Pour off all but 4 tablespoons of drippings from the skillet. Reduce the heat to medium and add the onions, peppers, and celery to the skillet. Cook, stirring occasionally, until brown and tender, about 10 minutes. 10: Move the vegetables to one side of the skillet and sprinkle the 2 tablespoons of flour over the other side of the skillet. Cook the flour until golden brown, stirring constantly. 11: Be careful not to let the flour burn. 12: Slowly pour in the water and stir until the gravy is smooth. 13: Divide the chicken between two heavy skillets with lids or place them all in a large heavy Dutch oven. 14: Top with the gravy and vegetables and cover the skillets or Dutch oven tightly. 15: Simmer over low heat until the vegetables are tender and the chicken is cooked through, about 15 minutes. 16: Check the seasoning and add salt and pepper as necessary . 17: Serve the chicken, spooning some of the gravy and vegetables over each piece. Pass extra gravy.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3198,"Fettuccine Alfredo","PT15M","PT0S","PT15M","This marvelous recipe is one I got off this newsgroup some months back, but am reposting for the Alfredo request since I have no idea if the original poster is still around to see the new request. Since it isn''t mine, I''ve also included the original poster''s notes and attribution. Yummy stuff!  Introduction: This is the real thing. You will not find a better Fettuccine Alfredo other than at Alfredo''s in Rome, Italy. The secret to his sauce is in the Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese (don''t even try this recipe without it), the balance of the pepper and nutmeg. For some reason restaurants never get it right. Be warned that the sauce is heavy. This recipe serves 2. Recipe by Ricardo Batista   Fettuccine Alfredo","< 15 Mins",4.5,11.0,1344.1,74.8,44.3,396.3,813.5,129.1,0.2,0.2,39.7,"2.0","Fettuccine Alfredo Recipe Instructions:  1: Grate the cheese, black pepper  and nutmeg if you need to. 2: Put 4 quarts of water to boil. 3: Cooking: Set small frying pan in mid-high heat.  Add the butter and the cream to the frying pan and mix well. 4: Stir the sauce frequently and add the black pepper, salt and nutmeg, boil and stir frequently until the sauce becomes heavier, then reduce the heat. Add the pasta to the boiling water along with some salt and cook to your liking. 5: Once the pasta is cooked, drain the pasta and add it to the sauce. Add the grated cheese to the sauce and pasta, and mix until the cheese is absorbed by the sauce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3200,"Bruschetta with Red Peppers and Goat''s Cheese","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Bruschetta with Red Peppers and Goat''s Cheese recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",5.0,1.0,415.2,23.1,7.4,19.6,520.2,40.9,3.6,3.3,12.1,"4.0","Bruschetta with Red Peppers and Goat''s Cheese Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat the oven to 375F. 2: Put peppers on an unoiled baking pan and roast them in oven f or 20-30 minutes, until they start to collapse and the skins blacken. 3: Transfer to a bowl and cover to trap moisture. Leave for about 10 minutes until the skin loosens. 4: Peel the peppers, cut open and remove the stem and seeds. 5: Tear pepper flesh into strips. 6: Dress with olive oil, salt and black pepper, and basil. 7: Rub hot bread with the garlic cloves and sprinkle with salt, black pepper and olive oil. 8: Lay the peppers on top and crumble the goat''s cheese over them. 9: Dribble over a little more olive oil and serve");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3201,"Quick Pear Butter","PT30M","PT10M","PT40M","Make and share this Quick Pear Butter recipe from Food.com.","Pears",2.0,2.0,9440.5,3.4,0.2,0.0,234.5,2446.9,78.9,2224.6,16.8,"0.0","Quick Pear Butter Recipe Instructions:  1: Place all ingredients in a stockpot. 2: Cook together for approximately 30 minutes, stirring frequently to prevent scorching. 3: If pears haven''t collapsed from cooking, mash them. 4: Serve when cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3202,"Pear Butter","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pear Butter recipe from Food.com.","Pears",0.0,0.0,4276.4,1.6,0.1,0.0,13.2,1111.1,40.9,1035.7,5.0,"0.0","Pear Butter Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash pears and remove core and peeling. 2: Cut into quarters and add a little water. 3: Cook until tender. 4: To pulp add sugar and mix well. 5: Bake at 350 degrees for 3 hours. 6: Stir occasionally. 7: Pour into jars and seal. 8: PEAR BUTTER pears water cinnamon Wash pears, do not peel; slice. Add small amount of water to start cooking. 9: Cook until very soft. Press through sieve. To each cup of pulp, add 1/2 cup sugar; add 1/2 tea-  spoon of cinnamon to each 3 cups of pulp. 10: Cook until thick, stirring frequently to prevent scorching. 11: Pour into sterilized jars and seal while hot. I cook mine in the crock-pot until desired thickness.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3203,"Shepherd''s Pie IIi","PT25M","PT5M","PT30M","Make and share this Shepherd''s Pie IIi recipe from Food.com.","Meat",0.0,0.0,94.4,1.9,0.8,43.2,748.4,16.7,1.3,1.2,2.6,"4.0","Shepherd''s Pie IIi Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 425°F. 2: Grease baking dish and line the bottom with mashed potatoes. 3: Season  meat with spices and afterwards, add gravy. 4: Add remaining mashed  potatoes and spread evenly over it. 5: In a cup, mix the egg yolk with the water and \ 6:  the top with it. 7: Bake in oven for 20 - 25  minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3204,"Indian Salad Dressing","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Indian Salad Dressing recipe from Food.com.","Salad Dressings",0.0,0.0,1445.1,155.0,23.8,503.5,2400.8,10.1,1.5,3.4,7.1,"0.0","Indian Salad Dressing Recipe Instructions:  1: Force the yolks through a strainer. 2: In a canning jar, add the crushed  yolks, salt, sugar, paprika, cayenne, white pepper, lemon juice, and  olive oil. 3: Shake until mixed well. 4: Add remaining ingredients and shake again. 5: Refrigerate until chilled.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3205,"Apple Slices","PT1H","PT30M","PT1H30M","My mother got this from a friend many years ago.  Should be similar to what you''re looking for.  It''s delicious.","Dessert",5.0,4.0,285.4,11.0,2.4,10.5,343.9,45.6,2.6,26.4,3.0,"18.0","Apple Slices Recipe Instructions:  1: Crust: Mix  flour and salt. Cut margarine inches. 2: Whisk egg yolk and milk together;  mix into flour. 3: Roll out 1/2 of dough large enough to fit into a jelly roll pan. 4: Filling: Sprinkle corn flakes over bottom crust. Spread apple slices evenly over crust. Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt; sprinkle over apples. 5: Roll out remaining  dough and cover fruit. Brush top with beaten egg white. Bake at 350°F  for about 1 hour, until crust is golden brown. 6: Glaze: Mix glaze ingredients  together well. 7: Brush on top crust while still hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3206,"BBQ Pork Sausage Balls With Sauce and Dip","PT30M","PT30M","PT1H","Make and share this BBQ Pork Sausage Balls With Sauce and Dip recipe from Food.com.","< 60 Mins",5.0,3.0,2574.2,187.0,73.7,647.9,7351.8,132.2,5.2,74.5,93.1,"0.0","BBQ Pork Sausage Balls With Sauce and Dip Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix sausage ball ingredients well. 2: Roll into balls about 1-inch in diameter. 3: Brown on all sides. 4: Pour off grease. 5: Mix sauce ingredients; ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar and soy sauce well. 6: Pour mixture over sausage balls. Turn to cover well. 7: Simmer for about 30 minutes. 8: Mix all Tangy Sour Cream Dip ingredients well. 9: Spear toothpick into hot sausage ball, then dip into tangy sour cream dip.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3207,"Busy Day Cabbage Rolls","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Busy Day Cabbage Rolls recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",0.0,0.0,5764.3,513.7,205.2,674.2,1612.9,211.1,41.7,74.6,86.3,"1.0","Busy Day Cabbage Rolls Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook onion, seasonings and meat until browned. 2: Meanwhile, prepare rice.Combine with meat mixture. Spread in oiled 9X13 pan. 3: Top with chopped cabbage.  Combine tomato soup and water and pour over mixture in pan. 4: Cover with foil and bake at 350F for 1 1/2 hours.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3209,"Best Bruschetta","PT10M","PT20M","PT30M","Make and share this Best Bruschetta recipe from Food.com.","European",0.0,0.0,447.4,35.7,13.8,62.5,391.8,25.8,1.4,0.2,6.9,"10.0","Best Bruschetta Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut bread diagonally in 1-inch slices, without cutting  through bottom crust. In food processor chop garlic finely;  add oil and blend until paste. Spread paste on bread. 2: Place  in 350 degrees oven, directly on rack, with a pan under to catch  drippings. 3: Bake 10 minutes. 4: Meanwhile, heat cream in a heavy  saucepan. 5: Do not boil. 6: Stir in cheeses. 7: Stir until smooth. 8: Add butter; mix well. 9: Place crispy bread in serving dish. 10: Finish cutting through bread. 11: Pour hot cheese sauce over top. 12: Sprinkle with parsley and paprika. 13: Serve IMMEDIATELY! This  cools very quickly!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3210,"Savory Bruschetta","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Savory Bruschetta recipe from Food.com.","European",5.0,2.0,109.7,6.4,2.6,10.9,159.2,10.5,0.7,0.3,2.7,"0.0","Savory Bruschetta Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix oil and garlic; spread on cut surfaces of bread. 2: Bake at 400F for 8 - 10 minutes or until toasted. 3: Cool   Mix cream cheese and Parmesan cheese with electric   mixer on medium speed until blended. 4: Stir in olives. 5: Spread on cooled bread halves. 6: Top with tomatoes and   basil leaves. 7: Cut diagonally into slices.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3212,"Tgi Friday''s Soy Dressing","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Tgi Friday''s Soy Dressing recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",0.0,1.0,743.5,72.1,12.2,0.0,2048.4,21.1,0.7,18.5,4.2,"0.0","Tgi Friday''s Soy Dressing Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients in a jar with a tight fitting lid. 2: Shake vigorously to combine all ingredients. 3: Keep refrigerated and covered. Use within a few  weeks.");
