INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3235,"Baked Caramel Corn","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Baked Caramel Corn recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,4472.6,190.3,38.8,0.0,5223.8,701.0,27.8,469.4,27.4,"0.0","Baked Caramel Corn Recipe Instructions:  1: Make popcorn and put in a large roasting pan. 2: Set aside.  Melt margarine in pan. 3: Stir in sugar, corn syrup and salt.  Bring to a boil stirring constantly. 4: Boil without stirring for 5 minutes. 5: Remove from heat.  Stir in baking soda and vanilla. 6: Pour over corn mixing well. 7: Bake at 250 F for 1 hour. 8: Stir every 15 minutes.Remove from oven. 9: Cool, break apart and store in tightly covered containers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3236,"Homemade Dill Pickles","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Homemade Dill Pickles recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",4.0,5.0,53.3,0.4,0.1,0.0,11.7,12.7,1.7,5.2,2.3,"0.0","Homemade Dill Pickles Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil. 2: Pour over (prepared jars ready for  canning) and seal. 3: Let set for 6 weeks. 4: (This recipe comes from a lady  who has been canning for years She forgot to  tell me how many cukes)");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3237,"Pumpkin Cheesecake","PT1H30M","PT30M","PT2H","Make and share this Pumpkin Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",4.5,4.0,630.8,39.8,23.2,152.4,459.6,60.8,1.1,33.9,9.7,"0.0","Pumpkin Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat the oven to 350°F. 2: Butter a 9- or 10-inch springform pan and coat lightly with flour in a medium bowl, toss the gingersnap crumbs with the melted butter until evenly moistened. 3: Press the crumbs into the bottom and 1 inch up the side of the prepared pan. 4: Bake for about 12 minutes, or until the crust begins to color. 5: Let the crust cool. 6: Reduce the oven temperature to 325°F. 7: In a large bowl, using an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese until smooth. 8: Beat in 1/2 cup of the granulated sugar and the brown  sugar, then beat in the eggs in 3 additions until the mixture is thoroughly combined, scraping down the side of the bowl occasionally. 9: In a medium bowl, combine the Pumpkin puree and heavy cream with 1 teaspoon of the vanilla and the cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg. 10: Add to the cream cheese mixture and beat until combined, scraping the bowl a few times. 11: Wrap foil loosely around the bottom and up the side of the springform pan. 12: Pour the cheesecake batter into the prepared pan and set it in a large baking dish or roasting pan. 13: Place in the middle of the oven and pour 1 inch of hot water into the baking dish. 14: Bake the cheesecake for about 70 minutes, or until the edges are firm and the center of the cheesecake is still slightly shaky. 15: In a small bowl, combine the sour cream with the remaining 1/2 cup of granulated sugar and 2 teaspoons of vanilla. 16: Remove the cheesecake from the water bath and pour on the sour cream topping. 17: Gently top the pan to spread the topping, and continue baking the cheesecake  for 10 more minutes. 18: Transfer the cheesecake to a rack and let cool for 1 hour. 19: Remove the foil and the side of the pan and refrigerate the cheesecake for at least 4 hours or overnight. If you like, remove the cheesecake from the bottom of the pan by sliding a metal spatula under the crust to loosen it completely, then use 2 large metal spatulas to transfer the cake to a serving plate. Alternatively, serve the cheesecake on the pan bottom.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3238,"Cabbage Roll Casserole","PT40M","PT20M","PT1H","Make and share this Cabbage Roll Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Lactose Free",3.5,2.0,596.6,26.6,10.2,115.7,916.4,52.0,10.5,13.3,42.1,"0.0","Cabbage Roll Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Chop cabbage into bite size pieces and place in bottom of large deep casserole.  Brown meat,  add onion, garlic, salt and pepper. 2: Add rice and one can of the  tomatoes. 3: Mix together well and pour over chopped cabbage. Spread drained  sauerkraut on top of meat and rice mixture. Spread the second can of tomatoes on top of kraut top with a dash of celery seed . 4: Bake uncovered at 350 for 20  minutes. 5: Cover and continue baking for another hour or until the rice is tender. 6: This makes a lot, you may want to cut it in half. 7: . Served with  Italian Cheese  Topped Bread and a Caesar salad. 8: Very filling.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3239,"Beef Stew","PT24M","PT10M","PT34M","Make and share this Beef Stew recipe from Food.com.","Stew",4.0,2.0,125.8,3.0,0.4,0.0,172.9,23.1,5.9,4.9,4.8,"12.0","Beef Stew Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown meat in oil in a large skillet. In a crockpot add enough water to cover ribs( note the store will cut them in half if you ask them to)  Place the ribs in the crockpot before you go to bed with all the spices and cook all night on low. 2: In the morning pull out the ribs and pull off the meat and chop up and then return to the crock.. 3: Add the rest of the stuff and let it cook all day on low. 4: Make sure there is enough water to cover everything. 5: A nice loaf of fresh Italian bread will work nicely with this. 6: using the ribs take a little more work but the taste is so much more than using beef cubes....");
