INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3241,"Japanese Salad Dressing II","0","PT10M","PT10M","Japanese Salad Dressing    The pungent miso also adds vitamins, protein, and nutrients to this healthy,  low-fat dressing, which contains just a 1/4 teaspoon of sesame oil. Serve  drizzled on top of a simple salad of iceberg lettuce and shaved carrots.","Salad Dressings",4.5,4.0,702.2,20.5,3.5,0.0,8684.3,105.6,15.0,54.4,28.6,"0.0","Japanese Salad Dressing II Recipe Instructions:  1: In a small bowl, combine miso and sugar. 2: Add mirin, water, soy sauce, sesame  oil, and sesame seeds. 3: Stir until well blended. 4: Serve over lettuce and  carrot slices. 5: Toss to combine.");
