INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3280,"Beef Stroganoff","PT15M","PT15M","PT30M","Make and share this Beef Stroganoff recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.5,47.0,487.5,37.6,19.8,145.5,485.4,10.3,0.8,3.3,26.9,"4.0","Beef Stroganoff Recipe Instructions:  1: Coat meat with flour. 2: Heat large skillet, add butter. 3: Add meat and brown quickly on both sides Add mushrooms, onion and garlic to skillet.  Cook 3-4  minutes until onion is crisp-tender. Remove mixture from pan Add butter to pan drippings, blend in flour. 4: Add beef broth. 5: Cook & stir over medium-high heat, until thickened & bubbly, then return meat mixture to pan. Stir in sour cream. 6: Cook slowly until heated through. 7: DO NOT BOIL! Serve over hot buttered noodles. Hope you enjoy!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3281,"Alfredo Sauce With Pasta","PT26M","PT0S","PT26M","Make and share this Alfredo Sauce With Pasta recipe from Food.com.","European",3.0,1.0,765.8,37.6,22.8,119.3,258.0,87.1,3.6,3.2,19.4,"0.0","Alfredo Sauce With Pasta Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook one to one and one-half pound of pasta. 2: Drain and put back in pot.  Add butter or margarine.  Mix well until butter melts. 3: Add cream. 4: Over VERY low heat, cook gently while stirring until cream thickens slightly. 5: Remove from heat and add cheese and seasonings. 6: Mix well and serve at once. Serve 4-6 hearty eaters.");
