INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3283,"Hush Puppies II","PT10M","PT10M","PT20M","Make and share this Hush Puppies II recipe from Food.com.","Healthy",5.0,1.0,173.6,2.4,0.6,52.9,499.3,30.4,2.5,0.7,5.2,"8.0","Hush Puppies II Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oil in frying pan or deep fryer to 350°F. 2: Mix first seven ingredients together and drop by tablespoons into hot oil and fry until golden. 3: Drain on paper towels and serve while still hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3284,"Hush Puppies IIi","PT10M","PT5M","PT15M","Make and share this Hush Puppies IIi recipe from Food.com.","Healthy",1.0,1.0,137.0,1.8,0.4,26.4,355.8,27.3,2.4,0.6,3.7,"8.0","Hush Puppies IIi Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oil to 350F in a large skillet or deep fryer. 2: Mix remaining ingredients to make a stiff batter - adding milk as needed. 3: Use small scoop or  tablespoon to scoop individual amounts and drop into hot oil. 4: Cook until  golden brown - drain on paper towel.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3285,"Hush Puppies Iv","PT10M","PT5M","PT15M","Make and share this Hush Puppies Iv recipe from Food.com.","Healthy",0.0,0.0,170.8,1.8,0.4,35.2,599.0,34.1,2.3,1.7,4.9,"0.0","Hush Puppies Iv Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oil to 350F in a large skillet or deep fryer. 2: Mix all ingredients together, adding milk until mixture forms a very thick batter. 3: Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. 4: Fry until golden brown. 5: Drain on paper towels and serve while still hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3286,"Beef Stroganoff II","0","PT10M","PT10M","This is a very simple and good recipe.  I use 99% fat free cram of mushroom soup to make it even better for you.","Meat",4.0,6.0,221.6,13.7,4.8,51.5,460.9,5.3,0.3,2.0,18.8,"6.0","Beef Stroganoff II Recipe Instructions:  1: Slice beef across grain into very thin strips. 2: In skillet over high heat in 1  tbs hot margarine cook 1/2 the beef and onion until meat is no longer pink and  onion is tender. 3: Set aside.  Repeat with remaining margarine, beef and onion. 4: Return meat mixture to skillet, stir in soup and paprika. 5: Heat through. 6: Stir  in sour cream. 7: Serve over cooked noodles.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3287,"Hush Puppies VI","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Hush Puppies VI recipe from Food.com.","Healthy",5.0,2.0,185.0,2.9,1.1,39.5,482.3,34.1,2.1,1.0,5.9,"6.0","Hush Puppies VI Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl. 2: In a separate bowl beat egg and milk together. 3: Add to dry ingredients and stir. 4: Stir in onion, red pepper and chives, if using. 5: Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat in a deep fryer, 375 degrees, and fry until golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3288,"Marinated Mushrooms","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Marinated Mushrooms recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",0.0,0.0,1210.8,109.1,15.1,0.0,155.6,47.8,4.3,35.5,9.7,"0.0","Marinated Mushrooms Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix vinegar, salad oil, sugar, hot sauce, salt and  pepper. 2: Pour over mushrooms and onions. 3: Refrigerate several  hours, stirring occasionally, before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3289,"Artichoke and Spinach Salad","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Artichoke and Spinach Salad recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.0,1.0,619.1,46.6,15.1,51.1,1456.6,31.5,19.8,3.1,28.5,"0.0","Artichoke and Spinach Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix oil, vinegar and cheese. 2: Cut artichokes in quarters and add to the vinaigrette along with oil they come in; mix gently and refrigerate for several hours or overnight. 3: Take fresh spinach, wash and remove tough stems and tear as for tossed salad. 4: Serve with the dressing. 5: This dressing works well with other salad  greens.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3290,"Winter Lettuce Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Winter Lettuce Salad recipe from Food.com.","Healthy",0.0,0.0,826.6,21.1,5.8,202.3,2879.2,125.1,22.2,14.0,33.5,"0.0","Winter Lettuce Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash, drain and tear lettuce into bite-size pieces. 2: Drain beans and heat. Fry  bacon until crisp. 3: Pour off excess fat except for 2 tablespoons. 4: Combine egg,  onion, sugar, salt, vinegar and savory and add to bacon. 5: Heat to boiling point.  Pour over lettuce and toss. 6: Add hot beans and serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3291,"Baked Lemon-Butter Salmon","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Baked Lemon-Butter Salmon recipe from Food.com.","Very Low Carbs",5.0,11.0,408.1,14.0,2.6,146.3,238.8,1.4,0.4,0.4,65.3,"4.0","Baked Lemon-Butter Salmon Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400 F. 2: Cut Salmon Filet width-wise into about 1-1/2 inch  pieces. 3: Spread a thin layer of butter/margarine over each salmon steak. 4: Slice  lemon, and place 1 slice of lemon on top of each salmon steak. 5: Squeeze lemon  juice out of unused portion of lemon evenly over each ste ak. 6: Bake for 15-20  minutes. 7: Serve with rice. Variations: The margarine is not necessary, however my husband says it''s too bland without  the margarine, and the lemon flavoring is stronger without the margarine.  It  also prevents drying if you like your salmon cooked thoroughly. 8: Rach");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3292,"Four Hour Oven Beef Stew","PT3H","PT0S","PT3H","This recipe was passed  on to me by my sister-in-law about 6 years ago.  I know you will enjoy the stew.","Stew",3.0,2.0,181.3,4.0,1.6,48.4,929.2,18.4,2.9,8.9,19.4,"12.0","Four Hour Oven Beef Stew Recipe Instructions:  1: There is no need to brown the meat first.  Simply combine all ingredients in a  large casserole or roaster. 2: Bake at 300 F for 4 hours. 3: Adjust the amounts of  the ingredients to make this stew your very own creation .");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3293,"Harvard Beets III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Harvard Beets III recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,3.0,774.5,23.6,14.7,61.1,1560.4,137.2,6.1,123.8,5.3,"1.0","Harvard Beets III Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook beets in water to cover until tender. 2: Cool under running water until touchable. Peel and slice. Mix together sugar, cornstarch, salt, vinegar and butter. 3: Bring to a boil over medium heat. Cook, stirring for 5 minutes. 4: Add beets and simmer for 15 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3294,"Microwave Caramel Corn","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Microwave Caramel Corn recipe from Food.com.","Candy",5.0,7.0,472.8,23.1,14.6,61.0,679.2,70.3,0.0,59.1,0.3,"0.0","Microwave Caramel Corn Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix sugar, butter, syrup, and salt in a bowl. 2: Microwave till boiling,  then 3: microwave 2 minutes longer. 4: Mix in baking soda. 5: Pour mixture over  popcorn that is placed in a brown paper bag and shake vigorously. 6: Microwave 30 seconds,  take out of microwave, and shake. Microwave 1  minute, take out, and shake.  Microwave 1 more minute and shake. Pour  out on a baking pan. 7: MMMM");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3295,"Pot Roast II","PT4H","PT0S","PT4H","Make and share this Pot Roast II recipe from Food.com.","Meat",3.0,1.0,161.8,7.9,1.0,0.4,389.9,21.1,4.1,7.2,3.6,"0.0","Pot Roast II Recipe Instructions:  1: Start with boiling the broth. 2: Thaw the roast completely and wait until it''s  room-temperature. Rub it with the garlic. Put it into a bag with the flour and  shake thoroughly. 3: Make sure every square inch of the roast is floured, but pat  it between your hands to dust off excessive amounts. 4: Heat the oil in a big,  coverable caserole until it is fragrant. Brown the roast on both sides (do not  seer). Once you''ve flipped the roast, add the peppers, carrots, and turnip. 5: Pour in the boiling broth. 6: Add the onion stuck with cloves, the pepper corns, and the bay leaf. 7: Bring to a boil, cover then reduce heat to low (or, optionally, place  in an oven preheated to 300 Deg. 8: F). This requires 2-3 hours to cook right. Flip the roast over once every hour. 9: Before the last hour, add the Worcestershire  sauce, thyme, basil, cumin, mace, turmeric, and rosemary. 10: Remove the bay leaf,  onion, and pepper corns before serving. 11: Naturally, the broth and vegetables go  with it. Serves best  with rice, but potatoes are more traditional. 12: Andrew Bernstein Montreal, CANADA");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3296,"Dirt Cake II","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Dirt Cake II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,12.0,578.5,33.7,19.6,55.0,766.3,65.1,1.2,49.1,6.5,"0.0","Dirt Cake II Recipe Instructions:  1: Crush the Oreo cookies in a blender or food processor; set aside. 2: Cream together butter or margarine and  cream cheese. 3: In a large bowl, mix 2 large boxes  of vanilla instant pudding (add amount of milk according to package of pudding). 4: Add cream cheese mixture and 8 ounces of Cool Whip. 5: Beat together until mixed. 6: In an 8 inch flower pot, layer the cookie mixture, the pudding mixture,  the cookie mixture, and so on. 7: End up with the cookie mixture (this looks  like dirt). 8: Add an artificial flower on top.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3297,"Lebkuchan","PT15M","PT15M","PT30M","Make and share this Lebkuchan recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,3084.1,32.9,4.3,211.5,943.2,676.8,16.1,441.3,47.9,"0.0","Lebkuchan Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat honey until it bubbles and cool. 2: Stir in sugar, egg, juice and rind. 3: Cool to lukewarm. 4: Add spices and flour.  Stir. 5: Add citron and nuts. 6: Dough  will be soft.  Cover bowl and refrigerate at least 8 hours (Up to one week). 7: Shape into 1-inch balls with floured hands. 8: Flatten with 1/2 of an almond. 9: Bake 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet, 12-15 minutes at 375°F until  lightly browned. 10: Glaze while warm. 11: Glaze:  1 cup sifted powder sugar  5 Tbsp rum or water stirred until smooth. 12: Store in air tight container and let mellow.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3298,"Silver Palate Salmon Mousse","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Silver Palate Salmon Mousse recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,3.0,109.4,10.6,5.0,29.7,272.8,3.1,0.0,0.7,1.0,"12.0","Silver Palate Salmon Mousse Recipe Instructions:  1: Soften gelatin in cold water in large bowl. 2: Stir in boiling water. 3: Whisk mix  until gelatin dissolves. 4: Cool. 5: Whisk mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, Tabasco  sauce, paprika, salt and dill. 6: Stir to blend. 7: Refrigerate until mixture begins  to thicken slightly, about 20 minutes. 8: Fold in salmon. 9: In separate bowl whip  cream to thicken then fold into salmon. 10: Transfer mixture to 6 to 8 cup bowl or  mold. 11: Cover and chill 4 hours. 12: Serve on toasts, black bread or crackers. 13: Serves  12 portions.");
