INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3301,"Salmon Club Sandwich with Roasted Shallot Smear","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Salmon Club Sandwich with Roasted Shallot Smear recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,2.0,335.2,10.5,2.9,6.9,844.8,49.6,5.9,4.1,10.9,"0.0","Salmon Club Sandwich with Roasted Shallot Smear Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat 1 Tbsp. 2: olive oil in medium saute pan over high heat and cook pancetta until crispy. 3: Season salmon with pepper and salt. Heat r emaining olive oil in large saute pan until smoking hot and sear salmon, about 3 to 4 minutes per side depending on thickness. 4: Toast or grill bread. 5: Spread 6 slices with roasted shallot smear and top with salmon. 6: Place slice of bread over salmon and smear with herb-cheese spread followed by pancetta and arugula and top with remaining slice of bread. 7: Cut at an angle and serve. Roasted Shallot Smear Drizzle 1/4 cup olive oil over 10 whole, peeled and halved shallots and 10 peeled garlic cloves and  roast in preheated 300F oven until soft. While pureeing in food processor, add 1/4 cup balsamic vinegar, 2 anchovies, 2 Tbsp. 8: chopped fresh rosemary and salt and pepper to taste. Herb Cheese Spread In food processor, combine 3 cloves peeled garlic, 1 Tbsp. 9: each of chopped fresh rosemary, basil and thyme, 1 cup cream cheese, 1/2 cup goat cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste. Makes 6 servings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3302,"Moist Chewy Brownies","0","PT0S","PT0S","These have got to be the most delicious brownies I have ever tasted in my life. You can never eat just one.  Moist Chewy Brownies","Bar Cookie",2.5,3.0,369.3,17.2,3.7,62.0,328.9,50.1,1.1,34.3,4.5,"0.0","Moist Chewy Brownies Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt in a bowl. 2: In a large bow l, beat the eggs until light; add sugar and beat again; beat in margarine. Stir in dry ingredients; blend well. 3: Stir in vanilla, corn syrup and nuts. 4: Mix well by hand. 5: Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. 6: Bake at 350: F about 35 minutes or until firm to the touch but not hard. 7: Enjoy.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3304,"Saigon Chicken Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Saigon Chicken Salad recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Thigh & Leg",0.0,0.0,569.8,35.0,5.5,114.5,1377.2,26.0,8.2,10.0,44.1,"4.0","Saigon Chicken Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine dressing ingredients and mix well. 2: In a large bowl, combine vegetables and toss with half the dressing. 3: Divide vegetables onto 4 plates. 4: In a non-stick skillet, heat sesame oil over medium heat. Add chicken and stir-fry for 3 minutes. 5: Add soy sauce, reduce heat and continue stir-frying until the soy sauce is absorbed and the chicken is no longer pink inside. Stir in peanuts. 6: Top each plate of vegetables with warm chicken and peanuts. 7: Drizzle with remaining dressing. 8: Serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3305,"Zesty Italian Veal Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Zesty Italian Veal Salad recipe from Food.com.","Veal",0.0,0.0,127.9,10.2,2.4,5.5,689.4,6.5,0.6,4.9,3.0,"4.0","Zesty Italian Veal Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Marinade 1/4 cup Italian dressing 2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar 1/4 teaspoon pepper In small bowl, combine marinade ingredients, mix well. 2: Place veal s teaks and marinade in plastic food-safe bag. 3: Close bag securely and marinate in refrigerator 6 hours (or overnight, if desired), turning occasionally. 4: Remove veal from marinade; discard marinade. Place steaks on grid over medium, ash-covered coals. 5: Grill, uncovered, 16 to 18 minutes for medium doneness, turning occasionally. 6: To serve, in large bowl, combine greens, tomatoes, cheese and dressing. 7: Toss lightly. 8: Divide equally among 4 plates. 9: Sprinkle veal with salt. Trim fat from veal; remove bones. 10: Carve veal crosswise into think slices; arrange over salad.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3306,"Paul Lynde Beef Vegetable Stew","PT6H","PT0S","PT6H","A friend of mine made this one night when she had us over for dinner and I have been making it every since,  It''s become a family favorite. This is a great recipe for cold winter days when you don''t feel like fussing in the kitchen.  I serve with warm bread or biscuits.  Paul Lynde Stew  Quantities can be increased depending on the size of your dutch oven and how many people you are going to be feeding.  The quantities listed are for a &quot;basic&quot; size dutch oven.","Stew",5.0,5.0,3364.0,164.6,64.2,598.8,4189.9,242.0,51.8,110.8,218.1,"0.0","Paul Lynde Beef Vegetable Stew Recipe Instructions:  1: Layer the above in dutch oven. 2: Bake at 250 degrees for 6 to 8 hours. 3: Stir after the first hour and then every hour or so thereafter. 4: Potatoes are optional    Give them about 3 hours to cook (good size pieces).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3307,"Penne Piperade","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Penne Piperade recipe from Food.com.","Penne",5.0,1.0,467.4,6.2,0.9,0.0,16.9,97.0,15.2,5.7,10.4,"4.0","Penne Piperade Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook the penne in at least 4 quarts of rapidly boiling water until al dente,  about 8 minutes. 2: Drain the pasta in a colander, refresh under cold water, and  drain well again. 3: Heat the olive oil in a large saute pan, preferably nonstick. 4: Add the peppers, onion, garlic, and prosciut to and cook over medium heat until  lightly browned, about 5 minutes. 5: Stir in the tomatoes, paprika, salt and  pepper, and half the parsley. 6: Cook until the tomatoes yield their juices and the mixture is moist and saucy, about 5 minutes. 7: Stir in the penne and bring to a  boil. 8: Correct the seasoning, adding salt or paprika to taste. The mixture should be highly seasoned. 9: Sprinkle penne with the remaining parsley. 10: Grate the cheese  on top, if using, and serve at once.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3308,"Stir-Fry Supreme","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Stir-Fry Supreme recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",4.0,1.0,158.8,2.5,0.4,0.0,386.8,29.9,10.5,9.8,10.9,"4.0","Stir-Fry Supreme Recipe Instructions:  1: In a wok or frying pan, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add garlic and onio n and cook 15 seconds. 2: Stir in broccoli florets, carrots and green pepper. 3: Add water,  cover and cook about 6 minutes or until vegetables are about half-done. Add soy  sauce, mushrooms and tofu. 4: Cook another 5 minutes. 5: Serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3309,"Spicy Pearl Onion Sours","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Spicy Pearl Onion Sours recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",0.0,0.0,106.8,0.2,0.1,0.0,4727.4,21.0,2.3,11.2,1.4,"0.0","Spicy Pearl Onion Sours Recipe Instructions:  1: Plunge onions into pot of boiling water for 1 minute; drain. 2: Peel and trim;  combine in large bowl with salt and cover with water. 3: Let stand for 8 hours or overnight. Drain; rinse in cold water and drain well. 4: In large heavy saucepan, bring to boil vinegar, sugar, juniper berries, cinnamon, cloves and peppercorns. 5: Remove from heat; cover and let stand for at least 30 minutes or up to 2 hours. 6: Strain out spices and discard. 7: Bring vinegar mixture back to boil. 8: Place tarragon sprig in each of three 2-cup (500 mL) sterilized canning jars. 9: Pack jars with onions; pour in vinegar mixture, leaving 1/4-inch (5 mm) headspace. Seal jars; process in boiling w ater bath for 10 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3310,"Another Russian Tea","PT20M","PT4H","PT4H20M","This is an old favorite around our house for those cold Michigan fall and winters, and especially nice at football games.","Beverages",4.0,2.0,2191.6,8.5,2.0,0.0,211.7,552.0,13.5,497.7,8.0,"0.0","Another Russian Tea Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil water with cloves and cinnamon rapidly for 20 minutes. 2: Remove from heat,  cover, and add 4 tea bags, and let \ 3:  for at  least 4 hours (we like to  let it steep overnight). 4: After \ 5:  is complete, in another pan combine: 2 cups Orange juice 2 cups Pineapple juice 1 cup Lemon juice 2 cups Sugar. Heat gently, stirring to melt and mix sugar. 6: Drain \ 7:  from tea mixture.  Combine all together and heat to enjoy.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3311,"White Russian Casserole","PT20M","PT30M","PT50M","Make and share this White Russian Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,1.0,177.7,1.8,0.6,2.5,33.7,36.7,5.2,3.6,5.3,"12.0","White Russian Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil or microwave the potatoes till nearly done.  When cool enough, remove the skins. Fry the sliced onions in a little oil till soft. Add the chopped cabbage, the chopped cauliflower, and 6 cloves of the crushed garlic, and fry till the cabbage and cauliflower are just tender. 2: Melt the cream cheese, and add to it the soy milk, yogurt and dill. 3: Mix together, and add to the vegetable mixture.  Drain and rinse the white beans, and add to the vegetable mixture. mix thoroughly, and add salt & pepper to taste. Slice the potatoes into rounds, and put half the slices on the bottom of an oiled baking dish. 4: Fill with the mixture. Fry or microwave the fakin'' bakin. Cover with the remaining potatoes. Mix the remaining 2 cloves of crushed garlic with a little bit of oil and spread over the potatoes. 5: Sprinkle with paprika. 6: Bake at 325F for about 20 minutes. 7: Sprinkle with the sesame seeds, bake a few minutes more. Serve immediately. 8: Variations: Use basil or cilantro instead of dill.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3312,"Zesty Chicken Stir-Fry","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Zesty Chicken Stir-Fry recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,35.0,254.7,9.9,1.5,72.8,1139.7,14.4,0.3,10.5,26.2,"4.0","Zesty Chicken Stir-Fry Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut chicken in desired sized strips or cubes. 2: Slice vegetables. 3: Prepare sauce. Heat oil in a large skillet or wok. 4: Stirfry chicken, sliced garlic, and ginger over medium/high heat until chicken is cooked. 5: Add vegetables and stirfry until vegetables are tender-crisp. 6: Add sauce ingredients, mixing well. 7: Cook and stir until sauce thickens. 8: Serve garnish with grated lemon or sesame seeds.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3313,"No-Fat Sweet Potato Dressing","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this No-Fat Sweet Potato Dressing recipe from Food.com.","Potato",0.0,0.0,710.2,0.5,0.2,0.0,450.3,166.4,24.7,34.5,13.0,"0.0","No-Fat Sweet Potato Dressing Recipe Instructions:  1: Process potatoes in juicer: strain through a fine-mesh strainer. 2: Let juice stand 2 hours to collect starch at bottom of container. 3: Pour juice into saucepan, being careful to leave starch behind in cont ainer. 4: Simmer juice until thickened. 5: It will have reduced down to about 1 cup. 6: Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients. 7: Let stand 5 minutes; strain.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3314,"Stewed Rhubarb Fruit Compote","PT15M","PT10M","PT25M","Make and share this Stewed Rhubarb Fruit Compote recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,11.0,81.1,0.4,0.2,0.9,15.2,19.1,2.1,15.7,1.6,"8.0","Stewed Rhubarb Fruit Compote Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut rhubarb into bite-sized pieces. 2: Peel, core and thinly slice apple. Grate  rind and squeeze juice from orange. Combine rhubarb, apple, orange rind and  juice, water and sugar in a saucepan. 3: Cover and bring to a boil. 4: Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until fruit is tender. 5: Stir occasionally. 6: Remove from heat  and add strawberries, if desired. 7: Add more sugar to taste. Serve warm or at room temperature. Top with spoonful of yogurt and sprinkle of brown sugar.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3315,"Veal Medallions with Blueberry-Citrus Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Veal Medallions with Blueberry-Citrus Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Veal",5.0,1.0,226.8,10.7,5.0,100.5,114.2,10.1,1.2,6.1,22.5,"4.0","Veal Medallions with Blueberry-Citrus Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine blueberries, orange juice, lemon juice, vermouth, orange peel, lemon peel and ginger. 2: Stir to blend and set aside. Melt butter in a large, heavy skillet and saute until brown and just cooked through. 3: Transfer veal to platter and keep warm. 4: Add blueberry mixture to skillet and cook until mixture thickens, scraping up any browned bits (about 2 minutes). Spoon blueberry mixture over veal and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3316,"Zesty Lemon Squares","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Zesty Lemon Squares recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",0.0,0.0,117.2,3.3,0.7,11.7,84.8,20.7,0.2,13.7,1.7,"0.0","Zesty Lemon Squares Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine flour, sugar, margarine and yogurt in food processor or blender. 2: Press evenly into lightly-greased 8-inch-square cake pan. 3: Bake at 325 for 25 minutes or until golden. 4: TOPPING: Combine sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, egg, egg white and lemon juice and rind in a food processor or bowl. 5: Mix well. 6: Pour topping over base and bake an additional 35 minutes or until top is set. Sift icing sugar over top when cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3317,"Crab Rangoon","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Crab Rangoon recipe from Food.com.","Crab",4.5,8.0,51.6,2.4,1.3,14.9,118.9,4.9,0.1,0.2,2.4,"36.0","Crab Rangoon Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine crabmeat, cream cheese, A-1 Sauce and garlic powder. 2: Place 1 heaping teaspoonful of this mixture in the center of a won-ton wrapper. 3: Gather edges together, moisten with egg yolk and pinch to seal. 4: Deep fry in hot oil in bunches until golden brown, about 3 minutes. 5: Drain on paper towels. 6: Serve hot.          - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3318,"Banana Pudding","PT12M","PT0S","PT12M","Make and share this Banana Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,38.0,546.0,13.7,4.9,82.6,222.7,100.2,3.2,53.7,8.5,"0.0","Banana Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine flour, 1 1/3 cups sugar and salt in a heavy sauce pan. 2: Beat egg yolks;  combine egg yolks and milk, mixing well. 3: Stir into dry ingredients; cook over  medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened. 4: Remove from heat; stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla. 5: Layer one-third of wafers in a 3-qt baking dish. 6: Slice bananas, and layer over wafers. 7: Pour one-third of custard over bananas. 8: Repeat layers twice. Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until foamy. 9: Gradually add 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons of sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time,  beating until stiff peaks form. 10: Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, and beat until blended. 11: Spread meringue over custard, sealing edges of dish. 12: Bake at 425° for 10-12 minutes or until golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3319,"Banana Nut Frosting","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Banana Nut Frosting recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,1.0,3468.3,170.6,93.2,168.9,603.5,502.4,22.8,462.1,15.5,"0.0","Banana Nut Frosting Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine bananas and lemon juice; set mixture aside. 2: Cream softened butter at medium speed of an electric mixer; add powdered sugar and milk, mixing well. 3: Add banana mixture, beating until fluffy. 4: Stir in toasted coconut and chopped pecans.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3320,"Impossible Taco Pie","PT32M","PT2M","PT34M","Make and share this Impossible Taco Pie recipe from Food.com.","Mexican",5.0,7.0,230.4,13.6,6.6,120.2,386.2,15.7,1.2,3.3,11.3,"6.0","Impossible Taco Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400. 2: Grease pie plate, 10x1 1/2\ 3: . 4: Cook and stir the ground beef and onion in 10\ 5: ,  6: ,  7: ,  8: ,  9: Garnish with lettuce, tomato and olives. 10: FOR 1/2 RECIPE; Use 1 qt square or round casserole. Decrease baking mix to 1/2 cup, milk to 3/4 cup and eggs to 2. 11: Divide remaining ingredients amounts in half. 12: Decrease beat time to 10 sec. in blender or 30 sec. with wire whisk or hand beater Increase bake time to 30-35 minute. 13: High Altitude For the 1/2 recipe only use 1 1/2 qt round or 1 quart square  casserole. no other adj necessary.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3321,"Cucumber Salad with Fresh Dill","PT10M","PT30M","PT40M","Make and share this Cucumber Salad with Fresh Dill recipe from Food.com.","Colombian",5.0,4.0,30.7,0.1,0.0,0.0,2.5,7.5,0.7,5.1,0.7,"4.0","Cucumber Salad with Fresh Dill Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash the cucumber(s) and partially remove the peel in lengthwise strips using a vegetable peeler or fork and leaving a little skin between each strip. 2: Thinly slice the cucumber lengthwise. Place the vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper in a bowl and whisk until the sugar is dissolved. 3: Add the cucumber, onion, and dill, toss well. 4: The salad can be served at once, but it will improve in flavor if you let the ingredients marinate for 5 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3322,"Banana Gingersnap Pudding","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Banana Gingersnap Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,3.0,369.6,4.9,1.8,59.0,210.2,70.5,3.6,41.7,8.2,"4.0","Banana Gingersnap Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix sugar and cornstarch together. 2: Pour milk into medium-size microwaveproof   bowl. 3: Whisk in sugar mixture until cornstarch dissolves. 4: Microwave on high 4  minutes, stirring once. Whisk a little of the hot milk  mixture into beaten egg; return to bowl. 5: Sti r in rum. 6: Microwave on high 1 to 2 minutes longer until  custard thickens. 7: Remove from heat; cool slightly. 8: Slice a layer of bananas  into each of 4  individual dessert dishes. 9: Add a layer of cookies and top with  another layer of bananas. 10: Pour custard over top bananas. 11: Serve warm or chilled. 12: Conventional method:  Mix sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan; stir in milk. 13: Cook, over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture begins to boil. 14: Whisk some of hot milk mixture into beaten egg; return to saucepan. 15: Bring to boiling, cook 1 minute. Follow procedure above.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3323,"Candied Yams","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Candied Yams recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",4.5,11.0,3162.2,172.6,27.1,0.0,1129.3,422.2,41.0,263.5,22.3,"0.0","Candied Yams Recipe Instructions:  1: Put mashed yams in casserole. Mix together margarine, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg,  brown sugar and honey. 2: Mix in yams with pineapple bits and pecans. 3: Top with  miniature marshmallows. 4: Bake at 325 degrees until heated through and  marshmallows are bubbly. 5: Note: You may want to cut back on the ginger, I only used 1 teaspoon.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3324,"French Toast","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this French Toast recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",5.0,13.0,413.0,12.7,5.0,269.2,682.7,56.2,1.9,14.0,17.3,"5.0","French Toast Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix eggs, milk, sugar, extract and nutmeg together with mixer. 2: Slice bread in thick slices, thoroughly dip into mixture coating well, spray  griddle with butter spray and brown on both sides, sprinkle with confectioner''s sugar. 3: If you don''t have time to prepare this, I have used commercial eggnog and added nutmeg. 4: You can buy it in a can and keep it in your pantry. 5: Marian Allen");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3325,"Fudgy Brownies","PT40M","PT15M","PT55M","I usually double this recipe and omit the walnuts since I don''t like nuts.  It makes a very rich, fudgy brownie, perfect for chocoholics!","Bar Cookie",4.5,6.0,60.0,3.3,1.5,8.6,21.8,7.6,0.4,5.6,0.8,"0.0","Fudgy Brownies Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat the oven to 300°F. 2: Butter an 8-inch square pan. 3: Line the bottom of the pan with wax paper, then butter and flour the paper. 4: In a saucepan over low heat, melt the chocolate with butter, stirring to blend. 5: Remove from the heat and stir in sugar, egg, salt, flour, walnuts and vanilla. 6: Spread in the prepared pan and bake for about 30 minutes. 7: Cool for 5 minutes, then turn out onto rack and peel wax paper from bottom. 8: Transfer to a cutting board and cut in squares. 9: Dust brownies with confectioners'' sugar if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3326,"Crabmeat Puffs","0","PT0S","PT0S","This recipe is not exactly crab rangoon,but it''s very similar.I like to add green onions or chives to the crab mixture.","< 15 Mins",5.0,1.0,1748.6,70.9,40.1,560.0,4064.9,190.8,5.8,0.9,81.3,"1.0","Crabmeat Puffs Recipe Instructions:  1: Drain crabmeat thoroughly; remove cartilage. Remove excess water by squeezing  crabmeat;chop. 2: Mix crabmeat,cream cheese,salt and garlic powder. 3: Brush wonton  skin with egg.Place heaping teaspoonful of crabmeat mixture in center of wonton  skin. 4: (Cover remaining skins with plastic wrap to keep them pliable.) Top with  another wonton skin; press edges to seal. 5: Brush egg on center of each side of  puff.Make a pleat on each of 4 sides,pressing to seal. 6: Repeat with remaining  wonton skins. 7: (Cover puffs with plastic wrap to keep them from drying out.) When puffs are room temperature, heat vegetable oil (1 1/2 inches) in wok to 350  degrees ( I use a deep fryer). Fry 4 or 5 puffs at a time, 2 minutes or until  golden brown, turning 2 or 3 times; drain on paper towels. 8: Serve with a sweet  and sour sauce if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3327,"Raisin-Applesauce Squares","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Raisin-Applesauce Squares recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",0.0,0.0,100.3,3.6,0.5,8.7,35.4,16.7,1.5,9.3,1.8,"0.0","Raisin-Applesauce Squares Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat egg in large mixing bowl. 2: Add oik, yogurt, brown sugar, applesauce, vanilla and lemon rind. 3: Mix well. 4: In anot her bowl, combine raisins, flour, bran, baking  powder, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg. 5: Add to wet ingredients and mix until  combined. 6: Pour into lightly-greased 8-inch-square baking pan and top with sliced almonds. 7: Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in  centre comes out clean.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3328,"Sweet Potato Pineapple Casserole","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sweet Potato Pineapple Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,4.0,1191.1,46.1,9.5,0.0,2087.3,185.6,18.6,98.6,16.7,"1.0","Sweet Potato Pineapple Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients except marshmallows in mixing bowl; beat well. 2: Butter   baking dish; place 1/2 of mixture in dish, dot with marshmallows. 3: Add remaining mixture and bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. 4: Remove from  oven, dot with  marshmallows and bake another 10 minutes or until golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3329,"Pork Liver Pudding ( Spread / Dip )","PT30M","PT24H","PT24H30M","Make and share this Pork Liver Pudding ( Spread / Dip ) recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",0.0,0.0,1665.4,63.9,22.0,1827.9,723.2,11.3,0.0,0.0,244.1,"0.0","Pork Liver Pudding ( Spread / Dip ) Recipe Instructions:  1: Simmer the pork liver and pork chops separately until tender. 2: Reserve  cooking liquid from pork chops. 3: Cool, cut both in small pieces and put  through medium or fine blade of food chopper. 4: (Food processor does not  work well as it makes it too pasty.) Combine ground liver and pork, adding 1-1/2 teaspoo ns salt, 1 teaspoon  black pepper, and 1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes. 5: Mix thoroughly, taste  and adjust seasonings. 6: Add 1/2 cup or more of reserved cooking liquid to  meat mixture, sufficient to bind but not soupy. 7: Pack mixture firmly into lightly greased Pyrex loaf pan. 8: Cover surface  of meat with greaseproof paper and bake at 350 degrees F. for 1/2 hour. 9: Cool to room temperature, then refrigerate for at least 24 hours to  develop flavor. 10: Slice and serve with toast points, melba toast, or make small sandwiches.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3330,"Blackberry Pie II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Blackberry Pie II recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,2.0,253.7,7.7,1.9,0.0,168.6,44.8,2.8,29.6,2.7,"8.0","Blackberry Pie II Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan. 2: Add 1 1/2 cups water. 3: Cook until clear;  remove from heat. Add 1 package blackberry Jell-O. 4: Stir to dissolve. Cool  slightly and add 1 pint or more of the blackberries. 5: Fold into Jell-O mixture  carefully. 6: Pour into chilled crust. Store in refrigerator. 7: Keeps well. 8: Serve  with whipped cream or ice cream. 9: Use 1 tablespoon less of Jell-O when using  fresh berries.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3331,"Blackberry Pie IIi","PT45M","PT10M","PT55M","Make and share this Blackberry Pie IIi recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,34.0,410.9,16.0,3.9,0.0,281.5,64.3,4.7,34.8,4.3,"8.0","Blackberry Pie IIi Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400°F. 2: Combine sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt; toss with blackberries. 3: Line 9-inch  pie plate with pastry. 4: Add black- berry mixture. 5: Adjust top crust; cut slits to allow steam to escape. 6: Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3332,"Wiener Schnitzel","0","PT0S","PT1H","Make and share this Wiener Schnitzel recipe from Food.com.","Meat",5.0,4.0,22.5,1.2,0.4,46.5,18.7,1.5,0.5,0.4,1.8,"4.0","Wiener Schnitzel Recipe Instructions:  1: Tenderize meat between 2 sheets of wax paper (or have butcher do it for you),  pat with salt and pepper. 2: Dip cutlets in flour, shake  off excess, dip in egg,  then in bread crumbs. 3: Brown meat in hot fat on both sides till golden brown. 4: Place briefly on paper towel to absorb excess fat.  Serve each Schnitzel with a  wedge of lemon and parsley sprigs. 5: Serve with a green salad, cauliflower, peas, green beans or carrots and new red potatoes, boiled, then quickly browned in  butter.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3333,"French Toast II","PT15M","PT10M","PT25M","Here''s the way French Toast has been made in my family for at least 4 generations - but until I got into high school, we called it "egg-bread", as my back-country French-American grandparents had.  Everyone I make it for loves it!","Breakfast",5.0,85.0,337.2,14.8,5.5,499.6,218.1,32.1,2.1,25.7,18.7,"0.0","French Toast II Recipe Instructions:  1: Whisk the eggs till frothy. 2: Add remaining ingredients, and mix well. 3: Over medium heat, lightly grease skillet with shortening (butter will burn very quickly, so exercise caution if using butter).  I use a paper towel, so I can use it repeatedly, with every 2 or 3 pans of French toast. Dip each slice of bread into the egg mixture, on both sides. 4: Do this quickly, so as not to completely soak the bread. 5: Cook in skillet over med/med-high heat for approx 5 min per side.  You may need to flip more than once to get th e desired golden-brown color. 6: Serve with butter and powdered sugar, or preserves (my favorite) or syrup.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3334,"Aunt Mary''s Biscuits","PT10M","PT15M","PT25M","This is my favourite recipe for making tea biscuits.  My mother-in-law has been using it for years.  Aunt Mary''s Biscuits","Breads",4.5,2.0,142.0,6.6,1.9,2.9,234.4,17.6,0.6,0.8,2.8,"12.0","Aunt Mary''s Biscuits Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine first 4 ingredients. 2: Cut in shortening with pastry cutter or two knives until it resembles coarse meal. 3: Pour milk into center and stir with fork until mixture leaves the sides of the bowl. 4: Knead carefully on floured board. 5: Roll or pat to 3/4 inch thickness and cut with 2-inch cookie cutter. 6: Place on ungreased sheet and bake at 450: F for 10 to 15 minutes until nicely browned. 7: If you wish, you can brush tops with milk to make them brown nicely.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3335,"Beer Dip","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Beer Dip recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",2.0,1.0,1583.1,158.2,99.6,499.0,1342.7,12.1,0.0,0.9,34.2,"1.0","Beer Dip Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix all together and refrigerate until ready to use. Take 1 large round loaf of  rye bread and scoop out center. 2: Put dip in the center. 3: Use the leftover bread  pieces for dipping. 4: A party favorite");
