INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3337,"Pierogies Shark Fins","0","PT5M","PT5M","Make and share this Pierogies Shark Fins recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,175.8,14.1,2.0,4.1,671.2,11.7,0.9,8.5,1.4,"8.0","Pierogies Shark Fins Recipe Instructions:  1: Deep-fry pierogies as per package directions. 2: Remove from oil; drain well. 3: Cut pierogies in half and stand up on serving platter to resemble shark fins. 4: Sprinkle with Cajun seasoning. 5: Serve on platter along with bowls of ketchup, hot mustard, barbecue sauce, ranch dressing and sweet an sour sauce for dipping.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3338,"Chicken and Sausage Gumbo","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chicken and Sausage Gumbo recipe from Food.com.","Gumbo",0.0,0.0,373.5,28.2,8.8,75.4,575.1,10.7,3.2,2.0,19.6,"0.0","Chicken and Sausage Gumbo Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut up chicken, remove skin if you like. Dredge the chicken with flour salt and  pepper. 2: Fry the chicken until brown. 3: Slice up a pound of the link sausage   For  a hotter sausage, try the Louisiana ''Andouille'', if a vailable. After the chicken is browned, place sausage in the same skillet -- use a heavy iron one. Brown the sausage on both sides. 4: Save the grease from chicken and sausage.  Fry the  tomato, onion and okra in about 2 Tbsp shortening or oil, until they become  tender. 5: Make a roux with 2 tsp oil and 2 tsp flour, stir and brown over a  medium-low heat until the roux is as dark as possible without burning it. Do not burn the roux,   just make it real dark. 6: Place chicken and sausage in the roux, stir a bit. Then place all ingredients into a heavy, deep iron pan, add water  and cook about 2 hours. 7: Cook slow, add water if needed. 8: The okra will thicken  the gumbo as it cooks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3339,"Herbed Cauliflower Bake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Herbed Cauliflower Bake recipe from Food.com.","Cauliflower",4.5,3.0,105.7,2.8,1.4,5.1,143.8,17.3,3.8,4.3,4.4,"4.0","Herbed Cauliflower Bake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 F. 2: Place cauliflower in a steamer basket over boiling water. 3: Cover and steam 4-5 minutes or until just tender. 4: Drain and keep warm. 5: Melt butter in a heavy nonstick skillet  over medium heat. Sauti onions, celery and mushrooms 4-5 minutes or until tender. 6: Stir in remaining ingredients except cauliflower and breadcrumbs. 7: Add salt and pepper to taste. Simmer another 2 minutes. 8: Stir in cauliflower. 9: Transfer mixture to a lightly oiled baking dish. 10: Top with breadcrumbs and bake 15 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3340,"Banana Split Cheesecake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Banana Split Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",5.0,1.0,700.9,44.5,24.5,237.0,432.7,67.7,1.4,50.6,10.1,"8.0","Banana Split Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: In a small bowl combine cracker crumbs, sugar and  butter. 3: Mix well then pat into the sides and bottom of a 10 i nch springform pan. 4: Set aside. In a large mixer bowl beat cream cheese and sugar until light. Add  eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. 5: Stir in cream, sour cream,  vanilla and cornstarch. 6: Blend well. 7: Stir in banana then transfer mixture to  springform pan. 8: Bake 1 hour or until edges are firm and center is set.                    - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3341,"Cappuccino Mix","0","PT5M","PT5M","Make and share this Cappuccino Mix recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",5.0,5.0,1315.0,38.7,34.4,0.0,655.5,234.2,4.5,210.2,12.2,"0.0","Cappuccino Mix Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients. 2: Store in airtight containers. 3: To use: 4: Add 3 Tablespoons cappuccino mix to 6 ozs. hot water; stir well.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3342,"Lemon Poppy Seed Loaf","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lemon Poppy Seed Loaf recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",0.0,0.0,2586.7,159.2,25.4,372.0,2614.0,267.2,8.7,117.2,29.4,"0.0","Lemon Poppy Seed Loaf Recipe Instructions:  1: Soak poppy seed in hot water at least 10 minutes. 2: Mix pudding, cake mix, oil and eggs. 3: Beat 1 minute. Add seed and water. 4: Mix well. 5: Bake 50 minutes at 350 degrees. 6: Use 2 loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan. 7: Let stand 10 minutes; remove from pan(s).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3343,"Wild Rice Cheddar Broccoli Bake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Wild Rice Cheddar Broccoli Bake recipe from Food.com.","Rice",5.0,5.0,397.0,14.4,8.7,40.7,272.7,53.9,4.1,2.0,14.9,"8.0","Wild Rice Cheddar Broccoli Bake Recipe Instructions:  1: In large saucepan, melt butter; add flour, salt and pepper. 2: Cook, stirring until mixture bubbles. 3: Add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens. 4: Boil 1 to 2 minutes. 5: Remove from heat. Stir in cheese until melted. 6: Combine cooked wild rice, broccoli, onion and cheese sauce. Turn into lightly greased 2-qt. casserole. In small bowl, combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top. 7: Bake at 3500F 30 to 35 minutes, or until hot and bubbly. 8: Note: Wild rice can be cooked a day or more in advance and refrigerated.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3344,"Banana Crackers","PT8M","PT10M","PT18M","Make and share this Banana Crackers recipe from Food.com.","< 30 Mins",4.0,5.0,24.6,1.6,1.0,4.1,21.0,2.5,0.2,0.5,0.3,"0.0","Banana Crackers Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 450 and grease a 12x15 inch cookie sheet. In a med. size bowl  using a pastry blender, mix butter, flour and 1/8 teaspoons salt together until crumbly. 2: Using a fork, stir in Tabasco and banana. 3: On a floured surface, knead  mixture gently adding a small amount of flour if necessary to make the dough  firm. 4: Divide dough into half and roll out one half at a time on a floured  surface until thin enough to cover prepared cookie sheet. Place dough on cookie  sheet and sprinkle lightly with the coarse salt. Using a pastry cutter, cut  through dough into 1\ 5: Bake 6-8 minutes or until lightly browned. 6: Remove crackers with a spatula and place on a wire rack to cool. 7: Repeat with second  half of the dough.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3345,"Swiss Chard Dolmades","0","PT0S","PT0S","Since we grow a lot of Swiss chard in our garden, I experimented with the smaller more tender leaves and found that they are even more delicious than grape leaves in preparing dolmades.  We have one vegetarian and two carnivores in our household, so I came up with two fillings to accommodate everyone.","White Rice",5.0,7.0,478.1,23.4,9.5,56.1,2234.5,51.7,6.0,6.9,18.0,"4.0","Swiss Chard Dolmades Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute rice/orzo  and  garlic in butter for 1 minute, add almonds. 2: Stir just  until almonds become a bit brown. 3: Turn off heat, stir in remaining ingredients. 4: Brown lamb and garlic in olive oil, add rice and stir just until rice begins to  brown. 5: Turn off heat, stir in remaining ingredients. 6: 3 cups canned tomato juice  Lemon wedges Have both the fillings prepared and ready to go. 7: In a 9X11\ 8:  deep. 9: Rinse chard leaves and cut off any stem. 10: Stack chard leaves in a steamer basket or metal colander over a large kettle of  boiling water: cover. 11: Allow leaves to steam 3-4 minutes or until soft and  pliable but  still quite green. 12: After 2 minutes of steaming you can  use two  spatulas to turn the whole stack of leaves over to allow the \ 13:  ones  on the top to steam more thoroughly. 14: Remove chard leaves to a plate.  Separate  them and allow  them to cool so they will be easier to handle.  Flatten a chard  leaf on the working surface and place about 2 tablespoons of chosen filling  1/2 inch above the bottom stem end. 15: Fold each side over the filling, then roll up  from the stem end \ 16: , ending with the top of the leaf folded over  the roll. 17: Place the dolmade \ 18:  in the tomato juice in the  prepared pan. 19: You should be able to see the roll, but not any of the seam, which should be underneath. 20: I differentiate the vegetarian and meat dolmades by  placing a sliver of carrot or red pepper on top of the vegetarian ones. 21: Repeat  with all of the remaining leaves. 22: If you tear a leaf and can''t use it or have  extra filling left over, you can sprinkle it into the tomato juice when you bake the dish and your sauce will be all the more delicious. 23: Pour remaining tomato  juice over the dolmades. 24: Two cooking methods: Bake in a moderate 350 degree oven for 35 minutes on the top shelf, uncovered. 25: or Simmer in a large stew pot on top of the stove.  If you choose this method,  weight the dolmades down by placing a plate on top of them and then putting  something  heavy (i.e. a heavy coffee mug or two) on top of the plate. Simmer at  low-medium heat on stove top for 20-25 minutes. 26: This method produces a more  compact dolmade that holds together better when you serve it.  Important:  When you take them from the oven or turn off the stove, let them sit for at least 10 minutes before serving. 27: They are much less likely to fall apart this way. 28: Serve 4 dolmades per guest with lemon wedges to squeeze over. 29: They  are delicious cold or room temperature as well. 30: Suggested accompaniments:  Avegolemo soup, tossed salad with black olives and feta cheese, fresh steamed  artichokes, garlic bread.");
