INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3454,"Papa Vaughn''s Thick Bread","0","PT0S","PT0S","My husband''s grandfather used to make this for him around Christmas time, but it''s really good anytime it''s cold out.  Papa Vaughn''s Thick Bread","Breads",0.0,0.0,4512.3,236.3,85.6,499.8,12745.4,415.5,60.0,85.1,184.3,"0.0","Papa Vaughn''s Thick Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to temperature according to package. Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions. 2: add everything but bell peppers. 3: Mix thoroughly. 4: Pour into greased baking dish, we usually use a 9x13x2 pan. 5: Place bell peppers on top before placing in oven. 6: Bake according to package directions. 7: or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. 8: Serve hot with a glass of ice cold milk. 9: This can be made into muffins instead. 10: We usually serve this with chili con carne. His grandfather used to m ake it for Christmas dinner and they usually had honey baked ham.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3455,"Lemon Lime Punch","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lemon Lime Punch recipe from Food.com.","Punch Beverage",5.0,2.0,3250.1,16.1,7.1,5.9,675.2,778.9,13.4,694.3,19.0,"0.0","Lemon Lime Punch Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix together lemonade, orange juice, pineapple juice, cold water, soda water and ginger ale. Pour into punch bowl. 2: Add the sherbet and stir for several minutes before serving. 3: Needs no ice cubes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3456,"Vegetable Lasagna","PT1H","PT30M","PT1H30M","Make and share this Vegetable Lasagna recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,17.0,736.2,23.7,14.1,86.1,1326.3,81.7,5.3,12.2,48.8,"6.0","Vegetable Lasagna Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute zucchini, yellow squash, mushrooms and garlic until tender in 2 Tbs  margarine. Add Italian seasoning and 1/4 tsp salt. Stir in carrots and  broccoli; set aside and cool. 2: Melt remaining margarine in saucepan; add flour,  pepper and remain  ing salt. Cook over medium heat 5 minutes. 3: Stir in milk and  cook until thickened. 4: Remove from heat and stir in Parmesan cheese. Set aside.  Cook pasta, according to package directions. 5: Rinse in cool water and drain. 6: Grease lasagna pan. 7: Spoon only enough white sauce into lasagna pan to barely  cover the bottom. 8: Line with 3 noodles; spoon 1/2 the vegetable mixture over  noodles, placing it down the center of each noodle; sprinkle 1/3 of the  mozzarella cheese over the vegetable mixture. Cover with another layer of  pasta; spread with 1/2 the spinach ; cover with 1/2 the remaining white sauce.  Repeat the layering; 3 noodles; remaining vegetables, 1/2 remaining mozzarella;  3 noodles, remaining ricotta, spinach and white sauce. Cover with remaining  mozzarella, sprinkle with parmesan and parsley over top. 9: Bake 45 minutes in a  preheated 350°F oven. 10: Let stand 15 minutes before serving. 11: Serve with crisp  green salad and fresh bread.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3457,"Pasta Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pasta Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",5.0,1.0,990.3,32.2,4.8,0.0,1437.5,126.8,30.3,74.0,28.7,"0.0","Pasta Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: In a 4 to 5 quart pan over medium heat, cook onion, garlic, basil,  tarragon, fennel and oregano in oil, stirring often until onion is limp, 10 to 15 minutes. 2: Add zucchini, mushrooms and green pepper. 3: Cook until mushrooms are limp, stirring often, 10 to 15 minutes. 4: Add wine, tomatoes, tomato paste and sugar to pan. 5: Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until sauce is thick, stirring occasionally, about 45 minutes. 6: Use hot. Makes about 7 cups. 7: Pasta Sauce: 2 Tbsp. 8: butter or margarine 2 Tbsp. 9: all-purpose flour 1 tsp. 10: McKay''s instant chicken seasoning 1 cup milk 2 to 3 Tbsp. 11: grated Parmesan cheese In a medium saucepan, melt butter or margarine over low heat. Blend in flour and seasoning. 12: Add milk, stirring constantly and cook over medium heat until sauce is moderately thick and bubbly. 13: Remove from heat and stir in Parmesan cheese. Makes approximately 1 cup sauce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3458,"Mississippi Candied Yams","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Mississippi Candied Yams recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",4.5,7.0,3255.3,95.3,59.2,244.0,720.9,599.7,62.0,212.3,23.7,"0.0","Mississippi Candied Yams Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine sugar, butter, orange juice, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt in small  sauce pan and heat gently to boiling, stirring frequently. 2: Set aside to  cool slightly. 3: Arrange sliced yams and lemon slices in large baking dish as one layer,  or slightly overlapping. 4: Pour syrup mixture over yams. 5: Bake at 325:F.  for 2 to 2-1/2 hours, basting thoroughly every 15-20 minutes with syrup  from baking pan. 6: Turn yams occasionally. 7: When done, yams should be  tender when pierced with point of sharp knife and syrup has been almost  completely absorbed and thickened. 8: This dish may be prepared early in the day, covered lightly and reheated  in oven or microwave.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3459,"Apple Crisp III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apple Crisp III recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,5.0,435.8,16.0,9.8,40.7,133.8,73.8,2.6,58.7,2.5,"12.0","Apple Crisp III Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees and lightly spray a 9 X 13 inch baking pan with  non-stick butter flavored cooking spray. 2: In a large bowl combine oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and granulated sugar. 3: Mix to combine. Using a pastry cutter, cut in  butter until mixture resembles coarse meal. 4: Place sliced apples in an even layer over the bottom of the prepared pan and sprinkle with salt and cinnamon to  taste. Top apple slices with oatmeal mixture and another dash of cinnamon. 5: Bake  40 minutes, or until golden. 6: Allow to cool 15 minutes before serving. 7: Serving Ideas : Serve warm with ice cream or cold cut into large squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3460,"Pumpkin Cheesecake II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pumpkin Cheesecake II recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",5.0,6.0,389.8,26.3,14.8,98.3,252.5,34.8,0.4,28.2,5.3,"16.0","Pumpkin Cheesecake II Recipe Instructions:  1: Crust: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar in a med. bowl. 2: Press  onto bottom and 1\ 3:  springform pan. 4: Bake in preheated 350 degree  oven for 6-8 min. 5: Do not allow to brown. 6: Cool on wire rack for 10 min. 7: Cheesecake: Beat cream cheese and sugars in large mixer bowl until fluffy. 8: Beat  in eggs, pumpkin and milk. 9: Add cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg. 10: Beat well. 11: Pour  into crust. bake at 350 degrees for 55-60 min., until edge is set but center  still moves slightly. 12: Topping: Combine sour cream, sugar and vanilla in med.  bowl. 13:  14: Spread over surface of warm cheesecake. Bake for an additional 5 min. 15: Cool on wire rack. 16: Chill for several hours or overnight. Remove side of springform  pan before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3461,"Grilled Steaks with Peppery Peach Salsa","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Grilled Steaks with Peppery Peach Salsa recipe from Food.com.","Sauces",4.0,1.0,125.8,0.2,0.0,0.0,233.3,30.7,1.4,21.0,0.7,"4.0","Grilled Steaks with Peppery Peach Salsa Recipe Instructions:  1: Sprinkle both sides of beef steaks with 1/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper. 2: Remove seeds from bell pepper, leaving pepper whole. Place steaks and bell pepper on grid over medium, ash-covered coals. 3: Grill steaks, uncovered, 15 to 18 minutes for medium rare to medium doneness, turning once. Grill bell pepper 2 to 3 minutes, turning occasionally. 4: While steaks continue to cook, cut four 1/2-inch thick rings from bell pepper; set aside for garnish. 5: Coarsely chop enough remaining bell pepper to make 1/4 cup. 6: In small saucepan, combine the 1/4 cup chopped bell pepper with salsa ingredients. 7: Place on grid near edge of grill to heat until warm. 8: Approximately 5 minutes before steaks are done, remove 2 tablespoons salsa from saucepan and brush on both sides of steaks. 9: To serve, place 1 bell pepper ring on each steak; fill rings with warm salsa. 10: Makes 4 servings (serving size: 1/4 of recipe). Tip: To broil, place steaks and bell pepper on rack in broiler pan so surface of meat is 3 to 4 inche s from heat. Broil bell pepper 5 minutes; remove and proceed as directed above. Broil steaks 13 to 17 minutes, turning once; approx. 11: 5 minutes before steaks are done, brush both sides with 2 tablespoons salsa.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3462,"Pumpkin Swirl Cheesecake","PT55M","PT1H","PT1H55M","Make and share this Pumpkin Swirl Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",5.0,5.0,481.7,28.1,14.8,144.8,460.7,50.9,1.4,27.6,7.8,"10.0","Pumpkin Swirl Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Crust: Mix crushed ginger snaps, but ter and 1 tablespoon flour in medium mixing bowl. 2: Press  onto bottom of 8 or 9 inch springform pan. 3: Filling:  Beat cream cheese in large mixing bowl until smooth. 4: Add sugar, the remaining 3 tablespoons flour, ginger, and  vanilla. 5: Beat on high until smooth. 6: Add eggs all at once.  Beat on low until  combined. 7: Stir in cream. 8: Measure 2 cups of filling, set aside.  To remaining  mixture add pumpkin, sugar and spices. 9: Spoon plain cream cheese mixture into  pan. 10: Carefully spoon pumpkin mixture over plain. 11: Use a spatula  to gently swirl batters, do not disturb crust.   Bake in 350F for 50-55 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3463,"Fish Sticks","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Fish Sticks recipe from Food.com.","Healthy",5.0,4.0,630.8,6.0,1.3,196.8,723.7,45.9,3.4,4.3,93.5,"1.0","Fish Sticks Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 475 degrees. 2: Cut fish into 8 stick-shaped pieces. 3: In small bowl, whisk together egg and milk until foamy. 4: Place bread in a plastic bag and crush  into fine crumbs using a rolling pin. 5: Measure 1 cup of crumbs and combine with  pepper, parsley and paprika. 6: Dip fish into egg mixture and coat with crumb  mixture. Place on a nonstick baking dish (or regular baking dish lightly coated  with vegetable oil) and squeeze lemon juice evenly over fish sticks. 7: Bake 20  minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3464,"Cucumber Spread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cucumber Spread recipe from Food.com.","Spreads",5.0,1.0,1856.5,175.6,90.7,515.1,1916.9,50.0,2.7,26.4,30.2,"0.0","Cucumber Spread Recipe Instructions:  1: Remove half of skin from cucumber and chop finely. 2: Drain in colander to remove liquid. 3: Chop onion. 4: Soften cream cheese in microwave for 20 seconds. 5: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until creamy, then beat in liquid red pepper and food coloring. 6: Mix in cucumber and onion. 7: Chill and serve on bread or crackers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3465,"Onions in Red Sauce for Hot Dogs","0","PT0S","PT0S","I can''t recall where I got this recipe, but it is delicious and I''ve made it several times. I find that it takes quite a while for the water to boil down......but it is well worth it.  Onions in Red sauce for Hot Dogs","Very Low Carbs",4.5,3.0,187.5,7.1,1.0,0.0,1451.2,28.6,3.3,11.9,2.7,"0.0","Onions in Red Sauce for Hot Dogs Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Saute sliced onion in the oil for 5 minutes, until onions are soft, but not brown. 2: Add water, tomato paste,  corn syrup, cornstarch, salt and red pepper flakes, and stir. 3: Bring mixture to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes. 4: Add vinegar. 5: Continue to  simmer for an additional 30 to 45 minutes  or until most of the liquid has  reduced and the sauce is thick. 6: Makes about 1 cup.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3466,"Microwave Polenta","PT25M","PT5M","PT30M","This is an easier way to make Polenta  Microwave Polenta   Use microwave.With 700 or more power. microwave safe container, (round is better)  Ratio.","Low Protein",5.0,9.0,220.8,2.2,0.3,0.0,615.2,46.9,4.5,0.4,5.0,"0.0","Microwave Polenta Recipe Instructions:  1: You may have to adjust ratio, depending on altitude and  or type of flour. 2: I use a Pyrex round unit with lid, large enough to hold (7) seven cups water and (2)  two cups cornmeal flour, Mix flour with water and salt , and microwave at f ull  power for 22 to 26 minutes, (depending on power and quantity) stopping to stir  every five to six minutes. 3: Suggestions. 4: You can substitute some broth or milk, not too much milk or it may boil over. 5: Makes 2-3 servings (2 with some leftovers).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3467,"Berry-Good Mousse","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Berry-Good Mousse recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,94.7,0.3,0.0,0.0,39.7,20.1,1.5,17.6,4.0,"6.0","Berry-Good Mousse Recipe Instructions:  1: GARNISH: Fresh strawberries, hulled In saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over orange juice. Let stand 5 minutes to soften. 2: Warm over low heat until gelatin has dissolved. 3: Meanwhile, hull strawberries and place in food processor or blender. 4: Add icing sugar and process just until  pureed. 5: Transfer to mixing bowl and stir in gelatin mixture. Refrigerate until  mixture is consistency of raw egg whites. 6: Whip cream (if using) and set aside.  In large bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form. 7: Whisk about < of beaten  egg whites into strawberry mixture. Fold strawberry mixture and whipped cream  into remaining beaten egg whites. 8: Pour into 6-cup glass serving bowl or  individual glasses and refrigerate at least 4 hours or up to days. 9: Garnish with  fresh strawberries.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3468,"Crock Pot Pork and Capsicum Pepper Casserole","PT8H","PT20M","PT8H20M","This one is tasty, I usually get it ready the night before then put it in the crock pot and leave it on low all day.","Pork",2.5,2.0,1916.1,70.9,18.2,417.6,650.6,95.2,15.0,38.0,170.1,"0.0","Crock Pot Pork and Capsicum Pepper Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut the pork into cubes and brown lightly in the oil. 2: Add chopped capsicum, thinly slice onions and sliced mushrooms and cook for 3 minutes. 3: Stir in the flour and cook 2 minutes. 4: Add the wine, stock, tomato puree, sage (if using), salt and pepper to taste and bring to the boil. 5: Peel the tomatoes, remove the pips and chop the flesh. 6: Add to the onions etc., then place in the crock pot.  Cover and cook on LOW 7 - 8 hours.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3469,"Fruity Chicken Salad","PT45M","PT20M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Fruity Chicken Salad recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",3.5,3.0,268.1,6.1,1.1,64.8,93.8,29.1,1.8,26.1,25.6,"6.0","Fruity Chicken Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut cooked chicken into bite-sized cubes to fill 3 cups and place  in large bowl. 2: Add celery, pineapple, oranges, grapes and nuts. 3: Toss. 4: In small bowl, mix yogurt, mayonnaise and lemon juice with a fork. 5: Add the dressing to the chicken mixture and gently toss.");
