INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3472,"Pumpkin Fruitcake","PT1H30M","PT0S","PT1H30M","Make and share this Pumpkin Fruitcake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,2.0,4600.1,198.8,120.3,911.0,2166.3,692.0,42.8,203.0,52.7,"0.0","Pumpkin Fruitcake Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter and  sugar, add  eggs and beat well. 2: Then add  cold mashed  pumpkin, flour sifted with  cream of tartar and  baking soda. 3: Lastly mix in 1 lb dried  mixed fruit.  Turn into greased pan Bake in slow oven 1 1/2 hours. 4: Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 5: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3473,"Albondigas Soup","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Albondigas Soup recipe from Food.com.","Low Cholesterol",5.0,5.0,312.9,13.2,3.5,77.7,2853.1,24.6,2.9,4.8,25.2,"0.0","Albondigas Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix together beef broth, salsa, 1 onion, tomatoes, dried basil, oregano,  and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. 2: (If you use condensed beef broth [e.g., Campbell''s],  eliminate the salt in the meatballs and use 5 cans [10.5 ounces each] broth  plus one quart water.) Bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes. 3: Combine ground chuck, sausage, 1 onion, egg, salt, 1/4 teas  poon pepper,  garlic powder, milk, fresh basil, and cornmeal, and mix well. 4: Form into tiny,  bite-size meatballs. 5: Add meatballs and rice to broth. 6: Simmer, covered, very slowly for 1 to 1  1/2 hours. 7: Makes 8 -10 servings");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3474,"Meatball Soup","PT40M","PT0S","PT40M","Make and share this Meatball Soup recipe from Food.com.","Meat",5.0,35.0,81.4,0.5,0.1,0.2,375.1,16.2,1.4,2.0,2.9,"0.0","Meatball Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring water to a boil in a large saucepan. 2: Add meatballs, tomato sauce,   bouillon, oregano, basil, thyme, salt and pepper to taste, celery, carrots,  and garlic, and simmer for 30 minutes. 3: Add macaroni and cook until pasta is done.  Top with Parmesan cheese to  serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3475,"Egg Noodles II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Egg Noodles II recipe from Food.com.","Healthy",0.0,0.0,1279.3,27.3,8.1,1057.5,2952.8,193.5,6.8,2.6,57.3,"1.0","Egg Noodles II Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat eggs with hand beater. 2: Mix just until blended. 3: Do not sift all flour into eggs. 4: Save about 1/2 cup. 5: Flour board and as you work, sift gradually flour, baking powder and salt into eggs. 6: Mix just until blended. 7: Flour board generously. 8: Turn dough onto board, flour hands to prevent sticking. 9: Knead very lightly. 10: Flour rolling pin to prevent sticking . 11: Roll out paper thin. 12: Roll up in tube. Cut in strips and shake out. Use as packaged noodles.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3476,"Onion Soup Mix","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Onion Soup Mix recipe from Food.com.","Low Cholesterol",4.5,4.0,49.0,0.2,0.0,0.0,76.5,11.1,1.8,3.1,1.7,"8.0","Onion Soup Mix Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine in order listed. 2: Keep the mixture in jar at room temperature. 3: Makes 2 cups. 4: 1/4 cup mix equals 1 envelope commercial soup mix TO USE: 1/4 cup mix to 4 cups boiling water. 5: Stir well until soup is dissolved.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3477,"Grandma Puckett''s BBQ Chicken","0","PT0S","PT0S","Especially good if served with wild rice. Recipe in honor of my Grandmother who passed away 1 year ago. This was always a wonderful treat when she made this!","Whole Chicken",5.0,5.0,381.7,21.8,5.9,86.2,628.1,24.3,0.9,21.5,22.7,"8.0","Grandma Puckett''s BBQ Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Flour chicken, Fry in skillet until lightly brown. 2: Place chicken in 2 qt. Casserole dish. 3: In a saucepan, melt butter, add onions & pepper, cook until tender. 4: Add mushrooms & remaining ingredients. 5: Bring to a boil. 6: Pour over chicken. 7: Cover and bake at 350* for 45 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3478,"Steak and Artichoke Croissant Sandwiches","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Steak and Artichoke Croissant Sandwiches recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",0.0,1.0,854.5,58.4,23.2,190.5,968.4,38.5,1.7,14.4,43.0,"4.0","Steak and Artichoke Croissant Sandwiches Recipe Instructions:  1: Begin at least 4 hours in advance or, preferably, the night before. Trim fat  from flank steak and cut into strips approximately 1/2 inch wide and 3 inches  long. 2: In hot oil, brown the steak strips over medium high heat until they are  cooked through and brown. 3: Don''t overcook or steak will be tough. 4: Drain off any  excess fat. Put steak strips in a 1-quart bowl and pour over the well-blended  Italian dressing. 5: Refrigerate for at least 3-1/2 hours or overnight. Open  artichokes and drain off all liquid. 6: Cut artichoke bottoms in fourths,  articho ke hearts in half. 7: If steak has not absorbed all of the Italian dressing, drain off any excess. 8: Combine sour cream, artichokes, steak and mix thoroughly. 9: This mixture will keep for some time if you want to refrigerate it until you are ready to assemble sandwiches. 10: When ready to serve, carefully slice open the  croissants and pile 1/4 of the steak/artichoke mixture inside each croissant. I have served these sandwiches with a light salad of mixed greens, mandarin orange segments and  slivered red onion.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3479,"General Tso''s Chicken II","PT20M","PT15M","PT35M","Make and share this General Tso''s Chicken II recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",4.5,9.0,576.7,39.3,8.2,185.7,1041.4,8.0,1.3,2.1,45.3,"0.0","General Tso''s Chicken II Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine soy sauce, rice vinegar, water or chicken and cornstarch mixture, dry  sherry, sesame oil, garlic and ginger; set aside. Combine egg and cornstarch  mixture well. 2: Add chicken and toss to coat. Heat oil until hot; fry chicken in  batches until crisp and brown (do not crowd pan). Drain on paper towels. 3: Pour  off all but 2 teaspoons oil from pan. 4: Add chilies and toss for a few seconds. 5: Return chicken to pan with soy sauce mixture and cook until glazed (1 to 2  minutes). Add pea pods; cook 1 more minute. Serve immediately. 6: If reheat ing, cut down on cooking time. Serves 6 to 8.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3480,"Madwizard''s Pumpkin Cookies","PT15M","PT10M","PT25M","These cookies taste like pumpkin pie without the crust. Especially when they''re  warm out of the oven. Enjoy!","Drop Cookies",5.0,29.0,106.4,3.7,2.2,16.7,96.8,17.1,0.4,8.7,1.4,"24.0","Madwizard''s Pumpkin Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Optional: 3/4 cup chopped nuts  Also optional: a small dash of cloves and a tiny dash of all-spice (very  optional--to your liking).  Preheat oven to 350°F 2: In a large bowl combine sugars; butter-beat until fluffy. 3: Add pumpkin, vanilla and the egg; blend well. 4: Add flour, baking powder and soda, and all spices; mix  well. 5: If you have chosen to add nuts, add and stir. 6: As for the  cooking you can do this one of 2 ways. 7: The first way if you like tiny little  cookies (HAH! Not me! but some like ''em  bite size) then you would drop them  by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches  apart onto a parchment-lined cookie  sheet. Bake these small ones at 350°F for 10-12 minutes. 8: DON''T FORGET TO PREHEAT  THE OVEN FIRST! Duh   many of us forget that sometimes.um.ok. I admit it has  happened before).  Now for those of us who adore larger cookies (OH JOY!) then drop by hefty  tablespoonfuls about 3 inches apart on a parchment-lined cookie sheet.  Bake at 350°F for 11-13 minutes. 9: Secret: Always use cookie sheets with no lips or edges. 10: Get a really good  quality sheet--its worth it! Wilton''s is very good. 11: (I use an insulated  sheet, and I just tried the Silverstone baking liners for the first time.  Good idea!) Also, let sheets cool to room temp before second batch. 12: (Or use  freezer to cool sheets faster). Or just use 2 sheets and alternate.)  The cookies won''t look done really but as they sit they solidify   They  are really cakey. 13: As an added treat you can whip up some cream cheese  frosting as a dip, if if you don''t mind them messier just squeeze a couple  lines over finished cookies. 14: Pure delight!  from: Ann and .topsecretrecipes.com.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3481,"Roast Peppers with Feta Cheese and Olives","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Roast Peppers with Feta Cheese and Olives recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",0.0,0.0,143.1,10.7,3.0,11.1,293.8,10.6,3.5,7.0,3.5,"0.0","Roast Peppers with Feta Cheese and Olives Recipe Instructions:  1: Place peppers on baking tin under broiler about 2 inches  from heat. Roast, turning peppers as skins blacken until  charred on all sides (10 to 15 minutes). Peel under cold  running water. 2: Remove stems, seeds and cut into 1 1/2 inch  wide strips. 3: Leave in colander to drain. 4: Combine drained  peppers with all ingredients but cheese. Marinate several  hours. 5: Remove the garlic clove and add the Feta cheese before  serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3482,"Spinach and Feta Cheese Quiche","PT35M","PT15M","PT50M","Make and share this Spinach and Feta Cheese Quiche recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",4.5,5.0,283.2,21.9,9.3,114.1,680.6,13.1,1.6,2.4,9.4,"8.0","Spinach and Feta Cheese Quiche Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375°F. 2: Chop onion and saute in oil 5 minutes. 3: Add frozen spinach in the 3 tablespoons oil and continue cooking, stirring often until all liquid is gone. 4: Transfer to a bowl and add remaining ingredients. 5: Pour mixture into unbaked pie crust and bake degrees for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3483,"Pear Bread Delight","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pear Bread Delight recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,22.0,2808.7,126.2,18.0,279.0,2410.3,389.6,18.3,220.0,41.4,"0.0","Pear Bread Delight Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl. 2: Make a well in center of mixture. Combine oil, eggs, sugar, pears, nuts and vanilla. 3: Add to dry ingredients, st irring just until moistened. 4: Spoon mixture into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3 inch loaf pans. 5: Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans. 6: Yields: 2 loaves. 7: Good with coffee.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3484,"Meatloaf With Sweet Potatoes","PT30M","PT10M","PT40M","Make and share this Meatloaf With Sweet Potatoes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",0.0,0.0,1007.1,43.5,16.4,218.7,1869.5,103.7,5.1,54.9,49.8,"0.0","Meatloaf With Sweet Potatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix ground beef, salt, egg, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs,  onion, green pepper and tomato sauce. Shape into loaf and  place in oblong baking dish. 2: Bake 30 minutes in 350 degrees oven. 3: Drain sweet potatoes and pour molasses over them. 4: Roll each  potato in crushed cracker crumbs. 5: Arrange around meat loaf and  place bacon on top of loaf. 6: Return to oven and bake additional  20 to 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3485,"Shrimp and Gruyere Cheesecake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Shrimp and Gruyere Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,4543.4,368.4,183.2,2507.3,8321.9,116.4,4.3,34.2,196.4,"1.0","Shrimp and Gruyere Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: cheese (about 5 oz.) 2: 1 Tsp. 3: pepper   --GARNISHES IF DESIRED:--   Red pepper strips   Whole cooked shrimp   Basil leaves   --TOMATO SAUCE:--   1/4 cup chopped onion   1 Clove crushed garlic   1 Tbsp. 4: olive oil   2 (14 Oz.) cans whole tomatoes  1 1/2 Tsp. 5: dried Italian seasoning   1 bay leaf  Serve with tomato sauce, recipe to follow. 6: Combine cracker crumbs and 1/4 cup  melted butter. 7: Press into bottom of 9 inch springform pan. 8: Chop cooked and  cleaned shrimp. 9: Saute peppers, onion and garlic in 3 tablespoons melted butter  for 4-5 minutes until tender, add chopped shrimp and saute another minute.  Drain well and set aside. Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise at high speed until  light and fluffy, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. 10: Gradually add milk beating on low speed just until blended. 11: Stir in shrimp  mixture, shredded Gruyere or Swiss and 1 teaspoon pepper. 12: Pour mixture into  pan. 13: Bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until set. Turn oven off  and open oven door partially leaving cheesecake in oven for 1 more hour. 14: Cool  on rack. 15: Cover and chill or serve at room temperature with hot tomato sauce.  Sauce: Saute onion and garlic in hot oil until tender. 16: Add t  omatoes (break up  with hands or spoon) and rest of ingredients, simmer about 20 minutes, uncovered  until of desired consistency. 17: Remove bay leaf. 18: Serve hot over slices of  chilled or room temperature cheesecake. P.S. 19: I have used both shrimp already  cooked and shrimp I have had to cook depending on the price at the time.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3487,"Appetizer Cheesecake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Appetizer Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",0.0,0.0,1058.3,98.4,54.7,240.8,3329.5,38.0,5.3,24.2,13.3,"1.0","Appetizer Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Layer half of cracker mixture (crackers and sour cream, may have to add some 2: butter to bind)  in bottom of 9-inch spring pan. 3: Blend all other ingredients in  blender; pour into pan. 4: Refrigerate at least 24 hours. 5: Top with remaining  crumbs. 6: Garnish with olive slices, pimiento and parsley. 7: Serve with rye or  pumpernickel rounds.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3488,"Lazy-Day Lasagna","PT55M","PT30M","PT1H25M","Make and share this Lazy-Day Lasagna recipe from Food.com.","European",5.0,6.0,386.2,14.4,7.0,37.6,1062.8,41.7,1.6,12.2,21.6,"10.0","Lazy-Day Lasagna Recipe Instructions:  1: In two greased 10x6x2-inch baking dishes, make layers in the following order:   half each noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella slices, spaghetti sauce, and  sprinkled Parmesan cheese. 2: Repeat. 3: Make certain the dry noodles are  completely  covered by sauce. 4: Wrap pans completely with foil; label and freeze. 5: (To make  this meal incredibly rich, add one 8-ounce package cream cheese. 6: Pinch off  nickel-sized  portions of cream cheese and plop evenly over lasagna just before  adding the second layer of uncooked  pasta.) 7: To Serve: To thaw, take meal from freezer at least 24 hours before serving. 8: Place in refrigerator. 9: Bake  tightly covered at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes, or  until edges are bubbly and center is hot. 10: Take cover off  during final 10  minutes of cooking time. 11: Let stand 10 minutes before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3489,"Lemon Shrimp with Fresh Vegetables","0","PT0S","PT0S","Asparagus, cucumbers and tomatoes are very tender vegetables with sweet fresh flavour, especially when cooked oriental style. To make Lemon Chicken, substitute cubes or strips of chicken breast for the shrimp.","Vegetable",3.0,1.0,407.2,15.0,2.5,143.2,652.7,52.8,3.2,43.3,18.3,"4.0","Lemon Shrimp with Fresh Vegetables Recipe Instructions:  1: Have all ingredients ready for stir-frying: Cut asparagus into 2-inch (5 cm) diagonal pieces; cut onion and tomatoes into wedges; cut cucumber in half lengthwise, then into 1/4-inch (6 mm) chunks; peel shrimp. 2: Lemon Sauce: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, water, lemon juice and vinegar; bring to boil, stirring. 3: Cook 1 or 2 minutes until thickened. 4: Season to taste with  salt, and add a few drops yellow food coloring if desired. 5: Keep sauce warm while stir-frying. 6: In large skillet or wok, heat 2 Tbsp (25 mL) oil. 7: Add asparagus and stir-fry for 1 minute. Add water and sprinkle lightly with salt; cover and steam until asparagus is nearly tender, about 2 minutes. 8: Remove asparagus and set aside. Drain skillet. Add remaining oil to skillet. Brown onion and ginger lightly; remove ginger. 9: Add shrimp and stir-fry for 2 minutes. 10: Add cucumber, tomatoes and asparagus; cover and steam for 2 or 3 minutes just until tender-crisp. 11: Taste and adjust seasoning. 12: Stir in lemon sauce and lemon slices; bring to boil, stirring gently. 13: Serve immediately.");
