INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3491,"Apple-Grape Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apple-Grape Salad recipe from Food.com.","Apple",0.0,0.0,78.9,0.2,0.0,0.0,13.3,18.4,1.2,15.2,1.9,"4.0","Apple-Grape Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Soften gelatin in water for 5 minutes. 2: Heat gelatin over low heat, stirring constantly, until dissolved. 3: Add apple juice.  Chill until mixture begins to thicken. 4: Stir in fruit and celery. 5: Pour into 3 cup mold. 6: Chill until set.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3492,"Steak & Roasted Vegetable Salad","PT45M","PT0S","PT45M","Make and share this Steak & Roasted Vegetable Salad recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,104.7,1.1,0.3,0.9,648.0,21.6,7.3,13.2,4.5,"4.0","Steak & Roasted Vegetable Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 4250 F. 2: Lightly spray 15-x 10-inch jellyroll pan with cooking spray. 3: Place vegetables in pan. 4: Generously spray vegetables with cooking spray. 5: Combine seasoning ingredients, drizzle over vegetables. 6: Roast in 4250 F oven 30 to 35 minutes or until tender, stirring once. Meanwhile, heat large nonstick skillet over medium bent until ho t. To serve, place beef steaks in skillet; cook 12 to 15 minutes for medium rare to medium doneness, turning once. Let stand 10 minutes. 7: Season steaks with salt. Trim fat from steaks; carve crosswise into thin slices. 8: To serve, place an equal amount of salad greens on each of four dinner plates. 9: Arrange beef and roasted vegetables over salad greens. 10: Serve immediately with dressing.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3493,"Gingerbread Cake","PT40M","PT15M","PT55M","Make and share this Gingerbread Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,196.8,4.5,2.6,25.7,290.6,37.6,0.6,16.8,2.4,"12.0","Gingerbread Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat brown sugar, butter or margarine, and orange rind until smooth, using an electric mixer. 2: Beat in egg and egg white, beating well after each addition. 3: Add applesauce, molasses and ginger; mixing until smooth. 4: Combine flour, baking  soda, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to sugar mixture; beating 2 to 3 minutes. 5: Bake in 8-inch square cake pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in centre comes out clean. 6: Serve warm or cold.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3494,"Low-Fat Cherry Sake Dressing","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Low-Fat Cherry Sake Dressing recipe from Food.com.","Salad Dressings",4.0,1.0,259.6,0.6,0.1,0.0,5.7,55.0,5.8,43.8,3.1,"0.0","Low-Fat Cherry Sake Dressing Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients in 3-qt. saucepan. 2: Boil 15 minutes to reduce liquid by half. 3: Transfer to 1-qt. stainless-steel bowl; cool in ice-water bath  to about 40F. 4: Blend chilled dressing in food processor fitted with metal blade until smooth, about 30 seconds.");
