INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3536,"Bayrischer Leberkaese","PT1H30M","PT0S","PT1H30M","Make and share this Bayrischer Leberkaese recipe from Food.com.","German",0.0,0.0,6676.2,466.6,192.0,2249.5,26714.3,21.4,4.0,6.5,597.8,"0.0","Bayrischer Leberkaese Recipe Instructions:  1: Put all meats through meat grinder. 2: DO THIS IN PORTIONS:  In large bowl, mix a portion of the meat with salt and water until you have a smooth thick mass. 3: When you have all meat mixed with the salt and water, mix the entire mass  very well. 4: Let rest in refrigerator for an hour. 5: Chop onion very  fine, then with the remainder of the ingredients mix into the meat mixture.  Put in well greased baking loaf form. 6: Push down and bake at 350F for 1 1/2 hours.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3537,"Muesli Cookies","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Muesli Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",0.0,0.0,4435.4,216.9,130.4,534.3,3732.8,615.2,46.7,312.3,58.3,"1.0","Muesli Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter, sugar and honey. 2: Combine the remaining ingredients and mix into the butter. 3: Place spoonfuls of the mixture on a greased baking sheet and bake at 1900C (3740F) for 15-20 minutes. 4: Cool on baking sheet so cookies become crisp. 5: These store very well in an airtight tin.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3538,"Spiced Beer Cake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Spiced Beer Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,2816.9,8.6,1.5,0.0,1580.3,638.1,54.1,311.7,60.1,"1.0","Spiced Beer Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve sugar in beer. 2: Sift flour, spices and baking soda into beer and mix until smooth. 3: Pour into greased baking tin and bake at 1900C (3740F) for 45-60 minutes. 4: Slice thinly and serve with cold butter on top. 5: Also great for cake-mix:  Mix everything except beer and put into a plastic bag labeled \ 6: . 7: :-)   //Klaus");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3539,"Chicken Dish","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chicken Dish recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",3.0,2.0,387.4,31.6,13.8,136.8,158.5,2.8,0.1,0.7,22.5,"16.0","Chicken Dish Recipe Instructions:  1: Divide the chicken into serving pieces and on the base of a shallow greased oven dish. 2: Blend all the other together except the parsley and pour over the chicken. 3: Place in a moderate oven until the sauce is lightly browned about 20 minutes. 4: Served garnished with parsley and bananas cooked in butter.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3540,"Caramel Apple Pie With Crunchy Crumb Topping","PT55M","PT45M","PT1H40M","Make and share this Caramel Apple Pie With Crunchy Crumb Topping recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,18.0,607.1,19.7,7.2,20.3,329.9,105.5,4.6,72.4,6.9,"0.0","Caramel Apple Pie With Crunchy Crumb Topping Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine flour, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon; spread into an ungreased 8-in. square baking pan. 2: Bake at 400 F for 6-8 minutes or until golden brown. 3: Cool; crumble and set aside. Sprinkle apples with lemon juice. Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon; toss with apples. 4: Place apples in pie shell. 5: Cut a circle of foil to cover apples but not the edge of pastry; place over pie. Bake at 425 F for 10 minutes. 6: Reduce heat to 375 F; bake for 35 minutes or until apples are tender. 7: Meanwhile, in a saucepan over low heat, melt caramels with milk , stirring frequently. 8: Remove foil from pie. Pour caramel mixture over apples. 9: Sprinkle with topping; return to the oven for 5 minutes. 10: Serve warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3541,"Breakfast Sausage Rolls","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Breakfast Sausage Rolls recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",5.0,1.0,3848.5,310.2,117.8,1513.7,7813.0,22.2,3.3,9.9,230.8,"1.0","Breakfast Sausage Rolls Recipe Instructions:  1: Allow dough to rise until nearly doubled. 2: Cook and crumble sausage. Add mushrooms and onions. 3: Cook and stir until sausage is brown and vegetables are tender. 4: Drain and cool. 5: Beat 1 egg and set aside. Add to sausage mixture 2 eggs, cheese and seasonings. 6: Roll each loaf of dough into a 16x12 inch rectangle. Spread each loaf with 1/2 sausage mixture, to within 1 inch of edges. 7: Roll up, starting at narrow end, seal edges. 8: Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350''F for 25 minutes; brush with beaten egg. 9: Bake at 5-10 minutes longer or until golden brown. 10: Serve warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3542,"Mom''s Apple Crisp","PT35M","PT10M","PT45M","Make and share this Mom''s Apple Crisp recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,58.0,561.6,24.4,14.8,61.0,217.0,85.8,6.0,57.6,4.3,"4.0","Mom''s Apple Crisp Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel apples and remove cores. 2: Slice apples into thin slices and put into lightly greased casserole dish. 3: Mix sugar and flour together. 4: Cut in butter until you have course crumbs. 5: Stir in oats and pour over apples. 6: Bake at 350°F for 35 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3543,"Fresh Fruit Crisp","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Fresh Fruit Crisp recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,1.0,415.9,12.6,7.5,30.5,95.3,77.4,6.8,56.5,3.1,"0.0","Fresh Fruit Crisp Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all dry ingredients but the granulated sugar in a food processor. 2: Cut the butter in smallish pieces - no need to soften. 3: Blend in food processor until butter is in small pieces and is well mixed. 4: Peel, core and slice fruit to make 5-6 cups. 5: Place fruit in a 10x6x2 baking dish an sprinkle with granulated sugar. 6: Cover fruit with crumb mixture.  Bake at 350 for 40-45 minutes. 7: Serve warm with ice cream - it''s great!! Enjoy!");
