INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3545,"Concord Grape Pie","PT35M","PT0S","PT35M","Make and share this Concord Grape Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,6.0,396.2,13.8,5.6,15.2,209.5,67.1,2.0,46.8,3.3,"8.0","Concord Grape Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Squeeze the end of each grape opposite the stem to separate skins from pulp. 2: Set skins aside. Place pulp in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil. 3: Boil and stir for 1 minute. Press through a strainer or food mill to remove seeds. 4: Combine pulp, skins, sugar, flour, lemon juice and salt; pour into pastry shell. 5: Combine oats, brown sugar and flour; cut in butter until crumbly. 6: Sprinkle over filling. 7: Cover edges of pastry with foil. 8: Bake at 425°F for 15 minutes. 9: Remove foil; bake 20 minutes more or until golden brown. 10: Cool on a wire rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3546,"Tiny Chocolate Cones","0","PT0S","PT0S","My neighbour made these for her little boy''s birthday, they were a great hit, she left out the nuts and mixed in Hundreds and Thousands.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,64.6,6.8,3.3,3.9,9.0,2.4,1.3,0.2,1.1,"0.0","Tiny Chocolate Cones Recipe Instructions:  1: To make the cones:- Cut twenty-five 9cm foil squares. 2: Fold each diagonally in half to make a triangle.  Hold each triangle with the long side towards you. 3: Bring lower right point over to meet top point.  Roll left side of foil around right side to form a cone with a tight point at the bottom; secure with tape.  Repeat with the other squares. 4: Place chocolate and butter in a medium bowl. 5: Heat, covered on HIGH 2 - 2 1/2 minutes, or until melted. 6: Remove from microwave and stir until smooth. 7: Stir in cream and vanilla. 8: Set the bowl over iced water; beat mixture until fluffy. 9: Fold in nuts, keeping 1 Tbsp. 10: Spoon the mixture in a  piping bag fitted with a medium star tube; pipe into foil cones. 11: Sprinkle with reserved nuts. 12: Put in the refrigerator for a least 1 hour or until set. Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 13: New Zealand.");
