INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3551,"Sweetheart  Apple Crisp for Two","PT25M","PT15M","PT40M","Make and share this Sweetheart  Apple Crisp for Two recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",3.0,2.0,170.4,0.6,0.1,0.0,2.9,40.6,5.5,21.9,3.1,"2.0","Sweetheart  Apple Crisp for Two Recipe Instructions:  1: Add apples to an oven proof baking dish. 2: Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg to taste. 3: Next, drizzle the 1 teaspoon honey over the top of the apples and seasonings. 4: TOPPING: 5: Mix together the whole wheat flour, honey, and real vanilla extract. 6: Spread topping mixture over the apples, seasonings and honey. 7: Place in 300 degree Fahrenheit oven and bake until a toothpick comes out clean. 8: Great with French vanilla ice cream or topped with whipped cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3552,"Jewish Apple Cake","PT1H","PT20M","PT1H20M","Make and share this Jewish Apple Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,14.0,792.5,30.3,4.4,93.0,320.2,125.0,4.7,83.4,8.4,"0.0","Jewish Apple Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat together until smooth--flour, 2 1/2 cups of sugar, baking powder, salt, vanilla, oil, eggs, and juice. Then in a separate bowl, mix apples, cinnamon, and sugar. 2: Layer the batter and apples in a greased tube pan. 3: **pour some batter--then layer it with apples--then switch back and forth until it is all used up**. 4: Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours to 1 3/4 hours.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3553,"Spumoni Slices (Neapolitan Cookies)","PT5M","PT0S","PT5M","Make and share this Spumoni Slices (Neapolitan Cookies) recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,1.0,50.0,3.0,1.6,8.0,20.3,5.5,0.2,2.5,0.6,"0.0","Spumoni Slices (Neapolitan Cookies) Recipe Instructions:  1: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. 2: Beat in egg and vanilla. 3: Gradually add flour and mix well. 4: Divide dough into three portions. 5: Stir chocolate into one portion; mix well. 6: Add pecans and green food coloring to the second portion. 7: Add cherries, almond extract and red food coloring to the third. 8: Roll each portion between two pieces of waxed paper into and 8x6-inch rectangle.  Remove waxed paper. 9: Place chocolate rectangle on a piece of plastic wrap. 10: Top with the green and pink rectangles; press together lightly. 11: Wrap with plastic wrap and chill overnight.  Cut chilled dough in half lengthwise. Return one rectangle to the refrigerator. 12: Cut remaining rectangle into 1/8 inch slices. 13: Place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheets. 14: Bake at 375 for 5-7 minutes or until set.  Cool for 2 minutes before removing to wire racks. 15: Repeat with remaining dough. 16: Note:  for another good and highly reviewed Neapolitan Cookie recipe, take a look at recipe number 47503.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3554,"Shrimp Linguine","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Shrimp Linguine recipe from Food.com.","Healthy",4.5,11.0,398.2,5.0,0.8,115.2,129.6,60.3,2.8,2.1,26.4,"6.0","Shrimp Linguine Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook linguine according to package directions, but do not add salt. Drain in a  colander. 2: Meanwhile, in a large skillet, combine broth, lemon juice, and bay  leaf. 3: Bring mixture to a boil over medium-high heat. Add shrimp; cook, covered,  until shrimp just turn pink, about 2 minutes. 4: Remove shrimp from skillet; cover  to keep warm. 5: Reserve poaching liquid. 6: In another skillet, heat oil over medium  heat. Add onion, garlic, and tomato paste; cook, stirring frequently, for 5  minutes. 7: Add reserved poaching liquid; cook until mixture thickens slightly,  about 3 minutes. 8: Remove bay leaf. 9: Add shrimp to skillet. Cook, stirring  constantly, until heated through, about 1 minute. Stir in basil and pepper. 10: Place linguine on a serving platter. 11: Spoon sauce over top. 12: Serve immediately. 13: Shelly''s cooking tip: To shell uncooked shrimp, start at the large end and peel away the shell. 14: The tail fin may or may not be left on the shrimp, depending on the desired effect http://members.xoom.com/shellyskit/index.htm Shelly''s Kitchen We have 100+ recipes");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3555,"Cheese-Topped Vegetables","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cheese-Topped Vegetables recipe from Food.com.","Cauliflower",3.0,1.0,98.1,3.0,0.9,3.6,163.6,11.2,2.4,2.9,7.8,"6.0","Cheese-Topped Vegetables Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400: F. 2: In a large saucepan, bring 2 quarts of water to a boil. 3: Add broccoli and cauliflower. 4: Cook for 3 minutes. 5: Add carrot and cook for 2  minutes. 6: Drain vegetables in a colander. 7: Place mixture in a 2 quart baking dish. 8: Stir in peas; set aside. To prepare the sauce, in a small saucepan, heat oil  over medium heat. Add flour; cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute. Gradually  whisk in milk and broth. 9: Bring to a boil and cook, whisking frequently, for 3  minutes. 10: Remove from heat. Stir in = cup of cheddar and the pepper. 11: Pour sauce  over vegeta bles; stir until coated. 12: Sprinkle remaining cheddar over top. 13: Bake  until cheese is bubbling, about 5 minutes. 14: Serve immediately.");
