INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3699,"Five Cup Salad II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Five Cup Salad II recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",0.0,0.0,1412.3,104.1,78.9,101.2,194.9,121.1,20.4,68.0,17.2,"0.0","Five Cup Salad II Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine ingredients, mix lightly. 2: Chill.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3700,"Ribbon Fudge","0","PT40M","PT40M","Make and share this Ribbon Fudge recipe from Food.com.","Candy",0.0,0.0,2027.2,86.2,25.3,17.9,848.0,307.1,6.4,266.3,18.2,"0.0","Ribbon Fudge Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1/3 cup milk in heavy saucepan. 2: Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. 3: Continue boiling 4 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. 4: Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted. 5: Add 1 cup Marsh-  mallow Creme and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; beat until well blended. 6: Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. 7: Repeat with remaining ingredients, substituting peanut butter for chocolate pieces. 8: Spread over chocolate layer. 9: Cool at room temperature; cut into squares. 10: Makes 3 pounds.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3701,"Funnel Cakes","PT13M","PT4M","PT17M","Make and share this Funnel Cakes recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,38.0,857.3,76.9,11.4,70.5,308.7,34.9,1.1,0.2,8.4,"0.0","Funnel Cakes Recipe Instructions:  1: In mixing bowl combine eggs and milk. 2: Sift together flour, baking powder and  salt. Add to egg mixture; beat smooth. 3: In deep skillet heat oil to 360 degrees. 4: Covering spout with finger, pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel. 5: Remove finger and  release batter into oil in a spiral, starting in center and winding out. Fry  until golden about 3 minutes. 6: Turn carefully, cook 1 minute more. Drain on paper towel, dust with powdered sugar.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3702,"Authentic Sauerbraten","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Authentic Sauerbraten recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.0,3.0,478.0,30.5,10.9,142.1,265.5,8.7,0.6,2.9,38.5,"10.0","Authentic Sauerbraten Recipe Instructions:  1: Place the beef roast in a deep ceramic or glass bowl. Add onions, peppercorns,  cloves, and bay leaf. Pour white vinegar and cider vinegar over the meat;  chill, covered, for 4 days. Turn meat twice each day. 2: Remove the meat from the marinade, dry it well with paper towels, and strain the marinade into a  bowl. Reserve onions and 1 cup marinade. 3: In a Dutch oven brown the meat on  all sides in hot vegetable oil. 4: Sprinkle meat with salt. Pour boiling water  around the meat. sprinkle in crushed gingersna ps, and simmer covered for 1  1/2 hours. Turn often. 5: Add 1 cup of reserved marinade and cook meat 2 hours  or more, until tender. 6: Remove the meat and keep it warm. Strain the cooking  juices into a large saucepan. 7: In a small bowl mix sour cream with flour. Stir  it into the cooking juices and cook, stirring, until sauce is thickened and  smooth. 8: Slice meat in 1/4 inch slices; add to hot gravy. 9: Arrange meat on a  heated plater and pour extra sauce over it.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3704,"Whole-Berry Cranberry Sauce","PT15M","PT5M","PT20M","Make and share this Whole-Berry Cranberry Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Sauces",5.0,40.0,165.7,0.1,0.0,0.0,3.1,43.1,3.7,36.5,0.3,"0.0","Whole-Berry Cranberry Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan. 2: Bring to a boil, cover, then turn to medium heat. 3: Continue cooking until all the berries pop. 4: Remove from heat and let cool. 5: Refrigerate until cold, or  serve warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3705,"Pacific Rim Glazed Flank Steak","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pacific Rim Glazed Flank Steak recipe from Food.com.","Steak",5.0,6.0,542.5,19.3,7.0,137.8,2852.3,38.8,0.6,35.9,51.6,"0.0","Pacific Rim Glazed Flank Steak Recipe Instructions:  1: In medium shallow dish, combine marinade ingredients, adding pepper, as desired; whisk until blended. 2: Remove and reserve 3/4 cup for basting. 3: With sharp knife, lightly score both sides of beef steak in a crisscross pattern. 4: Place steak in remaining marinade in dish, turning to coat. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes, turning once. Remove steak from marinade; discard marinade. Place steak on grid over medium, ash-covered coals. 5: Grill, uncovered, 17 to 21 minutes for medium rare to medium doneness, basting occasionally with reserved 3/4 cup marinade and turning once. Place remaining basting marinade in s mall saucepan; place on grid of grill and bring to a boil. 6: Meanwhile carve steak diagonally across the grain into thin slices; arrange on platter. 7: Spoon hot marinade over beef, as desired. 8: Garnish with orange slices and rosemary sprigs. 9: Tip: To broil, place steak on rack in broiler pan so surface of meat is 2 to 3 inches from heat. Broil 13 to 18 minutes, basting occasionally with reserved 3/4 marinade and turning once.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3706,"Cream of Soup Mix With Variations - Substitute","0","PT5M","PT5M","Make and share this Cream of Soup Mix With Variations - Substitute recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.5,5.0,181.1,7.7,4.8,27.9,144.9,20.1,0.1,11.2,7.7,"0.0","Cream of Soup Mix With Variations - Substitute Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients and store in covered container. Mix 1/3 cup dry mix with 1 1/4 cup cold water. 2: Cook stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Cook 2 more minutes. 3: Variations: 4: Mushroom Soup: Add 1/2 cup finely chopped mushrooms.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3707,"Light Fiesta Chicken Breasts","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Light Fiesta Chicken Breasts recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",0.0,0.0,706.9,19.3,10.5,214.7,1300.9,61.6,0.9,3.8,65.9,"4.0","Light Fiesta Chicken Breasts Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook fettuccine according to package directions. 2: Drain well and transfer to serving platter; keep warm. 3: Meanwhile, melt butter in large skillet over medium heat. Add chicken; cook 4 to 5 minutes per side or until golden brown and cooked through. 4: Place chicken over fettuccine. Top with pepper strips; keep warm. 5: Add green onions to drippings in skillet; cook 1 minute. Add flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. 6: Add broth, milk and wine; heat to a boil and cook until thickened, stirring constantly. 7: Add cheese; stir until melt ed. 8: Pour evenly over chicken, peppers and fettuccine; sprinkle with cilantro.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3708,"Blueberry-Oatmeal Muffins","PT25M","PT10M","PT35M","Make and share this Blueberry-Oatmeal Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,107.0,164.1,4.5,0.9,0.4,234.0,27.3,1.5,11.8,4.2,"0.0","Blueberry-Oatmeal Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 400F. 2: Line 12 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2x1 1/2 inches, with paper baking cups, or grease bottoms only of muffin cups. 3: Mix all ingredients except blueberries just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy). Fold in blueberries. 4: Divide batter evenly among muffin cups. 5: Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. 6: Immediately remove from pan. 7: High Altitude (3500-6500 ft): Heat oven to 425F. Decrease brown sugar to 1/3 cup. Bake about 20 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3711,"A-To-Z Bread","PT1H","PT20M","PT1H20M","An extremely versatile bread. Very moist and delicious. It''s a great way to use up odd and ends of frozen berries.","Quick Breads",5.0,22.0,367.0,19.5,2.5,34.9,261.0,44.4,1.3,25.4,4.7,"16.0","A-To-Z Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: In a mixing bowl, combine the sugar, oil and eggs; mix well. 2: Stir in A-to-Z ingredients of your choice and vanilla. 3: Combine flour cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt; stir into liquid ingredients just until moistened. Stir in nuts. 4: Pour into two greased 8-in. x 4-in. x 2-in. loaf  pans. Bake at 325 F for 55-65 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3712,"Rich Chocolate Truffles","PT1H","PT45M","PT1H45M","I made these one year and gave them as Christmas gifts. They were the most popular presents I ever gave! I can''t remember yield and times exactly now so they are a guess with cook time being chill time.","Candy",4.0,1.0,264.7,20.9,12.3,32.8,37.2,22.6,1.9,19.3,1.8,"24.0","Rich Chocolate Truffles Recipe Instructions:  1: In saucepan, combine whipping cream & butter. 2: Cook over medium heat,  stirring constantly, just until mixture boils; remove from heat. Stir in  chocolates until melted; continue stirring until mixture cools & thickens  slightly. 3: Stir in vanilla. 4: Pour into shallow glass dish. 5: Cover; chill until  firm. 6: With spoon scoop mixture into 1 inch balls. 7: Coating  Melt chocolate & shortening over low heat; stirring constantly. 8: (use 1  Tbsp of shortening for every 6 oz. of chocolate). 9: When mixture is smooth  remove from heat. Dip each truffle into coating. 10: (I found dr opping them  in the chocolate & then fishing them out with a spoon worked best. But work quickly or they will melt) Then either place them on foil or in foil candy papers & allow to  harden. 11: Mix powdered sugar & milk. 12: Drizzle over  truffles in various designs.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3714,"Microwave Truffles","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Microwave Truffles recipe from Food.com.","Candy",0.0,0.0,976.2,81.1,42.7,101.8,187.3,75.0,8.4,62.6,7.3,"0.0","Microwave Truffles Recipe Instructions:  1: Place 24 small foil candy cups in miniature  muffin cups or on a baking sheet. Spoon 1/2 teaspoon pecans into each; set cups and remaining pecans aside. 2: In a 2-qt. microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate and butter. Microwave at 50% power for 1-1/2 to 2 minutes or until melted. 3: Stir in cream and extract. Beat with an electric mixer until slightly thickened, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. 4: Immediately pour into prepared cups. Top with remaining pecans. Refrigerate until set. 5: /");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3715,"Wine Jelly","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Wine Jelly recipe from Food.com.","Jellies",4.0,3.0,3051.8,0.0,0.0,0.0,29.4,711.1,0.0,701.9,0.3,"0.0","Wine Jelly Recipe Instructions:  1: Stir wine and sugar together, set aside for 10 minutes. 2: Stirring occasionally. 3: Stir water and Certo together and then stir into wine mixture. Stir constantly for 3 minutes, then fill jelly jars to within 1/2\ 4: ,  5: ,  6: ,  7: ,  8: Tip: I have found this works best if you heat the wine and sugar while stirring. I couldn''t get the sugar to dissolve until I did.  I also filled the jars with hot water while making the jelly so they were warm when I filled them. This seemed to help the lids seal better.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3716,"Ginger Shortbread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Ginger Shortbread recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,115.7,7.8,4.9,20.3,54.7,10.5,0.3,2.5,1.2,"0.0","Ginger Shortbread Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine icing sugar, flour and ginger. 2: Cut in butter. 3: Mix together with your hands, as per a pie crust. When mixture holds together work in candied ginger. 4: Press into an ungreased 9-inch square pan, about 1/2-inch thick. 5: Prick through to bottom of the dough with a fork. 6: Bake at 300 degrees F for 50-60 minutes. 7: While warm, cut into desired shapes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3717,"Garlic Mashed Potatoes II","0","PT5M","PT5M","Make and share this Garlic Mashed Potatoes II recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,2.0,435.1,10.8,6.6,29.9,113.2,76.2,8.6,3.1,11.2,"4.0","Garlic Mashed Potatoes II Recipe Instructions:  1: Separate the garlic cloves and cook in boiling water for 2 mins; cool and peel. 2: Melt butter in heavy based saucepan and add peeled garlic.  Cover and cook on  low heat until tender but not browned. 3: Meanwhile cook potatoes for 20 mins, or  until tender. 4: Remove butter-garlic mixture from the heat and stir in flour. 5: Return to heat and cook 1 minute. Remove from heat again and stir in hot milk  and pepper. 6: Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, stirring all the  time. Push sauce through a sieve or blend until smooth,  return to heat and  simmer 2 minutes. 7: Drain and mash potatoes, and combine with sauce.  Serve with  any roast or poultry.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3718,"Honeyed Beef Stew","PT2H30M","PT15M","PT2H45M","Make and share this Honeyed Beef Stew recipe from Food.com.","Stew",4.5,4.0,150.0,7.5,1.0,0.0,289.3,21.1,3.5,15.3,2.1,"0.0","Honeyed Beef Stew Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 180°C. 2: Heat the oil in a flameproof casserole. 3: Add the beef  and fry briskly on all sides. 4: Add the vegetables and  fry a further 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. 5: Mix the remaining ingredients in a bowl, and stir into  casserole. 6: Cover and cook for 2 - 2 1/2 hours  or until meat is tender.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3719,"Clementine Beef","PT2H30M","PT0S","PT2H30M","Make and share this Clementine Beef recipe from Food.com.","Meat",0.0,0.0,60.5,0.2,0.1,0.1,117.5,13.5,1.9,4.7,1.6,"6.0","Clementine Beef Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut the beef into cubes and coat in the flour. 2: Melt dripping in a pan, add the beef and fry quickly until browned on all sides. 3: Stir in any remaining flour, then add the carrots and onions. 4: Mix the orange juice and cider together in a measuring jug and make up to 3/4 pint with water. 5: Stir into pan with the orange rind, stock cube and salt and pepper to taste.  Bring to the boil, cover and simmer 2 - 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3722,"Corn Chowder IV","PT45M","PT10M","PT55M","Make and share this Corn Chowder IV recipe from Food.com.","Chowders",5.0,2.0,463.8,29.8,18.2,100.0,74.6,47.2,5.4,1.3,7.7,"6.0","Corn Chowder IV Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter in soup kettle and saute onion until limp. 2: Add potatoes and water to kettle, season with salt and pepper, and bring to a boil. 3: Simmer over medium heat until potatoes are tender, about 30-40 minutes. 4: Add corn and cream. 5: Heat, stirring frequently, for ten minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3723,"Fresh Fruit Smoothies","0","PT5M","PT5M","Make and share this Fresh Fruit Smoothies recipe from Food.com.","Smoothies",5.0,8.0,290.6,1.1,0.2,0.0,8.5,73.5,6.4,51.9,2.5,"0.0","Fresh Fruit Smoothies Recipe Instructions:  1: Clean the strawberries and remove the stems. 2: Peel the bananas and break it  into chunks. 3: Place the strawberries and the bananas into a blender. 4: Then add  the fruit juice, ice cubes, and the honey. 5: Place the lid on the blender. 6: Fold a kitchen towel over the blender so that  it drapes over the top. 7: Turn the blender on high and blend the shake until  smooth. 8: Always keep your hand over the lid so that it doesn''t come off.");
