INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3725,"Gumdrop Cookies","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Gumdrop Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",4.5,3.0,6252.5,283.7,106.3,558.0,3184.4,882.3,31.7,529.5,65.0,"1.0","Gumdrop Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream together sugars and shortening. 2: Add eggs and vanilla. 3: Sift dry ingredients and add with coconut, oatmeal and cut-up gumdrops. 4: Mix well. 5: Drop by small spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.  Bake 350 degrees 8-10 min. 6: Remove from pan right away and cool on rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3726,"My Husband''s Favorite Carrot Cake","PT35M","PT15M","PT50M","Hi,this is a recipe that I used and my husband said it''s the best carrot cake he''s ever had. I hope this works for you.","Dessert",4.5,6.0,1018.5,74.7,19.8,154.7,658.6,81.7,3.8,53.9,9.8,"8.0","My Husband''s Favorite Carrot Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350F and grease and flour baking pan. 2: Blend sugar and oil. 3: Add eggs,one at a time. 4: Add flour,carrots,cinnamon and nuts. 5: Mix thoroughly. 6: Pour into prepared pan. 7: Bake for 30-35 minutes. 8: Cream butter and cheese. 9: Add sugar,one cup at a time. 10: Add nuts and vanilla. 11: Mix well.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3727,"Spicy Apple-Stuffed Squash","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Spicy Apple-Stuffed Squash recipe from Food.com.","Apple",4.0,2.0,93.0,2.1,1.3,5.0,21.1,19.9,2.8,7.0,1.0,"4.0","Spicy Apple-Stuffed Squash Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350-F degrees and lightly grease a 1-quart baking dish. 2: Halve  squash, remove seeds, and cut into quarters. 3: Place quarters skin-side up in dish and bake, covered, for 30 minutes. 4: Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine apple,  butter, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves. 5: Turn the squash''s cut sides  up and stuff them with the apple mix ture. Cover and bake for 30 minutes longer,  or until apples are tender. 6: Serve warm. 7: Kitchen Staff Tip: If you''re in a pinch for time, you may prepare this recipe in the microwave by preparing the squash as directed, placing cut-side up in a  microwave- safe dish, and cooking on high for 6 or 7 minutes. 8: Make sure to  rotate the squash halfway through cooking time. Top squash with the apple  mixture, cover with vented plastic wrap, and microwave on high 4 to 5 minutes or until apples are tender.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3728,"Spanish Croquetas With Jamon Serrano","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Often served as tapas, croquetas are a favorite throughout Spain.  I use jamsn serrano in almost all my food now, and it is particularly tasty in these hot tapas.  Also perfect with your favorite beer.
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3730,"Hot Spicy, Southwestern Buffalo Wings","PT45M","PT0S","PT45M","Make and share this Hot Spicy, Southwestern Buffalo Wings recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",5.0,3.0,1341.0,138.2,24.3,128.4,189.1,0.0,0.0,0.0,27.0,"8.0","Hot Spicy, Southwestern Buffalo Wings Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut off tips and separate each wing at the joint. Sprinkle wings with salt and pepper to taste. Heat oil in deep fryer or large heavy pot. When it is quite hot, add half the wings and cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. 2: When wings are golden brown and crisp, remove them and drain well. 3: Add remaining wings and repeat process. 4: Meanwhile, melt butter in saucepan, add hot sauce and vinegar to taste. Pour hot sauce over wings and mix well to cover. 5: Serve with Blue Cheese Dressing and celery sticks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3731,"Chicken & Lime Soup","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chicken & Lime Soup recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,5.0,1014.3,24.6,9.2,184.3,2255.3,89.2,11.6,27.1,110.8,"0.0","Chicken & Lime Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Poach chicken breasts then shred. 2: Combine stock, lime juice, oregano, basil, pureed chipotle and bay leaf in stockpot. Season to taste with salt and white pepper. 3: Bring to boil. 4: Simmer 15 minutes. 5: Add shredded chicken, tomatoes, red onion and cilantro. 6: Bring to boil. 7: Simmer 5 minutes. 8: Adjust seasonings to taste. Ladle very hot soup into warm soup bowls. 9: Drop in cheese cubes. 10: Garnish each serving with a few baked tortilla strips, lime slices, non-fat sour cream and cilantro sprig.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3732,"Beef Chow Mein","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Beef Chow Mein recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.0,2.0,342.7,13.6,4.8,124.5,1357.6,28.3,3.3,8.2,27.9,"4.0","Beef Chow Mein Recipe Instructions:  1: Slice beef about 1 inch long 1/2 inch wide and as thin as possible. Mix the salt, sugar and soy sauce together and mix well, then ad the beef and marinate for at least one hour, longer for more flavor. 2: Wash and slice the mushrooms, including stems. 3: Slice the bamboo into thin strips; slice the scallions into 1 inch pieces; soak, rinse and drain the bean sprouts. 4: In a separate bowl, mix the cornstarch and beef stock together. 5: Drain the beef reserving the marinade. Heat the sesame oil and stir fry the beef for 4 to 5 minutes. 6: Ad the cornstarch mixture and remaining marinade, bring to a boil stirring constantly; ad the vegetables and simmer for 5 minutes longe r. 7: Cook noodles in boiling water for 4 to 5 minutes; drain thoroughly. 8: Deep fry as needed draining on absorbent paper. 9: Beat the egg adding 1 tablespoon water and pour onto lightly oiled skillet. Make a small thin omelet and slice into thin strips. 10: Place cooked noodles on hot dish, top with beef mixture and garnish with the strips of omelet. Makes 4 servings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3733,"Cheesy Mushroom Canapes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cheesy Mushroom Canapes recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,162.5,7.2,4.1,18.6,296.9,17.7,1.1,0.3,6.7,"0.0","Cheesy Mushroom Canapes Recipe Instructions:  1: In a saucepan, melt butter. 2: Add mushrooms and cook gently 2 minutes. 3: Add flour and stir into mushroom mixture. Add cheese, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Stir well and heat through gently 2 minutes or until mixture begins to melt. Remove from heat and season to taste with pepper. 4: Preheat broiler. 5: Toast bread on one side only. 6: Spread cheese and mushroom mixture on untoasted sides. 7: Broil in preheated broiler 3-4 minutes or until melted and bubbling. 8: Cut slices in half and sprinkle liberally with parsley and paprika. 9: Garnish with parsley sprigs, if desired, and serve hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3734,"Rice with Roasted Red Peppers, Black Olives & Feta","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Rice with Roasted Red Peppers, Black Olives & Feta recipe from Food.com.","White Rice",5.0,6.0,226.9,4.5,1.4,5.6,146.7,41.4,1.8,2.4,5.0,"6.0","Rice with Roasted Red Peppers, Black Olives & Feta Recipe Instructions:  1: Charbroil the peppers - Position the rack so that the pan will be 6 inches from the heat. Preheat the broiler to high. 2: Place the pepper on a pan and broil, turning frequently (every 2 to 3 minutes), about 10 to 15 minutes or until charred on all sides. 3: Transfer the peppers to a paper or plastic bag or wrap in plastic wrap. Let stand until cool to touch. 4: Halve the pepper, core, seed, peel, and chop (into raisin size pieces). 5: Meanwhile steam the rice in an appropriate amount of liquid  for the cooker: yield about 3 cups. 6: In a small skillet, heat oil and saute the green onion until soft (3 to 4 minutes). Add garlic and soften (1 minute) and add parsley, lemon juice, sundried tomatoes, olives, black pepper and cook, stirring for 1 to 2 minutes, until the ingredients are heated through. 7: Toss the hot rice with the bell pepper. Serve hot with crumbled feta. 8: Refrigerate any leftovers and serve cold.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3735,"Hamburgers to Freeze","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Hamburgers to Freeze recipe from Food.com.","Kid Friendly",4.0,2.0,174.3,10.7,4.7,72.8,80.9,1.7,0.3,0.7,17.9,"0.0","Hamburgers to Freeze Recipe Instructions:  1: In large bowl, combine beef, onions, green pepper, egg, mustard, Worcestershire  sauce, pepper and hot pepper sauce. Mix until just combined, using spoon or  hands. 2: Divide mixture into 20 portions, shaping each into a round patty. 3: Place  on baking sheets and freeze until solid. 4: Stack with foil or paper plates between them and store in freezer bags and store up to 4 months in freezer.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3736,"Whiskey & Orange Punch","0","PT20M","PT20M","This is a recipe my mother has been been making for many, many (30 or more) years.  We all enjoy it, hope your do too.  pj","Punch Beverage",5.0,1.0,54.0,0.1,0.0,0.0,2.6,10.3,0.1,9.8,0.3,"0.0","Whiskey & Orange Punch Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix orange juice, lemonade and Southern Comfort together in a large punch bowl and let it sit for an hour or so. 2: When ready to serve, add the chilled 7-Up. 3: Garnish with orange slices and the frozen orange juice ring (this helps to keep the punch chilled - you could use frozen o.j. cubes instead). 4: *Mom uses less when there are going to be kids around - they really like this stuff.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3737,"Cheesy Chicken Rolls","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cheesy Chicken Rolls recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",2.0,1.0,154.4,2.0,0.6,67.0,102.4,4.2,0.6,2.3,28.9,"4.0","Cheesy Chicken Rolls Recipe Instructions:  1: For filling, in a small bowl combine cheese, mushrooms, the 1/4 cup yogurt, chives, parsley, and pimento. 2: Place 1 chicken breast half, boned side up, between 2 pieces of clear plastic wrap. 3: Working from the center to the edges, pound lightly with a meat mallet to 1/8\ 4: ,  5: ,  6: ,  7:  baking dish. 8: Combine bread crumbs and paprika. 9: Brush chicken with the 1 Tbs yogurt; sprin kle with crumb mixture. 10: Bake in 350 deg F. oven for 20-25 minutes or till chicken is tender and no longer pink.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3739,"Apple Orange Brownies","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apple Orange Brownies recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",5.0,1.0,322.5,13.8,6.1,46.6,323.7,47.2,1.5,29.0,4.3,"0.0","Apple Orange Brownies Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter and remove from heat.  Add brown sugar. Mix well.  Stir in apple  sauce, eggs, orange peel and vanilla. 2: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt  and baking soda. 3: Stir into apple sauce mixture.  Pour into a greased 9 inch x  13 inch pan. 4: Bake at 325 F for 30-40 minutes. 5: Cut into squares while still  warm and roll in icing sugar.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3740,"Light Soft Shell Chicken Tacos","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Light Soft Shell Chicken Tacos recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",0.0,0.0,397.7,15.1,7.3,63.9,865.5,38.3,3.5,5.6,27.1,"4.0","Light Soft Shell Chicken Tacos Recipe Instructions:  1: Place chicken in one layer in skillet; season with cumin. 2: Pour tomatoes and salsa over chicken. 3: Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes or until chicken is tender, turning once. Remove chicken; save liquid in skillet. Cool and shred chicken; add to skillet with green onion; cook 2 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed. 4: Divide chicken mixture evenly down center of each tortilla. 5: Top with shredded lettuce, chopped fresh tomato and cheese. Add cilantro; fold and serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3741,"Breakfast Pudding","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Breakfast Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",0.0,0.0,29.4,0.2,0.0,0.0,0.7,6.8,0.3,5.2,0.5,"6.0","Breakfast Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine the prunes and orange juice in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat. Remove from the heat, cover, and set aside for 30 minutes or longer. 2: Puree the prunes with all of the orange juice in two batches in a  food processor or blender. 3: Gently fold in the vanilla yogurt until blended. 4: Stir in the cinnamon and nutmeg. 5: Transfer to six 6-ounce custard cups. 6: Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3742,"A Real Philly Cheesesteak","PT15M","PT5M","PT20M","I come from Philly and now live in Alaska.  What they think is a Philly Cheese Steak involves green peppers and onions.  So if thats what you are looking for, then no dice.  If you want something similar to what they sell in every pizza place in the philly metro area, this is as close as you can get from outside the state","Lunch/Snacks",4.5,14.0,477.7,27.5,10.6,77.1,373.6,30.0,1.3,1.0,25.5,"4.0","A Real Philly Cheesesteak Recipe Instructions:  1: MEAT:  Make friends with your butcher.  You need him to partially freeze a hunk of Rib Eye, and then slice it very thin.  You want it sliced thin even though common sense tells us that thick is better.  You can buy the hunk of rib eye and freeze and slice it yourself, but the butcher generally does a better job than I do.  I can only get it about 1/8\ 2: ,  3: hero\ 4: Toppings: All of this is personal choice.  I like fried onions and mushrooms myself. 5: Cheeses used vary - I hate to admit it but I think cheese whiz tastes the best.  Provolone is awesome too and thats what I would use if I was afraid of the plastic orange stuff called whiz. 6: Cooking the steak: In a cast iron frying pan, or a grill pan heat some oil.  Saute toppings until pliable - make them however you like them.  Remove them from pan and set aside. 7: Pour some more oil in the pan (I use olive oil, but if you have access to the stuff they use in restaurants on grills it would taste even better) on medium high heat.  Place 1/4 to 1/3 of a pound of meat in the pan, lying the pieces flat and overlapping to form a shape that will fit nicely in a bun. 8: When the meat turns grey with doneness, flip it over and if you are using cheese slices now is the time to lie them on top of the meat.  Add the other toppings back into the pan next to the meat and allow to reheat.  Cover the pan to allow the cheese to melt.  This should take 1-2 minutes.  If the meat looks overcooked, thats ok - i t should be GRAY. 9: This is the time to toast the bread if you so wish.  I don''t like mine toasted at all.  Warmed is ok. 10: If you are using cheese whiz, warm it in the microwave. Pick up meat and melted cheese with a spatula and deposit on the roll.  IF using cheese whiz, use a butter knife or chopstick to smear whiz next to the meat. 11: Push the meat on one side of the roll and deposit the toppings next to it.  This is important because if you put the toppings ON the meat, they will not be in the bottom of the sandwich, which really sux. 12: You should get meat, toppings and cheese in every bite.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3743,"Easy Pineapple Pie","PT45M","PT10M","PT55M","Make and share this Easy Pineapple Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",4.5,9.0,321.9,13.7,3.2,69.8,183.7,47.7,0.6,40.5,3.4,"8.0","Easy Pineapple Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: * Substitute 1/2 cup packed brown sugar for 1/2 cup of the white sugar if  preferred. 2: Drain pineapple very well, reserving juice for other uses. 3: Cream butter and  sugar together until light and fluffy. 4: Add eggs and use a wire whisk to combine  thoroughly. 5: Add vanilla extract and drained pineapple; blend. 6: Pour into unbaked  9-inch pie shell and bake in preheated 350-deg ree oven for about 45 minutes. 7: Let cool for a few minutes before cutting, or serve cold.");
