INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3754,"Pineapple Posy Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pineapple Posy Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",0.0,0.0,1914.2,82.1,43.8,881.5,1065.7,265.8,3.8,247.1,36.9,"0.0","Pineapple Posy Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Soften gelatin in water at least 5 minutes. 2: Simmer pineapple juice in a  saucepan over low heat until it is reduced to  1/2 cup. Cool. 3: Beat egg yolks  into pineapple juice. Stir in gelatin and 1/2  cup sugar. 4: Place pineapple  mixture in the top of a double boiler. Cook for 10  minutes, stirring often. 5: Remove from heat. Stir in salt and orange peel. 6: Chill until mixture thickens,  but do not let it set. It usually takes about  45 minutes. 7: Beat egg whites  until frothy, then gradually add 1/4 cup sugar while  continuing to heat. Beat  until stiff peaks form. 8: Fold in whipped cream. 9: Fold  egg white mixture into  pineapple mixture, and spoon filling into cool pie  shell. Chill. 10: Garnish with 6 pineapple flowers made by arranging 5 pineapple tidbits  around a maraschino  cherry center.");
