INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3762,"Orange Tarragon Dressing","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Orange Tarragon Dressing recipe from Food.com.","Vegan",0.0,0.0,26.3,0.2,0.0,0.0,117.9,5.7,0.3,1.9,0.9,"6.0","Orange Tarragon Dressing Recipe Instructions:  1: Squeeze the garlic paste from the heads of roasted garlic into a blender. 2: Add the orange juice, mustard, vinegar, salt, and pepper and puree until smooth and creamy. 3: Add the tarragon and whirl briefly just to mix-there should be flecks of green throughout the golden dressing. 4: Set aside for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to marry. 5: Tightly sealed and refrigerated, the dressing will keep for about a week.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3763,"Parmesan Stuffed Tomatoes","PT10M","PT15M","PT25M","Make and share this Parmesan Stuffed Tomatoes recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,10.0,171.9,13.8,8.5,36.0,151.0,8.8,1.4,2.5,4.2,"8.0","Parmesan Stuffed Tomatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine bread crumbs with Parmesan, parsley, chives, tarragon, and pepper. 2: Mix onion, seasoned bread crumbs, and melted butter. 3: Cut tomatoes in half (horizontally) and seed them. 4: Fill with bread crumbs and bake in buttered baking dish for about ten minutes at 350 degrees. 5: Starting with room temperature tomatoes reduces cooking time and helps assure a firm tomato is served to guests.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3764,"Apple Cheese Phyllo Tart","0","PT20M","PT20M","Make and share this Apple Cheese Phyllo Tart recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,202.1,4.1,1.8,40.3,120.2,40.3,2.9,25.5,2.7,"6.0","Apple Cheese Phyllo Tart Recipe Instructions:  1: Place 2 sheets of phyllo in centre of a 9-inch pie plate, allowing edges to overhang. Brush lightly with butter. Repeat twice. 2: Spread bottom of phyllo with jam. 3: Whisk together cheese, 3 tablespoons sugar, lemon rind and egg; pour  over jam. 4: Combine apples with remaining sugar and cinnamon. Arrange apples over top of cheese layer. 5: Carefully roll and crumble overhanging edges of phyllo and tuck into pie plate, making a rim. 6: Bake at 375F for 45 to 55 minutes, or until apples are tender and cheese is set. Cool at room temperature; refrigerate.  Serve warm or cold.");
