INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3767,"Cheese Straws V","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cheese Straws V recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",0.0,0.0,4602.5,338.2,213.2,966.7,9108.7,244.5,8.5,3.4,147.7,"1.0","Cheese Straws V Recipe Instructions:  1: Grate cheese, add margarine, flour, salt and pepper and knead thoroughly. 2: Using one of the flat attachments to pastry tube, place on baking sheet in long strips. 3: Cut in desired lengths before baking. 4: Bake at 350 degrees until a delicate brown, about 10 minutes. 5: Remove from baking sheet with a spatula and place on paper towel until cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3768,"Apple Filled Acorn Squash","PT45M","PT0S","PT45M","Make and share this Apple Filled Acorn Squash recipe from Food.com.","Apple",5.0,32.0,285.9,10.5,1.4,0.0,56.8,50.5,5.5,24.3,3.5,"6.0","Apple Filled Acorn Squash Recipe Instructions:  1: COMBINE all ingredients except for squash. 2: Preheat oven to 350 deg F. 3: Cut squash in half lengthwise and scrape out  seeds. 4: Place cut side down in baking dish and bake for 25 minutes. 5: Mix the  other ingredients. 6: Turn squash cut side up, fill with apple mix and  continue baking for 20 minutes, or until squash is tender.");
