INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3795,"Cheese Bran Muffins","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cheese Bran Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",4.0,1.0,2168.7,104.4,34.8,342.4,3578.9,255.8,22.7,75.5,71.8,"0.0","Cheese Bran Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: In small bowl, combine cereal and buttermilk. 2: In medium bowl, beat egg until  frothy and stir in oil and cereal mixture. 3: In large bowl, combine remaining  ingredients. 4: Make a well in centre and pour batter into well. Stir to moisten.  Batter will be lumpy. 5: Fill greased muffin cups > full. Bake at 400 degrees for  20 to 25 minutes. TIP: Nice when served warm, but let stand 5 minutes first.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3797,"Dill-Lemon Rice","PT25M","PT5M","PT30M","Make and share this Dill-Lemon Rice recipe from Food.com.","Long Grain Rice",5.0,5.0,194.8,3.2,1.9,7.6,630.7,37.1,0.7,0.1,3.4,"0.0","Dill-Lemon Rice Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine rice, lemon peel, dill weed, salt and chicken bouillon in a large bowl and blend well. 2: Put into to a medium saucepan and add water and butter. 3: Bring to a boil over high heat; cover and reduce heat. 4: Cook for 15 to 25 minutes until liquid is absorbed.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3799,"Low-Fat Breakfast Brulee","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Low-Fat Breakfast Brulee recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",0.0,0.0,108.6,0.2,0.0,0.0,9.9,27.6,2.0,25.0,0.4,"6.0","Low-Fat Breakfast Brulee Recipe Instructions:  1: Divide berries among 6 custard cups. 2: Spread yogurt cheese evenly over berries. 3: Press brown sugar through sieve to get rid of any lumps. Sprinkle top  of each custard cup with about 2 Tbsp brown sugar. 4: Place custard cups on baking  sheet and broil for 1 to 2 minutes, watching carefully, until sugar melts and begins to brown (it burns very easily). Allow to rest for a few minutes until topping is firm, then serve immediately. 5: I estimate that three cups yogurt cheese is the result of draining the whey from 6 cups plain lowfat yogurt through a yogurt strainer, cheesecloth or a fine sieve overnight in a refrigerator.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3800,"Country Rice","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Make and share this Country Rice recipe from Food.com.","White Rice",4.5,3.0,66.9,0.3,0.1,0.6,31.0,13.9,0.7,0.5,1.7,"4.0","Country Rice Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring the stock to a boil with the green onion and pepper. 2: Add the rice; turn  down to a simmer and cover; cook for 20 minutes. 3: NOTE: If you want drier rice, remove the cover at 20 minutes and heat just a  minute or so longer. 4: VARIATIONS: Rice made with fish stock can be served with  fish, beef-stock rich with beef. 5: If you begin adding more vegetables, you will  end up with a jambalaya instead of a side course of Country Rice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3801,"Apple Cheese Crisp II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apple Cheese Crisp II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",3.0,2.0,3344.5,128.0,79.8,349.0,3802.5,532.7,26.2,402.3,41.4,"1.0","Apple Cheese Crisp II Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat over to 325 degrees. 2: Peel, core and slice apples. 3: Place apples into buttered 8 x 8 baking dish. 4: Combine sugar, brown sugar, lemon peel, cinnamon and coriander. 5: Sprinkle over apples. 6: Mix well with your hands. 7: Combine water/cider and lemon juice.  Sprinkle mixture over apples. 8: In medium bowl (or food processor) combine ingredients for topping. 9: Mix unt il crumbly. 10: Put topping over apples, patting down with your hands. 11: Bake for 55-60 minutes until mixture is golden brown and bubbles up in the center. 12: Serve warm with cream, whipped topping or ice cream. 13: (NOTE: ANY apples can be used in this.  It is a quick use for leftover eating apples such as Red Delicious.)");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3802,"Honey Fruitcake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Honey Fruitcake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,6503.8,262.3,78.3,802.0,2114.2,979.4,32.6,789.7,77.8,"1.0","Honey Fruitcake Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter, honey and eggs. 2: Combine dry ingredients and add alternately to  creamed mixture with whiskey. 3: Place in a well greased and paper lined loaf pan. 4: Bake in a preheated 350F oven until set ( about 1 1/2 to 2 hours ). Cool  completely and wrap in whiskey moistened cheesecloth and store airtight.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3803,"Honey Cheesecake","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Honey Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",5.0,4.0,416.0,33.6,20.6,184.4,297.5,21.2,0.1,19.0,9.4,"10.0","Honey Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Have ingredients at room temperature. Beat cream cheese smooth and fluffy. 2: Beat  in honey and vanilla. 3: Blend in eggs. 4: Pour into a  buttered and crumb lined  9 inch springform pan. 5: Place in a hot water bath. 6: Bake in a 350F oven until set ( about 1 1 /2 hours or less ). Remove from waterbath  to cool on rack. 7: Chill over night before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3804,"Biscuits and Sausage Gravy","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Biscuits and Sausage Gravy recipe from Food.com.","Breads",5.0,5.0,855.7,70.6,29.1,163.8,2070.7,23.2,0.4,0.1,31.0,"0.0","Biscuits and Sausage Gravy Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook sausage, remove from pan and drain. 2: In a saucepan over med.-high heat melt the butter-stir in the flour and whisk until smooth. 3: Add mustard, salt and pepper. 4: Gradually whisk in the milk and whisk until smooth. 5: Bring to a boil and stir 1 minute or until as thick as you want. Remove from the heat and add the cooked sausage. This recipe doubles really well. 6: Serve over hot biscuits. 7: Jan");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3806,"Saucy Round Steak for a Crowd","PT3H","PT30M","PT3H30M","Make and share this Saucy Round Steak for a Crowd recipe from Food.com.","For Large Groups",0.0,1.0,372.9,20.7,7.7,112.6,427.8,11.2,1.0,2.1,33.8,"50.0","Saucy Round Steak for a Crowd Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Cut steaks to serving sizes. 3: Roll steak in flour, salt and pepper mixture. 4: Brown steak in a fry pan with small amount of oil. 5: Layer a large baking pan with meat then vegetables; repeat until meat and vegetables are gone. 6: Cover with the cans of soup. 7: Bake several hours (3-4) or until meat falls apart.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3807,"Polish Sausage and Peppers","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Polish Sausage and Peppers recipe from Food.com.","European",0.0,1.0,404.6,31.4,11.3,76.2,958.4,12.7,2.1,4.7,16.6,"50.0","Polish Sausage and Peppers Recipe Instructions:  1: Put all the above into a roaster. 2: Stir occasionally  Cook at 250 - 300 deg. for most of the day (4- 5 hr.) 3: Serve the sausage and peppers and onions on French bread. 4: Always well liked.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3808,"Mediterranean Spaghetti","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Mediterranean Spaghetti recipe from Food.com.","Spaghetti",3.0,1.0,400.3,11.0,5.7,78.3,696.9,49.7,3.4,11.2,22.0,"60.0","Mediterranean Spaghetti Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. 2: Heat large nonstick skillet over medium high heat. Brown beef until no  longer pink. 3: Drain. 4: Saute onions,  oregano and garlic for 5 minutes. 5: Add wine through tomatoes (7 ingredients),  and bring to a boil. 6: Reduce heat, and simmer 10 minutes or until thick. 7: Combine flour, milk, and 1/4 tsp. nutmeg in medium saucepan and bring to  boil. 8: Reduce heat, and cook  for 7 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly. 9: Remove milk mixture from  heat.   Stir in feta cheese, half of Parmesan cheese and eggs. 10: Sprinkle half the bread crumbs into a 2 large professional-size baking  pans  coated with cooking spray. 11: Place half of the cooked spaghetti into the 2 pans, top with half th e beef    mixture and then half  of the cheese sauce.  Repeat layers. 12: Combine other half  of  Parmesan cheese  and bread crumbs and  sprinkle over the top of  pans. 13: Bake at 375 for 30 minutes or until golden brown (about 1 hour if recipe is   made ahead).  Let stand for 10 minutes before serving. 14: I found it cuts well  into squares  for serving.  Wonderful aroma, very tasty.  This recipe was used successfully by a church group.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3809,"Biscuits and Sausage Gravy II","PT20M","PT0S","PT20M","Make and share this Biscuits and Sausage Gravy II recipe from Food.com.","Breads",5.0,20.0,463.8,37.0,13.9,82.8,1093.4,13.9,0.1,0.0,17.6,"0.0","Biscuits and Sausage Gravy II Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare homemade biscuits or canned biscuits according to package directions. 2: Crumble sausage into skillet and brown. 3: Pour off excess  grease leaving about 4 tablespoons drippings in the skillet. Add  cornstarch to skillet; stir to loosen the crust bits in skillet. Slowly  add the milk and continue to stir until creamy and smooth. 4: Add more cold  milk if gravy thickens too fast. Return cooked sausage to the gravy. 5: Stir  well to blend. 6: Cut biscuits in half and spoon the sausage gravy on top.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3810,"Breakfast Sausage Gravy","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Breakfast Sausage Gravy recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",4.5,4.0,1849.2,148.4,55.5,331.4,4371.9,51.5,0.6,0.1,72.9,"0.0","Breakfast Sausage Gravy Recipe Instructions:  1: Use cast iron skillet, break up and brown sausage. Add flour to sausage; brown it up for awhile. This gives it a good color. 2: Add milk required to give thick gravy;  simmer to merge flavor. 3: Add glob of sour cream just before serving, after removing from heat.  Serving suggestions: Serve on top of toast, biscuit, hash browns, home fries or whatever you''re eating.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3811,"Tomato Soup Chocolate Cake","PT30M","PT0S","PT30M","Make and share this Tomato Soup Chocolate Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",2.0,1.0,5662.8,240.1,104.0,770.8,4981.6,854.0,32.5,600.9,75.8,"0.0","Tomato Soup Chocolate Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 deg. Grease and flour A 9\ 2:  pan or a Bundt pan. 3: Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs, and beat until fluffy. 4: Whisk together dry ingredients. 5: Mix tomato soup and water. 6: Add dry ingredients and soup mixture alternately to creamed mixture. Fold in nuts. 7: Pour into pan and bake 30 minute in 9x13\ 8: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3812,"Jewish Chicken Soup with Matzo Balls","PT30M","PT1H15M","PT1H45M","Make and share this Jewish Chicken Soup with Matzo Balls recipe from Food.com.","European",5.0,5.0,103.2,3.6,0.8,38.2,771.0,10.2,0.7,1.4,7.5,"10.0","Jewish Chicken Soup with Matzo Balls Recipe Instructions:  1: In a mixing bowl, whisk together eggs, egg white and salt. Whisk in matzo meal, oil and 3 Tbsp cold  water. 2: Cover and chill the mixture at least 1 hour or overnight. 3: In a large pot, bring chicken broth to a boil.  Add parsnips, carrots and onions, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 5 minutes. 4: Gently roll the chilled matzo dough by level teaspoonfuls into balls, dropping them into the simmering broth as you work.  Cook the matzo balls, covered, for 15 minutes.  Do not lift the lid; the broth must simmer rapidly to allow the matzo balls to expand properly. 5: Uncover the pot, add broccoli and mushrooms and simmer until the broccoli is just tender, 2 to 3 minutes. 6: Ladle into bowls, sprinkle with dill or parsley and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3813,"Light Fruitcake","PT3H","PT0S","PT3H","I don''t know how low fat these recipes are, but they have less butter and eggs than most Fruitcakes.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,5603.6,284.9,95.3,960.0,2655.8,739.6,52.1,373.3,80.4,"0.0","Light Fruitcake Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift flour with baking powder and salt. 2: Cream butter  and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.  Add grated orange and lemon rinds. 3: Add sifted flour mixture alternately with fruit juice. Mix well. 4: Stir in pecans and  fruits. 5: Pack into a greased and wax paper lined 9 x 13-inch  loaf pan. Bake in preheated oven at 250 degrees for 3 hours or until  cake tests done. Cool on rack. Remove from pan. 6: Wrap cooled cake in foil to keep moist.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3814,"Light Fruitcake IIi","PT1H15M","PT0S","PT1H15M","Make and share this Light Fruitcake IIi recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,13090.7,678.5,63.0,846.0,2689.0,1783.6,163.0,1402.5,154.1,"0.0","Light Fruitcake IIi Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add fruit and  mix well to coat with flour. 2: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.  Gradually beat in sugar. 3: Add fruit-flour mixture and nuts.  Mix well with hands. 4: Grease tube pan. Line with brown paper;  grease paper. 5: Bake at 275 degrees about 1 hour and 15 minutes or  until done. Let cake stand in pan about 10 minutes. Turn out  on rack to cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3815,"Light Fruitcake II","PT1H30M","PT0S","PT1H30M","Make and share this Light Fruitcake II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,1.0,6674.5,229.0,96.2,994.2,2794.2,1116.7,39.1,662.6,102.0,"0.0","Light Fruitcake II Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook raisins in water 10 minutes and then drain, cool and set aside. Cream butter and sugar, add beaten eggs, beat well. 2: Add flour, baking powder and salt, sifted together. 3: Add milk, lemon juice and mixed fruit; mix together raisins, walnuts, blending well. 4: Grease and flour angel food pan. 5: Fill half full, put rest of batter in a loaf pan and bake 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours at 300 degrees.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3816,"Jellied Cranberry Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Jellied Cranberry Salad recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",0.0,0.0,1299.2,18.5,2.4,0.0,768.4,284.3,11.1,263.9,14.8,"0.0","Jellied Cranberry Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve Jello in hot water. Add cold water. Chill  until partially set. 2: Fold in the diced orange, pineapple,  cranberry sauce and chopped nuts. Chill until firm. 3: May use  cream cheese on the top. 4: Fills a 9-inch square pan.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3817,"Jellied Cranberry Salad II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Jellied Cranberry Salad II recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",0.0,0.0,2848.7,71.1,9.5,0.0,1397.2,553.1,25.8,500.9,33.0,"1.0","Jellied Cranberry Salad II Recipe Instructions:  1: Grind cranberries. 2: Combine with sugar and let stand  until sugar dissolves. 3: Dissolve Jello in 3 1/2 cups water and  let partly set. Then add celery, nuts and orange to berries. 4: Mix well. 5: Stir mixture into Jello and let Jello completel  y set  up.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3818,"Jellied Cranberry Salad III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Jellied Cranberry Salad III recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",0.0,0.0,2255.4,116.8,47.5,249.9,1269.7,292.9,11.9,271.1,31.3,"1.0","Jellied Cranberry Salad III Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve Jello in hot water. 2: Add cold water and chill  until partially set. Fold in orange, crushed pineapple,  cranberry sauce and walnuts. 3: Chill until firm. 4: Cream cream  cheese w  ith some of juice off the fruit to use as dressing.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3820,"Biscuits for Biscuits and Gravy","PT8M","PT0S","PT8M","Make and share this Biscuits for Biscuits and Gravy recipe from Food.com.","Breads",5.0,25.0,81.2,3.8,1.0,0.8,332.7,10.2,0.3,0.9,1.5,"0.0","Biscuits for Biscuits and Gravy Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl. 2: Measure shortening and cut into flour mixture with pastry blender, two knives or blending fork, until mixture looks like \ 3:  Stir in almost all the milk. 4: If dough does not seem pliable, add the remaining milk. 5: Use enough milk to make a soft, puffy dough easy to roll out. Knead on a light floured board. 6: Too much handling makes tough biscuits. 7: Roll out 1/4-inch thick for thin crusty biscuits and 1/2-inch thick for thick biscuits. 8: Place on ungreased cookie sheet, close together for biscuits with soft sides, an inch apart for biscuits with crusty sides. 9: Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450 degrees. 10: ANGEL BISCUITS 1 pkg. dry yeast 1/4 cup warm water 2 1/2 cup flour 1/2 teaspoons baking soda 1 teaspoons baking powder 1 teaspoons salt 1/8 cup sugar 1/2 cup shortening 1 cup b uttermilk . 11: Dissolve the yeast in warm water and set aside. Mix the dry ingredients in the order given (flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar), cutting in the shortening as you normally do for biscuits or pie dough. 12: Stir in the buttermilk, also the water-yeast mixture. Blend thoroughly and the dough is ready to be refrigerated in a large covered bowl or made into biscuits. 13: When you are ready to make the dough into biscuits, turn it out onto a floured board and knead lightly as for regular biscuits. 14: Roll out and cut with a biscuit cutter and place in a greased pan. 15: Let the biscuits rise slightly (if the dough is cold, it will take a little longer for them to rise than when first mixed) and pop into a 400 degrees oven until lightly browned (about 20 minutes).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3821,"Shepherd''s Pie With Eggplant (Aubergine)","PT40M","PT30M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Shepherd''s Pie With Eggplant (Aubergine) recipe from Food.com.","One Dish Meal",5.0,5.0,262.8,9.6,5.6,25.3,511.6,36.6,8.5,7.0,10.9,"6.0","Shepherd''s Pie With Eggplant (Aubergine) Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Cook the potatoes (in their skins) in boiling water, until soft.  Drain, and mash the first 5 ingredients. Set aside. 3: In a large, heavy skillet, saute the onions and garlic in 1 1/2 Tbsp of butter, with salt and pepper, until the onions are soft (5-8 minutes). Add the celery, mushrooms, and eggplant.  Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally. 4: When the eggplant is cooked through (and this will happen more quickly if you cover the skillet between stirrings), add green pepper, herbs, and peas.  Continue cooking about 5 minutes longer. 5: Remove from heat; toss with cheese, wheat germ, and vinegar.  Spread this mixture into your buttered deep-dish casserole.  Spread the mashed potatoes on top, as a crust. 6: OPTIONAL (and OPTIMAL):  Sprinkle extra cheese plus some paprika on top. 7: Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3822,"Sweetened Soy Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","This isn''t "minimal-prep", but you can make a batch up and store it in the fridge for future reference. And it smells so good while simmering....  (translated from a Japanese TV cooking course)","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,906.2,0.4,0.1,0.0,16096.2,169.9,5.8,143.3,32.3,"1.0","Sweetened Soy Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Put all ingredients in pan, bring to boil, and simmer over low heat for approximately one hour, until liquid has reduced to about 2/3. 2: Strain, cool, and store in fridge for up to one month. 3: Use in same quantities as Oyster Sauce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3823,"Phil''s Italian Sausage","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Phil''s Italian Sausage recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,6.0,163.1,7.4,2.6,65.0,45.1,0.6,0.2,0.1,22.2,"0.0","Phil''s Italian Sausage Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix well. 2: Shape into patties. 3: Wrap individually to  freeze if desired. 4: To prepare, fry as any pork sausage. Will  make 24 patties. 5: Note: No salt is used in this recipe for diet reasons  and so many spices are used I have never noticed the salt being  deleted.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3824,"Homemade Sausage","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Homemade Sausage recipe from Food.com.","Pork",0.0,0.0,190.7,10.0,3.4,70.7,449.4,0.6,0.3,0.0,23.2,"0.0","Homemade Sausage Recipe Instructions:  1: Put pork through fine blade of meat grinder twice. 2: Put meat in mixing bowl; add remaining ingredients. Knead well with hands to blend spices thoroughly. 3: Shape into 36 patties. 4: Fry at once or freeze.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3825,"Toasted Pumpkin Seeds ( Pepitas)","PT30M","PT10M","PT40M","Make and share this Toasted Pumpkin Seeds ( Pepitas) recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,5.0,886.6,81.9,14.7,0.0,108.8,13.9,7.7,1.8,39.1,"0.0","Toasted Pumpkin Seeds ( Pepitas) Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Wipe fibers from pumpkin seeds but do not wash them. 3: Coat seeds with mixture of oil and margarine. 4: Spread seeds on a baking sheet. 5: Sprinkle with coarse salt to taste and toast for 30 minutes or until they are crisp and golden.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3826,"Pumpkin Seed Snack Combo","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pumpkin Seed Snack Combo recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",0.0,0.0,542.5,40.1,11.7,30.5,505.3,34.2,6.7,4.0,19.0,"0.0","Pumpkin Seed Snack Combo Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash pumpkin seeds and blot dry with paper towels.  Spread seeds on jelly roll pan and bake at 275 degrees for 5 minutes or until dry. Remove seeds from pan and set aside. 2: Melt butter in same pan. 3: Add Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt. Add seeds, cereals, chow mein noodles and peanuts,  stirring to coat. Bake another 40 minutes, stirring several times. 4: Cool mixture on paper towels. 5: Store in airtight container. 6: Add raisins just before serving if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3827,"C-C-P","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this C-C-P recipe from Food.com.","Cauliflower",0.0,0.0,449.4,30.4,4.8,0.0,157.2,36.3,11.6,15.0,16.3,"0.0","C-C-P Recipe Instructions:  1: Slice onion  thin; separate into rings. 2: Peel carrots and  slice diagonally. 3: Saute onion in oil 1 to 2 minutes. 4: Toss in  cauliflower and carrots. 5: Add a bit of water; cover and steam  vegetables about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. 6: Toss with  parsley and pumpkin seeds. 7: Serve hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3828,"Oven-Baked Caramel Corn","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Oven-Baked Caramel Corn recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,935.2,52.2,20.7,69.7,1116.4,114.2,8.0,66.9,10.5,"0.0","Oven-Baked Caramel Corn Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 250 degrees. 2: Place popcorn, peanuts, pumpkin seeds and sunflower seeds in a large container. 3: In medium sized saucepan, over medium high heat, bring all remaining ingredients except baking soda to a boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. 4: Remove from heat and carefully stir in baking soda. 5: Pour mixture over popcorn, mix in flat pans. 6: Bake in batches 1 hour, stirring several  times. 7: Remove from oven and stir occasionally while mixture cools. 8: Store in airtight containers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3829,"Cheese &amp; Yellow Squash Casserole","PT35M","PT30M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Cheese &amp; Yellow Squash Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",4.5,6.0,725.0,54.1,33.6,195.8,1262.6,22.1,2.9,5.2,39.2,"0.0","Cheese &amp; Yellow Squash Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Coat baking dish lightly with butter. 2: Grate all the cheese, then save a small  amount aside to sprinkle on top of the casserole. 3: Cut the squash into medium thin slices, the onion in very thin slices. 4: Cook squash/onion the following way:  place cut squash and onion in a pan of cold water. Bring to a boil, then  immediately remove from stove and drain well. 5: Combine squash/onion with most of  the shredded cheese, 1/2 stick of butter, 1 cup of seasoned bread crumbs. This  will form a thick \ 6:  mixture. 7: Add 1  beaten egg (or substitute). If mixture  is too runny, add a little more bread crumbs. If too dry, add a little milk. 8: Add to mixture a heavy \ 9:  of Worcestershire, 1/2 to 1 tsp of sugar (to taste), a dash of Tabasco sauce, a good dash of garlic powder, then salt and pepper to  taste. Mix well. 10: Spoon mixture into the buttered baking dish. Sprinkle top  lightly with bread crumbs and the small amount of grated cheese that was set  aside. Cut small amount of butter into a few thin slices and \ 11:  on top of  casserole. 12: Bake at 350 degrees F for 35 minutes. Let cool slightly before  serving to \ 13:  the casserole.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3830,"Slow Roasted Turkey","PT9H","PT0S","PT9H","Make and share this Slow Roasted Turkey recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",0.0,0.0,726.4,36.4,10.3,308.7,295.1,0.0,0.0,0.0,92.7,"8.0","Slow Roasted Turkey Recipe Instructions:  1: Rub or brush butter over turkey. 2: Place turkey in roaster. Cover with 9 cups of water. Cover with foil and place in 200 degrees oven for 30 minutes. 3: Then cook at 150 degrees for 6 to 8 hours. 4: Remove and slice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3831,"Cracker Barrel Old Country Store Fried Apples","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cracker Barrel Old Country Store Fried Apples recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",5.0,10.0,184.8,8.8,3.4,8.2,66.4,28.4,3.5,23.2,0.4,"6.0","Cracker Barrel Old Country Store Fried Apples Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large skillet, melt bacon drippings. 2: Pour apples evenly over skillet  bottom. 3: Sprinkle lemon juice over them, then brown sugar, then salt. Cover  and cook over low heat for 15 minutes until apples are tender and juicy. 4: Sprinkle with cinnamon & nutmeg.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3832,"Hot Cocoa Mix II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Hot Cocoa Mix II recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",0.0,0.0,99.2,0.3,0.3,0.8,41.2,22.4,0.5,20.5,2.1,"32.0","Hot Cocoa Mix II Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all of the ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Store in an  airtight container. 2: Combine 1/4 cup  of mix with 3/4 cup  of boiling water or milk. Stir well.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3833,"Deep-Fried Cornish Game Hens","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Deep-Fried Cornish Game Hens recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",5.0,2.0,395.0,11.3,2.9,309.9,231.5,0.0,0.0,0.0,68.2,"0.0","Deep-Fried Cornish Game Hens Recipe Instructions:  1: Don''t fill your stockpot more than half full with shortening/oil, to allow for the inevitable boiling up when the hens are added. 2: Also, be sure the hens are at room temperature so the fat temperature doesn''t drop dramatically from the shock of an ice-cold bird. 3: Rinse the hens and pat completely dry, inside and out, with paper towels.  Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour. 4: Preheat the oven to 200 degrees F. Place a large wire cake rack over a jelly roll pan/cookie sheet. 5: In a stockpot, melt vegetable shortening over high heat to a depth of 2 to 3 inches and heat it to 375 degrees F. 6: Carefully put 1 Cornish hen in the hot shortening.  Deep fry, turning occasionally, until golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3834,"Apple Pie Cake II","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Apple Pie Cake II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,2.0,255.4,9.1,1.2,26.4,327.8,41.5,1.5,24.0,3.6,"16.0","Apple Pie Cake II Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Generously grease and lightly flour a 9- or 10-inch fluted tube pan. 3: In a large mixer bowl at low speed beat pie filling, flour, sugar, oil, eggs, baking soda, vanil la, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and cloves for 30 seconds. 4: At medium speed beat for 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. 5: Stir in nuts. 6: Pour into pan. 7: Bake for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean. 8: Cool upright in pan on a wire rack for 2 hours or until completely cooled. 9: Remove from pan and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3835,"Applesauce Candy","PT15M","PT0S","PT15M","Make and share this Applesauce Candy recipe from Food.com.","Candy",0.0,0.0,1896.9,58.4,5.5,0.0,148.4,321.2,8.8,231.5,44.0,"0.0","Applesauce Candy Recipe Instructions:  1: Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. 2: Place sugar and applesauce in a medium saucepan. 3: Over medium heat bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes. 4: Stir in gelatin until dissolved; remove from heat.  Stir in nuts. 5: Pour into baking pan. 6: Cover lightly and let stand at room temperature for 24 hours. 7: Cut into 1-inch squares. 8: Roll in powdered sugar. 9: Let stand for 24 hours and roll in powdered sugar again.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3836,"Extra Rich Peanut Butter Fudge","PT20M","PT5M","PT25M","Make and share this Extra Rich Peanut Butter Fudge recipe from Food.com.","Candy",5.0,3.0,218.9,8.4,1.5,1.4,88.4,34.1,1.3,30.0,4.3,"16.0","Extra Rich Peanut Butter Fudge Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan. 2: Cook to soft ball  stage. Add remaining ingredients, stirring until blended. 3: Pour into 8-inch greased square pan and cool. 4: Cut into  squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3837,"Cloud Topped Peanut Butter Fudge","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cloud Topped Peanut Butter Fudge recipe from Food.com.","Candy",5.0,1.0,2232.5,96.0,42.0,116.4,1326.6,327.8,7.4,282.9,30.3,"0.0","Cloud Topped Peanut Butter Fudge Recipe Instructions:  1: In heavy saucepan combine evaporated milk, sugar, salt and butter. Bring  to a boil over moderate heat. Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly. 2: Remove  from heat, add morsels. Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth. 3: Spread into foil lined  9-inch pan. Chill 30 minutes. 4: In heavy saucepan,  combine brown sugar, butter and corn syrup. Stir until smooth. Bring to a  boil. 5: Remove from heat. Add confectioners sugar and walnuts. Stir until  well blended. 6: Spread over peanut butter fudge layer. 7: Chill until firm (2  hours).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3838,"No-Cook Peanut Butter Fudge","PT5M","PT5M","PT10M","Make and share this No-Cook Peanut Butter Fudge recipe from Food.com.","Candy",3.0,5.0,4207.9,282.7,58.9,0.0,2640.3,342.3,31.0,284.0,129.7,"0.0","No-Cook Peanut Butter Fudge Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt margarine. Add ingredients together and mix well. 2: Spread out on a  cookie sheet and then refrigerate. Makes 1 standard size cookie sheet of  delicious peanut butter fudge.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3839,"Chocolate Frosted Peanut Butter Fudge","0","PT40M","PT40M","Make and share this Chocolate Frosted Peanut Butter Fudge recipe from Food.com.","Candy",5.0,1.0,260.1,14.7,4.1,7.1,149.8,28.7,2.2,23.1,6.2,"0.0","Chocolate Frosted Peanut Butter Fudge Recipe Instructions:  1: In a heavy 2 quart saucepan, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk. 2: Stirring constantly, bring mixture to a full rolling boil over medium heat. Continue cooking and stirring 5 minutes. 3: Remove from heat. Add marshmallows, peanut butter, vanilla and 1/2 cup of the chopped peanuts. 4: Stir vigorously until marshmallows and peanut butter are melted and mixture blended. 5: Turn into a buttered 8-inch square pan. 6: Cool a few minutes until top \ 7: . 8: Sprinkle chocolate over top. 9: Let stand until chocolate melts, then  spread over fudge with a spatula. 10: Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup chopped peanuts over chocolate and press in lightly. 11: Cool, then cut into 1-inch squares. 12: Refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes approximately 2 1/2 pounds fudge.  To make Peanut-Butter Chocolate-Marbled Fudge: Follow recipe for Chocolate Frosted Peanut Butter Fudge except add semi-sweet chocolate pieces to fudge just before turning it into pan. 13: Stir just a few times to secure a marbled appearance. Turn into pan as directed previously. 14: Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup chopped peanuts over top and press nuts down gently into fudge.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3840,"Fabulous Zucchini Bread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Fabulous Zucchini Bread recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,43.0,927.0,29.3,4.6,111.6,979.0,153.8,8.3,83.1,17.6,"0.0","Fabulous Zucchini Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Cream together eggs, oil and applesauce.  Add sugar and vanilla. 2: Add dry ingredients and mix well. 3: Stir in zucchini. 4: Grease and flour loaf pans. 5: Large loaf pans bake for 50 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. 6: Small loaf pans bake approx. 25-30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. 7: Remove from oven to cooling racks and let cool until slightly warm before removing. 8: Because this is a moist bread it freezes very well.");
