INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3847,"Baked Stuffed Artichokes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Baked Stuffed Artichokes recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",5.0,3.0,596.2,48.5,18.1,61.0,2079.2,37.8,7.8,1.6,7.2,"4.0","Baked Stuffed Artichokes Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim artichokes and remove chokes.  Add juice and salt to a large kettle of boiling water. 2: Add artichokes and bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium and boil, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes or until a leaf can be pulled out easily. 3: Drain artichokes upside-down on paper towels. 4: Preheat oven to 375 F. 5: In a small bowl combine crumbs, 1/3 cup oil, garlic, oregano and pepper. 6: Spoon one-fourth of the mixture into the center of each artichoke. Brush all over with 2 tablespoons oil. 7: Place in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. 8: In a measuring cup combine water and bouillon; pour into bottom of baking dish. 9: Bake artichokes for 20 minutes or until heated through. 10: In a small saucepan over low heat melt butter. Stir for 3 to 5 minutes or just until butter begins to brown. Do not burn. 11: Remove from heat; add lemon juice.  Place artichokes on individual serving plates. 12: Spoon 1 tablespoon lemon-butter over the top of each artichoke. Serve remaining butter separately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3848,"Quick-N-Easy Blueberry Muffins","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Quick-N-Easy Blueberry Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",0.0,0.0,112.4,1.6,0.9,5.3,283.6,20.9,1.1,4.4,3.7,"6.0","Quick-N-Easy Blueberry Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: In a medium bowl, mix frozen yogurt and flour. 2: Fold in blueberries. 3: Spoon into 6 muffin tins coated with cooking spray. 4: Bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes or  until a toothpick inserted in muffins tests done.  While hot, sprinkle muffin  tops with sugar if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3849,"Pear Cake","PT1H30M","PT15M","PT1H45M","Make and share this Pear Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",3.5,2.0,755.3,41.7,5.7,63.5,114.0,90.5,3.6,56.5,8.3,"0.0","Pear Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs and vanilla; beat well. 2: Add flour and cinnamon with a spoon. 3: Add pears and nuts. 4: Pour in a greased bundt pan and bake 1-1/2 hours at 325 degrees Fahrenheit. 5: Icing: 6: Place powdered sugar in a bowl. Add pear juice and enough hot water to make a thin consistency to pour over cake. 7: Allow cake to cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3851,"English Muffin Bread II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this English Muffin Bread II recipe from Food.com.","Yeast Breads",5.0,13.0,107.2,0.3,0.1,0.4,220.0,21.8,0.9,0.6,3.7,"24.0","English Muffin Bread II Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large mixing bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking  soda. 2: Add warm milk and water; beat on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl  occasionally. 3: Beat on high for 3 minutes. 4: Stir in remaining flour (batter will be stiff.)   DO NOT KNEAD. 5: Spray with cooking spray two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2\ 6: ,  7: ,  8: ,  9: Bake at 375 for 35 minutes or until golden brown. 10: Remove from pans immediately  and cool on wire racks. 11: Slice and toast. 12: NOTES : If desired wrap 1 loaf in foil and freeze.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3852,"Shepherd''s Pie V","PT30M","PT15M","PT45M","Make and share this Shepherd''s Pie V recipe from Food.com.","Meat",3.0,2.0,939.8,81.5,33.8,114.5,651.0,40.3,3.3,6.2,13.5,"4.0","Shepherd''s Pie V Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Fry the ground meat and onion together until meat is brown and onion is translucent. 3: Drain the fat. 4: Add salt and pepper to taste. 5: Place into oven proof baking dish. 6: Pour cream style corn over the top. 7: Spread mashed potatoes over the top. 8: Bake for 30 min or until golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3854,"No Fat Fruitcake","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","Make and share this No Fat Fruitcake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,193.1,1.2,0.4,33.1,186.6,41.0,1.0,21.3,4.8,"24.0","No Fat Fruitcake Recipe Instructions:  1: Citrus Glaze:  Combine sugar and enough orange juice to make a glaze  consistency. 2: Cake:  Beat sugars, cream cheese, citrus rinds, and vanilla until smooth in  large bowl; beat in e ggs. 3: Mix in combined flour, cornstarch, baking soda, and  salt alternately sour cream. 4: Mix in fruit. Pour batter into greased 12 cup fluted tube pan. 5: Bake at 350°F until toothpick  inserted in center comes out clean, about 60 minutes. 6: Cool in pan on rack 10  minutes; remove from pan and cool. 7: Drizzle with glaze.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3855,"Aduki Bean Stew","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","This is an adopted recipe. I have not yet tried it, but hope to eventually. Please let me know if you try it and how it turns out via a review. Any opinions/changes will be taken into consideration! Thanks!","Stew",5.0,9.0,249.6,1.2,0.2,0.0,599.0,50.2,10.7,9.2,14.2,"3.0","Aduki Bean Stew Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute the onion in the margarine until golden. 2: Add the garlic, leek, carrot and mushrooms, and cook for another 5 minutes, until the vegetables are just soft. 3: Mix in the paprika and flour and stir for another minute. 4: Add the remaining ingredients, including the cooked aduki beans, plus enough reserved bean cooking liquid to half-cover the ingredients. 5: Stir well, cover and simmer for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally and adding more cooking liquid if it gets too dry. 6: Season with black pepper and parsley and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3856,"Vegetarian Shepherd''s Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Vegetarian Shepherd''s Pie recipe from Food.com.","One Dish Meal",4.0,7.0,309.8,4.3,0.7,0.0,364.9,59.0,9.2,5.9,10.9,"4.0","Vegetarian Shepherd''s Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash the beans and rice in plenty of cold water. Combine about 4 cups  of water with beans and rice and cook for 5o minutes or until the beans  are soft. Drain, reserving the stock for later. 2: Heat oil in a skillet. Fry the onions for 3 minutes. 3: Add the  carrots and cook covered for 5 minutes. 4: Add the cooked beans and rice.  Stir well and let saute for a few minutes, ensuring   that the mixture  does not burn. 5: Combine the soy sauce, tomato paste, herbs and stock. 6: Mix well and pour into the skillet. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to  very low, partially cover and simmer gently for 30 minutes, stirring  frequently to prevent it burning. Add more stock if necessary. 7: Transfer into a casserole.  Top the cooked vegetables with mashed potatoes. 8: Bake in a preheated  oven at 350F for 40 minutes, or until the potatoes are browned. 9: Serve with vegetables or a green salad.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3857,"My Shepherd''s Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this My Shepherd''s Pie recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,427.5,18.9,7.1,176.8,127.1,3.5,0.6,1.6,61.0,"4.0","My Shepherd''s Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Grind the roast beef. 2: Saute the onion and add Bovril, water, and 3: beef. 4: Cook for a short time.  Put in a casserole.  Top with mashed potatoes and put in 375 F oven for about 30 minutes. 5: Brown under broiler. 6: I must admit that I sometimes use a gravy mix instead of the Bovril and about 2 cups of gravy as a replacement is wonderful.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3858,"Pumpkin Cookies","PT12M","PT10M","PT22M","Make and share this Pumpkin Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",4.5,12.0,167.0,7.8,2.6,9.7,119.2,23.6,0.5,16.9,1.2,"0.0","Pumpkin Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine.  Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. 2: Bake at 350°F for 10-12 minutes. 3: Frosting: Boil first three ingredients together for 2 minutes. 4: Cool and add powdered sugar and vanilla. 5: Ice cool cookies.");
