INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3860,"Butter Bean Dip with Basil","0","PT0S","PT0S","Adapted from a recipe posted to rec.food.recipes originally adapted from a recipe by Jordans Naturally-Seasoned Chips","Beans",0.0,0.0,82.7,1.8,0.9,4.4,260.5,11.8,3.5,0.9,5.7,"4.0","Butter Bean Dip with Basil Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash the zucchini, but leave it whole. Cook in a pan of simmering water until very soft - about 20 minutes. 2: Squeeze most of the water out of the zucchini and chop roughly. 3: Put all ingredients into a blender and puree until smooth. 4: Let stand at least 30 minutes, then serve with dippers such as breadsticks or carrot sticks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3861,"Cobbler Made With Bisquick Mix","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","From the Bisquick Best Recipes booklet (I think I ordered this from an  ad a couple of years ago - you might try their 800-336-9331 number  (&quot;Quick and Easy Recipes&quot;) to see if you can get a copy.  Maybe  bettycrocker.com has a pointer too.  Fruit Cobbler","Dessert",0.0,0.0,142.1,6.2,2.5,6.1,329.1,18.8,0.5,5.0,2.6,"6.0","Cobbler Made With Bisquick Mix Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 425 degrees F. 2: Grease 1.5-quart casserole.  Heat pie  filling to boiling in 1-quart saucepan. 3: Pour into casserole. Stir remaining ingredients until dough forms. 4: Drop by 6 spoonfuls onto  hot pie filling;  sprinkle lightly with granulated sugar if desired. 5: Bake about 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown. 6: 6 servings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3862,"Pumpkin Bread Pudding With Ginger Cream","PT40M","PT15M","PT55M","Make and share this Pumpkin Bread Pudding With Ginger Cream recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,4.0,439.5,19.8,11.4,119.4,326.0,59.7,2.3,39.1,7.9,"9.0","Pumpkin Bread Pudding With Ginger Cream Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 350 degrees. 2: Spray 8 or 9-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray. 3: In large bowl, beat eggs until well blended. 4: Add 1 1/4 cups sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, butter and vanilla; beat well. 5: Add bread crumbs, milk and pumpkin; mix well. 6: Let stand 10 minutes. 7: Add raisins to batter; mix well. 8: Spread evenly in sprayed pan. 9: Bake for 37-47 minutes or until knife inserted 1 1/2-inches from edge comes out clean. 10: Cool 30 minutes. 11: In small bowl, beat whipping cream, gradually adding sugar and ginger until soft peaks form. 12: To serve: Cut pudding into squares. 13: Serve warm or cool topped with ginger cream. 14: Store in refrigerator.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3863,"Tangy Ambrosia Sald","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Tangy Ambrosia Sald recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",4.5,29.0,141.8,10.1,7.5,12.0,26.2,13.2,1.9,10.0,1.4,"10.0","Tangy Ambrosia Sald Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients except marshmallows; chill for several hours. 2: Add marshmallows right before serving. 3: Also good with chopped pecans added! 4: Note: the original recipe had you mix the marshmallows in at the same time as the other ingredients, but I prefer to add them later as stated to keep them from getting mushy.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3864,"Sugar-Free Pumpkin Pie","PT50M","PT10M","PT1H","Make and share this Sugar-Free Pumpkin Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",0.0,0.0,52.4,0.2,0.1,1.7,99.6,8.7,0.4,5.6,4.7,"0.0","Sugar-Free Pumpkin Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: In a mixing bowl, combine the pumpkin, milk, egg substitute, egg whites and sweetener, beat until smooth. 2: Add the spices and salt, beat until well mixed. 3: Stir in graham cracker crumbs. 4: Pour into a 9-in. pie plate that has been coated with nonstick cooking spray. 5: Bake at 325''F for 50-55 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. 6: Cool. 7: If desired, garnish with a dollop of whipped topping and sprinkling of cinnamon. 8: Store in the refrigerator. 9: Sweet ''N Low or Sweet One are recommended for baking.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3865,"Garlic Rosemary Turkey","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Garlic Rosemary Turkey recipe from Food.com.","Whole Turkey",5.0,9.0,1036.6,51.6,14.5,436.1,417.8,2.9,0.8,0.6,131.3,"0.0","Garlic Rosemary Turkey Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut six to eight small slits in turkey skin insert garlic between the skin and meat. Squeeze two lemon halves inside the turkey and leave them inside. Squeeze remaining lemon over outside of turkey. 2: Spray the turkey with nonstick cooking spray; sprinkle with rosemary and sage. Place on a rack in a roasting pan. 3: Bake, uncovered, at 325''F for 1 hour. 4: Cover and bake 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours longer or until a meat thermometer reads 185''F.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3866,"Hot Reuben Casserole","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Hot Reuben Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",0.0,0.0,2028.8,106.0,35.7,283.4,7603.2,186.6,23.8,30.7,85.6,"1.0","Hot Reuben Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare white sauce according to package directions using milk. Stir in the spicy brown mustard and caraway seeds. Set aside. Preheat oven to 350 F. 2: In a small bowl, combine sauerkraut and relish. 3: In another bowl, combine rye bread cubes and Thousand Island dressing. 4: Grease a medium casserole dish. 5: Spread half the bread mixture on the bottom followed by half the sauerkraut mixture and half the mustard sauce.  Add the corned beef and the Swiss cheese. Layer with remaining sauerkraut mixture and remaining sauce. Top with remaining bread mix ture. Bake until the top is golden and filling is cooked through, about 35 minutes.");
