INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3868,"Apple Cream Pie","PT50M","PT15M","PT1H5M","I got this recipe several years ago from Taste of Home. I really regret not making it sooner! We all loved it. The cream base complemented the apples beautifully. Excellent &quot;as is&quot; but also enjoyable with a little whipped cream on top. It''s also really good for breakfast. ;)","Pie",4.0,1.0,1940.4,89.1,55.0,326.1,97.9,293.5,12.6,251.9,8.6,"0.0","Apple Cream Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Place apples in pie shell. 2: Combine sugar, cream and flour, pour over apples; sprinkle with cinnamon. 3: Bake at 400''F for 10 minutes. 4: Reduce to 375''F for 35-40 minutes or until pie is set in center. 5: Serve warm or cold.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3869,"Crawfish Stew","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Crawfish Stew recipe from Food.com.","Stew",0.0,0.0,1148.3,109.8,14.3,0.0,2406.9,39.6,4.7,8.6,5.9,"1.0","Crawfish Stew Recipe Instructions:  1: In a heavy bottom pot, make a roux by adding flour to  heated oil. Over low heat stir constantly until a deep golden  brown. Take pot away from heat for fear of burning. 2: Add  onions, garlic and celery; cook about 5 minutes or until  tender. 3: Stir; return to heat and add 1 pint of water, tomatoes, sugar, salt and  pepper. Cook over high heat, stirring  until sauce simmers, then reduce heat again. 4: While sauce is simmering, combine remaining water with  crawfish fat in a large saucepot. Cook over high heat, stirring constantly until  it comes to a boil. 5: Add sauce to fat and  water; let simmer 1 hour. 6: Season with salt and pepper again if  needed. 7: Add crawfish tails, green onions and parsley. 8: Serve in soup plate over a scoop.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3870,"Crawfish Stew II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Crawfish Stew II recipe from Food.com.","Stew",0.0,0.0,2680.6,124.4,17.6,1457.3,1033.1,160.4,20.0,23.9,226.8,"1.0","Crawfish Stew II Recipe Instructions:  1: Use an iron pot if possible. Heat cooking oil. 2: Add flour and brown to a dark brown over a low fire. Be certain to keep stirring this mixture constantly. 3: If the phone rings, do not answer. 4: Add chopped seasoning; simmer over low heat about 1 hour. 5: Season crawfish tails with salt, black pepper and red pepper and add to sauce mixture. Cover and continue to simmer over low heat for about 1 more hour. 6: Serve over rice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3871,"Summer Mincemeat Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Summer Mincemeat Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",0.0,0.0,6908.3,100.4,59.5,244.0,8274.2,1565.5,74.9,1326.0,37.0,"0.0","Summer Mincemeat Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Core the tomatoes and apples, but do not peel. 2: Put both  through the food chopper and add remaining ingredients. 3: Pour  into a large kettle and mix thoroughly. 4: Bring to a boil and  keep boiling for 5 minutes. 5: Immediately put into jars and  seal. 6: This is ready to use as pie filling.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3872,"Green Tomato Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Green Tomato Pie recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,2.0,139.7,0.3,0.1,0.0,160.8,34.5,1.3,29.0,1.3,"8.0","Green Tomato Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Make crust for 9-inch pie. Core green tomatoes and cut into thin wedges, as you do for apple pie. Mix together dry ingredients. 2: Stir in lemon juice and tomatoes until tomatoes are coated. 3: Fill pie crust and add top crust. Flute edge and slit top 4 or 5 times. 4: Bake 30 minutes at 425 degrees. 5: Reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake another 20 minutes. 6: Tastes like mincemeat pie.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3873,"Any Fruit Cobbler Pie","PT30M","PT20M","PT55M","Make and share this Any Fruit Cobbler Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,4.0,450.4,22.6,12.1,47.1,533.1,58.9,0.8,37.6,4.5,"0.0","Any Fruit Cobbler Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Put  margarine or butter in 15 x 9-inch pan. 2: Put pan in oven until butter melts. 3: Add sugar and mix in pan with butter. 4: Add Bisquick in same pan. 5: Add the milk and mix well. 6: Pour fruit over the Bisquick. 7: Do not mix. 8: Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3874,"Sparkling Snickerdoodles","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sparkling Snickerdoodles recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,28.0,72.9,3.6,0.9,6.2,42.9,9.4,0.1,5.0,0.8,"0.0","Sparkling Snickerdoodles Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, sugar and eggs. 2: Sift together and stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and  salt. Roll into balls the size of small walnuts. 3: Roll in  mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. 4: Place  2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes  in medium to hot (400 degrees) oven until lightly brown but still  soft. These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out with  crinkled tops.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3875,"Moravian Christmas Cookies","PT12M","PT0S","PT12M","Make and share this Moravian Christmas Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,2.0,48.9,1.1,0.4,1.0,21.1,9.2,0.1,4.8,0.5,"100.0","Moravian Christmas Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine molasses, sugar, lard and soda dissolved in 2  tablespoons hot water over low heat. Melt and cool. 2: Add  orange extract. Gradually add flour sifted with spices. 3: Dough should be firm. 4: Mix and knead thoroughly. 5: Cover well and set in cool place to ripen. 6: Roll small amounts of dough to 1/16\ 7:  thick on a well floured board. 8: Cut into shapes with floured cutters.  Use old-fashioned cookie cutters for added interest. 9: Place on greased tins, smoothing out any air bubbles. 10: Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until light brown--watch carefully.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3876,"Mocha Walnut Christmas Cookies","PT10M","PT0S","PT10M","Make and share this Mocha Walnut Christmas Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",4.5,6.0,107.2,5.9,2.1,4.7,97.5,13.9,0.7,9.9,1.2,"40.0","Mocha Walnut Christmas Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°. 2: Melt over hot (not boiling)  water, 1/2 cup chocolate morsels. 3: Stir until smooth; cool to  room temperature. In small cup dissolve instant coffee in  boiling water; set aside. 4: In small bowl combine flour, baking  soda and salt; set aside. In large bowl combine margarine, sugar,  brown sugar and coffee; beat until creamy. 5: Add egg and melted chips; mix well. 6: Gradually add flour mixture, stir in remaining chocolate chips and walnuts. 7: Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. 8: Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes or until golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3877,"Merry Christmas Cookies","PT1H","PT20M","PT1H20M","Make and share this Merry Christmas Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",0.0,0.0,114.4,7.6,0.9,5.8,37.7,11.6,1.3,6.7,1.6,"0.0","Merry Christmas Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter and sugar. 2: Add eggs, flour, soda and cinnamon. 3: Add milk then fruit mixture and nuts. 4: Drop tea-  spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake 5 minutes at 300 degrees. 5: Makes more than a hundred.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3878,"Peanut Butter Fudge","PT30M","PT50M","PT1H20M","Make and share this Peanut Butter Fudge recipe from Food.com.","Candy",3.0,1.0,71.7,2.3,0.5,0.3,16.4,12.3,0.3,11.4,1.2,"0.0","Peanut Butter Fudge Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix granulated sugar, milk, peanut butter & corn syrup in sauce pan. 2: Heat to a boiling over medium heat, stirring frequently. 3: Boil & stir 1 minute; remove from heat. Cool, without stirring, until bottom of pan is lukewarm, about 45 minutes. 4: Stir in nuts & vanilla, add powdered sugar until mixture is very stiff. 5: Press into buttered loaf pan (9x5x3). 6: Refrigerate until firm, about 30 minutes. 7: Cut into 1 inch squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3879,"Peanut Butter Graham Cookies","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Peanut Butter Graham Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,8.0,77.5,4.6,0.9,0.0,52.9,7.8,0.6,4.3,2.4,"0.0","Peanut Butter Graham Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large bowl, combine peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs, confectioners'' sugar, and corn syrup. 2: Mix until smooth. 3: Shape into 1-inch balls. 4: Place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheets. 5: Drizzle melted chocolate over balls or roll in colored sprinkles. 6: Store covered in refrigerator.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3880,"Italian White Bean Salad","PT2H","PT0S","PT2H","Make and share this Italian White Bean Salad recipe from Food.com.","Beans",3.0,1.0,285.9,0.8,0.2,0.0,33.2,52.7,12.8,4.8,18.6,"6.0","Italian White Bean Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Note 1: OR borlotti beans, washed, picked over and soaked overnight or for at least 6 hours Serve this delicious salad warm in the winter or chilled in the summer. 2: It makes a wonderful main dish. 3: Drain the beans and combine with the white or yellow onion, the chopped garlic, the water and the bay leaf in a large, heavy-bottomed soup pot. Bring to a boil, reduce the heat, cover, and simmer for 1 hours. 4: Add salt to taste and half the minced garlic, cover and cook 30 min to an hour, or until tender. 5: Drain, reserving the cooking liquid. 6: Meanwhile, combine 1 Tbsp red wine vinegar and 1 C water in a bowl; add the red onion. 7: Add more water to cover if necessary and soak 30 minute. 8: Drain. 9: Mix together the lemon juice, vinegars, remaining garlic; mustard and 3/4 C cooking liquid from the beans. 10: Add salt and pepper to taste and adjust the seasonings. 11: Toss with the beans in a salad bowl, along with the red onion, bell pepper, herbs, pepper and more salt to taste. Serve warm or chilled.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3881,"Christmas Balls","PT2H","PT5M","PT2H5M","Make and share this Christmas Balls recipe from Food.com.","Christmas",3.5,4.0,10397.6,453.7,288.0,287.3,4466.5,1525.8,95.0,1088.7,154.8,"1.0","Christmas Balls Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix in large pan, refrigerate 2 hours. 2: Roll into balls then roll in coconut.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3882,"Orange Muffins","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Orange Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,1.0,159.5,2.6,0.2,0.0,98.4,32.3,0.8,12.0,2.4,"0.0","Orange Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Note that there are no are no eggs in this recipe, so these may be enjoyed by those who can''t eat eggs. 2: Preheat oven to 375F. 3: Spray 12 muffin tins with cooking spray. 4: Mix the flour, baking powder, and 1/4 cup sugar together. 5: Set aside. In a large bowl, beat the thoroughly thawed orange juice concentrate, oil, yogurt, and apricot preserves together. 6: Stir in the apricots. 7: Slowly stir the flour mixture into the liquid ingredients just until everything is moistened. 8: Do not overmix. 9: Spoon the batter into the muffin tins. 10: Mix the sugar, cinnamon, and nutmeg together, and sprinkle over the mu ffins. 11: Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until a cake tester comes out clean.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3883,"Curried Marmalade-Mustard Chicken","0","PT5M","PT5M","Make and share this Curried Marmalade-Mustard Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",4.0,1.0,349.4,11.9,3.1,72.6,448.0,37.4,1.6,33.0,25.3,"0.0","Curried Marmalade-Mustard Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Simmer first five ingredients in small saucepan for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. 2: Cool. 3: Brush chicken pieces on all sides with half of glaze. 4: Let stand 1 hour at room temperature. 5: Grill over medium heat.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3884,"Peanut Butter Fudge II","0","PT1H","PT1H","Make and share this Peanut Butter Fudge II recipe from Food.com.","Candy",5.0,7.0,202.0,9.1,3.4,10.6,85.7,28.5,0.7,24.3,3.4,"30.0","Peanut Butter Fudge II Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk; mix well and bring to a boil. 2: Turn heat to medium and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. 3: Add marshmallow creme, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts. 4: Beat well. 5: Pour into a buttered dish or pan & cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3885,"Caesar Salad","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Caesar Salad recipe from Food.com.","Low Cholesterol",4.5,2.0,90.6,4.0,1.5,13.3,269.4,8.4,1.9,3.8,5.8,"6.0","Caesar Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large bowl combine lettuce, crumbled bacon, onion and croutons. 2: Pour the dressing over and 1/2 the cheese, toss well. 3: Sprinkle with remaining cheese and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3886,"Bacon Roll-Ups","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Bacon Roll-Ups recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,3.0,98.4,6.9,2.6,11.5,178.4,6.6,1.0,0.8,2.9,"0.0","Bacon Roll-Ups Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine milk and cheese. Stir to spreading consistency. 2: Spread about 2 teaspoons on each side of bread, thin cut in 2 pieces. 3: Roll bread and wrap with bacon. 4: Place on broiler pan. 5: bake at 350F for 30 minutes or until bacon browns. 6: These freeze well. 7: thaw before cooking.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3888,"Baked Caramel Corn II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Baked Caramel Corn II recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,6.0,559.6,24.1,14.7,61.0,556.6,87.0,3.5,58.3,3.4,"8.0","Baked Caramel Corn II Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, then boil, without stirring for 5 minutes. 2: Remove from heat, stir in soda and vanilla. 3: Gradually pour over corn, mix well. 4: Turn into two large, shallow baking pans. 5: Bake at 250 degrees F for 1 hour, stir every 15 minutes. 6: Remove from oven, cool completely. 7: Break apart and store in tightly covered containers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3889,"Green Tomato Mincemeat","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Green Tomato Mincemeat recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",5.0,5.0,4826.3,51.7,11.1,0.0,4229.1,1136.5,58.0,1013.1,33.0,"1.0","Green Tomato Mincemeat Recipe Instructions:  1: This is the mincemeat I use all the time now. 2: Don''t peel tomatoes or apples. 3: Core and chop in processor. 4: Cook everything together slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. 5: Bottle in sterilized jars and hot water process for 25 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3890,"Cajun Crawfish Jambalaya","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cajun Crawfish Jambalaya recipe from Food.com.","Crawfish",0.0,0.0,4104.3,101.7,60.5,729.8,1172.8,654.2,19.0,12.2,126.2,"1.0","Cajun Crawfish Jambalaya Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute in margarine the bell pepper, garlic, onion, and celery. 2: Add 3: some of the crawfish fat for flavor. 4: Cook for about 30 minutes over a  low fire. Add crawfish tails, green onions, 2 T. 5: chopped parsley,  salt, pepper, cayenne pepper , and 4 cup of cooked rice. I sometimes  add a small can of stem and pieces mushrooms. 6: Let this steam for  about 5-10 minutes. 7: Add a little margarine or water if too dry.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3891,"Pappadeaux Crawfish Bisque","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pappadeaux Crawfish Bisque recipe from Food.com.","Crawfish",2.5,9.0,733.1,56.6,29.2,473.6,297.9,6.5,0.9,1.8,42.7,"6.0","Pappadeaux Crawfish Bisque Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil crawfish in a large pot of water. 2: Drain and cool until crawfish can be  handled easily, remove tail and save shells. Refrigerate tail meat. 3: Heat oil in  large sauce pan or Dutch oven. 4: Add crawfish shells, paprika and cayenne. Saute 5  minutes. 5: Add water and bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. 6: Strain  liquid into another pan. 7: Crush shells to remove remaining liquid and add that  liquid. Discard shells. 8: Return to heat and add onion, bell pepper, tomato paste,  cream and tomato. 9: Simmer 1 hour, stirring frequently. 10: Add brandy and crawfish  tail meat. Simmer 10 minutes. 11: Serve hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3892,"Oven Fried Chicken II","PT40M","PT10M","PT50M","Make and share this Oven Fried Chicken II recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",4.5,62.0,178.3,7.0,1.9,44.0,623.0,12.3,0.6,0.1,15.3,"4.0","Oven Fried Chicken II Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 450 2: Combine all dry ingredients in a plastic bag. 3: Wash your chicken and shake off excess water. 4: Drop in bag and shake each piece.  Place in a metal pan skin side down and put in preheated oven. 5: Turn pieces over after about 20 minutes. 6: Continue baking until crisp and browned.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3893,"Shrimp Fra Diavolo","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Shrimp Fra Diavolo recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.0,2.0,155.1,6.0,0.9,115.2,116.8,8.7,1.6,3.5,16.5,"6.0","Shrimp Fra Diavolo Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil for 3 minutes; 2: add remaining ingredients, except shrimp and pasta.  Simmer for 10 minutes. 3: Add shrimp and simmer until shrimp are translucent, about 4 minutes. 4: Cook pasta of choice according to directions, drain, and top with sauce. 5: We topped this dish with shredded cheddar cheese and black olives.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3896,"Oven-Dried Beef Jerky","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Oven-Dried Beef Jerky recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.0,1.0,64.6,0.1,0.0,0.0,4190.0,9.2,1.0,3.0,7.9,"1.0","Oven-Dried Beef Jerky Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim and discard all fat from meat. Slice meat in long 1/4-inch thick strips (easier if meat is partially frozen). Combine remaining ingredients. 2: Add meat strips, coating all surfaces. The meat will absorb most of  the liquid. v 3: Cover tightly (I use a Ziploc bag) and marinate overnight in refrigerator. 4: Drain off  any liquid. 5: Arrange meat strips together but not overlapping, directly on oven racks. 6: Dry meat at lowest oven temperature, 150 degrees to 200 degrees until meat turns brown, is dry and feels hard (about 10 hours or overnight). Cut into 1-inch pieces, using scissors. 7: Cool thoroughly before storing in airtight containers. Beef jerky keeps indefinitely at cool room temperature or in refrigerator.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3897,"Chocolate Espresso Fudge Cake","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","A smooth glaze sheathes discs of devil''s food cake and coffee-flavored ganache. The chocolate espresso fudge sauce echoes the coffee flavor in the ganache, and all is harmony on land and sea.","Dessert",0.0,1.0,1255.6,97.2,59.9,278.3,234.5,109.1,13.6,50.9,17.1,"8.0","Chocolate Espresso Fudge Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Make the devil''s food cake: Position a rack in the center of the oven and preheat to 350 degrees F. 2: Butter the bottom and sides o f a 17 1/2 by 11 1/2-inch jelly roll pan and line the bottom with baking parchment or waxed paper. Lightly dust the sides of the pan with flour and tap out the excess. 3: In the 4 1/2-quart bowl of a heavy-duty electric mixer, place the cake flour, sugar, cocoa powder, and baking powder. Using the paddle attachment, blend the dry ingredients on low speed, until combined. 4: Add the butter, one tablespoon at a time and continue to mix until the mixture resembles coarse meal. 5: At medium speed, beat in the water, scraping down the side of the bowl as necessary. Continue to beat the batter at medium speed for 2 minutes. 6: Beat in the eggs, one at a time, scralling down the sides of the bowl with a rubber spatula after each addition. 7: Scrape the batter into the prepared pan and, using an offset metal cake spatula, smooth it into an even layer. 8: Bake the cake for 18 to 22 minutes, until the cake springs back when gently touched in the center. 9: Run the tip of a knife around the edges of the pan. Invert the cake on to a wire rack. Carefully peel off the paper and cool the cake completely. 10: Make the chocolate espresso whipped garlache: 11: In a small cup, stir the espresso powder into the hot water until dissolved; set aside 12: Place the chocolate in a medium bowl: set aside. 13: In a small, heavy saucepan, combine the heavy cream and espresso mixture. Bring to a gentle boil. 14: Remove from heat and pour the mixture over the chocolate. Allow the mixt ure to stand for 1 minute to melt the chocolate. Gently whisk until smooth. 15: Cover the bowl and refrigerate the ganache for 2 hours, until chilled and slightly thickened. 16: Using a hand-held electric mixer, beat the ganache just until  lightened in color, about 30 seconds. Do not overbeat the ganache or it will become grainy. 17: Assemble the cakes: Using eight 3-inch (2 inches in height) metal ring molds, cut out 8 rounds of the devil''s food cake. Place the molds on a baking sheet and place a cake round in the bottom of each mold. 18: Fill a pastry bag fitted with a large plain tip with the whipped ganache. Pipe the ganache on top of each round, filling each mold to the top. 19: With a small, offset metal spatula, scrape the top of each mold to the level the ganache. Place the sheet of molds in the freezer for 2 hours. 20: Make the glaze: Place the chocolate in a medium bowl. 21: In a small saucepan, bring the cream and corn syrup to a gentle boil. 22: Pour the hot cream over the chocolate and let the mixture stand  for 1 minute to melt the chocolate. Gently whisk until smooth. 23: Cover the surface of the glaze with plastic wrap and let it stand at room temperature until ready to glaze the cakes. 24: Make the chocolate espresso fudge sauce: In a medium saucepan, stir together the cocoa, espresso powder and sugar. 25: Slowly whisk in the milk and cream. 26: Stir in the corn syrup. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until the sugar is completely dissolved. 27: Raise the heat to medium-high and while continuing to stir, bring the mixture to a boil. 28: Remove the pan from the heat and add the chocolate. Let the mixture stand for 30 seconds to melt the chocolate. Whisk until smooth. 29: Stir in the butter and vanilla. 30: Unmold and glaze the cakes: Remove the molds from the freezer. 31: Gently heat the side of each mold using a portable hair dryer or a hot, damp towel. Carefully slide off each mold. 32: Place the cakes on a wire rack set over a baking sheet. Place the baking sheet in the freezer for 15 minutes. 33: Remove the plastic wrap from the glaze and gently whisk until smooth. 34: Remove the desserts from the freezer and pour the glaze over each cake to coat it completely. 35: Place a spoonful of chocolate espresso fudge sauce on a dessert plate. Place a cake on top of the sauce; garnish with a candied violet, if desired. 36: Repeat with the remaining cakes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3899,"Justin Wilsons Crawfish or Shrimp Cocktail","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Justin Wilsons Crawfish or Shrimp Cocktail recipe from Food.com.","Crawfish",4.0,1.0,56.4,1.1,0.4,1.5,642.9,11.4,1.5,6.9,1.6,"6.0","Justin Wilsons Crawfish or Shrimp Cocktail Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients to make sauce. 2: Pour over crawfish or shrimp,   or dip the crawfish or shrimp in the sauce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3900,"Shrimp in Hot Cocktail Sauce","PT5M","PT5M","PT10M","Make and share this Shrimp in Hot Cocktail Sauce recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,3.0,177.1,2.4,0.7,277.6,609.6,6.5,0.8,3.3,30.8,"8.0","Shrimp in Hot Cocktail Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Add enough cold water to cover shrimp by 1 inch. 2: Add peppercorns, lemon peel, bay leaf and salt. Bring to boil high heat and boil shrimp 30 seconds or until just turn pink and just cooked. 3: Drain and rinse under running cold water and drain them thoroughly. 4: Sauce: In a bowl combine all ingredients and chill. 5: Line cocktail glasses with Bibb lettuce and add 1 tablespoon sauce to each glass. 6: Divide shrimp among the glasses and garnish them with the remaining sauce and a slice of lemon.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3902,"Vegetarian Mushroom Gravy","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Vegetarian Mushroom Gravy recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",4.5,3.0,126.7,0.7,0.1,0.0,7.6,24.7,2.1,2.4,7.1,"0.0","Vegetarian Mushroom Gravy Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine 1/3 cup stock and mushrooms in a heavy nonstick skillet over medium heat.  Saute mushrooms 7-8 minutes or until they begin to turn brown and liquid has almost evaporated. 2: Remove from heat and set aside.  Combine 1/4 cup stock and flour in a jar with a tight fitting lid. 3: Shake vigorously. 4: Combine with remaining stock in a heavy saucepan over high heat.  Bring to a boil. 5: Reduce heat to medium and simmer 15 minutes, whisking frequently, until mixture begins to thicken. 6: Add sauteed mushrooms and simmer until just heated throughout.  Season with salt and pepper to taste. Good luck, Robert");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3903,"Chocolate Almond Spoons","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chocolate Almond Spoons recipe from Food.com.","Microwave",5.0,2.0,5306.5,270.4,161.1,38.3,32.8,673.4,68.4,542.9,45.2,"4.0","Chocolate Almond Spoons Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine semisweet or sweet dark chocolate and whipping cream in a  1-cup liquid measuring cup. 2: Microwave at MEDIUM (50%) power 1 minute  or until chocolate melts, stirring after 30 seconds. 3: Stir in almond  extract.  Dip each spoon in melted chocolate covering bowl of spoon and 1/4  inch up handle;allow excess to drip off. 4: Place spoons on waxed paper  lined baking sheet; freeze 15 minutes or until set.  Melt vanilla coating and put in heavy duty zip lock bag. 5: Snip tiny  hole in one corner of bag, and drizzle coating over chilled spoons. 6: Leave on wax paper and store in refrigerator until ready to wrap. 7: I bought Handi wrap with little X-mas trees and candy canes at a  dollar store and plan to wrap about 3 together and tie with curling  ribbon. 8: I also guess you can substitute other extract flavors..mint,  strawberry, Amaretto etc. for the almond flavoring...Happy dipping  :-)");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3904,"Coffee House Chocolate Spoons","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Coffee House Chocolate Spoons recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,3.0,372.0,19.6,10.7,7.8,23.7,44.9,3.8,37.2,4.0,"4.0","Coffee House Chocolate Spoons Recipe Instructions:  1: Place a piece of waxed paper on a cookie sheet large enough to hold 20 to 24 of your plastic spoons. 2: Place semisweet chocolate pieces in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until the chocolate begins to melt. Immediately remove from heat; stir until smooth. 3: Dip spoons into chocolate, tapping the handle of the spoon against the side of the pan to remove excess chocolate. Place spoons on waxed paper; refrigerate for 30 minutes or until chocolate is set. 4: Place milk chocolate (or chocolate of your choice) in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until chocolate begins to melt. Immediately remove from heat; stir until smooth. Place the melted chocolate in a small, heavy self sealing bag. 5: Using scissors, make a small cut  in the corner of the bag; drizzle on or both sides of the covered spoons, making a decorative pattern. 6: (Small dots, zig-zag lines, circles, etc.) Refrigerate spoons for 30 minutes to allow chocolate to set. Wrap each spoon separately in clear or colored plastic wrap. 7: Use ribbon to tie off plastic wrap. Store in a cool dry place for 2 to 3 weeks until ready to give as gifts.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3905,"Caesar Salad","0","PT20M","PT20M","Here''s the best one I''ve found.  I found the recipe in the guest newsletter of the Elora Mill Inn, Elora, ON, CA.  I''ve been making it for years and everyone likes it.","< 30 Mins",5.0,7.0,189.6,20.2,3.1,83.0,32.5,1.3,0.1,0.3,1.3,"0.0","Caesar Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: For the salad you will need 1 head Romaine lettuce, freshly grated Parmesan cheese (to taste), home made croutons, bacon bits (optional: home made are best), and lemon wedges. 2: Make the dressing: Mix the pepper, garlic & egg yolks in a bowl. Slowly whisk in oil so the mixture thickens a bit.  Add Tabasco, mustard, Worcestershire, vinegar & lemon juice.  Whisk well. Salt to taste. 3: The dressing will keep in refrigerator for a little while if tightly covered with Saran Wrap. 4: The eggs will cause a skin to form eventually. If this happens, strain the dressing or whisk well before use. 5: Wash lettuce. Discard any damaged leaves. 6: Tear the good leaves into bite size pieces. 7: Put into salad bowl. 8: Add some dressing & toss to coat.  Add Parmesan, croutons & bacon bits. 9: Toss well to coat.  If too dry, add more dressing. 10: Serve immediately. 11: Offer lemon wedges & more Parmesan. 12: Accept praise gracefully. 13: Notes: 14: It barely makes enough dressing for one head of lettuce.  If it turns out too dry, just use less lettuce next time. 15: Tell your guests if they really want to ruin this great salad they can bring their OWN anchovies 16: If it''s too garlicky, strain the garlic solids out of the dressing before you serve [but CAN a dish be too garlicky?]. 17: If you want extra zing, use 2 - 3 dashes of Tabasco [be careful, a little bit goes a long way!].");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3906,"Peanut Butter Brownies","PT35M","PT15M","PT50M","Make and share this Peanut Butter Brownies recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",3.5,3.0,415.1,20.2,7.5,64.0,301.1,52.8,2.1,35.9,8.8,"0.0","Peanut Butter Brownies Recipe Instructions:  1: In small bowl, combine flour baking powder and salt.  In large bowl, cream butter, peanut butter, sugars and vanilla until smooth. 2: Beat in eggs one at a time.  Blend in flour mixture. Spread evenly in ungreased  15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. 3: Sprinkle surface with peanuts (lightly press into  batter). Bake 25-30 minutes at 350°F, then cool completely. 4: Cut into 2-inch squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3907,"Nippy Horseradish Cheese Spread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Nippy Horseradish Cheese Spread recipe from Food.com.","Spreads",5.0,1.0,1761.2,154.1,91.9,488.5,2588.8,28.3,4.7,19.9,71.7,"1.0","Nippy Horseradish Cheese Spread Recipe Instructions:  1: In top of double boiler over boiling water, combine the  cream cheese and Cheddar cheese. Stir until cheeses are melted  and blended together. 2: Add the mayonnaise and the horseradish. 3: Turn into bowl and let stand for at least 30 minutes for  flavors to blend. 4: Good served at room temperature or chilled. 5: To store, place in a covered container and refrigerate. For  dipping or spreading, fresh vegetables, Melba toast or crisp  crackers of your choice. Will keep in refrigerator for 2  weeks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3908,"Pier 4''s Cheese Spread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pier 4''s Cheese Spread recipe from Food.com.","Spreads",0.0,0.0,4315.5,367.1,232.0,1140.0,6308.7,17.0,0.2,8.0,230.3,"0.0","Pier 4''s Cheese Spread Recipe Instructions:  1: Have all ingredients at room   temperature. Using an  electric mixer, blend cream cheese and butter. 2: With mixer  still running, add the Cheddar cheese in small pieces until  blended. 3: Add remaining ingredients and continue to blend until  mixture is smooth and creamy. 4: Refrigerate until 1 hour before  serving. 5: Serve at room temperature.");
