INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3912,"Hot Cheese Toast","PT15M","PT10M","PT25M","Make and share this Hot Cheese Toast recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",0.0,0.0,1144.7,84.5,45.0,243.8,1974.8,22.3,3.5,5.2,74.8,"0.0","Hot Cheese Toast Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Mix all ingredients together; spread on slices of party rye bread. 3: Place on cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes. 4: Mixture can be kept in a sealed container for snacks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3913,"Cheese Toast","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cheese Toast recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",0.0,0.0,400.0,23.1,13.5,80.2,1291.3,31.6,1.0,0.7,16.7,"0.0","Cheese Toast Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter in a small saucepan. 2: Stir in flour and  salt. Stir in milk gradually and continue stirring over low  heat until sauce thickens and boils. 3: Add cheese, stir until  melted and pour over toast.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3915,"Rancheros Cookies","PT8M","PT20M","PT28M","Make and share this Rancheros Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",4.5,3.0,96.8,5.2,1.8,5.2,40.3,12.0,0.7,7.2,1.4,"72.0","Rancheros Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). 2: Sift together flour, salt,  baking soda and baking powder and set aside; Cream together shortening, brown  sugar and white sugar until light and fluffy; Beat in eggs, vanilla and  coconut. Add sifted ingredients and mix well; Stir in oatmeal, chocolate chips  and nuts, Mix thoroughly. 3: Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheets; Bake for 8--12 minutes until golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3916,"Oatmeal Chocolate Chip Cookies","PT12M","PT0S","PT12M","Make and share this Oatmeal Chocolate Chip Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",5.0,19.0,131.3,5.7,3.2,20.5,175.6,19.3,1.3,10.9,2.0,"0.0","Oatmeal Chocolate Chip Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat together the butter or margarine, eggs, brown sugar and vanilla. 2: Add oats, flours, baking soda, salt and chocolate chips. 3: Bake at 325°F (170°C) for 10-12 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3917,"Oatmeal Chocolate Chip Cookies (No Eggs)","PT36M","PT10M","PT46M","Make and share this Oatmeal Chocolate Chip Cookies (No Eggs) recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",5.0,89.0,137.9,7.6,4.5,13.6,114.8,17.4,1.0,9.7,1.5,"0.0","Oatmeal Chocolate Chip Cookies (No Eggs) Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat butter or margarine, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy. 2: Add  flour  and salt, mix well. 3: Dissolve baking soda in boiling water and add to mixture.  Stir in rolled oats, raisins and chocolate chips. 4: Drop by teaspoonful onto  ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees F  (175 degrees C) for 10-12  minutes. 5: Don''t over cook. 6: (There are no eggs in  this recipe, I didn''t forget to type it down).   Makes 3 dozen");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3918,"Pumpkin Bread Pudding with Pecans","0","PT0S","PT0S","Although I like traditional pumpkin pie, everyone needs a change now and then. Try this new twist on an old favorite, whether it''s for a holiday or just for a cozy night at home.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,302.2,15.6,5.1,106.8,283.9,33.2,2.3,9.7,8.4,"12.0","Pumpkin Bread Pudding with Pecans Recipe Instructions:  1: Line a 10-inch springform pan with foil. Place diced bread and toasted pecans in foil-lined pan, mix, and set aside. 2: In a medium-size bowl, mix half-and-half, pumpkin, and 3/4 cup sugar. 3: Add brown sugar, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, ground and crystallized ginger, nutmeg, and allspice. Pour over the bread and mix well. 4: Let stand for about 20 minutes, while preheating oven to 350. 5: Mix again before placing in oven. 6: Bake for 45 minutes, or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean To serve, slice pudding into individual servings. 7: Sprinkle each with about 2 teaspoons of sugar and caramelize the sugar with a propane torch. 8: If you do not have a torch available, serve warm with softly whipped cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3919,"Veal Orloff","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Veal Orloff recipe from Food.com.","Veal",5.0,1.0,5381.1,410.6,257.8,1297.2,2515.8,275.1,7.0,20.6,170.4,"1.0","Veal Orloff Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim excess fat from 1/2 veal short loin with bone.  Salt and pepper rack of veal and roast at 350 degrees for one hour. 2: Remove the eye of veal from the rack, saving the rack bones intact. 3: While the veal is cooking, bring 1/2 quart of milk to  boil. Saute 1 pound of onion, diced fine, in 6 ounces clarified butter. When onions are translucent (cooked until very  soft) add enough flour to absorb all butter. 4: Cook over low  heat for 10 minutes, taking care not to burn or color flour. 5: Add hot milk to onion flour mix and whip until thick. 6: Slice 1/2 pound of Prosciutto ham in small julienne slices 2-inches  long. 7: Dice 1 pound mushrooms very fine. Saute mushrooms in 4  ounce clarified butter. When cooked, drain excess liquid. 8: Add julienne of Prosciutto to mushrooms and cook briefly. 9: Add Madeira wine and chopped truffles. Add mushrooms, ham, truffle mix to the onion and milk sauce. Adjust seasoning with salt  and white pepper. 10: If mix is too loose, tighten with crushed  Ritz crackers. 11: Place empty rack (bones) on platter. Put a generous  amount of stuffing on bottom of rack. 12: Slice the eye of veal in  6 to 8 slices. 13: Place the slices, one at a time on top of stuffing. Between each slice put stuffing and shingle the  slices of veal. When complete, add more stuffing on top and  sides. 14: Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and chopped truffles on top,  and bake in a 350 degrees oven for 20 minutes, or until stuffing is  bubbling. 15: Serve with Perigodine sauce, which is a standard  brown sauce with Madeira wine and truffles.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3921,"Eggs, Cheese and Truffles","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Eggs, Cheese and Truffles recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",0.0,0.0,303.9,25.9,13.1,470.0,373.9,1.0,0.0,1.0,16.3,"4.0","Eggs, Cheese and Truffles Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt the butter in a large skillet and set over low heat. Add the cheese and let it melt. 2: Add the slices of truffle and mix well. 3: Break the eggs onto the cheese and truffles and season with salt and pinch of nutmeg. 4: Let the eggs set 5 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3922,"Lobster Tetrazzini","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lobster Tetrazzini recipe from Food.com.","Lobster",0.0,0.0,496.3,21.9,12.8,352.4,1055.5,25.3,1.2,1.6,43.1,"0.0","Lobster Tetrazzini Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut the meat from 4 pounds boiled lobster into strips,  reserving any coral. 2: Simmer the water the lobster was cooked  in until it is reduced to 2 cups and reserve it. Saute 1/2  pounds mushrooms thinly sliced in 3 tablespoons butter until  they are soft and lightly browned and reserve them. 3: In a  saucepan melt 3 tablespoons butter, stir in 2 tablespoons flour  and cook (the roux), stirring for a few minutes. 4: Add the  lobster coral and stir in gradually the  reserved cooking  liquid. 5: Cook the sauce, stirring, until it is smooth and  thick. 6: Then stir in 1 cup heavy cream and 3 tablespoons of  sherry. 7: Add a pinch of nutmeg and salt and pepper to taste.  Simmer the sauce for 10 minutes. 8: Add the lobster meat, the  mushrooms and 1/2 cup diced truffles. 9: Arrange 1/2 pound hot  cooked spaghetti in coils on platter. 10: Make a well in center of  the spaghetti and pour in the lobster sauce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3924,"Cheese Toast II","PT15M","PT0S","PT15M","I don''t know if this is the Texas Cheese Toast, but it sounds good! Here in East Texas we call Texas Toast the thick sliced loaf of bread that comes from Sunbeam. You could use that instead of french bread....","Breads",3.0,1.0,638.4,35.7,21.1,89.0,1123.0,60.1,3.5,0.5,19.2,"0.0","Cheese Toast II Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix first 5 ingredients. 2: In large skillet melt butter over low heat. Add garlic to butter. 3: Put  1/4 loaf of bread face down in butter. Be sure entire face of bread is coated. 4: Brush the back of the bread with butter from the pan. 5: Put the bread on a cookie sheet and spread cheese mixture over the face of the bread. 6: Heat for 8-10 minutes in 450 degree oven until edges begin to turn brown. 7: Broil quickly for 1-2 minutes if you like it crispier.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3925,"Nan''s Best Dark Fruitcake:","PT2H","PT30M","PT2H30M","Make and share this Nan''s Best Dark Fruitcake: recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,179.9,6.2,1.4,25.4,62.1,28.4,1.3,19.9,2.2,"50.0","Nan''s Best Dark Fruitcake: Recipe Instructions:  1: With 3/4 cup of the dark rum, pour over chopped fruit and nuts. Cover and let soak for at least 48 hours. The fruit should be stirred once a day or so. 2: Keep remaining rum for after baking directions -- see below. 3: Stir flour, salt, baking  soda and spices together Set aside. 4: In separate bowl, Cream shortening and brown sugar together till fluffy. 5: Add eggs and beat one at a time. 6: Add molasses, jam  and mix well. 7: Blend in dry ingredients. Fold in fruit. 8: Prepare your round fruit cake pan by oiling and line pan with paper. Oil and flour again lightly. 9: Ensure the top of the paper is about 1 inch or so above the top of the pan. 10: Fill prepared pans 2/3 full. 11: Bake in a slow oven 300°F for 2 hours or so. 12: Place a shallow pan of hot water on the bottom rack of the oven during baking. This will ensure the cake stays moist. Remove this pan of water during the last hour of  baking. 13: Cool completely before removing paper. 14: Storing and mellowing of fruit Cake: Wrap a cheese cloth that has been soaked  in the remaining 1/4 cup of rum over the cake, covering it completely. 15: Next wrap the cake and cheesecloth in aluminum foil wrap. 16: Place in a cool place.  Taste of cake is best when stored for 4 weeks or so!  I''ve often brushed egg white over the cake, rolled out almond paste and laid it over the top and sides of cake. I then ice it. Everyone raves!  NOTE: I''ve often doubled the recipe for a larger cake.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3926,"Godiva Chocolate Layer Cake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Godiva Chocolate Layer Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,4.0,555.1,33.2,20.4,124.8,199.7,65.1,4.1,43.1,7.0,"12.0","Godiva Chocolate Layer Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: For the buttercream: cream butter until smooth. 2: Sift the sugar and cocoa powder over the butter, add 1/3 cup of Godiva liqueur and slowly mix until smooth. 3: For the cake: sift together the flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. 4: Cream the butter and sugar and add the eggs one at a time beating after each addition. 5: On low speed, stir in the chocolate and gradually add the reserved sifted ingredients in three additions, alternating with the buttermilk and 1/2 of the liqueur, beat until smooth. 6: Divide the batter among 3 greased and floured 9\ 7: ,  8: ,  9: ,  10: ,  11: ,  12: Serve immediately or refrigerate. If not serving immediately and have it stored in the refrigerator, remove the cake 1 hour prior to serving. 13: Garnish with chocolate curls if using.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3927,"Boursin Cheese Spread","PT10M","PT10M","PT20M","Make and share this Boursin Cheese Spread recipe from Food.com.","Spreads",5.0,2.0,2123.6,226.4,134.8,664.4,2223.4,13.2,0.2,9.8,19.4,"0.0","Boursin Cheese Spread Recipe Instructions:  1: Blend all ingredients together in mixer. 2: Pack into container and chill until ready to serve. 3: Serve with crackers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3928,"Basic Cocktail Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Basic Cocktail Sauce recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.0,3.0,117.0,0.6,0.1,0.0,1097.4,31.2,1.5,24.4,2.1,"0.0","Basic Cocktail Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Shake all ingredients until well mixed. 2: Add celery salt and tabasco  sauce to your taste. Chill and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3929,"Sweet Potato Pecan Pie IIi","PT45M","PT15M","PT1H","Make and share this Sweet Potato Pecan Pie IIi recipe from Food.com.","Pie",3.0,1.0,3173.7,202.2,57.3,767.9,2793.0,314.9,21.1,144.9,45.2,"0.0","Sweet Potato Pecan Pie IIi Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream the butter and sugar together. 2: Add the sweet potatoes and eggs. 3: Mix well. 4: Combine with syrup, milk, salt, vanilla, and pecans. 5: Line  pie pan with the pastry shell. 6: Turn mixture into the pan. 7: Bake for 10  minutes in a 425* oven. 8: After the 10 minutes have expired, reduce  heat to 325* and bake for 35 - 45 minutes longer. 9: FOR REGULAR Sweet potato pie: OMIT the pecans and INCREASE the amount of potatoes to 1 1/2 cups.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3930,"Fruit Pound Cake","PT1H19M","PT20M","PT1H39M","Make and share this Fruit Pound Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,4735.6,250.2,61.8,1057.5,4081.6,573.1,16.1,353.6,66.3,"0.0","Fruit Pound Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream shortening and sugar together. 2: Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating  after each addition. 3: Add flour, salt, mace. Mix again. 4: Add vanilla  and beat. Add remaining ingredients and mix very well. 5: Bake in a  greased loaf pan for 60 -80 minutes with the oven temp set at 350*. 6: **NOTE: To make a basic pound cake, the use above recipe, OMITTING  the fruit and follow directions for baking/preparing.**.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3931,"Pork Pie II","PT55M","PT15M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Pork Pie II recipe from Food.com.","Pork",0.0,0.0,1038.9,52.6,16.1,157.4,1235.8,67.6,3.4,3.5,70.0,"0.0","Pork Pie II Recipe Instructions:  1: Roll out dough to fit a 9 inch pie plate. Place ground pork, rosemary, bread  crumbs, parsley, and onion in a medium-size bowl; mix until well blended. 2: Remove casings from sausage, and crumble into the mixture. Season with salt and pepper  to  taste. Sprinkle 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese into the bottom of pie shell. 3: Spread pork mixture on top of cheese, and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. 4: Place top crust over filling, and crimp the edges together. 5: Bake at 500 degrees  F (260 degrees C) for 15 minutes. 6: Reduce heat to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C),  and bake for 35 to 40 minutes. 7: Makes 1 - 9 inch pie.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3932,"Party Cheese Ball","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Party Cheese Ball recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",4.5,2.0,2511.7,233.1,147.3,736.3,2859.5,19.7,0.6,4.3,90.8,"1.0","Party Cheese Ball Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine cream cheese and cheddar cheese, mixing until well  blended. 2: Add  remaining ingredients; mix well. 3: Chill for 1/2-1 hour and then form into a  ball. 4: Roll ball in the chopped nuts until well covered. 5: Keep in refrigerator  until ready to serve. Can be made up to 48 hrs prior to serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3933,"White Chocolate Brownies","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this White Chocolate Brownies recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",3.5,2.0,5711.9,212.6,60.7,1304.4,1769.7,887.9,16.8,725.1,95.5,"1.0","White Chocolate Brownies Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt chocolate over warm water. 2: Melt butter. 3: Let both  cool. 4: Beat eggs and sugar together. 5: Stir in almond extract,  chocolate and butter. 6: Fold in flour, salt and walnuts. 7: Blend  thoroughly. 8: Pour into a buttered 12 x 18-inch baking pan and  bake in a preheated 325 degrees oven for 25 to 30 minutes. 9: Cool and  cut into squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3936,"Honey Bar Brownies","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Make and share this Honey Bar Brownies recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",0.0,0.0,327.4,18.2,2.3,14.2,23.6,39.9,1.2,26.2,2.9,"15.0","Honey Bar Brownies Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix all ingredients by hand. 2: Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. 3: Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees. 4: Do not overbake. Cool 15 minutes. 5: Icing: Melt butter; add milk and blend powdered sugar in bowl. 6: Then pour on brownies.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3937,"Grandma''s Oatmeal Toll-House Cookies","PT10M","PT20M","PT30M","Make and share this Grandma''s Oatmeal Toll-House Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",5.0,4.0,6084.1,327.7,116.1,372.0,3824.7,780.5,41.2,495.9,67.5,"1.0","Grandma''s Oatmeal Toll-House Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees 2: In large mixing bowl add the sugar, eggs and  shortening.  Blend  together. 3: Slowly add the flour, salt and baking soda and  mix well. 4: Add the water, vanilla and chocolate chips and mix. 5: Add oatmeal and  mix until all ingredients are blended together. 6: Using a spoon, drop dough onto  cookie sheet.  Bake for 8-10 minutes or until cookies appear a golden brown.   Repeat until all dough is used. 7: The size of the spoon will determine the size of the cookie.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3938,"Easy Pumpkin Dessert","PT45M","PT15M","PT1H","Make and share this Easy Pumpkin Dessert recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,16.0,290.9,14.0,5.2,54.9,259.8,38.3,0.8,24.3,4.7,"0.0","Easy Pumpkin Dessert Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix together pumpkin, eggs, spice, milk, and sugar. Pour into a greased 9 x 13  pan. 2: Sprinkle dry cake mix on top. 3: Pour melted butter over top and then sprinkle with walnuts. 4: Bake at 350 for 45 minutes until set. Serve with ice cream or cool whip.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3939,"Unbaked Chocolate Chip Oatmeal Cookies","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Unbaked Chocolate Chip Oatmeal Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",4.5,7.0,157.3,5.0,2.7,10.9,30.3,26.5,1.5,16.9,2.5,"24.0","Unbaked Chocolate Chip Oatmeal Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Put first 4 ingredients into a 2 quart saucepan and bring to a full,  rolling boil. 2: Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter. 3: Add  oatmeal and stir well. 4: Drop teaspoonfuls onto a well greased cookie  sheet. Chill for 1 hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3940,"Baked Salmon in Potato Shells","PT2H","PT20M","PT2H20M","Make and share this Baked Salmon in Potato Shells recipe from Food.com.","Potato",4.5,6.0,335.5,7.1,2.9,56.3,366.4,49.0,5.9,3.1,19.9,"8.0","Baked Salmon in Potato Shells Recipe Instructions:  1: Flake the salmon and try removing all bones and skin as much as  possible. 2: Slice tops of of the potatoes and scoop out. Put the shells  **skin of the potatoes** off to the side. In a bowl, mash the potato  meat, adding the milk and seasonings. 3: Add the salmon. Mix lightly. 4: Stuff the potato shells with the potato and salmon mixture. 5: Top it  off with the bread crumbs. Dot with the butter. 6: Bake at 400* for 25  minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3941,"Chicken Quesadillas","PT15M","PT5M","PT20M","I have found that it works great to make the &quot;filling&quot; up a head of time. Just prep and put in the refrigerator until needed. This is one of our favorite meals. NOTE: The friend who gave me this recipe uses canned cooked chicken. I''m sure the other precooked chicken tenders they sell now would also work.","Chicken Breast",5.0,28.0,356.6,16.1,7.1,52.9,798.0,31.9,2.5,2.6,20.5,"10.0","Chicken Quesadillas Recipe Instructions:  1: Broil the chicken for about 5 minutes on each side, or until no longer pink inside. Cool and then shred or cube the chicken. (I have found the slicer in my salad shooter works great for this!). 2: Mix chicken, salsa and cheese in a bowl. 3: Place 1/10th of the mixture on half of the tortilla, fold over and press down slightly to \ 4: . You can moisten the edges with water to help the edges seal but I usually don''t. I''ve found pressing firmly so that the tortilla sticks to the mixtures works fine. 5: Bake at 400°F for about 5 minutes or until tortillas start to brown. 6: Serve with additional salsa, sour cream, or guacamole for dipping. 7: Goes well with refried beans and/or Spanish Rice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3942,"Vanilla Cream Filling for Doughnuts","PT25M","PT10M","PT35M","Make and share this Vanilla Cream Filling for Doughnuts recipe from Food.com.","Breads",3.0,2.0,668.8,26.7,15.1,347.9,503.6,94.9,0.6,67.0,13.9,"0.0","Vanilla Cream Filling for Doughnuts Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix flour, sugar, and salt together. 2: Add the dry ingredients to the scalded milk--add all slowly/stirring. 3: Heat over a double boiler until thick and smooth. **about 15 minutes**. 4: Add butter. 5: Pour mixture over the egg yolks, stirring constantly. 6: Cool and add vanilla.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3943,"Beef Stuffed Acorn Squash II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Beef Stuffed Acorn Squash II recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",4.5,5.0,1212.0,91.4,40.0,143.3,652.9,74.7,4.4,0.6,23.8,"2.0","Beef Stuffed Acorn Squash II Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut squash in half; discard seeds. Sprinkle squash with a little salt. Bake, cut  side down in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish at 350 degrees until tender, 45 to 50  minutes. 2: Cook beef, onions and celery until meat is brown. 3: Drain off fat; stir in flour, salt and sage. 4: Add milk. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. 5: Stir in rice. Turn squash, cut side up, and fill with meat mixture. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes. 6: Top with cheese. Bake 3 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3946,"Candied Acorn Squash","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Candied Acorn Squash recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,24.0,223.2,7.9,4.9,20.3,78.1,40.4,3.3,16.8,1.8,"8.0","Candied Acorn Squash Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut squash in half lengthwise. Scoop out and discard seeds. Cut squash crosswise  into 1-inch slices. 2: Arrange slices slightly overlapping, in a buttered 13 x 9 x  2-inch baking dish. Bake, covered, in a 375 degrees oven for 35 minutes or until  almost tender. 3: Combine melted butter, brown sugar, syrup and cinnamon. 4: Spoon over squash. 5: Continue baking, uncovered, 15 minutes or until squash is tender,  basting occasionally with syrup mixture from bottom of pan.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3947,"South Carolina Scrapple","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this South Carolina Scrapple recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",0.0,0.0,610.1,22.4,7.2,190.4,153.8,33.0,3.3,1.0,65.9,"6.0","South Carolina Scrapple Recipe Instructions:  1: Select three pounds of bony pieces of pork.  For each pound of meat use a quart of water and simmer until the meat drops from the bone. Remove the meat from bones carefully being certain to get all the small pieces. 2: Bring the remaining broth to boiling point, adding sufficient water to make two cups. 3: Slowly add two cups of corn meal and cook until the mixture becomes a thick mush, stirring constantly. 4: Chop the meat and put it in the pot; also add salt, pepper and the juice of an onion. 5: Cook for two minutes, stirring constantly. 6: Pour the hot scrapple into a dampened oblong pan. 7: Let stand until cold and firm. 8: Slice and brown in hot skillet.  If the scrapple is rich with fat, no more fat is required for frying.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3948,"Golden Fruitcake I","PT2H30M","PT15M","PT2H45M","Make and share this Golden Fruitcake I recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,1.0,4580.1,235.2,121.7,802.0,4150.7,575.6,38.6,309.8,80.5,"0.0","Golden Fruitcake I Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter, add sugar gradually and continue beating. 2: Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. 3: Add orange juice, raisins, candied fruit, coconut and nuts. 4: Fold in sifted dry ingredients. 5: Turn into greased, double wax paper lined loaf pan and bake at 275°F for 2-1/2 to 3 hours. 6: Cool in pan for 10 minutes. 7: Turn out and cool completely on rack. 8: Wrap in plastic wrap; store for 3-5 weeks before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3950,"E. R. Rogers'' Baked Salmon Supreme","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this E. R. Rogers'' Baked Salmon Supreme recipe from Food.com.","Very Low Carbs",0.0,0.0,1117.0,77.7,42.6,353.0,1225.9,6.1,1.1,2.2,83.0,"2.0","E. R. Rogers'' Baked Salmon Supreme Recipe Instructions:  1: Place salmon in a small baking dish, skin side down. 2: Cover with wine,  butter and juice of the lemon. 3: Spread mustard evenly on top of each  fillet. Cover pan with foil and bake in a preheated 400 degrees oven for 8  to 10 minutes. 4: Remove from oven. 5: Cover salmon with cheese and sprinkle  with dill. 6: Return to oven until cheese has melted. 7: Place 4 shrimp on each  fillet and serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3951,"Baked Salmon (with Lime, Jalapeno Chive and Sour Cream Sauce)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Baked Salmon (with Lime, Jalapeno Chive and Sour Cream Sauce) recipe from Food.com.","Mexican",5.0,26.0,347.2,20.8,9.4,113.5,209.3,2.8,0.4,2.1,36.0,"2.0","Baked Salmon (with Lime, Jalapeno Chive and Sour Cream Sauce) Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 500 degrees. 2: Butter baking dish. Place salmon in dish skin  side down. 3: Mix lime juice and butter. Brush over salmon. 4: Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Let stand 15 minutes. 5: Bake until fish is almost opaque,  about 9 minutes per inch of thickness. 6: Meanwhile prepare sauce: 7: Melt  butter in heavy small saucepan over medium-low heat. Add chilies and cook  until tender, stirring occasionally, about 3 minutes. 8: Add sour cream and  stir until heated through; do not boil. 9: Mix in lime juice. Add salt and  pepper. 10: Transfer fish to platter. Spoon sauce over. 11: Sprinkle generously with chives. 12: Garnish with lime wedges.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3952,"Parmesan Crusted & Baked Salmon","PT25M","PT10M","PT35M","Make and share this Parmesan Crusted & Baked Salmon recipe from Food.com.","< 60 Mins",4.5,139.0,512.8,13.6,2.9,106.8,604.0,39.0,2.4,3.4,54.8,"2.0","Parmesan Crusted & Baked Salmon Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Fillet salmon and place skin side down on a glass baking dish. 3: Spread a generous amount of mayonnaise; cover entire top of fish. 4: Sprinkle liberally with seasoned salt, cheese and dry bread crumbs. 5: Bake about 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered. 6: Place under broiler until top turns brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3953,"Chinese Garlic Sauce","PT5M","PT5M","PT10M","Make and share this Chinese Garlic Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Chinese",4.5,2.0,668.7,57.3,10.0,7.2,3300.5,31.3,1.0,4.1,9.6,"0.0","Chinese Garlic Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat wok or deep pan over high heat until it is hot.  Add oil and wait until it is smoking, add ginger and garlic and leave for a minute or so. 2: Then add the oyster sauce and stock simmering for another few minutes. 3: Pour over your favorite fried rice, white rice or meat, especially chicken.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3956,"Herb-Baked Salmon","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Herb-Baked Salmon recipe from Food.com.","High Protein",4.5,13.0,342.1,9.4,1.8,78.4,442.5,21.1,2.1,1.9,41.0,"2.0","Herb-Baked Salmon Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 F. Line a baking tray with foil. Spray with  vegetable oil. 2: Wash salmon, pat dry and spread mustard over top. 3: Mix together parsley, oregano, thyme and bread crumbs. Season with salt and  pepper. Blend in egg white to bind mixture together. 4: Spread over the  mustard. 5: Bake 20 minutes for 1-inch thick fillet, 25 minutes for 2-inch  fillet.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3957,"Mustard Baked Salmon","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Mustard Baked Salmon recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,1.0,285.6,19.6,4.3,10.0,361.1,23.9,2.4,4.4,4.8,"4.0","Mustard Baked Salmon Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix in bowl: Lemon juice, lemon rind and both mustards. 2: Slowly pour in oil  and blend until medium-thick sauce forms. 3: Add breadcrumbs. (Can be made 1  day ahead and chilled). 4: Preheat oven to 375 (F) degrees. 5: Lightly grease  9x13-inch baking dish. 6: Arrange salmon in prepared dish, skin side down. 7: Press breadcrumb mixture onto fish. 8: Bake salmon until cooked through and  golden brown, about 18 minutes. 9: Using large spatula as aid, transfer salmon fillets to platter. 10: Serve, passing the following mustard sauce separately. 11: MUSTARD SAUCE: 12: Combine Mustard Sauce ingredients, mix with whisk in  bowl and serve with prepared salmon.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3958,"Baked Salmon with Herb Sauce","PT12M","PT5M","PT17M","Make and share this Baked Salmon with Herb Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Microwave",5.0,3.0,244.1,10.4,3.2,86.1,154.4,0.5,0.2,0.1,35.1,"4.0","Baked Salmon with Herb Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut fillet in 4 serving pieces. Place large side of fillet toward edge of  Pyrex baking dish with center open. Pierce fish, dot fish with butter, and  cover with plastic wrap. 2: Microwave Medium (50%) for 5 minutes. 3: Mix mayonnaise, parsley, onion, and dill together. 4: Spread mayonnaise mixture  on top of fillets and microwave Medium (50%) covered for 5-6 minutes  before serving. 5: Garnish with lemon wedges. 6: If steaks are used, arrange with thin ends toward center of dish. 7: One inch steaks should be microwaved 5 minutes a medium power,  covered with mayonnaise mixture and microwaved for 5-6 minutes longer.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3960,"China Bayles'' Baked Salmon","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this China Bayles'' Baked Salmon recipe from Food.com.","Very Low Carbs",0.0,0.0,564.1,11.0,1.8,165.4,224.8,6.1,0.0,2.3,63.6,"1.0","China Bayles'' Baked Salmon Recipe Instructions:  1: Place salmon on foil large enough to fold into a packet. Fold up the sides. 2: Scatter the cilantro and parsley on top. Pour on the wine. 3: Continue to fold the foil into a package, sealing the end and placing on a baking sheet. Bake in preheated 450F oven for 12 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3961,"Louisiana Hot Chili Pie","PT45M","PT0S","PT45M","Make and share this Louisiana Hot Chili Pie recipe from Food.com.","< 60 Mins",0.0,0.0,5195.9,423.9,184.0,1022.0,5030.1,122.9,20.2,50.9,226.2,"1.0","Louisiana Hot Chili Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute meat and drain; add onions, garlic, bell peppers and celery (after chopping fine in food processor). 2: Cook until cooked down. Season to taste with salt and pepper. 3: Add chili mix, tomato sauce, hot pepper (chopped)  and corn with juice. Mix well (if a little too thick, add chicken broth  until desired consistency). Simmer for about 15 minutes. 4: Spray pan (sheet cake size) with Pam and pour mixture in it. Top with Jiffy mix and can milk mixture. (Fix only when ready for this step. Mix box with 1 cup milk  and spread on top of mixture.) 5: Top with Cheddar cheese and sprinkle  Parmesan cheese on top. 6: Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3962,"Roley Poley Pork Roll","PT1H15M","PT15M","PT1H30M","Make and share this Roley Poley Pork Roll recipe from Food.com.","Pork",0.0,1.0,646.3,27.0,8.6,222.2,660.4,29.7,3.4,9.9,66.8,"6.0","Roley Poley Pork Roll Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Combine ground pork, tomato sauce, egg, green pepper and thyme or sausage seasoning; mix lightly. 3: Put meat mixture into 8 x 10 x 1/2-inch rectangle. 4: Top with mixture of remaining ingredients (cornbread mixture). 5: Spread not quite to edge. 6: Roll up jelly roll fashion. 7: Place on baking sheet. 8: Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3963,"Maraschino Cake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Maraschino Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,1.0,477.6,18.7,4.5,4.3,527.6,71.6,1.8,37.7,7.5,"8.0","Maraschino Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Prepare cake pans. 2: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a mixing bowl. 3: Add shortening, milk and flavoring. Beat 2 minutes. 4: Add another 1/3 cup milk and unbeaten egg whites. Beat 2 minutes more. 5: Pour cake batter into prepared cake pan(s). 6: Frost with your favorite white frosting using cherry juice for liquid called for in recipe. 7: Decorate with stems on maraschino cherries.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3964,"Stuffed Artichokes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Stuffed Artichokes recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,111.6,3.5,0.8,18.7,139.2,14.2,7.1,0.3,9.0,"10.0","Stuffed Artichokes Recipe Instructions:  1: Take out all the thick leaves around the artichoke. Cut the top horizontally.  Cut the base, too. With a tablespoon remove the hairy center, making a well in the center. 2: Do the same thing with the rest, putting them in a pan filled with water and 1/4 cup lemon juice when you finish each one, in order to preserve its color. 3: With one tablespoon butter, stir the meat, onions and pine nuts till brown. 4: Add the seasoning. 5: Fry the drained artichoke with 5 tablespoons vegetable oil till slightly brown. Drain. 6: Arrange in pan, pour in it a cup of water and 1/4 cup lemon juice. Stuff the artichokes with the meat mixture. Adjust the seasoning. 7: Bake in a 350 degree oven for 30 minutes till they are tender. 8: Serve with Aroz Mofalfal and green mixed salad.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3965,"Crunchy Pecan Bars","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","When Marilyn Martell started exhibiting at her local county fair, she won so many ribbons for cookies that she decided to share them in a cookbook entitled &quot;County Fair Prize Cookies&quot;, published in 1975. For a number of years now, she has competed at the state fair, continuing to win blue ribbons for baking. Crunchy Pecan Bars is a long-time favorite. These delectable toffee-flavored bars are quick to make and yield a large batch. Simply pat the dough into a jelly-roll pan. Long baking at a low temperature gives the thin bars their crisp texture. They keep well-if you hide them.","Bar Cookie",4.5,5.0,63.0,4.3,1.8,9.7,19.2,5.8,0.3,2.9,0.7,"0.0","Crunchy Pecan Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 275°F (135°C). Butter a 15 x 10 jelly-roll pan. 2: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. 3: Add egg yolk and vanilla; mix well. 4: In a medium-size bowl, mix flour and cinnamon. 5: Sfir flour mixture into creamed mixture, using hands to mix stiff dough, if necessary. 6: Spread evenly in buttered jelly-roll pan. 7: In a small bowl, beat egg white just until well mixed; spread over dough. 8: Sprinkle pecans evenly over top, then sprinkie lightly with sugar. 9: Bake in preheated oven about 1 hour or until set. Cut in 2 x 1\ 10: ,  11: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3966,"Old Fashioned Coconut Oatmeal Cookies","PT12M","PT0S","PT12M","Make and share this Old Fashioned Coconut Oatmeal Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",4.5,4.0,157.9,8.9,5.6,19.4,86.2,19.3,1.4,12.5,1.9,"0.0","Old Fashioned Coconut Oatmeal Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream together butter, sugars; add egg and mix thoroughly. 2: Add flour, oats, wheat germ, coconut, baking powder and baking soda. Mix well. 3: Stir in raisins. 4: Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets. Flatten slightly with floured fork. 5: Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes or until golden.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3967,"Dynamite Oatmeal Chocolate Chip Raisin Cookies","PT8M","PT0S","PT8M","Make and share this Dynamite Oatmeal Chocolate Chip Raisin Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",5.0,6.0,202.7,9.2,5.5,23.3,60.9,30.1,1.3,21.5,2.1,"0.0","Dynamite Oatmeal Chocolate Chip Raisin Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream the butter and the sugars, then add the eggs, vanilla and butterscotch extract. 2: Sift the baking soda, salt, cinnamon and flour together, then add in batches to the wet ingredients until mixed. 3: Add oatmeal, raisins, chips and pecan, if desired. 4: Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a lightly greased or parchment-lined cookie sheet. 5: Bake at 350° for 8-12 minutes or until golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3968,"Oatmeal Cookies","PT12M","PT0S","PT12M","For chocolate chunk oatmeal cookies, omit the raisins and add 2 coarsely chopped imported chocolate pieces or use half raisins, half chocolate chunks.","Dessert",3.0,3.0,167.4,9.8,4.6,18.6,37.8,19.4,1.1,12.2,2.2,"0.0","Oatmeal Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat the oven to 350°F 2: Cream the butter with the shortening to blend well. 3: Mix in the sugar and milk powder, then egg  and vanilla. 4: Stir in the hot water, which has been mixed with the  baking soda. 5: (All of these steps can be done in the food processor). Fold in the salt, flour, oatmeal, raisins, walnuts and chocolate  chips. 6: Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place on lightly greased or parchment-lined baking sheet. Dip hands in water and press cookies down to flatten. 7: Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown. 8: For chocolate chunk oatmeal: omit raisins and add 2 cups chocolate chunks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3970,"Chocolate Chip or M &amp; M Oatmeal Cookies","PT10M","PT20M","PT30M","These are really good, I like to use red and green m and m''s to replace the chocolate chips and serve them as christmas cookies.","Dessert",5.0,43.0,264.2,13.9,6.6,28.7,201.3,33.9,2.2,20.4,3.9,"0.0","Chocolate Chip or M &amp; M Oatmeal Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream the butter and both sugars. 2: Add eggs and vanilla; mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder, and soda. 3: Add chocolate chips, and nuts. 4: Roll into balls and place two inches apart on a cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes at 375 degrees.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3971,"Vegetarian Gravy","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Vegetarian Gravy recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,13.0,38.6,0.2,0.0,0.0,2.2,7.6,0.6,0.6,2.0,"0.0","Vegetarian Gravy Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute small onions and 4-5 mushrooms and 1 clove garlic in butter (or just heat up some butter if you want it plain.. I like onions) 2: When they soft, add about 2 Tbsp flour and mix it around until it is absorbed. 3: Pour on 1-1.5 cups vegetable broth and stir. 4: When that starts to warm up, pour a cup or less of cream or milk in and stir. 5: Let boil stirring a lot in the beginning to keep it from lumping. 6: and voila!  The amount of flour is kinda if-y. 7: I like it thick, and usually end up adding more flour later on in the process to make it thicker.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3972,"Linguine Pescatore","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Linguine Pescatore recipe from Food.com.","Mussels",5.0,8.0,1048.9,41.0,16.5,320.6,646.7,101.5,5.2,6.2,52.1,"1.0","Linguine Pescatore Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oil in a frying pan. Add garlic, chillies and onions, saute until softened, being careful not to burn the garlic. 2: Add the prawns, mussels and squid, saute 2 minutes and then add remaining seafood. 3: Saute 1 minute and add herbs and wine. 4: Bring wine to rolling simmer and add cream or tomato sauce. 5: Season with salt and pepper, heat to a simmer, add parsley  and desired amount of Hot cooked linguine. 6: Toss to coat pasta well. Serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3973,"Thai Noodles With Seafood","PT25M","PT10M","PT35M","This recipe is very simple,very fast and very good. The fresh rice noodles, thick and white, can be found in the refrigerator cabinet of any  good Asian grocery store. Don''t use frozen marinara mix--the recipe  deserves better. Any decent fishmonger will be happy to serve you with  half a dozen prawns, a few scallops, some squid, a small fillet of fish, a  handful of mussels or any other combination that appeals to you.","Mussels",1.0,1.0,179.4,9.9,1.3,47.3,1539.5,6.6,0.8,3.1,16.3,"0.0","Thai Noodles With Seafood Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut 500g of mixed seafood into bite-size pieces, first removing any shells. 2: If you are using mussels, wash and scrape the shells and open them by putting  them in a pot with a little boiling water. 3: Cover and boil for a few minutes, removing each mussel as it opens to prevent overcooking. 4: Chop a  handful of basil leaves and seed and finely slice 3 bird''s eye chillies. 5: In a frying pan or wok, heat 1 tablespoon of oil. 6: Brown 2 tablespoons of crushed garlic and saute the seafood for a couple of minutes. 7: Drain off the oil and set the garlic seafood mixture aside. Put another tablespoon of oil in the pan and increase the heat. Add 2 tablespoons of light soya sauce and the noodles and saute for 2-3 minutes. 8: Tip the seafood back into the pan and add 3 tablespoons of fish sauce. Stir well. 9: Add the basil leaves and chillies and cook for 1 minute more, stirring.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3974,"Seafood Locicero","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Seafood Locicero recipe from Food.com.","Mussels",0.0,0.0,770.6,17.3,7.2,263.0,1659.7,86.2,5.5,49.6,40.5,"4.0","Seafood Locicero Recipe Instructions:  1: In a sauce, reduce demi-glace (or broth) by half. 2: In a separate pan, 3: saute  peppers and ginger with the brown sugar. 4: Unglaze with the marsala wine and  reduce until almost all liquid is gone. Add the broth. 5: Reduce by half. 6: Add  soy sauce and lemon juice. KIWI PUREE-Peel and chop kiwi. 7: Cook kiwi and  sugar over a low flame until the sugar starts to break down. 8: Deglaze with  white wine. Reduce and add water. 9: Reduce again by half. 10: Puree and strain. 11: PASTA PANCAKES-Cook cappellini until just a little past done. Drain pasta. 12: In a mixing bowl, mix all ingredients thoroughly. 13: Mixture should bind  together; if not, add more bread crumbs. 14: Press mixture into a lightly  oiled 9\ 15: ,  16: ,  17: ,  18: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3975,"Linguini with Seafood - Buon''Appetito","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Linguini with Seafood - Buon''Appetito recipe from Food.com.","Mussels",0.0,0.0,574.1,10.3,1.6,142.5,985.8,71.6,4.2,5.8,43.2,"6.0","Linguini with Seafood - Buon''Appetito Recipe Instructions:  1: Serve pasta and sauce in a large bowl on the table and let people help themselves. 2: Vary the seafood according to your tastes. Grated Parmesan is traditionally not offered with seafood dishes. 3: If you prefer a  vegetarian version, saute mushrooms and peppers instead of seafood and add into tomato sauce. 4: In a large skillet, heat olive oil on medium-high heat.  Add shallots and garlic. Saute for 1 minute or until softened slightly,  then add lemon rind, parsley, shrimps and scallops. 5: Saute together until shrimps just turn pink and scallops are translucent, about 1-2 minutes. 6: Remove with a slotted spoon from skillet. Season with salt and pepper. 7: Add white wine to skillet, bring to boil and add mussels. Cover and steam  mussels until they open, about 3 minutes. 8: Remove mussels from skillet and reserve with shrimps and scallops. Remove mussel meats from half the mussels, leaving remainder in their shells. Discard any mussels that do not open. 9: Meanwhile drain tomatoes and chop, reserving juice. Add tomatoes, juice and chili flakes into skillet and bring to boil. 10: Stir in 2 Tbsp basil and simmer for 10 minutes to combine flavours. Season with salt and  pepper. 11: Sauce can be made ahead to this point. When ready to serve: bring a large pot of salted water to boil. 12: Add pasta and cook until al dente,  about 10-12 minutes. Drain well. 13: Return seafood to sauce, sprinkle with  remaining basil then reheat. Toss with pasta and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(3978,"Sweet Potato Pie IV","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sweet Potato Pie IV recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,2300.1,70.5,28.4,483.0,2396.3,315.3,8.7,199.5,26.5,"0.0","Sweet Potato Pie IV Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil until tender, peel, and mash sweet potatoes. 2: Mix sugar, salt, cinnamon, and nutmeg. 3: Add molasses and sweet potatoes;  beat well. 4: Stir in half and half, egg yolks, and sherry. 5: Beat the egg whites until stiff, fold into mixture, and pour into the pie shell. 6: Put into a preheated 425 degree oven. 7: Reduce heat to 375 and bake about 35 minutes. 8: The pie will be brown and set in the middle.  Serve warm or cold with whipped cream. 9: ** If no alcohol is wanted, simply delete it from the recipe    but the  taste will be completely different.");
