INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4039,"Coconut Drops","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Coconut Drops recipe from Food.com.","Candy",0.0,0.0,5018.1,398.9,313.5,62.3,547.4,357.5,64.7,292.1,53.4,"1.0","Coconut Drops Recipe Instructions:  1: Divide coconut between two bowls. 2: Add red food coloring to one bowl and green to the other; toss to coat.   In a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt candy coating. 3: Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper. 4: While coating is still warm, sprinkle half of each drop with pink coconut and the other half with green; press down gently. 5: Refrigerate until firm. 6: A family oriented website    http://home.sprynet.com/~jmjohnsn      Seasonal Page Topic - Fall Foliage");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4040,"Apple Nut Muffins","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apple Nut Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,7.0,496.1,23.9,12.8,97.6,549.1,64.9,2.1,34.6,7.2,"12.0","Apple Nut Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: In a saucepan, melt butter. 2: Stir in brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg until smooth. 3: Add apples; cook over medium-low heat for 10 minutes or until apples are tender, stirring frequently. 4: Remove from the heat; stir in nuts. 5: Set aside to cool. 6: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. 7: Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. 8: Beat in vanilla. 9: Combine the dry ingredients; add to the creamed mixture alternating with sour cr eam. 10: Spoon 1/4 cupfuls of batter into greased jumbo muffins cups. 11: Spoon apple mixture into the center of each (do not spread). Top with remaining batter. 12: Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar. 13: Bake at 350° for 25-27 minutes or until muffins test done. Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks. 14: Editors Note: If using regular-size muffin cups, fill cups half full with batter; add a rounded teaspoonful of apple mixture and remaining batter. 15: Bake for 16-18 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4041,"Blueberry Overnight French Toast","PT1H","PT30M","PT1H30M","Submitted in response to a request. I believe it was originally from a TOH magazine under &quot;light fare&quot;.","Breakfast",4.5,8.0,535.5,21.6,10.0,322.3,527.4,66.0,1.8,40.3,20.2,"8.0","Blueberry Overnight French Toast Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut bread into 1-in. cubes; place half in a 13-in. x 9-in. x 2-in. baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. 2: Cut cream cheese into 1-in. cubes; place over bread. 3: Top with blueberries and remaining bread. 4: In a large bowl, combine egg substitute, milk and syrup; mix well. 5: Pour over bread mixture. Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight. Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking. 6: Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. 7: Uncover; bake 25-30 minutes longer or until golden brown and the center is set. In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; add water. 8: Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. 9: Stir in blueberries; reduce heat. Simmer for 8-10 minutes or until berries have burst. Serve over French toast.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4042,"Soft Spice Bars","PT12M","PT15M","PT27M","Make and share this Soft Spice Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",4.5,6.0,111.0,4.9,3.0,18.4,166.9,16.1,0.3,9.1,1.1,"0.0","Soft Spice Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: In a mixing bowl, combine butter, 1 cup of sugar and molasses. 2: Beat in egg until smooth. 3: Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt; stir into the molasses mixture. Spread into a greased 15 x 10-in. baking pan. 4: Sprinkle with remaining sugar. 5: Bake at 375° for 10-12 minutes or until lightly browned. 6: Do not overbake. Cool on a wire rack before cutting.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4043,"Pudding Fudge","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pudding Fudge recipe from Food.com.","Candy",1.0,2.0,36.2,1.7,0.3,1.1,9.3,5.2,0.2,4.1,0.3,"0.0","Pudding Fudge Recipe Instructions:  1: In a heavy saucepan, combine dry pudding mix, sugar, milk and butter. 2: Bring to a boil; boil and stir until a candy thermometer reads 224, about 3 minutes. 3: Remove from the heat and beat rapidly for 1 minute. Add pecans; continue beating until mixture thickens slightly. 4: Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paperlined baking sheets. 5: Refrigerate until firm, about 45 minutes.");
