INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4048,"Low-Fat Carnitas","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Low-Fat Carnitas recipe from Food.com.","Pork",4.5,3.0,351.6,22.1,7.6,90.7,439.6,3.2,0.5,1.7,33.1,"12.0","Low-Fat Carnitas Recipe Instructions:  1: To a 7- to 8-quart pan, add pork, broth, onion, coriander, cumin, oregano, chilies in sauce, sauce, and bay leaves. Add water to cover the pork. 2: Cover the pan and bring to a boil on high heat, then reduce heat and simmer until meat pulls apart easily with a fork, 2 to 3 hours. 3: Strain broth. 4: Cover pork with enough broth to keep moist and use remaining broth for Spiced Black Beans. 5: To bake carnitas, pull pork large shreds and place in a shallow baking dish. 6: Spoon some broth over to keep moist. Broil pork until slightly crisp (watching carefully), turn, moisten if necessary and broil again. 7: .");
