INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4055,"Chocolate Chip Cookies","PT10M","PT0S","PT10M","Make and share this Chocolate Chip Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",5.0,8.0,162.0,8.5,5.1,25.4,110.5,21.3,0.8,13.0,1.8,"0.0","Chocolate Chip Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Set the oven to 190°C/375°F/Gas 5. 2: Beat the butter and sugars together in a mixing bowl until creamy. 3: Break the egg into the bowl and beat it into the mixture until smooth. 4: Then add the vanilla essence and mix. 5: Add the flour, salt and bicarbonate of soda to the mixture, a little at a time, and stir everything together well. 6: Now add the chocolate chips and stir them in until they are evenly spread through the mixture. 7: Butter the baking trays and spoon small mounds of the mixture on them leaving quite big spaces between the  mounds. 8: Bake the cookies for 10 to 12 minutes until they are an even golden  brown colour, then transfer them to a wire rack to cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4056,"Baked Salmon with Cucumber Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Baked Salmon with Cucumber Sauce recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,3.0,402.0,23.6,6.7,113.6,124.5,4.6,0.4,1.7,35.9,"4.0","Baked Salmon with Cucumber Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Place the salmon on a large piece of lightly buttered foil on a baking sheet.   Season lightly and sprinkle with lemon juice. 2: Wrap loosely and  bake at 170 C / 325 F / Gas 3 for 20-25 minutes until cooked.  Leave to cool in the foil. 3: Dice the cucumber very finely.  Cook in melted butter  for 2 minutes until  translucent. 4: Add wine to the pan, bring to the boil and simmer until all the  liquid has evaporated - about 10 minutes - and the cucumber is ''dry''. 5: Remove  from the heat, stir in the cream and dill and check seasoning. 6: Serve  immediately with the fish.");
