INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4069,"Hungarian Pork and Sauerkraut Goulash","PT2H","PT0S","PT2H","Make and share this Hungarian Pork and Sauerkraut Goulash recipe from Food.com.","Pork",4.0,2.0,218.8,16.6,10.1,33.8,2162.4,15.6,4.6,4.9,4.5,"6.0","Hungarian Pork and Sauerkraut Goulash Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut pork into 2-inch cubes. 2: In large Dutch oven, combine pork, onion, garlic, dill, caraway, salt, bouillon cube and boiling water. 3: Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour. 4: Add paprika; stir to dissolve. Add sauerkraut; mix well. 5: Simmer, covered, until meat is tender, 1 hour or longer. 6: Stir in sour cream; heat thoroughly.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4071,"Crisp Lasagna Chips","PT5M","PT15M","PT20M","Make and share this Crisp Lasagna Chips recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,2.0,1691.8,6.9,1.3,0.0,22.8,340.5,14.6,8.1,59.5,"0.0","Crisp Lasagna Chips Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare one 16 ounce package lasagna noodles as package directs. 2: Drain well and blot excess moisture with paper towels. 3: Cut each lasagna crosswise into about six 2-inch pieces. 4: In electric skillet, heat about 1-inch oil to 370 degrees. 5: Fry cooked lasagna until golden brown on both sides, about 5 minutes. 6: Drain well on paper towels. 7: Sprinkle fried lasagna lightly with salt and your favorite topping (e.g., paprika, bacon bits and Parmesan cheese) or use a flavored salt (e.g., seasoned salt, celery salt or garlic salt).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4072,"Scallop Lasagna","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Scallop Lasagna recipe from Food.com.","European",3.0,1.0,340.1,18.7,11.4,76.3,540.3,22.0,0.9,1.2,18.7,"0.0","Scallop Lasagna Recipe Instructions:  1: Rinse scallops well and drain, if using regular scallops, cut into 1/2-inch  pieces. 2: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a 12 to 14-inch frying pan. 3: Add onion,  garlic and thyme; stir on medium-high heat for 1 minute. Add scallops; cook,  stirring often, until they are opaque in the center (cut to test), 2 to 3  minutes. 4: Remove from heat; pour scallops into a large strainer pos  itioned over a  bowl; let drain for 20 to 30 minutes. 5: In the same frying pan, melt remaining  butter on medium heat. Add flour and stir until it turns a light golden color. 6: Remove from heat; smoothly mix in broth, cream and vermouth. 7: Return to high  heat; bring to a boil, stirring and set aside. Fill a 4 to 5-quart pan 3/4 full  with water and bring to boiling over high heat. Add lasagna to water and boil,  uncovered, until tender to bite, about 10 minutes; drain. 8: Rinse lasagna with  cold water until cool; drain again and set aside.  Pour scallop juices into a 1 to 1 1/2-quart pan; boil on high heat, uncovered,  until reduced to about 2 tablespoons; stir near the end to keep juices from  scorching. 9: Mix juices with cream sauce. Line bottom of a 9 x 12-inch buttered  baking pan or dish with 1/3 of the lasagna noodles. 10: Spread noodles with 1/3 of  the sauce; top with 1/3 of the scallops, then with 1/3 of the cheese. Repeat  layers twice more, ending with cheese on top. 11: Cover pan with a lid or foil;   if  made ahead, chill up to 1 day, then bring to room temperature. Bake lasagna in a  350 degrees oven for 20 minutes. 12: Remove foil and bake until cheese is golden,  about 20 minutes longer. 13: Let stand 15 minutes to firm before cutting; lift out  portions with a wide spatula. 14: Makes 12 servings as a first course, 6 as an  entree.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4073,"Lasagna Pierogi","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lasagna Pierogi recipe from Food.com.","One Dish Meal",4.5,5.0,620.9,39.9,25.0,109.8,529.1,55.4,6.3,4.1,13.5,"0.0","Lasagna Pierogi Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook lasagna and drain. 2: Chop onions and cook in butter or margarine only until  clear, but not brown. Saute on low heat. 3: Cook and mash potatoes; add cheese to  potatoes. 4: Spread 2 pieces of lasagna on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. 5: Spread  potatoes with cheese over top of lasagna, then spread butter and onions over  potatoes and start over with layer of lasagna, etc. End with layer of lasagna. 6: Then pour can of Pet milk over top and bake in oven at 350 degrees until milk  bubbles. 7: Cut in squares and serve with sour cream. 8: Sprinkle paprika on top of  potatoes (optional)");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4074,"Potato Lasagna","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Potato Lasagna recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,1.0,4043.4,389.4,246.8,1089.3,4090.4,60.2,7.7,25.5,92.7,"1.0","Potato Lasagna Recipe Instructions:  1: Make lasagna first. Boil for 8 minutes (slightly hard); rinse with cold water,  drain and let sit. Make mashed potatoes; saute 5 onions and 1 to 21 1/2 cups  margarine on low heat until onions are soft. Grat e Cheddar cheese and add to  potatoes; add onions and butter mixture. (Leave a little out to spread on top  when through layering.) In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer butter on bottom of pan, then  lasagna noodles, then potato mixture. After 3 layers (lasagna on top), spread  remaining butter and onions on top. 2: Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for  about 30 to 40 minutes. 3: Note: The layers of the potato mix should not be more  than 1/2-inch deep.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4075,"Golden Bran and Raspberry Muffins","PT25M","PT8M","PT33M","Make and share this Golden Bran and Raspberry Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,6.0,177.5,0.7,0.1,0.4,263.0,40.9,5.6,9.6,5.6,"6.0","Golden Bran and Raspberry Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350. 2: Line muffin tins with liners or spray with cooking spray. 3: In a large bowl, combine flour, bran, baking powder and baking soda until well  mixed. 4: In a medium size bowl, whisk the egg whites, and molasses until frothy. 5: Whisk  in the applesauce and milk. 6: Pour the liquid mixture in with the dry ingredients and stir until just combined, but do not over stir.  (if desired, this can be  left in the refrigerator over night, covered.)  The fruit should not be added  until just before baking. 7: Very gently fold in the raspberries, (try to prevent the fruit from breaking.)   Spoon an heaping 1/4 cup of the batter into each muffin cup, filling each  completely. 8: Bake for 25 minutes until golden brown. 9: Remove the muffins from the tins and  transfer to a wire rack to cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4076,"Sweet Potato and Raisin Muffins","PT25M","PT15M","PT40M","Make and share this Sweet Potato and Raisin Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",0.0,0.0,219.7,0.4,0.1,0.4,243.8,49.1,2.3,12.8,5.5,"7.0","Sweet Potato and Raisin Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350. 2: Line muffin tins with liners or s pray with cooking spray. 3: In a large bowl, whisk the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and cinnamon until well combined. 4: Add the liquids all at once over the dry ingredients and stir  until just combined. 5: Spoon a heaping 1/4 cup of the batter into each muffin cup, each should be full and well rounded. 6: Bake for 25 minutes or until golden  brown. 7: Turn the muffins out onto a wire rack to cool for 5 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4077,"Pineapple Filling","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Pineapple Filling recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,5.0,849.8,17.2,8.9,242.0,448.4,167.9,3.4,133.4,11.2,"0.0","Pineapple Filling Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix sugar, flour, and salt. 2: Add beaten egg, pineapple, and the juice, 3: Cook in double boiler until thick. 4: Add butter and mix well gain. 5: Remove from  heat and cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4078,"Pecan Filling","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Pecan Filling recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,1.0,2764.5,86.3,10.8,634.5,804.5,511.1,9.9,181.7,29.6,"0.0","Pecan Filling Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat eggs until light. Mix sugar and flour to the eggs. 2: Beat again. 3: Add  syrup, vanilla, salt, and pecans.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4079,"Orange Filling","PT15M","PT5M","PT20M","Make and share this Orange Filling recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,3.0,647.7,16.1,8.8,219.3,93.8,124.1,0.8,96.5,4.4,"0.0","Orange Filling Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix sugar and corn starch in double boiler. 2: Add beaten egg yolk and  orange juice. Cook for 10 - 15 minutes or until thick. 3: Remove from  heat, add butter and peel. 4: Cool. 5: Lemon Cream Filling  1 egg yolk, beaten  1/2 cup sugar  2 Tbsp corn starch  1/4 cup lemon juice  1/8 tsp grated lemon peel  1/2 tsp butter  1/2 cup water. 6: Combine yolk, sugar, corn starch, 1/2 cup water, lemon juice, lemon  peel and cook in double boiler for 15 minutes. Add butter. 7: Cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4080,"Bucket Lasagna","0","PT0S","PT45M","This is a method of preparing Lasagna which makes 6 dinners which can be frozen and re-heated in a crockpot.","European",5.0,6.0,916.9,52.8,20.0,403.3,846.6,5.3,0.0,4.2,99.1,"0.0","Bucket Lasagna Recipe Instructions:  1: I cook a large package of hamburger (apx 5 lbs), drain. 2: Place it back in the pan I cooked it in, (don''t dirty another pan) and add tomato sauce and spices as you like it. 3: In another large bowl, mix two large containers of cottage cheese, four eggs, and salt and pepper. 4: A third bowl has a large quantity of shredded mozzarella. 5: Open two packages of lasagna noodles, either no-bake or regular.  I prefer the regular, they are thicker--he no bake kinda disappear in my lasagna  because they are so thin. 6: Place all the ingredient bowls and pans in a row on  the counter. 7: Then I take 6 (one gallon) ice cream buckets or similar container. 8: Layer as follows: noodles, sauce, cheese and repeat til done. 9: That is it!  You end up with six lasagnas, and only 3 dirty pans. 10: Freeze. Once solid, slip from the ice cream bucket, and place in gallon Ziploc bags., Now they go back in the freezer, taking up much less space. I use the ice cream bucket because it makes it the exact correct size and shape for my 5 quart crockpot. You may find another container that works better for you. 11: When its lasagna eating day, just pop it in the crockpot on LOW, and let her go all day...come home, dinner is ready!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4081,"Lasagna Rolls","PT20M","PT45M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Lasagna Rolls recipe from Food.com.","Oven",0.0,0.0,209.4,12.0,7.1,86.0,366.5,12.1,0.8,0.4,13.5,"4.0","Lasagna Rolls Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix together the spinach, cottage cheese, egg and seasonings. 2: Roll up in the  lasagne sheets. 3: Place any remaining mixture on the base of a shallow ovenproof  dish, stand the lasagne on this. 4: Place butter, flour and milk in a saucepan,  heat stirring until the sauce thickens, boils and is smooth. 5: Remove from the  heat and stir in the cheese.  Pour around the rolls. 6: Bake at 190 C / 375 F /  Gas 5 for 20 minutes to heat through.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4082,"Cognac Truffles","0","PT25M","PT25M","Make and share this Cognac Truffles recipe from Food.com.","Candy",3.5,2.0,26.9,2.8,1.7,8.8,10.6,0.3,0.0,0.0,0.3,"24.0","Cognac Truffles Recipe Instructions:  1: -------------ENROBING-------------       1 lb Bittersweet chocolate       1 lb Cocoa   It is important to use an excellent quality chocolate when making truffles  since it is the primary ingredient. Valhrona is my first choice and Callebaut is my second. 2: BRING THE CREAM TO A BOIL and pour it over the cut chocolate. Allow  to stand 1-to-2 minutes and stir smooth. 3: Beat in the softened butter and cool to set. Beat with an electric mixer (using a paddle attachment if available) on  medium speed until light. Beat in Cognac. Pipe out small truffles on parchment  or waxed paper with a pastry bag fitted with a 1/2-inch plain tube. Refrigerate  to set. Melt the chocolate. Sift the cocoa into a deep pan. 4: Dip the truffles in  the melted chocolate and then deposit th em in the cocoa, shaking the pan to  cover  them. 5: After the covering sets, shake the truffles in a strainer to remove the excess cocoa.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4083,"Portuguese Red Bean Soup","PT50M","PT20M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Portuguese Red Bean Soup recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,4.0,456.0,29.3,10.2,47.5,983.1,32.0,5.4,11.0,17.3,"6.0","Portuguese Red Bean Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Finely chop all vegetables including tomatoes and potato. Drain soaked beans,  discarding liquid. 2: In a medium pot, add olive oil and butter. 3: When oil is hot, add  chopped carrot, onion, celery, tomatoes. Saute, but do not brown. Add  chopped potato, paprika, and chicken stock. 4: When this reaches a boil,  add  kidney beans and turn down heat to a simmer. Add tomato paste . 5: Let cook 45-60  minutes, stirring occasionally. When beans are soft to the touch add sausage and cayenne pepper. 6: Season to taste.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4084,"Honey Oat Biscotti","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Honey Oat Biscotti recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,9.0,102.5,4.1,0.8,10.3,106.8,14.9,0.9,6.0,2.0,"36.0","Honey Oat Biscotti Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375 F.  (will be turned down to 300F.  for second baking.) 2: Cream butter. 3: Beat in honey, eggs and vanilla. 4: Combine flour, cinnamon, baking  powder, baking soda and salt; mix well. 5: St into butter mixture.  Stir in oats  and nuts. 6: On greased  baking sheet, shape dough into 2 (10x3x1-inch) logs. 7: Bake at 375 F.  for 12-15 minutes, or until lightly browned. 8: Cool 5 minutes;  remove to cutting board. 9: Cut each log into 1/2-inch strips; place on cookie  sheet.  Bake at 300F., 25-30 minutes or until crisp throughout strip.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4085,"Ice Box Fruitcake II","PT24H","PT45M","PT24H45M","Make and share this Ice Box Fruitcake II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,6234.5,391.2,107.5,135.0,1683.2,660.8,55.1,346.8,84.8,"0.0","Ice Box Fruitcake II Recipe Instructions:  1: Combined crushed wafers, coconut, chopped cherries, pecans and pineapple and  place in large bowl. Mix well. Also add raisins, if desired. 2: Melt marshmallows  in top of double boiler. 3: Add milk to melted marshmallows and mix well. 4: Remove  from heat and pour onto wafer mixture. Mix well. 5: If desired, pour 1/4 to 1/2 cup of any good sweet wine - scuppernong, blackberry, pear, etc. When cool enough to handle, form into \ 6:  and wrap in waxed paper. 7: Chill at least 24 hours before serving -- the longer the chilling, the better. 8: Serving Suggestions Slice into  1/2\ 9: ,  10: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4086,"Onion with Tomato Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Onion with Tomato Sauce recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,2429.6,164.3,23.0,0.0,73.4,246.7,26.1,147.2,18.7,"0.0","Onion with Tomato Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all sauce ingredients and cook over medium heat for 30 minutes or until tender and pulpy. 2: Rub through a sieve with a wooden spoon to get out as much liquid as possible.  Peel onions and put in a heavy-based sauce pan. 3: Add the sauce and remaining ingredients and just enough water to cover the onions. 4: Bring to the boil, stirring. 5: Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 1 hour or until the onions are tender. 6: Remove the bouquet garni. 7: Season to taste adding a little sugar to counteract the acidity. 8: You can serve this hot, but it is better to let it cool, that lets the flavour  come through.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4087,"Old-Fashioned Scrapple","PT30M","PT40M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Old-Fashioned Scrapple recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",5.0,3.0,231.4,12.9,3.4,33.8,247.6,16.0,1.2,0.2,12.4,"0.0","Old-Fashioned Scrapple Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine pork, broth, cornmeal, thyme and salt in large  saucepan. Heat and stir to boiling. 2: Reduce heat, simmer  stirring constantly until mixture is very thick. 3: Remove from  heat. 4: Line 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with waxed paper allowing  3 to 4 inch overhang. 5: Spoon pork mixture into pan, press  firmly and refrigerate, covered 4 hours. 6: Using waxed paper. 7: In the morning or any time you like breakfast, cut into small squares and fry in a skillet with some oil on medium heat like breakfast sausage until browned on both sides and hot in the middle. 8: Fabulous with grits, eggs, homefries and toast.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4088,"Scrapple","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Scrapple recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",0.0,0.0,171.9,1.7,0.2,0.0,16.5,36.7,3.6,0.9,3.9,"0.0","Scrapple Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large saucepan, combine the broth, pork, cornmeal, onion, herbs, salt and pepper. Simmer for 1 hour. 2: Remove pan from heat and pour the mixture into large loaf pans. 3: Chill until scrapple sets. 4: When ready to serve scrapple, slice loaf into 1/2-inch slabs and saute in a butter-coated skillet.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4089,"Crunchy Christmas Cookies","PT15M","PT10M","PT25M","Make and share this Crunchy Christmas Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,8.0,89.7,4.7,2.5,12.7,79.8,11.1,0.7,6.0,1.2,"0.0","Crunchy Christmas Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter; add sugar, egg and vanilla. 2: Sift in dry ingredients. 3: Add  cornflakes, oats, coconut and nuts. 4: Roll into small balls an place 2-inches  apart on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4090,"Easy Christmas Cookies","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Easy Christmas Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,6.0,80.4,3.4,1.4,1.1,49.6,12.3,0.2,8.3,0.6,"0.0","Easy Christmas Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt together marshmallows and margarine in heavy saucepan over low heat,  stirring occasionally until smooth. 2: Pour over combined cereal and candies; toss  until lightly coated. 3: With greased fingers, gently shape mixture into 1 1/2-inch  balls. 4: Place on wax paper. 5: Let stand at room temperature until set. Makes about  3 dozen cookies.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4091,"Easy Christmas Cookies II","PT12M","PT0S","PT12M","Make and share this Easy Christmas Cookies II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,108.1,6.1,1.6,7.7,67.2,12.4,0.2,5.7,1.2,"0.0","Easy Christmas Cookies II Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream margarine, cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and flour. 2: Mix well; add vanilla. 3: Shape into long rolls. 4: Refrigerate a few hours or overnight. Slice and dip in colored sugar sprinkles. 5: Bake at 375° for 12-15 minutes or until lightly golden. 6: Can be used with a cookie press.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4092,"Christmas Cookies","PT8M","PT0S","PT8M","Make and share this Christmas Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",5.0,4.0,137.7,6.2,1.2,7.8,73.5,20.1,1.1,12.7,1.6,"55.0","Christmas Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix shortening, brown sugar and eggs; add salt, soda, buttermilk and flour. 2: Stir in cherries, dates and pecans into batter. 3: Chill 1 hour in refrigerator. 4: Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls. 5: Bake at 375° for 8-10 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4093,"Sweet Pumpkin Chips","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sweet Pumpkin Chips recipe from Food.com.","Yam/Sweet Potato",0.0,0.0,18715.9,8.5,2.6,0.0,176.2,4648.7,19.1,4553.1,16.0,"0.0","Sweet Pumpkin Chips Recipe Instructions:  1: Tie spices in cheese cloth. 2: Place cubed pumpkin in  colander and pour boiling water through until pumpkin is  thoroughly hot. Plunge in very cold water and drain. 3: Cook in  boiling syrup made with sugar, vinegar and spices. 4: Remove each  piece as it becomes clear. 5: When all are done, return to syrup  and let stand in cool place overnight. Drain. 6: Boil syrup. 7: Add pumpkin; bring to boiling point (do not boil). Repeat one  more time. Fill sterilized jars with chips. 8: Add boiling syrup  to 1/2-inch of top and seal.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4094,"Sweet Pumpkin Pickles","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sweet Pumpkin Pickles recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,2.0,609.8,0.2,0.1,0.0,10.3,149.9,1.2,137.0,2.3,"0.0","Sweet Pumpkin Pickles Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare pumpkin by peeling, cubing and discarding seeds and inner pulp. 2: Place pumpkin  cubes in colander and set over boiling water. Make sure water does not touch pumpkin. Cover and steam until just tender, 5 to 7 minutes. Drain. 3: Simmer vinegar, sugar and cinnamon for 15 minutes. 4: Add pumpkin and simmer 3 minutes. 5: Set aside for 24 hours. 6: Heat and simmer 5 minutes more. Remove cinnamon sticks. 7: Pack boiling hot in hot canning jars, leaving 1/2-inch headroom. 8: Adjust lids and process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.");
