INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4096,"Baked Butternut Squash With Orange","PT45M","PT0S","PT45M","Make and share this Baked Butternut Squash With Orange recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",5.0,2.0,191.6,3.8,0.5,0.0,13.3,41.5,7.4,12.4,3.6,"4.0","Baked Butternut Squash With Orange Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 200 C/400 F/Gas 6  Mix the parsley, orange zest and garlic in  the orange juice.  Cut the squash into 2 cm slices and brush with the olive oil. 2: Place the squash in an ovenproof dish and season. 3: Spoon the orange mix over the squash and cover with foil. 4: Bake for 40-45 minutes until the squash is slightly soft.  Serve with crusty bread rolls.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4098,"Jack Daniel''s Marinade","0","PT1H","PT1H","Make and share this Jack Daniel''s Marinade recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",1.0,1.0,319.5,0.1,0.0,0.0,5095.6,47.9,1.0,44.2,6.5,"0.0","Jack Daniel''s Marinade Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients. Blend well. 2: Use to marinate shrimp or scallops for 1 hour or beef, chicken, or pork in the refrigerator overnight. 3: Use to baste the shellfish or meat as it is grilled or broiled.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4099,"Mexicalli Onions","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Mexicalli Onions recipe from Food.com.","Onions",4.0,1.0,108.6,4.7,2.8,12.0,85.3,15.2,2.1,4.8,2.9,"6.0","Mexicalli Onions Recipe Instructions:  1: Place onions in boiling salted water and simmer for 10 minutes, Remove and cook slightly. 2: Cut the top and the root (do not remove the entire root or it will fall apart) from the onion and peel carefully. 3: With a spoon remove centre from the onions. 4: Chop centres to make 2 tablespoon of chopped onions. 5: Melt butter in saucepan and stir in flour and chilli powder. 6: Stir in milk until mixture thickens and boils. 7: Add capsicum, cheese, corn and 2 Tbsp chopped onion. 8: Season to taste.  Spoon filling into the onions, allowing some to spill over the sides. 9: Place in a baking dish and bake at 200 C for 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4100,"Beef Jerky II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Beef Jerky II recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,2.0,116.8,0.1,0.0,0.0,6019.2,22.4,0.9,11.5,8.1,"0.0","Beef Jerky II Recipe Instructions:  1: Remove fat from meat and place [meat] in freezer. 2: When semi-frozen, it is easily cut into 3/8- or 1/4-inch strips (the thinner the slices, the faster the drying). Note: meat cut with grain will be chewy, against grain, tender. 3: Combine everything in large bowl. 4: Marinate meat 1 hour with sauce in refrigerator, then drain in colander. 5: Place meat on cookie sheets to dry. 6: For fastest drying do not overlap meat and turn at least once during drying. 7: Dry in 145-degree oven [I use 155 degrees - Tom] for 8 to 10 hours on cookie sheets. 8: It is ready when it bends like a green willow without breaking. 9: Refrigerate for long-term storage.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4101,"Lasagna Rollups with Bechamel Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","I cut this recipe out of something (looks like maybe a newspaper a year or so ago), and it is terrific.  My family doesn''t eat the old fashioned lasagna anymore!","European",3.0,2.0,1393.2,121.2,57.8,234.8,1114.2,49.1,3.4,7.9,26.3,"6.0","Lasagna Rollups with Bechamel Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350. 2: Cook noodles in salted, boiling water until just tender.  Drain and place in large bowl of cold water and drain on paper towels. 3: Cook ground meat in microwave until done.  Mix cooked meat and breading mix from meatloaf mixture until well blended. 4: Spread meat mixture in thin layer on noodles and roll up  jelly roll fashion (don''t roll too tightly). 5: Spread all of sauce over bottom of 9/13 baking dish and arrange roll ups, seam side down on sauce. 6: Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350*. 7: Meanwhile, scald milk and bayleaf (I use microwave).  Let stand 5 minutes and remove leaf. 8: Melt butter in medium sauce pan, stir in flour, and cook stirring constantly with wooded spoon until mixture bubbles. 9: Stir in scalded milk, instant chicken broth, salt, pepper and nutmeg. 10: Continue cooking and stirring until sauce thickens and bubbles (about 3 minutes), and remove from stove. 11: After rollups have baked 30 minutes, remove  foil and spoon bechamel sauce over top and sprinkle with parmesan cheese. 12: Bake 10 minutes more or until bubbly hot and sauce is golden. 13: It''s not nearly as hard to make as it sounds, and the results are wonderful! All you need to round out  the meal is a salad, and garlic bread if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4102,"Cannoli with Amaretto Filling","0","PT1H","PT1H","Make and share this Cannoli with Amaretto Filling recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,11.0,268.6,14.7,9.1,46.3,117.5,29.9,1.8,11.1,6.0,"12.0","Cannoli with Amaretto Filling Recipe Instructions:  1: SHELLS: Combine flour, salt and sugar in a medium bowl. 2: Cut in butter until  mixture resembles coarse meal. 3: Stir in beaten egg. 4: Gradually stir in wine,  mixing well. 5: Shape dough into a ball, cover and refrigerate 30 minutes. 6: Turn  dough out onto a lightly floured surface and roll to 1/16-inch thickness. 7: Cut into 3 1/2-inch circles, and roll circles into 5-inch ovals. 8: Place a cannoli form, lengthwise,  down the center of each oval and roll dough around form. 9: Moisten seam with water to seal. 10: Pour oil to a depth of 3 inches into a Dutch oven and heat to 350°F. 11: Fry cannoli shells one minutes, or until golden brown. 12: Drain on paper towels and cool about 5 seconds. 13: Remove the form and cool cannoli shells completely. 14: FILLING: Thoroughly drain ricotta in a strainer, discarding the liquid. 15: Put  ricotta in a processor and process until smooth. 16: Combine ricotta,  mascarpone,  powdered sugar and Amaretto, if using, in a medium bowl and beat at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy. 17: Fold in two grated squares of  chocolate. Place in the refrigerator and chill 4 hours. 18: Pipe, or spoon. filling  into shells. 19: Sprinkle shells with remaining powdered sugar and exposed filling  with remaining chocolate. 20: NOTES :    A substitute for mascarpone cheese may be mad by combining 16 ounces cream cheese, 1/3 cup sour cream and 1/4 cup whipping cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4103,"Phyllo-Wrapped Salmon with Roasted Red Peppers","PT35M","PT10M","PT45M","Make and share this Phyllo-Wrapped Salmon with Roasted Red Peppers recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",4.5,4.0,397.8,20.0,9.0,95.0,709.5,20.9,1.0,0.1,31.8,"6.0","Phyllo-Wrapped Salmon with Roasted Red Peppers Recipe Instructions:  1: Puree red peppers. 2: Layer 2 sheets phyllo on work surface, brushing each with butter or spray  with nonstick spray; leave remaining sheets of phyllo covered with  plastic. Place 1 fillet crosswise on the pastry, 5 inches from the narrow  end. 3: Top with 1 T. puree. fold the 5 inch section of pastry over the  salmon and fold in the sides. 4: Roll the pastry into a rectangular packet  to enclose the salmon. 5: Brush with butter on all sides or spray with  nonstick spray. Repeat with the remaining pastry and salmon. 6: Place packets on baking sheet and bake at 400 degrees for 30-35 minutes  until the salmon is cooked through and the pastry is light golcen brown. 7: Top with the remaining pepper puree.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4104,"Whipping Cream Cake","0","PT0S","PT0S","My favorite cake recipe is Whipping Cream Cake.  It''s a variation on  the pound cake I fell in love with in the corner delis in New York  sold by the slice wrapped in celophane.  It''s fancy enough for company  with raspberry sauce and extra whipped cream, or great just plain in my  lunchbox the next day.","Dessert",5.0,18.0,6709.6,304.2,181.3,1930.1,2152.0,930.1,7.0,602.1,78.2,"0.0","Whipping Cream Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy. 2: Add the  eggs, flour, and whipping cream-mix well. 3: Stir in flavorings. 4: Spoon into  a greased and floured bundt pan. 5: Bake at 325 degrees for about an hour  or until cake tests done.  Cool in the pan for several minutes. 6: Invert  onto a wire rack to cool completely. 7: Garnish with powdered sugar, berry  sauce, ice cream, or whatever strikes your fancy. 8: It is also excellent  \ 9: ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4105,"Shrimp in Whiskey Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Shrimp in Whiskey Sauce recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,475.4,28.6,16.7,371.6,1403.5,9.2,0.2,0.1,32.7,"4.0","Shrimp in Whiskey Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Dredge shrimp lightly in flour. 2: Mix cream and mustard together. 3: Melt butter in saute pan over medium heat and saute shrimp lightly on both sides until they redden. 4: Pour in whiskey and ignite. When flames subside, add cream-mustard mixture to pan and stir until blended. 5: Serve in individual au gratin dishes. 6: This recipe should serve four, but don''t be surprised if your guests implore you for a second helping!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4106,"Mandarin Pork Chops","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Mandarin Pork Chops recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,63.0,477.3,21.8,6.5,137.3,127.7,27.1,2.1,21.8,42.5,"4.0","Mandarin Pork Chops Recipe Instructions:  1: In large skillet, brown chops in oil; remove from pan. 2: In skillet, add remaining ingredients except orange segments and green pepper; cook and stir until slightly thickened. 3: Add chops; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender. 4: Add orange segments and green pepper; heat through. 5: Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 6: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4108,"Cocoa Macaroon Muffins","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cocoa Macaroon Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",0.0,0.0,263.6,13.9,6.9,22.6,312.4,31.8,2.5,12.6,4.7,"0.0","Cocoa Macaroon Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Combine milk, egg and oil; mix well. 2: Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. 3: Spoon 2 tablespoonfuls into 12 greased or paper-lined muffin cups. 4: Combine 1 cup Coconut, condensed milk and extract;      place 2 teaspoonfuls in the center of each cup (do not spread). Top with remaining batter; sprinkle with remaining coconut. Bake at 400 F for 20-22 minutes or until muffins test done. Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4109,"Cold Mozzarella Cheese Dip","0","PT10M","PT10M","This dip is one that I am always told to bring to a gathering. We have found that we like to use half mozzarella and half colby cheese or I add some sharp cheddar for a change of pace. It is REALLY good as a spread on a ham sandwich as well. (This is the original recipe I was given, I have altered some of the ingredient amounts though for more flavor.)","< 15 Mins",4.5,8.0,14.3,1.2,0.7,3.6,17.3,0.3,0.0,0.3,0.6,"60.0","Cold Mozzarella Cheese Dip Recipe Instructions:  1: In a bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. 2: Cover and chill for at least 1 hour. 3: Serve with raw vegetables, tortilla chips or potato chips.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4111,"Ham and Cheese Spread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Ham and Cheese Spread recipe from Food.com.","Spreads",5.0,1.0,199.8,18.0,10.2,61.0,324.1,2.4,0.0,1.7,7.5,"0.0","Ham and Cheese Spread Recipe Instructions:  1: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream and soup mix until smooth. 2: Stir in ham and cheese. Form into ball or spoon into a plastic wrap-lined mold. 3: Roll in parsley or sprinkle parsley on top. 4: Refrigerate.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4112,"Pizza Dip","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pizza Dip recipe from Food.com.","High In...",0.0,0.0,975.0,71.1,44.5,246.8,3004.7,30.2,4.5,14.6,54.0,"1.0","Pizza Dip Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat process cheese spread according to package directions. 2: Mix together process cheese spread and pizza sauce. 3: Microwave on HIGH to 1 1/2  min or until thoroughly heated, stirring after 1 min. 4: Serve with breadsticks or vegetable dippers, if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4113,"Morning Maple Muffins","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Morning Maple Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,7.0,212.2,9.3,5.4,34.2,204.7,29.9,0.6,15.2,2.9,"0.0","Morning Maple Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large bowl, combine the flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt. In another bowl, combine the milk, butter, syrup, sour cream, egg and vanilla. 2: Stir into the dry ingredients just until moistened. 3: Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups two-thirds full. 4: For topping, combine the flour, sugar, nuts and cinnamon; cut in butter until crumbly. 5: Sprinkle over batter. 6: Bake at 400 F for 16-20 minutes or until muffins test done. Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4114,"Burst O'' Lemon Muffins","PT18M","PT25M","PT43M","Only try these if you love lemon as they are pretty intense. I used the grater on the zest of one lemon and it was no where near 1-2 tbs  but I think it was plenty. We liked them but my son preferred his without the glaze. 
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4115,"Mashed Potato Drop Doughnuts","PT5M","PT5M","PT10M","Make and share this Mashed Potato Drop Doughnuts recipe from Food.com.","Breads",5.0,2.0,308.5,7.3,3.8,61.5,223.0,52.6,1.7,13.9,7.4,"0.0","Mashed Potato Drop Doughnuts Recipe Instructions:  1: In a bowl, combine potatoes, sugar, egg, sour cream and vanilla. 2: Combine dry ingredients: stir into potato mixture. Heat oil in an electric skillet or deep-fat fryer to 375°F. 3: Drop dough by teaspoonfuls, 5 to 6 at a time, into hot oil. Fry for 1 minute per side or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. 4: Roll in sugar if desired. Serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4116,"Shrimp Spread","PT8H","PT5M","PT8H5M","Make and share this Shrimp Spread recipe from Food.com.","Spreads",5.0,2.0,16.0,1.6,0.9,4.9,20.1,0.3,0.0,0.2,0.3,"20.0","Shrimp Spread Recipe Instructions:  1: Finely chop the shrimp; place in a bowl. 2: Stir in the next six ingredients until well blended. 3: Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight. 4: Serve with crackers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4117,"Grandma''s Busy Day Casserole","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","Make and share this Grandma''s Busy Day Casserole recipe from Food.com.","< 60 Mins",5.0,2.0,305.1,13.8,5.1,77.1,415.5,17.8,1.8,1.9,26.1,"0.0","Grandma''s Busy Day Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown and drain hambuger. 2: Peel and slice potatoes into thin slices. 3: Add two cans of vegetable soup. 4: Mix well. 5: Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour (or until potatoes are done).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4118,"Cherry Almond Muffins or Coffee Cake","PT35M","PT25M","PT1H","I''m not sure where I originally got this recipe but I just recently tried it myself. Since the batter is more like a dough, I found it incredibly hard to layer in the muffin tins as described. Next time I''m going to use my springform pan and make a layered coffeecake instead and bake it for about 50 minutes.","Quick Breads",4.5,6.0,708.6,38.2,21.5,150.5,478.7,82.3,2.2,44.2,10.6,"0.0","Cherry Almond Muffins or Coffee Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cut in butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. 2: Beat the egg, sour cream and extract until smooth; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened (batter will be thick). 3: Combine flour and sugar in a small bowl; cut in butter until crumbly. Stir in almonds: set aside. 4: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla until smooth. 5: Fill greased jumbo muffin cups half full with batter. 6: Divide cream cheese filling and preserves evenly between muffin cups; swirl gently. Cover with remaining batter. Sprinkle with topping. 7: Bake at 350 F for 30-35 minutes or until muffins test done. Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks. 8: Editor''s Note: If using regular-size muffin cups, bake for 20-25 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4119,"Cappuccino Muffins","PT20M","PT15M","PT35M","My kids have declared these &quot;phenomenal!&quot; The muffins are good in their own right but the spread gives them an incredible extra dimension. Please note, it is a cream cheese spread and not a sweet icing. The chocolate chips will not change form much. Perfect with a big, cold glass of milk or cup of coffee!","Quick Breads",5.0,100.0,274.7,14.2,8.5,42.1,247.5,34.9,1.3,18.7,4.0,"14.0","Cappuccino Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: In a food processor (or using a hand mixer), combine the spread ingredients, cover and process until well blended. 2: Cover and refrigerate until serving. 3: For the muffins: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. In another bowl, stir milk and coffee granules until coffee is dissolved. 4: Add butter, egg and vanilla; mix well. 5: Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. 6: Fold in chocolate chips. 7: Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups two-thirds full. 8: Bake at 375°F for 17-20 minutes or until muffins test done. Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks. 9: Serve with espresso spread.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4120,"Applesauce Drop Doughnuts","PT15M","PT5M","PT20M","Quick &amp; easy to make. You can have the batter whipped up in the amount of time it takes for the oil to heat. (I use a Fry Daddy.) We actually like them better after they sit for 5-6 hours rather than warm like most doughnuts I make.","Breads",5.0,4.0,121.7,2.0,1.0,23.5,151.0,22.9,0.7,5.5,2.9,"0.0","Applesauce Drop Doughnuts Recipe Instructions:  1: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. 2: Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. 3: Beat in applesauce and vanilla. 4: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to the creamed mixture alternately with milk (batter will be extremely thick). In an electric skillet or deep-fat fryer, heat oil to 375°F. 5: Drop teaspoonfuls of batter a few at a time into hot oil. 6: Turn with a slotted spoon and fry until golden, about 1 minute on each side. Drain on paper towels; roll in sugar while warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4121,"Green Bean Casserole","PT30M","PT10M","PT40M","Make and share this Green Bean Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,9.0,113.1,3.3,0.8,0.0,721.4,18.3,4.5,4.2,3.8,"0.0","Green Bean Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 325°F. 2: Combine all ingredients except French fried onions. 3: Put in casserole dish; top with onion rings. 4: Bake 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4122,"Green Bean Casserole II","PT45M","PT0S","PT45M","Make and share this Green Bean Casserole II recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",4.0,1.0,3985.3,254.2,72.6,152.7,8046.8,377.4,19.6,55.9,63.0,"0.0","Green Bean Casserole II Recipe Instructions:  1: Drain beans, put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. 2: Drain corn, pour over beans. 3: Mix onions, celery soup, sour cream and  cheese. Pour over beans and corn. 4: Crush crackers, melt butter  and mix with crackers. 5: Spread over top and bake at 350 degrees for 45  minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4123,"Green Bean Casserole IV","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Green Bean Casserole IV recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,2267.8,158.6,68.3,322.1,8764.4,139.1,38.3,62.3,92.3,"0.0","Green Bean Casserole IV Recipe Instructions:  1: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside. Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender. 2: Drain off excess drippings. 3: Add stewed tomatoes and heat. Drain green beans and place in a 2 quart size casserole dish. 4: Add the tomato mixture and crumbled bacon mix. 5: Top with cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4124,"Cranberry Crumb Squares","PT1H5M","PT15M","PT1H20M","Make and share this Cranberry Crumb Squares recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",5.0,2.0,257.1,15.2,8.3,37.4,112.2,27.7,0.7,18.8,3.8,"24.0","Cranberry Crumb Squares Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C).  Cream together soft butter and  icing sugar until fluffy. 2: Gradually stir in 1 1/2 cups (375 mL) flour. 3: Press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch (3.5 L) baking pan. 4: Bake about 15 minutes or until lightly browned. 5: Reduce temperature to 325 degrees (160 degrees C). In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. 6: Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth. 7: Stir in ReaLemon. 8: Pour over prepared crust. 9: In small  bowl, combine 1 tablespoons (15 mL) of the brown sugar and cornstarch; mix well. 10: Stir in  cranberry sauce. Spoon evenly over cheese mixture.  In medium mixing bowl,  combine remaining brown sugar and 1/3 cup (75 mL) flour. 11: Cut in cold butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. 12: Stir in nuts. 13: Sprinkle evenly over cranberry mixture. 14: Bake 45 to 50 minute or until bubbly and golden. 15: Cool. 16: Serve warm or chilled. 17: Cover leftovers; refrigerate.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4126,"Farm-Style Sausage Patties","PT15M","PT15M","PT30M","Make and share this Farm-Style Sausage Patties recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",0.0,0.0,1427.7,120.5,42.9,314.6,2473.9,5.3,1.3,1.6,75.2,"0.0","Farm-Style Sausage Patties Recipe Instructions:  1: Put pork and salt pork through food chopper with coarse blade in place. 2: Blend in remaining ingredients thoroughly, adding just 1 tablespoon of salt at first. 3: Make a small patty of the meat and cook in skillet; taste; add more salt if desired. 4: Shape into patties and fry in large skillet until well browned on both sides and cooked through or wrap and refrigerate, or freeze.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4127,"Carne De Puerco En Chile Verde","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Carne De Puerco En Chile Verde recipe from Food.com.","Pork",4.0,5.0,264.6,10.6,3.5,95.2,70.2,8.5,1.5,4.3,32.8,"4.0","Carne De Puerco En Chile Verde Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut pork or beef into small cubes. 2: Saute in oil until well browned. 3: Drain off  all but 1 tablespoon fat. 4: Add chopped chiles, garlic, onion, tomato and water and season to taste with salt and pepper. 5: Cover tightly and simmer 1 hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4128,"Easy Crock Pot Chicken Cacciatore","PT4H","PT15M","PT4H15M","Make and share this Easy Crock Pot Chicken Cacciatore recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",4.5,21.0,550.2,34.6,9.9,170.1,1000.7,14.0,3.0,8.4,45.6,"6.0","Easy Crock Pot Chicken Cacciatore Recipe Instructions:  1: Place onions in bottom of crock pot.  Add chicken pieces. 2: Stir  together remaining ingredients. 3: Pour over chicken. 4: Cook on low 7  to 9 hours; high 3 to 4 hours. 5: Serve over angel hair pasta. 6: RJ''s Note:  I made this recipe on 9th of May 1998.  I substituted the tomato paste with a large can of tomatoes that I put through the blender.  The aroma of the chicken simmering in the crock pot sauce all day was fantastic. During the last ten minutes  I added some frozen mixed Chinese vegetables and served the cacciatore over home made pasta noodles (my first attempt at making pasta).  I only used one teaspoon of oregano.  Next time I''ll try two.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4129,"Breakfast Sausage","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Breakfast Sausage recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",4.5,5.0,141.3,7.6,2.1,71.7,144.0,1.1,0.3,0.0,16.1,"20.0","Breakfast Sausage Recipe Instructions:  1: Place ground meat in a large bowl and add garlic, thyme, fennel seeds, parsley,  red pepper, salt and oats. 2: Mix well, form into patties and individually wrap. 3: Use immediately or freeze for future use.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4130,"Never Fail Pie Crust","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Never Fail Pie Crust recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,37.0,1270.6,92.1,26.4,46.5,693.4,96.8,3.4,1.4,14.5,"0.0","Never Fail Pie Crust Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large mixer bowl combine the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. 2: Add the shortening and beat until mixture is crumbly, about 2 minutes. 3: In a small bowl beat the egg well and add the vinegar and water. 4: Pour over flour and beat until well combined, about 1 minute. Form dough into 4 balls, wrap in plastic and refrigerate overnight.           - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4131,"Carolina Pilau (Perloo)","PT40M","PT10M","PT50M","In the Carolinas rice often means pilau (pronounced perloo), a combination of meat, vegetables, or seafood and rice that can serve as an accompaniment to other dishes or stand alone as a staple.","Long Grain Rice",0.0,0.0,509.6,30.0,9.3,92.1,665.7,31.3,0.9,0.9,25.9,"10.0","Carolina Pilau (Perloo) Recipe Instructions:  1: Fry the bacon in a large skillet over very low heat, just until it reaches the crisp stage. Remove from pan, crumble and set aside. Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of the bacon fat, then add  the rice and stir, cooking slowly until rice is lightly browned. 2: Add the boiling stock, stir, and bring back to the boil. 3: Add chicken, vegetables, bay leaf, salt and pepper. 4: Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, or until rice, chicken and vegetables are done and liquid is absorbed. 5: Serving Ideas : Sprinkle with crumbled bacon and parsley.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4132,"Chiffon Pumpkin Pie","PT50M","PT0S","PT50M","Make and share this Chiffon Pumpkin Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",5.0,8.0,367.9,13.7,4.0,110.0,318.2,56.3,1.8,36.6,6.8,"6.0","Chiffon Pumpkin Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix pumpkin, sugar, spices and salt together. When  using fresh pumpkin I use blender. 2: Add milk and egg yolks. Mix  well. 3: In another bowl, beat egg whites until firm. 4: Fold into  pumpkin mix and pour into pie shell. 5: Bake at 450 degrees for 5  minutes, then at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. 6: I use the blender for  all mixing.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4133,"Favorite Pumpkin Pie","PT40M","PT10M","PT50M","Make and share this Favorite Pumpkin Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",4.5,9.0,231.8,11.0,3.3,75.1,459.5,28.8,1.4,13.2,5.2,"8.0","Favorite Pumpkin Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Mash and drain cooked pumpkin. 2: Add beaten egg yolks. 3: Stir in spices, salt and sugar. Mix well. 4: Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into pumpkin mixture.  Pour into unbaked crust. 5: Bake at 400 degrees for 40 minutes. If knife comes out clean, pie is done.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4134,"Cookies in a Jar","0","PT0S","PT0S","As a Nestle employee, I''d encourage non-Americans to use Smarties.:-) We also make red and green ones for the holiday season. (American ''Smarties'' are a completely different creature... pressed sugar candy. Don''t use them!)","Dessert",3.0,1.0,105.3,1.9,1.1,1.2,32.5,20.9,0.4,13.9,1.2,"0.0","Cookies in a Jar Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda. 2: Layer ingredients in order given in 1-quart wide-mouth canning jar. Press each layer firmly in place before adding next ingredient. 3: Attach this to the Jar M&M''s Cookies: 4: Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookie. 5: Empty jar of cookie mix into large mixing bowl. Use your hands to thoroughly blend mix. 6: Add: 1/2 cup butter or margarine, not diet, very soft;  1 egg, slightly beaten; and 1 tsp. vanilla (optional).  Mix until completely blended. You will need to finish mixing with your hands. 7: Shape into balls the size of walnuts. Place 2 inches apart on sprayed baking sheets.  Bake at 375 degrees for 12 to 14 minutes, until edges are lightly browned.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4135,"Chicken Pepperoni","PT25M","PT45M","PT1H10M","If you''re looking to impress  someone, you couldn''t do it better...and or easier. Just be careful that  you don''t overcook the chicken.","Chicken",4.5,11.0,446.1,4.5,0.9,72.9,1368.1,65.5,5.8,11.7,36.2,"4.0","Chicken Pepperoni Recipe Instructions:  1: * I used quartered low-fat pepperoni slices  without sacrificing the  taste.  While I needed to use olive oil to make up for the missing rendered  fat, I did save considerably on cholesterol. 2: Cook pasta according to package directions. 3: Dice pepperoni into 1/4\ 4: ,  5: ,  6: Dredge chicken pieces in seasoned  flour until coated. 7: Shake off excess flour and brown in the rendered  pepperoni fat (and olive oil, if needed) until the chicken is almost  cooked. 8: Remove from pan and set aside. Whisk tomato sauce, tomato paste, crushed red pepper flakes and 1/2 cup  water together in pan until smooth. 9: Return chicken and pepperoni to  pan. 10: Bring to simmer and cook, stirring, for 5 to 7 minutes. 11: Serve over a bed of pasta.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4136,"Chocolate Pudding Cake","PT35M","PT15M","PT50M","Make and share this Chocolate Pudding Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,431.0,20.1,3.4,46.5,459.4,60.8,2.7,39.5,6.9,"0.0","Chocolate Pudding Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix sugar, cocoa and water in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. 2: Sprinkle marshmallows on top. 3: Mix cake mix and pour over  mixture in pan. 4: Sprinkle with nuts. 5: Bake 35 to 40 minutes at  350 degrees.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4137,"Chocolate Pudding Cake II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chocolate Pudding Cake II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,5.0,304.9,11.1,1.6,1.9,209.8,49.0,1.9,33.1,4.1,"9.0","Chocolate Pudding Cake II Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Blend in milk, vegetable oil and vanilla. 2: Stir in nuts. 3: Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan; spread evenly. 4: Combine brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. 5: Spread evenly over batter. 6: Pour hot water over batter. 7: Do not stir. 8: Bake at 350 degrees f or 45 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4139,"Chicken Pasta Casserole","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chicken Pasta Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",3.0,4.0,767.6,42.7,21.2,175.8,1905.7,48.1,2.1,13.0,46.0,"8.0","Chicken Pasta Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Measure reserved broth and add enough water to equal 6 cups. 2: Add bouillon and onions. 3: Bring to boil and add spaghetti. Cook until tender. 4: Add cheese; stir until melted over medium heat. 5: Add garlic and both cans of tomatoes. 6: Stir well and add chicken meat. Place in a well greased, extra large casserole dish. 7: Place in a 325 degrees oven for 60 minutes; edges will be crispy brown. 8: Serve with French bread.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4140,"Pasta and Vegetable Salad with Chicken","PT3H","PT10M","PT3H10M","Make and share this Pasta and Vegetable Salad with Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",4.5,2.0,490.5,28.3,4.0,0.0,29.3,49.8,3.9,5.2,10.9,"4.0","Pasta and Vegetable Salad with Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook vermicelli as directed on box. Drain. Place in large bowl. 2: Whisk well oil, vinegar, mustard and garlic until well blended. 3: Pour 1/3 of dressing on mushrooms, broccoli, peas, tomatoes or peppers. Stir and chill 3 hours in separate bowl. 4: When ready to serve add chicken and nuts.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4141,"Cornbread With Corn Casserole","PT1H","PT5M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Cornbread With Corn Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Breads",5.0,159.0,272.3,11.3,2.6,47.1,727.9,39.7,3.6,2.9,6.0,"0.0","Cornbread With Corn Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix first 3 ingredients together. 2: Add: margarine and Jiffy corn bread mix, Pour into well greased 8x8 casserole dish. 3: Bake for 1 hour at 375 degrees.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4143,"Pineapple Roast Turkey","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pineapple Roast Turkey recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",3.0,1.0,62.4,0.1,0.0,0.0,253.2,13.2,0.9,10.2,0.9,"0.0","Pineapple Roast Turkey Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash turkey and pat dry. 2: If desired, rub cavity lightly  with salt. Fasten neck skin to back and skewer. 3: Fold wings  across back with tips touching. 4: Tuck drumsticks under band of  skin at tail or tie together with heavy string, then tie to  tail. 5: Place turkey breast side up on rack in open shallow  roasting pan. 6: Brush with vegetable oil. 7: Insert meat thermome-  ter so tip is in thickest part of inside thigh muscle or  thickest part of breast meat and does not touch bone. Roast  uncovered in 325 degrees oven for 3 hours. 8: Pare pineapple; cut lengthwise into halves. 9: Remove  core; cut each half crosswise int  o 8 slices. 10: Mix wine, honey,  soy, ginger, paprika and garlic. Arrange pineapple on rack  around turkey. 11: Brush turkey and pineapple with wine mixture.  Continue roasting uncovered, brushing turkey and pineapple  frequently with wine mixture, until thermometer registers 185 degrees,  about 1 hour longer, or move drumstick up and down (when done  the joint should give readily or break). Remove turkey and  pineapple, keep warm. 12: Pour d  rippings into 2 cup measuring cup; skim off any  excess fat. Add enough water to drippings to measure 2 cups. 13: Heat dripping to boiling in saucepan. 14: Mix cornstarch and cold  water; stir into drippings. 15: Boil and stir 1 minute. Serve  with turkey. 16: Yields about 16 servings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4144,"Honey Glazed Turkey","PT3H","PT30M","PT3H30M","Make and share this Honey Glazed Turkey recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",5.0,3.0,529.5,24.6,15.1,61.1,1909.2,77.4,4.9,65.5,6.8,"0.0","Honey Glazed Turkey Recipe Instructions:  1: Rinse turkey inside and out. Pat dry. Reserve giblets and neck for broth. 2: Make filling: Mix bread crumbs, green pepper, onion, chicken broth and spices. 3: Add orange peel and orange juice. 4: Spoon stuffing into cavity of turkey. Close openings with skewers. 5: Place turkey, breast side up, on a rack in a shallow pan. Insert meat thermometer in thickest part of thigh. 6: Roast turkey, uncovered, at 325 degrees for about 1 hour. 7: For glaze combine butter, orange juice and honey. 8: Brush turkey several times with glaze and pan drippings and roast it for another 1 1/2 to 2 hours until thermometer registers 180 degrees. 9: Remove turkey, keep warm; slice and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4145,"Tomato Scrapple","PT1H15M","PT15M","PT1H30M","Make and share this Tomato Scrapple recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",0.0,0.0,505.4,29.7,4.1,0.0,836.3,50.6,9.3,11.1,17.8,"4.0","Tomato Scrapple Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix tomatoes, onion, carrot, corn meal, sugar, and season to taste with salt and pepper. 2: Cook slowly until thick--about 1 hour. 3: Once this is completed, add peanuts and beat well. 4: Pack into a well oiled pan. 5: Refrigerate until cold. 6: Slice and fry up in bacon drippings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4147,"Strawberry Dump Cake","PT45M","PT0S","PT45M","Make and share this Strawberry Dump Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,8.0,4954.7,313.2,56.3,10.5,6490.9,512.8,21.5,294.9,50.6,"1.0","Strawberry Dump Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Pour pineapple into well greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish or pan. 2: Pour pie filling over pineapple and spread well. 3: Dump cake mix over pie filling. 4: Slice butter thin and lay over top of cake mix. 5: Bake in preheated 325 degrees oven for 45 minutes or until brown. 6: Cool in pan and serve in pan.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4148,"My Lazy Oven Turkey","PT2H15M","PT10M","PT2H25M","Make and share this My Lazy Oven Turkey recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",0.0,0.0,1032.2,51.5,14.5,436.1,417.3,1.5,0.2,0.6,131.1,"8.0","My Lazy Oven Turkey Recipe Instructions:  1: Remove giblets and neck from turkey; set aside.  Rinse and drain turkey. Pat dry. 2: Use a covered roasting pan that just fits the bird. 3: Cut onion in half and place inside turkey. 4: Blend herbs and make a paste with a little fat.  Spread on outside of turkey and press into skin. 5: Tie legs together. 6: Pour 1/2 inch water into pan and cover with lid. 7: Place pan in a 350 degree oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 185. 8: Uncover for last 10 minutes to brown if desired. 9: Remove from oven and let sit for 15 minutes before carving. 10: Drain liquid into a pot and return turkey to a warm oven until ready to carve(after standing 15 minutes).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4149,"Curried Peanut Chicken Nibbles","PT20M","PT0S","PT20M","Make and share this Curried Peanut Chicken Nibbles recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",0.0,0.0,75.1,6.3,1.0,20.7,70.3,2.8,0.7,0.4,2.5,"0.0","Curried Peanut Chicken Nibbles Recipe Instructions:  1: Chop peanuts finely in a processor. 2: Mix nuts, curry powder and breadcrumbs together. 3: Lightly beat eggs and cornflour together. 4: Dip chicken nibbles in egg mixture then the crumb mixture.  Heat oil in a roasting dish. 5: Place the nibbles in the dish and turn to coat in oil. 6: Bake at 180 C for 20 minutes or until cooked. 7: Serve warm or cold.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4150,"Fiesta Chicken Pizza","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Fiesta Chicken Pizza recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,2.0,96.5,5.0,2.0,27.5,679.2,4.9,1.4,2.2,8.5,"0.0","Fiesta Chicken Pizza Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven.  ( See pizza crust package directions) 2: Heat vegetable oil in large skillet over medium heat.  Add chicken; cook for 4 to 5 minutes or until no longer pink. 3: Add seasoning mix and water; mix well. 4: Spread salsa over crust. 5: Top with chicken mixture, cheese and vegetable toppings. 6: Bake according to pizza crust package directions or until crust is crisp and cheese is melted. 7: Drizzle with taco sauce and top with sour cream before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4151,"Ziti Pizzaiola","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Ziti Pizzaiola recipe from Food.com.","European",0.0,0.0,271.4,3.0,0.9,16.9,472.3,46.8,3.4,4.9,14.4,"0.0","Ziti Pizzaiola Recipe Instructions:  1: In large skillet over medium-high heat, stir together meat, mushrooms, green  pepper, basil, oregano and garlic powder.  Cook, covered, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. 2: Stir in tomatoes with reserved juice, tomato sauce, onion soup mix and sugar. 3: Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, or until meat is thoroughly cooked. 4: Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package directions; drain. 5: Toss hot pasta and one-half sauce; spoon remaining sauce on top. 6: Sprinkle with cheese.   Makes 12 servings (1 cup each)");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4152,"Potato Croquettes","PT10M","PT30M","PT40M","Make and share this Potato Croquettes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",0.0,0.0,206.7,6.9,3.4,82.1,587.6,29.4,2.0,2.3,6.4,"0.0","Potato Croquettes Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat 1 egg. 2: Mix with potatoes and white pepper, salt, butter, celery salt  If potatoes are dry, add a little bit of milk. 3: Heat mixture into a sauce  pan. 4: When it leaves the side of the pan, then remove it to a cool and flat  surface. Mold into croquettes patties. 5: Roll them in flour and dip into the  beaten egg Roll in the bread crumbs and deep fry at 375* until golden  brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4153,"Potato Fritters","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Potato Fritters recipe from Food.com.","Potato",0.0,0.0,155.7,5.8,3.2,67.6,759.6,21.4,1.7,2.4,4.3,"0.0","Potato Fritters Recipe Instructions:  1: Add the butter, salt, sugar, pepper, flour, and parsley to the mashed potatoes. 2: Beat the egg yolks and add them to the mixture. Mixing well. 3: Fold in the egg whites. 4: Drop by tablespoons into a deep fat fryer at 375* and cook for 5 - 8 minutes or until a delicate brown. 5: Drain on paper towels or brown grocery bags. 6: Yields = 6.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4154,"Chipped Beef Dip II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chipped Beef Dip II recipe from Food.com.","Meat",5.0,2.0,2731.5,249.6,136.0,720.7,5452.8,40.9,5.0,8.1,97.1,"0.0","Chipped Beef Dip II Recipe Instructions:  1: Blend cheese and milk together. 2: Add the beef, onions, green pepper,  black pepper, and the sour cream. 3: Place mixture into a pie plate.  Sprinkle the walnuts on top of it. Bake in oven at 350* for 20 minutes. 4: Serve with crackers or party rye.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4155,"Onion Herb Bread II","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Onion Herb Bread II recipe from Food.com.","Yeast Breads",4.0,1.0,106.0,1.3,0.3,0.2,115.4,20.2,0.9,1.3,3.1,"12.0","Onion Herb Bread II Recipe Instructions:  1: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water. 2: Add milk, butter, sugar, rosemary,  salt, dill, garlic powder, onion and 1 cup of flour. 3: Beat until smooth, about 1 minute.  Add the remaining flour and stir for about 1 minute.  Place in a bowl that has been sprayed with cooking spray. 4: Cover and let rise in a warm place  until doubled about 30 minutes. 5: Stir down raised batter in about 25 strokes. 6: Spread into a 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2\ 7: ,  8: Bake 375°F for 40 to 45 minutes. 9: Remove from pan; serve warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4156,"Pumpkin Bars","PT25M","PT20M","PT45M","Make and share this Pumpkin Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",5.0,11.0,209.1,9.2,3.5,36.5,131.5,30.6,0.3,23.9,2.0,"35.0","Pumpkin Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: In large mixing bowl stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices. 2: In another container, combine pumpkin, cooking oil and eggs till thoroughly mixed.  Add to dry mixture.  Stir until all dry ingredients are incorporated. 3: If desired, stir in walnuts. 4: Spread batter into a sprayed 15x10x1-inch-baking pan. 5: Bake in a  350 oven for 25 to 30 minutes or till a wooden toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. 6: Cool in pan on a wire rack. 7: Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting. 8: CREAM CHEESE FROSTING. 9: In a large mixing bowl beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla with an  electric mixer on medium to high speed till light and fluffy. 10: Gradually beat in enough of the remaining powdered sugar to make the  frosting of spreading consistency. 11: Cut into bars. 12: Store, covered. 13: **Note: Substitute one 16-ounce can of applesauce for the pumpkin and  presto! You have applesauce bars.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4158,"Nutty Apricot Bars","PT10M","PT0S","PT10M","Make and share this Nutty Apricot Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",0.0,0.0,107.4,4.4,2.4,7.6,51.3,17.0,0.9,12.2,1.0,"0.0","Nutty Apricot Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Cover apricots with water, and bring to a boil; reduce heat, and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes or until tender. 2: Drain, reserving 1/4 cup liquid. 3: Coarsely chop apricots, and set aside.  Combine reserved apricot liquid and 3/4 cup sugar in a saucepan; simmer 5 minutes. 4: Stir in chopped apricots. 5: Cream butter; gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy. 6: Combine flour, baking soda, and salt; add floured mixture to creamed mixture, mixing well (mixture will be crumbly).  Stir in coconut and pecans. 7: Pat about three-fourths of coconut mixture into and ungreased 13x9-inch pan. 8: Bake at 350°F for 10 minutes. 9: Spread apricot mixture evenly over crust, spreading to within 1/4 inch from edge of pan. 10: Sprinkle with remaining coconut mixture. Bake an additional 30 minutes. 11: Let cool in pan; chill. 12: Cut into bars. 13: Store in refrigerator.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4159,"Pastry Shells","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pastry Shells recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,1061.4,69.8,17.3,0.0,874.6,95.4,3.4,0.3,12.9,"0.0","Pastry Shells Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix and sift flour. 2: Cut in shortening with a knife. Add only enough  water to hold the ingredients together. 3: DO NOT KNEAD. 4: Divide the  dough into 2 parts and roll out onto a slightly floured wooden board. 5: Line the pie pan with only 1 of the dough parts. 6: Pinch the edges or  use a fork to make the edged design. 7: Poke the bottom of the shell  with the fork. 8: Bake in oven at 460* for 10 - 15 minutes. 9: **Cook the 2nd shell according to directions unless you are using the  2nd shell as a covering for a pie, then place it on top of the pie  raw and cook according to the pie''s directions.**  This recipe yields 2 pastry shells.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4160,"Scratch Hot Water Pastry","0","PT20M","PT20M","Make and share this Scratch Hot Water Pastry recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",3.5,3.0,1588.1,104.2,25.9,0.0,1839.8,143.4,5.1,0.5,19.4,"0.0","Scratch Hot Water Pastry Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream shortening with a fork into the 1/4 cup of boiling  water. 2: Mix  and sift the flour, salt, and baking powder. 3: Add the mixture to the  shortening slowly. 4: Blend well. 5: Form into a ball and refrigerate  until ready to use.  . 6: Yield = 1 pastry shell.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4161,"Easy Apricot Bars","PT40M","PT30M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Easy Apricot Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",0.0,0.0,96.4,5.2,2.6,14.1,29.9,12.2,0.3,6.4,0.9,"0.0","Easy Apricot Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream room temperature butter with sugar until fluffy. 2: Blend in the one egg  yolk. 3: Mix in 2 cups of flour , and the nuts  . 4: Divide dough in two parts. 5: Spread or press 1 part in a greased 9 x 13 pan. 6: Cover with the apricot jam. 7: Drop  remaining dough in spoonfuls over the jam, spreading to edges carefully. 8: Bake in a 350F oven about 40 minutes or until golden. 9: Cool and cut into squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4162,"Black and Tan Onion Rings","0","PT0S","PT0S","Despite the title, this recipe contains no alcohol. I created this recipe one day and pretty much improvised.   In any case, the reason for the title is the texture.  This recipe yields onion rings that are crispy and tasty on the outside and tender on the inside.  According to me the best results of this recipe are the texture of the product and the fact that these rings don''t taste as fatty as most other varieties.  Honestly, these are the best onion rings I have ever had.  If you''ve seen other recipes for onion rings, you''ll probably notice the absence of buttermilk and the presense of chicken or vegetable stock here. I did this because I simply had no buttermilk at the time and instead of using a bland ingredient or another ingredient that would yield more fat content, I opted for the stock.","Onions",5.0,7.0,159.3,1.3,0.2,1.4,68.1,31.7,2.5,2.5,5.3,"8.0","Black and Tan Onion Rings Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut onions into 1/4-inch slices and separate concentric rings.  Set aside. 2: Mix flour, salt (optionally), paprika, cayenne pepper, and the pepper flakes. 3: Add stock until mixture takes on a  batter consistency -- see note below. 4: Pour oil  into heavy saucepan, wok, or deep fryer to a depth of 2 to 3 inches.  Heat to 350F. 5: Preferably with tongs, coat each ring individually until completely covered with batter. 6: In batches, place rings into the oil until batter takes on  various shades of medium and dark brown. 7: Remove rings from oil and place on dioxin-free paper towel to absorb the excess oil. 8: * I''m not sure exactly how much stock to use here but start with the recommended 1 1/2 cups and add flour and stock intermittently until a batter texture is achieved.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4163,"Birdseed Bar","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Birdseed Bar recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",4.5,2.0,406.4,28.6,10.8,17.8,130.6,36.1,4.7,24.2,7.7,"12.0","Birdseed Bar Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat the first four ingredients, one after another in a large frying pan, until toasted and lightly browned. 2: Mix with sultanas in a large bowl. 3: Heat butter, honey and brown sugar to the soft ball stage, then pour over mixture in bowl. 4: Mix well. 5: Press into pan so it is 2cm thick. 6: When nearly cold, cut into bars. 7: Store in airtight container. 8: Cheers  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 9: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4164,"Pumpkin Walnut Fudge","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pumpkin Walnut Fudge recipe from Food.com.","Candy",1.0,1.0,5317.0,196.3,41.8,125.8,171.4,902.0,16.3,825.2,45.2,"1.0","Pumpkin Walnut Fudge Recipe Instructions:  1: In a 4 quart heavy saucepan combine sugar, milk, corn syrup, pumpkin and a pinch of salt. Cook the mixture over med. 2: heat, stirring, until sugar dissolves and  cook it undisturbed, until a candy thermometer registers 238 degrees. 3: Remove the pan from heat, add butter (do not stir it into mixture), and let the mixture  cool until it is 140 degrees. 4: Stir in vanilla a nd walnuts. 5: Beat the mixture with a wooden spoon for 30 sec-1 min. 6: , or until it begins to lose its gloss. 7: Pour  immediately into a buttered 9\ 8: Let the fudge cool until it begins to harden. 9: Cut it into squares. 10: Let it cool completely. 11: - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  NOTES : The fudge keeps, stored between sheets of waxed paper in an airtight  container, in a cool place for 2 weeks. 12: Makes 2 pounds.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4165,"Spicy Fish Cakes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Spicy Fish Cakes recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",4.0,2.0,1515.0,79.6,18.3,608.8,2905.1,89.0,12.5,7.4,109.6,"0.0","Spicy Fish Cakes Recipe Instructions:  1: Slice onions finely. 2: Chop the flesh of the capsicum finely. 3: Cut the potatoes into 1cm cubes. 4: Place all into a bowl with the Creole seasoning. 5: Cut the fish into small pieces and mix through the potato mixture with the eggs, flour, salt and parsley. 6: Heat frypan and add oil and butter. 7: Cook 1 Tbs of the mixture, turning to brown both sides. 8: Place fritters on absorbent paper. 9: Serve with Corn Salsa, relish or a fruit chutney. 10: Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 11: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4166,"English Bangers","0","PT1H","PT1H","Make and share this English Bangers recipe from Food.com.","Pork",0.0,1.0,934.0,42.8,14.5,386.4,2191.3,1.6,0.8,0.2,126.8,"0.0","English Bangers Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash the sausage casings thoroughly inside and out in running water, making sure they do not escape down the drain! Fill with tepid water, and leave to soak in the sink while preparing the sausage meat. 2: Cut all the meat into 1\ 3: ,  4: ,  5: ,  6: Take a small patty and cook it in a frying pan to check the seasoning. Re-season if needed. 7: Slide the skins onto the filling tube and fit to the mincer. Fill the casings, taking care not to fill too tightly, or the sausages will burst when cooked. 8: Twist into suitable sized links and hang up in a cool place to mature 24 hours before freezing or cooking.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4167,"Chocolate Almond Shortcake","PT40M","PT30M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Chocolate Almond Shortcake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,4093.6,196.3,120.1,859.6,2226.8,549.2,7.6,336.8,42.7,"0.0","Chocolate Almond Shortcake Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter and sugar, add egg, beat well. 2: Add sifted dry ingredients. 3: Press into swiss roll tin. 4: Bake 20 minutes about 400 0°F. 5: ALMOND TOPPING- Beat egg and butter, add essence, then dry ingredients.  Mix well. 6: Spread on base.  Allow to set. 7: Ice with chocolate icing.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4168,"Alfredo Fettuccine","PT10M","PT15M","PT25M","Make and share this Alfredo Fettuccine recipe from Food.com.","European",4.5,62.0,716.9,51.5,30.1,192.1,698.5,45.1,1.9,3.1,19.9,"4.0","Alfredo Fettuccine Recipe Instructions:  1: In large saucepan combine cream cheese, parmesan, butter and milk, stirring constantly until smooth. 2: Toss pasta lightly with sauce, coating well. 3: Leftovers freeze well.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4169,"Beef and Guinness Casserole","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Beef and Guinness Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.0,2.0,1078.0,53.2,18.5,130.0,537.0,48.3,1.7,5.2,36.5,"6.0","Beef and Guinness Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut steak into 5cm pieces.  Heat oil in a large frying pan and brown over a moderately high heat until well browned.  Transfer to casserole dish. 2: Peel and quarter the onions and break into \ 3: , add to the pan and cook them for about 3 minutes, then add the garlic and cook for one more minute. 4: Sprinkle the flour over the onion and stir well to coat the onions in the oil. 5: Gradually pour in the stout and beef stock and bring to the boil to make a smooth sauce. 6: Pour over the meat in the casserole dish, then stir in the bacon, thyme and orange rind. 7: Cook at 160 C for 1 1/2 - 2 hours or until the meat is tender. 8: Serve with mashed potatoes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4170,"Microwave Gravy","0","PT0S","PT0S","These recipes are adapted from Barbara Kafka''s Microwave Gourmet. They are based on an oven of 650 to 700 watt oven, which is low by today''s standards. If your microwave is lower or higher power, you should adjust the times.  Veloute","Low Protein",5.0,3.0,559.2,56.3,34.9,193.6,520.1,9.5,0.2,0.5,5.8,"0.0","Microwave Gravy Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat butter in an 8 cup glass measuring cup at 100%, uncovered, for 2 min. 2: Remove from oven. 3: Thoroughly whisk in flour. 4: Cook, uncovered at 100% for 2 min more.  Remove from oven. 5: Whisk in cream and broth. 6: Cook, uncovered at 100% for 2 min; stir and cook for 3 min more. Remove from oven, add salt and pepper and whisk until smooth. 7: Add lemon juice to taste. Variation with mushrooms (This is my standard Thanksgiving gravy.) Increase butter (or fat) to 4 tbsp. 8: Add flour and cook as for Veloute. Add 1/4 lb fresh mushrooms,  quartered and sliced (If the mushrooms are very large, cut in smaller pieces). You may also substitute dried mushrooms for a portion of the fresh mushrooms. 9: Add lemon juice and a dash of cayenne pepper. 10: (The recipe also lists 2 Tbsp of chopped dill as an optional ingredient, but I''ve never used it.) Cook, uncovered at 100% for 3 min, finish as for Veloute above. Another microwave sauce to use as gravy is Marchand du Vin  Sauce Makes 1 1/2 cups 1/4 cup chopped shallots (about 5 medium shallots) 1 clove garlic, smashed, peeled, and minced 2 cups red wine 1 cup chicken, duck, or veal broth 1 Tbsp chicken, duck or veal glaze (very concentrated broth) 2 tsp cornstarch dissolved in 3 tsp cold water (optional) fresh ground pepper Put shallots, garlic, wine and 1/2 cup of broth in a 8 cup glass measure. Cook, uncovered, at 100% for 20 minutes, until reduced by one half. 11: Remove from oven and deglaze roast cooking pan with this mixture, then cook on top of the stove until slightly thickened, and season to taste. If not deglazing, briskly stir in cornstarch slurry and cook uncovered, at 100% for 2 minutes. 12: Season to taste.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4171,"Italian Sausage, Sicilian Style","0","PT1H","PT1H","To stuff the casings, you will need a meat grinder with a sausage horn attachment. If you don''t have such a device, use the mixture to make fried patties by shaping 1/4 cup of filling into a 1/2 inch thick patty and frying in hot oil until golden brown on both sides.","Pork",5.0,2.0,2120.3,229.8,87.2,160.3,611.0,2.2,0.8,0.2,7.1,"4.0","Italian Sausage, Sicilian Style Recipe Instructions:  1: To prepare casings: Let casings soak in cool water about five minutes to remove salt on outer surface (no longer, or they will become too tender to stuff) and flush salt from the inside by placing one end on faucet nozzle and turn on cold tap water (if you see holes or water leaking, cut and discard). 2: Remove casing from faucet and gently squeeze out water; cover rinsed casings and refrigerate until ready to use. 3: Mix all the ingredients and let stand for 1 hour. 4: Mix again and then stuff into casings. 5: Column: ''Sausages like Mama used to make''  Frugal Gourmet News column.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4172,"Coronation Chicken II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Coronation Chicken II recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",0.0,0.0,6798.9,483.4,136.3,2602.3,2156.5,25.8,5.5,8.6,518.6,"1.0","Coronation Chicken II Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large pot, place chickens, carrot, bouquet garni, salt and peppercorns in enough water and a little wine to barely cover. Bring to a simmer and poach for 40 minutes or until tender. 2: Cool in the liquid and then remove chicken and cut up, discarding skin and bones. Cut meat into cubes or pieces. 3: Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the onion and cook gently 2-4 minutes. 4: Add the curry powder and cook for two minutes. 5: Add tomato puree and wine, water, bay leaf. Bring to a boil. 6: Season with the salt, sugar black pepper, lemon slices and juice. Simmer, uncovered for 5-10 minutes. Strain and cool. 7: Add mayonnaise gradually with apricot puree to taste. adjust seasonings. Add more lemon juice if desired. 8: Stir in whipped cream. 9: Mix chicken with enough of the curry sauce to moisten. Serve arranged on a platter and topped with remaining sauce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4176,"Baklava","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","Make and share this Baklava recipe from Food.com.","< 60 Mins",5.0,13.0,362.7,23.3,9.0,38.7,191.5,38.0,1.5,27.5,3.9,"30.0","Baklava Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients for syrup in saucepan, bring to boil, simmer for 10 min., strain, and allow to cool. 2: Mix egg, sugar, cinnamon and allspice well. 3: Coarsely grind or chop walnuts and almonds; mix thoroughly with bread crumbs and egg, sugar, cinnamon, allspice mixture.  Brush a 9\ 4: x2\ 5: ,  6: Cover with remaining filo sheets; brush ea. sheet with butter. 7: With a very sharp knife, cut the top filo sheets into triangles (cutting diagonally across pan).  Insert clove in center of ea. triangle. 8: Bake (350 degrees F.) for 1 hr. until baklava is evenly browned. 9: Remove from oven; pour cooled syrup evenly over it, so that it penetrates the layers. 10: Cool several hrs. before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4177,"Danish Applepork","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Danish Applepork recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,5.0,229.2,7.4,2.6,64.5,46.6,18.0,2.6,12.2,22.6,"4.0","Danish Applepork Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut the pork into cubes, and fry them on a dry frying pan. 2: Remove the pork. 3: Cut the onions into slices, and fry (brown) them in the lard from the pork. 4: Remove the onions. 5: Cut the apples into slices, and fry them \ 6:  on the frying pan, with the frying pan covered. 7: Sprinkle the sugar over the apples. 8: Mix the pork and onions with the apples. 9: It tastes wonderful together with dark bread or mashed potatoes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4178,"Helen''s Husband''s Delicious Cheese Spread","0","PT0S","PT0S","The name?  Well, Helen didn''t like to cook so her husband made this for her to take to potlucks. I like to make it at Christmas time.  It keeps in the refrigerator for 3-4 weeks.  That way I make a mess once and have a spread to take to several events.","Spreads",4.5,2.0,6204.4,545.8,273.1,1295.9,11981.5,25.1,7.0,8.7,299.7,"1.0","Helen''s Husband''s Delicious Cheese Spread Recipe Instructions:  1: Put everything except mayonnaise through meat grinder. 2: Mix in mayonnaise. Serve with bread or crackers. 3: Also makes good finger sandwiches. 4: This makes a large mixing bowl of spread.  Makes enough spread for 4 loaves of bread.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4179,"English Spiced Beef","0","PT0S","PT0S","This was one of the great Victorian Christmas season dishes; the perfect centre piece for a cold supper buffet. A neat round joint of silverside or topside is the best for this kind of dish.","Meat",5.0,1.0,53.4,0.0,0.0,0.0,7388.0,13.8,0.0,13.6,0.0,"0.0","English Spiced Beef Recipe Instructions:  1: Saltpeter is a necessary preservative when curing meat and also adds a pleasing red color otherwise the beef will turn out a murky grey. 2: Rub the meat all over with the sugar and put it in a pot with a lid for 2 days. Leave it in a cool place, turning and rubbing the meat occasionally with the sticky liquor that develops. 3: Crush the peppercorns, juniper and allspice with a pestle and mortar and mix with the salt and saltpeter. 4: Rub this mixture well into the meat and leave it in the pot for a further 9 days. Turn the meat and rub the pickling mixture into the flesh daily. 5: When the pickling is complete, remove the beef and rub off any excess spices adhering to the surface. Do not rinse it. 6: Wrap the meat in cooking foil [the Victorians used suet] and put into a large ovenproof pot. Add about 10 fl oz water, cover the pot with a double layer of foil and fit the lid on tightly. 7: Preheat the oven to 275 deg F. 8: Bake the meat slowly allowing 45 min per lb. 9: When the meat is cooked, remove the pot and set aside until it is quite cold. 10: Unwrap the meat, drain off any excess liquid and place on a board. 11: Cover with foil, put a weight on it and leave for at least 24 hr. 12: Carve the meat into thin slices and serve with anything from good mustard to pickled kumquats.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4180,"Vegetable Chili","PT45M","PT0S","PT45M","Make and share this Vegetable Chili recipe from Food.com.","Beans",5.0,5.0,125.0,2.0,0.4,0.0,399.1,21.7,7.8,6.6,7.1,"6.0","Vegetable Chili Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add green onions and garlic; saute 2 minutes. 2: Add chili powder, cumin, and cinnamon; saute, 30 seconds. 3: Add tomato and next 5 ingredients; bring to a boil. 4: Reduce heat, and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes. 5: Stir in beans; cook 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4181,"Honey Oat Bread (Bread Machine)","PT3H5M","PT5M","PT3H10M","Make and share this Honey Oat Bread (Bread Machine) recipe from Food.com.","Yeast Breads",5.0,53.0,255.3,4.3,0.6,0.0,293.8,48.3,2.1,8.9,5.9,"8.0","Honey Oat Bread (Bread Machine) Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine ingredients in breadmaker per your manufacturer''s instructions. 2: You can replace 2 cups white bread flour with 2 cups whole wheat flour but include 1 tbsp vital wheat gluten (the  original recipe suggested this). 3: Makes a moist, sweet loaf. 4: NOTE: cook time is for the basic/white cycle (medium crust; 1½ lb loaf) using a BreadmanPlus bread machine; your machine may differ.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4184,"Salad Dressing Dry Mix","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Salad Dressing Dry Mix recipe from Food.com.","Salad Dressings",3.5,2.0,179.3,14.4,1.9,0.0,1777.4,11.8,2.5,4.6,3.1,"8.0","Salad Dressing Dry Mix Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix salt, garlic powder, seasoning, mustard, paprika, pectin and sugar substitute in jar with tight-fitting lid.  Store in a cool, dry place. 20 cal per tsp. 2: SALAD DRESSING Whisk dry mix, vinegar, water and oil in a bowl. Refrigerate up to 3 days. 3: VEGETABLE SALAD  Combine onion, celery, broccoli, tomato, squash, zucchini and cucumbers in large bowl. 4: Toss with 1/2 cup dressing. 5: Marinate in refrigerator for 30 minutes. 6: Spread lettuce over platter. 7: Spoon vegetables over lettuce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4186,"British Christmas Cake","PT4H","PT3H","PT7H","Make and share this British Christmas Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,1275.0,61.4,25.5,252.1,415.8,163.9,8.7,95.9,20.9,"8.0","British Christmas Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Grease a 8 inch square cake tin; line it with greased greaseproof paper. Tie double brown paper round the outside. 2: Sift the flour and spices together into a large mixing bowl and stir in the grated lemon rind. 3: Cream the butter in a separate bowl and gradually beat in the sugar until light and fluffy. 4: Add the treacle and fold into mixture. 5: Add the eggs beating the mixture after each egg. 6: If the mixture curdles add a little flour. 7: Lightly fold in the sifted flour with the fruit, nuts and mixed peel until evenly distributed. 8: Add and mix in the  brandy ( 3 tablespoons ) 9: Spoon the mixture into the cake tin and level the  surface. Knock tin to get rid of air bubbles. 10: Make an indentation in the centre to allow for the cake rising in the centre.  Cover and leave in a cool place for 24 hours. 11: Place an ovenware container of water on the bottom of the oven. Then place cake tin on a double piece of brown paper on middle shelf of oven and bake at 150 deg. C or 300 deg. F for 4 hours. 12: Test to see if cooked by inserting a skewer in the cake which should come out  clean. 13: Cool cake in the tin for an hour then turn out onto a wire rack and remove the paper. 14: When cold, prick the cake top with the skewer and spoon the  remaining brandy over the cake surface. Wrap in fresh greaseproof paper then foil. 15: Place inverted into an airtight tin for at least one month before covering the cake with almond paste. Finish off with royal icing and decorate to your preference.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4187,"Meatless Chili","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Meatless Chili recipe from Food.com.","Beans",0.0,0.0,297.6,1.2,0.2,0.0,26.1,60.0,10.4,4.2,13.0,"8.0","Meatless Chili Recipe Instructions:  1: In Dutch oven or soup pot, simmer onion and celery in small amount of water. 2: Add  tomatoes and mash into small pieces. 3: Add beans and liquid. 4: Add chili powder and  white pepper to suit taste. (Salt may be added, if you want.) Cover and simmer  for 1 hour. 5: Stir occasionally. 6: Prepare rice in separate saucepan according to  package directions. 7: To serve, place small amount of prepared rice in each bowl. 8: Top with chili mixture and stir.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4189,"Meatless Chili II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Meatless Chili II recipe from Food.com.","Beans",0.0,0.0,317.5,3.4,0.5,0.0,657.6,56.5,17.3,8.5,19.0,"4.0","Meatless Chili II Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute onions in oil. 2: Add ingredients. 3: Stir. 4: Simmer 20  to 25 minutes. 5: Celery should be crisp. 6: Serve over rice or  with bread and salad. 7: May be frozen in oiled baking  dish. 8: Defrost and bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4190,"Meatless Chili III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Meatless Chili III recipe from Food.com.","Beans",5.0,1.0,255.0,4.0,0.6,0.0,577.4,46.4,12.5,9.0,11.5,"6.0","Meatless Chili III Recipe Instructions:  1: In 5-quart saucepan heat oi l. 2: Add onion, garlic, chili powder, basil leaves,  oregano and cumin. 3: Cook, stirring, 5 minutes or until onion is tender. 4: Add  zucchini and carrots. 5: Cook, stirring, 1 to 2 minutes. 6: Stir in remaining  ingredients. 7: Bring to boil. 8: Reduce heat; simmer 30 to 35 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4194,"Poulet Aux Amandes - Almond Chicken","PT10M","PT20M","PT30M","Make and share this Poulet Aux Amandes - Almond Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Thigh & Leg",0.0,0.0,466.9,35.9,5.8,79.0,629.8,11.5,5.4,3.0,26.9,"4.0","Poulet Aux Amandes - Almond Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut the chicken in 1 cm cubes.  Marinate the chicken in the wine, egg white, soy sauce, sugar, and salt for twenty minutes. 2: Toast the almonds until they are speckled brown. 3: Dice the scallions into 2 cm. pieces. 4: Finely chop the ginger. 5: Mix the cornstarch (thickener) well in one Tbsp. cold water. 6: Heat the pan for 30 seconds on high heat.  Add peanut oil and heat the pan 30 seconds more. 7: Add the chicken.  Cook for 7 minutes while stirring. 8: Add the almonds, the scallions, and the ginger.  Allow the mixture to cook 2 minutes. 9: Incorporate the cornstarch mixture.  Lower the flame to low heat. While turning, allow the mixture to cook one minute until all ingredients are lightly glazed. 10: Pour the contents of the pan on a heated plate and serve immediately. 11: Remarks: 12: 1.  You can replace the chicken with pork or ham.  The cooking time for the meat would have to be increased from 7 to 12 minutes. 13: 2.  You can replace the almonds with pine nuts or cashews.  You must toast the pine nuts, but you do not need to cook them with the other ingredients. You would sprinkle them on the completed dish when serving. 14: 3.  You may add to the dish 1/4 lb. peeled shrimp, allowing it to be cooked for three minutes with the chicken. 15: 4.  Instead of the scallions you may substitute small onions.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4195,"Walnut Baklava","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Walnut Baklava recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",0.0,0.0,753.4,57.6,18.4,61.0,493.2,52.8,4.8,11.4,12.2,"10.0","Walnut Baklava Recipe Instructions:  1: THE SYRUP    4      cups          sugar    3      cups          water    1 1/2  cups          honey    1                    cinnamon stick    6                    whole cloves  Preheat oven to 250 degrees. 2: Mix together the walnuts, sugar and cinnamon. 3: Select a pan the size of the phyllo sheets and brush well with some melted butter. 4: Place 4 sheets phyllo, brushing each with butter, in the  bottom of the prepared pan. 5: To p with a sheet of unbuttered phyllo then sprinkle with a handful of the walnut mixture. Cover with a buttered sheet then an unbuttered sheet and another sprinkling of walnuts. 6: Repeat this layering until all ingredients are used up, reserving 5 sheets phyllo for the top. 7: Place last 5 sheets of phyllo, brushing each with butter, on top of pastry and pour remaining butter over all. 8: Cut the baklava into traditional diamond pattern , being careful not to cut through bottom layers. 9: Bake for 1 hour. 10: Remove from oven and let cool. 11: SYRUP Combine sugar and water in a large saucepan and boil for 5 minutes. 12: Add the honey, cinnamon stick and cloves and continue boiling 5 minutes longer. 13: Pour hot syrup over completely cooled baklava. 14: Cool completely, cut through bottom layers following previous cuts and serve.                    - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - NOTES :    Be sure baklava is completely cooled before adding hot syrup or it will be soggy.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4196,"Sicilian Style Sausage","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sicilian Style Sausage recipe from Food.com.","Pork",0.0,0.0,1867.2,203.9,77.1,141.2,604.7,0.9,0.4,0.0,6.2,"10.0","Sicilian Style Sausage Recipe Instructions:  1: Grind meat and fat together through a coarse disk. 2: Place in a large bowl. Add  remaining ingredients to meat and mix well to combine. 3: Stuff mixture into casings and twist off into 3 - 4 inch links. 4: Refrigerate and use within 3 days or freeze.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4197,"Glazed Teriyaki Salmon","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Glazed Teriyaki Salmon recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.0,1.0,303.4,14.1,2.2,73.1,1459.9,4.7,0.4,2.4,35.5,"4.0","Glazed Teriyaki Salmon Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine first 9 ingredients in a shallow dish or large zip-lock bag; add  salmon fillets. 2: Cover or seal and chill 30 minutes, turning once. Remove the  fillets from marinade, reserving marinade. Place fillets in a 9x13 pan. 3: Bake at  450: for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. 4: Remove from oven  and keep warm. 5: Bring marinade to a boil in a small saucepan; cook stirring  often, 6-8 minutes or until reduced by half. 6: Pour over fillets.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4198,"Baked Oriental Salmon","PT15M","PT15M","PT30M","Make and share this Baked Oriental Salmon recipe from Food.com.","< 30 Mins",4.0,1.0,192.6,6.0,0.9,78.8,561.5,1.9,0.0,1.6,30.9,"3.0","Baked Oriental Salmon Recipe Instructions:  1: In a bowl combine marinade ingredients. 2: Place salmon in a glass baking  dish-pour the marinade over the fillets. 3: Let stand 10 minutes at room temp. 4: Bake at 425: 10-15 minutes basting once or twice with the pan juices until the  fish flakes easily with a fork.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4200,"Blueberry Dump Cake","PT50M","PT5M","PT55M","Make and share this Blueberry Dump Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,12.0,312.7,16.0,5.9,21.2,355.0,41.1,1.7,23.5,3.0,"0.0","Blueberry Dump Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Pour pineapple and berries into 13 x 9-inch pan. 2: \ 3:  cake mix (sprinkle) over berries and pineapple. Melt stick of butter. 4: Pour over cake mix. 5: Sprinkle nuts over the top. 6: Bake at 375 degrees for 35 to 50 minutes, depending on oven, until bubbly.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4201,"Dump Cake II","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","Make and share this Dump Cake II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,581.1,23.2,9.0,30.5,624.4,92.2,3.5,58.5,5.1,"8.0","Dump Cake II Recipe Instructions:  1: Butter pan. 2: Dump pineapple and juice into pan. 3: Dump pie filling on top. 4: Dump cake mix over all. 5: Slice remaining butter over cake and add nuts. 6: Bake at 350  degrees for 45 to 60 minutes. 7: Serve warm with ice cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4202,"Dump Cake IIi","PT1H","PT10M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Dump Cake IIi recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,2.0,506.5,34.4,14.7,0.8,496.7,48.2,5.0,27.2,5.5,"12.0","Dump Cake IIi Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350F and lightly grease a 13 x 9 pan. 2: Spread each of the ingredients evenly in oblong pan or Pyrex dish, one on top of the other, in the order listed (pineapple, coconut, cake mix, nuts and  margarine). 3: Do not mix. 4: Bake 1 hour. 5: Deluxe Dump Cake: Same as before with the additional ingredient of 1 can cherry pie filling as the first ingredient.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4203,"Mashed Potato Casserole (Perunasoselaatikko)","0","PT0S","PT0S","This casserole is a traditional Christmas food, eaten with ham, boiled peas, boiled dried plums and pickled beets. Names in parentheses are used in  Finland.","Potato",5.0,5.0,780.4,41.0,24.2,307.2,357.0,89.5,10.0,12.4,16.8,"1.0","Mashed Potato Casserole (Perunasoselaatikko) Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel potatoes. 2: Boil them in salted water until soft. Mash them. 3: Add milk and butter. 4: Beat soft. Add eggs one at the time, beating. 5: Add sugar and nutmeg. 6: Pour into buttered casserole pot. (Sprinkle bread crumbs and little butter cubes on top.) Bake in 200 C oven for  30 - 40  minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4204,"Sweet Potato Casserole (Imelletty Perunalaatikko)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Following casseroles are traditional Christmas food, eaten with ham, boiled  peas, boiled dried plums and pickled beets. Names in parentheses are used in  Finland. Please note: Sweet potato casserole pot  should not be filled more than half full to avoid bubbling over in oven.","Potato",4.0,1.0,2044.9,21.1,12.4,72.4,7351.0,415.0,46.7,40.9,60.5,"1.0","Sweet Potato Casserole (Imelletty Perunalaatikko) Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel potatoes. 2: Boil them until soft. Mash them. 3: Add sugar and  half of the flour and sprinkle the rest on top. 4: Place in a warm  place covered with a cloth for an hour. 5: Add enough milk to get  runny mixture. Add nutmeg and salt Pour in two casserole pots. 6: Bake in 175 C oven for an hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4206,"Margaritas En Jarra","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Margaritas En Jarra recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",4.0,2.0,24.3,0.0,0.0,0.0,6.5,6.2,0.1,5.2,0.4,"6.0","Margaritas En Jarra Recipe Instructions:  1: In blender container, combine the crushed ice, tequila, lime juice, powdered sugar, egg white and Triple Sec. Cover and blend until very frothy. 2: Transfer to pitcher; garnish with lime slices. 3: Serve in salt-rimmed cocktail glasses. 4: To prepare glasses: Rub the rim of each cocktail glass with a little lime juice. Invert glass in a shallow dish of salt; shake off excess salt.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4207,"Frosted Margaritas","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Frosted Margaritas recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",5.0,3.0,66.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,4.3,17.5,0.1,15.2,0.1,"2.0","Frosted Margaritas Recipe Instructions:  1: Rub rim of 2 cocktail glasses with wedge of lime. Place salt in saucer; spin rim of each glass in salt. 2: Combine remaining ingredients in container of an electric blender; process until mixture reaches desired consistency. 3: Pour into the prepared glasses.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4208,"Margarita Mix","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Margarita Mix recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",0.0,0.0,2640.5,1.3,0.1,0.0,238.4,658.8,0.9,636.3,15.7,"0.0","Margarita Mix Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix ingredients together and keep in the refrigerator for future use. 2: For two drinks: Blend 1 cup mix and two shots tequila. Serve in salted glass with lime garnish.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4209,"Potato Pancakes II","0","PT0S","PT40M","Make and share this Potato Pancakes II recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",5.0,6.0,246.6,2.8,0.8,105.8,720.7,47.4,5.2,2.6,8.7,"4.0","Potato Pancakes II Recipe Instructions:  1: Grate potatoes, place in a colander and rinse under cold water to remove starch. Drain well. 2: Grate onion, place in a colander and press with the back of a wooden spoon to remove excess moisture. 3: Combine potatoes and onion in a large bowl. 4: Beat eggs into mixture. Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and pepper. 5: Heat 1/8 inch oil in a large skillet. Drop about 2 tablespoonful of batter into the oil and flatten with the back of a wooden spoon. 6: The flatter the pancake the crisper it will be. Brown well on both sides. 7: Drain on paper towel. Keep cooked pancakes warm in a 100 degree oven.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4210,"Potato Pancakes - German Style","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Potato Pancakes - German Style recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",5.0,11.0,259.1,2.7,0.9,93.0,498.8,50.4,5.7,3.0,9.1,"6.0","Potato Pancakes - German Style Recipe Instructions:  1: Keep potatoes covered with cold water until ready to grate in the food  processor. 2: Fit the medium shredding blade into food processor and shred  potatoes and onion. 3: Dry potatoes and onion between sheets of paper towel. 4: In a large bowl combine potato mixture with eggs, flour, baking powder,  parsley and salt.   In a large skillet heat 1/8 inch vegetable oil until hot. Pour in 1/3 cup  potato mixture, flattening with the back of a wooden spoon, and fry until  crisp and golden brown on both sides, about 3 minutes per s  ide.   Drain on paper towel and keep warm in a 100 degree oven. 5: Serve with  applesauce.   - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4212,"Vegetable Cheese Soup","PT45M","PT10M","PT55M","This is a family favorite.  My grandchildren do not like peas so I omit the peas when I make this for them.","Cheese",4.5,3.0,603.3,35.2,22.1,106.9,1174.5,49.4,6.5,5.5,24.2,"0.0","Vegetable Cheese Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook vegetables and seasonings until tender.  DO NOT DRAIN. 2: Blend butter and flour, and then add milk.  Cook until thickened and add 2 cups shredded cheese. 3: Stir into the vegetable mixture.  ENJOY!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4213,"Stained-Glass Cake (Fruitcake)","PT1H30M","PT0S","PT1H30M","From the traditional to the (comparatively) new-fangled. Stained glass or bishopcakes, very popular in the UK, are so called, one presumes, because they consist almost entirely of glace fruit and nuts, and the glace fruit has something of the translucency of a stained-glass church window.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,647.4,40.1,5.9,52.9,95.8,69.2,7.6,46.4,12.1,"8.0","Stained-Glass Cake (Fruitcake) Recipe Instructions:  1: Butter a large cake tin. Line with waxed paper. Butter the paper. 2: Chop the glace fruits roughly. 3: Sift together the flour and baking powder. 4: Mix in all the fruits, together with the nuts. 5: Put the mixture into the cake tin, wet hands and press mixture down firmly. 6: Bake in a preheated 300F degree oven for 1 1/2 hours. 7: Take cake out  of the oven and drizzle the Grand Marnier or Cointreau over the top. 8: Leave the cake in the oven to cool until warm, then wrap it, tin and all, in aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.  Remove from tin, peel away paper and store in airtight tin.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4214,"Helen''s Light Fruitcake","PT3H","PT0S","PT3H","Make and share this Helen''s Light Fruitcake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,1483.3,67.0,27.0,309.1,579.1,209.6,12.3,134.4,26.7,"10.0","Helen''s Light Fruitcake Recipe Instructions:  1: Clean sultanas, slice pineapple thinly, halve cherries. 2: Mix and sift flour,. 3: baking powder and spice and add half to prepared fruit.   In a large bowl, cream  butter and gradually beat in sugar. 4: Add well beaten eggs and beat well. 5: Fold  other half of flour mixture into creamed mixture alternately with juices and  beat well. 6: Add fruit to to creamed mixture. Combine mixture til thoroughly  blended. 7: Split almonds and add to mixture, saving some whole for top. 8: Add  flavourings. 9: Pour mixture into cake pans which have been lined with 3  thicknesses of newspaper  , with top layer of greased wax paper. 10: Bake cake at 275°F. 11: for approximately 3 hours or til firm and until cake mixture is firm when  pressed. 12: Cool on cake rack until thoroughly cold. 13: Wrap in foil and store in  cake tins.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4215,"Berkshire Fruitcake","PT3H20M","PT0S","PT3H20M","Make and share this Berkshire Fruitcake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,9067.8,223.5,127.3,1757.0,4648.2,1757.8,77.8,1175.6,124.2,"1.0","Berkshire Fruitcake Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift flour once, measure, add baking powder, salt, and spices; sift together three times. 2: Cream butter thoroughly, add sugar gradually, and cream together until light and fluffy. 3: Add eggs and beat well. 4: Add fruit, grape juice, and molasses, and mix well. 5: Add flour gradually, beating after each addition until smooth. 6: Turn into tube pan, which has been greased, lined with heavy paper, and again greased. 7: Bake in very slow oven ( 250 F.) 4-1/2 hours, or until done.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4216,"Rich Boiled Fruitcake from Mary Killen","PT1H15M","PT15M","PT1H30M","Make and share this Rich Boiled Fruitcake from Mary Killen recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,3880.6,150.1,32.2,372.0,3054.2,616.7,23.0,386.3,49.8,"1.0","Rich Boiled Fruitcake from Mary Killen Recipe Instructions:  1: Place margarine, sugar, fruit and water into saucepan. Bring to a boil and simmer for approximately 10 minutes. Leave to cool. 2: Sieve flour, spices, and baking soda and add to contents of saucepan. 3: Beat eggs into mixture and pour into a greased and lined 7\ 4: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4217,"Grandma West Cream Fruitcake","PT1H10M","PT0S","PT1H10M","Make and share this Grandma West Cream Fruitcake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,1964.8,100.1,39.4,268.8,1080.7,247.4,10.7,106.6,29.1,"4.0","Grandma West Cream Fruitcake Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream well sugar, Crisco and eggs. 2: Mix together cloves, almond extract and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture. Add soda to whipping  cream, mix real well. Don''t leave any lumps. 3: (Important to add soda to whipping cream, fresh whipping cream makes the cake taste much better.) Add whipping cream to creamed mixture. Mix well by hand with spoon. 4: Add 2 cups flour to creamed mixture. Mix well. Mix by hand, mixture too thick to use mixer. 5: Add mixed fruit; mix well. Add nut  meats; mix well. 6: Bake in 3 small bread pans (I use disposable pans)  greased, lined with wax paper (let paper edges hang out of pan), and  then grease wax paper. 7: Pour cake mixture in and bake at 300 degrees  for 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. 8: Cool,  wrap in aluminum foil and freeze until ready to use.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4219,"Potato Tomato Bake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Potato Tomato Bake recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,1.0,458.7,21.4,12.6,149.0,377.2,44.5,6.2,5.3,23.7,"0.0","Potato Tomato Bake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. 2: Scrub potatoes well. 3: Slice potatoes (about 3/8 inch thick) and boil until just tender. 4: Drain. 5: Slice tomatoes. 6: Grease two 10-inch glass pie plates. 7: Arrange potatoes in a single layer on bottom on pie plate. Follow with a layer of tomatoes and a generous sprinkle of cheese. Repeat this procedure until pie plate is full. 8: Last layer of tomatoes should be attractively arranged on top. 9: Beat eggs and milk together. 10: Add seasoned salt and pepper, to taste. Pour egg mixture over potatoes and tomatoes. 11: Top with some chopped parsley. 12: Bake at 375 degrees for 50 minutes to 1 hour until pie is set. Makes 6 to 8 servingd (2 pies)");
