INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4224,"Black Bean-Orzo Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Black Bean-Orzo Salad recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.5,15.0,143.2,5.2,0.7,0.0,74.8,20.7,1.9,2.0,4.2,"6.0","Black Bean-Orzo Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix beans, olives, tomatoes, onions and cilantro in large bowl. 2: Mix oil, lime juice, cumin, pepper and salt; toss with bean mixture. Stir in pasta. 3: Let stand for 1 hour to blend flavors. 4: Serve at room temperature as a side dish or on spinach");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4225,"Maui Onion Rings","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Maui Onion Rings recipe from Food.com.","Onions",0.0,0.0,187.5,0.5,0.1,0.0,3.7,40.2,2.2,3.6,4.8,"0.0","Maui Onion Rings Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine flour, cornstarch and salt and pepper to taste in large bowl. 2: Whisk in ale until smooth. 3: Cut onions into 1/4- to 1/3-inch-thick slices. 4: Heat oil in deep fryer to 400F. 5: Coat onion rings with batter. 6: Gently add to hot oil without crowding pan and cook until golden brown. 7: Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4226,"Low-Fat Chicken With Caramelized Onions","PT30M","PT10M","PT40M","Make and share this Low-Fat Chicken With Caramelized Onions recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,9.0,168.6,3.3,0.8,72.6,614.2,6.6,0.7,4.2,25.8,"4.0","Low-Fat Chicken With Caramelized Onions Recipe Instructions:  1: Coat large skillet with cooking spray and place over medium heat until hot. Add onion. 2: Cover and cook 10 minutes until deep golden stirring often. 3: combine salt, thyme, red pepper and black pepper. 4: Sprinkle half the mixture over onions. 5: Add 1/4 cup chicken broth and cook 10 minutes, stirring frequently. 6: Add 6 tablespoon broth and cook until liquid evaporates. 7: Repeat procedure with remaining broth. 8: Add vinegar and cook an additional 2 minutes or until most of the liquid evaporates. 9: Remove from pan and keep warm. 10: Rub chicken with remaining spice mixture. Coat skillet with cooking spray and heat. Add chicken and cook for 2 minutes on each side. Serve with onions.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4228,"Potato Cakes","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Potato Cakes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,10.0,58.4,0.8,0.1,0.0,60.8,11.0,1.2,0.6,1.9,"6.0","Potato Cakes Recipe Instructions:  1: In a medium size bowl, combine potatoes, egg white, onion, flour, salt and pepper. 2: Meanwhile, heat oil in a large skillet over medium high heat. 3: When hot, put about 2 tablespoons potato mixture for each  cake into skillet. Cook until well browned, then turn with a spatula and cook other side until brown. 4: Continue making cakes, keeping  first ones warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4230,"Leftover Potato Cakes","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Make and share this Leftover Potato Cakes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",4.0,3.0,87.2,0.6,0.3,2.1,317.1,18.4,1.6,1.6,2.0,"4.0","Leftover Potato Cakes Recipe Instructions:  1: Roll the potatoes into balls and flatten them. 2: Dip them in Melted butter. 3: Roll them in crushed cornflakes. 4: Place them in a greased pan. 5: Bake the balls at 350F until they are well heated (20-30 minutes).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4232,"Galletes de Pommes de Terre Potato Cakes","0","PT0S","PT0S","The potato cakes go well  with all meats and broiled (grilled) or roasted poultry, even if already garnished with other vegetables.  Once the potato gained acceptance, nineteenth-century French cooks had to invent interesting ways of preparing it. There was an infinite number of possibilities  and, nowadays, chefs are still inventing new recipes. These potato cakes were once the star dish for vegetarians.","Potato",5.0,2.0,223.7,6.9,1.2,0.0,12.8,37.2,4.7,1.7,4.3,"2.0","Galletes de Pommes de Terre Potato Cakes Recipe Instructions:  1: Divide the potato into 4 and shape into small cakes; season. 2: Heat the oil in an 11 inch (28 cm) nonstick skillet. 3: Add the potato cakes and cook over low heat,  with the pan half-covered, for about 5 minutes. 4: Turn the cakes and cook for 5  minutes, until golden and crispy. 5: Serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4233,"Garlic Herb Spread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Also makes a tasty vegetable dip, sandwich spread, or dressing for baked potatoes.   Diabetic, Low-Fat","Spreads",0.0,0.0,260.2,1.2,0.4,4.9,948.6,46.1,2.7,24.5,19.2,"0.0","Garlic Herb Spread Recipe Instructions:  1: Wrap the garlic head in aluminum foil and bake in a preheated 375F oven for 35 minutes. 2: Remove the foil and press the baked garlic until all the flesh squeezes out. You should have 1 heaping tablespoon of puree. . 3: Bring the sun-dried tomatoes to a boil in a small amount of water. 4: Let sit for 15 minutes, then drain on paper towels. Chop finely when dried. 5: Combine all the ingredients except the bread with a wire whisk. 6: Allow to sit for at least 30 minutes. If using the bread, lightly toast the slices on a baking sheet at 325F for 15 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4234,"Vanilla Pudding","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Vanilla Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,81.0,270.9,9.2,5.1,122.8,318.0,42.0,0.1,30.1,5.5,"5.0","Vanilla Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: In medium double boiler, cook sugar, cornstarch, milk  and salt. When mixture begins to thicken, add part of mixture  to egg yolks; mix well, then pour egg mixture back into mixture  in double boiler. 2: Cook until thick; take off stove, then add  butter and vanilla. 3: You can use as pudding and top with Cool  Whip or use pudding with bananas for banana pudding  You can also add 2 unsweetened chocolate squares at the  beginning and make a chocolate pie or pudding. 4: For butterscotch pie or pudding, use 3/4 cup light brown  sugar firmly packed and 1/4 cup sugar instead of 3/4 cup sugar,  then cook as directed. 5: You can also make a banana plate pie with the vanilla  mixture, just cook as directed. 6: In baked pie shell, line  bottom with bananas; pour a layer of pudding, then a layer of  ba  nanas, then pudding. 7: You can top with Cool Whip or meringue.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4235,"Peanut Butter Pudding","PT12M","PT0S","PT12M","Make and share this Peanut Butter Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,2.0,597.7,38.6,10.5,23.5,524.7,47.0,4.0,22.9,21.7,"4.0","Peanut Butter Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Peanut Butter Pudding: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt. Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat until thick and bubbling. 2: Stir constantly. 3: Remove from heat, add 1 cup peanut butter and 2 teaspoons vanilla. 4: Cool; times do not include refrigeration time.");
