INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4301,"Salsa II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Salsa II recipe from Food.com.","Sauces",0.0,0.0,165.1,9.8,1.4,0.0,3121.4,19.0,5.4,10.0,3.6,"0.0","Salsa II Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut the tomatoes into chunks and put them in a colander to drain juice, reserve liquid since you may need it later. 2: Put oil, lime juice, and serrano peppers and a couple of jalapenos in a blender, and chop up very fine.  If it''s too thick add a little juice from tomatoes. 3: Chop onions in food processor, not too fine, chop tomatoes in processor, not too fine, fine chop garlic in processor, add  cilantro to processor ( I add a couple of mild banana peppers for taste) I also use Italian parsley in place of cilantro,  If it''s too hot for your taste add more tomatoes . 4: I puree the peppers, so when you eat it, you can taste the  flavor of the vegetables, then you get the taste of the hot peppers  (I used some small about one inch long peppers much stronger than jalapenos.)");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4302,"Low-Fat Oven Easy Turkey & Potato Dinner","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Low-Fat Oven Easy Turkey & Potato Dinner recipe from Food.com.","Potato",0.0,0.0,377.4,14.9,5.5,49.3,319.9,41.4,5.5,2.5,22.6,"6.0","Low-Fat Oven Easy Turkey & Potato Dinner Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350. 2: In a 2-quart casserole dish, firmly press hash brown potatoes evenly across bottom to form a shell; set aside. 3: Meanwhile, in a skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Add turkey, onions, and bell peppers. Cook until turkey is longer pink and vegetables are tender. 4: Stir in water, gravy mix, and salt; bring to a boil. 5: Add mixed vegetables; reduce and cook, uncovered, 5 minutes. 6: Remove from heat. Stir in 1/2 cup cheddar cheese. 7: Spoon in hash brown potato shell. Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until heated through. 8: Top with remaining cheddar cheese. Bake, uncovered again, for 5 minutes more.");
