INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4323,"Bourbon Chocolate Bread Pudding","PT55M","PT15M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Bourbon Chocolate Bread Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,467.0,21.3,12.2,116.6,224.7,64.8,4.3,40.8,10.1,"12.0","Bourbon Chocolate Bread Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350*. In a large mixing bowl stir together  milk, eggs, syrup, brown sugar, and vanilla. 2: Spread bread cubes in an ungreased 3 qt. rectangular baking dish. Sprinkle with chopped semisweet and white chocolate. 3: Pour egg mixture evenly over bread. 4: Bake, uncovered, for 50 to 55 minutes or until pudding is puffy and knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool slightly (pudding will fall in center). Drizzle with warm Bourbon Chocolate Sauce. 5: Bourbon Chocolate Sauce:  In a heavy saucepan stir 4 ounces chopped semisweet chocolate over low heat just until melted. Stir in 2/3 cup whipping cream and 1/4 cup sugar. 6: Cook and stir over medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes or just until mixture begins to boil. 7: Remove from heat; whisk until smooth. Stir in 2 to 3 Tbsp.  bourbon, if desired.C ool slightly before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4324,"Pumpkin Bread Pudding with Caramel Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pumpkin Bread Pudding with Caramel Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,278.7,11.2,6.0,129.7,204.0,36.9,0.9,19.1,8.4,"0.0","Pumpkin Bread Pudding with Caramel Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350*.Cut pumpkin into quarters; remove seeds.Discard seeds or save for roasting.Place pumpkin, cut side down, on a lightly greased baking pan.Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until almost tender.Remove peel; cut baked pumpkin into 3/4 inch pieces. 2: In a large mixing bowl stir together milk, eggnog, eggs, sugar,  vanilla and pumpkin pie spice.sprinkle raisins on bottom of an ungreased 3 qt. rectangular baking dish.Spread bread over raisins.Pour egg mixture evenly over bread. 3: Carefully stir in cubed pumpkin. 4: Bake for 50 minutes or until the pudding is puffy and a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. 5: Cool pudding slightly (pudding will fall in center). Drizzle with Warm Caramel Sauce. Makes 12 servings. 6: Warm Caramel Sauce: In a heavy saucepan melt  caramel squares with whipping cream over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth. 7: Stir in  anise seed and  rum flavoring, if desired. 8: Cool slightly before serving Recipes from Better Homes and Gardens Magazine");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4328,"Kesari Bhat","PT25M","PT0S","PT25M","Make and share this Kesari Bhat recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,1.0,645.1,28.8,17.7,75.4,31.3,91.8,2.6,54.5,7.8,"4.0","Kesari Bhat Recipe Instructions:  1: Put Rava, Bananas, Sugar, Milk in a saucepan. 2: Wait for a while till it gets sufficiently heated. 3: Continue stirring until the rava is cooked. (all the milk and ghee will have been absorbed and the banana is completely incorporated- It could take about 20 minutes). 4: Fry cashew, raisins and pista in ghee and add it to the above. 5: Add Saffron [ Saffron immersed in 1 tbsp milk ].");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4329,"Oyster Stuffing","PT15M","PT10M","PT25M","Make and share this Oyster Stuffing recipe from Food.com.","Winter",4.5,12.0,278.9,9.4,4.5,44.5,674.3,37.1,2.5,4.9,11.1,"8.0","Oyster Stuffing Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400°F and toast the bread until golden brown on the middle rack. turn into a large bowl. 2: Meanwhile heat butter until melted and foam subsides.  Add onions and celery and cook about 5 minutes until tender. 3: Remove from heat and stir in the spices. 4: Stir in the bread cubes, and drained oysters and toss well, until the stuffing is moist, but not packed together; stir in the stock and eggs.  Put in bird while moist, remoisten and adjust spices as necessary. If cooked in a casserole dish at 350°F until heated through with a crust on the outsides, 25 to 40 minutes. 5: Oyster juice may be used in place of some of the stock.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4330,"Lightened Green Bean Casserole","0","PT40M","PT40M","classic thanksgiving dish, this replaces the heavy in fat cream of mushroom soup version.  Ok, this is my recipe.  I made it for Thanksgiving 2002 and I was also extremely disappointed.  I originally got it from Cooking Light, and made it a few years ago.  I loved it back then, but this year it just didn''t work.  Not sure what is wrong...","Vegetable",4.0,6.0,83.8,3.4,1.7,9.4,348.2,8.5,1.8,1.6,5.6,"8.0","Lightened Green Bean Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: coat medium saucepan with cooking spray and place over medium heat until hot. 2: add onion, saute 5 min. 3: add flour, and cook 1 min, stirring constantly. 4: gradually add the milk, stirring until blended. 5: stir in the cheese, sour cream, sugar and salt, cook 5 min until thick and bubbly. 6: place green beans in an 8 in square baking dish, pour sauce over. 7: combine stuffing mix, margarine and egg white; and sprinkle over green beans. 8: bake at 350 for 25 min.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4331,"Garlic Mashed Potatoes III","PT25M","PT15M","PT40M","Make and share this Garlic Mashed Potatoes III recipe from Food.com.","Potato",4.5,27.0,168.6,4.2,1.4,4.0,239.4,29.1,2.5,2.0,4.4,"8.0","Garlic Mashed Potatoes III Recipe Instructions:  1: Place potatoes and garlic in a sauce pan, cover with water and bring to a boil.  reduce heat and simmer for 20 min and drain. 2: Return potatoes and garlic to the pan, add remaining ingredients. 3: Beat at medium speed or mash until smooth.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4332,"Homemade Cranberry Relish","PT10M","PT2M","PT12M","Make and share this Homemade Cranberry Relish recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",5.0,10.0,228.4,0.1,0.0,0.0,2.3,59.0,2.8,53.6,0.3,"8.0","Homemade Cranberry Relish Recipe Instructions:  1: combine everything (except almonds) in a skillet. 2: cook uncovered over medium heat until most of the cranberries pop open and the mixture is thickened, 7-10 minute. 3: if desired, add almonds. 4: let cool, and serve or refrigerate up to a day.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4333,"Roasted Potatoes With Sage and Garlic","PT35M","PT20M","PT55M","Make and share this Roasted Potatoes With Sage and Garlic recipe from Food.com.","Potato",4.5,8.0,230.4,8.3,2.5,7.6,28.4,35.7,4.4,2.0,4.2,"4.0","Roasted Potatoes With Sage and Garlic Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 450°F and place a large, heavy skillet or roasting pan in the oven to heat. 2: Place the potatoes in a large saucepan and cover with cold salted water.  Put on high heat to boil.  Once boiling, lower heat and simmer for 5 minutes. 3: Drain the potatoes well, and place on paper towels.  put the flour on a plate.  When the potatoes are dry, roll them in the flour to coat. 4: Remove the hot skillet from the oven and add the oil and potatoes.  Roast, shaking the pan occasionally until the potatoes are golden brown all over, about 30 minutes. 5: Remove from the oven and add the garlic, sage and butter. Return to the oven for one minute. 6: Season generously with salt and pepper and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4334,"Fried Sage Leaves","PT1M","PT5M","PT6M","an unexpected treat.  i first discovered these at a favorite restaurant in seattle, marco''s supper club.  this dish is a lot of fun and a big surprise for guests.","Summer",4.5,2.0,549.8,61.3,8.0,0.0,1.0,2.0,0.1,0.2,0.3,"2.0","Fried Sage Leaves Recipe Instructions:  1: place the vegetable oil in a skillet and heat over medium heat. 2: combine the mayo, olive oil, garlic and lemon juice into a dipping sauce.  season with salt as necessary. 3: lightly dust the sage leaves with flour, shaking off any excess.  drop into the hot oil and cook until crispy and bright green, ~30 seconds.  remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels. 4: serve with the dipping sauce.  you can experiment with other savory sauces as well, though the sage leaves are rather fragile, so you will need to be careful.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4335,"Sage Biscuits","PT15M","PT10M","PT25M","Make and share this Sage Biscuits recipe from Food.com.","Breads",5.0,5.0,189.0,9.4,5.8,24.6,432.2,22.4,0.8,1.1,3.6,"9.0","Sage Biscuits Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 450. 2: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.  Cut the cold butter into the flour until it resembles coarse meal.  Stir in the sage.  Stir in the buttermilk until the dry ingredients are just moistened. 3: Lightly flour your hands and work the dough into a square about 7\ 4: , 1/2\ 5: ,  6: Serve warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4336,"Trout Roasted with Sage, Walnuts and Bacon","PT15M","PT10M","PT25M","Make and share this Trout Roasted with Sage, Walnuts and Bacon recipe from Food.com.","Trout",5.0,1.0,436.7,30.6,5.5,102.5,217.4,3.0,1.0,0.4,37.1,"4.0","Trout Roasted with Sage, Walnuts and Bacon Recipe Instructions:  1: preheat the oven to 450. 2: in a medium skillet, fry the bacon until it is cooked through and very lightly browned, ~5 min.  remove the bacon and set aside.  pour out the excess bacon grease and return the skillet to the stove. 3: add the shallot and walnuts, toasting and shaking the pan, until the walnuts are lightly browned, 3-4 min.  remove the pan from the heat and stir in the bacon and sage leaves. 4: season the fish inside and out with salt and pepper.  brush the skin lightly with vegetable oil.  divide the bacon mixture between the 4 trout, stuffing it in the cavity of each fish.  place the fish in a large roasting pan fitted with a rack.  roast until the fish is just cooked through, ~15 min. 5: transfer to plates and serve with lemon and garnished with the watercress.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4337,"Rack of Lamb With Sage Crust","PT15M","PT20M","PT35M","Make and share this Rack of Lamb With Sage Crust recipe from Food.com.","Lamb/Sheep",5.0,6.0,1165.0,91.2,39.8,187.5,629.5,40.4,2.7,3.5,43.1,"4.0","Rack of Lamb With Sage Crust Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat the oven to 475°F. 2: Season the lamb generously with salt and pepper. 3: Place a large cast-iron skillet over high heat, when very hot, add the oil and sear one of the racks all over until it is very brown, about 2 minutes per side. 4: Transfer to a roasting pan fitted with a rack, laying it rounded side up. 5: Repeat with the remaining rack. 6: Cover with foil and set aside. 7: Place the remaining ingredients, except the vinegar, in a food processor. 8: Add 1/2 tsp salt and 1/4 tsp pepper, and process until it forms a paste. 9: Press the paste onto the racks. 10: Roast until desired doneness, 15 min for medium rare. 11: Allow to rest for 5 min, covered, then carve and serve drizzled with balsamic vinegar.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4338,"Chocolate Bread and Butter Pudding II","PT30M","PT24H","PT24H30M","Make and share this Chocolate Bread and Butter Pudding II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,699.6,55.2,33.1,238.3,326.0,45.0,4.8,18.8,10.7,"6.0","Chocolate Bread and Butter Pudding II Recipe Instructions:  1: Remove the crusts from the bread and cut each slice into 4 triangles, set aside. 2: In the top of a double boiler, combine chocolate, cream, rum, sugar, butter, and cinnamon, and place over simmering water.  cook, stirring occasionally, until everything is completely melted.  Set aside. 3: Whisk the eggs, then slowly add the chocolate mixture to them.  spoon half of the mixture into a 7x9x2 baking dish.  Arrange half the bread pieces in the next layer; repeat with chocolate and bread.  Gently press the top layer down so it becomes covered with chocolate. 4: Cover the dish with plastic and allow to stand at room temperature for 2 hours, and then refrigerate for 24 or 48 hours. 5: When ready to cook, preheat oven to 350°F  Bake on top shelf of oven til the top is crunchy, but the inside is soft, 30-35 minutes. Let stand 10 min before serving with whipped cream.");
