INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4363,"Shrimp and Cream Cheese Appetizer","0","PT5M","PT5M","Make and share this Shrimp and Cream Cheese Appetizer recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",4.0,2.0,113.0,10.0,6.3,58.8,115.7,0.8,0.0,0.1,5.1,"8.0","Shrimp and Cream Cheese Appetizer Recipe Instructions:  1: Place cream cheese on serving dish. 2: Cover with cocktail sauce. 3: Top with shrimp. 4: Serve with your favorite crackers or chips.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4364,"Roasted Garlic Puree Dip","PT1H","PT5M","PT1H5M","This recipe is very versatile.  The roasted garlic puree can be used on cooked vegetables, fish, steaks, salad greens and baked potatoes.","Cheese",0.0,0.0,395.2,33.1,20.9,101.6,508.2,13.9,0.7,0.6,12.7,"6.0","Roasted Garlic Puree Dip Recipe Instructions:  1: Remove outer covering on garlic.  Do not peel or separate the cloves.  Place each garlic head on a large square of heavy aluminum foil.  Fold up the foil so the cloves are completely wrapped.  Bake for 1 hour at 350°F  Remove garlic from oven and cool for ten minutes.  Separate cloves and squeeze cloves to remove cooked garlic.  Discard skins. 2: In food processor, mix  garlic, cheeses, milk,  and dill until smooth.  Place in serving dish.  Sprinkle with parsley. 3: Serve in hollowed out red cabbage in basket surrounded by assorted vegetables for dipping. 4: Note: This recipe is very versatile.  The roasted garlic puree can be used on cooked vegetables, fish, steaks, salad greens and baked potatoes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4365,"Drunken Dogs","PT1H","PT5M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Drunken Dogs recipe from Food.com.","Meat",5.0,2.0,413.6,27.0,10.6,48.1,1440.2,24.6,0.3,22.4,11.0,"0.0","Drunken Dogs Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine ketchup, brown sugar, bourbon and water in electric skillet or crock-pot. 2: Add wieners and onion, stirring well. 3: Cover and cook on low heat for 1 hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4367,"Broccoli Ziti Bake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Broccoli Ziti Bake recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,332.1,12.7,5.8,61.6,633.8,35.9,3.1,3.5,19.0,"6.0","Broccoli Ziti Bake Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut the broccoli into 2 inch bite size pieces. Peel the stalk of the broccoli and cut it into 2 inch pieces. 2: Place the broccoli in a steamer and steam for 10 minutes. Do not over cook them. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. 3: In a small  bowl, add the crushed garlic and salt. Mash into a paste and set aside. 4: In a small skillet, cook the bacon until crisp. Remove and drain on paper towels. 5: Heat the olive oil in a medium skillet. Add the onion, garlic, bacon, thyme, basil, mushrooms and black pepper. Saute until limp and all water has gone. 6: In the meantime, bring a large pot of water to a rapid boil. Add the ziti and stir. Cook for 10-12 minutes or until tender. 7: Drain and return the ziti to the pot.  Add the egg and stir to blend. 8: Stir in the broccoli and mushroom mixture. 9: Transfer half the pasta to a 9x9 baking dish. 10: Sprinkle the layer with half of the Mozzarella cheese and Romano cheese. 11: Add the remaining half of pasta to the baking dish and sprinkle with the cheeses. 12: Bake covered in a preheated 350: F  oven for 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4368,"Boulangere Potatoes","PT1H","PT20M","PT1H20M","Make and share this Boulangere Potatoes recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,4.0,3066.5,233.6,71.9,228.1,1327.0,221.5,26.3,34.2,35.5,"0.0","Boulangere Potatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute the potatoes in hot oil until golden. Drain. 2: Saute the onions in the butter until soft. 3: Layer the potatoes and onions in a baking dish. 4: Add the stock and garnish. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4369,"Lemon Cranberry Anise Bread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lemon Cranberry Anise Bread recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",4.0,1.0,148.5,2.6,0.4,14.1,170.2,27.6,1.7,8.9,4.2,"0.0","Lemon Cranberry Anise Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 3500F. 2: Spray an 8-1/2 x 4 in. 3: loaf pan with non-stick cooking spray; set aside. In a large bowl, stir together the flours, anise seeds, baking powder, baking soda and salt unti l well combined. 4: In a food processor or blender, place the banana, buttermilk, eggs, brown sugar, oil, lemon juice, peel and vanilla; process until smooth. 5: Pour mixture into the dry ingredients; stir just until moistened. 6: Stir in the cranberries. 7: Spoon into the prepared pan. 8: Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. 9: Remove from the pan; cool completely on a wire rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4370,"Baked Chicken with Yogurt Crust & Peaches","PT20M","PT25M","PT45M","Make and share this Baked Chicken with Yogurt Crust & Peaches recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,3.0,358.2,5.3,2.1,144.8,181.6,17.8,2.4,16.0,58.0,"2.0","Baked Chicken with Yogurt Crust & Peaches Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. 2: In a food processor or blender, reduce the stuffing mix to coarse crumbs. Pour them onto a sheet of wax paper. 3: Coat one piece of chicken breast with yogurt as thickly as possible (admittedly, this is a messy step), then dip it into the crumbs to coat. 4: Lay the chicken in an oiled baking dish large enough to hold chicken and peaches in one layer. Repeat with the remaining chicken. 5: Surround the chicken with the peach halves, cut side down. Sprinkle the peaches (not the chicken) with cinnamon sugar. 6: Bake for 20 minutes, or until the breasts are just cooked through but not dry.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4371,"Low-Fat Creamy Green Chile Soup (High Fiber)","PT15M","PT5M","PT20M","Make and share this Low-Fat Creamy Green Chile Soup (High Fiber) recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",1.0,2.0,174.7,3.3,1.3,7.2,314.8,27.3,3.0,8.2,11.2,"4.0","Low-Fat Creamy Green Chile Soup (High Fiber) Recipe Instructions:  1: In a 3 quart casserole combine onion, celery, garlic and margarine and cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap. 2: Microwave at High for 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. 3: Add flour; stir well. 4: Dissolve bouillon in hot water. 5: Gradually add bouillon, milk, chili powder and pepper to mixture and stir well. 6: Microwave at High for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring every 3 minutes. 7: Stir in chiles and microwave at High for 1 minute. Stir well before serving. 8: To Serve: Ladle soup into individual serving bowl and top each bowl with 1 tablespoon cheese. Serve immediately. 9: Makes 6 (1-cup) servings Makes 4 servings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4372,"Low-Fat Roasted Onion-Garlic Soup","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","Make and share this Low-Fat Roasted Onion-Garlic Soup recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,3.0,193.6,5.6,1.8,5.5,850.1,16.5,1.8,4.4,9.6,"4.0","Low-Fat Roasted Onion-Garlic Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Set oven rack at lowest level, preheat to 450 degrees. 2: Combine onions, shallots, garlic and oil in large shallow roasting pan. Roast for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes, or until onions are golden brown. 3: Remove from oven and pour in 1 cup of chicken broth. Stir liquid in pan, scraping the bottom to loosen and dissolve caramelized bits. 4: Transfer the onion mixture to a soup pot and add brandy, thyme and remaining broth. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. 5: Season to taste with salt and pepper. 6: Serve topped with Parmesan and perhaps some toasted French bread");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4373,"Low-Fat Thai Steak Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Low-Fat Thai Steak Salad recipe from Food.com.","Meat",5.0,9.0,2630.3,164.0,66.1,966.7,1564.0,8.5,1.5,4.2,263.6,"4.0","Low-Fat Thai Steak Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat broiler or grill. 2: Sprinkle the sirloin with soy sauce and rub it into the surface. Broil or grill until done to your liking, about 5 minutes on each side for rare. 3: Let the steak relax for 10 minutes, then slice thinly against the grain. 4: Toss with the onion and cucumber and red bell pepper. 5: In a small bowl combine the lime juice, fish sauce, garlic and hot pepper sauce. Taste dressing and add sugar to taste. Pour over the salad an toss well to combine. Arrange the salad on lettuce and serve warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4374,"Creamy Cucumber Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Creamy Cucumber Salad recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",4.5,3.0,293.6,5.0,2.9,15.9,88.9,54.4,5.3,34.5,10.7,"1.0","Creamy Cucumber Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Put cucumbers in a non-metallic bowl. 2: Mix together the vinegar, water and sugar. 3: Pour over cucumbers, cover with plastic wrap and allow to marinate in the refrigerator for 24 hours. 4: Drain cucumbers and mix in the green onions and yogurt (or sour cream or mayonnaise). You can also add some sliced sweet onions (i.e., Vidalia) to the cucumbers when you marinate them. 5: This recipe is on the tart side.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4375,"Beef and Macaroni","PT15M","PT7M","PT22M","Make and share this Beef and Macaroni recipe from Food.com.","Meat",5.0,2.0,289.7,10.5,3.9,57.1,91.2,26.8,3.7,8.0,22.5,"4.0","Beef and Macaroni Recipe Instructions:  1: Place hamburger in large skillet. Separate into small pieces and saute till meat is brown. Remove meat from skillet and drain off most liquid. 2: Place pasta in boiling water for 8 minutes and drain. 3: Add 1 Tbsp olive oil to skillet and saute onion, celery, peppers, and garlic till soft. 4: Add cooked pasta, hamburg, tomatoes, bouillon, parsley, sugar and pepper. Toss ingredients. Simmer slowly for 20-minutes while stirring frequently. 5: Serve when flavors have blended. 6: A small bowl of dry American cheese should accompany the meal with crusty bread, and green salad.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4376,"Lemon Jam","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lemon Jam recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",5.0,1.0,761.9,0.4,0.1,0.0,10.9,199.1,3.5,190.2,1.4,"0.0","Lemon Jam Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash the lemons and, working on a large dish to catch the juices, cut the fruit into slices, remove the pips and tie them in a muslin bag. 2: Put the fruit, juices, bag and water into a preserving pan, cover and bring carefully to the boil, simmer until the rind is soft 3: .  Remove from the heat and add the warmed  sugar, stirring well until it has dissolved. 4: Bring to the boil and reduce the heat to keep it just boiling.  In about 10 minutes the jam will be cooked and thick. 5: Remove the bag, squeezing well and put the pulp through a liquidiser or mincer.  Return to the pan. 6: Heat gently beating well with a wooden spoon to ensure that you have a soft smooth jam.  Bring to the boil stirring continuously and taking great care not to burn it.  Remove from the heat almost immediately. 7: Pot and seal.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4377,"Potato Squares","PT50M","PT40M","PT1H30M","Make and share this Potato Squares recipe from Food.com.","Potato",4.5,9.0,159.6,9.4,5.4,94.3,136.5,11.7,1.3,1.2,7.3,"9.0","Potato Squares Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel 4 medium large potatoes and grate directly into 1 cup of milk in a well buttered 8 inch square baking pan. 2: Grate a small onion into the milk and add 3 Tbsp chopped green pepper, grated cheddar cheese, salt and pepper to taste.  Beat 3 eggs well and combine.  Dot with 2 tsp of butter. 3: Bake at 350 F for about 50 minutes to 1 hour or until the pudding is richly browned. 4: Cut into squares to serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4378,"Festive Carrots &amp; Pineapple","PT10M","PT10M","PT20M","Make and share this Festive Carrots &amp; Pineapple recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",5.0,2.0,656.4,12.8,7.5,30.5,432.6,138.9,15.3,107.7,5.4,"0.0","Festive Carrots &amp; Pineapple Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine reserved pineapple juice, sugar, butter, cornstarch and cinnamon. 2: Cook and stir until sauce is clear and thickened. 3: Add pineapple and carrots. 4: Heat and serve immediately. 5: If desired, garnish with lime peel.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4379,"Chicken Tart","PT20M","PT15M","PT35M","Make and share this Chicken Tart recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",0.0,0.0,342.0,23.6,11.1,65.1,70.7,22.2,0.8,0.1,9.8,"4.0","Chicken Tart Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift the flour and a pinch of salt into a bowl. 2: Rub in the butter and lard and mix to a stiff dough with cold water. 3: Roll out the pastry on a floured board and use to line a 8 - 9 inch flan tin. 4: Prick the base, line with foil and fill with dried beans. 5: Bake at 400 F for 15 minutes. 6: Remove the beans and foil, and return the pastry to the oven for another 5 - 15 minutes or until crisp and golden brown. 7: Cut the chicken into small pieces. 8: Put the cream into a small saucepan and heat gently. 9: Add chicken, lemon juice and tarragon, and season well with salt and pepper. 10: Heat gently until the chicken is hot, then turn the filling into the pastry case.  Serve with salads.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4380,"Caramel Bread Pudding","PT1H","PT10M","PT1H10M","As my son says, it is like eating French Toast for dessert. :) It is very much like French Toast with a lovely caramel sauce on it. We all like it warm best. Make sure you use a 2-quart dish. Trust me, it will boil over in your stove in a 1 1/2-quart one. Oops! And don''t worry, it will fall a little bit as it cools.","Dessert",5.0,91.0,371.6,7.0,3.1,135.4,275.1,69.5,0.7,53.5,8.8,"6.0","Caramel Bread Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Place bread in greased 2-qt. baking dish. 2: Combine water and brown sugar; pour over bread. 3: Combine remaining ingredients; pour over bread. 4: Bake at 350 degrees F for 50-60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. 5: Serve warm or cold.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4381,"Macadamia and Ginger Panforte","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","Make and share this Macadamia and Ginger Panforte recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,118.4,5.8,1.0,0.0,0.8,16.8,1.0,6.8,1.3,"0.0","Macadamia and Ginger Panforte Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift the flour, cocoa, mixed spice, pepper and cinnamon into a large bowl.  Stir in ginger and nuts, make a well in the centre. 2: Warm the syrup in a saucepan over a low heat.  Sprinkle in castor sugar and stir continuously until sugar has dissolved. 3: Add vanilla essence and bring to the boil. 4: Once the mixture is boiling remove it from the heat and allow the bubbles to subside. 5: Pour the liquid into the well in the dry ingredients and mix with a sturdy wooden spoon until incorporated.  The mixture become quite hard to mix. 6: Press the dough into a well-greased 23cm spring-form cake tin lined with baking paper and press down firmly with your hands. 7: If your hands get sticky, wet them slightly. 8: Bake at 170 C for 30 minutes.  The centre will be soft and the edges firm. 9: Cool in tin for at least 30 minutes before turning out on to a cake rack.  Cool thoroughly. If possible, keep the panforte in an airtight container 2 - 3 days. 10: Serve dusted with a thick layer of icing sugar and cut into tiny wedges. 11: If making small panforte, divide the mixture between four 10cm greased cake tins lined with baking paper.  Bake at 170 C for 20 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4382,"Shrimp Starter","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Shrimp Starter recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,387.3,5.8,0.7,630.0,4382.6,10.6,2.5,2.2,70.0,"0.0","Shrimp Starter Recipe Instructions:  1: Place shrimp in a bowl. 2: Combine all remaining ingredients and pour over the shrimps, turning to coat well. 3: Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours for flavours to develop. 4: Serve in cocktail glasses and garnish with fresh chopped herbs.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4383,"Ginger and Cashew Rice","PT20M","PT5M","PT25M","Make and share this Ginger and Cashew Rice recipe from Food.com.","Long Grain Rice",5.0,3.0,647.3,28.7,11.0,32.1,126.1,86.4,2.8,1.9,12.3,"2.0","Ginger and Cashew Rice Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine rice and water in a large shallow dish, and cook on HIGH for 15 minutes, stir occasionally. 2: Combine butter, garlic and nuts in a dish, cook on HIGH 2 minutes, stir occasionally. 3: Stir in rice and remaining ingredients, cook on HIGH for about 3 minutes or until the mixture is heated through, stir occasionally.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4384,"Fudge Rum Balls","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","These freeze REALLY well. I like to make them a month or so before Christmas so if an unexpected party comes up or I need a last minute gift, they are ready to go. They also ship really well.","Candy",5.0,5.0,165.4,6.7,1.1,0.0,177.1,26.7,1.2,18.2,1.9,"24.0","Fudge Rum Balls Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375°F Grease and flour 13x9x2 inch pan. 2: Prepare, bake and cool cake following package directions. 3: Crumble cake into large bowl. Stir with fork until crumbs are fine and  uniform in size. 4: Add 1 cup nuts, rum, confectioners sugar and cocoa. Stir until well blended. 5: Shape heaping tablespoonfuls mixture into balls.  Garnish by rolling balls in finely chopped nuts. Press firmly to adhere nuts to balls. 6: Tip: you can also roll them in coconut.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4386,"Jiffy Corn Pudding","PT45M","PT10M","PT55M","Make and share this Jiffy Corn Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Corn",5.0,38.0,315.7,14.5,6.7,70.2,463.8,43.0,3.9,11.3,7.1,"8.0","Jiffy Corn Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix all ingredients. 2: Grease 9x13-inch pan and pour in batter. 3: Dot with butter; bake at 350F for 45 minutes to 1 hour. 4: Cut in squares and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4387,"Eggplant (Aubergine) With Mushroom Stuffing","PT40M","PT45M","PT1H25M","Make and share this Eggplant (Aubergine) With Mushroom Stuffing recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",1.0,1.0,152.4,1.5,0.3,0.0,79.2,32.1,13.9,11.2,8.3,"3.0","Eggplant (Aubergine) With Mushroom Stuffing Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 450. 2: Halve eggplants lengthwise. Score the flesh of each half lightly to make a border about 3/8 inch from the skin. 3: Score center of each half lightly three times to allow heat to penetrate. Sprinkle cut surface with salt. Place eggplants, cut side up, on a lightly sprayed sheet pan and bake until flesh is tender, 20-25 minutes. 4: Let cool slightly. 5: Meanwhile, spray vegetable oil in a large skillet over low heat. Add shallots and saute about 30 seconds until soft but not brown. 6: Add mushrooms and season with salt and pepper. 7: Cook over high heat, stirring continuously, until mixture is dry, 3-5 minutes. 8: Set as ide. Cut each eggplant gently along scored border and remove pulp carefully with a spoon without piercing skin. 9: Put shells in large, oiled gratin dish. 10: Chop eggplant flesh. 11: Mix with mushroom stuffing and stir in garlic, parsley and cayenne pepper. 12: (or, just throw it all in the food processor! ;^) Spoon stuffing into eggplant shells. 13: Sprinkle with bread crumbs, then mist with vegetable spray or drizzle with oil, if desired. 14: Bake until hot, 10-15 minutes. 15: If bread crumbs have not browned, run under a broiler for a few seconds. 16: Serve hot. Optional: sprinkle with Parmesan or nonfat pizza cheese.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4388,"Triple- Chocolate Bundt Cake","0","PT0S","PT0S","You can substitute two (1.4- ounce) packages of sugar- free chocolate fudge instant pudding mix for the regular pudding mix in the recipe.","Dessert",1.0,2.0,504.2,12.7,2.6,1.4,949.1,97.0,4.0,58.3,5.6,"0.0","Triple- Chocolate Bundt Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; beat at low speed of a mixer for 30 seconds. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. 3: Pour batter into a 12- cup Bundt pan coated with cooking spray.  Bake at 350 degrees  for 50 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. 4: Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pan.  Cool completely on a wire rack. 5: Combine sugar and 4 teaspoons of milk in a small bowl; drizzle over cake.  Let stand for 10 minutes. 6: Place chips in a small heavy- duty ziptop plastic bag; seal.  Submerge bag in very hot water until chips melt or put in microwave at  MEDIUM-HIGH (70% power) 1 minute.   Snip a tiny hole in 1 corner of bag; drizzle chocolate over cake.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4389,"Apple Pecan Bread Pudding","PT4H","PT0S","PT4H","Make and share this Apple Pecan Bread Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,464.2,25.6,9.7,107.4,184.3,49.8,3.7,31.9,7.7,"8.0","Apple Pecan Bread Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350. 2: Spread pecans in a shallow baking pan and bake until golden, about 8-10 minutes, stirring occasionally. 3: Meanwhile, place bread cubes in a greased 3 qt. or larger slow cooker. 4: Peel, core and thinly slice the apples. 5: Mix lightly together the sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg, add eggs and mix well. 6: Blend in half and half or milk and then stir in bourbon or brandy. 7: Lightly mix pecans with  bread and apples. 8: Pour egg mixture over bread. Drizzle with butter. 9: Cover and cook on low until apples are tender when pierced and custard is set; about 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 hours. 10: Let pudding stand, covered, for about 15 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4391,"Bread and Butter Pudding","PT45M","PT10M","PT55M","Make and share this Bread and Butter Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,6.0,386.9,9.5,4.2,175.7,369.7,64.4,1.6,37.7,12.1,"4.0","Bread and Butter Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 325 degrees F. 2: Butter a deep dish 9 inch pie plate or 9 inch square cake pan 3: Generously butter one side of bread, cut in half to make two triangles. 4: Arrange triangles, buttered side up, in prepared dish. 5: In bowl, beat eggs well mixed. 6: Add milk, sugar and vanilla; beat together. 7: Stir in raisins. 8: Slowly pour over bread making sure all bread is well soaked. 9: Bake 45 minutes or until custard has set. Serve with warm maple syrup.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4392,"English Bread Pudding","PT50M","PT30M","PT1H20M","Make and share this English Bread Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,5.0,588.6,31.9,17.0,55.7,366.5,72.1,4.3,39.2,6.6,"6.0","English Bread Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Soak bread in water for 1/2 hour then squeeze out water and drain. 2: Put in a bowl with all other ingredients, mix and put in greased tin and bake until cooked - about 45 minutes on 350 F.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4396,"Spinach & Artichoke Dip with Pita Chips","0","PT30M","PT30M","Here''s the best spinach & artichoke dip recipe I''ve found.  Tastes wonderful with homemade pita chips (recipe included).  Guten Appetit!","< 30 Mins",3.5,2.0,396.4,26.0,15.9,75.6,765.1,14.7,3.7,6.5,29.1,"4.0","Spinach & Artichoke Dip with Pita Chips Recipe Instructions:  1: Thaw and drain spinach. 2: Be certain to get all the liquid out. Add the rest of  the ingredients, mix. 3: Bake at 350 degrees Fahrenheit for 20-30 minutes, until  top is golden brow n. 4: - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Serving Ideas : Delicious with pita chips. 5: *  Exported from  MasterCook  *                               Pita Chips Recipe By     : Claudia Landis Serving Size  : 1    Preparation Time :0:30 Categories    : Appetizers Amount  Measure       Ingredient -- Preparation Method --------  ------------  --------------------------------  1       package       whole wheat pita bread -- cut into wedges                       olive oil or vegetable cooking spray                       seasoning (such as Mrs. 6: Dash) Cut pitas into 8-12 wedges per slice. Place the pita wedges onto a cookie sheet in a single layer. 7: If using olive oil, brush the pita wedges with olive oil, then sprinkle with seasoning. 8: If using cooking spray, sprinkle the pita wedges with seasoning, then spray. 9: Bake at 350 degrees Fahrenheit until crisp, about 20 minutes. 10: Pita chips may need to be turned half-way through in order to crisp on both sides.");
