INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4493,"Low-Fat Zippy Kidney Bean Dip","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Low-Fat Zippy Kidney Bean Dip recipe from Food.com.","Beans",3.5,2.0,46.7,0.7,0.4,1.9,45.8,6.4,1.7,1.2,3.9,"12.0","Low-Fat Zippy Kidney Bean Dip Recipe Instructions:  1: In a blender or food processor, puree the beans to a coarse paste or mash very well by hand. 2: Put into a bowl and add all of the other ingredients, blending well. 3: Serve at room temperature.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4494,"Cornbread II","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Make and share this Cornbread II recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",0.0,0.0,232.6,15.1,2.5,72.7,376.3,19.4,1.6,2.7,5.9,"9.0","Cornbread II Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 425°F. 2: Put a little oil or bacon drippings in  9 x 9 brownie pan or you can use large cast iron fry pan. 3: put pan in oven to heat oil. 4: Mix all the ingredients together and pour into pan. 5: bake 15 to 20 minutes or until top is browned. 6: I cook mine at a little lower temperature for longer since my oven cooks hotter. 7: You''ll know it''s ready when top has lightly browned.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4495,"Low-Fat Angel Hair Pasta with Onion-Mushroom Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Low-Fat Angel Hair Pasta with Onion-Mushroom Sauce recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,2.0,280.4,4.1,0.9,0.0,375.6,50.9,3.5,4.1,10.5,"4.0","Low-Fat Angel Hair Pasta with Onion-Mushroom Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: In a 2-quart saucepan, bring the broth, crepes and shiitake to a boil over medium-high heat. Remove the pan from the heat and let the mixture stand for 20 minutes. 2: In a 3-quart saucepan, melt the margarine over medium heat. Add the button mushrooms, onions and garlic, and cook, stirring frequently, until the onions are tender, 4 to 5 minutes. 3: Drain the crepes and shiitake, reserving the liquid. 4: Add the drained mushrooms to the onion mixture and cook, stirring frequently, until they are tender, 10 to 15 minutes. 5: Stir in the reserved liquid, thyme and lemon peel; cook for 2 minutes. 6: Spoon over the hot pasta and toss.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4496,"Apple Country Chicken","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apple Country Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,1.0,294.9,2.7,0.7,98.8,211.0,25.7,2.1,19.0,41.1,"4.0","Apple Country Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Place curry powder in a wide frying pan and stir over medium heat until slightly darker in color. 2: Add apple, onion, lemon juice, mushrooms, bullion and 1 1/2 cups apple juice. Increase heat to high and bring to a boil. 3: Rinse chicken and pat dry. 4: Add to pan. 5: Reduce heat, cover and simmer until meat is no longer pink (about 30 minutes). Transfer chicken to a platter and keep warm. 6: In small bowl, blend flour and remaining 1/2 cup apple juice. Gradually add to sauce in pan, stirring constantly and cook until sauce is thickened. 7: Pour over chicken. 8: Garn ish with green onions and sour cream or yogurt. Serve over rice");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4497,"Honey Cake","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Honey Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,210.2,0.6,0.1,0.1,147.7,48.6,0.9,33.5,3.4,"24.0","Honey Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: In a saucepan, combine the honey and coffee, bring to a boil and cool. 2: Soak currants in brandy. 3: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. 4: In the bowl of an electric mixer, blend the applesauce, brown sugar and egg substitute. Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices. 5: Stir the dry ingredients alternately with the coffee into the egg mixture. Fold in the currants and orange zest. Spray Pam in two 9x5-inch loaf pans (or use non-stick pans). Pour the batter in and bake for 1 hour; the top will be sticky, but a toothpick inserted into the center should come out cle an.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4498,"Patty Mae''s Bar-B-Que Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Patty Mae''s Bar-B-Que Sauce recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,943.7,7.8,0.6,0.0,8025.9,211.2,7.5,167.9,15.8,"0.0","Patty Mae''s Bar-B-Que Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Whisk mustard and ketchup together in a mixing bowl. 2: Slowly whisk in vinegar. 3: Stir in remaining ingredients. 4: Makes about 4= cups. 5: This sauce is better after it sits for a couple of days to let the flavors blend, but you can use it right away if necessary. 6: It''s great with pork. 7: I cook a pork roast in the crock pot until it falls apart, then pull the meat apart, add the sauce, and let it cook another couple of hours.");
