INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4500,"Christmas Prusurate","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Christmas Prusurate recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,6914.1,117.3,21.4,685.7,12331.4,1305.1,58.4,546.2,139.8,"1.0","Christmas Prusurate Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix flour and baking powder together. 2: Beat eggs, sugar and milk together. 3: Add flour mixture to egg mixture. 4: Add rinds and juices. Fold in apples, raisins and pecans. 5: Heat oil in fry daddy or deep fryer. Drop batter by Tablespoonfuls into hot oil. Fry until golden brown. 6: Drain on paper towels until cooled. 7: Sprinkle with powdered sugar or make a glaze of powered sugar and milk and drizzle over cooled balls.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4501,"English Mustard From Scratch","0","PT0S","PT0S","This recipe calls for brown and yellow mustard seed; however, it also requires some mustard powder. I would think that you can grind enough mustard seed to give you 1 cup of  powder, using it as directed. Maybe a mix of brown and yellow depending on how sharp you prefer the mustard.","European",0.0,1.0,672.9,38.8,2.0,0.0,785.8,51.8,20.0,10.5,34.0,"0.0","English Mustard From Scratch Recipe Instructions:  1: In a non-reactive container, combine mustard seeds with beer and vinegar. Let sit 48 hours. Check periodically to make sure seeds are covered by liquid; add more if necessary. 2: Transfer seeds and liquid to a food processor. Add remaining ingredients. Process until creamy, four to six minutes. 3: Transfer to jars. Allow mustard to mature, 3 to 4 weeks, before serving. 4: Note: You can vary the mustards flavor by substituting your favorite ingredients, the basic technique remains the same.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4502,"Crusty Coconut Custard","PT30M","PT30M","PT1H","Make and share this Crusty Coconut Custard recipe from Food.com.","Pie",2.5,3.0,289.2,12.7,10.1,81.5,39.7,42.2,2.6,38.9,4.0,"8.0","Crusty Coconut Custard Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F 2: In a bowl, dump coconut and add milk to it, let set until coconut soaks up the milk. 3: Beat sugar and eggs together, then add vanilla. 4: Add coconut to the egg mixture. Bake  for 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4503,"New Orleans Fruitcake","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","Make and share this New Orleans Fruitcake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,6709.6,338.1,31.4,423.0,991.8,923.5,57.8,768.6,69.5,"0.0","New Orleans Fruitcake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until frothy; 3: Coat fruits with flour mixture (flour and baking powder). 4: Add egg mixture. 5: Line 2 loaf pans with wax paper and dump 1/2 mixture in each pan. 6: Bake in oven for 1 hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4505,"Almond-Walnut Baklava","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Almond-Walnut Baklava recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,9193.7,498.6,177.8,610.1,4563.5,1096.3,54.3,552.9,134.7,"1.0","Almond-Walnut Baklava Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon, cloves and honey. 2: Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. 3: Increase heat and boil gently until reduced to 2 1/2 cups, about 10 minutes. 4: Strain into bowl and mix in brandy. 5: Cool completely. 6: Nut Filling: 7: Toast almonds and walnuts and finely chop in processor. 8: Transfer to large bowl. 9: Mix in cinnamon and breadcrumbs. 10: Pastry: 11: Butter bottom and sides of 13x9x2-inch glass baking dish. 12: Unroll stacked phyllo  sheets, press folds to smooth, and cut crosswise in half. 13: Place 1 sheet of  phyllo in bottom of prepared dish (k eep remaining sheets covered with plastic  wrap and damp towel to prevent drying). Because many brands of phyllo are not  long enough to touch both ends of the dish, it may be necessary to stagger  sheets to end of dish. 14: Brush first sheet with melted butter. 15: Top with second  phyllo sheet. Brush with melted butter. 16: Repeat, using 12 more sheets, buttering  each sheet. Sprinkle 3/4 cup nut mixture over. 17: Cover with 4 more sheets,  buttering each. 18: Sprinkle 3/4 cup nut mixture over. 19: Cover with 4 more sheets,  buttering each. 20: Sprinkle 3/4 cup nut mixture over. 21: Cover with 4 more sheets,  buttering each. 22: Sprinkle 3/4 cup nut mixture over. 23: Cover with 4 more sheets,  buttering each. 24: Sprinkle 3/4 cup nut mixture over. 25: Top with 18 more sheets,  buttering each. 26: Brush top sheet generously with butter. 27: Cut baklava lengthwise into thirds and make 8 diagonal cuts. 28: Top each section with a whole clove. Lightly sprinkle the top with water and bake at 350 degrees in center of oven until pastry is golden brown, about 1 hour. 29: Gradually pour syrup over hot baklava and cool completely.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4506,"Mascarpone Cheese - Substitute - Homemade","0","PT5M","PT5M","An Italian cream cheese, which is used in many things, especially Tiramisu can  be found in many specialty stores as well as many good supermarkets. It usually  comes in a flat tub. It is quite expensive,  so this is an inexpensive substitute.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,907.2,80.9,51.0,255.2,686.7,31.4,0.0,25.6,17.5,"0.0","Mascarpone Cheese - Substitute - Homemade Recipe Instructions:  1: Whip regular cream cheese in a mixer, until soft. 2: At a slow speed, mix in about  2 tablespoons sugar per cup of cream cheese, and fold in a touch of whipped cream for  airiness.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4507,"Fried Chicken Livers III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Fried Chicken Livers III recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Livers",4.0,1.0,687.0,15.1,7.3,245.7,2880.6,108.2,3.4,0.7,27.2,"1.0","Fried Chicken Livers III Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix milk and egg; set aside.  Mix dry ingredients in separate bowl. 2: Add seasoning (I use Tony Cachere''s Creole Seasoning) to flour mixture.  Soak liver in milk and egg. 3: Drain. 4: Shake in flour mixture. Fry in hot oil.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4508,"One-Dish Chicken Bake","PT35M","PT0S","PT35M","Make and share this One-Dish Chicken Bake recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,23.0,502.3,24.3,11.6,116.4,1388.9,38.1,1.4,5.3,31.5,"4.0","One-Dish Chicken Bake Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix contents of vegetable/seasoning packet, hot water, and butter in large bowl until butter is melted. 2: Stir in stuffing crumbs just to moisten. Let stand 5 min. 3: Place chicken down center of 12x8-inch baking dish. 4: Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken. 5: Spoon some of the stuffing over chicken. Spoon remaining stuffing along both sides of chicken. 6: Bake at 375 for 35 min. or until chicken is cooked through.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4509,"Texas Two-Step Chicken Picante","PT20M","PT5M","PT25M","Make and share this Texas Two-Step Chicken Picante recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,20.0,381.4,3.5,0.8,75.5,722.5,56.1,2.0,13.0,29.9,"0.0","Texas Two-Step Chicken Picante Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix sauce, sugar and mustard. 2: Place chicken in 2 quart shallow baking dish. 3: Pour picante sauce mixture over chicken. 4: Bake at 400°F for 20 minutes or until chicken is done.  Serve with rice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4511,"Crepes Suzette","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Crepes Suzette recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",0.0,0.0,481.6,26.1,13.8,373.4,858.7,41.0,1.1,0.7,19.9,"2.0","Crepes Suzette Recipe Instructions:  1: Suzette Sauce: 1/3 cup orange juice 1/4 cup butter 2 Tbsp sugar 1/4 tsp grated orange peel Reserve 1/4 Grand Marnier In medium bowl with wire whisk, beat butter and remaining crepe  ingredients  until smooth. 2: Chill 2 hours. 3: Brush bottom of 7\ 4:  skillet with  melted butter. 5: Over medium heat, heat pans; pour scant 1/4 cup patter into  crepe  pan to coat bottom; cook 2 minutes until top is set, underside  slightly  browned. 6: Loosen crepe; invert into hot 10\ 7: Slip crepe onto waked paper. 8: Meanwhile, start cooking  another crepe.  Stack  crepes between waxed paper. 9: Use  immediately or wrap in foil and refrigerate.  Approx 30 minutes before serving, Prepare Suzette sauce: In 10\ 10: ,  11: ,  12: Heat the Grand Marnier a minute or two, then remove  from stove.   Light a long match (such as those used to light kindling in a   fireplace).  Apply match to the crepes and sauce in the skillet. Serve crepes  and sauce immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4512,"Ground Beef &amp; Orzo Soup","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","Make and share this Ground Beef &amp; Orzo Soup recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,255.5,9.6,3.6,51.2,981.3,21.4,3.4,5.5,20.5,"0.0","Ground Beef &amp; Orzo Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute pepper, onion and hamburger in soup pot. Add water, bouillon cubes and tomatoes; simmer for 45 minutes. 2: Add Veg-All and orzo; simmer for 15 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4513,"Elmo''s Orzo Soup","PT4H10M","PT0S","PT4H10M","Make and share this Elmo''s Orzo Soup recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.0,1.0,844.7,3.5,0.7,0.0,110.0,172.1,10.3,10.8,29.4,"1.0","Elmo''s Orzo Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Cover soup meat with water. Add celery, onion, garlic  powder, basil, salt and pepper. Simmer 3 to 4 hours. 2: Drain broth (about 8 cups) into another pan and bring to a boil. Add orzo. Cook about 10 to 12 minutes or until tender. 3: Serve with lots of grated cheese sprinkled on top. 4: Soup meat can be cut into small pieces and combined with lettuce, sliced onions, oil and vinegar for a good salad. Or meat can be added to soup.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4514,"Garden Italian Salad","0","PT0S","PT20M","Make and share this Garden Italian Salad recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,290.6,13.8,4.4,17.9,496.1,31.9,2.5,4.8,10.3,"5.0","Garden Italian Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook orzo to desired doneness as directed on package;  drain. Rinse with cold water. 2: In large bowl, combine orzo, zucchini, carrot, olives, onions and pimento. 3: Pour dressing over salad; toss well. 4: Refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors. 5: Add Mozzarella cheese just before serving; garnish with parsley. Refrigerate leftovers. 6: Tip: Substitute 2 1/2 cups cooked macaroni for the orzo.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4517,"Berlin Chocolate Ring","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Berlin Chocolate Ring recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,5591.1,243.3,131.1,1359.7,3150.9,767.0,23.8,281.3,98.0,"0.0","Berlin Chocolate Ring Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees (190 c.). Grease an 8 cup fluted ring mold; set aside. 2: In a large bowl, beat together butter and sugar. Beat in eggs  until light and fluffy. 3: Sift together flour and baking powder. 4: Gradually add flour mixture and milk, alternately, to butter mixture. Stir in vanilla, lemon peel and currants. 5: Batter should hold its shape when mixed,  but should be moist enough to drop slowly off a wooden spoon. 6: Pour batter into greased mold. 7: Bake 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. 8: Cool 5 to 10 minutes in pan, then turn out of pan on a  cooling rack. 9: Spoon melted chocolate over warm cake, coating completely. 10: Sprinkle nuts over cake. Cool completely.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4518,"Swiss Torta","PT1H30M","PT15M","PT1H45M","Make and share this Swiss Torta recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,3353.2,103.7,44.3,798.0,2337.9,565.7,14.5,397.2,70.3,"1.0","Swiss Torta Recipe Instructions:  1: Warm milk. Add sugar, salt and bread. 2: When this mixture is cool enough,  add slightly beaten eggs, melted butter, ground chocolate, lemon rind, raisin and citron; mix thoroughly. 3: Pour into 9 x 8-inch greased pan. Bake in 325 degrees oven for 1 1/2 hours. 4: (When cool, sprinkle red or green sugar or cake decorations for a holiday treat.)");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4519,"Beef Pine Nut Pies","PT15M","PT1H10M","PT1H25M","Make and share this Beef Pine Nut Pies recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",0.0,0.0,4937.4,124.1,37.9,355.9,9850.0,747.3,34.7,29.7,197.8,"1.0","Beef Pine Nut Pies Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown onions lightly in butter. 2: Add beef. Stir and brown about 10 minutes. 3: Add pine nuts and seasoning. Then simmer for 5 minutes. Cool slightly. 4: To make dough, dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water. 5: Mix into the flour and salt. Knead for 5 minutes until smooth. 6: Cover and let rise 45 minutes. 7: Cut dough in walnut size pieces. Roll out and place spoonfuls of filling on each round of dough. 8: Roll up and pinch dough so filling does not escape.  Bake on buttered cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes. 9: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. 10: May place under broiler 1 to 2 minutes for crispy brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4523,"Seven Layer Bars","PT30M","PT15M","PT45M","Make and share this Seven Layer Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",5.0,16.0,105.8,6.6,3.5,6.4,56.9,11.1,1.0,8.7,1.9,"40.0","Seven Layer Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan. 2: Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over the melted butter and press down. 3: Sprinkle the coconut on next, chocolate and  butterscotch pieces and nuts. Then drizzle condensed milk over all. 4: Press lightly. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.  [Editor''s note: added temp 12/16/2001]. 5: Cool in pan on wire rack. Cut into bars.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4524,"Chinese Chicken Sandwich","PT5M","PT5M","PT10M","Make and share this Chinese Chicken Sandwich recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",4.0,1.0,210.2,3.3,0.5,0.0,681.9,40.2,6.4,2.4,9.0,"1.0","Chinese Chicken Sandwich Recipe Instructions:  1: Place one lettuce leaf inside each pita half. 2: In a small bowl stir together remaining ingredients. 3: Fill pita halves with mixture. Wrap in plastic wrap and  chill.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4525,"Cherry Pecan Carrot Layer Cake","PT40M","PT15M","PT55M","Make and share this Cherry Pecan Carrot Layer Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,1124.1,57.7,29.9,198.3,887.8,147.6,3.9,117.6,9.3,"8.0","Cherry Pecan Carrot Layer Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 350°F 2: Butter and flour two 9-inch cake pans. 3: In large mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. 4: Add eggs, one at time; beat well. 5: Add mangoes and mango juice. Beat until light and fluffy. 6: In another bowl, combine flour and dry ingredients. 7: Add to creamed butter mixture and mix well. 8: Stir in cherries and pecans. 9: Divide batter between the two cake pans. 10: Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. 11: Remove cakes from oven; let cool 10  minutes. 12: Loosen edges of cake and invert onto cooling racks. Cool completely. 13: Make Cherry Frosting. In small saucepan, heat cream and cherries over medium heat until cherries are very soft, about 3 minutes. 14: Cool mixture 5 minutes. 15: Stir in vanilla and rum. 16: Cool in refrigerator about 15 minutes. 17: In large mixer bowl, cream butter and cream cheese until light. 18: Beat in cooled cherry mixture. 19: Gradually beat in sugar until creamy. 20: Place one layer of cake on serving plate. Spread with frosting. 21: Top with second cake layer and frost tip and sides of cake.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4526,"Bacon and Mushroom Stir-Fry","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Bacon and Mushroom Stir-Fry recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,5.0,1411.7,104.4,34.5,154.2,4105.9,79.4,23.4,36.7,50.5,"1.0","Bacon and Mushroom Stir-Fry Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook bacon until fat is rendered out, remove with slotted spoon, reserve. Pour off all but 2 Tbsp of bacon fat, keeping the excess in reserve if you wish to use it in the stir frying of the vegetables. Vegetable oil is really better. 2: Combine all sauce ingredients in a small bowl, stir until cornstarch is dissolved. 3: Pour over vegetables and bacon; cook and stir only until sauce thickens. 4: Serve over hot brown rice, or Chinese noodles, topped with additional soy sauce and toasted sesame seeds.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4528,"Cheesecake Brownies","PT30M","PT5M","PT35M","Make and share this Cheesecake Brownies recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",4.0,2.0,517.8,23.2,6.8,68.2,489.9,73.8,1.0,56.6,5.7,"12.0","Cheesecake Brownies Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 325°F. 2: Mix together cake mix, egg, nuts and margarine; press  into 13 x 9 ungreased cake pan. 3: Then mix the confectioners sugar, eggs and cream cheese; pour over crust mix. 4: Bake about 35 to 45 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4529,"Cheesecake Brownies II","PT45M","PT0S","PT45M","Make and share this Cheesecake Brownies II recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",4.0,1.0,624.8,34.6,13.0,151.5,447.7,72.5,1.6,24.0,10.5,"9.0","Cheesecake Brownies II Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat cream cheese, butter or margarine, sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla together for 7 minutes. 2: Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish. 3: Beat brownie mix with eggs, water and nuts. 4: Spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Swirl chocolate into cream cheese with a knife. Bake at 325°F for 40 to 45 minutes.");
