INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4531,"Basic Bread Pudding","PT1H30M","PT15M","PT1H45M","Make and share this Basic Bread Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,3.0,1847.4,75.9,39.6,839.5,2616.8,205.0,5.6,10.8,84.1,"1.0","Basic Bread Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat some of the milk to help dissolve the sugar. 2: Use another small amount of  milk to dissolve the cornstarch. 3: Beat the eggs. 4: Mix all liquids together and pour into baking dish. 5: Slice bread into cubes (size is not relevant) and drop into  liquid. 6: Dot the top generously with butter and sprinkle nutmeg on it. Place baking dish in a larger broiler pan with at least 1 inch of water and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees. 7: NOTES: Raisins, currants, etc. may be added. For an extra flavor soak raisins  for at least an hour (overnight is best) in brandy, rum, etc. to plump. The resultant raisin flavored liquor may be added to fruit cake, cookies, as a fruit compote, over crepes, or even simply drunk. Additionally a nonalcoholic sauce of your own choice may be made to accompany this.");
