INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4533,"Asparagus Pasta","0","PT30M","PT30M","Make and share this Asparagus Pasta recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,1.0,1046.7,28.1,8.0,22.0,2682.9,144.0,12.6,11.5,55.0,"0.0","Asparagus Pasta Recipe Instructions:  1: Place pasta and broth in a 4-5 quart pan over high heat, cover, and bring to a boil. 2: Reduce heat to medium-high, cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. 3: Add asparagus and cook, stirring occasionally, until pasta is barely tender to bite, 8-10 minutes. 4: Stir in cheese; remove pan from heat. 5: Meanwhile, cook oil in a medium frying pan over medium heat, 3-4 minutes. Add sage leaves, stir often until edges begin to curl, 2-3 minutes. 6: Remove from heat. With a slotted spoon, lift sage to a towel. 7: Reserve oil. 8: Crumble sage leaves; add sage and oil to pasta and mix. 9: Garnish with sage sprigs. Add pepper to taste.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4534,"Layer Cookies (Magic Layer Bars)","PT25M","PT15M","PT40M","I can still remember the first time I had one of these cookies at a church picnic as a kid...MMmmm. I''ve loved them ever since. Easy to make and always popular. A classic!","Bar Cookie",5.0,83.0,336.2,20.6,11.5,23.7,190.3,36.4,2.1,30.4,4.7,"16.0","Layer Cookies (Magic Layer Bars) Recipe Instructions:  1: Place melted butter in a 9 x 13 baking pan. Spread graham cracker crumbs over top. (I actually prefer to melt my butter in the microwave, mix in the graham cracker crumbs and then pat into the pan. It makes a more even bottom crust, I think.). 2: Layer the coconut and chips in order given. Pour sweetened condensed milk over all. Top with nuts. DO NOT mix together. 3: Bake at 350°F for 25 minutes or until lightly browned. (Please check earlier if your oven runs hot!).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4535,"Cinnamon Raisin Bread","PT2H30M","PT20M","PT2H50M","Make and share this Cinnamon Raisin Bread recipe from Food.com.","Yeast Breads",4.5,7.0,125.5,1.1,0.3,0.0,234.3,26.1,1.0,5.8,2.8,"0.0","Cinnamon Raisin Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. 2: Stir in 1 3/4 cups warm water, 3 tablespoons sugar, the salt, shortening and 3 1/2 cups of the flour. 3: Beat until smooth. 4: Mix in raisins and enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes. 5: Place in greased bowl, turn greased side up. 6: Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour. 7: (Dough is ready if an indentation remains when touched.) Punch down dough; divide into halves. 8: Roll each half into rectangle, 18 x 9-inches. 9: Mix 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. 10: Sprinkle each half with 1 tablespoon water and half the sugar mixture. Roll up and place in pans. 11: Brush with butter; let rise 1 hour. 12: Bake at 425 degrees f or 25 to 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4536,"Hershey''s Old Fashioned Rich Cocoa Fudge","PT2H30M","PT40M","PT3H10M","This is a crumbly, sugary old fashion fudge....from the back of the Hershey''s Cocoa can. Cook time is cooling time. If you are having trouble with it &quot;setting up&quot;, you probably didn''t cook it long enough. I have learned (the hard way!) to not trust my candy thermometer and to use to soft ball stage water test to make sure it is the right temperature. Even under cooking it by 2-3&deg; will result in a soft, sticky mess. It still taste good though. :)
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4537,"Chicken Tortilla Soup","0","PT30M","PT30M","This soup is quick to make, flavorful, and filling! Serve with warm corn bread or tortillas. This also freezes well.","Chicken Breast",5.0,60.0,244.9,8.1,1.9,30.9,224.1,26.9,7.5,6.6,18.4,"6.0","Chicken Tortilla Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: In a medium stock pot, saute onion and garlic in oil. 2: Stir in chili powder, oregano/Italian seasoning, tomatoes, broth and water. 3: Bring to boil and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes. 4: Add corn, hominy, chili peppers, beans, cilantro, and chicken. Simmer for 10 minutes. 5: Ladle soup into individual serving bowls and garnish with avocado, grated Jack cheese, chopped green onion, or crushed tortilla chips.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4540,"Pumpkin Cookies II","PT15M","PT20M","PT35M","Make and share this Pumpkin Cookies II recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",4.0,6.0,109.2,5.4,3.3,19.4,115.2,14.7,0.6,8.2,1.1,"0.0","Pumpkin Cookies II Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350F and grease cookie sheet. 2: Sift dry ingredients together into a large bowl. 3: In another bowl, beat butter and sugar together until fluffy; add remaining ingredients. 4: Add batter to dry ingredients and mix well. 5: Drop by spoonfuls on prepared cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes. (ovens will vary).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4541,"Oatmeal Bread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Oatmeal Bread recipe from Food.com.","Yeast Breads",4.0,1.0,2004.8,25.8,5.9,0.0,3520.5,393.8,15.2,74.2,45.5,"0.0","Oatmeal Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Pour the boiling water over the quick oats, shortening, salt, molasses and 1/2 cup sugar. 2: Let stand until lukewarm. 3: Dissolve yeast and sugar in 1/2 cup lukewarm water and add to oat mixture. Add flour and knead until firm. 4: Let stand until double in size. Form into 2 loaves and let rise again until double in size. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4542,"Barbecue Sauce with Mustard","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Barbecue Sauce with Mustard recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",4.5,2.0,2034.9,38.4,4.3,0.0,7953.8,427.7,9.4,343.7,15.2,"0.0","Barbecue Sauce with Mustard Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine sugar, oregano. 2: thyme, salt, pepper, cayenne pepper, and  cornstarch in a small saucepan. 3: Stir in enough vinegar to make a paste.  Combine molasses, ketchup, mustard, oil and remaining vinegar; add to  herb paste. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. 4: Reduce heat and  simmer 10 minutes. 5: Remove from heat; cool completely. 6: Pour into a glass  jar; cover tightly. 7: Store in refrigerator up to 3 months. 8: Best used for  chicken, turkey, ham or hot dogs.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4543,"Mustard Based Central South Carolina BBQ Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Mustard Based Central South Carolina BBQ Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",4.5,2.0,770.8,43.1,7.1,0.0,1508.4,98.2,3.4,81.4,5.5,"0.0","Mustard Based Central South Carolina BBQ Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine ingredients and set aside. 2: Grill meat (do not add anything). During the last 4-10 minutes baste with this sauce. 3: Boil the remaining sauce and spoon 2 tablespoons onto each plate, adding the meat portion.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4544,"Zabaglione","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Zabaglione recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,111.0,3.8,1.4,174.8,8.3,11.8,0.0,10.8,2.3,"0.0","Zabaglione Recipe Instructions:  1: TO COOK THE ZABAGLIONE: Set up a double boiler or a medium-size stainless-steel bowl over a pot of simmering water. Check to make sure the bottom of the bowl is not touching the water, or the eggs may scramble. 2: With a hand held electric mixer, beat the egg yolks and sugar together until pale yellow. 3: Add the Marsala and set the bowl over the simmering water. 4: Continue to beat with the electric mixer until the eggs triple in volume,  thicken and reach a temperature of 140 F., as registered on an instant thermometer. Be sure to beat the eggs until they reach this temperature at  which salmonella bacteria is killed. This will take about 10 to 15 minutes.  Be sure to move the beater around the bowl so the eggs cook evenly; there will be quite a bit of spattering. 5: TO SERVE THE ZABAGLIONE: Transfer the mixture to wine glasses and serve immediately accompanied by ladyfingers or Italian cookies known as \ 6:  7: An alternative way to serve this is to take slices of pound cake or panettone and set them on a broiler pan. Cover the cake slices with a  layer of sliced strawberries or peeled Comice pear, and ladle a portion of the zabaglione over the fruit. Broil the slices for a minute or until the zabaglione is bubbling and lightly browned. 8: Serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4545,"Roasted Loin of Wild Boar with Apple Charlotte","0","PT0S","PT0S","Boar is a greatly ignored meat in the chef''s repertoire. While admittedly difficult to find, it can be special ordered, and it is a sublime gastronomic treat. This homespun preparation by Joe Mannke, chef a Rotisserie for Beef and Bird in Houston, marries the boar with a tasty apple charlotte that is the perfect companion.","Pork",3.0,1.0,337.4,18.4,10.7,123.7,1433.2,35.0,2.9,12.4,3.5,"6.0","Roasted Loin of Wild Boar with Apple Charlotte Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 450F. 2: Rub boar on all sides with salt, pepper, and thyme. Place boar in a roasting pan and add water to pan. Roast in preheated oven for 40 minutes. Remove roasting pan from oven. 3: Prepare charlotte by adding apples, zest, ginger, cinnamon, cloves, brown sugar, wine, and Calvados around the roast. 4: Return pan to oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until apples are cooked through. 5: Mix together applesauce, salt, and egg yolks and pour over apples. 6: Return to oven for 5 minutes longer. 7: Mix the butter with the bread cubes. 8: Sprinkle over the apple mixture and bake for 10 minutes longer, or until golden brown, or when meat thermometer registers 160F. 9: Remove roasting pan from oven, remove boar, and let rest for a few minutes. 10: Slice boar on the bias. 11: Using a spatula, transfer charlotte to a large serving platter. Place sliced boar atop charlotte. Garnish with thyme sprigs and serve. 12: Recommended wines: A full bodied Chardonnay will mar ry nicely with the apple flavor in the charlotte. A Zinfandel will emphasize the meaty flavors of the boar. Either wine is a treat with this dish.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4546,"Deb''s Zabaglione","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Deb''s Zabaglione recipe from Food.com.","Sauces",0.0,0.0,306.9,9.0,3.2,419.6,23.7,24.1,0.0,20.2,5.5,"2.0","Deb''s Zabaglione Recipe Instructions:  1: On top of a double boiler or bain-marie, whisk the egg yolks and sugar   until dissolved.  (I use an electric hand mixer) 2:  3: Add the marsala   slowly, while whisking constantly. 4: Continue to whisk until the   mixture is thick and VERY fluffy. 5: Serve warm in a pretty long   stemmed glass. 6: This can also be served as a sauce on top of fruit and   or angel food cake.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4547,"Italian Cream Cake","PT25M","PT45M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Italian Cream Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,3.0,912.3,48.9,11.9,109.0,417.5,109.6,2.4,86.8,13.9,"0.0","Italian Cream Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream margarine and shortening with sugar. 2: Add egg yolks; mix well. 3: Combine flour and soda; add alternately with buttermilk. 4: Add vanilla, coconut and nuts; fold mixture in egg whites. 5: Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. 6: Italian Cream Cake Frosting:  Beat together cream cheese and margarine, then add sugar  and vanilla. 7: Ice cake; put black walnuts between layers and on top.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4548,"Sweet Potatoes and Black Walnuts","PT30M","PT20M","PT50M","Make and share this Sweet Potatoes and Black Walnuts recipe from Food.com.","Potato",4.0,1.0,2109.3,103.8,44.3,186.8,1113.8,274.5,27.6,133.2,35.9,"0.0","Sweet Potatoes and Black Walnuts Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel, boil and mash sweet potatoes. 2: Add hot milk, sugar and 3 tablespoons butter. 3: Add black walnuts and salt; mix thoroughly. 4: Place in greased baking dish. 5: Pour melted butter on top of potato mixture. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350 degrees.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4549,"West Virginia Black Walnut Cake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this West Virginia Black Walnut Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,7887.4,390.1,195.0,1199.7,6239.2,1019.4,24.9,756.9,121.0,"1.0","West Virginia Black Walnut Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butterscotch morsels in water; cool. 2: Sift together flour, salt, soda and  baking powder; set aside. 3: Add sugar gradually to butter, creaming well. 4: Blend in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. 5: Blend in melted butterscotch morsels, mix well. 6: Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk beginning and  ending with dry ingredients. Blend thoroughly. 7: Fold in black walnuts. 8: Turn into  two (9-inch) round layer pans well greased and floured lightly. 9: Bake at 350  degrees for 30 minutes or until done. Cool. 10: Filling:  Combine sugar and cornstarch for filling in 2 quart pan. Stir in milk, water, butterscotch and egg yolk. Cook over medium heat. Stirring constantly, until thick. 11: Remove from heat and add butter, coconut and black walnuts. Cool. 12: Spread butterscotch filling between layers and on top to within 1/2-inch of edge. 13: Frosting:  Cream butter in bowl with wooden spoon until very soft.  Slowly add sugar, mixing thoroughly; add a drop of milk at a  time as mixture gets too stiff. Flavor with 1/4 teaspoon vanilla. 14: For chocolate butter icing, add 1/2 ounce melted chocolate.  The yolk of one egg will make yellow icing.  Strong coffee instead of milk will make mocha icing.  Using, of course, only one flavor at a time. 15: Frost with Butter Frosting around sides and on top of cake to meet the filling.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4550,"Sally Anne Cookies","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sally Anne Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,7210.3,380.9,166.6,1219.9,3239.9,861.8,26.2,415.8,109.2,"1.0","Sally Anne Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: These cookies should be mixed the evening before you want to bake them. 2: They should be placed in a cold place or refrigerator overnight. Beat the 2 sugars, butter and lard together until well blended. 3: Add the well beaten eggs and blend. 4: Sift the dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture. Put in the black walnuts (any nuts will do if you don''t care for the black walnuts) and mix well. 5: Make into a roll and wrap in waxed paper. 6: The next morning take out of refrigerator and slice and bake in  a 350 degrees oven.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4551,"Bagels II","0","PT0S","PT2H","Make and share this Bagels II recipe from Food.com.","Yeast Breads",4.0,4.0,177.2,0.5,0.1,0.0,583.8,37.4,1.5,3.3,5.1,"0.0","Bagels II Recipe Instructions:  1: In large mixer bowl, combine yeast and 1 3/4 cups of flour. 2: Combine water, sugar and salt. Add to yeast mixture. Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly. 3: Beat 3 minutes at high speed. 4: By hand, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough. 5: Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead until smooth, 5 to 8 minutes. 6: Cover, let rest 15 minutes. 7: Cut into 12 portions and shape into smooth balls. 8: Punch a hole in center of each with a floured finger. 9: Pull gently to enlarge hole, working each bagel into uniform shape. Cover, let rise 20 minutes. 10: In large kettle combine 1 gallon water and 1 tablespoon sugar; bring to a boil. 11: Reduce temperature to a simmer. 12: Cook bagels 4 or 5 at a time, for 7 minutes, turning once. Drain and place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in 375 degrees oven for 30 to 35 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4552,"Cheese Puffs","PT5M","PT15M","PT20M","Make and share this Cheese Puffs recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",0.0,0.0,12.1,1.0,0.6,3.0,23.3,0.2,0.0,0.1,0.7,"20.0","Cheese Puffs Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix all ingredients--but not the crackers. 2: Spread this mixture onto  the crackers--edge to edge. Chill. 3: Just before serving, broil them 6 inches from the broiler until they are a golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4553,"Spiced Pecans","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Spiced Pecans recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",0.0,0.0,2770.4,209.7,43.2,122.0,564.9,237.8,26.0,208.8,21.6,"0.0","Spiced Pecans Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil sugar, water, butter, and spices in a large pan until it forms a soft ball. **About 2 - 3 minutes** 2: Remove from heat and gradually add the pecans. Stir gently until it turns sugary. 3: Put it all onto a waxed paper cookie sheet. 4: Next, butter up your hands and pull apart  the pecans into tiny clusters.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4554,"Lipton Onion Sticks","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lipton Onion Sticks recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",4.0,1.0,2543.8,196.0,118.9,490.0,6482.6,175.5,9.8,20.7,27.8,"1.0","Lipton Onion Sticks Recipe Instructions:  1: Blend the soup mix into the butter, mixing well. **This mixture will make 1 1/4 cup ** 2: Spread the mixture onto the bread slices w/  1/2 cup of the onion/butter spread. Cut the slices into strips. 3: Bake at 375*  for 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet. 4: You can also prepare it for freezing. Follow instructions above and then cool off. Once it is completely cooled, place in zippy bags and  freeze. The left over spread freezes well also.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4556,"Hot Sauteed Shrimp","PT15M","PT15M","PT30M","Make and share this Hot Sauteed Shrimp recipe from Food.com.","Very Low Carbs",5.0,1.0,215.9,10.3,2.7,148.1,817.3,1.5,0.0,0.1,17.7,"6.0","Hot Sauteed Shrimp Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat broiler. 2: Melt 1/4 cup margarine in a large frying pan. 3: Add shrimp and rum mixture with garlic salt. 4: Saute 8 to 10 minutes or until shrimp is cooked through. 5: Sprinkle with cheese and pepper. 6: Broil 2 to 3 minutes until cheese browns.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4557,"Sauteed Shrimp","PT5M","PT10M","PT15M","Make and share this Sauteed Shrimp recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,18.0,145.8,5.4,2.6,200.7,1085.7,2.5,0.3,0.3,20.9,"3.0","Sauteed Shrimp Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter in a 10-inch skillet over high heat. 2: Add shrimp with onions, salt and pepper, stirring constantly, until shrimp are pink, about 3 to 5 minutes. 3: Add sherry and parsley. 4: Serve while hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4558,"Southern Biscuits","PT30M","PT15M","PT45M","I normally don''t use a recipe for my biscuits,but I''ve learned from experience that the recipe on the bag of flour does not make the best biscuits. Here is an approximate recipe.","Breads",5.0,4.0,215.9,10.9,2.8,1.5,435.5,24.9,0.8,1.8,4.3,"10.0","Southern Biscuits Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix flour and shortening in a mixing bowl. 2: Using a pastry blender or a fork,  cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. 3: Add buttermilk and stir. 4: Start out with a little and add more as you need. 5: The dough should be wet and gummy. 6: THEN, sprinkle a little flour on top and work it in with your hands. 7: Then flip the dough and do the same on the other side. Continue to do this until the dough isn''t sticky on the outside, it doesn''t take much. 8: Then flour your hands and take a small amount of dough and roll it into a ball, then place on a greased cookie sheet or baking pan and flatten slightly into a biscuit shape. When you''ve finished with the dough, b ake the biscuits in a 400 degree oven for about 10 minutes, just until they start to brown, then take them out and preheat the broiler, and then stick the biscuits back in until they are brown. 9: You can brush them with melted butter if you like. This may take some practice, but after a few times you will know what the consistency of the dough should feel like. I hope this works for you.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4559,"Spritz Cookies","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Spritz Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,43.8,2.8,1.7,18.4,18.7,4.1,0.1,1.4,0.5,"0.0","Spritz Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. 2: Allow butter to slightly soften.  In medium-sized mixing bowl, mash with back of wooden spoon until creamy. 3: Blend in egg yolks, sugar and almond extract. 4: Add flour gradually, mixing well. 5: Mixture should be firm, yet soft enough to force through cookie press, following directions for making stars, snowflakes, etc. If you don''t have a cookie press, the mixture may be rolled into 3/4-inch balls, placed 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet and flattened to about 1/4-inch thickness with bottom of a glass lightly dipped in flour. 6: Decorate cookies with colored sugar or sprinkles, bits of candied cherry, green citrus or other candied fruit. To make colored sugar, mix a drop of red or green food coloring into 1/4 cup of sugar and stir thoroughly. 7: Bake Spritz cookies for about 10 minutes or just until light brown around the edges.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4560,"Chocolate Spritz Cookies","PT5M","PT0S","PT5M","Make and share this Chocolate Spritz Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,31.0,61.4,3.6,2.2,12.5,53.1,6.8,0.3,2.5,0.8,"0.0","Chocolate Spritz Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla in a large mixin  g  bowl until light and fluffy. 2: Add mixture of flour, cocoa and  salt gradually; mix well. 3: Press through cookie press onto cool  ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until set. Remove onto wire rack. 4: Cool completely.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4561,"Butter Spritz Cookies","PT10M","PT0S","PT10M","Make and share this Butter Spritz Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,4.0,65.0,4.0,2.5,14.6,28.8,6.6,0.2,2.1,0.8,"0.0","Butter Spritz Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter; Add sugar and beat until fluffy. 2: Beat in  egg and almond extract. Blend in flour. 3: Divide dough into  thirds. 4: Add a few drops red food coloring to 1/3, green  coloring to 1/3 and leave 1/3 plain. 5: Fill cookie press with  each color or combine colors for a rainbow effect. Form into  desired shapes and decorate. Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes. 6: Makes about 4 dozen.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4562,"Swedish Spritz Cookies","PT8M","PT0S","PT8M","Make and share this Swedish Spritz Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,38.6,2.3,1.4,8.3,16.5,4.0,0.1,1.2,0.5,"0.0","Swedish Spritz Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°. 2: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. 3: Beat in egg and extracts. 4: Gradually blend in flour. 5: Fill cookie press with dough. 6: Using star attachments, form \ 7:  shapes on ungreased cookie sheets. 8: Bake cookies 8-10 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4563,"Shoo Fly Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Shoo Fly Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",0.0,0.0,401.3,11.8,3.0,23.2,230.0,70.6,0.9,36.8,4.3,"8.0","Shoo Fly Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve soda in hot water; add molasses and egg. 2: Combine sugar and flour and rub in the shortening to make crumbs. 3: Pour one-third of the liquid into an unbaked pie crust. Add one-third of the crumb mixture. Continue alternate layers, putting crumbs on top. 4: Bake at 375: for approximately 35 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4564,"Yam Flambe","PT45M","PT10M","PT55M","Make and share this Yam Flambe recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,563.3,11.8,7.3,30.5,406.8,102.8,8.8,40.8,3.5,"0.0","Yam Flambe Recipe Instructions:  1: Scrub yams well with vegetable brush.  Place in a medium saucepan; add water to cover and salt.  Over medium heat, bring to boiling. 2: Reduce heat; simmer,  covered 30 minutes or until just fork-tender. Drain; let cool. 3: Then peel and slice crosswise 1/2 inch thick. Lightly coat each slice with brown sugar. 4: In hot butter in a medium skillet, saute slices until browned, about  2 minutes on each side.  With a slotted utensil, lift to serving dish. 5: Drain fat from pan. In the same skillet, gently heat the rum just until steaming, ignite: pour over yams.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4565,"Cranberry Citrus Marinade","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cranberry Citrus Marinade recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",0.0,0.0,1367.2,0.2,0.0,0.0,34.2,354.1,5.3,330.4,1.0,"0.0","Cranberry Citrus Marinade Recipe Instructions:  1: Remove peel from 1 grapefruit and 1 orange; scrape excess white membrane from peel.  Cut peel into thin strips. 2: In large kettle, combine peel and 2 1/2 cups water; cook,  covered, over low heat till tendeer, 20 minutes. 3: Section grapefruit and orange; chop fruit.  Add with 3 cups fresh cranberries to peel;  simmer 10 minutes, stirring constantly. 4: Stir in one 1 3/4-ounce package powdered fruit pectin. 5: Bring to boil; stir in 6 1/2 cups sugar. Bring to full rolling boil; boil hard 1 minute stirring constantly. 6: Remove from heat and skim foam.  Let stand 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. 7: Ladle into hot sterilized glasses.  Seal.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4566,"Cranberry Relish","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cranberry Relish recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",5.0,1.0,360.9,0.3,0.0,0.0,42.7,93.5,6.0,83.5,0.8,"0.0","Cranberry Relish Recipe Instructions:  1: Using coarse blade of food chopper, grind cranberries,  celery, and apple. 2: Stir in sugar and lemon juice. 3: Cover and refrigerate.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4567,"Grapefruit Cranberry Relish","PT20M","PT0S","PT20M","Make and share this Grapefruit Cranberry Relish recipe from Food.com.","Citrus",5.0,1.0,371.7,0.2,0.0,0.0,1.9,96.2,4.4,78.8,1.1,"0.0","Grapefruit Cranberry Relish Recipe Instructions:  1: Put cranberries through food chopper. 2: Add sugar; mix well. 3: Peel, section, and dice grapefruit; stir into cranberries. 4: Chill.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4568,"Cranberry-Orange Relish","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cranberry-Orange Relish recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",5.0,12.0,478.4,0.2,0.0,0.0,3.7,123.8,7.7,111.2,1.1,"0.0","Cranberry-Orange Relish Recipe Instructions:  1: Put cranberries and oranges through a grinder. 2: Stir in 1 1/2 cups sugar. 3: Chill. 4: Or, freeze in airtight containers for longer storage.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4569,"Cranberries Jubilee","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cranberries Jubilee recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,412.0,0.1,0.0,0.0,6.9,89.7,3.7,83.1,0.3,"0.0","Cranberries Jubilee Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine sugar and water in saucepan, stirring to dissolve sugar. 2: Bring to boiling; boil 5 minutes. 3: Add cranberries and bring to boiling again; cook 5 minutes. 4: Turn into heat-proof bowl or blazer pan of chafing dish. 5: Heat brandy. 6: Ignite brandy and pour over cranberry mixture. Blend into sauce and serve immediately over ice cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4570,"Cranberry Chocolate Candy","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cranberry Chocolate Candy recipe from Food.com.","Candy",0.0,1.0,3623.8,137.5,46.6,49.3,1886.0,591.4,31.7,363.2,49.3,"1.0","Cranberry Chocolate Candy Recipe Instructions:  1: In saucepan, combine cranberries, sugar, and 1/2 cup water.  Bring to boil; simmer for 3 minutes, or until cranberries are tender but hold their shape. 2: Drain, reserving 2 tbsp. syrup. 3: Melt chocolate with milk; stir till smooth.  Add vanilla. 4: Stir in remaining ingredients, cranberries, and reserved syrup. 5: Pat in well-greased 9x9x2-inch baking dish.  Chill till firm. Cut in squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4571,"Okonomiyaki - Japanese Pizza","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Okonomiyaki - Japanese Pizza recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",4.5,16.0,326.9,16.4,2.6,93.0,408.1,33.8,2.4,6.1,7.7,"4.0","Okonomiyaki - Japanese Pizza Recipe Instructions:  1: Toast the nori by waving it over a flame until it stiffens slightly, but be careful--it burns easily.  Crumble into little pieces and set aside. 2: Combine all the sauce ingredients in a small saucepan and simmer for 30 seconds, stirring constantly. 3: Remove from the heat and cool to room temperature. 4: Beat the eggs in a large bowl. 5: Add the flour and water and continue beating until you have a batter the consistency of pancake batter. 6: Add the sake and salt. 7: Fold in the cabbage, carrots, and scallions.  Be sure to mix the batter and vegetables together evenly.  Each okonomiyaki will use 1/4 of this mixture. 8: Heat 1 tbsp. of the oil in a standard 10-inch skillet.   Spoon 1/4 of the batter onto the hot skillet (like a pancake) making sure the vegetables are evenly distributed. 9: Then sprinkle 1/4 of the shrimp or meat of you choice on top. 10: Cook each side on medium heat for 2 minutes, until lightly browned. Reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for another 5 minutes, occasionally turning and gently pressing the okonomiyaki with a spatula. 11: Prepare three more okonomiyaki as above.  Keep the finished pancakes warm in a low oven while making the rest, or use two skillets and make two okonomiyaki at a time. 12: Serve hot with the sauce to taste--I recommend 1 tbsp. per okonomiyaki-- and  top with about a tsp. of mayonnaise and a sprinkling of toasted nori.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4572,"Gypsy Tart II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Gypsy Tart II recipe from Food.com.","Pie",0.0,1.0,454.1,15.0,5.5,19.2,248.1,75.5,1.1,54.6,6.3,"6.0","Gypsy Tart II Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400 F. 2: Whisk evaporated milk and sugar together for 10 - 15 minutes until light and fluffy. The mix should be coffee coloured. 3: Pour the mix into the pastry case and bake in the oven for 10 minutes. 4: The gypsy tart will have a slightly sticky surface but will not be set completely until it has been left to cool. 5: Serve cold.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4574,"Seven Layer Cookies","PT30M","PT10M","PT40M","Make and share this Seven Layer Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",4.0,3.0,1155.8,78.7,32.6,15.4,527.2,111.4,7.1,91.1,13.1,"4.0","Seven Layer Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Pour melted margarine in 8x13 pan Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine 2: Sprinkle next 4 ingredients in order. Pour milk over all. 3: Bake at 350* for 30  minutes (No Longer) 4: Cool, cut into squares Keep refrigerated");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4577,"Chocolate Cheesecake Brownies","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chocolate Cheesecake Brownies recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",4.5,2.0,198.3,10.5,6.1,65.6,69.0,25.6,1.7,18.3,3.4,"24.0","Chocolate Cheesecake Brownies Recipe Instructions:  1: Brownie batter - preheat oven to 350~. Butter 13\ 2: x2\ 3: ,  4: ,  5: ,  6: ,  7: ,  8: Add sugar and beat until fluffy. Beat in eggs, flour, and coffee liqueur. 9: Set aside 1/2 cup brownie batter for topping. 10: Pour remaining batter into prepared pan.  Carefully spoon cream cheese mixture over batter, covering completely. Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over cream cheese layer. 11: Drop reserved batter by spoonfuls over cream cheese layer. 12: Using small knife, swirl batter into cream cheese mixture to resemble marble pattern. 13: Bake brownies until edges are light golden and toothpick inserted into center comes out with some crumbs still  attached; about 30 mins. 14: Cool completely in pan on rack; cut into squares.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4579,"Bog Fog","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Bog Fog recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",0.0,0.0,126.3,0.2,0.0,0.0,2.2,15.0,0.1,12.7,0.4,"2.0","Bog Fog Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine. Stir briskly. 2: Serve over ice in 2 glasses.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4580,"Taco Soup II","PT2M","PT15M","PT17M","Make and share this Taco Soup II recipe from Food.com.","Beans",5.0,1.0,196.7,7.0,2.8,28.1,852.0,22.1,4.4,5.0,12.2,"12.0","Taco Soup II Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown the beef in a large saucepan. 2: Stir in all other ingredients and simmer on low for 2 hours.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4583,"Snowballs","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Snowballs recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,3.0,56.5,3.8,2.0,8.1,31.6,5.1,0.2,1.0,0.7,"0.0","Snowballs Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream sugar, salt and margarine thoroughly in small mix  bowl. 2: Add vanilla. 3: Gradually stir flour into creamed ingredients. 4: Work nuts into  dough. 5: Chill well; form into 1-inch  balls. 6: Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in 400 degrees oven, 10  to 12 minutes. 7: Roll in confectioners sugar. 8: Cool on rack,  roll again in confectioners sugar.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4584,"Pecan-Orange Snowballs","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pecan-Orange Snowballs recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,4792.2,343.6,130.5,488.1,1314.5,410.8,28.9,194.0,47.9,"1.0","Pecan-Orange Snowballs Recipe Instructions:  1: In the large bowl of an electric mixer, cream together  the butter and sugar. 2: Stir in the flour, pecans, orange rind  and vanilla. 3: Shape the dough into walnut-size balls. 4: Bake the  balls on ungreased cookie sheets on the cent  er rack of the oven  at 300 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes. 5: Cool the balls slightly and roll");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4586,"Honey Pumpkin Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Honey Pumpkin Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",4.0,1.0,212.4,6.6,3.5,85.6,230.5,38.5,0.6,35.4,3.3,"0.0","Honey Pumpkin Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry disk. 2: Flute the edge. With fork, prick shell all over. 3: Place in freezer for 30 minutes. 4: Line pastry shell with foil or parchment paper, then fill with pie weights or pie chains. 5: Bake empty shell on the lowest rack in 400 F oven for 10 minutes. 6: Remove both weights and foil; continue baking for about 10 minutes longer or until pastry is set. FILLING: Meanwhile, in large bowl, beat eggs lightly. 7: Add pumpkin, honey, light cream, cinnamon, cloves, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Combine thoroughly and  pour into the pastry shell. 8: Combine sour cream with milk; pour into plastic dispenser with very, very, very narrow opening. 9: Hold finger over the opening and position the dispenser above the pie. Remove finger and quickly drizzle mixture in spiral pattern over filling. 10: Beginning at centre, pull tip of knife towards the perimeter through filling and sour cream mixture at 8 evenly spaced intervals about 1/4 inch deep. 11: Beginning  at outside, pull knife through middle of intervals toward centre to create web pattern. 12: Bake on lowest rack in 350 F oven for about 1 hour or until filling is set and point of knife inserted into centre comes out clean. 13: Let cool on rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4587,"Braised Beef Liver With Vegetables II","PT1H30M","PT0S","PT1H30M","Make and share this Braised Beef Liver With Vegetables II recipe from Food.com.","Beef Organ Meats",4.0,1.0,4075.1,133.3,47.6,4481.6,3071.7,341.4,39.3,28.6,363.6,"0.0","Braised Beef Liver With Vegetables II Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat the drippings in a heavy skillet. Brown the liver, onions,  celery. 2: Put it into a greased casserole; add the stock and salt.  Place the bacon strips on top of the liver. 3: Cook uncovered in a 350* oven for 30 minutes. 4: Next, add the potatoes and carrots. Return to  the oven, covered and cook until the vegetables are done. **About 45  mins**. 5: Remove the cover and continue baking until the bacon strips are crispy.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4588,"Holiday Cheese Ball","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Holiday Cheese Ball recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",4.5,2.0,3157.3,315.3,113.2,499.0,1346.9,59.8,23.5,21.6,55.4,"0.0","Holiday Cheese Ball Recipe Instructions:  1: Soften cheese. Gradually add the pineapple. Mix in 1 cup of the nuts  and add the rest of the ingredients. 2: Chill well. 3: remove from  refrigerator and shape into 1 or 2 balls. 4: Roll into the rest of the  remaining nuts. 5: Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until you serve. 6: Garnish the  ball with jarred cherries and pineapple rings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4589,"Dark Rich Fruitcake","PT2H30M","PT0S","PT2H30M","This is a dark cake with spots of colour from the glace cherries. This recipe has been in the family for about 100 years now, and may be what you are looking for!","Dessert",0.0,0.0,836.3,28.5,11.4,146.4,376.4,140.6,7.2,107.1,12.0,"24.0","Dark Rich Fruitcake Recipe Instructions:  1: Day One -Wash and scald raisins to plump. 2: Drain and dry well. 3: Place all fruit and almonds into a large bowl. 4: Sprinkle spices over fruit  and add the lemon and orange rind and juice. Stir in the rum and let stand overnight, stirring occasionally. 5: Day Two -Cream butter. 6: Gradually add sugar, bea ting well after each addition. 7: Add  egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition. 8: Add flavourings. 9: Add 1 cup of flour to fruit and nut mixture. Toss to coat well. 10: Add  remaining flour alternately with cold coffee to the creamed mixture. Stir  in fruit mixture.  Beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form. 11: Fold into batter. 12: Pour batter into 3 pans which have been lined with two thicknesses of brown  paper and the top layer greased and dusted with flour. 13: (We used tube/funnel  pans.)  Bake at 275F for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours or until a cake tester comes out  clean from the centre. Cool cakes completely in the pans on cake racks. 14: Remove from pans and peel  off paper. 15: Wrap cakes in cheesecloth (moistened with rum); then in foil. 16: Keep in a cool place for four to six weeks to allow the flavours to join. 17: NOTES: Grandma used to open the foils and re-moisten the cheesecloth at least once  in the ripening process. 18: (By drizzling in about 2 Tbsp rum There is note of timings for different  fruit cake pans. 19: (I think originally the recipe would make one each of the 4, 6 and 8 inch  pans.) 4x4 - 2 1/2 hours 6x6 - 3 hours 8x8 - 3 1/2 hours or until tests clean - in a 2750F Oven.");
