INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4591,"Party Punch","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Party Punch recipe from Food.com.","Punch Beverage",5.0,3.0,3219.4,2.0,0.1,0.0,1192.5,817.8,18.2,741.1,6.9,"1.0","Party Punch Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix fruit punch and sugar in punch bowl; stir. 2: Add 7-Up  or substitute and frozen strawberries last, stir gently. 3: Better  to have fruit punch chilled or a few ice cubes can be added. 4: Put in strawberries, still frozen, helps keep punch cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4592,"Party Fruit Punch","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Party Fruit Punch recipe from Food.com.","Punch Beverage",0.0,0.0,37.5,0.0,0.0,0.0,10.1,9.6,0.1,9.2,0.1,"100.0","Party Fruit Punch Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix fruit punch drink mix with 2 quarts of water and add  2 cups of sugar. 2: Add all frozen juices. 3: Add crushed pineapple  and chopped cherrie  s. 4: Mix well or until all ingredients are  melted. 5: Before serving, add 8 quarts of water. 6: In a large  punch bowl put 2 quarts mix, 2 quarts ice, 1/2 liter of ginger  ale. Mix well and serve. Makes approximately 4 gallons;  enough to serve 100.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4593,"Holiday Fruit Punch with Orange Slice Wreath","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Holiday Fruit Punch with Orange Slice Wreath recipe from Food.com.","Punch Beverage",0.0,0.0,122.8,0.5,0.1,0.0,7.6,30.3,0.4,1.3,0.3,"18.0","Holiday Fruit Punch with Orange Slice Wreath Recipe Instructions:  1: In punch bowl, stir together punch, orange concentrate and water. 2: Unmold ice wreath by dipping in warm water to loosen. 3: Add to punch, orange side. Garnish wreath with cherries. 4: If desired, add 1 to 2 cups vodka to punch. 5: Orange Slice Wreath: Pour 3 cups water into 5 1/2-cup ring mold. 6: Freeze 1 hour or until top is solid. 7: Slice 1 large orange, then cut slices in half and arrange petal fashion in 2 layers on ice around ring. 8: Pour 1 cup water over oranges and freeze solid.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4594,"Turkey Bone Gumbo","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Turkey Bone Gumbo recipe from Food.com.","Gumbo",4.0,2.0,300.9,23.4,8.3,37.6,1107.1,14.8,1.7,2.6,7.6,"0.0","Turkey Bone Gumbo Recipe Instructions:  1: Place carcass in large soup kettle; cover with water. 2: Bring to a boil;  cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours. 3: Drain turkey; reserve broth. 4: Remove meat  from carcass; chop and set aside. Heat drippings in kettle; add flour  gradually, stirring constantly until a rich brown roux is formed, about 25  minutes. 5: Add vegetables and cook until tender. 6: Add broth and other  seasonings; simmer 1 hour. 7: Add turkey and sausage  ; cook 15 minutes. 8: Add  rest of ingredients; cook 10 minutes longer. 9: Serve over hot cooked rice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4596,"Turkey Chowder","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Turkey Chowder recipe from Food.com.","Chowders",4.0,1.0,881.5,53.2,28.2,818.1,511.9,64.6,6.7,7.9,38.3,"0.0","Turkey Chowder Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large kettle, combine all of the bones and any leftover skin of the  roast turkey with the bouquet garni and the cloves. 2: Add the water, bring  to a boil, reduce the heat to low, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. 3: Strain the broth through a fine sieve into a clean kettle. Let it cool,  then refrigerate and, when the broth is cold, skim off the cake of fat  from the top. 4: Return the turkey broth to the heat. Add the potato  ,  carrot, green pepper, onion, garlic and marjoram. 5: Cook until the  vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes and season to taste with salt and  black pepper. 6: Stir in the milk mixed with the egg yolks and add, if used,  the dry sherry, chopped turkey and hard-boiled eggs. 7: Just before serving,  stir in the butter. 8: Serve with hot toasted, buttered crackers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4598,"Taco Soup IIi","PT2H","PT15M","PT2H15M","Make and share this Taco Soup IIi recipe from Food.com.","Meat",5.0,1.0,260.2,13.2,4.7,52.2,654.0,20.2,3.2,5.1,16.7,"12.0","Taco Soup IIi Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut up onion and put into large stockpot with ground meat. 2: Cook until meat is brown and onions are translucent, then drain out the grease from the pot. 3: Add remaining ingredients. 4: Cook on low for several hours. 5: Use more or less liquids for thinner/thicker soup.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4599,"Zucchini Cilantro Dip","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Zucchini Cilantro Dip recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,3.0,745.3,44.4,6.1,0.0,755.1,75.8,18.0,12.0,20.0,"0.0","Zucchini Cilantro Dip Recipe Instructions:  1: Line a large baking sheet with a clean dish towel;  spread zucchini over towel. 2: Sprinkle with 3/4 teaspoon salt; let stand 5 minutes. 3: Roll zucchini in towel; squeeze out moisture.  In food processor, combine zucchini, garbanzo beans, cilantro, and garlic; process until smooth. 4: Add vinegar, oil, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, and jalapeno, if desired; process 10 seconds. 5: Adjust salt to taste.  Serve dip with chips, carrot sticks, cucumber slices, or pita wedges. 6: It only takes about 15 minutes to make.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4600,"Lemon-Blueberry Muffins","PT22M","PT10M","PT32M","Make and share this Lemon-Blueberry Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",4.5,27.0,203.6,8.4,3.4,28.5,159.4,28.9,1.3,12.5,4.0,"0.0","Lemon-Blueberry Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400°F. 2: Grease a 12 cup muffin tin. 3: In a  large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir  in walnuts and lemon peel. 4: In a small bowl beat egg, milk,  butter and vanilla. 5: Pour egg mixture into dry ingredients and  stir just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).  Fold in blueberries. 6: Spoon into muffin cups and bake 20 to 22  minutes or until tops are golden.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4601,"Lemon Blueberry Muffins","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Make and share this Lemon Blueberry Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,3.0,197.5,4.7,1.1,16.3,294.1,35.5,1.2,18.4,3.7,"12.0","Lemon Blueberry Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. 2: Grease 12 (3 x 1 1/4-inch) muffin cups. 3: In a large bowl, stir together flour, the 2/3 cup sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. In another bowl, stir together yogurt, butter, eggs, lemon peel and vanilla until blended. 4: Make a well in center of dry ingredients; add the yogurt mixture and stir just to combine. Stir in the blueberries. 5: Spoon batter  into the muffin tins and sprinkle with the remaining 1 tablespoon of sugar. 6: Bake 20 to 25 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4602,"Quick Chicken Casserole","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Quick Chicken Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",5.0,1.0,231.3,8.2,1.6,64.9,398.4,32.8,1.5,0.9,6.5,"9.0","Quick Chicken Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine diced chicken, chopped celery and walnuts with  rice. In separate pan, mix chicken soup, salt and pepper,  lemon juice, mayonnaise and water. 2: Add to chicken mixture.  Gently stir in hard-cooked eggs. 3: Turn mixture into a greased  9-inch casserole dish. 4: Bake in very hot 450 degrees oven for 15  minutes, top with crushed potato chips and cook until mixture  is bubbly (about 5 more minutes).  **Can be made the day before and kept in refrigerator. 5: Heat thoroughly before adding potato chips. 6: **Leftover turkey can be substituted for chicken.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4604,"Quick Chicken Casserole II","PT35M","PT10M","PT45M","Make and share this Quick Chicken Casserole II recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",0.0,0.0,470.6,21.0,10.9,68.6,1188.3,50.4,4.2,11.5,22.5,"0.0","Quick Chicken Casserole II Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions on package. 2: Preheat oven to 350°F. 3: Cook chicken and broccoli until tender. 4: Mix all ingredients in large casserole. 5: Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and cook in oven for 35 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4605,"Titta Bere","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Titta Bere recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,574.0,27.1,16.6,91.2,159.0,84.9,8.5,65.4,4.8,"1.0","Titta Bere Recipe Instructions:  1: About 1 week before serving, cook the apple and pear  (peeled and chopped) with the sugar to mush. 2: Add the chopped  vanilla bean and jar of lingonberries. 3: Cook for a short time;  cool and store in refrigerator for a week (stir once in a  while). When ready to serve, beat one pint of whipped cream;  add lingonberry mixture to it and serve in sherbet glasses.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4606,"Tjock Pan Kaka (Swedish Thick Pancake)","PT30M","PT10M","PT40M","Make and share this Tjock Pan Kaka (Swedish Thick Pancake) recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",4.5,5.0,268.3,13.4,7.3,152.9,171.2,26.9,0.8,0.2,9.5,"6.0","Tjock Pan Kaka (Swedish Thick Pancake) Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan. 2: Stir together the eggs,  salt and flour. 3: Add milk, but do not beat. Pour into pan with  the melted butter. 4: Bake at 400 degrees until browned, about 30  minutes. 5: Will puff up like popovers. 6: Cut into serving slices  and serve immediately with strawberries,  lingonberries or  syrup.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4608,"Lingonberry Sauce (Lingonsylt)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Lingonberry Sauce (Lingonsylt) recipe from Food.com.","Vegan",0.0,1.0,1316.5,0.0,0.0,0.0,7.0,340.1,0.0,339.5,0.0,"0.0","Lingonberry Sauce (Lingonsylt) Recipe Instructions:  1: Pour off liquid on lingonberries. 2: Pick over berries carefully. 3: Place lingonberries in saucepan. 4: Add water. 5: Cover saucepan tightly and bring to boiling point. Cook slowly 15 minutes. 6: Remove from heat. Add sugar and stir until sugar is dissolved and sauce is cold.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4609,"Deep Dark Secret","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Deep Dark Secret recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,5578.8,248.7,124.1,883.8,3824.4,815.8,74.9,490.2,77.3,"1.0","Deep Dark Secret Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine dates, soda and butter. 2: Pour boiling water over; cool. 3: Add flour, sugar, salt, egg and vanilla. 4: Beat 1 minute; stir in nuts. 5: Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. 6: About 1 hour (or more) before serving, put on platter about half the cake broken in pieces. 7: Slice 3 or 4 bananas, 2 oranges, cut up (or use Mandarin oranges) and 1 pint raspberries, drained. 8: Add last half of cake pieces and pour over top 1 can crushed pineapple (juice and all). 9: Put in refrigerator and just before serving, top with 1 pint whipping cream.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4610,"Amish Stuffing (Dressing)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Amish Stuffing (Dressing) recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",0.0,0.0,306.6,11.6,3.6,89.8,465.1,33.7,2.1,3.3,16.1,"20.0","Amish Stuffing (Dressing) Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 F. 2: On 2 cookie sheets, toast the bread cubes for 15 minutes, or until the bread is golden brown. 3: Transfer to a very large mixer bowl. 4: Bone the chicken and very finely chop the meat, discarding the skin. (I do this in the food processor while chicken is still warm.) 5: Add the chopped vegetables and chicken meat to the bread, along with the seasonings. Toss. 6: In a medium bowl, beat the eggs;add the evaporated milk and broth. 7: Pour over the bread mixture and blend. 8: The mixture will be quite moist. Allow to stand 1 hour. 9: Preheat oven to 350 F 10: Transfer the dressing to an oiled 3 quart glass casserole that is 10 inches in diameter and 3 inches deep (at this point, dressing can be frozen for future use; thaw before baking.) 11: Bake dressing for 2 hours, or until the center of the");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4611,"Mesquite Grilled Cajun Turkey","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Mesquite Grilled Cajun Turkey recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",5.0,2.0,57.1,0.3,0.1,31.1,20.1,1.4,0.2,0.5,11.5,"8.0","Mesquite Grilled Cajun Turkey Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare grill using mesquite chips or coals. 2: Brush turkey with oil. 3: Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over turkey. 4: Place turkey on grill. 5: Cover grill and cook according to package directions. 6: Wrap in foil and let stand 10 to 15 minutes. 7: Remove netting from turkey and slice it.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4612,"Creamed Onions","PT1H","PT10M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Creamed Onions recipe from Food.com.","Onions",3.0,1.0,156.4,7.6,3.9,20.2,562.0,17.0,1.8,5.4,6.0,"6.0","Creamed Onions Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350F and butter a casserole dish. 2: Slice white onions to pretty much fill casserole. 3: Dilute celery soup with milk; add grated cheese and pour over onions. 4: Sprinkle top evenly with cracker crumbs. 5: Bake for 1 hour.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4613,"Creamed Onions III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Creamed Onions III recipe from Food.com.","Onions",4.0,1.0,1523.7,99.8,62.4,296.5,2125.6,126.7,10.7,28.5,38.0,"1.0","Creamed Onions III Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook onions until tender. 2: Add mushrooms; set aside. Make sauce of butter, cream cheese, flour, salt and milk. 3: Put onions and mushrooms in buttered casserole. Pour sauce over top. 4: Cover with cheese and cracker crumbs. 5: Bake at 400 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4616,"Lemon Cheesecake Bars","PT35M","PT15M","PT50M","Make and share this Lemon Cheesecake Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",3.5,2.0,208.0,13.1,5.9,44.0,93.6,21.2,0.6,16.4,2.6,"0.0","Lemon Cheesecake Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: In a food processor, whirl butter, sugar, flour, and nuts until a dough forms. 2: Or rub mixture with your fingers until fine crumbs form, then pat firmly  together. 3: Press mixture evenly into an 8- or 9-inch diameter baking pan with a  removable bottom. 4: Bake in a 350°F oven until a medium brown color, about 20  minutes. 5: Spread cheesecake topping (other ingredients mixed until smooth in food processor) evenly over crust. Bake until topping is set  in center when gently shaken, about 15 minutes. 6: Cool, cover and chill until  firm, at least one hour or up to 2 days. 7: Remove rim from pan and cut cookie into  12 wedges. 8: Sprinkle with lemon peel;  remove from pan with a spatula. 9: Serve, or  arrange in a single layer, cover, and chill up until the next day.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4618,"Corn Ball Fritters","PT5M","PT15M","PT20M","Make and share this Corn Ball Fritters recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",1.0,1.0,2012.6,33.5,11.8,669.2,3662.2,364.9,22.3,16.8,75.1,"0.0","Corn Ball Fritters Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat deep fryer to 375°F. 2: Stir all ingredients together. 3: If too thin, add more flour. 4: If too thick, add a little more milk. 5: You want mixture to be the consistency of a thin dough. 6: Drop by teaspoonfuls in hot oil. 7: Cook until golden brown on all sides. 8: Remove from oil to paper towels to drain. 9: Sprinkle with salt to desired taste.  Chicken bouillon cube can be omitted if chicken flavor is not desired or beef bouillon cube can be substituted. 10: Just dissolve cube first. For spicy cornball fritters, add 1/4 cup of diced jalapeno peppers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4619,"Steak Tartare","PT2H","PT15M","PT2H15M","Make and share this Steak Tartare recipe from Food.com.","Meat",3.5,3.0,474.5,32.6,12.6,138.8,393.3,1.0,0.2,0.1,40.1,"8.0","Steak Tartare Recipe Instructions:  1: Chop sirloin into cubes. 2: Place in food processor and chop/puree until meat is the consistency of ground beef. 3: Mix with remaining ingredients;  refrigerate for 2 hours. 4: Serving Suggestions:  Mound on a pretty plate and decorate the top with well-drained capers. 5: Serve with thinly sliced rye or party rye. Chop fine hard-boiled eggs and red onions. 6: Put in bowls alongside.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4620,"San Fernando Beans","0","PT0S","PT0S","I got this recipe from David Wade''s (a renowned chef) radio show last Spring.  He got the recipe from some place in San Fernando.  They are delicious and the flavor can be changed depending on the type of apples, spiciness of the sausage and amounts of chili powder.  Only problem I have is remembering to soak them overnight.","Beans",3.0,2.0,1616.1,50.8,18.1,213.1,8236.0,224.2,14.9,163.9,85.6,"1.0","San Fernando Beans Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash beans and soak overnight in cold water. 2: In the same water, bring to hard boil. 3: Cover and simmer, 1 - 2 hours. 4: Drain beans and keep warm. 5: Combine all rest of ingredients in pan and mix thoroughly  (you don''t have to precook anything).  Bring to a hard boil. 6: Mix in drained beans and simmer for 2 hours with a tight fitting lid.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4621,"Pork Cutlets","PT15M","PT15M","PT30M","Make and share this Pork Cutlets recipe from Food.com.","Pork",4.5,8.0,43.9,2.5,0.8,105.8,35.0,1.7,0.1,0.2,3.4,"4.0","Pork Cutlets Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat half butter and oil in heavy frying pan. 2: To prepare cutlets, I use dried breadcrumbs (seasoned if desired) on one plate, lightly beat a couple of eggs in a soup platter, roll cutlets in breadcrumbs on both sides, then in eggs, then again in the breadcrumbs making sure they are well covered. 3: Place in frying pan and fry on medium hot to avoid burning 5-7 minutes (depending how thick they are cut) on one side until golden in color, turn over and repeat. You can lift cutlets with spatula to let some fat get under the cutlets. 4: I make a cut with a sharp knife to make sure meat is well done and if necessary fry a couple more minutes on both sides. 5: I have also cut up onions and sauteed them right along with the pork cutlets. 6: After removing cutlets from pan (keep warm) I use a heaping tbs of flour, browning in the pan until golden, then add vegetable broth to make a gravy. 7: Use salt and pepper to taste. Serve over cutlets.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4622,"Bulgur Fruit Salad","PT15M","PT5M","PT20M","Make and share this Bulgur Fruit Salad recipe from Food.com.","Melons",0.0,0.0,134.1,0.8,0.2,0.3,463.7,30.2,7.1,8.4,4.0,"0.0","Bulgur Fruit Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Put the bulgur in a bowl and stir in the boiling bouillon. 2: Let stand 15 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed. 3: Chill if desired. 4: When ready to serve, stir in the remaining ingredients.");
