INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4624,"Polenta Triangles","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Polenta Triangles recipe from Food.com.","Low Cholesterol",4.5,7.0,40.6,2.3,1.5,8.3,248.3,2.5,0.3,1.1,2.5,"8.0","Polenta Triangles Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine grits and 1/2 cup broth; mix well and set aside. 2: Pour remaining 1 cup broth into heavy, large saucepan; bring to a boil. 3: Add garlic and moistened grits; mix well and return to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 20 minutes. 4: Remove from heat; add feta cheese. Stir until cheese is completely melted. 5: Add red pepper; mix well. 6: Spray 8-inch square pan with cooking spray. Spoon grits mixture into prepared pan. Press grits evenly into pan with wet fingertips. 7: Refrigerate until cold. 8: Preheat broiler. Spray baking sheet with cooking spray. 9: Turn polenta out onto cutting board and cut into 2-inch squares. Cut each square diagonally into 2 triangles. 10: Place polenta triangles on prepared baking sheet and spray tops lightly with cooking spray. Place under broiler until lightly browned and crisp. 11: Serve warm or at room temperature. Garnish with fresh oregano and chives if desired. 12: Exchanges  1 starch/bread.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4625,"Baked Tomatoes with Orzo and Olives","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Baked Tomatoes with Orzo and Olives recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",4.0,2.0,291.2,4.9,1.1,2.8,92.3,51.3,3.3,3.6,10.4,"8.0","Baked Tomatoes with Orzo and Olives Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees or grill 2: Halve and hollow tomatoes, place in a baking dish. 3: Mix the rest of the ingredients except the cheese together in a small bowl and season with salt and pepper to taste. 4: Carefully stuff the tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese. 5: Bake for 20 minutes and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4626,"Blueberry Lemon Bread","PT1H15M","PT10M","PT1H25M","Make and share this Blueberry Lemon Bread recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,56.0,2683.7,85.7,50.0,572.3,1164.8,452.1,10.9,290.0,38.5,"0.0","Blueberry Lemon Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 325 degrees F.  Butter 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2 loaf pan. 2: Combine first 3 ingredients in small bowl. 3: Using electric mixer, cream butter with 1 cup sugar in large bowl until mixture is light and fluffy. 4: Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. 5: Add lemon peel.  Mix in dry ingredients alternatively with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. 6: Fold in blue berries. 7: Spoon batter into prepared loaf pan. 8: Bake until golden brown and toothpick inserted into center comes out clean, about 1 hour 15 minutes. 9: Meanwhile, bring 1/3 cup sugar and lemon juice to boil in small saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves. 10: Pierce top of cake all over with toothpick.  Pour hot lemon mixture over loaf in pan. 11: Cool 30 minutes in pan on rack. 12: Turn bread out of pan and cool completely on rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4627,"Aloha Sweet Potatoes","PT10M","PT25M","PT35M","Make and share this Aloha Sweet Potatoes recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",0.0,0.0,136.9,2.9,1.8,7.6,62.6,26.9,2.2,12.4,1.1,"8.0","Aloha Sweet Potatoes Recipe Instructions:  1: Boil sweet potatoes in their jackets until tender, about 25 minutes. 2: Let cool, then peel and cut into 1/2 inch thick slices. 3: In a large skillet, melt pineapple preserves and butter; add sweet potatoes to skillet. 4: Cook gently; tossing lightly until sweet potatoes are glazed.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4628,"Chicken Lo Mein","0","PT30M","PT30M","Make and share this Chicken Lo Mein recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",5.0,4.0,361.3,7.8,1.5,84.2,688.5,48.2,3.6,3.9,23.6,"4.0","Chicken Lo Mein Recipe Instructions:  1: In a medium-sized bowl mix together the marinade ingredients. Add the meat and stir to cover. 2: Let sit for 30 minutes. Drain well. Discard the marinade. 3: In a small bowl mix together the sauce ingredients. Set aside. 4: In a wok or large skillet heat the vegetable oil over high heat. When the oil begins to smoke, add the marinated meat. Stir-fry until just cooked. 5: Push to one side and add the vegetables. Stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly. 6: Mix with the meat. Pour in the sauce. 7: When the sauce begins to bubble, add the noodles. Toss lightly to mix together. Let cook until the needles are hot.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4629,"Five-Spice Appetizer Meatballs","PT40M","PT10M","PT50M","Turn these miniature meatballs into a main dish by spooning several meatballs and sauce over hot cooked rice or noodles.","Meat",0.0,0.0,25.1,0.6,0.2,5.6,40.0,2.6,0.1,1.9,2.2,"0.0","Five-Spice Appetizer Meatballs Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large bowl combine egg white, bread crumbs, five-spice powder, and 1/2 teaspoon salt.  Add beef; mix well. 2: Shape into 48 1\ 3: ,  4: x10\ 5:  baking pan. 6: Bake in a 350 oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until no pink remains in center of meatballs. 7: Drain. 8: Meanwhile, in a large saucepan stir together orange juice, honey, cornstarch, soy sauce, and ginger. 9: Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. 10: Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.  Add sweet pepper and meatballs in saucepan ; cook and stir until heated through. 11: Keep warm in a fondue pot or chafing dish. 12: Serve with toothpicks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4630,"Egg-White French Toast","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Egg-White French Toast recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",5.0,30.0,182.4,2.9,1.1,4.9,339.0,28.6,1.2,5.5,9.4,"4.0","Egg-White French Toast Recipe Instructions:  1: In medium bowl beat egg whites well. Add milk, vanilla and cinnamon to egg whites and continue to beat. 2: Dip bread slices into batter and coat on both sides. 3: Cook one of the following ways: Place dipped bread in greased and heated skillet. Cook by turning a few times to brown. 4: Or, place dipped bread on greased or oiled baking sheet. Then broil in the oven (watching closely), turning only once. (Approximately 2-3 minutes each side when placed 5 inches from broiler top).");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4631,"Avocado ''N Everything Pizza","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Avocado ''N Everything Pizza recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",0.0,0.0,1962.4,114.0,26.3,49.4,4497.0,202.0,25.8,45.1,42.6,"1.0","Avocado ''N Everything Pizza Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 425F. 2: Stir together buttermilk mix and water with fork in small bowl. 3: Pat or roll into 12-inch circle on ungreased baking sheet or pizza pan. 4: Mix together tomato sauce and green onion; spread over pizza dough. 5: Top with cheese, mushrooms, olives and tomato slices. 6: Drizzle olive oil over top. 7: Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until edge of crust is golden brown. 8: Remove pizza from oven and arrange avocado slices over top. 9: Garnish with basil leaves and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4632,"Peppercorn Dressing","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Peppercorn Dressing recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,2.0,378.5,34.9,20.2,90.3,1370.0,14.7,2.1,8.4,5.5,"1.0","Peppercorn Dressing Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve bouillon cube in warm water. 2: Combine all ingredients (except milk) in medium bowl and whisk to blend. 3: Put in tightly-lidded bowl and refrigerate three hours. 4: Should keep for 10 days. 5: If mixture is too thick, add a few drops of milk.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4634,"Crepes Suzette II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Crepes Suzette II recipe from Food.com.","Breakfast",4.5,2.0,491.5,31.1,17.9,283.2,149.9,41.1,1.6,13.0,12.6,"4.0","Crepes Suzette II Recipe Instructions:  1: Crepes: Whisk together or combine the flour, eggs, milk and salt in a blender or food processor. Blend just until smooth. 2: Add melted butter and combine. The batter should be the consistency of light cream. 3: Let sit in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour or overnight. 4: Lightly oil 1 (6-inch) crepe pan and set over medium heat. 5: Pour about 1/4 cup batter into pan and swirl until the pan is coated. Cook crepes until the top begins to look dry, about 60 seconds. 6: Turn and cook the other side 30 seconds, wiping the pan with an oiled paper towel if crepes begin to stick. 7: Sauce: In large skillet, melt the butter. When foamy, add sugar and stir until dissolved. 8: Add rind and juice; bring to a simmer. Turn heat to lowest settings. 9: Fold each crepe in half and place 2 at a time in the warm sauce. Using tongs or spatula, fold crepes in half again. 10: Repeat until all crepes have been added. Work quickly so the first crepes do not absorb all the sauce. 11: Warm liqueur briefly and pour over the pan of crepes. Using a long match, ignite the sauce. Remove pan from heat. When flames subside, place crepes on dessert plates. 12: Dust with confectioners sugar; garnish with orange slices and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4635,"Quick Mix Steamed Chocolate Pudding","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Quick Mix Steamed Chocolate Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,304.2,11.7,2.9,29.6,560.3,48.9,1.6,25.1,5.4,"8.0","Quick Mix Steamed Chocolate Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare the cake mix with the egg and milk or water according to directions on 2: package. Pour into a greased 2 to 2 1/2 qt pudding mold and cover with a lid,  foil or greased double wax paper. 3: Place the mold in a sauce pan of boiling  water and the level of the water half way up mold during cooking. 4: Steam for 1  1/2 hours. 5: Unmold the pudding while hot and serve with cream, ice cream, or  custard. 6: NOTE: When cooking for smaller numbers, make up the whole cake mix as directed,  put pour only half the cake batter   into a 1 1/2 qt mold and steam for 1 hour. 7: Alternately, fill individual molds and steam for 20-25 minutes. 8: Bake remaining  cake batter.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4636,"Quick Mix Steamed Golden Pudding","PT1H30M","PT0S","PT1H30M","Make and share this Quick Mix Steamed Golden Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,336.9,9.1,1.9,30.9,456.9,60.5,0.7,31.3,4.4,"8.0","Quick Mix Steamed Golden Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Place syrup in bottom of pudding mold before adding batter. 2: Prepare the cake  mix with the egg and milk or water according to directions on package. 3: Pour  into a greased 2 to 2 1/2 qt pudding mold and cover with a lid, foil or greased  double wax paper. 4: NOTE: When cooking for smaller numbers, make up the whole  cake mix as directed, put pour only half the cake batter into a 1 1/2 qt mold  and steam for 1 hour. 5: Alternately, fill in- dividual molds and steam for  20-25 minutes. 6: Bake remaining cake batter.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4637,"Quick Mix Steamed Upside-Down Pudding","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Quick Mix Steamed Upside-Down Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,363.2,11.9,3.7,38.6,473.5,60.3,0.9,36.0,4.5,"8.0","Quick Mix Steamed Upside-Down Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix butter with brown sugar an 2: d spread in bottom of pudding mold. 3: Add fruit or nuts of choice. Prepare the cake mix with the egg and milk or  water according to directions on package. Pour into a greased 2 to 2 1/2 qt  pudding mold over fruit/nut mixture and cover with a lid, foil o greased double  wax paper. 4: Place the mold in a sauce pan of boiling water and keep the level  of the water half way up mold during cooking. 5: Steam for 1 1/2 hours. 6: Unmold t  he  pudding while hot and serve with cream, ice cream, or custard. 7: NOTE: When  cooking for smaller numbers, make up the whole cake mix as directed, put pour  only half the cake batter into a 1 1/2 qt mold and steam for 1 hour. 8: Alternately, fill individual molds and steam for 20-25 minutes. 9: Bake remaining  cake batter.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4638,"Steamed Treacle Sponge Pudding","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Steamed Treacle Sponge Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",3.0,1.0,831.2,39.6,23.6,252.1,1128.6,112.1,1.5,51.4,10.5,"4.0","Steamed Treacle Sponge Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Grease the bowl, and foil. 2: Get your steamer prepared and  start it heating. 3: Put 3 Tbsp golden syrup in bottom of bowl. 4: In a large bowl, sift flour and baking powder into it. 5: Add  butter, eggs, sugar and black treacle.  Beat for 2 minutes with  a hand mixer. 6: Spoon mixture into  greased bowl and level  with  the back of your spoon. 7: To serve loosen pudding with a knife and invert onto a warm   plate. Pour Extra 3 Tbsp golden syrup over top and serve with  custard or creme'' fraiche.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4640,"Cranberry Relish II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cranberry Relish II recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",0.0,0.0,421.6,11.1,1.1,0.0,16.4,82.8,2.7,74.8,3.6,"0.0","Cranberry Relish II Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine cranberries, sugar and water. 2: Cook over low heat 15 minutes, stirring frequently. 3: Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients. 4: Cover and refrigerate. You may put in jars.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4641,"Beef Liver with Onion Gravy","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Beef Liver with Onion Gravy recipe from Food.com.","Beef Organ Meats",5.0,3.0,813.6,30.4,3.8,1.9,3134.6,118.9,6.0,8.0,15.8,"1.0","Beef Liver with Onion Gravy Recipe Instructions:  1: Coat liver in flour and sear in a skillet with oil, browning on both sides quickly. 2: Add onion soup mix and enough water to cover liver and cook until tender. 3: Remove liver from pan and make gravy, return liver to pan to coat with gravy. 4: Serve with boiled potatoes This is the only way my children would eat liver!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4642,"Turkey Scaloppine With Dijon Sauce","PT5M","PT5M","PT10M","Make and share this Turkey Scaloppine With Dijon Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",4.0,1.0,168.8,13.4,1.7,0.0,87.2,13.4,0.3,12.4,0.5,"4.0","Turkey Scaloppine With Dijon Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine first seven ingredients. 2: Brush onto turkey scallopini. 3: Grill over medium heat 2 to 4 minutes each side or until no longer pink in centre. 4: As an alternative, the turkey can be pan-fried in 15 mL (1 tbsp) vegetable  oil for approximately 2 minutes each side.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4644,"Baked Spinach Artichoke Dip","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Baked Spinach Artichoke Dip recipe from Food.com.","Mexican",0.0,0.0,301.3,18.5,8.8,46.9,961.7,17.3,6.5,1.5,18.7,"0.0","Baked Spinach Artichoke Dip Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). 2: In a medium bowl combine the spinach, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, artichokes, pepper, lemon juice and mozzarella cheese; blend thoroughly. Place in an ovenproof dish. 3: Top with the reserved 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. 4: Bake until hot and bubbly, about 15 to 25 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4645,"Honey Salmon","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Honey Salmon recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,39.0,673.9,50.7,8.8,93.5,271.8,19.6,0.6,17.8,35.6,"2.0","Honey Salmon Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine the oil, honey, mustard, garlic, cayenne, coriander, lemon juice and salt in a shallow dish. Mix well. 2: Add the salmon and let marinate for 30 minutes at room temp. 3: Place the salmon on a med.-hot fire, grill the salmon five to six minutes per side or until they flake easily. 4: Remove from grill and garnish with the dill sprigs.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4646,"Cucumber-Mint Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cucumber-Mint Salad recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,6.0,26.5,0.1,0.0,0.0,293.9,5.8,0.7,3.1,0.7,"0.0","Cucumber-Mint Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Peel cucumber and chop into 1/4-inch cubes. 2: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix. 3: Serve at room temperature.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4647,"Flank Steak With Lime-Chipotle Sauce","PT15M","PT1H","PT1H15M","Make and share this Flank Steak With Lime-Chipotle Sauce recipe from Food.com.","Steak",5.0,40.0,487.8,10.7,4.0,77.1,326.0,78.6,1.6,70.9,26.1,"0.0","Flank Steak With Lime-Chipotle Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix honey with chilies, mustard, lime juice, garlic, cumin, allspice, and cilantro. 2: Season to taste with salt and pepper. 3: Marinate steak at least 1 hour. 4: Drain off marinade into small sauce pan and simmer. 5: Grill or BBQ steak, basting with marinade. 6: Slice steak against the grain and pour remaining marinade over meat.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4648,"Shoo-Fly Pie","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","This recipe has been in my wife''s family for generations.  It is from her Great  Grandmother (or perhaps it was her Great, Great Grandmother, I''m not sure).","Pie",5.0,2.0,561.7,18.8,4.7,0.0,282.6,94.5,1.9,51.3,5.1,"6.0","Shoo-Fly Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Make crumbs by combining flour, sugar and shortening. 2: Line pie pan with pastry. 3: Dissolve baking soda in hot water and combine with molasses. 4: Pour into shell. 5: Top with crumbs and bake at 350 degree s until firm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4649,"Tater Tots Chicken Casserole","PT40M","PT10M","PT50M","Make and share this Tater Tots Chicken Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",5.0,5.0,929.5,55.7,16.2,170.1,1288.5,58.0,7.9,2.3,50.6,"0.0","Tater Tots Chicken Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375°F. 2: In a non-stick skillet over medium heat, brown the ground chicken and the onion until the chicken is no longer pink. 3: Stir in pepper, water and mushroom soup and heat till bubbling. 4: Add frozen vegetables and stir cook until the vegetables are warm. 5: Pour the mixture into a 2 quart (2L) casserole. Arrange tater gems in a single layer on top of the chicken mixture. Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes or until the tater gems are crisp and the chicken mixture is bubbling.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4650,"Eggless Homemade Ice Cream","PT4H","PT5M","PT4H5M","This is a fabulous recipe!  We had to come up with it a few years ago  because my sister was allergic to eggs.","Frozen Desserts",4.5,4.0,3577.6,93.5,57.9,355.5,2800.4,610.2,0.0,490.7,83.3,"0.0","Eggless Homemade Ice Cream Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix together and put in ice cream freezer until done to desirable  thickness. 2: *Fun for the kids:  Blend all ingredients in blender. 3: Divide mixture among  Ziploc sandwich baggies. 4: Seal the baggies; then place them into gallon size  baggies. 5: Pour dry ice into the gallon baggies making sure to completely  surround the smaller baggies. 6: Seal the gallon baggies. 7: Then let the  children squeeze and punch on the baggies continuously. 8: You''ll have to fill  up the dry ice a few times before getting it to desired consistency, but you  do that in an ice cream freezer anyway. 9: Besides this is an excellent  learning tool for chemistry and it''s fun for the kids, too!");
