INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4697,"Shoepeg Corn Casserole","PT45M","PT10M","PT55M","This is an awesome recipe my sister shared with me.  I absolutely love it!  and it''s even great leftover (if there IS any!)","Corn",4.5,9.0,557.2,36.3,15.2,54.6,1028.8,51.3,3.9,2.9,9.6,"8.0","Shoepeg Corn Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 325F and spray a 13 x 9 baking dish with cooking spray. 2: Mix first 8 ingredients together; add pepper to taste. 3: Pour into prepared baking dish. 4: Mix butter and Ritz crackers together; sprinkle evenly over top of casserole. 5: Bake uncovered for 45 minutes, or until bubbly and golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4698,"Bourbon Mustard Chicken","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Bourbon Mustard Chicken recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",4.5,6.0,287.4,13.6,4.2,54.0,848.1,15.2,0.7,13.8,16.0,"4.0","Bourbon Mustard Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: Place chicken between 2 sheets of waxed paper; pound to 1/4\ 2: ,  3: ,  4: ,  5: ,  6: ,  7: ,  8: Remove chicken to a serving platter, and keep warm. Drain and discard pan drippings. 9: Add reserved marinade to a skillet; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. 10: Pour sauce over chicken.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4699,"Sweet Potato Casserole III","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Make and share this Sweet Potato Casserole III recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,12.0,391.3,19.2,9.1,81.6,166.1,53.1,2.3,40.8,3.9,"8.0","Sweet Potato Casserole III Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and milk; mix well. 2: Spoon into a 2 quart casserole. 3: Combine topping ingredients and sprinkle over sweet  potatoes. 4: Casserole can be refrigerated at this point for up to 2 days. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until heated through. 5: Makes 8 sinful servings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4700,"Pigeon with Mushrooms","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pigeon with Mushrooms recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",0.0,0.0,2470.5,201.0,74.4,786.7,511.8,6.0,0.2,0.0,147.9,"1.0","Pigeon with Mushrooms Recipe Instructions:  1: Drain, wash and stuff pigeons with crumbs and chopped fat pork, seasoned with onion juice, salt and pepper. 2: Prepare a bed of vegetables - minced carrot, onion, celery and parsley. 3: Lay the pigeons upon it; add stock of butter and water; cover and cook gently 1 hour or until tender. 4: Dish the birds and keep hot; rub the gravy through a sieve into a saucepan. 5: Season to taste and add cut mushrooms. 6: Simmer 5 minutes; thicken with butter mixed with flour. 7: Cook until smooth and pour over the pigeons.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4702,"Stuffed Jalapenos","PT10M","PT15M","PT25M","Make and share this Stuffed Jalapenos recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,4.0,73.3,4.5,2.6,12.7,432.2,6.5,2.5,3.4,3.0,"0.0","Stuffed Jalapenos Recipe Instructions:  1: Rinse and drain jalapenos. Slit lengthwise on one side. Remove seeds and veins, leaving stem attached. 2: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. 3: Beat in Cheddar cheese and green onion. 4: Stuff each pepper with part of mixture. 5: Arrange on heatproof serving plate or baking sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes, or until cheese melts. 6: Top each pepper with a pimento strip.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4703,"Chocolate Truffles With Rum","0","PT15M","PT15M","Make and share this Chocolate Truffles With Rum recipe from Food.com.","Candy",5.0,1.0,1716.7,144.3,88.6,309.1,83.7,124.4,10.0,105.5,10.8,"0.0","Chocolate Truffles With Rum Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine cream, butter and sugar in saucepan until hot. Stir in chocolate chips until melted. 2: Stir in flavoring and transfer into bowl. 3: Chill, stirring often, about one hour. 4: Drop from teaspoon to waxed paper and chill 1/2 hour or until firm. 5: Roll into balls. 6: Roll in cornstarch and brush off excess, then dip into melted dipping chocolate, or roll in chopped nuts, unsweetened cocoa powder or serve in small tin cups.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4704,"Fofo - Fufu","0","PT0S","PT20M",""foo-foo" is an African meal made with noodley mashed potatoes made with way too much starch to make it sticky, with killer spicy beef mixed in, all eaten with the hands.  Fufu (from Ghana):","Potato",0.0,0.0,257.0,0.2,0.1,0.0,56.1,59.8,4.2,2.5,5.0,"2.0","Fofo - Fufu Recipe Instructions:  1: Warm a medium saucepan with 200 mL (7 oz) of the boiling water. 2: In a small jug blend the potato flour with the 200 mL (7 oz) of lukewarm water (mixing some of the boiling water with part of the cold water; the water must not be hot or it will cook the starch to form a creamy mixture. Empty the water from the warmed saucepan. 3: Pour the potato flakes into the saucepan and add the remaining boiling water, enough to fully cover the potato flakes. 4: Do not stir yet. Using a wooden spoon , stir the potato flour mixture in the jug and quickly add this to the saucepan. 5: Speed is of the essence here, as is dexterity! Stir the 2 mixtures together vigorously, pulling the dough in from the centre against the inside of the saucepan with one hand and gripping the pan firmly with the other. 6: When the dough is firm and smooth, moisten a small bowl with small quantities of the cold water and scoop the dough into this bowl, either as one large ball or individual balls, and serve with soup. 7: Serves 2");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4705,"Cornmeal and Blueberry Scones","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cornmeal and Blueberry Scones recipe from Food.com.","Scones",0.0,0.0,444.6,20.7,12.5,52.6,492.6,59.0,2.8,10.3,7.0,"5.0","Cornmeal and Blueberry Scones Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees and line a baking sheet with parchment  paper. 2: In the bowl of a food processor combine flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and baking powder. Pulse to combine. 3: Add butter and pulse until mixture resembles coarse meal. 4: Add cornmeal and blueberries. 5: Add 6 tablespoons milk and pulse. Add more milk, 1 tablespoon at a time, until dough forms a ball. 6: Remove dough to a lightly floured surface and form into five, 3 inch rounds 1 inch thick. 7: Place on prepared pan and bake until golden, about 35 - 40 minutes. 8: Remove to a wire rack to cool slightly. Serve warm.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4706,"Merry Cherry - Nut Yeast Scones","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Merry Cherry - Nut Yeast Scones recipe from Food.com.","Scones",0.0,0.0,4751.4,254.7,58.6,19.6,7536.0,526.0,24.6,35.1,95.4,"1.0","Merry Cherry - Nut Yeast Scones Recipe Instructions:  1: In a small bowl combine warm water, yeast and sugar and let proof 10 minutes. 2: In a large bowl combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. 3: Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. 4: Gradually add in yeast mixture and buttermilk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. 5: Stir in cherries and walnuts, cover and chill at least 1 hour or up to 48 hours. 6: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. 7: Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead 3 -  4 times. Flatten to 1/2 inch thickness and cut with a 2 inch round cutter. 8: Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake until golden, about 10 minutes. 9: Serve hot with Mock Devonshire Cream and, if desired, jelly. 10: MOCK DEVONSHIRE CREAM:  In a mixer bowl, beat cream cheese and butter at high speed until fluffy. 11: Add Cool Whip and beat at medium speed until blended.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4708,"Rum Truffles","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Rum Truffles recipe from Food.com.","Candy",0.0,0.0,3998.7,397.4,225.6,652.1,264.5,174.6,63.0,51.0,60.9,"1.0","Rum Truffles Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring cream to a boil. 2: Add rum or cognac and simmer about 5 minutes. 3: Add chocolate and melt, stirring continuosly for about 2-3 minutes, then add nuts.  Blend in well. 4: Turn off heat and let cool for 10 minutes, then add sweeteners.  Mix well. 5: Line baking sheet with wax paper. 6: Spread chocolate mixture evenly on  sheet. Cover with foil and put in refrigerator. 7: Let set for several hours or overnight. 8: When ready to serve, cut chocolate spread into squares and put in tin container.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4709,"Broccoli with Sour Cream","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Broccoli with Sour Cream recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",3.5,3.0,1273.7,69.4,38.1,169.5,1421.3,127.4,23.3,26.7,48.9,"0.0","Broccoli with Sour Cream Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut off the thickest stalks of the broccoli. 2: Use a flat microwave dish. 3: Place broccoli on the plate with the stalks to the out side. Cover and cook on HIGH 8 - 12 minutes until tender crisp. 4: Drain. 5: Spoon the sour cream over the broccoli. 6: Sprinkle with pepper, then add the breadcrumbs. 7: Top with the cheese.  Cook uncovered on MEDIUM 3 - 4 minutes, or place under a grill for 1 - 2 minutes until bubbly. 8: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4710,"Cranberry-Orange Relish II","0","PT0S","PT0S","This relish is chunky and tartly suited to turkey, whether it''s hot on the big day or cold in sandwiches. The recipe makes enough to enjoy with a really big bird.","Fruit",4.0,2.0,675.1,19.4,1.8,0.0,27.4,131.2,8.2,112.8,5.7,"0.0","Cranberry-Orange Relish II Recipe Instructions:  1: In food processor or grinder, chop cranberries and apple. 2: In bowl combine cranberry mixture with sugar, pecans, raisins, marmalade, lemon rind, juice and  cinnamon (if using). 3: Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours or, better still, up to 1 week.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4712,"Mock Pecan Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Mock Pecan Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",3.0,1.0,251.6,2.0,0.6,79.3,45.8,55.7,1.9,50.2,4.3,"8.0","Mock Pecan Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. 2: Beat sugar, salt and eggs together. 3: Add beans. 4: Mix well. 5: Let ingredients stand for 1/2 hour. 6: Pour into pie shell. 7: Bake at 425  until crust begins to brown, then reduce temp to 375 degrees and bake 30 additional minutes or until center of pie is set.  Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.");
