INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4714,"Pineapple Cheese Ball","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pineapple Cheese Ball recipe from Food.com.","Pineapple",5.0,6.0,1974.1,165.9,104.0,517.0,1626.3,92.4,9.2,57.1,43.6,"0.0","Pineapple Cheese Ball Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix the package of ranch dressing mix with the softened cream cheese until well mixed. 2: Then add 1/2 can of crushed pineapple, (no juice), the 2 stalks of green onion chopped and the shredded cheese.  Mix well and cool in the fridge for 20 minutes. 3: Turn out onto a cheese board or platter.  Mound it in the center and shape into a ball with a spoon. 4: If you like you can cover the ball with sliced almonds, sprinkle with dill weed, parsley or paprika. 5: Chill completely before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4715,"Honey Pumpkin Pie II","PT45M","PT0S","PT45M","Make and share this Honey Pumpkin Pie II recipe from Food.com.","Pie",2.0,1.0,620.4,22.2,7.5,111.3,639.5,98.8,2.2,68.8,10.8,"8.0","Honey Pumpkin Pie II Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix the sugar, salt, flour and spices. 2: Add slightly beaten eggs and pumpkin with honey. 3: Blend well. 4: Stir in milk and water. 5: Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells. 6: Bake at 450 degrees for 20 minutes; then reduce heat to 350 degrees and continue baking 25 minutes. 7: HONEY PECAN PUMPKIN PIE 2 cup cooked or canned pumpkin 1 cup honey 1/2 cup brown sugar 1/2 teaspoons salt 1/2 teaspoons ginger 1 teaspoons cinnamon 1/4 teaspoons nutmeg 3 eggs, slightly beaten 1 can evaporated milk 1 cup chopped pecans. 8: Mix pumpkin, honey, sugar, salt and spices. 9: Add eggs and milk; mix and pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with pecans. 10: Bake at 450 degrees for 10 minutes. 11: Reduce heat to 325 degrees and bake 45 minutes or until set. 12: HONEY  PUMPKIN PIE 2 large eggs 1/4 cup honey 1 cup evaporated skimmed milk 1 (16 oz.) can cooked pumpkin 1 1/2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice 1/4 teaspoons salt 2 teaspoons unsweetened orange juice concentrate 1 (9-inch) unbaked pastry crust. 13: In mixing bowl with electric mixer, beat eggs until foaming. 14: Add honey, milk, pumpkin spice, salt and juice concentrate. Beat until well blended. 15: Pour pumpkin filling into unbaked pie shell. 16: Bake at 375 degrees for 60 to 65 minutes. 17: Serves 8.");
