INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4919,"Curried Pork Chops","PT10M","PT20M","PT30M","Make and share this Curried Pork Chops recipe from Food.com.","Pork",4.5,10.0,416.1,27.2,8.4,68.8,66.1,24.1,2.7,11.2,19.9,"4.0","Curried Pork Chops Recipe Instructions:  1: Stir together flour, seasoned salt and black pepper in a shallow dish. 2: Dip pork  chops into flour mixture, coating both sides. 3: Heat Wesson Oil in large skillet.  Cook and stir onion and apple in hot oil until onion is tender. 4: Remove from skillet; set aside. Cook chops in hot skillet until lightly brown on both sides. 5: Remove chops from skillet.   Drain off fat.  Stir Hunt''s Ready Tomato Sauce Chunky Special, raisins, curry powder, sugar and ground red pepper into skillet.  Return chops, apple, and  onion to skillet.  Bring to boiling; reduce heat.  Simmer, covered, 10-15 minutes or until pork chops are tender and no longer pink.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4920,"Crock Pot Chicken Taco Meat","PT6H","PT0S","PT6H","I adopted this recipe from the Recipezaar account, and I''m so glad that I did. This has become a regular addition to my OAMC and I have created a public cookbook filled with recipe ideas using this recipe. This is a three-ingredient wonder that''s easy (5 minutes of your time), delicious and versatile.","Chicken Breast",5.0,316.0,71.4,1.6,0.4,36.3,239.3,0.7,0.2,0.3,12.7,"8.0","Crock Pot Chicken Taco Meat Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve taco seasoning into chicken broth. 2: Place chicken breasts in crock pot and pour chicken broth over. 3: Cover and cook on low for 6-8 hours. 4: With two forks, shred the chicken meat into bite-size pieces. 5: To freeze, place shredded meat into freezer bags with the juices. 6: Press out all the air and seal.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4922,"Pizza with Stilton and Caramelized Onions","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pizza with Stilton and Caramelized Onions recipe from Food.com.","European",0.0,0.0,1428.3,76.7,28.9,94.3,1304.6,59.4,2.4,37.7,20.4,"1.0","Pizza with Stilton and Caramelized Onions Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine 2 Tbsp olive oil and garlic in a bowl; set aside. 2: Melt butter with 1  Tbsp olive oil in a large heavy skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion, 3/4 cup wine, vinegar, sugar, and Sherry. Boil until almost all of the liquid evaporates, stirring often, about ten minutes. 3: Add 1 cup wine, 1/2 cup at a time, boiling until liquid evaporates after each addition. 4: Add 1/2 cup of wine; cook until onions are brown and the mixture is syrupy, stirring often, about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. 5: Preheat oven to 350 F. 6: Brush Boboli crust with garlic oil. Cut the crust into squares or diamonds approximately 2\ 7: ,  8: ,  9: ,  10: , ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4923,"Smoked Salmon and Brie Pizza","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Smoked Salmon and Brie Pizza recipe from Food.com.","Very Low Carbs",3.0,3.0,730.3,62.3,24.3,134.1,1421.2,2.3,0.2,1.3,40.2,"0.0","Smoked Salmon and Brie Pizza Recipe Instructions:  1: To prepare the Brie, discard the rind and cut the cheese in small pieces. 2: Slice the onion very thinly and quarter the slices. Separate the onion pieces. 3: Cut the salmon into small pieces. 4: Prepare the dough and preheat the oven as directed in the basic recipe. Shape the pizza dough. 5: Divide the dough and roll into small pies, about 3 to 4 inches  in diameter. Prick dough all over with the tines of a fork, then brush with  olive oil. 6: Transfer the pie to the preheated baking surface and bake until the crust just begins to brown, about 6 minutes. 7: Remove from the oven and cover with the cheese, leaving a 1/2 inch border around the edges. 8: Arrange the salmon and onion on top and drizzle evenly with olive oil. 9: Return to the oven and bake  until the crust is golden brown and puffy, the cheese begins to melt and the salmon is heated through, about 4 minutes. 10: Remove from the oven to a cutting tray or board and lightly brush the crust with olive oil. 11: Garnish with the dill. 12: Slice and serve immediately. 13: Recipe found on the Chatelaine recipe forum site.   - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4928,"Pseudo Cinncinnati Chili","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pseudo Cinncinnati Chili recipe from Food.com.","Tex Mex",0.0,0.0,1183.9,86.0,35.4,119.8,122.6,70.1,9.7,3.3,32.6,"4.0","Pseudo Cinncinnati Chili Recipe Instructions:  1: Bring 2 1/2 quarts of unsalted water to a boil in a soup pot. When  the water  reaches a rapid boil, add the spaghetti and cook until tender 7  to 9 minutes. 2: Meanwhile heat the oil on high heat just until hot. Using your  fingers crumble  the ground beef into the  skillet. Immediately wash your  hands with soap and hot water. 3: Peel and coarsely chop the onion, adding it to the skillet as you chop. 4: Stir the meat occasionally. 5: Rinse and seed the  pepper and cut ii into 1/4 inch  dice. Cook, stirring frequently until the ground beef is finely crumbled  and  completely browned, about 2 minutes Reduce the heat to medium. 6: Add the tomato  sauce, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, cumin, cinnamon, allspice and cloves. 7: Stir to mix well. 8: Reduce the  heat to simmer, and continue to cook,  stirring from time to time, until the  pasta is done. Season with cayenne pepper and slat, to taste if desired. 9: Meanwhile, rinse and drain the beans, and place  in a microwaveable  safe bowl. 10: Cover with a paper towel and microwave 1 minutes  at high or  until heated through. 11: To serve, divide the spaghetti among 4 serving bowls. 12: Top each  serving with chili, 1/2 cup kidney beans and 1 tablespoon  shredded cheese.  Serve at once.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4929,"Apricot Glazed Ham Patties","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apricot Glazed Ham Patties recipe from Food.com.","Pork",5.0,1.0,304.8,10.7,4.3,128.1,1911.1,21.7,0.4,12.4,29.9,"6.0","Apricot Glazed Ham Patties Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 350 F. 2: Combine ham with crumbs, milk, eggs, onion, cheese,  Worcestershire, 1 tsp mustard, sage and pepper. Shape into 6 patties. 3: Place in shallow baking dish; bake 30 minutes. 4: Combine preserves, vinegar and remaining mustard; brush on patties. 5: Bake 10 more minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4930,"Bleu Cheese & Port Bread","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Bleu Cheese & Port Bread recipe from Food.com.","Yeast Breads",5.0,3.0,2133.7,53.9,18.7,64.2,4257.6,340.2,14.6,32.0,56.3,"1.0","Bleu Cheese & Port Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Place all ingredients in bread machine pan, in order given Can be made with the regular and rapid bake cycles. 2: No need to use an expensive port here, just one with good flavour. 3: The sharper the blue cheese, the stronger the flavour in the  bread. 4: We like the Danish blue best. As with all cheese recipes, loaf appearance may vary but the flavour is worth it.  This moderately textured loaf makes great croutons and wonderful toast points for parties - delicious served warm with your favourite steak.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4931,"Broccoli En Bleu Ala Rick","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Broccoli En Bleu Ala Rick recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,6.0,368.7,24.7,15.2,68.5,952.9,23.6,5.0,2.9,15.9,"4.0","Broccoli En Bleu Ala Rick Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: Melt together the cream cheese, blue cheese, butter, salt and flour. 3: Add milk  and bring to a boil. 4: Add broccoli and mix well. 5: Transfer to a 1 quart greased  casserole and top with bread crumbs. 6: Bake 1/2 hour. 7: Jo Anne in Spokane");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4932,"Cherry Cheese Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cherry Cheese Salad recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",5.0,1.0,136.0,8.9,3.1,9.5,193.2,10.8,1.3,7.8,3.7,"0.0","Cherry Cheese Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: In a small bowl, combine onion with 2 cups water and lemon juice; chill 15 to 30 minutes. Drain well. 2: To make dressing, whisk together Merlot, fruity extra-virgin olive oil, raspberry vinegar, honey, and Dijon mustard. 3: In a large boil, combine onion, salad greens, radicchio, cherries, and dressing; mix lightly. 4: Sprinkle salad with cheese and season with salt and pepper to taste.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4933,"Roasted Parsnips and Onions","PT45M","PT10M","PT55M","Make and share this Roasted Parsnips and Onions recipe from Food.com.","Low Protein",4.0,1.0,192.6,7.3,1.1,0.0,16.5,31.4,7.7,10.3,2.7,"4.0","Roasted Parsnips and Onions Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat the oven to 425F. 2: In a roasting pan, combine the parsnips, onions and rosemary. 3: Season with salt and pepper. 4: Add the olive oil and toss until the vegetables are thoroughly coated. 5: Roast for 40 to 45 minutes, shaking the pan every 15 minutes, until the vegetables are deep amber.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4934,"Christmas Rye Bread","PT45M","PT2H","PT2H45M","Make and share this Christmas Rye Bread recipe from Food.com.","Yeast Breads",0.0,0.0,1884.2,18.5,2.4,0.0,732.0,376.7,22.9,54.8,41.2,"0.0","Christmas Rye Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine the stout, seed, and oil being sure they are at a warmish room temperature. 2: Pour into large mixing bowl and add syrup, orange rind, sugar, and salt. Mix well. 3: Add 2 cups of flour and one cup of the rye  flour. Beat until smooth. 4: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to mixture. Beat until thoroughly mixed. 5: Add remaining flour. 6: Turn dough out on lightly floured bread board or pastry cloth and knead until smooth and elastic, approximately 20 minutes. 7: Place in greased bowl, cover with dish towel and let rise until double in bulk. 8: Punch down, let rise again until double in bulk, 1 to 1 1/2 hours. 9: Divide the dough into 2 portions, shape into loaves and place in a greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan. 10: Prick loaves 5 to 6 times with fork. 11: Bake at 350 for 45 to 50 minutes. 12: Remove from oven, brush with hot water. Cool on cake rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4936,"Barbecue Chicken Pizza","PT14M","PT0S","PT14M","Make and share this Barbecue Chicken Pizza recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,9.0,333.8,22.3,11.8,85.6,469.5,7.5,0.9,2.8,25.4,"4.0","Barbecue Chicken Pizza Recipe Instructions:  1: Place baking sheet on rack in oven and preheat oven to 450 degrees. 2: Toss the chicken with 1/4 cup barbecue sauce. Spread remaining barbecue sauce on pizza crust. Spread half of cheese on crust. Arrange chicken evenly over crust. Sprinkle with remaining cheese, red onion, green onion, and cilantro over pizza. 3: Transfer pizza to hot baking sheet. Bake until  bottom of crust is crisp and cheese on top melts, about 14 minutes. 4: Let pizza stand 5 minutes before cutting.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4938,"Mary Krull''s Rosemary Onion Tarts (Pizza)","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Mary Krull''s Rosemary Onion Tarts (Pizza) recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,306.3,10.4,1.3,0.0,591.0,46.5,3.2,3.2,7.4,"4.0","Mary Krull''s Rosemary Onion Tarts (Pizza) Recipe Instructions:  1: For the dough: Sprinkle the yeast over the water and let it sit for 10 minutes. 2: Add flour, salt and rosemary, stirring to form a dough. 3: Turn the  dough out onto a lightly floured board and knead a few minutes. 4: Transfer  to a greased bowl, cover tightly with plastic wrap and let rise in a warm place for 1 hour. 5: For the topping: In a bowl combine the vinegar, ricotta and garlic and set the mixture aside. In a saute pan, heat the oil, and when it is hot, add the shallots, onions and rosemary. 6: Turn down the heat and cook 20 minutes or until the onions are softened. 7: Roast the pepper under the broiler until it is evenly charred. 8: Put the pepper in a paper bag, seal tightly and allow to sit 10-15 minutes so the skin loosens;  then scrape off the skin and remove the seeds and stem. Cut it into strips. 9: Set the oven at 425 degrees. 10: Punch down the dough, divide it into 2 pieces, and pat them out into pizza rounds. Transfer to a baking sheet. 11: Divide the ricotta mixture between the rounds, top with onions, pepper, scallions which have been cut into 2 inch lengths and halved lengthwise, and pine nuts. 12: Bake the pizzas for 15 minutes or until the crust is firm and golden brown. 13: Serve at once. Serves four.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4940,"Oat Bran Pizza","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Oat Bran Pizza recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,2.0,1765.4,77.5,29.4,141.5,4260.5,223.4,30.1,26.3,84.3,"1.0","Oat Bran Pizza Recipe Instructions:  1: Have a 14 inch pizza pan or 17 by 14 baking sheet ready. 2: Mix flour, oat bran, and salt in a medium bowl. 3: Sprinkle the yeast over the warm water in measuring cup. 4: Add one tablespoon of the olive oil. 5: Stir until the yeast is dissolved and add to the flour mixture. Knead on a lightly floured surface about 5 minutes until smooth. 6: Roll out into a 15 inch circle and transfer to the pizza pan. 7: Pinch the dough around the edge to make a rim. 8: Brush the surface with the remaining tablespoon of oil. let the dough rise in a warm draft free place 15 to 20 minutes until puffy. 9: Heat the oven to 450 degrees. Bake 10-12 minutes until lightly browned. 10: Meanwhile mix tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano in a small bowl. 11: Spread evenly over the crust, arrange vegetables on top and sprinkle evenly with cheeses. 12: Return to oven and bake 12-15 minutes longer or until cheese has melted and browned slightly. 13: Let cool a few minutes before cutting into wedges.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4941,"Tuna & Macaroni Casserole Siciliana","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Tuna & Macaroni Casserole Siciliana recipe from Food.com.","Tuna",3.5,4.0,111.9,1.9,0.5,18.7,466.1,11.0,1.6,3.6,12.4,"8.0","Tuna & Macaroni Casserole Siciliana Recipe Instructions:  1: In a skillet, heat oil over medium flame. Add onions, bell peppers, and garlic. Cook until all is tender. 2: Stir in crushed tomatoes, tomato sauce, parsley, salt, sugar, basil, oregano, and lemon juice. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. 3: Stir in tuna and cooked elbow macaroni. Heat over low flame, 5 minutes. 4: Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4942,"Vegetable Lasagna II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Vegetable Lasagna II recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,223.1,9.0,5.2,25.3,315.2,27.6,3.0,6.0,8.9,"8.0","Vegetable Lasagna II Recipe Instructions:  1: In a 2 quart saucepan, cook onions, celery and green  pepper in butter until tender. 2: Add tomatoes, water and season-  ings. 3: Bring to a boil. 4: Reduce heat. Simmer over low heat,  uncovered, for 30 minutes. 5: Remove from heat. Add 3/4 cup of  the cheese. Stir until smooth. 6: In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish,  spread 1 cup of sauce. Top with 3 noodles, 1 cup zucchini and  1 cup sauce. Repeat noodles, zucchini and sauce, noodles and  sauce. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover tightly with  foil. 7: Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. 8: Remove foil and bake 15  minutes longer. 9: Remove  from oven. 10: Let stand 15 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4943,"Vegetable Lasagna III","PT30M","PT15M","PT45M","Make and share this Vegetable Lasagna III recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,5551.6,239.1,138.3,1141.8,8487.0,468.5,39.9,49.7,388.0,"1.0","Vegetable Lasagna III Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine cottage cheese, onions, eggs, oregano, garlic and basil leaves. 2: Cook lasagna, fry bacon half way. 3: Put 1 layer of lasagna, then cottage cheese, then broccoli, then Mozzarella, then Monterey Jack and then mushrooms. 4: Repeat for second layer. 5: Top with fried bacon. 6: Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4944,"Crock Pot Chicken &aacute; La Antoinette","PT2H","PT10M","PT2H10M","I use the slow cooker during the summer for this recipe. I just set it on low and leave it all day while I am at work.","Chicken Breast",4.5,31.0,382.6,19.9,5.0,94.3,641.9,12.2,0.7,1.7,32.2,"8.0","Crock Pot Chicken &aacute; La Antoinette Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute onions and mushrooms in olive oil. 2: Add chicken. 3: Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken mixture. Slow cook on top of stove  for 1 1/2  to 2 hours. (You can also combine ingredients in the Crock Pot and cook on low for up to 12 hours). 4: Serve over Rice or Pasta.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4946,"Sauteed Beef with Snow Peas","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Sauteed Beef with Snow Peas recipe from Food.com.","Meat",3.0,2.0,782.3,62.4,14.8,111.1,1425.3,11.5,2.2,4.4,36.6,"6.0","Sauteed Beef with Snow Peas Recipe Instructions:  1: Remove end tips from snow peas and cook in boiling water 3 minutes  oruntil tender, but still crisp. 2: Drain. 3: Cut steak into bite-sized pieces and toss with sherry. 4: soy sauce and cornstarch. 5: Heat 1/2  cup oil in a  skillet and saute until lightly browned. 6: Remove. Heat the remaining 1/2 cup oil in another skillet and saute the snow  peas 2 minutes. 7: Stir in the beef, garlic, sugar and soy sauce. Mix well.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4947,"Sweet Potato & Pear Soup","PT30M","PT10M","PT40M","Make and share this Sweet Potato & Pear Soup recipe from Food.com.","Yam/Sweet Potato",5.0,12.0,123.3,2.5,1.2,3.8,91.2,23.2,3.7,9.6,4.2,"8.0","Sweet Potato & Pear Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: In a pot, heat butter on medium heat. Add onion, carrot and celery and saute for 1 minute. 2: Add sweet potatoes, pears and thyme and saute for about 2 minutes. 3: Add paprika and chicken broth. Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes or until sweet potato is soft. 4: Puree in a blender or food processor until smooth. 5: Return to pot. Add cream, maple syrup and lime juice. Simmer for 5 minutes. 6: If soup is too thick add a little extra broth. Season with salt and pepper, adding more syrup or lime juice as needed. 7: Can be made up to 2 days ahead of time.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4948,"Double Cheese Bread","PT1H","PT15M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Double Cheese Bread recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",5.0,1.0,341.2,18.6,8.1,68.6,440.8,34.5,1.9,13.8,9.4,"20.0","Double Cheese Bread Recipe Instructions:  1: Stir together the flours, baking powder, baking soda, salt and walnuts. Set aside. 2: In large bowl of mixer, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. 3: Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. 4: Stir flour mixture into creamed mixture alternately with milk and wine. 5: Spoon half the batter into another bowl. Stir cheddar into one portion of batter and blue cheese into the other. 6: Spoon half the Cheddar batter into each of 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 inch loaf pans, distributing batter down one long side of each pan. Then spoon half the blue cheese batter into each pan alongside cheddar batter. If you prefer, you can make 1 Cheddar loaf and 1 blue cheese loaf by putting all of one type of  batter into 1 pan etc. 7: Sprinkle poppy seeds over cheddar batter and sesame seeds over blue cheese batter. 8: Bake at 350°F for about 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean. 9: Let cool in pans for 10 minutes, then turn out onto racks to  cool completely. 10: May be wrapped and frozen for up to 2 months. 11: To serve, cut bread into 3/4 inch thick slices. 12: It has a tendency to crumble so don''t try to slice thin.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4949,"Grape/Bleu Cheese/Walnut Focaccia","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Grape/Bleu Cheese/Walnut Focaccia recipe from Food.com.","Breads",5.0,1.0,2730.5,157.5,36.1,271.2,4002.4,265.9,18.2,52.2,78.3,"1.0","Grape/Bleu Cheese/Walnut Focaccia Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees. 2: Using your fingers, press the focaccia dough  ut into a 12-inch circle, about 1/4 -inch thick, onto a round baking sheet (I use a rectangular cookie sheet). Brush with  olive oil. 3: Season the bread with salt and white pepper. 4: Press the grapes into the dough, leaving a 1-inch border  around the edges. 5: Sprinkle the cheese and walnuts over the dough. Brush the edges of the dough with the egg wash. 6: Bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.  Place on wooden board and slice. 7: BASIC FOCCACIA DOUGH:  Place all ingredients in bread machine in the order suggested for YOUR machine.  Process on Doug h/ Manual cycle.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4950,"Jean''s Buffalo Chicken Lasagna","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Jean''s Buffalo Chicken Lasagna recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,4.0,270.9,9.1,5.1,53.2,398.8,23.6,0.9,1.2,22.5,"10.0","Jean''s Buffalo Chicken Lasagna Recipe Instructions:  1: Spray a la  rge skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.  Add chicken; saute 4 minutes. 2: Drain well. 3: Stir in spaghetti sauce, water, hot  pepper sauce, vinegar and garlic salt. In a bowl, combine ricotta cheese and egg  substitute. Set aside. Spray a 9\ 4:  baking pan with spray. 5: Spread 1 cup of  the sauce over the bottom of the pan. 6: Arrange four pieces of lasagna (3  lengthwise, 1 widthwise) over the sauce. Cover  with 1 1/2 cups of the sauce.  Spread half of the ricotta mixture on top. 7: Arrange another four pieces of  lasagna over ricotta and top with another 1 1/2 cups of sauce. Spread the  remaining ricotta mixture over the top. 8: Arrange final four pieces of lasagna  over ricotta mixture; cover with remaining sauce.  Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. 9: cover lasagna with foil and bake for 1 hour and  10 minutes. 10: Uncover lasagna, sprinkle blue cheese or mozzarella cheese over the  top, bake an additional 5 minute uncovered. 11: let stand 15 minutes covered, before  serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4951,"Pecan Blue Cheese Crackers","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Pecan Blue Cheese Crackers recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",0.0,0.0,2368.4,205.1,69.2,455.5,85.0,116.4,17.6,6.7,33.8,"0.0","Pecan Blue Cheese Crackers Recipe Instructions:  1: In a preheated 350 degree oven toast 1/2 cup pecans, about 7 minutes, and cool. 2: Finely chop toasted pecans 3: In a bowl with a fork cream butter and Saga until smooth. 4: Separate egg. Add egg yolk, stirring until combined well. 5: Add flour and chopped pecans and stir until mixture just forms a dough. 6: Halve dough and on separate sheets of waxed paper form each half into a 12 by 1  1/4-inch log, using waxed paper as a guide. Freeze logs, wrapped in waxed paper,  just until firm, about 30 minutes. 7: Preheat oven to 375 degrees and lightly grease 2 large baking sheets. 8: Cut logs crosswise into 1/4-inch thick slices and arrange slices about 1/2-inch apart on baking sheets. 9: Top each cracker with a remaining pecan half, pressing lightly into dough . 10: Brush tops of crackers, including pecans, with lightly beaten egg white. Bake crackers in batches, if necessary, in upper and lower thirds of oven, switching position of sheets halfway through baking, until golden brown, about 12 minutes total. 11: With a spatula transfer crackers to paper towels to blot and transfer to a rack to cool.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4953,"Dried Mushroom Soup","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Dried Mushroom Soup recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,4.0,795.9,20.7,12.8,78.5,1279.1,136.0,1.3,127.7,20.2,"0.0","Dried Mushroom Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender. 2: Crush morels or other mushrooms with rolling pin, set aside. 3: Stir the flour into the onion-celery mixture, add the water and crushed mushrooms. Simmer until the mushrooms are tender, (about 5 minutes). 4: Add bouillon, milk and seasonings. Heat, but do not boil, and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4954,"Easy Cheesy Biscuits","PT15M","PT10M","PT25M","These are so moist, you''ll throw away your old biscuit recipe! Although they are best served fresh baked and warm from the oven, they can be made ahead and lightly toasted under the broiler.","Breads",4.0,1.0,91.5,3.5,2.1,9.4,139.7,11.2,0.4,0.1,3.6,"0.0","Easy Cheesy Biscuits Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 450F(230C). 2: Sift together flour and baking powder into a large bowl. 3: Cut butter into flour mixture with pastry blender or 2 knives until particles are the size of small peas. 4: Stir in cottage cheese all at once. 5: Drop by generous tablespoons onto a lightly greased cookie sheet. 6: Bake for 15 minutes or until golden.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4955,"Cold Pea Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cold Pea Salad recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,1.0,607.2,16.2,7.9,215.8,406.7,78.1,25.6,33.3,40.0,"0.0","Cold Pea Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Drain peas. 2: Combine next 6 ingredients and mix well. 3: Add peas, eggs and mayonnaise and mix gently. 4: Chill throughly. 5: You can increase the amount of celery, onion, green pepper, pimento, relish and mayonnaise to suit your taste.  Jan");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4959,"Apple-Sage Chutney","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Apple-Sage Chutney recipe from Food.com.","Chutneys",0.0,0.0,1474.5,4.6,1.6,0.0,68.5,383.5,42.3,307.2,9.4,"0.0","Apple-Sage Chutney Recipe Instructions: ");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4960,"Chicken with Dried Cherries and Sour Cream","PT45M","PT25M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Chicken with Dried Cherries and Sour Cream recipe from Food.com.","Chicken Breast",5.0,1.0,423.3,23.5,8.2,103.1,413.2,11.1,2.9,3.8,29.6,"4.0","Chicken with Dried Cherries and Sour Cream Recipe Instructions:  1: Soak cherries in either brandy or sherry, set aside. Heat oven to 425x. 2: Sprinkle salt and pepper, 1/2 teaspoon paprika and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon on  chicken breasts, which have been sliced in half to make thin cutlets. 3: Bake, for  10 to 15 minutes, until almost done . 4: Cover with foil to keep warm. 5: Melt butter  in a skillet large enough to hold the chicken in one layer; add onions and cook  10 minutes. 6: Add remaining paprika and cinnamon. 7: Add stock and red wine. Cook  on high heat until reduced. 8: Add cherries and soaking liquid, and walnuts. 9: Add  the chicken to the   sauce and heat through. 10: Remove from the heat, and mix in the  sour cream. 11: Serve at once.  Good with rice pilaf and green salad. 12: NOTES : This is a very rich dish and a little goes a long way. 13: Follow with a  light dessert.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4963,"Chicken and Dumplings Like Cracker Barrel''s","PT2H","PT1H","PT3H","This tastes just like Cracker Barrel''s, if you have ever tried it. From book &quot;Old Fashioned Country Cooking&quot; found at Cracker Barrel.","Chicken",5.0,81.0,710.5,41.4,11.7,172.0,1275.7,33.4,1.2,1.6,47.7,"0.0","Chicken and Dumplings Like Cracker Barrel''s Recipe Instructions:  1: Place chicken in a Dutch oven.  Add water and 2 teaspoons salt.  Bring to a boil. 2: Cover, reduce the heat, and simmer for 1 hour or until tender (should almost fall off bone). 3: Remove the chicken from the broth and cool.  Bone the chicken and cut meat into bite-sized pieces. 4: Bring the broth to a boil and add pepper. 5: Combine the flour, baking soda, and salt.  Cut in the shortening.  Add the buttermilk, stirring with a fork until moistened. 6: Knead the dough 4 to 5 times (never done), and pat to 1/2-inch pieces and drop into boiling broth (I do not pat it out, just pinch off pieces).  Reduce the heat to medium-low, and cook for about 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. 7: Stir in the chicken and serve. I make it in the pressure cooker, much quicker and easier. 8: I pressure it for only 30 minutes. 9: It can also be done in the crockpot with 3-4 cups water but someone has that book so at this time I cannot give cooking times. 10: Good Luck! Hope you enjoy.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4965,"Chocolate Cookies","PT8M","PT20M","PT28M","Make and share this Chocolate Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,5.0,83.5,5.1,3.2,13.1,35.3,8.9,0.4,2.8,1.0,"0.0","Chocolate Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Pre-heat oven to 190/ 375 / Gas5. 2: Cream the sugar and butter. 3: Add the remaining ingredients and mix well. 4: Divide the mixture in half and then tear off and shape a total of 18 balls. 5: Place on a lined baking sheet and squash slightly to make a squat flat circle. Bake for 8 minutes. 6: Leave to cool for 1 minute and place on to a cooling rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4966,"Classic Pizza Crust","PT15M","PT1H","PT1H15M","Make and share this Classic Pizza Crust recipe from Food.com.","Low Cholesterol",5.0,5.0,640.6,8.6,1.2,0.0,1171.3,120.7,5.2,0.4,17.6,"0.0","Classic Pizza Crust Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large mixing bowl, combine the yeast, 1 cup of flour, and the  salt. Mix. 2: Next, add the water and oil. 3: Beat on low speed for 30  seconds. 4: Scrape the sides of the bowl and continue to beat on high  speed for 3 minutes. 5: By hand, stir in enough flour to make the dough  stiff. 6: Knead until smooth which can take up to 10 minutes. 7: Place in a  well greased bowl and turn the dough until it is lightly greased. 8: Cover and let rise for about 1 1/2 hours or until the dough has  doubled in size. Punch it down and chill for 2 hours. 9: Cut the dough  in half. 10: On a floured surface, roll the halves into 12 inch circle  and about 1/8 inch thick. 11: Brush the surfaces of the dough with olive  oil and add the toppings of your choice. Cook at 425* for 25 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4967,"Appetizer Sweet and Sour Meatballs","PT55M","PT20M","PT1H15M","Make and share this Appetizer Sweet and Sour Meatballs recipe from Food.com.","Meatballs",0.0,0.0,116.3,0.8,0.2,18.6,150.0,27.1,0.9,23.8,1.4,"0.0","Appetizer Sweet and Sour Meatballs Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook first 4 ingredients together slowly until the cranberry sauce has dissolved. 2: Soak the bread in water until it is soggy but not overly soggy. Remove and place in a mixing bowl. 3: Add the meat, salt/pepper, and egg. Mix very well. Form into small balls. 4: Add them to the pan of liquid cranberry sauce. Simmer for about 40 minutes or until done. Place them on a chafing dish and serve with toothpicks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4968,"Crisp Spring Greens with Creamy Tomato Dressing","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Crisp Spring Greens with Creamy Tomato Dressing recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,431.4,40.8,5.7,0.0,154.0,16.8,1.2,13.4,1.1,"0.0","Crisp Spring Greens with Creamy Tomato Dressing Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare greens, store in a sealed airtight plastic bag in the refrigerator until ready to serve. Arrange greens in individual salad bowls or on individual salad plates, dividing evenly. 2: Top each with sliced green onions and tomato wedges or slices. 3: Garnish each with crumbled blue or Roquefort cheese and/or crisp croutons, if desired. 4: Pass Creamy Tomato Dressing. 5: CREAMY TOMATO DRESSING Combine the first 9 to 11 ingredients together in a blender container. 6: Cover and blend at medium speed for 30 seconds; uncover and with the motor at low speed, gradually add oil, blending until mixture is smooth and completely mixed. 7: Season with salt and pepper to taste. Cover and increase motor speed to high; beat for 30 seconds. 8: Store, tightly sealed, in an airtight glass container or jar in the refrigerator for up to two weeks. 9: NOTE: May use about 1/4 to 1/3 cup extra virgin olive oil and 1/3 to 1/2 cup other salad oil, if desired. 10: The flavor of 3/4 cup olive oil is too intense for this dressing. 11: VARIATION: May add 1/2 crumbled blue or Roquefort cheese to prepared dressing, if desired. Or, may add 1/2 cup crumbled cheese to dressing mixture while beating and then stir in 1/2 cup crumbled cheese after preparation, if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4969,"Baked Sweet Potato Chips","PT35M","PT3M","PT38M","Make and share this Baked Sweet Potato Chips recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",3.5,4.0,103.5,0.1,0.0,0.0,62.6,24.4,3.6,5.6,1.9,"8.0","Baked Sweet Potato Chips Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl. 2: Layer potatoes in a baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray (nonfat). 3: Add any remaining liquid from bowl and cover dish with foil and bake at 350 degrees F for 30-35 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4972,"Irish Cream (Almost Like Bailey''s)","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Irish Cream (Almost Like Bailey''s) recipe from Food.com.","Beverages",4.0,1.0,556.3,18.2,11.3,62.8,147.2,56.9,0.2,51.7,9.3,"0.0","Irish Cream (Almost Like Bailey''s) Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix in blender or with wire whip. 2: Refrigerate or freeze. Serve over  crushed ice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4973,"Turkey Tenderloins with Spiced Cranberry Sauce","0","PT0S","PT0S","A tasty option to the whole bird. Tenderloins or fillets are the feather-shaped part of the breast. This recipe featuring tenderloins serves four to six people, depending on the size of the tenderloins. The recipe can easily be doubled for a larger crowd.","Poultry",5.0,6.0,320.8,6.0,3.7,15.3,93.2,69.5,1.7,67.7,0.6,"0.0","Turkey Tenderloins with Spiced Cranberry Sauce Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown tenderloins in butter in skillet. Lower heat to simmer and cover. Cook about 20 minutes until meat juices run clear. 2: Remove tenderloins and keep warm. Pour off excess drippings. 3: Add cranberry sauce, cloves and sugar to skillet. Heat over low heat. Add orange pieces. 4: Spoon sauce over tenderloins to serve or spoon some sauce onto serving plate and top with sliced tenderloins. 5: Garnish with orange twists if desired. 6: Serve with wild or brown rice.  Enjoy.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4975,"Chicago Style Deep Dish Pizza Crust","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chicago Style Deep Dish Pizza Crust recipe from Food.com.","Yeast Breads",5.0,8.0,300.8,6.8,1.2,62.0,26.9,49.8,2.1,1.6,9.1,"6.0","Chicago Style Deep Dish Pizza Crust Recipe Instructions:  1: Whisk together water, yeast and sugar in a bowl and set aside to proof for 10 minutes. 2: In a large bowl sift together flour and salt and sprinkle in thyme. Mix eggs into yeast mixture. Pour liquid into dry ingredients and mix until a soft sticky dough forms. 3: remove dough to a lightly floured surface and knead 5 minutes, until dough is no longer sticky. 4: Place in a well oiled bowl, turning to coat all sides, cover and allow to rise until doubled in bulk 2 - 3 hours. 5: Punch dough down and place into a well oiled 12\ 6: using your hands, move dough around the bottom of the pan and 2/3 the way up the sides. 7: Set aside and let rise 10 minutes. 8: Brush crust lightly with olive oil and add toppings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4977,"Ukrainian Borschtsch","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Ukrainian Borschtsch recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,1638.5,92.6,35.8,120.9,18645.4,137.2,34.4,56.3,47.5,"0.0","Ukrainian Borschtsch Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large stockpot bring the beef to a boil in 2 1/2 quart. Water with 1 tbs of salt. After 10 minutes of boiling reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes more, then remove meat, cool and remove meat from bone & cube 1/2\ 2: ,  3: ,  4: Drain the beet-carrot-onion and potato mixture and add to stockpot. Reduce heat and cook for 20 min. 5: then add cabbage, tomato paste and pork butt. Cook another 30 to 45 minutes. 6: Remove from heat and allow to cool to room temperature. Refrigerate overnight, re-heat and serve. A large dollop or 2 of sour cream in the soup is mandatory when served. Allow each person to stir it in themselves. 7: *NOTE: You may add 1 1/2 cups of cooked white beans to this soup if you wish but if you do so soak them in vinegar then add them to the soup.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4978,"Dawn Hornsby''s Unusual Green Bean Casserole","PT30M","PT5M","PT35M","My mom used to make this all the time. She would experiment with all types of food and in turn, her creations were wonderful!! Though, I do not know if this is one of her original recipes but it was handwritten in her notebook of recipes that was given to me at the time of her death.","Vegetable",5.0,10.0,850.9,32.6,9.5,79.3,8594.3,127.7,30.9,30.6,25.3,"0.0","Dawn Hornsby''s Unusual Green Bean Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine water, beans and salt. Bring to a quick boil. 2: Reduce heat until it has thawed and slightly crisp. **About 4 minutes** Drain them. 3: In a 2 quart casserole dish, layer the beans and chestnuts. 4: Next, mix the milk and soup into a separate bowl. Add pepper. 5: Pour this over the beans and chestnuts. Bake at 350* for 25 minutes. 6: Remove from oven and top with the onion rings and bake again until they are a golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4979,"Trader Vic''s Crab Rangoon","PT25M","PT10M","PT35M","Make and share this Trader Vic''s Crab Rangoon recipe from Food.com.","Crab",5.0,7.0,95.7,4.9,2.6,31.7,154.4,8.4,0.2,0.4,4.4,"18.0","Trader Vic''s Crab Rangoon Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine crabmeat with cream cheese, steak sauce and garlic powder in medium bowl and blend to a paste. 2: Place heaping teaspoon on each won ton.  Gather four corners of won ton together at top. Moisten edges with egg yolk and pinch or twist together gently to seal. 3: Heat oil in wok, deep fryer or electric skillet to 375 degrees. 4: Add won tons in batches and fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes.  Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels. 5: Serve hot with Chinese mustard and/or red sauce for dipping.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4980,"Vegetable Ravioli","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Vegetable Ravioli recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,2366.9,12.6,2.4,73.5,4660.0,468.4,15.4,2.1,82.4,"6.0","Vegetable Ravioli Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine the tomatoes, onion, mushrooms, and garlic in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat until the mixture is somewhat dry. Set aside to cool. 2: Combine the tomato mixture, spinach, cottage cheese, and basil in a large bowl. Add pepper to taste 3: On a cutting board, lay out a single layer of pot-sticker shells. Using a pastry brush, moisten the edges with water. Place 1 tablespoon of the spinach mixture onto the center of each shell. Cover with a second pot-sticker shell and press the edges together with a fork to seal. Repeat with remaining shells. 4: Cook the ravioli in boiling water for 3-4 minutes. 5: Serve hot with pasta sauce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4981,"Crock Pot Orange-Herbed Pork Roast","PT10H","PT15M","PT10H15M","Make and share this Crock Pot Orange-Herbed Pork Roast recipe from Food.com.","Oranges",4.5,14.0,1526.2,82.8,26.4,571.8,434.7,11.5,0.7,6.0,171.9,"8.0","Crock Pot Orange-Herbed Pork Roast Recipe Instructions:  1: Trim fat from pork. If necessary, cut roast to fit into a 3- to 4-quart crockery cooker. 2: In a small bowl combine oregano, ginger, and pepper. Rub spice mixture over entire surface of meat. 3: Spray a large unheated, nonstick skillet with nonstick coating. Preheat over medium heat. Add roast and brown on all sides. 4: Transfer meat to the crockery cooker; add onions. 5: In a bowl combine 1 cup of the orange juice (chill remaining orange juice), the sugar, grapefruit juice, steak sauce, and soy sauce. Pour over meat in the crockery cooker. 6: Cover and cook on low-heat setting for 8 to 10 hours or on high-heat setting for 4 to 5  hours. 7: Transfer roast to a serving platter; keep warm. 8: For sauce, measure pan juices into a glass measure. Skim off fat. Add additional orange juice, if necessary, to make 2-1/4 cups. 9: In a medium saucepan combine cornstarch, remaining 1/4 cup orange juice, and the reserved orange peel; stir in reserved pan juices. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. 10: Cook and stir for 2 minutes more. Pass sauce with meat. If desired, serve with noodles.");
