INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4984,"Best Oatmeal Cookies","PT10M","PT0S","PT10M","Make and share this Best Oatmeal Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.5,28.0,65.5,0.4,0.1,0.0,28.5,14.5,0.7,7.9,1.4,"0.0","Best Oatmeal Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine and sugars until light and fluffy. Add egg whites. 2: In a medium size bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to sugar mixture. 3: Stir in oats, raisins and vanilla. Chill 1 hour. 4: Preheat oven 350°F. 5: Roll a teaspoon of dough into a ball and place on an ungreased cookie sheet. 6: Grease the bottom of a glass with margarine, dip glass in sugar and use to flatten ball of dough. continue, leaving adequate space between cookies. 7: Bake 10 minutes. 8: Cool on racks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4985,"Sweet Potatoes With Apricot and Orange","PT15M","PT15M","PT30M","Make and share this Sweet Potatoes With Apricot and Orange recipe from Food.com.","Potato",0.0,0.0,187.0,3.9,0.8,0.0,128.5,36.5,5.3,11.3,2.7,"0.0","Sweet Potatoes With Apricot and Orange Recipe Instructions:  1: Arrange the sweet potatoes in a shallow baking dish. 2: Combine the margarine and cinnamon. Pour over the potatoes. 3: Arrange the apricot halves on top. 4: Cover the dish and bake in a 425F oven for about 15 minutes. 5: Add the orange slices and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4986,"Smoked Salmon Fettuccine","PT20M","PT0S","PT20M","Make and share this Smoked Salmon Fettuccine recipe from Food.com.","Healthy",4.5,9.0,314.0,6.8,3.4,20.1,275.7,45.6,1.9,1.0,14.3,"8.0","Smoked Salmon Fettuccine Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter and whisk in flour. Gradually add milk and sour cream. Season with salt and pepper. Stir until thick. 2: Add Scotch or Bourbon, salmon and parsley. 3: Cook pasta and drain. 4: Combine salmon mixture with pasta. 5: Sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan cheese.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4987,"Potato Spinach Soup","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Potato Spinach Soup recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,31.0,1180.3,84.0,52.5,254.7,5230.4,97.3,11.9,10.5,15.4,"0.0","Potato Spinach Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt butter in a pan. 2: Add onions and celery. 3: Cover and cook until tender - about 15 minutes. 4: Stir occasionally. 5: Blend in flour, and add potatoes, water and salt. Stir constantly until boiling. 6: Simmer 30 minutes. 7: Add spinach    cook 2 minutes. 8: Then add cream. 9: Top with grated cheese if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4988,"Baked Fillet of Sole","PT15M","PT0S","PT15M","Make and share this Baked Fillet of Sole recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",3.5,2.0,193.1,2.3,0.5,81.8,145.6,4.3,1.1,1.7,34.3,"2.0","Baked Fillet of Sole Recipe Instructions:  1: Place fillets in a greased baking dish. 2: Combine rosemary, wine, lemon juice and pour over the fish. 3: Top with scallions and mushrooms. 4: Cover with aluminum foil. 5: Bake in preheated 350-degree oven for about 15 minutes or until flaky. 6: Sprinkle with parsley and season with salt and pepper.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4989,"Cajun Beef Tips with Rice","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cajun Beef Tips with Rice recipe from Food.com.","White Rice",5.0,8.0,258.3,13.5,5.2,82.8,71.4,8.2,2.3,4.6,26.3,"4.0","Cajun Beef Tips with Rice Recipe Instructions:  1: Brown the meat, onion, green pepper, and mushrooms in a small amount of oil in a heavy skillet. Cook until vegetables are soft and meat is browned. 2: Remove from heat. Add tomatoes and spices. 3: Bring to a boil then lower heat to a simmer. 4: Cook 10 minutes. 5: Serve over white rice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4990,"Orange Angel Cake II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Using orange juice concentrate in place of some of the water in the angel cake mix gives this cake a delicate orange flavor and color.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,166.8,0.3,0.1,0.6,268.9,37.6,0.2,23.0,4.1,"0.0","Orange Angel Cake II Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare angel cake as directed on package, except pour 1/3 cup of the thawed orange juice concentrate into a 2-cup measure; add enough water to the concentrate for the mixture to equal the amount of water called for in the package directions. 2: Continue with package directions, baking the batter in an ungreased 10\ 3: ,  4: ,  5: ,  6: Spread topping mixture over top and sides of cake. If desired, garnish with citrus roses made from grapefruit or orange peel. Store in the refrigerator. 7: Citrus Rose: Cut the peel from stem end of a Florida Orange or Grapefruit, forming a circular base (do not sever). Continue cutting a strip of peel about 3/4\ 8:  wide in a spiral motion to opposite end of fruit, making one lon g, continuous strip and slicing thinly (do not cut into white membrane). Start coiling strip tightly, beginning at end opposite base. Coil the strip onto the base to form a rose. Garnish with mint leaves and small strips of peel, if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4991,"Tuna Noodle Casserole with Pimentos","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Tuna Noodle Casserole with Pimentos recipe from Food.com.","Tuna",5.0,19.0,460.1,20.3,10.5,101.5,706.1,42.0,3.0,2.6,27.1,"4.0","Tuna Noodle Casserole with Pimentos Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook noodles or macaroni according to pkg directions and set aside. 2: Meanwhile, in a saucepan cook celery and onion in butter or margarine till softened. Stir in soup and milk. 3: Gently stir in tuna, pimiento and the cooked noodles or  macaroni. 4: Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 375 degrees for 25 to 30  minutes or until heated through. 5: Extra-Creamy Tuna Noodle Casserole: Prepare as above, but substitute 8 oz carton of sour cream or plain yogurt for the milk. 6: Stir 1 to 2 tbsp of milk into mixture if needed to obtain desired consistency. 7: Vegetable Tuna Noodle Casserole: Prepare as above and stir in 1 cup cooked vegetables with tuna.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4992,"Decadent Crust Lemon Bars","PT50M","PT10M","PT1H","Make and share this Decadent Crust Lemon Bars recipe from Food.com.","Bar Cookie",5.0,63.0,181.6,8.6,5.1,51.3,143.4,24.4,0.4,15.1,2.4,"0.0","Decadent Crust Lemon Bars Recipe Instructions:  1: For crust, mix together flour, sugar, and butter until crumbly. 2: Pat into bottom and 1/4-inch up sides of a buttered 9x13 inch baking pan. Bake in a 350°F oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until lightly browned. 3: Meanwhile prepare topping. Beat eggs slightly. 4: In a separate bowl, stir together sugar and flour. Add to eggs. Beat well. 5: Add lemon juice, peel, baking powder, and salt. Beat until smooth. 6: Pour over baked crust. Return to oven and bake 25-30 minutes longer, or until just set. 7: Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot. Let cool and cut into bars.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4993,"Baked Brown Rice & Tuna Casserole","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Make and share this Baked Brown Rice & Tuna Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Tuna",5.0,10.0,482.0,9.8,3.2,108.7,99.8,73.2,3.8,1.8,23.6,"6.0","Baked Brown Rice & Tuna Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Saute celery in butter until tender crisp. 2: Add brown rice, tuna, eggs and lemon juice. Fold in mayonnaise. Season to taste. 3: Turn into shallow buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole. Top with onion rings. 4: Bake at 350 for 20 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4994,"Emeril''s Essence","0","PT5M","PT5M","This is a recipe for Emeril''s Essence spice, used in many of his recipes.  May also be used within many of your own dishes as an extra kick of flavor.","Low Cholesterol",5.0,108.0,268.1,5.6,1.2,0.0,18651.2,58.3,21.1,4.8,11.8,"0.0","Emeril''s Essence Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine all the ingredients in a mixing bowl. 2: Blend well. 3: Can be stored in an airtight container in your spice cabinet for up to 3 months.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4995,"Waldorf Salad III","0","PT15M","PT15M","I experiment and add whatever fruit, nuts and vegetables taste good with this.  The original recipe from Woman''s Home Companion Cookbook. 1946.","Fruit",5.0,3.0,407.7,26.1,2.5,0.0,84.4,45.0,10.3,29.6,7.4,"1.0","Waldorf Salad III Recipe Instructions:  1: Core apples, pare if desired or leave red skinned apples unpeeled; dice and sprinkle with lemon juice.  Combine with celery and mayonnaise to moisten. 2: Pile in lettuce cups or on other salad greens on individual plates. 3: Just before serving sprinkle with nuts. 4: Note: a little grated orange rind may be mixed with the salad or sprinkled over the nuts.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4996,"Dancer''s Potato Skins","PT1H","PT40M","PT1H40M","Make and share this Dancer''s Potato Skins recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,25.0,304.0,18.6,10.7,47.4,250.6,28.0,2.6,1.4,7.2,"6.0","Dancer''s Potato Skins Recipe Instructions:  1: You can add these ingredients to the mashed potato centers if desired. 2: 1/3 cup milk 1/4 cup butter salt and pepper a few drops hot sauce Scrub potatoes, dry, then pierce with fork several times. 3: Arrange on a baking sheet and bake in 375 degree oven for about 1 hour or until tender. 4: Let stand until cool enough to handle. Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out centers, leaving 1/8\ 5: ,  6: ,  7: ,  8: When ready to prepare skins, melt the 1/3 cup butter. 9: Brush shells with the butter, inside and out. Place, cut side up, on baking sheet. Bake in a 500 degree oven for 20 minutes or until brown and crisp. 10: Distribute some bacon, onion, and cheese in each shell. 11: Bake just until cheese melts. 12: Serve hot. If the potatoes are large, you may want to cut in half crosswise before serving. 13: You may want to double this recipe if you are serving several people, especially if they are hungry!  Serves: 6.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4997,"Parmesan Rice and Pasta Pilaf","0","PT0S","PT0S","After the pasta and onion are sauteed, the oil is drained to minimize the fat content of this interesting pilaf.","White Rice",5.0,7.0,169.4,5.5,1.1,1.5,189.9,25.3,0.5,0.3,3.9,"0.0","Parmesan Rice and Pasta Pilaf Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large skillet, heat oil. Saute vermicelli and onion until golden brown, about 2 to 4 minutes over medium-high heat. Drain off oil. 2: Add rice, stock, water, pepper, and bay leaf. Cover and simmer 15-20 minutes. 3: Fluff with fork. Cover and let stand 5-20 minutes. 4: Remove bay leaf. Sprinkle with cheese and serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4998,"Orange-Chocolate Muffins","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Orange-Chocolate Muffins recipe from Food.com.","Quick Breads",4.0,1.0,172.4,7.7,2.2,19.1,55.4,24.2,0.9,11.1,2.9,"0.0","Orange-Chocolate Muffins Recipe Instructions:  1: Grease twenty-four 2-1/2\ 2: ,  3: ,  4: ,  5: ,  6: Bake in a 400  degree oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden. 7: Remove from pans; serve warm. 8: If desired, brush muffin tops with a little orange juice concentrate.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(4999,"Chocolate-Orange Mousse","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Chocolate-Orange Mousse recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,145.9,6.1,2.7,1.0,38.9,20.3,0.7,16.7,3.6,"6.0","Chocolate-Orange Mousse Recipe Instructions:  1: In a medium mixing bowl combine dessert topping mix and 1/2 cup of the milk. 2: Beat with an electric mixer on high speed about 2 minutes or until mixture forms stiff peaks (tips stand straight). Set aside 1/4 cup of the whipped topping.Add  the remaining milk, thawed concentrate, and pudding mix to remaining topping. 3: Beat on low speed just until mixed. 4: Beat on medium speed about 2 minutes more or until well mixed. 5: Spoon the mixture into 6 dessert dishes. 6: Cover and chill about 10 minutes or until set. To serve, top with reserved whipped topping, chopped pecans, and if desired, orange peel strips.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5000,"Roti","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Roti recipe from Food.com.","Breads",4.5,4.0,228.1,0.6,0.1,0.0,237.4,48.0,1.7,0.2,6.5,"4.0","Roti Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; add water  to make a soft dough. 2: Knead well; cover and leave for 1/2  hour. 3: Divide dough into 4 portions, form into balls. 4: Roll out  dough to thin thicknesses on floured board. 5: Apply shortening  or oil to the surface of dough. 6: Fold up each dough and set  aside. Heat large skillet or griddle; wipe with grease. Roll  out dough again on floured board until thin thickness and place  on hot griddle or in skillet, turning frequently from side to  side and rubbing surface of dough with oil or shortening. 7: Cook  over medium heat until dough has a lightly brown color. 8: Put  into a towel and press to give a leafy effect.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5001,"Roti and Beef Curry","0","PT1H","PT1H","Make and share this Roti and Beef Curry recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,3.0,576.5,33.4,13.6,45.0,251.8,56.4,3.1,0.8,11.3,"10.0","Roti and Beef Curry Recipe Instructions:  1: Pour the boiling water over the flour. Use a big spoon for mixing as dough will be really hot. Mix until smooth so it will be easy to roll out (like a pie shell); grease frypan before frying. 2: Make them the size of taco shells. Also oil both sides of roti and fry. 3: Keep it warm in a covered pan or bowl while frying the remaining roti. 4: Serve with curry. 5: Heat the oil first. Fry the ginger, garlic and the onion until brown. 6: Add the salt and curry powder. 7: Stir for about 2 minutes. 8: Add small cubes of beef and let it cook until the beef is tender. 9: Then add potato cubes. 10: If the meat is kind of dry, add a little water. 11: Also the meat and potatoes will cook better. 12: When curry mixture is done, put some in each roti shell (something like tacos) and wrap the roti shell around the curry mixture (like a package).");
