INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5003,"Mexican Avocado Dip","PT30M","PT0S","PT30M","Make and share this Mexican Avocado Dip recipe from Food.com.","Mexican",0.0,0.0,1051.3,103.8,65.2,302.2,743.6,13.0,0.1,1.0,21.3,"0.0","Mexican Avocado Dip Recipe Instructions:  1: Blend all ingredients well until creamy. 2: Place on round platter, garnish with tomato bits, green onions (chopped) and shredded Cheddar cheese. Serve with corn chips. 3: Chill for about 30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5004,"Potato Korv","PT45M","PT15M","PT1H","tonights dinner.  To stuff the casings, you will need a meat grinder with a sausage horn attachment. If you don''t have such a device, use the mixture to make fried patties by shaping 1/4 cup of filling into a 1/2 inch thick patty and frying in hot oil until golden brown on both sides.","Breakfast",0.0,0.0,584.9,36.4,16.0,140.0,3705.5,26.8,2.1,1.2,36.6,"6.0","Potato Korv Recipe Instructions:  1: To prepare casings: Let casings soak in cool water about five minutes to remove salt on outer surface (no longer, or they will become too tender to stuff) and flush salt from the inside by placing one end on faucet nozzle and turn on cold tap water (if you see holes or water leaking, cut and discard). 2: Remove casing from faucet and gently squeeze out water; cover rinsed casings and refrigerate until ready to use. 3: Mix ingredients in order given (ground beef, ground pork, potatoes, onion, milk, allspice, salt and white pepper). 4: Fill the casings make links by twisting the sausage where you wish the links to be (four inches is a good size for a regular serving, smaller links may be made for appetizer servings). 5: To cook, bake in 350F oven 1 hour; remove from oven and brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5005,"Gumdrop Cake","PT45M","PT25M","PT1H10M","Candy plus dried fruit and nuts. Cooking time is a guess, please watch carefully and mention in your review if you make this.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,10903.4,365.3,137.1,1046.0,3529.0,1904.9,73.6,1128.1,116.4,"0.0","Gumdrop Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix soda in warm water. 2: Cream butter and sugars. 3: Beat in eggs. 4: Mix raisins,  gumdrops orange candy and pecans together. 5: Stir spices into applesauce. 6: Combine all ingredients together and turn into greased Bundt pan.  Bake at 325 until cooked through.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5006,"Potato Stuffing","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Potato Stuffing recipe from Food.com.","Potato",5.0,2.0,2265.4,50.9,11.6,186.0,5889.6,376.1,28.9,34.9,72.0,"0.0","Potato Stuffing Recipe Instructions:  1: Put egg into mashed potatoes and mix well. 2: Melt margarine in large skillet and saute onions and celery. 3: Stir in the bread crumbs to toast for a few minutes. 4: Add other ingredients together and combine with potato mixture. Mix thoroughly. 5: Put in margarine greased bread pans. 6: Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. 7: Note: You can toast bread crumbs in oven instead of putting in skillet.");
