INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5008,"Grandma''s Potato Stuffing","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Grandma''s Potato Stuffing recipe from Food.com.","Potato",0.0,1.0,2239.3,47.2,12.9,25.6,3084.6,394.9,32.0,38.6,60.5,"0.0","Grandma''s Potato Stuffing Recipe Instructions:  1: Soak bread in milk, set aside. 2: Saute finely chopped celery and onions in margarine over low flame. Add cold or freshly mashed potatoes and mix with celery and onions. Add seasoning, squeeze bread dry and mix all ingredients together being careful to keep flame low. 3: Let cool. 4: Spoon into salted cavity of chicken or turkey.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5009,"Cream-Filled Chocolate Cookies (Like Oreo Cakesters)","PT5M","PT25M","PT30M","Make and share this Cream-Filled Chocolate Cookies (Like Oreo Cakesters) recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",4.5,10.0,352.6,19.4,4.4,19.6,175.7,42.3,0.8,27.6,3.5,"0.0","Cream-Filled Chocolate Cookies (Like Oreo Cakesters) Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350°F. 2: Sift flour, baking soda, salt, and cocoa together into a large bowl. 3: Add remaining ingredients; mix together. 4: Drop chocolate batter by teaspoons about 3-inches apart  on cookie sheet. 5: Bake for 5 minutes. 6: Remove to a cooling rack. 7: Beat filling ingredients together until creamy. 8: Put the white filling  between two cooled chocolate cookies like a sandwich, then wrap in  plastic wrap.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5010,"Italian Chocolate Cookies","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Italian Chocolate Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,2.0,166.1,7.7,2.8,19.0,74.0,22.2,1.5,6.2,3.4,"0.0","Italian Chocolate Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream butter, then cream shortening. 2: Add sugar and mix. 3: Add remaining ingredients and mix well until smooth consistency. 4: Roll a golf-ball size amount of batter into a ball. 5: Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325 degrees about 25 minutes. 6: Keep checking to see if they are not too doughy, or too done. 7: Frost with white frosting. 8: Italian White Frosting:  Beat egg whites until stiff. 9: Add sugar and juice. Stir until completely mixed. 10: Dip chocolate cookies into frosting mixture upside down, holding onto bottom. 11: Place on waxed paper until frosting dries. 12: When dried, put into covered containers. 13: Makes enough frosting for approximately 10 dozen cookies.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5011,"Super Fudgy Chocolate Cookies","PT7M","PT0S","PT7M","Make and share this Super Fudgy Chocolate Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,72.0,3.1,1.6,3.4,18.2,10.0,0.6,6.4,1.2,"0.0","Super Fudgy Chocolate Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: In medium saucepan, combine morsels, sweetened condensed milk, and butter. 2: Cook and stir over low heat until morsels are melted. 3: Remove from heat, add remaining ingredients; mix well. 4: Divide dough into one-thirds, shape each into 8-inch roll. 5: Wrap in wax paper. Chill until firm (about 2 hours). 6: Preheat oven to 350°. 7: Cut into 1/4-inch slices. 8: Place on ungreased cooking sheet. Bake 7-9 minutes or until top is slightly crusted.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5012,"Chewy Chocolate Cookies","PT9M","PT0S","PT9M","Make and share this Chewy Chocolate Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",5.0,371.0,123.7,6.5,3.6,18.2,100.7,14.6,0.7,9.8,2.1,"0.0","Chewy Chocolate Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 350°. 2: In large mixer bowl; cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. 3: Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. 4: Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually blend into creamed mixture. Stir in peanut butter or chocolate chips. 5: Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8-9 minutes. (Do not overbake; cookies will be soft. They will puff while baking and flatten while cooling.). 6: Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet onto wire rack. Cool completely.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5014,"Beef Bake","0","PT0S","PT0S","This recipe is one of my favourites.  It is also wonderful made with ground  turkey or chicken.  It is also really good if you add some grated cheese to the  top in the last 5 minutes of cooking.  I don''t remember where this recipe came  from.  I have had it for years in my recipe box.  Hope you enjoy it.","Meat",0.0,0.0,299.0,20.1,6.7,79.4,389.2,8.0,1.8,4.6,23.0,"0.0","Beef Bake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375f, Heat oil in a skillet over moderate heat.  Add onion and  garlic.  Cook uncovered 5 min. 2: Push to one side and add beef. 3: Stir occasionally until browned. 4: Mix coriander, ginger, tomatoes, brown sugar, parsley, salt, pepper, and peppers in a bowl. 5: Add to beef. 6: M ix well and transfer to ungreased 1 quart casserole  dish. 7: Bake uncovered 20 minutes. 8: Serve over rice.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5017,"Mahogany Chicken Wings","PT1H","PT25M","PT1H25M","Make and share this Mahogany Chicken Wings recipe from Food.com.","Chicken",4.5,4.0,389.4,18.8,5.2,87.9,1613.5,22.2,0.9,12.2,23.9,"20.0","Mahogany Chicken Wings Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine sauce ingredients (that is everything except chicken wings  in a large pot and bring to a boil and then stir and simmer for 5 minutes. 2: Correct flavoring as desired. 3: Place wings in a large roasting pan(s). Pour over sauce on wings and coat evenly. 4: Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight. 5: Drain off sauce and reserve. 6: Roast wings in a 375 oven basting frequently with some of the reserved sauce, turning to brown until wings cooked and done (about 1 hour). Serve warm or cool and serve at room temperature.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5018,"Holiday Dip for Fresh Fruit","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Holiday Dip for Fresh Fruit recipe from Food.com.","Fruit",0.0,0.0,7628.6,618.3,384.5,2282.4,3101.0,477.0,4.7,427.6,44.9,"0.0","Holiday Dip for Fresh Fruit Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large mixing bowl place dry pudding mix and both thawed undiluted juice concentrated and mix well on low speed with electric mixer. 2: Beat heavy cream and brandy and mix well into pudding mixture well. 3: Place in a glass serving bowl. 4: Chill mixture well . 5: Serve with fresh fruit on the side. Party size- serves many.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5020,"Caramel Pie","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Caramel Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",4.0,4.0,518.6,17.9,6.8,110.7,287.6,83.5,1.2,66.1,7.4,"6.0","Caramel Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Sift together flour and 1 cup sugar. 2: Add egg yolks; beat until smooth. 3: Add milk, butter and vanilla; set aside. 4: Brown remaining 1/2 cup sugar in skillet; add 1/2 cup hot water. 5: Then add to flour mixture, stirring well. Cook until thick. 6: Pour in baked pie shell. 7: Meringue: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff. 8: Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time. Beat well. 9: Add vanilla. 10: Cover with meringue and bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes, until golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5021,"Waldorf Salad Iv","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Waldorf Salad Iv recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",0.0,0.0,118.3,6.1,0.8,0.0,93.2,16.1,3.5,10.3,2.4,"4.0","Waldorf Salad Iv Recipe Instructions:  1: Toss apples, celery and nuts with mayonnaise. 2: Spoon  into lettuce cups and if desired, garnish with maraschino cherries. 3: Waldorf Salad Supreme: Decrease celery to 1 medium  stalk and nuts to 1/4 cup. 4: Stir in 1 can (8 1/4 ounces)  pineapple chunks, drained, 1/2 cup miniature marshmallows and  1/3 cup cut up dates.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5022,"New York Waldorf Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this New York Waldorf Salad recipe from Food.com.","Low Cholesterol",4.0,1.0,254.3,14.3,2.0,0.0,243.2,29.5,4.6,18.6,7.5,"4.0","New York Waldorf Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Toss ingredients together. 2: Serve on a bed of lettuce  with dressing. 3: Waldorf Salad Dressing:  1/4 cup creamy peanut butter  1/4 cup honey  1/2 cup mayonnaise  Blend ingredients. 4: Serve over Waldorf Salad.");
