INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5025,"Old-Fashioned Chocolate Cake","PT40M","PT15M","PT55M","Make and share this Old-Fashioned Chocolate Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,5.0,459.0,17.9,2.8,24.4,292.0,71.6,1.3,53.8,4.3,"16.0","Old-Fashioned Chocolate Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Cream oil, sugar and cocoa. 2: Add eggs. 3: Add flour  mixture alternately with buttermilk. 4: Add soda and salt. Add  vanilla to hot water and fold water into cake. Bake in 9 x  13-inch pan at 350 degrees for about 40 minutes or until done. 5: Icing For Old-Fashioned Chocolate Cake:  Bring margarine, cocoa and whole milk to boil. 6: Remove  from heat and add powdered sugar and vanilla. 7: Mix until smooth and of spreading consistency. 8: This is my favorite chocolate cake.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5026,"Cherry Chocolate Cake","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Make and share this Cherry Chocolate Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,15.0,658.1,26.0,11.4,100.5,626.8,106.7,3.2,61.1,7.9,"8.0","Cherry Chocolate Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 350 degrees. 2: Combine cake mix, eggs and cherry fruit filling; blend well. 3: Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. 4: Bake 25 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched. 5: Frost after cooling with the following. 6: Combine sugar, butter and milk in small pan; bring to boil, stirring constantly. 7: Cook 1 minute; remove from heat. Stir in chocolate pieces until melted and smooth. 8: Spread on cake. Yummy!");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5027,"Irish Cream","0","PT10M","PT10M","(LIKE BAILEY''S IRISH CREAM) I make this all the time and everyone likes it.  Refrigeration time not included in preparation time.","Beverages",0.0,0.0,195.9,3.9,2.2,47.3,56.8,19.4,0.0,19.4,3.9,"12.0","Irish Cream Recipe Instructions:  1: Put all ingredients in blender until smooth. 2: Put in a bottle; a liter is best because is almost fills it. 3: Place in a refrigerator for 24 hours to rest. 4: Keep refrigerated. 5: Enjoy.");
