INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5031,"Lemon-Garlic Olives","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Lemon-Garlic Olives recipe from Food.com.","Lunch/Snacks",5.0,2.0,440.7,43.9,5.8,0.0,4440.0,18.3,10.1,3.1,3.8,"0.0","Lemon-Garlic Olives Recipe Instructions:  1: Drain and rinse the olives, reserving brine. 2: Layer olives, oregano sprigs, garlic, lemon wedges and peppercorns in olive jar. (Reserve the olives that do not fit back into the jar for another use). 3: Add fresh lemon juice and top off with reserved brine. 4: Shake well and let olives marinate for at least 1 week in refrigerator.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5032,"Blue Cheese Ball","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Blue Cheese Ball recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",0.0,0.0,618.0,60.5,28.6,147.3,762.4,7.9,1.7,4.6,14.5,"0.0","Blue Cheese Ball Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix cream cheese and blue cheese together. 2: Add some sour cream or mayonnaise to make it smoother and easier to spread. 3: Chill, divide into 2 small balls, and roll each ball in pecans.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5033,"Irish Cream II","0","PT0S","PT0S","This is a good recipe for Bailey''s equivalent.  If you can''t get the Cacoa  Essence try it without - it''s almost as good!","Beverages",0.0,0.0,1477.3,39.7,24.5,140.1,213.6,133.3,0.0,113.6,13.7,"0.0","Irish Cream II Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve sugar in water and bring to boil. 2: Do not overboil. 3: Cool. 4: Mix all  ingredients together and put in refrigerator for 2 hours. 5: It''s then OK to  drink. 6: Keep in refrigerator due to cream content.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5034,"Italian Cheesecake","0","PT0S","PT2H30M","Make and share this Italian Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",4.0,5.0,317.4,15.9,8.8,108.9,148.8,32.7,0.6,25.9,12.6,"12.0","Italian Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and 1 tablespoon honey in a small mixing bowl and mix well. 2: Place in a 9 inch springform pan and spread evenly across the bottom.  Refrigerate 30 minutes to chill. 3: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. 4: In a large bowl of an electric mixer, add ricotta and beat in eggs one at a time until incorporated. 5: Add remaining 1 cup honey, vanilla and flour. Beat until smooth. 6: Fold in lemon peel and almonds. 7: Pour mixture into chilled crust and scatter pumpkin seed on top. 8: Bake for 1 hour or until just firm and lightly colored on top. 9: Turn oven off, open door, and leave cake inside to cool for 30 minutes. 10: Remove from oven, refrigerate, and chill for 2 hour to  overnight before serving.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5035,"Cream Cheese Spritz","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cream Cheese Spritz recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",4.0,2.0,32.4,2.4,0.8,2.3,26.5,2.5,0.0,1.3,0.3,"108.0","Cream Cheese Spritz Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended. 2: Add flour; mix well. 3: Chill. 4: Force dough through cookie press onto ungreased  cookie sheets. 5: Bake at 400 degrees for 6-8 min. 6: or until set and very lightly  browned.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5039,"Spritz Cookies II","PT8M","PT0S","PT8M","Make and share this Spritz Cookies II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,2.0,102.0,5.9,3.7,19.1,59.9,11.2,0.2,4.2,1.1,"0.0","Spritz Cookies II Recipe Instructions:  1: Stir together flour and baking powder. 2: Beat butter for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat until fluffy. 3: Add egg, vanilla and almond extract; beat well. 4: Gradually add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating till well combined. 5: Do not chill. 6: Force dough through a cookie press onto an ungreased cookie sheet. If desired,  sprinkle with colored sugars or with ground almonds dyed red or green with food  coloring. 7: Bake in a 400° oven for 7-8 minutes. 8: Cool on wire rack.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5040,"Christmas Chocolate Pistachio Thumbprints","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Christmas Chocolate Pistachio Thumbprints recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,217.3,13.6,7.2,30.7,109.1,22.8,1.1,13.1,2.5,"0.0","Christmas Chocolate Pistachio Thumbprints Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat powdered sugar, butter, vanilla, almond extract, pudding mix and egg. 2: Add flour and chocolate chips. Mix well. 3: Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in nuts. With thumb, make imprint in center. 4: Bake at 350 degrees, 10 minutes or until light golden brown. 5: Cool completely. 6: Combine all filling ingredients. Melt butter and mix into powdered sugar.  Add milk and food coloring to make a thick red filling. 7: Spoon scant teaspoon in the center of each cookie. 8: Melt chocolate chips and shortening. Drizzle over cookies. 9: Let set until icing is hard.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5041,"Ile Iflotante [paris] = Madartej [hungary]","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Ile Iflotante [paris] = Madartej [hungary] recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,230.8,8.4,4.3,169.3,202.1,30.2,0.0,23.3,8.7,"8.0","Ile Iflotante [paris] = Madartej [hungary] Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat eggs and egg yolks lightly with a fork and strain them (to remove cords)  directly into the top of a glass or stainless steel or enameled double boiler. 2: Stir in sugar; sift and stir in flour. 3: Scald milk in a separate saucepan,  heating just until bubbles form around the edges. 4: Gradually stir the milk into  the eg g mixture, and cook over simmering, but not boiling water, stirring  constantly with a wooden spoon until the mixture coats a metal spoon. 5: Remove  from heat immediately, stir in the salt and vanilla, and pour into a large  shallow bowl. 6: Stand the bowl in cold water to cool rapidly, then chill in  refrigerator. 7: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and salt until frothy. 8: Add vanilla and  then add sugar one tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition. 9: Continue beating until stiff and shiny. 10: Heat milk in a frying pan. 11: When bubble start to form around the edges, drop in the egg white mixture a tablespoon full  at a time.  Do not cover. 12: Cook over low heat until the meringues are firm, but  not hard, about 5 minutes. 13: Using a slotted spoon, lift them carefully out of  the milk and slide them onto the custard. 14: Chill until ready to serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5042,"Blue Cheese and Pear Salad","0","PT10M","PT10M","Make and share this Blue Cheese and Pear Salad recipe from Food.com.","Cheese",5.0,2.0,341.7,27.6,5.5,11.3,501.9,21.5,3.5,14.9,5.8,"4.0","Blue Cheese and Pear Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Cover each salad plate with a modest bed of baby green lettuce. 2: Slice and core a half pear for each plate. 3: Thinly slice pears from bottom to just before the very end and then fan out the slices over the lettuce. 4: Top with toasted walnuts and a generous serving of crumbled blue cheese. 5: Whisk dressing ingredients and spoon over the salad mixture.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5043,"Pecan Pie","PT45M","PT0S","PT45M","Make and share this Pecan Pie recipe from Food.com.","Pie",4.5,4.0,650.1,31.6,10.5,132.8,422.1,92.3,1.8,52.3,5.7,"6.0","Pecan Pie Recipe Instructions:  1: Prepare pie crust. In a large bowl, combine corn syrup, brown sugar, eggs,  butter, salt and vanilla; mix well. 2: Pour filling into pie crust and top with pecan halves. 3: Bake at 350 for 45 to 50 minutes or until center is set. If using an electric oven you might have to add 15 to 20 minutes to the baking time. In either case, test with a toothpick after 45 minutes. 4: If crust appears to be getting too brown, cover with foil for remaining baking time.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5044,"Baker''s Christmas Cookies","0","PT0S","PT25M","Make and share this Baker''s Christmas Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,135.0,11.1,4.4,10.2,28.6,9.6,1.3,5.4,1.6,"0.0","Baker''s Christmas Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Place softened cream cheese and butter in a bowl. 2: Gradually add flour to form a dough. 3: Chill dough in refrigerator. 4: Roll out and cut with a 2\ 5: ,  6: ,  7: ,  8: ,  9: ,  10: Sprinkle non-pareils on top of warm melted chocolate.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5045,"Molasses Cookies","PT10M","PT40M","PT50M","Make and share this Molasses Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,13.0,142.6,6.0,1.3,7.8,224.5,21.2,0.3,12.4,1.4,"0.0","Molasses Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. 2: In 3-quart saucepan, melt margarine or butter over low heat. Remove saucepan from heat and, with wire whisk, beat in molasses and 1 cup sugar until blended, whisk in egg. 3: With spoon, stir in flour and remaining ingredients until mixed. 4: Transfer dough to medium bowl and freeze 15 minutes or until firm enough to handle. Spread remaining 1/4 cup sugar on waxed paper. 5: Roll dough into 1-inch balls, roll balls in sugar to coat. Place balls, 2 1/2 inches apart, on ungreased large cookie sheet. Bake cookies 10 to 12 minutes, until cookies spread and da rken. 6: Let cookies remain on cookie sheet on wire rack 1 minute to cool slightly. 7: Transfer cookies to wire rack to cool completely. 8: Repeat with remaining dough. 9: Store cookies in tightly covered container up to 2 weeks.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5046,"Southern Chicken and Dumplings","PT2H","PT15M","PT2H15M","Make and share this Southern Chicken and Dumplings recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",5.0,60.0,784.8,50.1,15.1,202.1,1223.5,34.9,1.1,0.1,45.5,"0.0","Southern Chicken and Dumplings Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine chicken, salt and pepper in a large pot and cover with water. Cook until chicken is tender. 2: Remove chicken from water. 3: Remove bone and skin. 4: Set chicken aside (while chicken is cooking, prepare dumplings.). 5: Dumplings: In a large bowl, mix flour, salt, baking powder and shortening with a fork. 6: Add egg and 1/2 cup milk; mix to form dough. 7: Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness on floured surface. 8: Cut into four-inch strips with sharp knife. 9: Drop dumplings into simmering chicken broth. 10: Cover and simmer until dumplings are done. 11: Add chicken to dumplings and 1 cup milk. 12: Cook slowly for 10 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5047,"Granny''s Chicken Dumplings","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Granny''s Chicken Dumplings recipe from Food.com.","Whole Chicken",4.0,1.0,2106.0,87.2,18.1,208.6,6428.3,237.1,9.7,4.1,85.0,"1.0","Granny''s Chicken Dumplings Recipe Instructions:  1: Clean chicken; cut into pieces and place in large pot with water (enough to cover) and boil until tender (skim top). 2: Remove chicken and, when cooled, remove meat from bones. 3: While chicken is cooling, add enough water to broth to make 2 quarts and finely chopped celery, green onions, chopped parsley, chicken bouillon cubes and salt and pepper to taste. Let simmer while you debone chicken and make dumplings. 4: Dumplings: Combine flour and oil or Crisco. 5: Use milk to make manageable dough and roll thin. 6: Cut in strips about 1 1/2-inches wide and then 4 to 5-inch strips or break pieces and drop in briskly boiling broth, one at a time, and move around so they will not stick together. 7: After you get them all to boil for a few minutes, cut down heat; simmer covered 10 minutes. 8: If you don''t have enough broth, add boiling water for more gravy in dumplings. 9: While simmering, add chicken to dumplings.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5049,"Crab Rangoon III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Crab Rangoon III recipe from Food.com.","Crab",5.0,3.0,1008.0,80.3,44.4,415.7,1372.5,19.8,3.3,10.2,54.4,"1.0","Crab Rangoon III Recipe Instructions:  1: In bowl, mix together softened cream cheese, A.1. 2: sauce, garlic powder and onions until well blended. 3: Add crabmeat (thawed, drained and squeezed dry) and again mix well. 4: Assem- ble each hors d''oeuvre as follows:  Place won ton skin on working area with one corner pointed towards you. 5: Spoon about 1/2 teasposon crab mixture on lower half of skin. 6: Roll away from you so that filling is in cylindrical shape. Use small dab of water to seal point.  Twist ends. 7: Fry in hot 360 degrees oil until lightly browned and crispy.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5050,"Graham Cracker Pudding","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Graham Cracker Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,2898.0,132.8,97.0,948.5,1887.2,381.0,0.0,346.8,53.4,"1.0","Graham Cracker Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Dissolve gelatin in milk. 2: Mix in sugar, salt and egg yolks. Be sure yolks are completely mixed in. 3: Cook over medium heat until mixture starts to thicken. Do not let boil. 4: Cool until firm. 5: Beat egg whites until stiff. Set aside. 6: Beat cooled mixture until creamy. 7: Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla. 8: Fold in egg whites. 9: Place a layer of crumbs on the bottom of a serving bowl. 10: Pour pudding in and top with more cracker crumbs.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5051,"Graham Cracker Pudding II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Graham Cracker Pudding II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,2694.4,125.7,71.4,672.9,2484.6,370.1,3.5,281.2,33.3,"1.0","Graham Cracker Pudding II Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix together topping. 2: Reserve 1/2 cup for topping Press remainder into deep pie plate or  shallow baking dish. 3: Bake in slow oven (325) until brown. 4:  5: Cook in double boiler and fill crust. 6: Sprinkle the  remaining 1/2 cup crumbs on and cover with meringue. 7: Brown in oven.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5052,"Graham Cracker Pudding III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Graham Cracker Pudding III recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,2152.9,153.7,93.5,917.9,608.4,163.1,0.0,135.4,37.4,"1.0","Graham Cracker Pudding III Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat gelatin and salt in double boiler to dissolve the gelatin. 2: Add egg yolks, sugar and salt to gelatin mixture and make hot. Cool quickly. 3: Beat egg whites. 4: Beat whipping cream or Dream Whip. 5: Combine whites, whipped cream and vanilla. 6: Fold into cool mixture and into cracker lined 9-inch square pan. 7: Top with crackers");
