INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5055,"Broccoli Casserole","PT30M","PT30M","PT1H","A favorite of my husband and daughter. A few reviewers have mentioned the number of pans used. This is how I avoid that being a problem. After I cook &amp; drain the broccoli, I place it in the casserole dish while I use the same pan to make the sauce. I then pour the broccoli back into the pan to coat it and return it all to the casserole dish. Rinse the saucepan out, it doesn''t need to be ''clean'' just rinsed, and then use the same pan to make the melted butter and bread crumb mixture. If you use the microwave to cook your broccoli, just use the casserole dish to cook it in. Hope that helps!","Vegetable",4.5,56.0,657.8,50.9,16.8,44.8,1714.5,33.3,5.7,5.0,20.4,"0.0","Broccoli Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook  broccoli until tender, drain. 2: In saucepan, heat mushroom soup and grated cheddar cheese, until cheese melts. 3: Add cooked broccoli and stir. 4: Put in baking dish. 5: Melt margarine in pan and add seasoned bread crumbs. 6: Stir until moist with margarine and put on top of broccoli. 7: Bake at 350 F until bubbly, about 25-30 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5057,"Pizzelle Alle Nocciole","0","PT0S","PT0S","Here are a couple of Pizzelle recipes for you. I also make them with almond  extract. I would not hesitate to try them with others. Margie:                                Pizzelle Alle Nocciole  Time :0:00","European",5.0,1.0,581.1,29.8,11.9,181.7,328.8,70.9,4.1,34.5,11.9,"6.0","Pizzelle Alle Nocciole Recipe Instructions:  1: WHISK THE EGGS WITH THE SUGAR and salt until light.  Melt the butter and   stir  in. 2: Sift together all the remaining ingredients except the hazelnuts   and fold in. 3: Stir in the hazelnuts last. Heat Pizzelle iron and place 1   teaspoon of  batter on each imprint.  Close iron and bake 30 seconds. 4: Cool on   racks. 5: NICK MALGIERI - PRODIGY GUEST CHEFS COOKBOOK                    - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5058,"Ricotta Cheesecake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Ricotta Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",0.0,0.0,4716.1,211.1,125.1,2206.7,1648.7,507.5,6.8,406.6,209.7,"1.0","Ricotta Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat ricotta until smooth, gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar and egg yolks, beating after each addition. 2: Beat in flour, lemon rind and vanilla. 3: Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar. 4: Fold whipped cream and egg whites into ricotta mixture and turn into a 12\ 5: ,  6: ,  7: Freezes well. 8: Dust with powdered sugar when served.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5059,"Ricotta Cheese Filled Cake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Ricotta Cheese Filled Cake recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,12.0,4725.9,197.9,90.9,1218.7,4493.1,588.9,5.8,380.5,150.7,"1.0","Ricotta Cheese Filled Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix cake according to directions on box. 2: Grease and flour 13x9 inch pan. 3: Pour  cake mix into pan. 4: Mix Ricotta, sugar, beaten eggs and vanilla. 5: Pour filling  mixture over cake batter and spread evenly. 6: Do not mix with batter! Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. 7: Cool completely. 8: Cut  into squares to serve.  Holly Wickstrom Guild of St.  Mary of the Nativity, Scituate, MA                    - - - -  - - - - - - - - - - - - - -");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5060,"Norwegian: Lefse Med Kling From Sogn","0","PT1H","PT1H","Make and share this Norwegian: Lefse Med Kling From Sogn recipe from Food.com.","Breads",0.0,0.0,776.1,65.8,41.4,176.5,470.2,41.7,1.5,1.3,6.5,"30.0","Norwegian: Lefse Med Kling From Sogn Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix the butter into the flour with your hands until crumbly. 2: Then, mix in all remaining dry ingredients into the butter/flour mixture. 3: Add the kefir milk.  Work the mixture until you have a nice dough.  It should be like a pie crust dough, not a bread dough. 4: Take a ball of dough, about 150 grams in weight and roll with a pin until you have thin 50cm diameter circle.  This means you will have a very thin circle when it''s finished.  You use a thin, 70cm long 2-3cm diameter rolling pin to roll the dough out.  You must constantly reposition the piece on the work surface, rolling it up onto the pin on occasion and flipping it over and unrolling it to work the other side. It mustn''t stick to the work surface so make sure there is a dusting of flour on the surface at all times.  You can''t work the dough too much or it will absorb the flour and become stiff and unusable.  It''s a bit of an art to get it right and you''ll need to practice. 5: Bake the dough on a special electric frying pan (called a \ 6:  in Norwegian).  It probably is the same pan used to bake Mexican tortillas. You cook it like a pancake, on both sides, until brown spots just begin to appear. 7: When done, let the lefses cool. 8: When you are ready to eat them, spray them (or dunk them) in water, drain quickly and let them rest a couple minutes on a towel. The excess water is absorbed by the towel and the remainder moistens the lefse. 9: Kling filling:  Mix all the ingredients together, slowly, a bit at a time until you have an even batter.   : 10: Spread onto the lefse and roll up/fold together.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5061,"Bbq Meatballs","PT30M","PT10M","PT40M","Make and share this Bbq Meatballs recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",0.0,0.0,49.8,1.1,0.3,10.2,78.2,7.7,0.2,6.9,2.5,"0.0","Bbq Meatballs Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 400F. Chop onion. 2: Combine meatball ingredients using Pastry Blender; mix well. 3: Form meatballs. 4: Place meatballs in a single layer in baking dish. Bake 10 minutes. 5: Meanwhile, combine all sauce ingredients, mixing well; pour over meatballs. 6: Bake 20 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5062,"Holiday Turkey and Biscuits","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Holiday Turkey and Biscuits recipe from Food.com.","Poultry",0.0,0.0,228.2,9.4,5.6,24.1,588.1,30.0,2.6,2.3,6.3,"6.0","Holiday Turkey and Biscuits Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 400*. 2: Heat butter in a 2-quart casserole in oven until melted. 3: Stir in remaining ingredients except spinach and Biscuits. 4: Bake 20 minutes, stirring once, until sauce is slightly thickened. 5: Stir in spinach. 6: Prepare Biscuits. 7: Place around edge of casserole, overlapping biscuits slightly to fit.  Increase oven temp to 425*. 8: Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until biscuits are golden brown. 9: Cut butter into flour, baking powder and garlic salt with pastry blender until mixture resembles small peas. 10: Stir in just enough milk until dough forms a ball. 11: Knead on lightly floured surface 5 to 7 times. 12: Roll or pat  dough 1/2 thick. 13: Cut with floured 2-inch cutter.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5064,"Date Candy","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Date Candy recipe from Food.com.","Candy",5.0,2.0,3973.8,96.1,25.1,81.8,1181.2,785.2,26.6,718.6,40.2,"1.0","Date Candy Recipe Instructions:  1: Put milk and sugar in pan and as soon as it boils, add dates and butter. 2: Boil until it forms a good soft ball in cold water (watch carefully but don''t stir more than absolutely necessary). 3: Remove from fire; add nuts and stir. Beat until very stiff. 4: Dip out on a cloth wrung from cold water; knead and mold into a long roll. 5: Let stay in damp cloth until hard and cold. 6: Slice and serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5065,"Date Candy II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Date Candy II recipe from Food.com.","Candy",3.5,2.0,4479.7,124.9,43.0,164.7,1473.9,844.7,26.6,736.8,45.6,"1.0","Date Candy II Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix sugar, milk, butter and syrup; bring to a boil,  stirring constantly. 2: (Use medium heat to bring to a boil.) Add  dates when it gets to soft ball stage or 238 degrees. 3: Remove from  heat and add nuts and vanilla. 4: Beat until thick. 5: Turn on  board and shape.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5066,"Date Candy III","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Date Candy III recipe from Food.com.","Candy",0.0,0.0,3486.2,180.3,92.8,156.2,1394.4,466.1,26.2,412.3,38.0,"1.0","Date Candy III Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook to form a soft ball in cold water. 2: Then add package of dates. 3: Cook until it leaves the side of pan. 4: Take off fire and beat in 1 cup of coconut and 1 cup nuts. 5: Beat as long as you can; then spread on wet cloth and roll up.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5067,"Peppermint Candy Crisps","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Peppermint Candy Crisps recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",1.0,1.0,1882.4,70.0,41.4,310.1,1892.2,304.5,8.2,170.8,27.3,"1.0","Peppermint Candy Crisps Recipe Instructions:  1: In mixing bowl, cream butter and honey until fluffy. 2: Add melted chocolate. Mix well. 3: Blend in egg and milk. 4: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture and mix well. 5: Chill dough at least 30 minutes. 6: Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart. Press each cookie with bottom of glass coated with flour to flatten. 7: Sprinkle each cookie with crushed peppermint stick candy. 8: Bake at 350 degrees F 8 to 10 minutes until done. Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet. Cool on rack. 9: Microwave: Follow recipe directions. 10: Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper or microwave baking sheet. Cook on HIGH: 6 cookies - cook for 1 minute, 15 seconds. 11: 12 cookies - cook for 2 to 2-1/2 minutes. 12: Cool cookies slightly before removing.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5068,"Parsnip Pie II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Parsnip Pie II recipe from Food.com.","Pie",0.0,0.0,1189.2,42.3,23.6,467.2,1060.7,186.6,6.8,156.8,22.5,"1.0","Parsnip Pie II Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook parsnips mashed fine and strain. 2: While still warm, add the butter and salt. Beat the eggs, add sugar and nutmeg. 3: Add milk and the parsnip mixture and mix well. 4: Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry and pour in the mixture. Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake in 400 degrees oven about 30 minutes or until the custard is thick and nicely browned.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5069,"Cincinnati Chili II","PT1H30M","PT15M","PT1H45M","This is my family''s favorite Chili.  We serve this over Spaghetti.  Can be served with Cheddar Cheese, Kidney Beans, Onions  and Oyster Crackers","Meat",5.0,11.0,294.6,18.7,7.4,77.1,895.7,9.3,3.2,4.1,23.1,"8.0","Cincinnati Chili II Recipe Instructions:  1: In a 4 quart saucepot, add ground beef to water. Stir until beef separates to a fine texture. Boil slowly for half an hour. 2: Add all other ingredients. Stir to blend, bringing to a boil; reduce heat and simmer uncovered for about 3 hours. 3: Last hour, pot may be covered after desired consistency is reached. 4: Chili should be refrigerated overnight so that fat can be skimmed from the top before reheating. 5: If you use very lean (95% or higher) beef you may not need to skim.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5070,"Nova Scotia Donairs","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Nova Scotia Donairs recipe from Food.com.","Meat",4.5,3.0,5992.9,283.3,111.2,1591.7,2568.0,333.9,8.5,253.1,501.6,"1.0","Nova Scotia Donairs Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix well loaf ingredients and shape into 1 or 2 loaves. 2: Bake on broiler pan or cake rack on cookie sheet at 300 degrees for 1 1/2 hours and cool. 3: Slice very thin and warm before using (heat in frypan). This can also be frozen and used any time. Method: Run water over Lebanese bread and fry in pan with a little oil. 4: Spread with sauce and add meat, finely chopped onion, chopped tomato and lettuce.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5071,"Roast Duck","PT2H","PT1H","PT3H","Make and share this Roast Duck recipe from Food.com.","Whole Duck",5.0,43.0,2359.3,123.3,33.2,1543.6,3123.1,15.3,0.6,12.2,280.4,"0.0","Roast Duck Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash and dry duckling. 2: Combine remaining ingredients and brush inside and out over duckling; let stand for 1 hour, turning occasionally. 3: Preheat oven to 350°F. 4: Roast for 2 hours, turning and basting with drippings occasionally.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5072,"Roast Wild Duck","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Roast Wild Duck recipe from Food.com.","Whole Duck",0.0,0.0,5989.3,550.7,184.8,1040.9,1754.8,92.7,8.7,68.9,161.7,"1.0","Roast Wild Duck Recipe Instructions:  1: Wash and dry duck thoroughly. 2: Rub the insides with  salt. Fill the cavity with chopped apples and raisins. 3: Cover  the breasts with bacon slices. 4: Roast the duck in moderate 325 degrees  oven for 20 minutes to the pound. 5: Duck can be seasoned more  with salt and paprika if desired.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5073,"Roast Duck II","PT5H","PT0S","PT5H","Make and share this Roast Duck II recipe from Food.com.","Whole Duck",0.0,0.0,3108.4,164.5,54.5,864.0,651.1,43.5,0.4,22.6,190.1,"1.0","Roast Duck II Recipe Instructions:  1: Soak ducks in salt water all night. Drain and rinse ducks. 2: Salt and pepper ducks inside and out. Stuff them with oranges and celery. 3: Place ducks in roasting pan on a rack with water in the bottom. 4: Pour sherry and orange juice over ducks. 5: Roast 5 hours at 325 degrees.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5076,"Gumdrop Cake II","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Gumdrop Cake II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",0.0,0.0,9396.8,280.6,127.8,911.0,3658.3,1688.0,47.4,945.7,91.0,"1.0","Gumdrop Cake II Recipe Instructions:  1: Fry pecans in butter (small amount). Sift dry ingredients. 2: Use some flour mixture to dredge cut up raisins and  gumdrops. 3: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs. 4: Add flour mixture alternately with applesauce to cream mixture.  Stir in soda mixture; add vanilla. 5: Add gumdrops, raisins and pecans. 6: Pour batter into 2 or 3 small loaf pans lined with waxed paper or greased brown paper. 7: Bake 2 hours at 300 degrees to 325 degrees. 8: Cool well and wrap in brandy soaked cloth, wax paper and  foil.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5078,"Cheesecake Fudge","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Cheesecake Fudge recipe from Food.com.","Candy",0.0,1.0,161.1,13.3,7.4,43.9,92.5,8.7,0.5,2.0,2.4,"0.0","Cheesecake Fudge Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine flour, butter and brown sugar in large bowl. 2: Beat with electric mixer on low until butter is cut into dry ingredients. (Pastry blender may be used.) 3: Place this mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes. 4: Meanwhile, mix frosting and cream cheese until combined. 5: Add eggs and beat until smooth. 6: Carefully spread chocolate mixture over hot crust. Sprinkle with almonds. 7: Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until chocolate mixture is set. Cool. 8: Cut into bars and store in refrigerator.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5079,"Linguini Alfredo","PT20M","PT10M","PT30M","Make and share this Linguini Alfredo recipe from Food.com.","European",5.0,5.0,664.0,48.8,30.3,153.6,357.0,45.2,1.9,1.7,12.4,"8.0","Linguini Alfredo Recipe Instructions:  1: Cook linguini as directed on box. 2: While noodles cook heat butter and garlic in small saucepan over medium heat until butter is melted and garlic is browned. 3: Add cream and heat until bubbling. 4: Add cheese, parsley, basil, salt and pepper. 5: Return drained noodles to kettle. Pour sauce over noodles, stirring gently until all are well coated.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5080,"Luscious Ricotta Cheesecake","PT45M","PT20M","PT1H5M","Make and share this Luscious Ricotta Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",0.0,0.0,1290.2,72.8,41.4,860.3,673.6,87.4,1.5,56.2,71.7,"0.0","Luscious Ricotta Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 2: Butter and flour 6-cup spring- form pan. 3: Beat eggs with sugar in a large bowl. 4: Add the Ricotta and continue to beat. Slowly add the flour and baking powder, then add all remaining ingredients, continuing to beat until smooth. 5: Pour batter into prepared pan and bake for 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean and the cake has a light golden color. 6: Let cake cool in pan, then run a thin flexible knife or spatula around the pan to loosen the cake. Carefully remove the rim of the spring-form and slide the cake out.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5081,"Ricotta Cheesecake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Ricotta cheesecake has a delicate texture and many times it is best to serve the cake from the baking pan. Make sure the cake is well chilled before serving it either at room temperature or slightly chilled. Slice into even wedges and either sprinkle it with a dash of liqueur or serve it with fresh fruit.","Cheesecake",4.5,5.0,802.2,54.7,33.4,281.5,374.9,62.5,0.2,50.8,17.7,"0.0","Ricotta Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. 2: Mix ingredients together, adding eggs, one at a time at low speed; then mix at medium speed for 20 minutes. 3: Grease the bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan. 4: Pour in mixture and bake in preheated oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes. 5: Turn off oven and allow pan to remain in the oven for 1 more hour. 6: Remove and let cheesecake cool to room temperature before you refrigerate. Refrigerate overnight. May also be frozen for up to 4 months.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5082,"Golden Ricotta Cheesecake","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Golden Ricotta Cheesecake recipe from Food.com.","Cheesecake",0.0,0.0,2720.4,111.6,66.3,1018.2,1671.6,316.1,11.4,281.8,130.4,"1.0","Golden Ricotta Cheesecake Recipe Instructions:  1: Drain peaches; set aside. In top of double boiler, combine 1/4 cup of sugar and gelatin. 2: Add egg yolks and beat until light and frothy. 3: Add salt and milk. Cook over simmering water until mixture forms a custard thick enough to eat with a spoon. 4: Whirl Ricotta in a food processor or blender until smooth. 5: Stir into custard mixture with lemon juice, peel and vanilla. 6: In large bowl beat egg whites until stiff peaks form using remaining 1/2 cup sugar. 7: Fold custard into egg whites. 8: Pour into 9-inch spring-form pan. 9: Arrange peaches cut side down. 10: Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours. 11: Unmold. 12: Crush gingersnaps and sprinkle on top of cake.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5084,"Green Bean and Ham Soup","PT8M","PT20M","PT28M","Make and share this Green Bean and Ham Soup recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,6.0,223.0,6.7,2.2,30.0,838.8,26.2,4.1,3.9,15.3,"6.0","Green Bean and Ham Soup Recipe Instructions:  1: In a 4- or 6-quart pressure cooker combine green beans, potatoes, ham, onion, water, and oil.  Lock lid in place. Place pressure regulator on vent pipe. Over high heat, bring cooker up to pressure. 2: Reduce heat just enough to maintain pressure and pressure regulator rocks gently; cook for 3 minutes. 3: Quick-release the pressure. Carefully remove the lid. 4: Stir together flour, dill, salt, black pepper, and milk, half-and-half, or light cream til smooth. Add to cooker. Cook over medium heat till thickened and bubbly. 5: Cook and stir for 1 minute more.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5085,"New England Clam Chowder (Pressure Cooker)","PT30M","PT30M","PT1H","Make and share this New England Clam Chowder (Pressure Cooker) recipe from Food.com.","Chowders",5.0,10.0,559.3,34.6,16.0,121.3,1699.8,28.4,2.1,1.9,32.9,"0.0","New England Clam Chowder (Pressure Cooker) Recipe Instructions:  1: Drain clams and reserve liquid.  Measure clam liquid; add enough water to make 4 cups liquid and set aside. 2: In the pressure cooker, brown diced bacon until golden.  Remove bacon and set aside. 3: Drain off all but 1/4 of the fat and saute onion for several minutes. 4: Add potatoes, salt, pepper and reserved clam liquid (mixed with water) and bring to a boil. 5: Seal, bring up to 15 lb. pressure, reduce heat to stabilize pressure and cook for 10  minutes. 6: Remove from heat, depressurize and remove lid. 7: Add half and half, milk, butter and clams; heat gently (but do not boil).  Serve immediately.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5086,"Italian Sprinkle Cookies","PT12M","PT0S","PT12M","Make and share this Italian Sprinkle Cookies recipe from Food.com.","Drop Cookies",5.0,5.0,102.7,3.4,0.9,17.9,37.2,16.5,0.2,9.5,1.5,"0.0","Italian Sprinkle Cookies Recipe Instructions:  1: Using a heavy-duty electric mixer on high speed, beat eggs until light and foamy, about 5 minutes. Set aside. 2: In another mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar and baking powder; gradually add shortening and extracts until a bead-like texture is formed. 3: Gradually add beaten eggs (dough will be stiff). 4: Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased baking sheets. 5: Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. 6: The tops of the cookies will not brown, but the bottoms should brown slightly. 7: For glaze, combine milk and extracts in a large bowl. 8: Add sugar; whisk until all lumps are dissolved and the glaze is smooth. 9: As soon as cookies are removed from the oven, quickly immerse two or three at a time into the glaze. Remove with a slotted spoon or fingers. 10: Place cookies on wire racks to drain. 11: Quickly top with sprinkles. 12: Let dry 24 hours before storing in airtight containers.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5087,"Raspberry Mousse Cake","PT15M","PT1H","PT1H15M","A real treat. BUT-When you assemble this I would advise you to put the sponge base in a springform tin or something that will keep the sides straight. My girlfriend and I made it and the mousse started to ooze down the sides, the picture she had showed it looking really straight sided. But it was soooooooo yummy.","Dessert",3.5,2.0,2960.5,209.6,121.0,1045.4,1089.2,237.8,28.5,160.0,50.2,"0.0","Raspberry Mousse Cake Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 180°C. 2: Brush a 20cm round spring form tin with melted butter. 3: Sift flours and cornflour 3 times onto greaseproof paper. 4: Beat eggs until thick and pale.  Add sugar gradually, beating constantly until dissolved and mixture is pale yellow and glossy. 5: Transfer mixture to a large mixing bowl. 6: Using a metal spoon , fold in dry ingredients quickly and lightly. 7: Spread mixture into prepared tin. 8: Bake 15 minutes or until sponge is lightly golden and shrinks from the side of tin. 9: Leave sponge in tin for 3 minutes before turning onto wire rack to cool. 10: To Make Mousse: Process 315g of the raspberries to a smooth texture in blender or processor, pass through a fine sieve.  Reserve half of the puree for serving. 11: Beat egg and sugar together until creamy. 12: Add cream cheese, beat until smooth. 13: In a separate bowl beat cream until soft peaks form. 14: Combine gelatin with water in a small bowl, stand bowl in hot water, stir until gelatin dissolves. 15: Using a metal spoon, fold gelatin, half of the puree and reserved whole raspberries into cream cheese mixture, then fold in cream. 16: Cover with plastic wrap and put in the refrigerator 10 minutes or until the mixture has thickened, stirring occasionally. 17: To Assemble:  Cut cake in half horizontally. 18: Place first cake layer on a board. 19: Spread cake evenly with mousse. 20: Top with remaining cake layer, refrigerate until mousse is set. For serving, sift icing sugar over top of the cake.  Cut cake into wedges, place on individual serving plates and spoon reserved puree around cake.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5088,"Apple Butter","PT10M","PT30M","PT40M","My mother taught me how to use the pennies!! It is really a life saver because it helps keep the butter from burning--which I have done.","Apple",4.5,11.0,506.8,0.4,0.1,0.0,2.6,131.8,5.8,123.5,0.6,"0.0","Apple Butter Recipe Instructions:  1: Preparing the apples/pulp: Wash the apples and remove the stem and the blossom ends. DO NOT PEEL nor CORE. Cut the apples into small chunks. 2: Add 2 cups of water and simmer until the apples are nice and soft. 3: Once this is done, press the apples through a sieve or a food mill. YOU MUST HAVE at least 2 quarts of apple pulp. 4: Next, in a large pot, place the pennies on the bottom. It must cover the bottom completely.  NOTE: COPPER PENNIES help keep the butter from sticking and burning! Very important! 5: Add the apple pulp, sugar and spices. Cook slowly until it is thick and will stick to a wooden spoon without dripping. Stir butter frequently to keep from sticking.  If it is too thick for you, add apple juice to mellow out the thickness. 6: You may can the rest of what you do not use. Wash, sterilize the jars and lids. 7: Ladle the rest of the butter into the pint sized jars, leaving 1/4 inch headroom from the neck of the jar to the rim of the jar is called \ 8:   Loosely tighten the jar lids to the jar. 9: Make sure you take a clean cheesecloth and clean the rim. You do not want food particles on the rim.  Once this is done, place in a hot boiling water bath. 10: Make sure there is at least 1 inch of water over the top of the lids Boil for 10 minutes. 11: Remove from canner and set on counter. Let cool. 12: When they have properly sealed, the lids will make a popping sound. Store on shelf or in your fruit/canning cellar. 13: You will notice how nice and shiny your pennies will be too. The acid in the apple butter will clean the pennies. Don''t worry, your apple butter is safe. Just remember to clean, wash, and sanitize your pennies before using them. A small solution of dish soap. Rinse with clear water. Place them in a small solution of bleach water. Rinse again.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5089,"Molded Cheese Spread","PT24H","PT10M","PT24H10M","Make and share this Molded Cheese Spread recipe from Food.com.","Spreads",0.0,0.0,4479.3,367.1,213.0,1048.0,7403.9,58.2,9.7,25.9,246.4,"0.0","Molded Cheese Spread Recipe Instructions:  1: In a food chopper, add onions, nuts, green pepper. 2: Grind. 3: Next, add the cheese, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce,  ketchup, mustard and hot sauce. Mix. 4: Mold it into your type of shape. Let it sit over night in the refrigerator. 5: Covered. 6: Next day, soften the cream cheese with a little bit of mayonnaise. \ 7:  the shape with the cream cheese. Decorate with chopped nuts, olives, and pimentos. 8: **NOTE: Do not frost until at least several hours before serving with crackers.");
