INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5091,"Crab Bisque","PT25M","PT10M","PT35M","Make and share this Crab Bisque recipe from Food.com.","Crab",4.0,3.0,384.7,30.1,18.9,87.9,778.0,14.0,0.9,1.8,6.4,"4.0","Crab Bisque Recipe Instructions:  1: Melt 4 Tbsp butter in skillet. Add the green pepper, onion, scallion, parsley, mushrooms, and sauté until all vegetables are soft (about 5 minutes). 2: In another large sauce pan, melt the remaining butter. 3: Add flour and stir well. 4: Add milk and cook until smooth and thick. 5: Add salt, pepper, and the vegetable sauce from the skillet and the half and half. Bring to a boil. 6: Reduce heat and stir. 7: Add the crabmeat and simmer uncovered for 5 minutes. 8: Just before serving, add sherry and stir. 9: NOTE: You can sub crabmeat with lobster--using the same measurements as the above recipe. For shrimp--use 2 cups of small shrimp.** Great with a tiny layer of cheddar cheese on top or green tops from fresh chives--chopped.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5095,"Chocolate Biscotti II","PT35M","PT35M","PT1H10M","Make and share this Chocolate Biscotti II recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,9.0,100.8,5.4,2.1,9.5,47.8,12.5,0.6,7.8,1.5,"72.0","Chocolate Biscotti II Recipe Instructions:  1: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugars, baking powder and salt. Add melted  unsweetened chocolate, eggs, oil, juice, rum, peel and vanilla; stir to  combine. Add baking chips and nuts; mix until dough is well blended. 2: Quarter dough; shape into 4 logs, each about 2 1/  2\ 3:  long. 4: Place 2 logs on each of 2 lightly oiled (10x15\ 5: ,  6: ,  7:  wide slices. 8: Place  slices cut side down on pans; bake until crisp, about 15 min. more. 9: Cool cookies. 10: Meanwhile, in a double boiler, melt white chocolate and  shortening over hot water, stirring until smoot  h (or heat in a nonmetal  bowl in a micro oven on 100 percent power for 15 sec. at a time, stirring  after each interval, until soft and smooth, about 1 1/2 min.total). Dip 1  end of each cookie about 1\ 11: Serve, or wrap airtight to  store up to 2 days; freeze for longer storage.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5097,"Little-Bitty Coffee-Hazelnut Biscotti","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Little-Bitty Coffee-Hazelnut Biscotti recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",5.0,2.0,8.0,0.3,0.0,2.4,0.8,1.2,0.1,0.6,0.2,"180.0","Little-Bitty Coffee-Hazelnut Biscotti Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Line a cookie sheet with foil. 2: Beat eggs, sugar and coffee granules in a med. bowl with electric mixer until coffee granules dissolve and mixture is thick. 3: Fold in 1/2 cup flour, nuts and remaining 1/2 cup flour until well blended. 4: Spoon batter into a gallon size zipper-type plastic bag and snip off a corner to make a 1/2\ 5:  round tip). 6: Pipe nine 12\ 7:  apart on prepared cookie sheet. 8: Bake 6-8 min. until strips look dry and spring back when lightly touched. Do not brown. 9: Remove from oven. (Increase temperature to 400 degrees). 10: Let cool on sheet  1-2 min. 11: While still warm, peel 1 strip at a time from foil, place on a  cutting board and with a serrated knife, cut diagonally into 20 slices. 12: Remove foil from cookie sheet. Scatter slices over ungreased cookie sheet. 13: Bake 10-12 min., turning slices once with a metal pancake turner, until dry and toasted. 14: Slide cookies onto countertop to cool completely. Store loosely covered in a cool, dry place up to 1 month.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5099,"White Chocolate-Cranberry Biscotti","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this White Chocolate-Cranberry Biscotti recipe from Food.com.","Dessert",4.0,4.0,132.9,5.2,3.0,36.9,71.6,19.2,0.5,9.4,2.4,"30.0","White Chocolate-Cranberry Biscotti Recipe Instructions:  1: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. 2: Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. 3: Beat in vanilla. 4: Combine flour and baking powder; gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in cranberries and vanilla chips. 5: Divide dough into 3 portions. 6: On ungreased baking sheets, shape each portion into a 10x2\ 7: ,  8: ,  9: ,  10:  slices. 11: Place cut side down on ungreased baking sheets. 12: Bake for 15-20 min. 13: or until golden brown. 14: Remove to wire racks to cool. 15: Store in airtight container.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5100,"Ring of Crab","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Ring of Crab recipe from Food.com.","Crab",0.0,0.0,2076.4,55.6,22.6,631.6,3867.8,244.1,19.6,21.7,142.0,"1.0","Ring of Crab Recipe Instructions:  1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. 2: Mix all ingredients except crab meat, then add crab meat. Unroll crescent dough and separate into 16 triangles. 3: Arrange triangles on a cookie sheet or pizza pan forming a circle. Make sure there is a circle opening in the middle. Spoon crab mixture into middle of dough, forming a circle. Fold dough over crab mixture towards middle, pressing down on the dough around circle opening, sealing dough. 4: Make sure crab mixture is covered by dough ring. 5: Bake 20-25 minutes or until deep golden brown. 6: If desired, sprinkle additional cheese on top after ring is removed from oven. 7: Slice into desired thickness.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5101,"Spiced Peach Jello Salad","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Spiced Peach Jello Salad recipe from Food.com.","Gelatin",4.0,3.0,899.3,1.1,0.1,0.0,403.7,220.5,7.0,211.0,10.8,"0.0","Spiced Peach Jello Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Drain peaches, measuring 3/4 cup syrup. 2: Chop peaches coarsely. 3: Bring syrup, vinegar, sugar and spices slowly to a boil. 4: Add peaches, simmer for 10 minutes. 5: Strain syrup and discard cloves. 6: Add enough peach juice or water to make 1 cup. 7: Dissolve Jello in hot syrup. 8: Add cold water (if I have enough peach syrup, I use what I have) and peaches. 9: Cool, then pour into mold. 10: (The times I made this recipe, I have doubled it.)");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5102,"Borscht II","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","Borscht is like chili; there''s no one recipe for it.  This recipe is somewhat unusual because it does not have cabbage; the addition of lime juice and sugar may also not be traditional.  My mother did get it from a Russian coworker.  It is the borscht I grew up with and I love it.","Vegetable",5.0,6.0,498.9,25.5,9.3,93.1,778.3,32.4,2.4,19.1,34.0,"0.0","Borscht II Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine the first five ingredients in a large non-reactive pot.  Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and allow the soup to simmer for 2= hours. 2: Half an hour before serving, remove beets, keeping the broth at a simmer. 3: When beets are cool enough to handle, peel and grate them (the peels should slip right off).  Then  return them to the pot.  Stir in lime juice and sugar, then season with salt and pepper. 4: Serve, garnished with a dollop of sour cream and/or some snipped chives.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5103,"Hungarian Angel Wing Fry Cookies (Csoroge)","PT4M","PT0S","PT4M","These cookies are those wonderfully crispy, light as a feather fried dough cookies always made for Weddings. They look so beautiful when piled high in a pyramid on a cut crystal platter. These pastries would also be made for a Sunday dinner and served with coffee after a meal of Beef Gulyas or Chicken Paprikas. It always left traces of powdered sugar on your upper lip, and sometimes on the tip of your nose.","Dessert",5.0,1.0,79.4,1.5,0.6,52.9,15.8,13.2,0.4,1.1,2.3,"12.0","Hungarian Angel Wing Fry Cookies (Csoroge) Recipe Instructions:  1: Place in the center of a bread board one cup of flour. Make a dent or well in the center. Add the whole yolks, sour cream, sugar, rum and salt. With a fork mix until the liquids are well combined. 2: Gradually work into the flour. The dough should be of the consistency of a noodle dough. Knead for a few minutes to make the dough smooth. 3: Split the dough into 2 portions. On a lightly floured board roll out each section until paper thin. 4: If you have a pie crimping wheel, use it to cut the dough into squares of 3 1/2-inches or a rectangle of 3 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches. They will have beautiful serrated edges. 5: With a paring knife make three or four gashes about 2 to 2 1/2-inches evenly spaced. 6: Fry in a deep fat (Lard preferred, Crisco OK) until golden brown. 7: Drain on paper towel. 8: Sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5105,"Strawberry Hazelnut Gateau","PT1H","PT45M","PT1H45M","Make and share this Strawberry Hazelnut Gateau recipe from Food.com.","Strawberry",5.0,2.0,4470.9,344.9,180.0,663.2,629.8,368.6,47.8,274.9,68.9,"0.0","Strawberry Hazelnut Gateau Recipe Instructions:  1: Beat the egg whites with salt until soft peaks form, gradually add sugar, beat until the sugar is dissolved and mixture is of meringue consistency. 2: Beat in the vinegar and vanilla. 3: Line bases of two 20cm springform pans with greased greaseproof paper which has been lightly dusted with cornflour. 4: Spread meringue mixture evenly into tins. 5: Sprinkle ground hazelnuts evenly over meringue in both tins. 6: With a knife or small spatula, swirl hazelnuts lightly through meringue.  Smooth over top of meringue with the back of a spoon. 7: Bake in moderate oven 35 - 40 minutes or until meringue is crisp to touch; release sides of pan, cool on the base of the pan. 8: Chop chocolate.  Combine with water in top of double saucepan; stir over simmering water until melted; cool. 9: Remove cakes from bases. 10: Place a layer of meringue on a serving plate, flat side down; spread with a thin layer of chocolate.  Spread whipped cream over chocolate.  Reserve 4 strawberries, wash and hull the remainder, cut in half, arrange over cream. 11: Spread the underside of second meringue with remaining chocolate mixture, place on top of strawberry layer, chocolate side down. 12: Whip extra cream, cover sides and top of cake and if desired, pipe cream decoratively on top. 13: Arrange reserved halved strawberries on top of cake.  Refrigerate until ready to serve.  If desired, brush strawberries used for decoration with warmed, sieved strawberry jam to give them a pretty glaze before arranging on cake. Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 14: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5106,"Bean and Corn Casserole","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Bean and Corn Casserole recipe from Food.com.","Corn",5.0,1.0,1757.8,165.8,58.6,194.1,3386.8,52.0,7.2,20.8,24.7,"1.0","Bean and Corn Casserole Recipe Instructions:  1: Drain green beans and corn. 2: Layer beans, then corn, in  greased casserole dish. 3: Mix soup, sour cream, onion and cheese  together. 4: Spread on top of beans and corn. 5: Melt margarine,  add crackers and then put on top of casserole. Bake at 350 degrees  for 40 to 45 minutes.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5107,"Corn and Pea Salad","PT2M","PT10M","PT12M","Make and share this Corn and Pea Salad recipe from Food.com.","Corn",5.0,10.0,2370.1,80.7,10.8,0.0,3852.8,387.7,50.5,254.7,46.2,"0.0","Corn and Pea Salad Recipe Instructions:  1: Drain corn, peas, green beans and pimentos. 2: Combine all ingredients in bowl and  set aside. Dressing: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil in saucepan. 3: Let cool. 4: Pour dressing over vegetables and mix well.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5108,"Ice Cream Christmas Pudding","PT8H","PT30M","PT8H30M","Make and share this Ice Cream Christmas Pudding recipe from Food.com.","Frozen Desserts",0.0,0.0,3831.6,152.3,80.2,449.1,929.5,564.9,69.3,392.1,65.0,"0.0","Ice Cream Christmas Pudding Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix the almonds, peel, raisins, currants and rum in a bowl, cover with plastic wrap and leave overnight.  Chill a 2 litre pudding basin in the freezer. 2: Soften the vanilla ice cream slightly and mix in the glace cherries. 3: Working quickly, spread the ice cream around the inside of the chilled basin, spreading it evenly to cover the base and side.  Return the basin to the freezer and leave overnight.  Check the ice cream a couple of times and spread it evenly to the top. 4: Next Day:-  Mix the spices and chocolate ice cream with the fruit mixture.  Spoon it into the centre of the pudding basin and smooth the top. 5: Freeze overnight, or until very firm. 6: Turn the pudding out onto a chilled plate, decorate and leave to stand 5 minutes. 7: Cut into wedges to serve. Cheers,  Doreen Doreen Randal,  Wanganui. 8: New Zealand.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5109,"Chicken for College Student","PT15M","PT10M","PT25M","Chicken for College Student  I made this in college in my crockpot and always got good reviews.  My French grandmother called it &quot;Parisian Chicken&quot; and you will see variations of it all around.","Chicken",4.0,11.0,691.6,51.4,18.9,189.9,916.5,14.2,0.5,4.9,42.1,"0.0","Chicken for College Student Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix soup, mushrooms, sour cream, wine, onion and garlic, pepper to taste, and flour in crockpot or casserole dish. 2: Add chicken and make sure all pieces are coated with mixture.  Sprinkle top with paprika. 3: Cover crockpot or casserole.  Cook on low setting in crockpot for 6 hours (or you can start with frozen chicken and cook for 8 hours in crockpot) or about 1-1/2  hours in the oven at 375 degrees (deeper casserole dishes take longer than flat ones). 4: Serve with mashed potatoes or rice or noodles. 5: Nicole Schultheis Baltimore, MD.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5110,"Oyster Stew with Vegetables","PT1H","PT0S","PT1H","Make and share this Oyster Stew with Vegetables recipe from Food.com.","Stew",5.0,1.0,245.9,10.6,5.6,70.7,316.3,22.1,1.9,0.5,16.4,"6.0","Oyster Stew with Vegetables Recipe Instructions:  1: Cut up any large vegetables. 2: In a 3 quart saucepan combine vegetables, onions,  bouillon granules, peppers, bay leaf and 1/2 cup water. 3: Bring to boiling. 4: Reduce  heat. Cover and simmer over medium heat 5 to 7 minutes. 5: Do not drain. 6: Stir in  evaporated milk. 7: Heat through. 8: Add undrained oysters to vegetable mixture. Cook  over medium heat about 5 minutes or until edges of oysters curl, stirring  frequently. 9: If using canned oysters, just heat through. 10: Remove bay leaf.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5111,"Ribbon Oyster Scallop","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Ribbon Oyster Scallop recipe from Food.com.","< 15 Mins",5.0,1.0,194.9,11.0,4.3,40.6,822.6,16.4,0.5,0.5,7.7,"8.0","Ribbon Oyster Scallop Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oyster stew very slowly until thawed in large heavy saucepan. 2: Lift out  oysters with slotted spoon; set aside. Drain liquid from canned oysters and  mushrooms into stew in pot; heat just to boiling. 3: Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the  crackers; heat, stirring constantly, 3 minutes, or until mixture thickens. 4: Remove from heat. Stir in red pepper seasoning, oysters and mushrooms; spoon  into 6 cup shallow baking dish. 5: Sprinkle with parsley. 6: Melt butter. 7: Add 1/2 cup  cracker crumbs; mix well. 8: Spoon in diagonal rows over oyster mixture. Bake in  hot 425 degrees oven for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5115,"Favorite Milk Sweet Cream Base","0","PT0S","PT0S","Most popular base, has creamy texture, medium body, and a subtle, understated  taste. It''s especially good as a background for fruit, cookies, and candy.","Frozen Desserts",0.0,0.0,2525.9,195.0,118.3,1109.3,440.4,175.4,0.0,151.2,30.3,"1.0","Favorite Milk Sweet Cream Base Recipe Instructions:  1: Whisk the eggs in a mixing bowl until light and fluffy, 1 to 2 minutes. 2: Whisk in the sugar, a little at a time, then continue whisking until  completely blended, about 1 minute more. Pour in the cream and milk and  whisk to blend.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5116,"Simple Milk Sweet Cream Base","0","PT0S","PT0S","This simple recipe is made with a minimum of ingredients and requires no  cooking. It makes a very creamy ice cream with 25% butterfat, but it does not  store well in home freezers, so be prepared to eat it all.","Frozen Desserts",0.0,0.0,2433.5,194.8,121.2,712.1,247.4,170.2,0.0,150.7,14.6,"1.0","Simple Milk Sweet Cream Base Recipe Instructions:  1: Pour the cream into a mixing bowl. 2: Whisk in the sugar, a little at a  time, then continue whisking until comple  tely blended, about 1 minute  more. Pour in the half-and-half and whisk to blend.");
