INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5121,"Waldorf Astoria Beef Stew - Crock Pot (Copycat)","PT5H","PT15M","PT5H15M","Make and share this Waldorf Astoria Beef Stew - Crock Pot (Copycat) recipe from Food.com.","Stew",4.5,12.0,193.8,0.9,0.2,0.0,318.3,44.7,6.0,21.1,4.5,"0.0","Waldorf Astoria Beef Stew - Crock Pot (Copycat) Recipe Instructions:  1: Place all in a large crock pot. 2: Cover and cook at low setting for 5 hours. 3: Do  not stir. 4: Add whatever additional vegetables you like.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5122,"Crock Pot Beef Chow Mein","PT8H","PT10M","PT8H10M","Make and share this Crock Pot Beef Chow Mein recipe from Food.com.","Steak",3.5,2.0,262.1,13.4,5.3,83.0,915.8,8.6,1.3,3.1,25.9,"6.0","Crock Pot Beef Chow Mein Recipe Instructions:  1: Place first eight ingredients in crockpot. 2: Cook 8 to 10 hours on low in crockpot. 3: One hour before serving, add Chinese vegetables, cornstarch and water.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5123,"Texas Chili Con Carne With Beans","PT10H","PT45M","PT10H45M","Make and share this Texas Chili Con Carne With Beans recipe from Food.com.","Pork",3.5,4.0,930.3,84.7,34.7,116.8,884.8,25.5,8.8,7.5,17.6,"8.0","Texas Chili Con Carne With Beans Recipe Instructions:  1: Fry bacon until crisp. 2: Remove bacon and drain on paper towel. 3: Brown half the  beef cubes in pan with bacon drippings five minutes. 4: Place in slow cooker. 5: Repeat with remaining meat. Stir bacon and remaining ingredients into 3 1/2  quart slow cooker. 6: Cover and cook on low setting about 10 hours or until beef  is tender. 7: Stir occasionally. 8: If you don''t have a slow cooker place in large  pot, cover, place on stove under low heat and follow directions above.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5124,"Salmon & Vegetable Loaf","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Salmon & Vegetable Loaf recipe from Food.com.","Vegetable",5.0,3.0,163.1,7.5,1.1,44.2,86.2,3.9,0.8,1.9,19.2,"4.0","Salmon & Vegetable Loaf Recipe Instructions:  1: Heat oil in pan and cook onion and peppers 2-3mins till onion softens. 2: Combine 3: salmon, breadcrumbs, chives, parsley and onion mixture in a   bowl. 4: Season  lightly with pepper. 5: Fold egg whites in lightly. 6: Spoon   into lightly greased  and lined loaf tin. 7: Bake 350F 45 mins or till   firm. 8: Stand 10 mins before  turning out.  Cut into slices to serve.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5125,"Spicy Chili Seasoning","0","PT0S","PT0S","Make and share this Spicy Chili Seasoning recipe from Food.com.","Tex Mex",4.0,1.0,187.8,9.0,3.1,54.4,87.0,6.5,2.3,2.9,20.5,"0.0","Spicy Chili Seasoning Recipe Instructions:  1: Combine the first six ingredients. 2: Store in an airtight container in a cool dry place. Yield: 4 batches (20 teaspoons total). To prepare chili: Lightly brown steak in oil in a Dutch oven; add 3 teaspoons of the seasoning mix and toss to coat. Add ground beef; cook until meat is no longer pink. 3: Add onion; cook until tender. 4: Add tomatoes and 2 more teaspoons of mix. 5: Stir in one can of chili beans. 6: Place the other can in a blender cover and process until smo oth. 7: Add to chili. 8: Cook on low for 30-40 minutes or until meat is tender.");
INSERT INTO recipes VALUE(5133,"Pete''s Scratch Pancakes","PT5M","PT15M","PT20M","It was the Fall of 1987 when Pete Nyhus walked into our office, just to visit. We started talking about breakfast, and he reached into a wastepaper basket and pulled out a scrap of teletype paper. He wrote out this recipe, and my family has never used pre-mix since.","Breakfast",5.0,722.0,209.6,8.2,4.7,61.5,334.9,28.1,0.8,4.3,5.9,"0.0","Pete''s Scratch Pancakes Recipe Instructions:  1: Mix the dry items first. 2: Combine the eggs and melted butter to the milk and slowly stir into the flour mixture. 3: Heat the griddle to325 F or the pan to medium high let sit at least 10 minutes while heating the griddle orpan. 4: These will be high, but light and fluffy -- .");