This is excellent for fajitas, pasta salads,  chicken salad, soup, added to beans and rice, just laying on bread for chicken  sandwiches, or just eating cold.","Whole Chicken",5.0,12.0,247.2,17.3,5.0,86.2,99.9,0.0,0.0,0.0,21.4,"8.0","All-Purpose Crock Pot Chicken Recipe Instructions:  1: If using thigh portions or a cut up fryer, etc, remove all skin and as much fat  as possible. I boil the skins with garlic for the dog. 2: There is no need to bone  the chicken. 3: Put about 1/4 inch water in the slow cooker. 4: Rinse the chicken  well, getting into the crevices, and sprinkle with the Cajun seasoning on both  sides. 5: Go easy at first; this is NOT low-salt and it tends to be a little spicy. 6: I start immediately placing the chicken in the slow cooker. 7: I rinse one piece,  season both sides, and layer it in the pot. When you are done seasoning all the  chicken (I generally do 2-3 lbs in a batch; less is not worth the time), cover  the pot and let the chicken stand for 30 minutes. 8: At the end of that time, cover the chicken fully with water (don''t skimp) and set the cooker on \ 9:  Cooking time is up to you. 10: A minimum of 8-10 hours is what I recommend.  I  usually set the chicken cooking in an afternoon, and let it cook overnight.  Often it will cook for 12-24 hours. 11: This is an excellent dish for those of us  who never learned to properly debone a chicken ;) At the end of the cooking  time, merely pull out the chicken pieces and separate the bones from the meat.  It will literally fall apart. Save the broth for adding to mashed potatoes,  gravy, rice or soup. 12: You will have a good deal of chicken here. Separate into  smaller portions and freeze.");
